详细释义: prep.在……里，在……地方，在……期间，在……方面，进入……里面，穿着……；  adj.在里面的，时髦的；  adv.在家，入，进，向里，在某地，在某种关系中
例句: Stay in the car, so you don't get wet.
例句释义: 呆在车里，你就不会被淋湿了。

英文释义: hold or possess something
例句: They have a lovely daughter.
例句释义: 他们有一个可爱的女儿。

例句: IT has made considerable changes to the world in 21st century.
例句释义: 在21世纪，信息技术极大地改变了世界。

英文释义: in or into a position covering, touching or forming part of a surface
例句: There's a phone on the desk.
例句释义: 桌上有一部手机。

英文释义: to speak or tell somebody something, using words
例句: Why do you have to say it so loudly?
例句释义: 你为什么要说这么大声？

例句: His hair is starting to go grey.
例句释义: 他的头发开始变灰了。

详细释义: v.得到，获得，赢得；  link-v.成为，变成，变得
英文释义: to reach a particular state or condition; to make somebody/something/yourself reach a particular state or condition
例句: They all get what they want.
例句释义: 他们都得到了他们想要的。

英文释义: used to say that one thing can, will or might happen or be true, depending on another thing happening or being true
例句: If it is a sunny day, I will go out.
例句释义: 如果这是一个晴天，我就出去玩。

英文释义: used as the past form of will when reporting what somebody has said or thought
例句: He said if he won a million dollars he would buy a house.
例句释义: 他说如果他挣了一百万美元，他就会买一栋房子。

详细释义: det.全部，所有；  pron.全部；  adv.完全（地）
英文释义: (used with plural nouns. The noun may have the, this, that, my, her, his, etc. in front of it, or a number.) the whole number of
例句: All his answers were wrong, so he got a zero.
例句释义: 他所有的答案都错了，所以他得了零分。

详细释义: adv. 附近，大约，转向，左右，周围；  prep. 在附近，关于，在……周围，忙于
英文释义: on the subject of somebody/something; in connection with somebody/something; used to describe the purpose or an aspect of something; busy with something; doing something
例句: The lipstick costs about 220 yuan.
例句释义: 这口红的售价大约是220元。

英文释义: to have information in your mind as a result of experience or because you have learned or been told it
例句: You always know the answer―give someone else a chance.
例句释义: 你总是知道答案，给其他人一个机会吧。

英文释义: used for talking about or predicting the future
例句: He had a strong will, believing he could win the championship.
例句释义: 他意志坚强，相信自己一定能够夺冠。

详细释义: n.时间；（完成竞赛）所用的时间；  v.安排……的时间；  adj.时间的
英文释义: what is measured in minutes, hours, days, etc.
例句: Look at the time! I'm late again! My boss is going to kill me.
例句释义: 看看时间！我又迟到了！我老板会杀了我的。

英文释义: the period from 1 January to 31 December, that is 365 or 366 days, divided into 12 months
例句: 2020 is the Year of the Rat.
例句释义: 2020年是鼠年。

英文释义: to have an opinion about someone or something
例句: There are so many problems to think about.
例句释义: （我们）有很多问题要思考。

英文释义: used with uncountable nouns or plural countable nouns to mean ‘an amount of’ or ‘a number of’, when the amount or number is not given
例句: The woman is putting some sugar in her coffee.
例句释义: 女人正往她的咖啡里加入一些糖。

英文释义: the ordinary men and women of a country rather than those who govern or have a special position in society
例句: There are many different people in the world.
例句释义: 世界上有许多不同的人。

英文释义: to carry or move something from one place to another
例句: It takes twenty-five minutes to prepare this dish.
例句释义: 做这道菜要花费二十五分钟。

详细释义: adv.（表示不在原状态）脱离；出来
英文释义: away from the inside of a place or thing; away from or not at home or their place of work; away from the edge of a place
例句: I feel left out of the group.
例句释义: 我感觉被落单了。

英文释义: to a position in or inside something
例句: This sign means that you are allowed to enter into the room.
例句释义: 这个标志表明允许你进入这个房间。

英文释义: exactly
例句: I have just enough money to pay the bills.
例句释义: 我的余额恰好能够支付账单。

例句: The woman did see why the man was upset.
例句释义: 女人了解男人为什么不高兴。

英文释义: to move to or towards a person or place; to arrive somewhere in order to do something or get something
例句: This woman asked me to come with her.
例句释义: 这个女士让我和她一起。

英文释义: used as the past tense of ‘can’
例句: She could run fast when she was young, but can't now!
例句释义: 她年轻的时候可以跑得很快，但她现在不能了。

英文释义: (at) the present time
例句: Now, the time is 3:32 p.m.
例句释义: 当前时间为下午3:32。

英文释义: used for comparing amounts, numbers, distances, etc.
例句: As you can see, I'm heavier than my little sister.
例句释义: 如你看到的那样，我比妹妹要重一些。

英文释义: to find somebody/something pleasant, attractive or of a good enough standard; to enjoy something
例句: He looks like his father.
例句释义: 他看起来像他爸爸。

英文释义: used to refer to people or things that are additional or different to people or things that have been mentioned or are known about
例句: No, I don't want to buy apples. I want some other fruit.
例句释义: 不，我不买苹果。我想买点儿其他的水果。

详细释义: adv.然后；那么（通常用于句首或句尾）
英文释义: used to introduce the next item in a series of actions, events, instructions, etc.
例句: Type in your password, then take out your money.
例句释义: 输入你的密码，然后取走你的钱。

详细释义: det.更多的；  adv.（程度上）更强
英文释义: to a greater degree than something else; to a greater degree than usual
例句: There are more and more coins in the jar.
例句释义: 罐子里的硬币越来越多了。

详细释义: v.需要；  n.短缺，需要的东西
英文释义: to have a desire or a wish for something
例句: This company wants a 20-year-old with 10 years of work experience.
例句释义: 这家公司想招一个年龄20岁却有10年工作经验的人。

英文释义: a road, path or street for travelling along
例句: There's a way across the field.
例句释义: 这儿有一条路穿过田地。

英文释义: to turn your eyes in a particular direction; to try to find somebody/something; to pay attention to something
例句: I look at myself in the mirror before work.
例句释义: 上班前我照了照镜子。

详细释义: det. 第一；  adv. 最初
英文释义: happening or coming before all other similar things or people; 1st
例句: Crossing the finish line in first place is an amazing feeling.
例句释义: 第一个越过终点线是一种很棒的感觉。

英文释义: (not used with negative verbs) in addition; too
例句: She is also drinking his juice.
例句释义: 她也在喝他的果汁。

英文释义: recently bought; different from the previous one
例句: The man loves his new motorbike!
例句释义: 这个男人超爱他的新摩托车！

英文释义: for the reason that
例句: The tooth is in pain because his master ate lots of sugar.
例句释义: 这颗牙齿很痛苦，因为他的主人吃了太多甜食。

英文释义: a period of 24 hours
例句: A day has 24 hours.
例句释义: 一天有24小时。

详细释义: vt.使用，利用；  n.使用，运用
英文释义: to do something with a machine, a method, an object, etc. for a particular purpose
例句: I use a pencil to draw a picture.
例句释义: 我用一支铅笔来画画。

英文释义: an adult male human
例句: The man smiles happily.
例句释义: 这个男人笑得很开心。

详细释义: v.找到；发现；  n.发现物，被发现的人
英文释义: to discover something/somebody by searching, studying or thinking carefully
例句: You might find the criminals if you follow the footprints.
例句释义: 如果你跟着这些脚印，也许能找到罪犯！

详细释义: n. 东西，事物；事件，事态
英文释义: objects, clothing or tools that belong to somebody or are used for a particular purpose
例句: These are different things that people need in daily life.
例句释义: 这些都是日常生活中人们需要的东西。

英文释义: to hand something to somebody so that they can look at it, use it or keep it for a time
例句: The child is giving the old man a piece of bread.
例句释义: 小孩给了那个老人一块面包。

详细释义: det.许多的；  n.多数人；  adj.相对多的
英文释义: consisting of or amounting to a large but indefinite number
例句: I've wrapped so many gifts for Christmas.
例句释义: 我把这么多圣诞节礼物都包好了。

英文释义: in a good state or position; in good health
例句: Both my parents are very well.
例句释义: 我的父母都很健康。

英文释义: to give information to somebody by speaking or writing
例句: She can tell that the bread is not edible anymore.
例句释义: 她能识别出这个面包已经不能食用了。

例句: They are very excited.
例句释义: 他们非常激动。

详细释义: adj.实力相当的；  adv.甚至；  v.使打平，使相等
英文释义: (of an amount of something) equal or the same for each person, team, place, etc.
例句: It was an even match so neither side could defeat the other.
例句释义: 这是一场势均力敌的比赛，谁也没法打败对方。

英文释义: the part of the human body that is on the opposite side to the chest, between the neck and the tops of the legs; the part of an animal’s body that corresponds to this
例句: His back hurt so much that he couldn't stand up straight.
例句释义: 他的背疼得他站不直。

详细释义: pron.任何一个；  adv.一点儿也（不）
英文释义: one or more of a number of people or things, especially when it does not matter which
例句: You can ride any of these bikes.
例句释义: 你可以骑这些自行车里的任何一辆。

英文释义: of high quality or an acceptable standard
例句: She said I did a good job.
例句释义: 她说我干得不错。

英文释义: an adult female human
例句: My grandmother is such an elegant woman!
例句释义: 我的奶奶是一个多么优雅的女人啊！

详细释义: prep.通过；  adj.直通的；  adv.自始至终
英文释义: from one end or side of something/somebody to the other
例句: I can run through brick walls―what can you do?
例句释义: 我能奔跑着穿过砖墙――你能干什么？

英文释义: living things
例句: Life is a long journey from birth to death.
例句释义: 生命是一个从出生到死亡的漫长旅程。

英文释义: a young human who is not yet an adult
例句: What a cute child!
例句释义: 好可爱的小朋友啊！

英文释义: to do things as part of your job
例句: The medicine works! I feel well!
例句释义: 这个药有效果！我感觉很好！

详细释义: adv. 向下，在下面；  n. 绒毛，汗毛
英文释义: to or at a lower place or position
例句: The mother is walking down the stairs with her daughter.
例句释义: 这位母亲正和女儿一起走下楼梯。

英文释义: the fifth month of the year, between April and June
例句: We like May, because we can have many days-off.
例句释义: 我们喜欢五月，因为可以有很多假期。

英文释义: later than something; following something in time
例句: There was a rainbow in the sky after the rain.
例句释义: 雨后，天空中出现了一道彩虹。

英文释义: used to show what is right, appropriate, etc., especially when criticizing somebody’s actions
例句: When you are working, you should sit up straight.
例句释义: 工作时，你应该挺身坐直。

详细释义: n.通话，打电话；  v.把……叫作
英文释义: the act of speaking to somebody on the telephone
例句: He gave his mother a phone call from work.
例句释义: 他上班的时候给母亲打了个电话。

英文释义: the earth, with all its countries, peoples and natural features
例句: His dream is to travel around the world.
例句释义: 他的梦想是环游世界。

详细释义: adv.越过；翻倒；遍布；结束；  adj.多余的；  prep.在……上方；遍及
英文释义: beyond the top or upper surface or edge; forward from an upright position
例句: The boy is jumping over the stream.
例句释义: 那个男孩正在跳过小溪。

英文释义: a place where children go to be educated
例句: They are the students in the School of Biology at the university.
例句释义: 他们是这所大学生物学院的学生。

详细释义: adv.还，仍；  n.寂静；  v.使安静，使镇定下来；  adj.静止的
英文释义: not moving; calm and quiet
例句: He has been exercising for 3 months, but he's still fat!
例句释义: 他减了三个月的肥，可还是很胖！

详细释义: v.试图，努力；  n.努力，尝试
英文释义: to use, do or test something in order to see if it is good, suitable, etc.
例句: The woman is trying on a pair of high heels.
例句释义: 这个女人正在试穿一双高跟鞋。

详细释义: det.最后的，仅剩下的；最近的，上一个的；  v.持续，坚持；  pron.最后的东西（或人）；  adv.最近，上次
英文释义: happening or coming after all other similar things or people
例句: We need one last piece to finish the puzzle.
例句释义: 我们只需最后一块图案就能完成拼图。

英文释义: to say or write something in the form of a question, in order to get information
例句: The man is asking a stranger for directions.
例句释义: 这个男人正在向陌生人问路。

英文释义: to be in a condition or situation in which you must have (something) :to require (something)
例句: The baby girl badly needs her mother.
例句释义: 这个小女孩非常需要她的妈妈。

英文释义: used before adjectives and adverbs to say that something is more than is good, necessary, possible, etc.
例句: The box is too small for him to sit in.
例句释义: 这个盒子太小了，它坐不下。

英文释义: to have a particular physical quality which you become aware of by touching
例句: He felt tired after working for such a long time.
例句释义: 在长时间的工作后，他感到很累。

详细释义: n.州；状态，情况；  v.说明，陈述
英文释义: an organized political community forming part of a country
例句: Alaska is the northernmost state of America.
例句释义: 阿拉斯加是美国最北边的州。

英文释义: not ever :not at any time
例句: She never eats junk food.
例句释义: 她从不吃垃圾食品。

英文释义: to start to be something
例句: This little green shoot will soon become a beautiful flower.
例句释义: 这棵绿色的小苗很快就能长成漂亮的花朵。

英文释义: in or into the space separating two or more points, objects, people, etc.
例句: The dragon is between the two boxes.
例句释义: 小龙在两个箱子中间。

英文释义: at or to a position or level that is a long way up from the ground or from the bottom
例句: That's a high performance computer.
例句释义: 那是一台高性能计算机。

英文释义: used to say what is actually the fact or the truth about something
例句: He's not really good at shooting arrows.
例句释义: 其实他不太擅长射箭。

详细释义: pron.某事物；有价值或重要的人或事物；  adv.有点，稍微
英文释义: a thing that is not known or mentioned by name
例句: Here, there is something in the box for you.
例句释义: 给，盒子里有给你的一些东西。

英文释义: to the greatest degree; very; extremely; completely
例句: Most of the balloons are green.
例句释义: 大多数气球是绿色的。

英文释义: different; a different person or thing
例句: You have another way to the train station if you are in a traffic jam.
例句释义: 如果你遇到交通堵塞，你可以从另一条道路前往火车站。

英文释义: used with uncountable nouns, especially in negative sentences to mean ‘a large amount of something’, or after ‘how’ to ask about the amount of something. It is also used with ‘as’, ‘so’ and ‘too’.
例句: He drank too much cola at one time.
例句释义: 他一口气喝了太多可乐。

详细释义: n.氏族，家庭；  adj.家庭的，家族的
英文释义: a group consisting of one or two parents, their children and close relations
例句: There are five people in my family.
例句释义: 我家里有五口人。

英文释义: one or ones belonging to oneself
例句: This boy once owned a black cat.
例句释义: 这个男孩曾经拥有一只黑色的猫。

英文释义: to go away from a person or a place
例句: There was some trash left in the stadium after the match.
例句释义: 比赛结束后，体育场内留下了一些垃圾。

英文释义: to cause (someone or something) to be in a particular place or position
例句: Being stuck in a traffic jam had put him in a bad mood.
例句释义: 遇上堵车使他心情不好。

英文释义: having lived for a long time; no longer young
例句: Though you are old, I will always love you.
例句释义: 虽然你老了，我也永远爱你。

详细释义: conj.在……的时候，和……同时；  n.一会儿，一段时间
英文释义: at the same time as something else is happening
例句: The boy is playing a game while his roommate is reading a book.
例句释义: 男孩玩游戏的时候，他的室友正在看书。

详细释义: v.表示，打算；  n.平均值，中庸；  adj.吝啬的
英文释义: a quality, condition, or way of doing something that is in the middle of two extremes and better than either of them; (mathematics) the value found by adding together all the numbers in a group, and dividing the total by the number of numbers see
例句: The green light means we can cross the road.
例句释义: 绿灯表示我们可以通行。

英文释义: to continue having or holding (something) :to not return, lose, sell, give away, or throw away (something)
例句: It's so strange that she has kept young all these years.
例句释义: 真奇怪，这么多年来她一直都保持着年轻的状态。

详细释义: n. 学生；学者; 大学生
英文释义: a person who is studying at a school, especially a secondary school
例句: The students are reading the book.
例句释义: 学生们正在看书。

例句: Let me clean the classroom.
例句释义: 让我来打扫教室吧。

英文释义: very large; much bigger than average in size or quantity
例句: Vincent van Gogh is one of the greatest painters in the history of Western art.
例句释义: 梵高是西方艺术史上最伟大的画家之一。

详细释义: adj.相同的；  pron.同样的人或事物；  adv.同样地
英文释义: exactly the one or ones referred to or mentioned; not different
例句: The little boys are wearing the same hats and clothes.
例句释义: 小男孩们戴着相同的帽子，穿着相同的衣服。

英文释义: large in size, degree, amount, etc.
例句: It's a big hamburger, but I can finish it!
例句释义: 这个汉堡包很大，但是我能吃完！

英文释义: a number of people or things that are together or in the same place
例句: A group of people are sitting over here.
例句释义: 一群人在这儿坐着。

英文释义: to start doing something; to do the first part of something
例句: The bell rings and class begins.
例句释义: 上课铃响就开始上课。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to give the impression of being or doing something; used to make what you say about your thoughts, feelings or actions less strong; used to suggest that something is true when you are not certain or when you want to be polite
例句: It seems that it is going to rain.
例句释义: 好像快要下雨了。

英文释义: an area of land that is controlled by its own government
例句: Each country has its own national flag.
例句释义: 每个国家都有自己的国旗。

英文释义: the act of helping somebody to do something
例句: I offered her some help during the mountain climbing.
例句释义: 爬山的时候，我向她提供了帮助。

英文释义: to say things; to speak in order to give information or to express feelings, ideas, etc.
例句: They are talking to each other to share ideas.
例句释义: 他们正在聊天以分享想法。

英文释义: a bend or corner in a road
例句: Green leaves turn brown in autumn.
例句释义: 秋天，绿叶变成黄褐色。

详细释义: n.问题；  adj.成问题的，难对付的
英文释义: a thing that is difficult to deal with or to understand
例句: Ladies, is there a problem? You've been yelling for hours!
例句释义: 女士们，有什么问题吗？你们已经争论了几个小时了！

详细释义: det.每个，每一；每隔（一定的数目或时间）的，每……之中的
英文释义: used with singular nouns to refer to all the members of a group of things or people
例句: Every snowman has a carrot nose.
例句释义: 每一个雪人都有一个胡萝卜鼻子。

英文释义: to begin doing or using something
例句: The couple has started their own flower shop.
例句释义: 这对夫妻开了一家花店。

英文释义: the part of the body at the end of the arm, including the fingers and thumb
例句: She handed the gift to her friend.
例句释义: 她把礼物交给了朋友。

英文释义: used as the past tense of may when reporting what somebody has said
例句: I think it might rain later, so I should take an umbrella.
例句释义: 我想一会儿或许会下雨，所以我应该带把伞。

详细释义: adj.美国的，美国人的；  n.美洲人
英文释义: of or connected with N or S America, especially the US
例句: These items are all related to American culture.
例句释义: 这些东西都与美国文化相关。

详细释义: v.（提供事实、信息）证明，表明
英文释义: a theatre performance, especially one that includes singing and dancing; a programme on television or the radio
例句: His planner shows that he will be quite busy in the coming days.
例句释义: 他的每日计划显示他接下来几天会很忙。

英文释义: a separate piece or area of a human or animal body or of a plant
例句: She parted the curtains and looked out.
例句释义: 她拉开窗帘向外看。

英文释义: opposing or disagreeing with somebody/something
例句: He's against the teacher's proposal.
例句释义: 他反对老师的提议。

英文释义: a specific area or region of the world :a particular city, country, etc.
例句: She carefully placed the folder back in the filing cabinet.
例句释义: 她小心地把文件夹放回档案柜里。

英文释义: of the type already mentioned
例句: Look! Such a beautiful view.
例句释义: 看！这是多美的景色啊！

英文释义: one more time; on another occasion
例句: It looks like it will rain again.
例句释义: 看起来又要下雨了。

英文释义: used with plural nouns and a plural verb to mean ‘not many’
例句: There are very few people on the train.
例句释义: 地铁上几乎没什么人。

英文释义: (often in compounds) a container or covering used to protect or store things; a container with its contents or the amount that it contains
例句: He always takes the black case to work.
例句释义: 他总是带这个黑色公文包去上班。

英文释义: a period of seven days, either from Monday to Sunday or from Sunday to Saturday
例句: They are talking about the week's plan.
例句释义: 他们在谈论这周的计划。

英文释义: a business organization that makes money by producing or selling goods or services
例句: The girl enjoys her father's company.
例句释义: 这个女孩喜欢父亲的陪伴。

英文释义: an organized set of ideas or theories or a particular way of doing something
例句: Android is a very popular operating system for phones.
例句释义: 安卓是一种很流行的手机操作系统。

详细释义: det.每人，每个；  pron.每人，每个，每件；  adv.每个
英文释义: used to refer to every one of two or more people or things, when you are thinking about them separately
例句: Each person is taking a photo.
例句释义: 每个人都在拍照。

英文释义: true or correct as a fact; correct in your opinion or judgement
例句: They have the right to vote.
例句释义: 他们享有选举权。

英文释义: a set of instructions in code that control the operations or functions of a computer; something that people watch on television or listen to on the radio; a plan of things that will be done or included in the development of something
例句: Leave me alone! I’m trying to write a program on the computer!
例句释义: 别理我！我只想好好地在电脑上写代码！

英文释义: to listen to (someone or something)
例句: What did you say? I can't quite hear you.
例句释义: 你说什么？我听不清楚。

英文释义: doubt or confusion about something
例句: The woman raised her hand and questioned what the man was saying.
例句释义: 那个女人举起手，质疑男人所说的内容。

英文释义: throughout the entire time of (an event, period, occurrence, etc.)
例句: It's rude to talk on the phone during dinner.
例句释义: 在吃晚餐时讲电话很没礼貌。

英文释义: to do things for pleasure, as children do; to enjoy yourself, rather than work
例句: The children are playing in the park.
例句释义: 孩子们正在公园里玩耍。

英文释义: a particular system used for controlling a country, state, etc.
例句: The offices of the local government are in this building.
例句释义: 当地政府的办公室就在这栋楼里。

英文释义: to move using your legs, going faster than when you walk
例句: For a while, she ran a restaurant.
例句释义: 她曾有一段时间在经营餐馆。

英文释义: not large in size, number, degree, amount, etc
例句: This is a small model of my real house.
例句释义: 这是我房子的一个小模型。

英文释义: a word or symbol that represents an amount or a quantity
例句: In total there are 10 numbers here.
例句释义: 这里总共有10个数字。

英文释义: away from work or duty
例句: He had to be off in a hurry.
例句释义: 他不得不匆忙离开。

英文释义: at all times; on every occasion
例句: This store is always open.
例句释义: 这家商店一直营业。

详细释义: v. 移动；  n. 迁居
英文释义: to change the place where you live, have your work, etc.
例句: He's using a truck to help him move house.
例句释义: 他正用卡车搬家。

英文释义: the darkness that occurs during the nighttime
例句: When night falls, the moon begins to shine.
例句释义: 夜幕降临，月亮开始照耀大地。

英文释义: to remain alive, especially at a particular time
例句: The students are having a live online PE class at home.
例句释义: 学生们正在家里上体育直播课。

英文释义: the sharp thin end of something
例句: What was the point of playing piano to a cow?
例句释义: 对牛弹琴的意义何在？

英文释义: to regard the existence of God as a fact; to have religious beliefs
例句: Some people believe WeChat is a good place to make a fortune.
例句释义: 有些人相信微信是个发财致富的好地方。

详细释义: vt.拿住，握住；  n.（飞机、船的）货舱
英文释义: to put your arms around (someone) :to embrace or hug (someone)
例句: I'm holding a cup of coffee latte in my hands.
例句释义: 我正用手握着一杯拿铁咖啡。

详细释义: n. 今天；现今；  adv. 现在；在今天
英文释义: this day
例句: Today is the day for me to pay my taxes.
例句释义: 今天是我要交税的日子。

英文释义: to come to a place with someone or something
例句: This photo album brings back memories.
例句释义: 这本相册勾起了一些回忆。

英文释义: to take place, especially without being planned
例句: How did this horrible accident happen?
例句释义: 这桩可怕的事故是如何发生的？

详细释义: adj.（时间）紧接的；（位置）贴近的；  n.下一个人（东西）；  adv.其次，然后
英文释义: coming after this one :coming after the one that just came, happened, etc.
例句: Their children are sleeping in the next room.
例句释义: 他们的孩子正在隔壁房间里睡觉。

英文释义: not in the company of somebody
例句: I feel so lonely without you.
例句释义: 没有你我感觉好孤单。

详细释义: prep.在……前面（空间）；  conj.在……之前（时间）；  adv.以前
例句: There's only one person before me in line!
例句释义: 在队伍里我前面就只有一个人。

英文释义: great in size or amount
例句: She has a very large cup.
例句释义: 她有一个非常大的杯子。

英文释义: 1?000?000; a very large amount
例句: The businessman holds one million dollars in his arms.
例句释义: 这个商人怀里抱着一百万美元。

英文释义: used to say that something is necessary or very important (sometimes involving a rule or a law)
例句: You must leave the game!
例句释义: 你必须离开比赛！

英文释义: the house or flat/apartment that you live in, especially with your family; a house or flat/apartment, etc., when you think of it as property that can be bought and sold; a place where people who cannot care for themselves live and are cared for by others
例句: These tomatoes were destined for the home market.
例句释义: 这些番茄被运往国内市场。

详细释义: prep.在……之下；在……的领导下；  adj.下面的；  adv.在下方
英文释义: in, to or through a position that is below something; below the surface of something; covered by something
例句: There's a cute little girl playing under the table.
例句释义: 一个可爱的小女孩正在桌下玩呢。

详细释义: n. 水；  vt. 给……浇水，给……供水
英文释义: a liquid without colour, smell or taste that falls as rain, is in lakes, rivers and seas, and is used for drinking, washing, etc.
例句: Would you like a glass of ice water?
例句释义: 你要一杯冰水吗？

英文释义: a part of a building that has its own walls, floor and ceiling and is usually used for a particular purpose
例句: There was enough room in the van for the suitcase.
例句释义: 车里有足够的地方放行李箱。

英文释义: to make letters or numbers on a surface, especially using a pen or a pencil
例句: The price of this shirt is written on the label.
例句释义: 标签上写明了这件衬衫的价格。

英文释义: a piece of land or part of a building that is used for a particular activity; a particular part of a town, a country, a region, or the world
例句: The area of the office is about 40 square meters.
例句释义: 办公室的面积大约是40平方米。

详细释义: adj.国家的，民族的；  n.（某国的）公民
英文释义: connected with a particular nation; shared by a whole nation
例句: Baseball is the national game of the U.S.
例句释义: 棒球是美国的国民运动。

英文释义: what you earn by working or selling things, and use to buy things
例句: Money, money, money, always money―it's a rich man's world.
例句释义: 钱钱钱！到处都是钱！――这就是有钱人的世界啊。

英文释义: an account, often spoken, of what happened to somebody or of how something happened
例句: Mary is reading a bedtime story to her kids.
例句释义: 玛丽正在给她的孩子们讲睡前故事。

英文释义: not yet old; not as old as others
例句: Our company is quite young, founded one month ago.
例句释义: 我们公司很新，于一个月前成立。

英文释义: something that truly exists or happens: something that has actual existence
例句: My photo proved the fact that the ghosts weren't real.
例句释义: 我的照片证明了一个事实：这些鬼都是假的。

英文释义: a period of time that lasts about four weeks or 30 days
例句: There are twelve months in a year.
例句释义: 一年有12个月。

英文释义: not the same as somebody/something; not like somebody/something else
例句: The red tomato looks so different from others.
例句释义: 红色的西红柿看起来与其他的如此不同。

英文释义: a large number or amount
例句: I have a lot of pencils.
例句释义: 我有许多铅笔。

英文释义: to spend time learning about a subject by reading, going to college, etc.
例句: Her studies are all about genetic engineering.
例句释义: 她的研究都与基因工程相关。

英文释义: a set of printed pages that are fastened inside a cover so that you can turn them and read them
例句: The boy booked a table for Valentine's Day.
例句释义: 男生为情人节预定了餐厅。

详细释义: n.眼睛；眼状物；  v.送秋波
英文释义: either of the two organs on the face that you see with
例句: The little baby has beautiful blue eyes.
例句释义: 这个小宝宝有一双美丽的蓝眼睛。

英文释义: a particular task or piece of work that you have to do
例句: It is my job to put the books back on the shelves.
例句释义: 我的责任是把书放回书架上。

英文释义: a single unit of language which means something and can be spoken or written
例句: The word on the paper was written in blue ink.
例句释义: 纸上的词是用蓝墨水写的。

英文释义: despite the fact that
例句: Even though he failed the exam, he was happy.
例句释义: 虽然他考试没及格，但他还是很开心。

英文释义: the activity of making, buying, selling or supplying goods or services for money
例句: What she does to relax herself is her own business.
例句释义: 她做什么来放松是她自己的事。

详细释义: n.问题；发行物；  v.发行；宣布，公布
英文释义: an important topic that people are discussing or arguing about
例句: Food standards for fish are an important issue being talked about in the news.
例句释义: 鱼类食用标准成了最近新闻讨论的热点话题。

详细释义: n.边；一边，一侧；  adj.旁边的，侧面的；  v.站在同一边
例句: There are many trees on both sides of the river.
例句释义: 小河两边的岸上都有许多树。

详细释义: adj. 善良的，仁慈的，亲切的，和蔼的；  n. 种类
英文释义: caring about others; gentle, friendly and generous
例句: He's a kind young man who always helps others.
例句释义: 他是个善良的年轻人，总是帮助别人。

详细释义: n. 头；领导人；  v. 率领
英文释义: the part of the body containing the brain, eyes, ears, nose, and mouth
例句: My head aches―maybe I think too much.
例句释义: 头好痛，也许是我用脑太多了。

详细释义: adv.（空间或时间）远，久远；  adj.远方的；  n.远方
英文释义: a long distance away
例句: Though we're far apart, you're always in my heart!
例句释义: 虽然我们相隔遥远，但我会一直记得你的。

英文释义: having the very darkest colour, like coal or the sky at night
例句: Her shiny black hair is beautiful.
例句释义: 她的闪亮黑发很美。

详细释义: vi.渴望，极想；  adj.长的；  adv.长久地，长期地
英文释义: measuring or covering a great length or distance, or a greater length or distance than usual
例句: That girl longed to see her boyfriend again.
例句释义: 那个女孩渴望再见到她的男朋友。

详细释义: pron.两者（都）；  conj.既…且…；  det.两者的；两个
英文释义: used with plural nouns to mean ‘the two’ or ‘the one as well as the other’; not only… but also…
例句: Both of them are outstanding.
例句释义: 他们两个人都很优秀。

英文释义: not big; small; smaller than others
例句: He paid little attention to what she was saying.
例句释义: 他几乎没有注意她在说什么。

英文释义: a building in which a family lives
例句: They work for a publishing house.
例句释义: 他们在一家出版公司工作。

详细释义: excl. 答话时表示正确或真实；  n. 是；肯定
英文释义: an answer that shows that you agree with an idea, a statement, etc.; a person who says ‘yes’
例句: Yes, I promise to be a good boy.
例句释义: 好，我保证做一个好男孩！

英文释义: from a time in the past until a later past time, or until now
例句: The ground is quite wet since it rained yesterday.
例句释义: 由于昨天下雨了，所以地面非常潮湿。

英文释义: to give something to somebody or make it available for them to use; (of a law or rule) to state that something will or must happen
例句: This restaurant provides free juice.
例句释义: 这家餐厅提供免费果汁。

详细释义: n.服务；公共服务事业（或系统）；维修保养
英文释义: a system that provides something that the public needs, organized by the government or a private company
例句: The cleaning lady provides a range of cleaning services.
例句释义: 这位清洁女工提供一系列清洁服务。

英文释义: surrounding somebody/something; on each side of something; on, to or from the other side of somebody/something
例句: They sit around the teacher.
例句释义: 他们围坐在老师身边。

英文释义: a person you know well and like, and who is not usually a member of your family
例句: Gina is my best friend.
例句释义: 吉娜是我最好的朋友。

英文释义: having a great effect on people or things; of great value
例句: You have an important message!
例句释义: 你有一条重要消息！

英文释义: to rest your weight on your bottom with your back vertical, for example on/in a chair
例句: The little boy is sitting on the ground.
例句释义: 小男孩坐在地上。

英文释义: to a different place or in a different direction
例句: The blue balloon flies away.
例句释义: 蓝色气球飞走了。

详细释义: prep.到……为止；  conj.到……为止，直到……才
英文释义: used to indicate the time when something will happen, become true, etc.
例句: He continued work until it got dark.
例句释义: 他一直工作到天黑。

英文释义: physical strength used in action; physical strength that somebody possesses and might use
例句: He has great power and can lift the car with one hand.
例句释义: 他力大如牛，能一只手举起汽车。

英文释义: one of the 24 equal parts of a day; 60 minutes
例句: I get a break at one o'clock―only an hour to go!
例句释义: 一点的时候我可以休息一下，只有一个小时！

详细释义: n.游戏，比赛；  adj.甘愿尝试的，有冒险精神的
英文释义: an activity or a sport with rules in which people or teams compete against each other
例句: We had a good time playing the board game together.
例句释义: 我们一起玩桌游玩得很开心。

英文释义: used in negative sentences and questions to talk about something that has not happened but that you expect to happen
例句: I studied hard, yet I still failed in the exam.
例句释义: 我学习很努力，但考试还是没及格。

英文释义: a long narrow mark on a surface; a row of people or things next to each other or behind each other
例句: There is a yellow line in the middle of the road.
例句释义: 道路中间有条黄线。

英文释义: of or relating to politics or government
例句: The young man is giving a political speech to the public.
例句释义: 这个年轻人在向公众发表一场政治演说。

详细释义: n. 结果，结局；末端，终点；  v. 结束
英文释义: to finish; to make something finish
例句: The end of the race was very close.
例句释义: 比赛结果很接近。

英文释义: surrounded by somebody/something; in the middle of somebody/something
例句: There is an apple among the other fruits.
例句释义: 这个苹果在这些水果之中。

英文释义: used in negative sentences and questions, or sentences with if to mean ‘at any time’
例句: Ever since I was born, you've been my best friend.
例句释义: 自从我出生以来，你就是我最好的朋友。

详细释义: v. 忍受；起立；  n. 讲台
英文释义: to be on your feet; to be in a vertical position
例句: He often wondered how he could stand living below such a noisy person.
例句释义: 他常常在想他怎么能忍受住在这么吵闹的人的楼下。

英文释义: unpleasant; full of problems; of poor quality; below an acceptable standard
例句: After hearing the bad news, she cannot fall asleep.
例句释义: 听到这个坏消息后，她睡不着了。

详细释义: v.（在竞争或比赛中）输掉；失去；遗失
英文释义: to have something/somebody taken away from you as a result of an accident, getting old, dying, etc.; to have less and less of something, especially until you no longer have any of it
例句: The boxer lying on the ground lost to his more skilled opponent.
例句释义: 这个躺在地上的拳击手输给了比他更厉害的对手。

详细释义: adv. 然而，不过；无论如何，不管多么
英文释义: used with an adjective or adverb to mean ‘to whatever degree’
例句: He got a great test score; however, he's still upset.
例句释义: 他考了个好成绩，然而他还是不开心。

英文释义: a person, a country or an organization that has joined a particular group, club or team
例句: I've always wanted to be a member of the group.
例句释义: 我一直很想成为这个组织中的一员。

英文释义: to give somebody money for work, goods, services, etc.; to give somebody money that you owe them
例句: He paid for his coffee and bread.
例句释义: 他付了咖啡和面包的钱。

英文释义: the whole system or set of rules made by the government of a town, state, country, etc.
例句: Nobody is above the law.
例句释义: 没有人能凌驾于法律之上。

英文释义: to come together formally in order to discuss something
例句: This production chain ensures that the supply of milk meets the demands.
例句释义: 这条生产链保证了牛奶的供应满足需求。

英文释义: a road vehicle with an engine and four wheels that can carry a small number of passengers
例句: There is a green car parked at the side of the road.
例句释义: 路边停着一辆绿色的车。

英文释义: a place where people live that is larger or more important than a town :an area where many people live and work
例句: This is a big city with a large number of high-rise buildings.
例句释义: 这是一座有很多高层建筑的大城市。

英文释义: not quite
例句: He almost reached the diamonds.
例句释义: 他差一点就挖到钻石了。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) if one thing includes another, it has the second thing as one of its parts; to make somebody/something part of something
例句: Elephants, frogs and birds can be included in the category of "animals."
例句释义: 大象、青蛙和鸟可以被包括在“动物“这个类别里。

英文释义: to keep existing or happening without stopping; to keep doing something without stopping
例句: She continued running when the others stopped.
例句释义: 当其他人停下的时候，她还在继续奔跑。

详细释义: n.一套，一副，一批；  v.（小心地）放置；建立，设立，树立；调整好；（故事等）以……为背景
英文释义: a group of similar things that belong together in some way
例句: Many girls own a set of makeup.
例句释义: 很多女孩子有成套的化妆品。

英文释义: at a time in the future; after the time you are talking about
例句: I'm doing my homework now so I can play basketball later.
例句释义: 我正在写作业，那我过一会儿就可以打篮球了。

英文释义: all the people who live in a particular area or place; a group of people who are similar in some way; (biology) a group of plants and animals growing or living in the same place or environment
例句: The largest Chinese community in this city lives in its Chinatown.
例句释义: 唐人街里住着这座城市最庞大的华人群体。

英文释义: to give a name to somebody/something
例句: What should we name our new baby?
例句释义: 我们应该给我们的新宝宝取什么名字？

英文释义: on one occasion only; one time
例句: Once they knew the price of that house, they decided to take it.
例句释义: 他们一知道那房子的价格，就决定买下它。

详细释义: adj.白色的；白种人的；  n.白色；白种人；蛋白
英文释义: having the color of fresh snow or milk
例句: There is a white piece of paper on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上有一张白纸。

详细释义: det.最少的，最小的；  adv.最少地，最小地
英文释义: smallest in size, amount, degree, etc.
例句: Piggy has the least toes among his friends.
例句释义: 小猪的脚趾头在他的朋友里面是最少的。

英文释义: the head of the government in some countries
例句: All of them are great American presidents.
例句释义: 他们都是伟大的美国总统。

英文释义: to gain knowledge or skill by studying, practicing, being taught, or experiencing something
例句: He just learned about the earthquake from the newspaper.
例句释义: 他刚刚从报纸上得知了地震的新闻。

详细释义: adj.真实的；  n.实在的东西；  adv.很，非常
英文释义: actually existing or happening; not imaginary
例句: The mirror did not show his real reflection.
例句释义: 这个镜子没有反映出他真实的样子。

英文释义: the act or result of something becoming different
例句: That's three dollars change.
例句释义: 这是找给您的三美元。

英文释义: a group of people who play a particular game or sport against another group of people
例句: Your tug-of-war team may be stronger, but our team has better smiles.
例句释义: 你们的拔河队也许更强，但我们这一队笑得更灿烂！

详细释义: n.一分钟；片刻；  adj.微小的，极小的；  vt.记录
英文释义: each of the 60 parts of an hour, that are equal to 60 seconds
例句: It's going to be 12 o'clock after 5 minutes.
例句释义: 5分钟后就到12点。

英文释义: of the most excellent type or quality; most enjoyable; happiest; most suitable or appropriate
例句: The restaurant in the middle is the best of the three.
例句释义: 中间那家餐厅是三家当中最好的。

详细释义: det.几个；  adj.各自的，分别的
英文释义: more than two but not very many
例句: I have several apples for you!
例句释义: 我给你准备了几个苹果！

英文释义: a plan, thought or suggestion, especially about what to do in a particular situation
例句: He came up with a good idea to solve that problem.
例句释义: 他想到了一个好主意来解决这个问题。

英文释义: (informal) a child or young person
例句: Those kids are happily playing in the playground.
例句释义: 小孩子们正在操场上快乐地玩耍。

英文释义: the whole physical structure of a human or an animal
例句: The man's body is so strong!
例句释义: 这个男人的身体真强壮！

详细释义: n. 信息，情报，资料，通知
英文释义: facts or details about somebody/something
例句: The Internet is my main source of information about other countries.
例句释义: 因特网是我获取其他国家信息的主要来源。

例句: There's nothing in this box.
例句释义: 盒子里什么也没有。

英文释义: used in expressions of time with the simple past tense to show how far in the past something happened
例句: I started going to school a few years ago.
例句释义: 我几年前就上学了。

详细释义: v.领导；  n.领先地位，榜样
英文释义: to connect one object or place to another
例句: Few people lead; many people follow.
例句释义: 少数人领导；多数人跟随。

英文释义: relating to activities that involve meeting and communicating with other people
例句: WeChat is great for building social relationships.
例句释义: 微信对建立社交关系很有帮助。

英文释义: to know the meaning of (something, such as the words that someone is saying or a language)
例句: Eventually, I started to understand what the teacher was saying.
例句释义: 最后我才明白老师说的是什么。

英文释义: used to show that something is true in either of two cases
例句: The mother still doesn't know whether it's a boy or a girl.
例句释义: 这位母亲还不知道宝宝是男是女。

详细释义: n. 表；看守；  v. 观看，注视
英文释义: a device that shows what time it is and that you wear on your wrist or carry in a pocket
例句: He bought an expensive watch so he could show off to his friends.
例句释义: 他买了只昂贵的表，这样就可以在朋友面前炫耀了。

详细释义: adv.一起；同时；  adj.自信而妥当的
英文释义: with or near to somebody/something else; with each other
例句: This place is even more beautiful to me because we're here together.
例句释义: 因为有你在身边，所以这个地方变得分外美丽。

英文释义: to come or go after or behind somebody/something
例句: He followed the doctor's advice about when to take the medicine.
例句释义: 他听从了医生关于何时服药的建议。

英文释义: a person’s father or mother
例句: New shoots appear from the parent plant.
例句释义: 新芽从母株上生长出来。

英文释义: to not do something that you have been doing before; to not continue doing something
例句: The road worker held up his hand to stop the car.
例句释义: 修路工人举手让车停下来。

详细释义: n.脸；表面，外面；  v.面对，面临
英文释义: the front part of the head between the forehead and the chin
例句: The beautiful woman is touching her face.
例句释义: 这个美丽的女人正在摸自己的脸。

英文释义: a thing of any kind
例句: Welcome! Is there anything I can help you with?
例句释义: 欢迎光临！请问有什么可以帮您的吗？

英文释义: to make something happen or exist
例句: The writer created many characters.
例句释义: 这位作家创造了很多角色。

详细释义: adj.公共的；公然的；  n.公众，民众
英文释义: not private; open to or concerning the people as a whole
例句: There are many non-smoking signs in public places.
例句释义: 公共场所有许多禁烟标志。

英文释义: before now or before a particular time in the past
例句: The concert already started at 7 o'clock, hurry up!
例句释义: 演唱会七点就已经开始了，快点啊！

详细释义: v.说话，谈及；说（某种语言）；演讲
英文释义: to talk to somebody about something; to have a conversation with somebody
例句: When he speaks, everybody else listens carefully.
例句释义: 他说话的时候别人都在认真地听。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to look at and understand the meaning of written or printed words or symbols
例句: The young lady is reading a book in the library.
例句释义: 这位年轻的女士正在图书馆读书。

详细释义: n.水平，标准，等级；  v.瞄准；对准目标；  adj.等高的
英文释义: having the same height as something else
例句: Players are separated into three levels in this game.
例句释义: 玩家们在这个游戏中被分为三个等级。

英文释义: to let somebody/something do something; to let something happen or be done
例句: The green light allows you to go.
例句释义: 绿灯(表示)允许你通行。

英文释义: to put (something) with another thing or group of things
例句: Add some milk to the bowl.
例句释义: 加点儿牛奶在碗里。

英文释义: a building or room in which people work at desks doing business or professional activities
例句: I like office work―I can wear smart clothes and stay indoors.
例句释义: 我喜欢在办公室工作――可以穿得漂亮而且不用外出。

英文释义: to give money to pay for goods, services, etc.
例句: They like spending time together as a family.
例句释义: 他们喜欢全家一起共度些时光。

英文释义: a piece of wood, glass, etc. that is opened and closed so that people can get in and out of a room, building, car, etc.; a similar thing in a cupboard/closet
例句: Where does the door lead to?
例句释义: 这扇门通向哪里？

英文释义: the state of being physically and mentally healthy
例句: Eating lots of fruits and vegetables is good for your health.
例句释义: 多吃蔬菜水果对你的健康是有益的。

英文释义: a human as an individual
例句: These two persons are drinking coffee together.
例句释义: 这两个人正在一起喝咖啡。

英文释义: the use of the imagination to express ideas or feelings, particularly in painting, drawing or sculpture
例句: Painting and dance are forms of art.
例句释义: 绘画和舞蹈都是艺术的表现形式。

详细释义: adv. 当然，确实地，无疑地；  adj. 肯定的
英文释义: used to say ‘yes’ to somebody; used to emphasize something that you are saying
例句: I am sure that the tortoise can win because the rabbit is still asleep.
例句释义: 我确信乌龟可以赢得这场比赛，因为兔子还在睡觉呢。

英文释义: a situation in which two or more countries or groups of people fight against each other over a period of time
例句: These two countries are having a war.
例句释义: 这两个国家在打仗。

英文释义: all the events that happened in the past; the past events concerned in the development of a particular place, subject, etc.; the study of past events as a subject at school or university
例句: These books are about Chinese history.
例句释义: 这些书是关于中国历史的。

详细释义: n.派对，聚会；（共同旅行的）队，组
英文释义: a social event in which entertainment, food, and drinks are provided
例句: Everyone had a great time at my birthday party.
例句释义: 在我的生日聚会上每个人都玩得很开心。

详细释义: prep.在……之内；  adv.在内部，在内心里
英文释义: before a particular period of time has passed; during a particular period of time
例句: Deep within the earth it is hot enough to melt iron.
例句释义: 地球内部深处的温度高得足以熔化钢铁。

英文释义: to exist and develop in a particular place; to make plants grow
例句: The seed grows into a tree.
例句释义: 种子长成了一棵树。

英文释义: a thing that is caused or produced because of something else; the mark/grade you get in an exam or in a number of exams
例句: He was pretty excited after finding out his exam results.
例句释义: 他在得知考试成绩后非常开心。

英文释义: allowing things or people to go through
例句: The job is still open for applicants.
例句释义: 这个职位仍对应聘者开放。

英文释义: the early part of the day; the time of day from sunrise until noon
例句: Every morning, I wake up at six.
例句释义: 我每天早上六点起床。

英文释义: to spend time walking for pleasure
例句: Many people are walking on the road.
例句释义: 许多人行走在路上。

详细释义: n.原因；  v.论证，推理，劝说
英文释义: a cause or an explanation for something that has happened or that somebody has done
例句: The reason why he's late for school is that he stayed up late doing homework.
例句释义: 他迟到的原因是昨晚熬夜写作业了。

英文释义: at or near the bottom of something
例句: When temperatures are this low, it's best to just stay inside.
例句释义: 当气温有这么低时最好宅在家里。

英文释义: to be the most successful in a competition, race, battle, etc.; to get something as the result of a competition, race, election, etc.; to achieve or get something that you want, especially by your own efforts
例句: Yeah! Our team has won the basketball match!
例句释义: 耶！我们队赢了篮球赛！

详细释义: n.研究，调查；  v.研究，调查
英文释义: careful study that is done to find and report new knowledge about something
例句: They are carrying out medical research in the lab.
例句释义: 他们正在实验室里进行医学研究。

英文释义: a young woman; a female child
例句: The girl with brown hair is so cute.
例句释义: 这个棕色头发的女孩太可爱了。

英文释义: a man
例句: Look at this guy! He is handsome!
例句释义: 看看这个男人！他真帅！

详细释义: adj. 早的，早期的；  adv. 早，先
英文释义: near the beginning of a period of time, an event etc.
例句: It is far too early in the morning to get up!
例句释义: 现在起床太早了！

英文释义: things that people or animals eat; a particular type of food
例句: Do you like eating Western food?
例句释义: 你喜欢吃西餐吗？

英文释义: a very short period of time; an exact point in time
例句: The girl is using her phone to capture the moment.
例句释义: 这个女孩正在用手机记录这个瞬间。

详细释义: n. 空气；天空，空中；感觉，神态；曲调；  vi. 通风
英文释义: the mixture of gases that surrounds the earth and that we breathe; the space above the ground or that is around things;  the particular feeling or impression that is given by somebody/something; the way somebody does something; (often used in the title of a piece of music) a tune
例句: The fresh air in the morning made her feel alive!
例句释义: 早晨清新的空气令她神清气爽。

英文释义: a person whose job is teaching, especially in a school
例句: Our teacher showed us where America and China were in the world.
例句释义: 老师指给我们看了美国和中国在地球上的位置。

详细释义: v. 强迫；推动；凭借武力前进；  n. 力量；武力；势力
英文释义: to make somebody do something that they do not want to do
例句: The girl forced the boy to kiss her.
例句释义: 这个女孩强迫男孩去亲她。

详细释义: n.录取（或录用）通知书；出价；  v.表示愿意 (做某事)；出价
英文释义: An offer is something that someone says they will give you or do for you.
例句: That company's job offer is so nice! I can't say no!
例句释义: 那家公司的工作机会太赞了！我没法拒绝！

详细释义: det.足够的；  adv.足够地；  pron.很多
英文释义: used before plural or uncountable nouns to mean ‘as many or as much as somebody needs or wants’
例句: No, no, no, I already have enough food.
例句释义: 别给我夹菜了，已经够多了。

英文释义: a particular kind of teaching or training
例句: Nowadays students receive most of their education in the classroom.
例句释义: 如今，孩子们在课堂里接受大部分教育。

英文释义: from one side to the other side of something; on the other side of something;
例句: She got across the stream by walking on the rocks.
例句释义: 她踩在石头上穿过了小溪。

英文释义: used to mean ‘but’ or ‘however’ when you are commenting on a statement
例句: Although it is a rainy day, the girl is still having fun.
例句释义: 尽管这是一个雨天，小姑娘还是玩得很开心。

英文释义: to have or keep an image in your memory of an event, a person, a place, etc. from the past
例句: I still remember the day he asked me to marry him.
例句释义: 我还记得他向我求婚那天的情景。

详细释义: n.脚；底部；  vi.步行；  vt.走在……之上
英文释义: the lowest part of the leg, below the ankle, on which a person or an animal stands
例句: She is lying in the sun with bare feet.
例句释义: 她光着脚躺在阳光下。

详细释义: n.秒；第二名；  adv.第二，其次
英文释义: happening or coming next after the first in a series of similar things or people; 2nd
例句: This digital clock is able to tell the time to the exact second.
例句释义: 这个数字时钟能精确到秒。

英文释义: used when you are not certain that something will happen or that something is true or is a correct number
例句: Maybe your cat is in that box.
例句释义: 你的猫可能在那个盒子里。

英文释义: in the direction of somebody/something
例句: The little girl is walking toward her father.
例句释义: 这个小女孩正向爸爸走去。

英文释义: (used as a modal verb) to have the skill, intelligence, opportunity, etc. needed to do something
例句: Now he is able to walk without the help of crutches.
例句释义: 现在他能够脱离拐杖走路了。

英文释义: the number of years that a person has lived or a thing has existed; a particular period of a person’s life; a particular period of history
例句: Women over the age of 20 can get married in China.
例句释义: 在中国，20岁以上的女性可以结婚。

英文释义: a plan of action agreed or chosen by a political party, a business, etc.
例句: Some company policy forbids employees to have relationships with each other.
例句释义: 一些公司政策规定员工之间不准谈恋爱。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to have very strong feelings of affection for somebody
例句: You can't define the love between two people; you can only feel it.
例句释义: 你无法定义两人之间的爱，你只能去感受。

详细释义: n.步骤，过程；进程；  v.加工；处理
英文释义: to treat raw material, food, etc. in order to change it, preserve it, etc.
例句: Follow the process to create a cute paw-shaped ice cream!
例句释义: 按照这个步骤来做可爱的爪爪冰激凌吧！

英文释义: sounds that are arranged in a way that is pleasant or exciting to listen to. People sing music or play it on instruments.
例句: Let's put some music on!
例句释义: 让我们放点儿音乐吧！

例句: The supermarket sells various fruits, including apples and oranges.
例句释义: 这家超市出售各种水果，包括苹果和橘子。

英文释义: to think about (something or someone) carefully especially in order to make a choice or decision
例句: I will consider your offer, but I think I can get a better one.
例句释义: 我会考虑你给的职位，但我觉得我能找到一个更好的。

英文释义: to become visible; to begin to be seen
例句: I'm so excited! My idol is about to appear on stage!
例句释义: 我太激动了！我的偶像马上要出现在舞台上了！

英文释义: in actual fact
例句: She may appear to be reading, but actually Mary is thinking about food.
例句释义: 玛丽看起来像是在看书，但实际上她正想着食物。

详细释义: v. 买；  n. 所购的物品
英文释义: to obtain something by paying money for it
例句: The couple was excited to buy their first home together.
例句释义: 这对恋人因为一起买了他们的第一栋房子而很兴奋。

英文释义: very likely :almost certainly
例句: It will probably rain later, so I brought my umbrella.
例句释义: 一会儿或许要下雨，所以我带了雨伞。

英文释义: a person rather than an animal or a machine
例句: Water is important for the human body.
例句释义: 水对人体很重要。

英文释义: to stay where you are or delay doing something until somebody/something comes or something happens
例句: She is waiting for her flight.
例句释义: 她正在等她的航班。

英文释义: to work or perform duties for a person, an organization, a country, etc.
例句: The man served the customer a cup of coffee.
例句释义: 这个男人为顾客端上了一杯咖啡。

详细释义: n. 市场；行情；销路；  v. 销售
英文释义: an occasion when people buy and sell goods; the open area or building where they meet to do this; business or trade, or the amount of trade in a particular type of goods; a particular area, country or section of the population that might buy goods
例句: I usually buy fruits and vegetables at the market.
例句释义: 我通常在市场里买水果和蔬菜。

英文释义: to stop living
例句: The old dog died peacefully at home.
例句释义: 那只老狗在家里安详地死去了。

英文释义: to cause (a letter, an e-mail, a package, etc.) to go or to be carried from one place or person to another
例句: She sent a message to her friend.
例句释义: 她给她的朋友发了一条信息。

英文释义: to think or believe that something will happen or that somebody will do something
例句: The little rabbit is expecting the girl to feed it carrots.
例句释义: 小兔子正期待着女孩喂它吃胡萝卜。

英文释义: one of the five powers (sight, hearing, smell, taste and touch) that your body uses to get information about the world around you
例句: I'm blind, but I can read this book using my sense of touch.
例句释义: 我是盲人，但是我能用我的触觉来读这本书。

详细释义: v.建造；逐步增强；  n.构造
英文释义: to make (something) by putting together parts or materials
例句: They are building a block of offices.
例句释义: 他们正在建造一座办公楼。

英文释义: to continue to be in a particular place for a period of time without moving away
例句: Some shops stay open 24 hours a day.
例句释义: 一些商店24小时营业。

英文释义: to drop down from a higher level to a lower level
例句: An apple fell from the tree and hit Newton.
例句释义: 苹果从树上落下并砸中了牛顿。

英文释义: a country considered as a group of people with the same language, culture and history, who live in a particular area under one government
例句: These flags represent different nations.
例句释义: 这些国旗代表着不同的国家。

英文释义: a detailed map of a building, town, etc.; a set of things to do in order to achieve something, especially one that has been considered in detail in advance; something that you intend to do or achieve
例句: The architect is drawing up plans.
例句释义: 建筑师正在画平面图。

英文释义: to make an opening or a wound in something, especially with a sharp tool such as a knife or scissors;  to remove something or a part of something, using a knife, etc.; to make or form something by removing material with a knife, etc.; to divide something into two or more pieces with a knife, etc.; to make something shorter by cutting
例句: I like the way he cuts my hair.
例句释义: 我喜欢他给我剪的头发。

英文释义: (often in names) (in Britain) a place where students go to study or to receive training after they have left school; (often in names) (in the US) a university where students can study for a degree after they have left school
例句: After high school the boy went to study at college.
例句释义: 高中毕业后，这个男孩进入大学学习。

英文释义: the feeling that you have when you want to know or learn more about somebody/something
例句: We have to balance our economic and environmental interests.
例句释义: 我们必须兼顾经济利益和环境利益。

英文释义: the fact of somebody dying or being killed; the state of being dead
例句: The funeral ceremony was for the death of her good friend.
例句释义: 这是她好朋友的葬礼。

英文释义: a series of lessons or lectures on a particular subject
例句: The college student took a math course online.
例句释义: 这个大学生在网上学习数学课程。

英文释义: a person who is not known or mentioned by name
例句: Someone left the pen on the desk.
例句释义: 有人把笔落在桌上了。

详细释义: n.经历，感受，体验；  vt.体验，感受
英文释义: the knowledge and skill that you have gained through doing something for a period of time; the process of gaining this; the things that have happened to you that influence the way you think and behave; an event or activity that affects you in some way; events or knowledge shared by all the members of a particular group in society, that influences the way they think and behave
例句: That roller coaster ride was a frightening experience!
例句释义: 这趟过山车真是一次可怕的经历！

详细释义: prep.在……后面；  n.（口语）屁股；  adv.（时间或空间上）在后面
英文释义: at or towards the back of somebody/something, and often hidden by it or them
例句: Who is the girl standing behind the boy?
例句释义: 站在那个男孩子后面的小女孩是谁？

详细释义: v.伸手够到；抵达；达到，发展到；与……取得联系
英文释义: to arrive at the place that you have been travelling to
例句: The baby boy is trying to reach for the red ball.
例句释义: 小宝宝正努力伸手去够红球。

英文释义: belonging to or connected with the particular place or area that you are talking about or with the place where you live
例句: The local people have their own clothing and culture.
例句释义: 当地人有自己的服装和文化。

英文释义: to make somebody/something die
例句: The policeman shot the criminal and killed him.
例句释义: 这位警察把罪犯击毙了。

详细释义: v.剩余；逗留；  link-v.保持；  n.剩余物（复数）；遗迹；残骸
英文释义: to continue to be something; to be still in the same state or condition and do not change
例句: Only one puppy remained in the cage as the rest were sold.
例句释义: 笼子里只剩下一只小狗，其他的都售出了。

详细释义: n.效果；结果；影响；  v.使发生，引起
英文释义: a particular look, sound or impression that somebody, such as an artist or a writer, wants to create
例句: That lighting effect makes the stage look mysterious.
例句释义: 那种灯光效果使舞台看起来很神秘。

英文释义: to put forward an idea or a plan for other people to think about
例句: You look terrible! I suggest you go to see a doctor!
例句释义: 你看起来糟透了！我建议你去看医生！

详细释义: n.课，上课；阶级，社会等级，等级制度
英文释义: a group of students who are taught together
例句: Be quiet when the class begins.
例句释义: 开始上课时要保持安静。

详细释义: v.控制，管理；克制；  n.控制，管理；克制
英文释义: to have power over a person, company, country, etc. so that you are able to decide what they must do or how it is run
例句: The little boy can control the direction of his toy car.
例句释义: 小男孩可以控制玩具汽车的方向。

详细释义: v.举起，抬高；筹集；增加，提高
英文释义: to lift or move (something or someone) to a higher position
例句: The kitten raises his friend up to steal the fish.
例句释义: 这只小猫咪把朋友举起来偷鱼。

英文释义: the process of caring for somebody/something and providing what they need for their health or protection
例句: The nurse is taking care of the old man.
例句释义: 这个护士正在照顾老人。

英文释义: possibly but not certainly
例句: Perhaps she likes me, perhaps she doesn't. I just don't know!
例句释义: 也许她喜欢我，也许她根本不在乎……噢，我真的不知道。

英文释义: arriving, happening or done after the expected, arranged or usual time
例句: She stayed up late working.
例句释义: 她工作到很晚。

英文释义: solid, firm or stiff and difficult to bend or break
例句: The bed is soft but the chair is hard.
例句释义: 床是软的，椅子是硬的。

英文释义: an open area of land without trees or buildings
例句: There is a large field around the farm house.
例句释义: 农舍周围有一大片田野。

英文释义: different; in addition to something already mentioned
例句: I'm happy, but everybody else is sad.
例句释义: 我很高兴，但是别的家伙都苦着一张脸。

详细释义: v.给，传递；通过；  n.飞机或人造卫星等的一次掠过
英文释义: to give something to somebody by putting it into their hands or in a place where they can easily reach it
例句: Pass me the stick. Quick!
例句释义: 把棒子递给我，快！

英文释义: that existed in earlier times; that used to have a particular position or status in the past;  used to refer to the first of two things or people mentioned
例句: The first photograph is our former headmaster.
例句释义: 第一张照片是我们的前任校长。

英文释义: to exchange (something) for money
例句: She sells eggs on the street.
例句释义: 她在这条街上卖鸡蛋。

英文释义: [usually before noun] very large or important
例句: A major cause of lung cancer is smoking.
例句释义: 导致肺癌的一个主要原因是吸烟。

英文释义: occasionally rather than all of the time
例句: Sometimes, the weather will change every day.
例句释义: 有的时候，天气每天都在变。

英文释义: to need something; to depend on somebody/something
例句: The worker is required by law to wear a helmet to work.
例句释义: 法律要求工人佩戴安全头盔进行工作。

英文释义: in a line matching the length or direction of (something)
例句: She walked along the road for a long time.
例句释义: 她沿着马路走了很久。

英文释义: the gradual growth of something so that it becomes more advanced, stronger, etc.
例句: This picture shows the development of phones over time.
例句释义: 这张图展示了电话发展变化的历程。

详细释义: n.报道；报告，汇报；  v.报道；报告，汇报
英文释义: a written or spoken description of a situation, event, etc.
例句: She wrote a newspaper report about him.
例句释义: 她写了一篇关于他的新闻报道。

英文释义: an actor’s part in a play, film/movie, etc.
例句: The actress played challenging roles in many different TV series.
例句释义: 这名女演员在不同的电视剧里尝试了具有挑战性的角色。

详细释义: adj.更好的；  adv.更好地；  v.改善；  n.更优者
英文释义: of a higher standard or less poor quality; not as bad as something else
例句: Her figure gets better and better through daily exercise.
例句释义: 通过每天运动，她的身材越来越好了。

详细释义: adj. 经济上的，经济学的
英文释义: (of a process, a business or an activity) producing enough profit to continue
例句: There is a huge economic increase in this country.
例句释义: 这个国家正在经历巨大的经济增长。

英文释义: an attempt to do something especially when it is difficult to do
例句: She makes efforts to do exercise so that she can keep fit.
例句释义: 她努力健身以保持身材。

英文释义: to think carefully about the different possibilities that are available and choose one of them; to make an official or legal judgement; to affect the result of something; to be the reason why somebody does something
例句: It's time to decide which way to go.
例句释义: 是时候决定走哪条路了。

英文释义: a measurement of the speed at which something happens
例句: My heart was beating at a normal rate.
例句释义: 我的心脏以正常速度跳动着。

英文释义: (of people, animals, etc.) having a lot of physical power so that you can lift heavy weights, do hard physical work, etc.
例句: The strong man has a muscular body.
例句释义: 这个强壮的男人有着一身健壮的肌肉。

英文释义: that can be done or achieved; that might exist or happen but is not certain to
例句: The base tries to find out if it's possible there are aliens in the universe.
例句释义: 这个基地试图弄清宇宙中是否有外星人存在。

英文释义: a kind or generous feeling for other people
例句: I gave you my heart. Treat it nicely, please.
例句释义: 我把心给你了，请好好待它。

英文释义: an illegal substance that some people smoke, inject, etc. for the physical and mental effects it has; a substance used as a medicine or used in a medicine
例句: The doctor gave me some drugs.
例句释义: 医生给了我一些药。

英文释义: a person who leads a group of people, especially the head of a country, an organization, etc.; a person or thing that is the best, or in first place in a race, business, etc.
例句: The workers are happy to follow and work for their team leader.
例句释义: 员工们乐意跟随他们的小组领导工作。

详细释义: v. 点火，照亮；  adj. 不严重的；  n. 光亮；  adv. 轻轻地
英文释义: If a place or object is lit by something, it has light shining on it
例句: She is lighting a candle.
例句释义: 她正在点蜡烛。

英文释义: the sound or sounds produced through the mouth by a person speaking or singing
例句: Many smart phones have a voice recognition function.
例句释义: 很多智能手机都有语音识别功能。

英文释义: a married woman; the woman someone is married to
例句: The man looked at the wedding photo and missed his wife.
例句释义: 男人看着结婚照片，思念他的妻子。

详细释义: adj. 整个的；  n. 整体；  adv. 完全，整个
英文释义: full; complete
例句: The boy ate the whole watermelon by himself.
例句释义: 男孩自己吃了一整个西瓜。

详细释义: n.警察，警方；  v.维持治安，管辖，监督
英文释义: an official organization whose job is to make people obey the law and to prevent and solve crime; the people who work for this organization
例句: We know he's a police because of his car and uniform.
例句释义: 我们根据他的车子和制服得知他是一位警察。

详细释义: n.头脑，思想；  v.注意；记住
英文释义: the part of a person that makes them able to be aware of things, to think and to feel
例句: Here's a hard question for you: Are your mind and your brain the same thing?
例句释义: 问你个难题：你的思想和头脑是一个东西吗？

英文释义: used to introduce the last in a list of things
例句: He finally got served for drinks after queueing for one hour.
例句释义: 排了一小时队，他终于买到了饮料。

英文释义: to hold something firmly and use force in order to move it or try to move it towards yourself
例句: The team of boys began to pull on the rope!
例句释义: 这队男生开始拉绳子了！

英文释义: to come or go back from one place to another
例句: Return to where you came from.
例句释义: 从哪儿来回哪儿去。

详细释义: adj.自由的；  v.使自由，解放；  adv.自由地
英文释义: able to do what you want to do/able to move, go, or act without being stopped
例句: After quitting my job, I feel free as a bird escaping its cage.
例句释义: 辞职以后，我感觉自己像一只逃出鸟笼的鸟。

英文释义: soldiers; the armed forces
例句: University freshmen are required to participate in military training.
例句释义: 大学新生需要参加军训。

英文释义: the amount of money that you pay for something or that something costs
例句: I like to go shopping during sales when the prices are low.
例句释义: 我喜欢在打折的时候去买东西，那个时候价格很便宜。

英文释义: used with uncountable nouns to mean ‘a smaller amount of’
例句: It seems that every day I have less and less money.
例句释义: 看起来我的钱是一天比一天少。

英文释义: a choice or judgement that you make after thinking and talking about what is the best thing to do
例句: Facing three paths in the forest, he made a decision to take the left one.
例句释义: 面对森林中的三条小道，他决定走左边的那一条。

英文释义: to tell somebody about something in a way that makes it easy to understand
例句: The doctor is explaining the patient's illness to her.
例句释义: 医生正在向病人说明她的病情。

英文释义: something that you wish for
例句: My hope is to go to a world-famous university one day.
例句释义: 我希望有一天能上一所世界著名的大学。

英文释义: to gradually grow or become bigger, more advanced, stronger, etc.; to make something do this; to think of or produce a new idea, product, etc. and make it successful; to begin to have something such as a disease or a problem; to start to affect somebody/something; to start to have a skill, ability, quality, etc. that becomes better and stronger; to become better and stronge
例句: We can watch the seed develop into a plant.
例句释义: 我们能够观察到这颗种子发育为一株植物的过程。

详细释义: n.风景；视野；观点，看法；  v.查看，观察；把…视为，看待；观看，收看
英文释义: used when you are talking about whether you can see something or whether something can be seen in a particular situation; what you can see from a particular place or position, especially beautiful countryside
例句: What an amazing view from up here!
例句释义: 从山顶看到的风景太棒啦！

英文释义: the way in which two people, groups or countries behave towards each other or deal with each other
例句: These five people have different relationships with each other.
例句释义: 这五个人之间有不同的关系。

详细释义: vt.携带（疾病、病菌）；运载；  n.运输，运送
英文释义: to support the weight of somebody/something and take them or it from place to place; to take somebody/something from one place to another
例句: It is widely believed that bats carry many viruses.
例句释义: 目前，人们广泛认为蝙蝠携带着大量病毒。

详细释义: n. 城镇，市镇；闹市区；  adj. 城镇的
英文释义: a place with many houses, shops/stores, etc. where people live and work. It is larger than a village but smaller than a city
例句: This is a map of the town.
例句释义: 这是那个镇的地图。

英文释义: a hard surface built for vehicles to travel on
例句: We will be driving on this road for a while.
例句释义: 我们要在这条路上开一会儿。

英文释义: to operate a vehicle so that it goes in a particular direction
例句: The man is driving along the coast.
例句释义: 这个男人沿着海边开着车。

详细释义: n.手臂；臂状物；  vt.供给，提供
英文释义: either one of the two long body parts that join the top of your body at the shoulder and that end at the hand or wrist
例句: She is showing how strong her arm is.
例句释义: 她正在展示她那强壮的手臂。

英文释义: connected with facts rather than things that have been invented or guessed
例句: Take off his mask and you'll see his true face.
例句释义: 摘下他的面具，你就会看到他的真实面孔。

详细释义: adj. 联邦政府的；联邦制的
英文释义: having a system of government in which the individual states of a country have control over their own affairs, but are controlled by a central government for national decisions, etc.
例句: The center of the federal government of the United States is in this building.
例句释义: 美国联邦政府的中心就在这座建筑内。

英文释义: to be damaged and separated into two or more parts, as a result of force
例句: The football broke the glass into pieces.
例句释义: 足球把玻璃打碎了。

例句: Can you spot the differences between these two pictures?
例句释义: 你能找出这两张图的不同之处吗？

详细释义: v. 感谢；  n. 谢意，感谢
英文释义: to tell somebody that you are grateful for something
例句: The patient's family are thanking the doctor for saving his life.
例句释义: 病人家属在感谢医生救了病人的命。

英文释义: to get or accept something that is sent or given to you
例句: The girl received some flowers from the boy.
例句释义: 女孩收到了男孩送的一些花。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to think that somebody/something is important
例句: Which do you value more―the economy or the environment?
例句释义: 经济和环境，你更重视哪个呢？

英文释义: connected with or involving two or more countries
例句: All of them are international students from different countries.
例句释义: 他们都是来自不同国家的国际学生。

英文释义: a structure such as a house or school that has a roof and walls
例句: In this modern city center, every building looks the same.
例句释义: 在这座现代化城市的中心，每栋建筑看起来都一样。

详细释义: n.行为；  v.务必对……进行处理
英文释义: the process of doing something in order to make something happen or to deal with a situation; a thing that somebody does; the way a part of the body moves or functions; the mechanical parts of a piano, gun, clock, etc. or the way the parts move
例句: It is a polite action to offer your seat to old people.
例句释义: 给老人让座是一个有礼貌的行为。

详细释义: adj.满的，充满的；很受感动的；  n.完全，全部
英文释义: containing or holding as much or as many as possible; having no empty space
例句: The cup on the left is full of water.
例句释义: 左侧的杯子中装满了水。

详细释义: n. 模型；模特；  v. 模仿
英文释义: a copy of something, usually smaller than the original object
例句: The girl looks at her model house with a smile.
例句释义: 这个女孩微笑地看着她的房子模型。

详细释义: v.连接，结合；  n.连接，结合
英文释义: to fix or connect two or more things together
例句: When they join the four pieces together, it will make a square.
例句释义: 当他们把这四块拼图拼起来时，就成了一个正方形。

英文释义: one of the four periods (spring, summer, autumn, and winter) into which the year is commonly divided
例句: There are four seasons in a year.
例句释义: 一年有四个季节。

英文释义: people in general, living together in communities
例句: In a modern society many people can live peacefully.
例句释义: 在现代社会中，许多人都可以和平地生活。

英文释义: money that you have to pay to the government so that it can pay for public services
例句: The amount of tax people pay to the government depends on their income.
例句释义: 人们向政府纳税的数额取决于他们的收入。

英文释义: one of a group of senior managers who run a company; a person who is in charge of a particular activity or department in a company, a college, etc.; a person in charge of a film/movie or play who tells the actors and staff what to do
例句: It's agreed that he is an excellent director.
例句释义: 人们一致认为他是一名优秀的导演。

英文释义: the place where somebody/something is located
例句: He tried all kinds of positions to get to sleep.
例句释义: 他试过各种姿势来入眠。

英文释义: a person who takes part in a game or sport
例句: I am a player on my local basketball team.
例句释义: 我是本地篮球队的队员。

英文释义: to have the same opinion as somebody; to say that you have the same opinion
例句: She agreed to go shopping with her friend.
例句释义: 她同意和朋友一起去购物。

例句: The little girl loves drinking juice, especially orange juice.
例句释义: 小女孩很爱喝果汁，尤其是橙汁。

详细释义: v.录制，录（音、像）；记录；  n.记录
英文释义: to keep a permanent account of facts or events by writing them down, filming them, storing them in a computer, etc.
例句: They are using the camera to record the meeting.
例句释义: 他们正在使用摄像机来记录这场会议。

详细释义: vt.挑选；采摘；  n.精品，精华
英文释义: to pull or remove something or small pieces of something from something else, especially with your fingers
例句: He picked out the block from the middle of the row.
例句释义: 他挑出了这排中间的木块。

英文释义: to have something on your body as a piece of clothing, a decoration, etc.
例句: She loves to wear white coats.
例句释义: 她爱穿白色的大衣。

详细释义: n.纸；试卷，论文；  vt.贴墙纸
英文释义: the material that is used in the form of thin sheets for writing or printing on, wrapping things, etc.
例句: I like to make notes on a small piece of paper.
例句释义: 我喜欢在小纸片上做笔记。

英文释义: different from what is normal or usual
例句: Their wedding anniversary was a very special day to them.
例句释义: 结婚纪念日对他们来说是特别的一天。

详细释义: n.（可利用的）空间，空地；（两物或某物两部分之间的）空当，空隙，间隔，距离；  v.留间隔，隔开
英文释义: the amount of an area, room, surface, etc., that is empty or available for use
例句: I cleared a space for you to sit.
例句释义: 我给你腾出了一个坐的地方。

英文释义: the surface of the earth
例句: The man is lying on the ground.
例句释义: 这个男人正躺在地上。

详细释义: n.形体；形状；方式；表格；  v.形成，产生
英文释义: the particular way something is, seems, looks or is presented
例句: You can walk quicker and easier if your movements have the correct form.
例句释义: 如果你的动作正确，你就能走得更快更轻松。

详细释义: v.支援；支撑；  n.支持；支持者，支撑物
英文释义: encouragement and help that you give to somebody/something because you approve of them and want them to be successful
例句: Doctors and resources are being sent from other areas to support this province.
例句释义: 其他地区派遣医生、运送物资来支援这个省。

英文释义: one of the races or competitions in a sports programme
例句: The university's sports meeting is a popular event.
例句释义: 大学运动会是很受欢迎的一项活动。

详细释义: adj.官方的，正式的；公务的，公职的；  n.官员
英文释义: (often in compounds) a person who is in a position of authority in a large organization
例句: Official documents need to be stamped and signed.
例句释义: 官方文件需要有盖章和签名。

英文释义: used in questions to ask who something belongs to
例句: Whose phone and umbrella are those?
例句释义: 这是谁的手机和雨伞啊？

英文释义: to be important
例句: Food, water and housing matter for survival.
例句释义: 食物、水和房子对生存来说至关重要。

英文释义: every person; all people
例句: Everyone in the world should care about the planet.
例句释义: 世界上的每个人都应该关爱地球。

详细释义: n. 中央，中心；  v. 集中
英文释义: the middle point or part of something
例句: You'll get lots of points if you hit the center of the target.
例句释义: 如果击中目标的中心，你会得很高的分数。

详细释义: n.夫妇；一对；  v.配对，连接，结合
英文释义: two people who are married or who have a romantic or sexual relationship
例句: The happy couple smiled all throughout their wedding day.
例句释义: 这对幸福的夫妇在婚礼的一整天都面带微笑。

英文释义: a place where a building, town, etc. was, is or will be located
例句: Take measurements at the construction site.
例句释义: 去施工现场测量。

英文释义: a planned piece of work that is designed to find information about something, to produce something new, or to improve something
例句: This large project, which involved building an entire hospital, was completed in just six days!
例句释义: 这个包含建设一整个医院的大项目，短短六天就完成了！

详细释义: v.命中；完成（指标）；  n.很受欢迎的事物
英文释义: an act of hitting somebody/something with your hand or with an object held in your hand
例句: The man was hit by the ball.
例句释义: 这个男人被球砸中了。

详细释义: n.地基；底座；  adj.卑鄙的，无耻的
英文释义: the bottom or lowest part of something; the part on which something rests or stands
例句: A firm base is very important for building a house.
例句释义: 稳固的地基对于建造房屋十分重要。

英文释义: a thing that you do for interest or pleasure, or in order to achieve a particular aim
例句: We all like outdoor activities, such as playing tennis and flying kites.
例句释义: 我们都喜欢参加户外活动，比如打网球和放风筝。

英文释义: a large ball of burning gas in space that we see as a point of light in the sky at night; an object, a decoration, a mark, etc., usually with five or six points, whose shape represents a star; a famous and excellent singer, performer, sports player, etc.;  a person who has the main part, or one of the main parts, in a film/movie, play, etc.
例句: There are many happy stars.
例句释义: 这里有很多快乐的星星。

英文释义: a piece of furniture that consists of a flat top supported by legs
例句: The meeting room had a large table big enough for fifteen people to sit around.
例句释义: 这间会议室有一个大桌子，足够坐下十五个人。

详细释义: n.法院，法庭；球场；  v.招致灾祸
英文释义: a formal legal meeting in which evidence about crimes, disagreements, etc., is presented to a judge and often a jury so that decisions can be made according to the law
例句: The aim of the court is to provide justice.
例句释义: 法庭致力于寻求公正。

英文释义: to make things to be sold, especially in large quantities
例句: The factory produced things quickly.
例句释义: 这家工厂生产产品的速度很快。

英文释义: to put food in your mouth, chew it and swallow it; to have a meal
例句: The boy is eating watermelon.
例句释义: 那个男孩正在吃西瓜。

英文释义: to give lessons to students in a school, college, university, etc.; to help somebody learn something by giving information about it
例句: The father is teaching his daughter how to draw.
例句释义: 这位父亲正在教他的女儿画画。

详细释义: n.油，食用油；  v.给（机器等）上油，涂油
英文释义: a smooth thick liquid that is made from plants or animals and is used in cooking
例句: The salad tastes better if you add some oil.
例句释义: 加些菜油，沙拉会更好吃。

英文释义: one of two equal or nearly equal parts into which something can be divided
例句: Compared to the left, the plastic bottle on the right side is half full.
例句释义: 相比左边的来说，右边的塑料瓶是半满的。

英文释义: all the circumstances and things that are happening at a particular time and in a particular place
例句: The general is analyzing the current situation of the war.
例句释义: 将军正在分析当前战争的形势。

英文释义: not difficult; done or obtained without a lot of effort or problems
例句: It is easy for the tall boy to touch the ceiling.
例句释义: 这个高个子男孩很容易摸到天花板。

英文释义: the amount of money that you need in order to buy, make or do something
例句: The cost of this new house is one million dollars.
例句释义: 这座新房子的价格是一百万美元。

英文释义: the production of goods from raw materials, especially in factories; the quality of working hard
例句: Heavy industry is important for our economy. Build more factories!
例句释义: 重工业对于我们的经济很重要，建造更多的工厂吧！

英文释义: the shape or form of a person's body
例句: She maintains her figure by doing yoga.
例句释义: 她通过做瑜伽来保持身材。

英文释义: a road in a city or town that has houses or other buildings on one or both sides
例句: There are no people on the street at night.
例句释义: 到了晚上，街上就空无一人。

例句: He is describing the image of the thief to the police.
例句释义: 他正在向警方描述小偷的形象。

英文释义: a device that is connected to a telephone system and that you use to listen or speak to someone who is somewhere else
例句: They are all using their phones.
例句释义: 他们都在玩自己的手机。

详细释义: det.二者之一；（两者中的）各方；  adv.（用于否定句或短语后）也
例句: The girl is choosing between getting either a cat or a dog.
例句释义: 这个小女孩正在考虑是要一只狗呢，还是猫呢？

英文释义: information that is produced or stored by a computer
例句: A huge amount of data can be stored on a computer.
例句释义: 一台电脑可以储存大量数据。

英文释义: to put something over, on top of, or in front of (something else) especially in order to protect, hide, or close it
例句: He covers his face with sunglasses and a face mask.
例句释义: 他用墨镜和口罩遮住了脸。

英文释义: to a great degree; very; really
例句: The woman in front is quite tall compared to the woman behind.
例句释义: 和后面的女人相比，前面那个女人相当高。

英文释义: a painting or drawing, etc. that shows a scene, a person or thing; a photograph
例句: We took a group picture by this famous attraction in Rome.
例句释义: 我们在罗马的这个著名景点前拍了一张合照。

详细释义: adj.清澈的；清楚的；  vi.变清澈；  vt.清除；  n.空隙；  adv.不靠近
英文释义: very obvious; easy to see/hear, not causing or allowing doubt
例句: The water here is so clean and clear!
例句释义: 这里的水真是干净清澈！

英文释义: to do an activity or train regularly so that you can improve your skill
例句: The little girl practices yoga with her mom everyday.
例句释义: 小女孩每天都同妈妈练习瑜伽。

英文释义: an amount that is cut or separated from a larger section of something
例句: The yellow cup smashed into pieces.
例句释义: 这个黄杯子碎成了很多块。

英文释义: the surface of the earth that is not sea
例句: This land is covered with green grass.
例句释义: 这片土地上长满了青草。

英文释义: that happened or began only a short time ago
例句: These are my recent photos.
例句释义: 这些是我最近拍的照片。

英文释义: if you describe a person, object, event, or situation, you say what they are like or what happened
例句: She described her missing child to a passer-by.
例句释义: 她向一位路人描述她走失的孩子的模样。

英文释义: a cream, jelly or liquid that you put on your hair or skin to make it look better; a thing that is grown or produced, usually for sale; a thing produced during a natural, chemical or industrial process
例句: We sell a range of products for skincare and health.
例句释义: 我们卖一系列护肤和保健产品。

详细释义: n.医生，医师；  vt.窜改，伪造
英文释义: a person who is skilled in the science of medicine :a person who is trained and licensed to treat sick and injured people
例句: I love being a doctor and saving lives, but it's also very hard.
例句释义: 我想成为一名拯救生命的医生，但是这非常困难。

详细释义: n. 墙；  v. 堵塞；用墙围住
英文释义: a long vertical solid structure, made of stone, brick or concrete, that surrounds, divides or protects an area of land
例句: This wall is made up of oddly shaped bricks.
例句释义: 这道墙由形状不规则的砖砌成。

详细释义: n.病人，患者；  adj.有耐心的，能忍耐的
英文释义: a person who is receiving medical treatment, especially in a hospital
例句: As a nurse, I love to work closely with my patients.
例句释义: 作为一名护士，我喜欢近距离接触我的病人们。

英文释义: (often in compounds) a person who works, especially one who does a particular kind of work; a person who is employed in a company or industry, especially somebody who does physical work rather than organizing things or managing people
例句: The worker was ready to work.
例句释义: 工人准备好工作了。

英文释义: reports of recent events that appear in newspapers or on television or radio; new information about something that has happened recently
例句: I try to keep up with the latest news about developments in our industry.
例句释义: 我会努力跟上行业发展的最新动态。

英文释义: a set of questions or problems that are designed to measure a person's knowledge, skills, or abilities
例句: If you study for the test, it will be easy.
例句释义: 如果认真准备了，考试会很简单。

英文释义: a showing of a movie in a theater
例句: We are going to see an open-air movie.
例句释义: 我们准备看一场露天电影。

详细释义: adj.有把握的；肯定的，必然的
英文释义: that you can rely on to happen or to be true
例句: This actor is certain that he will win the award.
例句释义: 这个演员确信他可以获奖。

详细释义: adj.北方的；  adv.向北方；  n.北方
英文释义: in or towards the north
例句: The North Pole is at the northern part of the Earth.
例句释义: 北极在地球的北端。

英文释义: your own; not belonging to or connected with anyone else
例句: He is riding his personal bike.
例句释义: 他正在骑他自己的自行车。

详细释义: adv. 简单地；仅仅，只不过
英文释义: in a way that is natural and plain
例句: The room is simply furnished.
例句释义: 这间屋子陈设简单朴素。

详细释义: num.第三的；第三；  n.三分之一
英文释义: occupying the number three position in a series
例句: The bronze medal was awarded for the third place.
例句释义: 铜牌被颁发给了第三名。

英文释义: the use of science in industry, engineering, etc. to invent useful things or to solve problems; machinery or equipment designed using technology
例句: Now there are more and more technology products in our lives.
例句释义: 现在我们的生活中出现了越来越多的科技产品。

英文释义: to use your hands to grasp and hold onto (someone or something)
例句: She enjoys catching butterflies.
例句释义: 她可喜欢捉蝴蝶了。

详细释义: n.脚步，脚步声；  vi.走，举步
英文释义: the act of lifting your foot and putting it down in order to walk or move somewhere; the sound this makes
例句: He's so excited to see his baby girl take her first step.
例句释义: 看到他的宝贝女儿迈出第一步，他激动极了。

英文释义: a very young child or animal
例句: What a cute hat for a baby!
例句释义: 好可爱的婴儿帽啊！

英文释义: an electronic machine that can store and work with large amounts of information
例句: Why is there only a white background on the computer screen?
例句释义: 为什么电脑屏幕上只有一个白色的背景？

英文释义: a class or group of people or things that share particular qualities or features and are part of a larger group; a kind or sort
例句: There are several types of dogs for sale.
例句释义: 这里有几个种类的狗在售卖。

英文释义: the act of listening to, looking at or thinking about something/somebody carefully; interest that people show in somebody/something; things that somebody does to try to please you or to show their interest in you; special care, action or treatment
例句: Only one student in the class was paying attention to what the teacher was saying.
例句释义: 班上只有一个学生在专心听老师讲课。

详细释义: v. 画；吸引；  n. 平局
英文释义: to make (a picture, image, etc.) by making lines on a surface especially with a pencil, pen, marker, chalk, etc., but not usually with paint
例句: The girls are sitting on the ground drawing pictures.
例句释义: 女孩们正坐在地上画画。

详细释义: n. 电影；薄层；  v. 拍摄
英文释义: a series of moving pictures recorded with sound that tells story, shown on television or at the cinema.
例句: This film tells of a love story that is happening on a ship.
例句释义: 这部电影讲述了一个发生在船上的爱情故事。

详细释义: adj. 共和国的，共和政体的；  n. 共和主义者
英文释义: a person who supports a form of government with a president and politicians elected by the people and with no king or queen
例句: The United States has a republican form of government.
例句释义: 美国政府是共和制的。

英文释义: a tall plant that can live a long time. Trees have a thick central wooden trunk from which branches grow, usually with leaves on them
例句: People are resting under the big tree.
例句释义: 人们在这棵大树下休息。

英文释义: a person, book or document that provides information, especially for study, a piece of written work or news
例句: Milk, delivered straight from the source.
例句释义: 牛奶，从源头新鲜直送。

详细释义: adj. 红色的；  n. 红色
英文释义: having the color of blood
例句: I like painting with red paint, because red is a lucky color.
例句释义: 我画画的时候喜欢用红色的颜料，因为红色象征着幸运。

英文释义: almost; not quite; not completely
例句: The ball nearly went in!
例句释义: 那个球差点儿就进了！

英文释义: a group of people who form a business, club, etc. together in order to achieve a particular aim
例句: The UN is an organization which supports world peace.
例句释义: 联合国是一个支持世界和平的组织。

英文释义: to decide which thing or person you want out of the ones that are available; to prefer or decide to do something
例句: You should choose healthy foods if you don't want to get fat.
例句释义: 如果你不想长胖，你就应该选择健康的食物。

详细释义: v. 引起，使发生；  n. 原因，理由
英文释义: to make something happen, especially something bad or unpleasant
例句: Smoking can cause lung cancer.
例句释义: 吸烟可致肺癌。

英文释义: the substance that looks like a mass of fine threads growing especially on the head; one of these threads growing on the body of people and some animals
例句: The lady has such long smooth hair.
例句释义: 这位女士有一头长而柔顺的秀发。

英文释义: any of the periods of 100 years before or after the birth of Christ
例句: The telephone was invented in the 19th century.
例句释义: 电话是19世纪发明的。

英文释义: the facts, signs or objects that make you believe that something is true
例句: He is collecting evidence at the crime scene.
例句释义: 他正在犯罪现场收集证据。
