英文释义: an opening in the wall or roof of a building, car, etc., usually covered with glass, that allows light and air to come in and people to see out; the glass in a window
例句: The old man stood at the window and looked out.
例句释义: 老人站在窗前，向外看去。

详细释义: adj. 困难的，难做的；难对付的，不易相处的
英文释义: not easy; needing effort or skill to do or to understand
例句: It is difficult for her to carry such a huge stone.
例句释义: 让她搬起这么大的一块石头实在太难了！

英文释义: to pay attention to somebody/something that you can hear
例句: The dog is listening to music.
例句释义: 这只狗正在听音乐。

英文释义: in a short time from now; a short time after something else has happened
例句: It'll soon be the New Year.
例句释义: 马上就到新年了。

详细释义: n.文化；文明；（细菌或细胞）培养；（作物）种植
英文释义: the customs and beliefs, art, way of life and social organization of a particular country or group
例句: China is a beautiful country full of culture and history.
例句释义: 中国是一个具有深厚文化和历史底蕴的美丽国家。

详细释义: num.十亿；数以十亿计；大量；  adj.大量的
英文释义: 1?000?000?000; one thousand million
例句: The baby counted 9 zeros in the number 1 billion.
例句释义: 这个小孩从10亿这个数字里数出了9个零。

详细释义: n.机会；偶然，偶发事件；  vi.偶然发生；  adj.偶然的；  vt.冒……的险
英文释义: a possibility of something happening, especially something that you want
例句: I have a chance to win the prize.
例句释义: 我有机会赢得这个奖品。

英文释义: usable power that comes from heat, electricity, etc.
例句: The man is full of energy every morning.
例句释义: 这个人每天早晨都精力充沛。

英文释义: a length of time during which a series of events or an action takes place or is completed
例句: He became a math teacher over a period of four years.
例句释义: 他花了四年的时间成了一名数学老师。

详细释义: n.夏季；  adj.夏季的，在夏季的；  vi.避暑
英文释义: the warmest season of the year that is after spring and before autumn
例句: During summer, people like to eat watermelons and go swimming.
例句释义: 在夏天，人们喜欢吃西瓜和去游泳。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to understand or become aware of a particular fact or situation
例句: "So that's how the word is spelled!" the little boy finally realized.
例句释义: “原来这个单词是这样拼的！”小男孩终于意识到了这一点。

英文释义: the number 100
例句: Whose face is on the hundred-dollar bill?
例句释义: 一百元美钞上是谁的脸？

详细释义: adj. 可用的，可获得的；有空的；可找到的
英文释义: that you can get, buy or find; (of a person) free to see or talk to people
例句: The receptionist has told me that there was only one room available.
例句释义: 前台接待员告诉我只有一个房间可以入住。

英文释义: a living thing that grows in the ground, usually has leaves or flowers, and needs sun and water to survive
例句: There are many different kinds of green plants.
例句释义: 这里有许多不同种类的绿色植物。

详细释义: adj.有可能的；适合的；  adv.很可能
英文释义: probable or expected
例句: It's likely that after thunder, there'll be rain.
例句释义: 打雷后可能要下雨了。

英文释义: a time when a particular situation makes it possible to do or achieve something
例句: She saw the opportunity on a billboard to realize her dream to become a singer.
例句释义: 她在广告牌上看到了实现梦想，成为歌手的机会。

英文释义: each of the various parts in a series, an equation, etc.
例句: The autumn term in China begins from September 1st.
例句释义: 中国的秋季学期是从9月1日开始的。

详细释义: adj.矮的，短的；  adv.缺少，未达到；  n.电影短片
英文释义: measuring or covering a small length or distance, or a smaller length or distance than usual; (of a person) small in height; lasting or taking a small amount of time or less time than usual; (of a period of time) seeming to have passed very quickly; not having enough of something; lacking something; being a shorter form of a name or word; (of a person) speaking to somebody using few words in a way that seems rude
例句: Short hair is in style now.
例句释义: 现在很流行短发。

英文释义: a message that is written down or printed on paper and usually put in an envelope and sent to somebody
例句: The little girl is learning the letters.
例句释义: 小女孩正在学习字母。

详细释义: n.环境，形势；状况，状态；疾病；  v.使适应，使处于良好状态
英文释义: the circumstances or situation in which people live, work or do things
例句: The living conditions here are really poor.
例句释义: 这儿的生活条件真的很差。

英文释义: an act of choosing between two or more possibilities; something that you can choose;  the right to choose or the possibility of choosing
例句: It's hard for him to make a choice between new shoes and a new game console.
例句释义: 对他来说，在新鞋和新游戏机中做选择非常困难。

详细释义: adj.单个的；未婚的；单身的；  n.单程票
英文释义: (of a person) not married or having a romantic relationship with somebody
例句: There is a single shoe on the ground.
例句释义: 地上有一只单独的鞋。

详细释义: v. 统治，控制；  n. 规则，规定，规章，条例
英文释义: to control and have authority over a country, a group of people, etc.
例句: Once upon a time, there was a king ruling the country.
例句释义: 很久以前，有一位国王统治着这个国家。

英文释义: a person’s female child
例句: The father is staring at his daughter with a smile.
例句释义: 这个爸爸微笑着看着他的女儿。

英文释义: the activities that relate to running a company, school, or other organization; the people who plan, organize and run a business, an institution, etc.; the government of a country, especially the US; the act of giving a drug to somebody
例句: He works in administration.
例句释义: 他在管理部门工作。

详细释义: adv.向南方，在南方；  adj.南方的；  n.南方
英文释义: towards the south
例句: A large number of birds fly south every winter.
例句释义: 每年冬季，大量鸟类向南方迁徙。

英文释义: the man that somebody is married to; a married man
例句: She gave her husband a glass of water.
例句释义: 她递给她丈夫一杯水。

详细释义: n.国会；代表大会；议会；立法机关
英文释义: (in the US and some other countries) the name of the group of people who are elected to make laws, in the US consisting of the Senate and the House of Representatives
例句: A congress is a large meeting that is held to discuss national policies.
例句释义: 国会是讨论国家大事的大型会议。

详细释义: n.地板，地面；楼层；底部；  vt.铺地板；击倒
英文释义: the part of a room on which you stand
例句: The floor of this room is made of wood.
例句释义: 这个房间的地板是木头做的。

详细释义: n.（社会性、政治性）活动，运动；  v.从事活动
英文释义: a series of planned activities that are intended to achieve a particular social, commercial or political aim
例句: Many people launched a campaign to call for environmental protection.
例句释义: 许多人发起了一场呼吁环保的运动。

详细释义: n.材料，原料；  adj.物质的，客观存在的
英文释义: a substance that things can be made from; cloth used for making clothes, curtains, etc.; things that are needed in order to do a particular activity; information or ideas used in books, etc.
例句: Many different materials are needed for construction work.
例句释义: 建造工程需要很多种不同的建筑材料。

英文释义: all the people who live in a particular area, city or country; the total number of people who live there; a particular group of people or animals living in a particular area
例句: The population of the world is over seven billion.
例句释义: 世界人口超过70亿。

英文释义: the relationship between production, trade and the supply of money in a particular country or region; a country, when you are thinking about its economic system
例句: The economy is improving and people have more money.
例句释义: 经济正在改善，人们也有了更多的钱。

英文释义: of or relating to the treatment of diseases and injuries; of or relating to medicine
例句: There is a lot of medical equipment in the operating room.
例句释义: 手术室里有很多医疗器材。

英文释义: a large building where people who are ill/sick or injured are given medical treatment and care
例句: The patient was taken to the hospital for treatment.
例句释义: 病人被带进医院进行治疗。

英文释义: a building that is used for Christian religious services
例句: The church is located in a beautiful suburb.
例句释义: 教堂位于一处美丽的郊区。

详细释义: v.关闭；  n.结束；  adj.关闭的；亲密的；  adv.（时间/距离）接近地
英文释义: to put something into a position so that it covers an opening; to get into this position
例句: The man is closing the door.
例句释义: 这个人正在关门。

详细释义: num. 一千，一千个；  n. 许多，无数
英文释义: the number 1,000
例句: I've got a thousand followers online. I'm so popular!
例句释义: 我在线上有一千位粉丝。我真是太受欢迎啦！

英文释义: to put something valuable or important in a dangerous situation, in which it could be lost or damaged; to do something that may mean that you get into a situation which is unpleasant or harmful for you
例句: The fireman risks his life by running into the fire.
例句释义: 消防员冒着生命危险冲进火场。

详细释义: adj.当前的，现在的；流动的；  n.水流，电流
英文释义: happening now; of the present time
例句: "Is the news current?" "No, it's from yesterday."
例句释义: “这是最新的新闻吗？”“不，这是昨天的了。”

详细释义: n. 火；火灾；  v. 解雇
英文释义: the light and heat and especially the flame produced by burning
例句: There is a fire burning by the sea.
例句释义: 海边有一堆燃烧的火。

英文释义: the period of time that will come after the present time
例句: Maybe humans will live on other planets in the future.
例句释义: 人类在未来也许会居住在其他星球上。

英文释义: not right or correct
例句: This little kid is wearing her shoes the wrong way round.
例句释义: 这个小孩把鞋穿错了。

英文释义: to make somebody take part in something
例句: Making a cake involves mixing milk, eggs, flour and sugar before baking.
例句释义: 制作蛋糕需要在烘焙前混合牛奶、鸡蛋、面粉和糖。

英文释义: the act of defending someone or something from attack
例句: The iron fence built by the shepherd is a great defense against the wolf.
例句释义: 牧羊人建造的铁栅栏可以有效地防狼。

英文释义: used instead of someone in negative sentences and in questions after if/whether, and after verbs such as prevent, forbid, avoid, etc.; any person at all; it does not matter who; (in negative sentences) an important person
例句: Would anyone like some gum?
例句释义: 有人想要口香糖吗？

详细释义: v. 增加，提高；  n. 增加，增强，提高
英文释义: to become or to make something greater in amount, number, value, etc.
例句: The population has increased dramatically in recent years.
例句释义: 近年来，人口急剧增加。

英文释义: a place at an airport where you go after your passport has been checked so that officials can find out if you are carrying illegal drugs or weapons
例句: You must go through the security check at the airport.
例句释义: 在机场，你必须进行安全检查。

详细释义: n.银行；  v.把钱存入银行
英文释义: an organization that provides various financial services, for example keeping or lending money
例句: Is my bank a safe place to keep my money?
例句释义: 我的银行是保管钱的安全之所吗？

详细释义: adv.无疑，确定；当然，没问题（用于回答）
英文释义: without doubt
例句: Every human is certainly born and will certainly die.
例句释义: 每个人无疑都会经历出生和死亡。

详细释义: n.西方，西部；  adj.西的，西方的；  adv.向西方
英文释义: the direction where the sun sets :the direction that is the opposite of east
例句: On the compass, "W" stands for west.
例句释义: 在指南针上，“W”代表西方。

英文释义: activity that you do for pleasure and that needs physical effort or skill, usually done in a special area and according to fixed rules
例句: He can play various sports.
例句释义: 他擅长多种运动。

详细释义: n.木板；董事会；  v.上（飞机、车、船等）
英文释义: a flat piece of material (such as wood or cardboard) that is used for a special purpose
例句: There is a board hanging on the outside of the door.
例句释义: 门外挂着一块木板。

英文释义: to search for (someone or something)
例句: Let's play hide-and-seek!
例句释义: 让我们来玩捉迷藏吧！

英文释义: used to express the cost or amount of something for each person, number used, distance travelled, etc.
例句: You are allowed to drive at 80 kilometers per hour on this road.
例句释义: 这条路限速每小时80公里。

详细释义: n.科目；实验对象；  vt.使臣服，使顺从
英文释义: an area of knowledge that is studied in school; a thing or person that is being discussed, described or dealt with
例句: English was my favorite subject in school.
例句释义: 英语是我在学校里最喜欢的学科。

英文释义: a person who has a position of authority or command in the military
例句: He's a friendly police officer.
例句释义: 他是一个和善的警察。

英文释义: belonging to or for the use of a particular person or group; not for public use
例句: Do not enter! This is Mr. Dog's private property.
例句释义: 禁止进入！这是狗先生的私人住宅。

详细释义: n.休息；剩余的部分；  v.休息
英文释义: a period of time in which you relax, sleep, or do nothing after you have been active or doing work
例句: On Sunday I like to sleep late and get more rest.
例句释义: 星期天我喜欢睡懒觉，多休息会儿。

英文释义: the way that somebody behaves, especially towards other people
例句: People's behavior often reflects their personal qualities.
例句释义: 人们的举止通常可以体现出他们的个人素质。

英文释义: an agreement, especially in business, on particular conditions for buying or doing something
例句: So we agree, you'll buy my house? Do we have a deal? Good!
例句释义: 那么你确定要买我的房子？我们说好了吧？很好！

详细释义: n.表演，演出；表现；执行；性能
英文释义: the act of performing a play, concert or some other form of entertainment; the way a person performs in a play, concert, etc.
例句: Their music was great. I really loved the performance.
例句释义: 他们的音乐听起来很棒，我很爱这场演出。

详细释义: v.打架，对抗；  n.斗争；比赛
英文释义: to take part in a war or battle against an enemy
例句: "Let's fight!" the man said to the other player.
例句释义: "来吧，让我们战斗吧！" 那个男人对他的对手说道。

详细释义: v. 扔，抛，投掷；  n. 投，掷
英文释义: to cause (something) to move out of your hand and through the air by quickly moving your arm forward
例句: The two kids are throwing balls to each other.
例句释义: 这两个孩子在互相扔球。

详细释义: n.顶部；  adj.最高的；  vt.达到顶端
英文释义: the highest part or point of something
例句: He stands on the top of the mountain.
例句释义: 他正站在山顶上。

英文释义: fast; soon; after a short time
例句: She runs and eats so quickly.
例句释义: 她跑步和吃饭都超快。

详细释义: prep.经过；  adv.经过；  adj.过去的，结束的；  n.过去
英文释义: on or to the other side of somebody/something
例句: She walked past me without stopping.
例句释义: 她从我面前走过去，连停都没停。

英文释义: the act of kicking or hitting the ball into the goal; a point that is scored for this
例句: The boy's goal is to become as strong as the man in the poster.
例句释义: 男孩的目标是变得像海报里的男人一样强壮。

英文释义: a piece of furniture for sleeping on
例句: My bed is so comfortable.
例句释义: 我的床相当舒服。

英文释义: to ask for sth. to eat or drink in a restaurant, bar, etc.
例句:
"Can I help you?"
"Yes, we'd like to order some food."
例句释义:
请问有什么需要吗？
我们想点一些吃的。

英文释义: a person who writes books or the person who wrote a particular book
例句: Lu Xun is the author of this book.
例句释义: 鲁迅是这本书的作者。

英文释义: to make something full of something; to become full of something
例句: The bottle is filled with juice.
例句释义: 这瓶子里装满了果汁。

英文释义: to be a symbol of something
例句: This hand gesture represents love.
例句释义: 这个手势象征着爱。

英文释义: a point or distance at which the outline of an object is clearly seen by the eye or through a lens
例句: Make sure your subject is in focus before taking the photo.
例句释义: 拍照前你要确保拍摄对象已对焦。

英文释义: in or from a country that is not your own
例句: Our English teacher is from a foreign country.
例句释义: 我们的英语老师来自外国。

英文释义: to fall or allow something to fall by accident
例句: I accidentally dropped my phone. So hurt!
例句释义: 我不小心把手机弄掉了。真疼！

英文释义: the red liquid that flows through the bodies of people and animals
例句: The doctor took some blood from me during my checkup.
例句释义: 医生在给我检查时抽了点儿血。

英文释义: in or into a position covering, touching or forming part of a surface
例句: Once upon a time, there was a temple upon a mountain.
例句释义: 从前有座山，山上有座庙。

英文释义: a business or an organization that provides a particular service especially on behalf of other businesses or organizations; a government department that provides a particular service
例句: It's more convenient to buy tickets from a ticket agency.
例句释义: 从车票代售点买票更方便。

英文释义: to use your hands, arms or body in order to make somebody/something move forward or away from you; to move part of your body into a particular position
例句: The man tried very hard to push the car.
例句释义: 这个男人非常努力地推车。

英文释义: all the plants, animals and things that exist in the universe that are not made by people; the way that things happen in the physical world when it is not controlled by people
例句: She loves to relax surrounded by nature.
例句释义: 她喜欢在大自然的环绕下进行放松。

英文释义: the appearance that things have that results from the way in which they reflect light. Red, orange and green are colours.
例句: The kids painted their hands every color of the rainbow.
例句释义: 小孩子们把彩虹的几种颜色都画在手上。

英文释义: not long ago
例句: He recently spent some time on the beach and got a tan.
例句释义: 他最近在海滩上待了一段时间，晒黑了。

详细释义: n. 商店；储存品；  v. 贮藏，储存
英文释义: a large shop that sells many different types of goods
例句: I took my daughter to the grocery store to buy some food.
例句释义: 我带着女儿去杂货店买一些食物。

英文释义: to make something less or smaller in size, quantity, price, etc.
例句: The price of this phone is reduced to ￥998 in the sale.
例句释义: 这款手机的价格在促销中降至998元。

详细释义: n.声音，声响；  v.听起来；  adj.正当的，有根据的
英文释义: what you can hear coming from a television, radio, etc., or as part of a film/movie
例句: The sound coming from the speakers was very loud.
例句释义: 喇叭里传出来的声音很大。

英文释义: a short piece of writing to help you remember something
例句: This board is covered with notes we left.
例句释义: 告示板上贴满了我们之前留下的便条。

详细释义: vt.罚款；  n.罚款；  adj.好的，优质的；精致的；  adv.合适地，恰好地
英文释义: a sum of money that must be paid as punishment for breaking a law or rule
例句: The policeman fined the driver for driving too fast.
例句释义: 警察因那个司机超速而对他处以罚款。

详细释义: prep. 靠近；  adv. 近，接近；  adj. 近的
英文释义: at a short distance away from somebody/something
例句: The little boy sits near the fire.
例句释义: 这个小男孩坐在靠近火堆的位置。

英文释义: the act of moving your body or a part of your body; a group of people with a common ideology who try together to achieve certain general goals
例句: Dancing is the art of movement.
例句释义: 舞蹈是动作的艺术。

英文释义: one side of a sheet of paper especially in a book, magazine, etc.
例句: Please turn your book to the next page.
例句释义: 请把书翻到下一页。

英文释义: to go or come into (something)
例句: Two men and a woman are entering the building.
例句释义: 两男一女正在走进大楼。

详细释义: v.分享；分配，均分；  n.一份，份额
英文释义: to have or use something at the same time as somebody else
例句: Would you like to share some ice cream with me?
例句释义: 你想和我一起分享冰激凌吗？

英文释义: happening often; existing in large numbers or in many places
例句: Both boys share a common interest.
例句释义: 这两个男孩有共同的爱好。

英文释义: deserving pity and sympathy; having very little money; not having enough money for basic needs
例句: The poor homeless man begged for money on the street.
例句释义: 这个可怜的无家可归的男人在街上乞讨。

详细释义: adj.自然界的；天然的；正常的；天生的
英文释义: existing in nature and not made or caused by people :coming from nature
例句: There are more green trees in the natural environment than in the urban environment.
例句释义: 自然环境中的绿树比城市环境中的多。

详细释义: n. （速度上的）比赛；  v. 参加竞赛
英文释义: a competition between people, animals, vehicles, etc. to see which one is the fastest
例句: It was fun participating in the race.
例句释义: 参加赛车比赛真的很好玩。

英文释义: a feeling of worry, especially one that is shared by many people; a desire to protect and help somebody/something
例句: She showed genuine concern towards her depressed friend.
例句释义: 她对沮丧的朋友表现出真诚的关心。

详细释义: n.一连串；系列，系列节目；连续比赛
英文释义: several events or things of a similar kind that happen one after the other; a set of radio or television programmes that deal with the same subject or that have the same characters
例句: A series of coinciding incidents resulted in the glass-breaking.
例句释义: 一连串巧合的事件导致玻璃被打碎。

英文释义: having a special or secret meaning that is not understood by everyone
例句: This day is significant for me because it's my father's birthday.
例句释义: 这一天对我意义重大，因为这天是我爸爸的生日。

英文释义: like somebody/something but not exactly the same
例句: These two girls are very similar.
例句释义: 这两个女孩长得很像。

英文释义: [(hot up) (informal) to become more exciting or to show an increase in activity
例句: A fan is useless when it's this hot.
例句释义: 天气这么热，电风扇都没用了。

英文释义: any one of the systems of human language that are used and understood by a particular group of people
例句: People from different countries speak different languages.
例句释义: 不同国家的人讲不同的语言。

英文释义: in the way that is usual or normal; most often
例句: We usually have lunch at 12:00.
例句释义: 我们通常在十二点吃午饭。

英文释义: a spoken or written answer
例句: He gave a response to the question raised by his student.
例句释义: 他对学生提出的问题给予作答。

英文释义: no longer alive or living: no longer having life
例句: The fish is dead.
例句释义: 这条鱼死了。

详细释义: v.升起，上升，上涨；起身；增长；  n.增长；升起，上升，上涨
英文释义: to come or go upwards; to reach a higher level or position
例句: The bright sun rises on the horizon.
例句释义: 明亮的太阳从地平线上升起。

英文释义: a living thing that is not a human being or plant
例句: There are many kinds of animals on Earth.
例句释义: 地球上的动物种类繁多。

英文释义: a number that divides into another number exactly
例句: An important factor for him when buying a car is its appearance.
例句释义: 车的外观是他买车时的一个重要考虑因素。

英文释义: a period of ten years, especially a continuous period, such as 1910C1919 or 2000C2009
例句: People can change a lot after a decade.
例句释义: 十年会给人带来很大的变化。

英文释义: a piece of writing about a particular subject in a newspaper or magazine
例句: She is reading the article in the newspaper.
例句释义: 她正在阅读报纸上的文章。

详细释义: v.射门；射击，射伤；  n.新芽
英文释义: to try to kick, hit or throw the ball into a goal or to score a point
例句: The Argentine star shot with his right foot, scoring a vital goal.
例句释义: 这位阿根廷队球星用他的右脚射进了关键性的一球。

详细释义: n. 东方；  adj. 朝（或向）东方的；  adv. 在东方
英文释义: the direction that you look towards to see the sun rise; one of the four main points of the compass
例句: The sun rises from the east.
例句释义: 太阳从东边升起。

详细释义: v.储蓄；节省；  n.（守门员的）救球
英文释义: to keep money instead of spending it; to put money away especially in a bank so that you will have it in the future
例句: You have to try to save money for emergency.
例句释义: 你应该试着存点钱，以备不时之需。

英文释义: a person who creates works of art, especially paintings or drawings; a professional entertainer such as a singer, a dancer or an actor
例句: The artist is spraying colors on the wall.
例句释义: 这个艺术家在朝墙上喷涂颜料。

英文释义: a view that you see
例句: The sunset over the road created quite a beautiful scene.
例句释义: 道路尽头的日落创造了一幅唯美的景象。

英文释义: a supply of something that is available for use
例句: The stock was enough to fulfill the demand for the next three months.
例句释义: 库存足够满足接下来三个月的需求了。

英文释义: the series of jobs that a person has in a particular area of work, usually involving more responsibility as time passes
例句: She has built her career as a businesswoman.
例句释义: 她以一个女商人的身份开始了职业生涯。

英文释义: used to show that something happened or is true although something else might have happened to prevent it
例句: Despite the windy day, the reporter still worked outdoors.
例句释义: 尽管风很大，这个记者仍然在户外工作。

英文释义: in the centre of an area or object; easily reached from many areas
例句: We should all meet at a central point.
例句释义: 我们都应该去中心点那儿碰头。

英文释义: as a result of something just mentioned
例句: She exercises every day, thus has managed to lose some weight.
例句释义: 她每天都锻炼，因此减肥成功了。

英文释义: something that is done to cure an illness or injury, or to make somebody look and feel good
例句: She is receiving treatment for a hand injury.
例句释义: 她的手受伤了，正在接受治疗。

英文释义: more than something
例句: The equation is beyond me, and it won't come out.
例句释义: 这道方程题超出了我的理解范围，怎么也解不出来。

英文释义: feeling or showing pleasure; pleased
例句: Look at her big smile! She is so happy.
例句释义: 快看她那大大的笑容，她真的很快乐。

英文释义: used to emphasize that something is correct in every way or in every detail
例句: I want all my grass to be exactly the same height!
例句释义: 我要我的草都完全一样高。

英文释义: to make sure that somebody/something is not harmed, injured, damaged, etc.
例句: The woman protected her child from danger.
例句释义: 那个女人保护孩子不受伤害。

英文释义: to come near to somebody/something in distance or time
例句: The turtle is slowly approaching the finish line.
例句释义: 乌龟正缓缓爬向终点线。

详细释义: vi.躺；说谎，欺骗；  n.谎话，假象
英文释义: (of a person or an animal) to be or put yourself in a flat or horizontal position so that you are not standing or sitting
例句: She likes to lie down next to her baby brother.
例句释义: 她喜欢躺在她弟弟旁边。

英文释义: how large or small a person or thing is
例句: These shoes come in different sizes: medium, small and large.
例句释义: 这些鞋子有不同的尺寸：中号、小号和大号。

英文释义: an animal with four legs and a tail, often kept as a pet or trained for work, for example hunting or guarding buildings. There are many types of dog, some of which are wild.; a male dog, fox or wolf
例句: Your dog is really cute.
例句释义: 你的狗真可爱。

详细释义: n.资金，基金；  v.拨款，提供资金
英文释义: an amount of money that is used for a special purpose; money on deposit on which checks or drafts can be drawn
例句: These coins are my holiday fund.
例句释义: 这些零花钱是我的假日基金。

英文释义: needing to be thought about carefully; not only for pleasure; sincere about something; not joking or meant as a joke
例句: He is always very serious while working.
例句释义: 他工作时总是很认真。

英文释义: to happen
例句: Car accidents can occur very quickly.
例句释义: 车祸会发生在一瞬间。

英文释义: the main ways that large numbers of people receive information and entertainment, that is television, radio, newspapers and the Internet
例句: These days we get information from all kinds of different media.
例句释义: 如今，我们从各种不同的媒体获取信息。

详细释义: adj. 准备好的；现成的；  v. 预备，准备
英文释义: fully prepared for what you are going to do
例句: He is ready to run.
例句释义: 他准备好起跑了。

详细释义: v. 签署；  n. 记号，符号
英文释义: to write your name on a document, letter, etc. to show that you have written it, that you agree with what it says, or that it is genuine
例句: Please sign your name on this paper.
例句释义: 请在这张纸上签下你的名字。

英文释义: an idea, plan, opinion, picture, etc., that is formed in your mind; something that you think of
例句: He has many thoughts about his future.
例句释义: 他对未来有很多想法。

详细释义: n. 目录，表，名单；  v. 记入名单内
英文释义: a series of names, items, figures, etc., especially when they are written or printed
例句: I am checking my shopping list.
例句释义: 我在核对我的购物清单。

详细释义: adj.个别的，单独的；属于个人的；  n.独立的个体
英文释义: connected with one person; designed for one person
例句: She is the individual girl in this graduation photo.
例句释义: 在这张毕业照里，她是唯一一个女生。

英文释义: not complicated; easy to understand or do
例句: You can solve this problem―it's simple!
例句释义: 你可以解决这个问题的，它很简单！

详细释义: n. 质量；  adj. 优质的
英文释义: the standard of something when it is compared to other things like it; how good or bad something is
例句: The quality of this spoon is terrible!
例句释义: 这勺子的质量真是太差了！

英文释义: the force or weight with which something presses against something else
例句: The pressure of the giant pear is unbearable!
例句释义: 这个大鸭梨的压力实在是难以承受！

详细释义: v.接纳，认可；接受（所提供或给予的物品）
英文释义: to take willingly something that is offered; to say ‘yes’ to an offer, invitation, etc.
例句: She accepted his marriage proposal.
例句释义: 她接受了他的求婚。

英文释义: something that you say, write or do to react to a question or situation
例句: When the teacher asked a question, the boy gave his answer.
例句释义: 老师提问时，男孩给出了答案。

英文释义: a supply of something that a country, an organization or a person has and can use, especially to increase their wealth; something that can be used to help achieve an aim, especially a book, equipment, etc. that provides information for teachers and students; personal qualities such as courage and imagination that help you deal with difficult situations
例句: The world's oil supply is a limited resource.
例句释义: 世界石油资源是有限的。

英文释义: to find or discover somebody/something
例句: Your fingerprints are unique, so they can help identify you to police.
例句释义: 你的指纹是独一无二的，所以它们可以帮助警察识别出你。

英文释义: on or to the left side
例句: There's half a bottle of milk left.
例句释义: 这儿还剩下半瓶牛奶。

英文释义: a situation in which two or more people meet together, because they have arranged it or by chance
例句: The business group is having a meeting.
例句释义: 那个商业团队正在开会。

英文释义: to discover the facts about something
例句: The chubby dog is determined to lose weight.
例句释义: 这只胖狗下定决心要减肥。

英文释义: to make something or somebody ready to be used or to do something
例句: They are preparing to launch the poor guy into the sky.
例句释义: 他们正准备把这个可怜的人发射到空中。

英文释义: an illness affecting humans, animals or plants, often caused by infection
例句: There is a disease spreading around the family.
例句释义: 有一种疾病在这家人之间传播。

详细释义: pron.无论什么；  det.无论什么样的
英文释义: any or every; anything or everything
例句: Whatever the weather, he sticks out swimming outdoors.
例句释义: 无论什么天气，他都坚持在户外游泳。

英文释义: the fact that you have achieved something that you want and have been trying to do or get; the fact of becoming rich or famous or of getting a high social position
例句: After reaching the top of Mount Qomolangma, they enjoyed their success.
例句释义: 到达珠穆朗玛峰峰顶后，他们享受着成功的感觉。

英文释义: to speak angrily to somebody because you disagree with them
例句: The boy is arguing with his mother.
例句释义: 男孩在和妈妈争吵。

详细释义: n.（一）杯（的容量）；  v.窝成杯形
英文释义: the contents of a cup
例句: I like having a cup of coffee before going to work.
例句释义: 我喜欢在上班之前喝一杯咖啡。

英文释义: more than usually
例句: All of us need to work harder―particularly our boss.
例句释义: 我们所有人都需要更加努力工作，尤其是我们的老板。

详细释义: n.数量，总额；  v.（to）总计，接近
英文释义: (used especially with uncountable nouns) a quantity of something
例句: The amount of sugar in this product is 28g.
例句释义: 这一产品中糖的总量是28克。

英文释义: the fact that somebody/something is able to do something; a level of skill or intelligence
例句: He has the ability to run on water.
例句释义: 他可以在水上跑。

详细释义: n.全体职员，员工；  adj.职员的
英文释义: all the workers employed in an organization considered as a group
例句: The doctors and nurses are important members of the hospital staff.
例句释义: 医生和护士都是重要的医院职员。

英文释义: to know who somebody is or what something is when you see or hear them or it, because you have seen or heard them or it before
例句: The little boy recognized his mother in the photo.
例句释义: 小男孩认出了照片里的妈妈。

英文释义: to make somebody notice somebody/something, especially by pointing or moving your head
例句: Can you guess what the graph indicates?
例句释义: 你能猜到这张图想说明什么吗？

英文释义: a person or an animal in a book, play or film/movie
例句: The two characters are created to be different in personality.
例句释义: 这两个角色的性格设定不同。

详细释义: n.生长，成长；发展，进步；增长
英文释义: (of people, animals or plants) the process of growing physically, mentally or emotionally; something that has grown
例句: The marks on the wall show the growth of the girl.
例句释义: 墙上的标记展现了女孩的成长。

英文释义: the state of no longer having something or as much of something; the process that leads to this
例句: The football fan of Argentina cried about the loss of the game.
例句释义: 这名阿根廷球迷因为比赛的失败而哭泣。

英文释义: the qualification obtained by students who successfully complete a university or college course; a unit for measuring temperature
例句: I finally got my degree after four years of studying!
例句释义: 经过四年的学习，我终于拿到了学位！

详细释义: v. 想知道；  n. 惊奇，惊异
英文释义: to think about something and try to decide what is true, what will happen, what you should do, etc.
例句: He was wondering what was in the box.
例句释义: 他想知道箱子里是什么。

详细释义: v.攻击，袭击；毁坏；  n.疾病发作
英文释义: to use violence to try to hurt or kill somebody; to use weapons, such as guns and bombs against an enemy in a war, etc.; to criticize somebody/something severely
例句: The soldiers attacked the enemy during the war.
例句释义: 在战争中，战士们对敌人发起了攻击。

英文释义: one of the areas that a country is divided into, that has its own customs and/or its own government; a large area of land, usually without exact limits or borders
例句: Milk is produced in these regions.
例句释义: 这些地区生产牛奶。

英文释义: a piece of electrical equipment with a screen on which you can watch programmes with moving pictures and sounds; the system, process or business of broadcasting television programmes
例句: We can watch the games on television.
例句释义: 我们可以通过电视看球赛。

详细释义: n. 盒子，箱子；  v. 拳击
英文释义: (especially in compounds) a container made of wood, cardboard, metal, etc. with a flat stiff base and sides and often a lid, used especially for holding solid things
例句: The box of books is really heavy.
例句释义: 这一箱书可真沉。

例句: We can watch TV at my house.
例句释义: 我们可以在我家看电视。

英文释义: the process of preparing to take part in a sports competition by doing physical exercises
例句: He performs strength training in the gym.
例句释义: 他在健身房做力量训练。

英文释义: (especially of a woman, or a girl) attractive without being very beautiful
例句: I'm the most loyal fan of these pretty boys.
例句释义: 我是这几个可爱男孩最忠实的乐迷。

详细释义: n.贸易，商业；  v.经商，交易
英文释义: the activity or process of buying, selling, or exchanging goods or services
例句: International trade has become a major source of income for this company.
例句释义: 国际贸易成了这家公司的一项主要收入来源。

英文释义: the process of choosing a person or a group of people for a position, especially a political position, by voting
例句: In an election, we decide who our leaders will be.
例句释义: 在选举中，我们决定谁来当我们的领导人。

详细释义: adj. 身体的，肉体的；  n. 体格检查
英文释义: connected with a person’s body rather than their mind
例句: Physical exercise is good for the body and the mind.
例句释义: 体育锻炼有益身心健康。

详细释义: v.放置，摆放；下蛋，产卵；铺，铺设
英文释义: to place (someone or something) down gently in a flat position
例句: The mother carefully laid the baby into the cot.
例句释义: 妈妈小心地把婴儿放到了婴儿床上。

详细释义: adj.普遍的，总的；一般的，普通的；大致的，笼统的；  n.将军
英文释义: affecting all or most people, places or things;  normal; usual; including the most important aspects of something; not exact or detailed; approximately, but not exactly, the direction/area mentioned; not limited to a particular subject, use or activity; not limited to one part or aspect of a person or thing; highest in rank; chief
例句: In general, the chart shows an increase.
例句释义: 总的来说，这张图呈现了一个上升趋势。

详细释义: n.(内心和感官的)感觉，感触，情绪；  v.感觉
英文释义: an emotional state or reaction
例句: We have different feelings, such as joy, worry, and anger.
例句释义: 我们有着不同的情绪，如高兴、担忧和愤怒。

英文释义: a level of quality, especially one that people think is acceptable;  a level of quality that is normal or acceptable for a particular person or in a particular situation
例句: Should this be the standard for the perfect figure?
例句释义: 这种身材应该是完美身材的标准吗？

英文释义: a document that says how much money you owe for something you have bought or used
例句: The waiter said, “Here is your bill, sir.”
例句释义: 服务员说：”这是您的账单，先生。“

详细释义: n.消息，信息，留言；  v.发消息
英文释义: a written or spoken piece of information, etc. that you send to somebody or leave for somebody when you cannot speak to them yourself
例句: She left a message on the table for her son.
例句释义: 她在桌子上给儿子留了一条消息。

英文释义: to not be successful in achieving something; to not pass a test or an exam; to decide that somebody/something has not passed a test or an exam
例句: The boy felt sad because he failed his exam.
例句释义: 这个小男孩很难过，因为他考试不及格。

详细释义: adv. 在户外，在外面，向外面；  n. 外部；  adj. 外部的；  prep. 在……外面，不在……范围内
英文释义: not in a room, building or container but on or to the outside of it; not inside a building
例句: I like my kids to play outside on the grass.
例句释义: 我喜欢孩子们到外面的草地上玩耍。

英文释义: to get to a place, especially at the end of a journey
例句: She arrived at the airport on time.
例句释义: 她准时抵达了机场。

英文释义: a careful examination of a substance in order to find out what it consists of
例句: Could you write up an analysis of how the market is moving this week?
例句释义: 你能写一篇关于这周市场走势的分析报告吗？

英文释义: to be useful to somebody or improve their life in some way
例句: Jogging has a lot of benefits for people's health.
例句释义: 慢跑对人体健康有诸多好处。

详细释义: n.性别；色情；  v.区分性别
英文释义: physical activity between two people in which they touch each other’s sexual organs, and which may include sexual intercourse
例句: The application form asks for your sex.
例句释义: 这张申请表需要填上您的性别。

详细释义: adv.向前，前进；  adj.向前的，前面的；  v.转寄，转投
英文释义: towards a place or position that is in front;  towards a good result; towards the future; ahead in time
例句: Forward, men! Let's reach our goal today!
例句释义: 向前吧，伙计们！我们今天就能达成目标了！

英文释义: a person who is trained and qualified to advise people about the law and to represent them in court, and to write legal documents
例句: The group of lawyers are standing in the courtroom.
例句释义: 律师团队站在法庭里。

详细释义: n.礼物；  adj.出席的；  v.颁发，授予
英文释义: something that you give to someone especially as a way of showing affection or thanks
例句: A present for me? Thank you! You're so sweet.
例句释义: 给我的礼物吗？谢谢，你真好！

英文释义: a separate part of a document, book, etc.
例句: The Earth can be divided into different sections.
例句释义: 地球可以被划分为不同的部分。

英文释义: connected with the natural conditions in which people, animals and plants live; connected with the environment
例句: Air pollution from factories has caused many bad environmental problems.
例句释义: 工厂产生的空气污染造成了很多严重的环境问题。

英文释义: (often in compounds) a container made of glass, used for drinking out of
例句: I like collecting glasses of all shapes and sizes.
例句释义: 我喜欢收集各种形状、大小的玻璃杯。

英文释义: a particular ability or type of ability
例句: Different jobs need different skills.
例句释义: 不同的职业需要不同的技能。

英文释义: a girl or woman who has the same mother and father as another person
例句: The girl is the little boy's sister.
例句释义: 这个女孩是小男孩的姐姐。

英文释义: a teacher especially of the highest rank at a college or university
例句: The man standing in front of the whiteboard is a professor.
例句释义: 站在白板前的男人是个教授。

英文释义: the process of cutting open a part of a person’s body in order to remove or repair a damaged part
例句: The doctors performed the operation carefully.
例句释义: 医生小心地做手术。

英文释义: connected with money and finance
例句: Online banking makes it easier to manage your financial accounts.
例句释义: 网上银行使得管理金融账目更加容易。

详细释义: n.罪行；犯罪行为，非法活动
英文释义: an illegal act or activity that can be punished by law
例句: They are committing a crime in the old couple's house.
例句释义: 他们在这对老夫妇的家里实施犯罪。

英文释义: a raised area, usually in a theatre, etc. where actors, dancers, etc. perform
例句: The children are playing music on the stage.
例句释义: 孩子们正在舞台上演奏音乐。

英文释义: to examine people or things to see how they are similar and how they are different
例句: It's smart to compare products when you go shopping.
例句释义: 当你购物时，比较一下商品是很明智的。

英文释义: the people or an organization who have the power to make decisions or who have a particular area of responsibility in a country or region; the power to give orders to people
例句: The authority declared that catmint would be banned completely in 3 months.
例句释义: 当局宣称猫薄荷将在三个月后被全面禁止。

详细释义: vt.未击中，未投中；错过；  n.年轻未婚女子
英文释义: to feel sad because you can no longer see somebody or do something that you like
例句: How can the little angel miss his target with so many arrows?
例句释义: 丘比特怎么能一支箭也射不中他？

详细释义: n. 设计；图样；  vt. 设计
英文释义: the general arrangement of the different parts of something that is made, such as a building, book, machine, etc.
例句: I am working on the design for the new website.
例句释义: 我正在为新网站做设计。

详细释义: v.把……分类，整理，挑选；  n.种类
英文释义: to arrange things in groups or in a particular order according to their type, etc.; to separate things of one type from others
例句: I sorted the books into piles of big ones and small ones.
例句释义: 我将书按大小分成了几摞。

详细释义: v.表演，扮演；  n.行为，行动
英文释义: perform an action, or work out or perform (an action)
例句: The girl will act the part of princess in the play.
例句释义: 这个女孩将在剧中扮演公主的角色。

英文释义: information, understanding, or skill that you get from experience or education
例句: People can gain knowledge through reading books.
例句释义: 人们可以通过读书获取知识。

英文释义: a weapon that shoots bullets or shells
例句: The man looks cool with a gun in his hand.
例句释义: 这个拿枪的男人看起来太酷了。

详细释义: n.车站；站，局；  v.安置，驻扎
英文释义: a place where trains stop so that passengers can get on and off; the buildings connected with this
例句: The train at the station is about to leave.
例句释义: 车站里停着的火车快要出发了。

详细释义: adj. 蓝色的；  n. 蓝色
英文释义: having the colour of a clear sky or the sea/ocean on a clear day
例句: There are a few white clouds in the blue sky.
例句释义: 蓝色的天空里飘荡着朵朵白云。

英文释义: a plan that is intended to achieve a particular purpose; the skill of planning the movements of armies in a battle or war; an example of doing this
例句: I like strategy games that require deep thinking, like chess.
例句释义: 我喜欢需要深思熟虑的策略性游戏，比如国际象棋。

英文释义: without doubt or question
例句: I can see everything so clearly with my new glasses.
例句释义: 有了新眼镜，我能清楚地看到一切。

英文释义: to talk about something with somebody, especially in order to decide something
例句: The students discussed the topic on the blackboard.
例句释义: 学生们讨论了黑板上的话题。

英文释义: used to emphasize a positive statement or answer; used to add information to a statement
例句: I indeed lost sleep last night.
例句释义: 我昨晚的确失眠了。

英文释义: the true facts about something, rather than the things that have been invented or guessed
例句: The truth is that the "Batman" is actually just the cat's shadow.
例句释义: 真相是这个“蝙蝠侠”只是这只猫的影子。

英文释义: a short piece of music with words that you sing
例句: We all sang a song together on New Year's Day.
例句释义: 在元旦我们一起唱了一首歌。

英文释义: a person or way of behaving that is seen as a model that should be followed
例句: The math example was completed by Mr. Li.
例句释义: 这道数学例题是李老师完成的。

详细释义: adj.民主的，民主政体的，民主党的
英文释义: (of a country, state, system, etc.) controlled by representatives who are elected by the people of a country; connected with this system; based on the principle that all members of society are equal rather than divided by money or social class; connected with the Democratic Party in the US
例句: In a democratic society, everyone has the right to vote.
例句释义: 在一个民主的国家，人民有权投票选举。

详细释义: v.检查；阻止；  n.支票；阻止；检查；阻碍物
英文释义: to look at (something) carefully to find mistakes, problems, etc., or to make sure there is nothing wrong with it
例句: Let me check if your blood pressure is OK.
例句释义: 让我查查你的血压是否正常。

详细释义: n.自然环境；生活或工作环境
英文释义: the conditions that affect the behaviour and development of somebody/something; the physical conditions that somebody/something exists in; the natural world in which people, animals and plants live
例句: They are picking up trash to help keep the environment clean.
例句释义: 为了保持环境整洁，他们正在捡垃圾。

英文释义: one of the long parts that connect the feet to the rest of the body
例句: The man puts his legs on the desk.
例句释义: 男人把腿放在桌子上。

详细释义: n. 黑暗，暗处；  adj. 黑暗的，昏暗的
英文释义: the lack of light in a place, especially because it is night
例句: The black cat is hiding in the dark.
例句释义: 这只黑猫隐藏在黑暗中。

英文释义: having many different features; several different
例句: We saw various types of fish during our dive.
例句释义: 潜水时，我们看到了各种各样的鱼。

详细释义: adv.相当；有点儿；更确切地讲
英文释义: used to mean ‘fairly’ or ‘to some degree’, often when you are expressing slight criticism, disappointment or surprise
例句: It's rather cold today.
例句释义: 今天相当冷。

英文释义: to make the sounds and movements of your face that show you are happy or think something is funny
例句: The photographer told them to laugh, so they laughed.
例句释义: 摄影师让他们笑，所以他们笑了。

详细释义: v. 猜测，推测；  n. 猜测，推测
英文释义: to try and give an answer or make a judgement about something without being sure of all the facts
例句: The daughter wants her mother to guess the fruit by smell.
例句释义: 女儿想让她妈妈凭气味猜水果。

详细释义: n. 经理；行政人员；  adj. 执行的
英文释义: a person who has an important job as a manager of a company or an organization
例句: The executives of both companies discussed the issue in depth.
例句释义: 双方公司的经理深入地讨论了这个问题。

英文释义: to use facts, evidence, etc. to show that something is true
例句: It takes one second to say "I do," but a lifetime to prove it.
例句释义: 说一句“我愿意”只用一秒，可证明它却需要一辈子。

英文释义: to kill somebody, usually as a punishment, by tying a rope around their neck and allowing them to drop; to attach something, or to be attached, at the top so that the lower part is free or loose
例句: A luxurious drop lamp is hanging on the ceiling.
例句释义: 一盏奢华的吊灯挂在天花板上。

英文释义: (used when you are emphasizing that the whole of something is involved) including everything, everyone or every part
例句: There's half a chocolate pie and an entire lemon cake on the shelf.
例句释义: 架子上有半个巧克力派和一整个柠檬蛋糕。

英文释义: the shore of a sea or ocean

例句释义: 海边有许多大块的岩石。

英文释义: to be unable to remember sth that has happened in the past or information that you knew in the past

例句释义: 他离开公寓时忘了把钥匙从门锁上拔下来！

详细释义: v.认领，要求（拥有）；声称；断言；主张；索赔；  n.索赔；主张；声明；断言
英文释义: to demand or ask for something because you believe it is your legal right to own or to have it
例句: She claimed her baggage before leaving the airport.
例句释义: 她在离开机场前认领了自己的行李。

英文释义: to get rid of something unpleasant, dirty, etc.; to make something disappear
例句: Use the other end of the hammer to remove nails.

英文释义: a person who is in charge of running a business, a shop/store or a similar organization or part of one
例句: The manager has three employees under her.
例句释义: 经理手下管理着三名员工。

英文释义: to get pleasure from something; to be happy and get pleasure from what you are doing; to have something good that is an advantage to you
例句: A birthday party should be an event everyone can enjoy.
例句释义: 生日派对应该是每个人都能享受的事情。

详细释义: n.网络；广播网，电视网；  v.建立关系网；使联网
英文释义: a number of computers and other devices that are connected together so that equipment and information can be shared

例句释义: 互联网其实就是连接数十亿台电脑的网络。

英文释义: allowed or required by law; connected with the law
例句: Now I have my driver's license; it's legal for me to drive on the road.
例句释义: 我考到驾照了，可以合法上路了。

英文释义: (of a person) believing strongly in a particular religion and obeying its laws and practices
例句: He is a religious believer; he goes to church every week.
例句释义: 他是个虔诚的教徒，每周都会去教堂。

详细释义: adj. 寒冷的；  n. 寒冷
英文释义: having a lower than usual temperature; having a temperature lower than the human body
例句: I prefer the cold, snowy mountains over warm places.

详细释义: adj.最后的；决定性的；  n.当日报纸的末版
英文释义: that cannot be argued with or changed
例句: The competition is in its final stage.
例句释义: 比赛进入了最后阶段。

详细释义: adj. 主要的，最重要的；  n. 干线，总管道

例句: The main part of this river leads to the sea.
例句释义: 这条河的主流通向大海。

例句: Physics and chemistry are two different areas of science.
例句释义: 物理和化学是科学的两个不同领域。

详细释义: adj. 绿色的，青的，草绿色的；缺乏经验的；  n. 绿色
英文释义: having the colour of grass or the leaves of most plants and trees; covered with grass or other plants

例句释义: 我对巴黎的记忆比照片美多了。

英文释义: a game or games in which playing cards are used; a small piece of stiff paper or plastic with information on it, especially information about somebody’s identity
例句: Here is my card. It has my phone number and email on it.
例句释义: 这是我的名片，上面有我的电话号码和邮箱地址。

详细释义: prep.在……之上；过于，超出；  adj.上面的，上述的；  adv.在……上面，上文中
英文释义: at or to a higher place or position than something/somebody
例句: The bird is flying above the water.
例句释义: 鸟儿在水面上飞行。

详细释义: n.座位；  v.能提供...人座位
英文释义: a place where you can sit, for example a chair
例句: There are many seats in this cinema.
例句释义: 这家电影院有很多座位。

英文释义: the smallest part of an animal or plant that is able to function independently
例句: White blood cells help protect the body against viruses.
例句释义: 白细胞可以保护身体，消灭病毒。

英文释义: to start having a relationship, especially a formal one, with another person, group or country
例句: The two businessmen are trying to establish links.
例句释义: 这两个商人试图建立联系。

英文释义: pleasant, enjoyable or attractive
例句: She has a nice smile.
例句释义: 她的笑容很美好。

详细释义: n.审判，审理；考验；  adj.试验的，试验性的
英文释义: the determination of a person's innocence or guilt by due process of law
例句: The trial has begun. What will be the outcome?

英文释义: a person with special knowledge, skill or training in something
例句: The expert is sharing his knowledge of traditional Chinese medicine on the TV show.
例句释义: 这个电视节目里的专家正在给观众讲授传统中医知识。

英文释义: the season between winter and summer when plants begin to grow
例句: In China, the flying swallows are a sign of spring.
例句释义: 在中国，飞燕是春天的标志。

详细释义: n.事务所；  adj.较硬的；（人）坚决的，强势的；牢固的，稳固的；（决定或意见）确定的；（证据或信息）确凿的
英文释义: a business or company
例句: The lawyers decided to create their own firm.
例句释义: 这些律师决定创立自己的事务所。

详细释义: n. 民主党人，民主主义者
英文释义: a person who believes in or supports democracy
例句: The donkey is the symbol of the democrats, while the elephant represents the republicans.
例句释义: 驴子是民主党人的象征，而大象代表共和党人。

英文释义: the system or process that is used for sending and receiving signals through the air without using wires
例句: The woman is listening to the radio with a cup of coffee in her hand.
例句释义: 这位女士手端着咖啡，正在听收音机。

详细释义: vt.拜访；  n.访问参观，游览；  v.看望，探望；参观，访问
英文释义: to make an official visit to somebody, for example to perform checks or give advice
例句: Our neighbors always visit us after work.
例句释义: 邻居下班之后经常来串门。

英文释义: the act of running and controlling a business or similar organization; the act or skill of dealing with people or situations in a successful way
例句: The company's success was a result of good management.
例句释义: 公司的成功源于良好的管理。

英文释义: to prevent something bad from happening; to keep away from somebody/something; to try not to do something
例句: The driver avoided hitting the dogs on the road.
例句释义: 司机避免了撞到路上的狗。

详细释义: v.想象，幻想；设想，猜想；认为
英文释义: to form a picture in your mind of what something might be like
例句: She is imagining herself wearing a pretty dress.
例句释义: 她在想象自己穿上漂亮裙子的样子。

英文释义: on or during the evening or night of today
例句: Tonight's news is about the accident that happened earlier today.
例句释义: 今晚的新闻是关于今天早些时候发生的一起事故。

英文释义: very large :very great in size, amount, or degree
例句: There is a huge yellow duck floating on the lake.
例句释义: 有一只大黄鸭漂在湖上。

英文释义: a round object used for throwing, hitting or kicking in games and sports
例句: Kick the ball into the net!
例句释义: 把球踢进网！

英文释义: to stop doing something or making something because it is complete; to come to an end; to bring something to an end
例句: She has finished her meal.
例句释义: 她吃完了这一餐。

英文释义: a formal set of ideas that is intended to explain why something happens or exists
例句: It can be inferred from his theory that the earth is expanding.
例句释义: 我们可以从他的理论推测出地球在膨胀。

详细释义: n.冲击力；碰撞，冲击；  v.影响；有影响
英文释义: the act of one object hitting another; the force with which this happens
例句: The impact of the hammer completely destroyed my computer.
例句释义: 这一锤的冲击彻底把我的电脑给毁了。

详细释义: v.回答，回复；做出反应，回应
英文释义: to do something as a reaction to something that somebody has said or done
例句: The little boy responds to the customers.
例句释义: 这个男孩儿接了客人的来电。

英文释义: a formal or official account of facts or opinions; something that you say or write that gives information or an opinion
例句: The company made a statement confirming that the couple will no longer work with them.
例句释义: 这家公司宣布这对情侣已被辞退。

英文释义: to support somebody/something over a long period of time by giving money, paying for food, etc.
例句: I wash my car daily to maintain its shine.
例句释义: 我每天都洗车来维持它的光洁如新。

详细释义: v. 充电，充值；索价；控告；  n. 主管；费用
英文释义: to give an amount of electricity to (something); to put electricity into a battery so that a machine or device will run
例句: I finally plug my phone and let it charge.
例句释义: 我终于插上手机，让它充上电了。

英文释义: liked or enjoyed by a large number of people

例句释义: 这个人非常受欢迎，很多人邀请了他。

英文释义: being part of the beliefs, customs or way of life of a particular group of people, that have not changed for a long time
例句: We like traditional Chinese clothing.
例句释义: 我们都喜欢中国传统服饰。

英文释义: used with verbs to express movement on or to a particular place or position
