例句释义: 他踏上了竹筏。

英文释义: to make something known to somebody
例句: He opened the curtain to reveal a landscape painting.
例句释义: 他掀开帘布，一幅风景画展现在我们眼前。

详细释义: n.方向，方位；（复数）指令，说明
英文释义: the general position a person or thing moves or points towards
例句: There are two different directions, left and right.
例句释义: 这里有左和右两个不同的方向。

英文释义: an object such as a knife, gun, bomb, etc. that is used for fighting or attacking somebody
例句: There are a number of different kinds of weapons on the floor.
例句释义: 地上有很多种不同的武器。

英文释义: a person who is paid to work for somebody
例句: These six employees make a great team.
例句释义: 这六名雇员组成了一个很好的团队。

英文释义: connected with the culture of a particular society or group, its customs, beliefs, etc.; connected with art, literature, music, etc.
例句: These cultural symbols are very important to Chinese people.
例句释义: 这些文化符号对中国人来说非常重要。

英文释义: to have or include (something)
例句: Sea water contains salt.
例句释义: 海水含有盐分。

英文释义: a quiet and calm state
例句: This kind of bird always stands for peace.
例句释义: 这种鸟一直代表着和平。

英文释义: the feelings that you have in your body when you have been hurt or when you are ill/sick
例句: He is suffering great pain in his neck and back.
例句释义: 他感觉脖颈和后背特别疼。

英文释义: to put or spread something such as paint, cream, etc. onto a surface; to ask formally for something (such as a job, admission to a school, a loan, etc.) usually in writing
例句: Don't forget to apply sunscreen if you spend time out in the sun.
例句释义: 如果你要长时间待在太阳下，一定别忘记涂防晒霜。

详细释义: vt.测量；估量；  n.措施，方法；尺寸；计量标准
英文释义: to find the size, quantity, etc. of something in standard units
例句: He measures himself―he is 2 meters tall!
例句释义: 他测量了自己的身高――他有2米高！

详细释义: adj. 宽阔的；广泛的；  adv. 完全地
英文释义: extending throughout a specified area
例句: The sofa was wide enough for many people.
例句释义: 这张沙发很宽，足够坐很多人。

英文释义: to move or have parts of your body move in short, quick movements and in a way that you are not able to control
例句: Shake the bottle well before drinking.
例句释义: 饮用前请摇晃瓶子。

英文释义: to move through the air with wings
例句: I'd like to fly up towards the sun, like an eagle.
例句释义: 我想像老鹰一样高高飞向太阳。

英文释义: a formal meeting at which somebody is asked questions to see if they are suitable for a particular job, or for a course of study at a college, university, etc.; a meeting (often a public one) at which a journalist asks somebody questions in order to find out their opinions
例句: During the job interview, the man seemed nervous.
例句释义: 在求职面试过程中，这位应聘者似乎很紧张。

英文释义: to control or be in charge of a business, a team, an organization, etc.
例句: He managed his time well to complete all of his tasks.
例句释义: 他将自己的时间管理得很好，完成了所有的任务。

英文释义: a piece of furniture for one person to sit on, with a back, a seat and four legs
例句: Sitting in the dentist chair always fills me with fear.
例句释义: 当坐在牙医的椅子上时，我总是不由自主地害怕。

详细释义: n.鱼（单复数同形）；  v.钓鱼
英文释义: a creature that lives in water, breathes through gills, and uses fins and a tail for swimming
例句: Fish have very simple lives.
例句释义: 鱼过着很简单的生活。

详细释义: adj.特别的，不寻常的；格外的；  n.细节
英文释义: used to emphasize that you are referring to one individual person, thing or type of thing and not others
例句: You should pay particular attention to spelling.
例句释义: 你需要特别注意你的拼写。

英文释义: a device that is used for taking photographs or for making movies, television programs, etc.
例句: She is able to take high quality photos with that camera.
例句释义: 她能用那台照相机拍出高质量的照片。

英文释义: something (such as a house, tower, bridge, etc.) that is built by putting parts together and that usually stands on its own
例句: There are so many new structures going up.
例句释义: 许多新的建筑正拔地而起。

英文释义: the activities involved in getting and using power in public life, and being able to influence decisions that affect a country or a society
例句: He is so keen on politics that he participates in many public events.
例句释义: 他是如此热衷于政治，因此他参加了很多公众活动。

英文释义: to entertain an audience by playing a piece of music, acting in a play, etc.
例句: A band is performing on the stage.
例句释义: 一支乐队正在舞台上表演。

英文释义: a small amount or piece of something
例句: He broke the loaf into bits to feed the ducks.
例句释义: 他把面包掰成小块喂鸭子。

英文释义: how heavy somebody/something is, which can be measured in, for example, kilograms or pounds; the fact of being heavy
例句: The weight of the apples you chose is 2 kilos.
例句释义: 你所选的苹果的重量是2千克。

英文释义: quickly and unexpectedly
例句: Suddenly, my friend surprised me from behind.
例句释义: 我的朋友突然从后面给我来了个惊喜。

英文释义: to be the first person to become aware that a particular place or thing exists; to find somebody/something that was hidden or that you did not expect to find
例句: The expert discovered a vase from the Tang dynasty.
例句释义: 这名专家发现了一个唐朝的花瓶。

英文释义: a person who is trying to be elected or is applying for a job
例句: The candidates are presenting the speeches for the election.
例句释义: 候选人正在为选举发表演说。

英文释义: the process of growing or making food, goods or materials, especially large quantities
例句: Thousands of cars are under production in this factory.
例句释义: 数以千计的汽车在这家工厂进行生产。

英文释义: to give medical care or attention to a person, an illness, an injury, etc.
例句: The doctor is carefully treating the wound on the little girl's leg.
例句释义: 医生正在仔细治疗小女孩腿上的伤。

详细释义: n.旅行，远足；  v.绊倒，失足
英文释义: a journey to a place and back again, especially a short one for pleasure or a particular purpose; the experience that somebody has if they take a powerful drug that affects the mind and makes them imagine things
例句: He is going to make a trip by plane.
例句释义: 他打算坐飞机去旅行。

英文释义: to produce a change in somebody/something; (of a disease) to attack somebody or a part of the body; to make somebody become ill/sick; to make somebody have strong feelings of sadness, pity, etc.
例句: Secondhand smoking may affect people's health.
例句释义: 吸二手烟会影响人的健康。

详细释义: prep.在……之内；  adj.里面的；  adv.在里面，在内部；  n.里面，内部
英文释义: on or to the inner part of something/somebody; within something/somebody
例句: Guess what? I've got a rabbit inside the box!
例句释义: 你知道吗？我的盒子里面有一只小兔子！

英文释义: a large official meeting, usually lasting for a few days, at which people with the same work or interests come together to discuss their views; a meeting at which people have formal discussions
例句: He is delivering his speech at the pet owners' conference.
例句释义: 他正在宠物主人会议上发表演讲。

详细释义: n.整体；部门，单位；课本单元
英文释义: a single thing, person or group that is complete by itself but can also form part of something larger
例句: We will succeed if we work as a unit.
例句释义: 如果我们万众一心，就能成功。

英文释义: a particular design of something, especially clothes; the quality of being fashionable in the clothes that you wear
例句: She has a very distinctive style; she doesn't dress like anybody else.
例句释义: 她的风格非常独特，她穿着打扮不像其他任何人。

英文释义: a fully grown person who is legally responsible for their actions
例句: An adult is a person who is 18 years old or over.
例句释义: 成年人的年龄大于或等于18岁。

详细释义: v.（使）焦虑，（使）烦恼；  n.烦恼，焦虑，担忧
英文释义: to think about problems or fears :to feel or show fear and concern because you think that something bad has happened or could happen
例句: Being in the hospital makes him worry about money.
例句释义: 在医院住院，他很担忧他的钱。

详细释义: n.射程；一系列；放牧场；  v.排成一排；排列；  adj.牧场的
英文释义: a variety of things of a particular type
例句: The target is within range. I bet I can hit it!
例句释义: 目标在射程内。我肯定能射中它！

英文释义: to write or speak about something/somebody, especially without giving much information
例句: She mentioned her child during their conversation.
例句释义: 她在谈话中提到了她的孩子。

英文释义: having a large distance from the top or surface to the bottom
例句: No one has found the ship's treasure because it lies deep under the sea.
例句释义: 没有人能找到船里的宝藏，因为它在大海中很深的地方。

详细释义: n.（悬崖、峭壁的）边缘；  v.徐徐移动；给……开刃，使锐利
英文释义: the outside limit of an object, a surface or an area; the part furthest from the centre
例句: The chicken is so afraid when standing on the edge.
例句释义: 站在悬崖边的小鸡感到非常害怕。

英文释义: detailed and exact
例句: I want that specific peach―the one right there!
例句释义: 我要那个桃子，就是那个！

英文释义: a person whose job is writing books, stories, articles, etc.
例句: Who do you prefer out of these famous foreign writers?
例句释义: 在这些著名的西方作家中，你最喜欢谁？

英文释义: something that is wrong with a machine, vehicle, etc.
例句: My car has broken down; I'm in big trouble now!
例句释义: 我的车坏了，我现在麻烦大啦！

英文释义: that is needed for a purpose or a reason
例句: Food and water are necessary for life.
例句释义: 食物和水是生命所需。

英文释义: during the whole period of time of something
例句: It snowed throughout the day and night.
例句释义: 雪下了整整一天一夜。

英文释义: a new or difficult task that tests somebody’s ability and skill
例句: Walking on the tight rope is a big challenge for him.
例句释义: 走绳索对他来说是个很大的挑战。

英文释义: to be frightened of somebody/something or frightened of doing something
例句: The girl feared the dog because it might bite her.
例句释义: 这个女孩害怕这只狗，因为它可能会咬她。

英文释义: either of the two parts of the body between the top of each arm and the neck
例句: The old man has pain in his shoulder.
例句释义: 这位老年人肩膀疼。

英文释义: an organization founded and united for a specific purpose
例句: The United Nations is an international institution.
例句释义: 联合国是一家国际机构。

详细释义: n.中部，中间；  adj.中部的，中间的
英文释义: in a position in the middle of an object, group of objects, people, etc.; between the beginning and the end of something
例句: This is my mom and my daughter, and that's me, in the middle.
例句释义: 这是我妈妈和我女儿，在中间的就是我。

英文释义: the salt water that covers much of the Earth's surface
例句: The sea looks so calm today.
例句释义: 今天，这片海看起来很平静。

英文释义: to experience a series of images, events and feelings in your mind while you are asleep; to imagine and think about something that you would like to happen
例句: In my dream, I was on a beach in Hawaii.
例句释义: 我在梦里去了夏威夷海滩。

英文释义: a long wide wooden surface where drinks, etc. are served
例句: There's no one drinking in the bar; it's too early.
例句释义: 酒吧里现在没人在喝酒，因为太早了。

英文释义: having beauty; pleasing to the senses or to the mind
例句: She looks beautiful in her new black shirt.
例句释义: 她穿着新买的黑色衬衫，真好看。

英文释义: land and buildings; a building or buildings and the surrounding land
例句: As a wealthy man, I have a large number of properties.
例句释义: 作为一个富人，我有大量财产。

英文释义: in the place of somebody/something
例句: Have some healthy food instead of hamburgers.
例句释义: 吃点健康食品，别再吃汉堡包了。

英文释义: to become better than before; to make something/somebody better than before
例句: The grades show that her English has improved a lot.
例句释义: 这些分数说明她的英语提高了很多。

详细释义: n.东西；材料；原料；  vt.把……塞进；装满
英文释义: used to refer to a substance, material, group of objects, etc. when you do not know the name, when the name is not important or when it is obvious what you are talking about
例句: We keep all of the baby's stuff in his bedroom.
例句释义: 我们把孩子所有的东西都放在他的卧室里。

英文释义: a small individual fact or item; a less important fact or item; the small facts or features of something, when you consider them all together
例句: When the leaf is seen up close, you can see a lot of fine details.
例句释义: 近距离看树叶时，你可以看到很多细节。

英文释义: a particular way of doing something
例句: This is the correct method for washing your hands.
例句释义: 这是正确的洗手方法。

英文释义: a person who is not known or mentioned by name
例句: Somebody sends me the flowers, but I don't know who he is.
例句释义: 某人给我送了花，可是我不知道他是谁。

英文释义: a type of large thin book with a paper cover that you can buy every week or month, containing articles, photographs, etc., often on a particular topic; a radio or television programme that is about a particular topic
例句: I like to read magazines about fashion and celebrities.
例句释义: 我喜欢阅读关于时尚和名人的杂志。

英文释义: a building where people stay, usually for a short time, paying for their rooms and meals
例句: This is a five-star hotel.
例句释义: 这是一家五星级酒店。

英文释义: a member of an army, especially one who is not an officer
例句: With the helmet and rifle, the dog looks like a real soldier!
例句释义: 戴着头盔、背着步枪，这只狗看起来像一个真正的士兵！

英文释义: to show the image of somebody/something on the surface of something such as a mirror, water or glass
例句: The mountains are reflected in the water.
例句释义: 群山倒映在水中。

详细释义: adj. 重的；重型的；  adv. 笨重地
英文释义: having great weight :difficult to lift or move
例句: Don't drop those containers-they're heavy!
例句释义: 当心别让这些集装箱掉下来，它们很重！

英文释义: connected with the state of being male or female
例句: A happy family is based on sexual equality.
例句释义: 一个幸福的家庭建立在性别平等的基础上。

英文释义: (often in compounds) a container made of paper or plastic, that opens at the top, used especially in shops/stores; a strong container made from cloth, plastic, leather, etc., usually with one or two handles, used to carry things in when shopping or travelling
例句: This white bag is so big! You can put so much in it.
例句释义: 这个白色的包真大！你可以放很多东西进去。

详细释义: n.高温；【物理学】热；  v.加热
英文释义: hot weather; the hot conditions in a building/vehicle, etc.
例句: Charcoal gives off heat when it burns.
例句释义: 木炭在燃烧时释放出热量。

英文释义: the ceremony in which two people become husband and wife; the state of being married
例句: After they exchanged rings, the couple entered into marriage.
例句释义: 交换戒指之后，这对新人迈入了婚姻生活。

英文释义: physically strong and likely to be violent
例句: Stay away from that man―he looks tough.
例句释义: 离那个男的远一点，他看起来很健壮。

例句: I didn't know that cats could sing.
例句释义: 我不知道猫儿还能唱歌。

详细释义: n.表面；外表，外观；  v.浮出水面
英文释义: the top layer of an area of water or land
例句: There is some oil on the surface of the soup.
例句释义: 汤的表面有一些油花。

例句: They are all running for the same purpose―to win the race!
例句释义: 他们都为了同样的目的在奔跑――赢得比赛！

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to be real; to be present in a place or situation
例句: Do aliens exist on other planets?
例句释义: 其他星球上会有外星人存在吗？

详细释义: n.图案；模型，模式；典范；版式；样品；  vt.形成图案；促成（某种行为模式）
英文释义: a design, set of instructions or shape to cut around that you use in order to make something
例句: The pattern consists of many different colored triangles.
例句释义: 这个图案由许多不同颜色的三角形组成。

英文释义: used instead of ‘who’ as the object of a verb or preposition
例句: Do you know whom the reporters are discussing?
例句释义: 你知道记者们在讨论谁吗？

详细释义: n. 皮肤；  v. 去皮
英文释义: (often in compounds) the skin of a dead animal with or without its fur, used for making leather, etc.
例句: Those people have different skin colors.
例句释义: 这些人有着不同的肤色。

英文释义: a person whose job is to act for, or manage the affairs of, other people in business, politics, etc.; a person whose job is to arrange work for an actor, musician, sports player, etc. or to find somebody who will publish a writer’s work
例句: There are some real estate agents waiting for customers at the subway entrance.
例句释义: 一些房产中介在地铁口等待顾客。

英文释义: a person who owns something
例句: She is the owner of the milk tea shop.
例句释义: 她拥有这家奶茶店。

详细释义: n.机器，机械；  vt.用机器加工
英文释义: a piece of equipment with moving parts that does work when it is given power from electricity, gasoline, etc.
例句: You can use this machine to make coffee.
例句释义: 你可以用这台机器冲咖啡。

英文释义: any substance like air that is neither a solid nor a liquid, for example hydrogen and oxygen are both gases
例句: The chemical plant releases poisonous gas into the air.
例句释义: 化工厂释放有毒的气体到空气中。

详细释义: adv.领先地；提前地；  adj.在前的，向前的
英文释义: further forward in space or time; in front
例句: I am running ahead of the rest of the group.
例句释义: 跑步的时候，我领先于小组的其他人。

英文释义: all the people who were born at about the same time;  the average time in which children grow up, become adults and have children of their own, (usually considered to be about 30 years)
例句: My family includes three generations of people.
例句释义: 我们家三代同堂。

详细释义: adj.贸易的，商业的；  n.商业广告
英文释义: connected with the buying and selling of goods and services
例句: This city has been a major center of commercial activity for a long time.
例句释义: 长期以来，这个城市都是一个主要的商业活动中心。

详细释义: n.地址；致辞；  v.写姓名地址
英文释义: details of where somebody lives or works and where letters, etc. can be sent
例句: You must write down the address before sending a letter.
例句释义: 寄信之前必须写上地址。

详细释义: n.癌症；（迅速蔓延的）恶劣的或危险的事物
英文释义: a serious disease caused by cells that are not normal and that can spread to one or many parts of the body
例句: Smoking may cause lung cancer.
例句释义: 吸烟可能会导致肺癌。

英文释义: one thing on a list of things to buy, do, talk about, etc.
例句: He sells some of his unwanted items in the yard sale.
例句释义: 他在庭院大甩卖中卖一些不需要的物品。

英文释义: the true situation and the problems that actually exist in life, in contrast to how you would like life to be
例句: The photo without filter makes me realize the reality.
例句释义: 没有滤镜的照片使我认清了现实。

详细释义: n.教练；四轮大马车；  vt.训练，指导
英文释义: a person who trains a person or team in sport
例句: The volleyball coach is talking to her team.
例句释义: 这位排球教练正在和她的队员们交谈。

英文释义: an area outside a building, usually with a hard surface and a surrounding wall
例句: My yard is full of flowers and plants.
例句释义: 我的院子里种满了花花草草。

详细释义: v.敲打；打败；（心脏）跳动；搅拌；  n.敲打；节拍
英文释义: to hit (something) repeatedly
例句: He is beating the drum hard with two sticks.
例句释义: 他正用两根鼓槌用力击鼓。

英文释义: violent behaviour that is intended to hurt or kill somebody
例句: The two boys used violence to end the quarrel.
例句释义: 这两个男孩动用武力结束了争吵。

详细释义: adj.整个的，总体的；  n.总数
英文释义: being the amount or number after everyone or everything is counted or added together
例句: What's the total number of ducks in the pond?
例句释义: 池塘里一共有多少只鸭子呢？

英文释义: to be likely to do something or to happen in a particular way because this is what often or usually happens; to care for somebody/something
例句: They tend the tree with care.
例句释义: 他们小心地照料这棵树。

英文释义: the act of giving time or effort to a particular task in order to make it successful
例句: Buying property is a common type of investment nowadays.
例句释义: 购买房产是当今一种常见的投资方式。

英文释义: the process of discussing somebody/something; a conversation about somebody/something
例句: The teacher and kids are in a discussion about the Earth.
例句释义: 老师和孩子们在进行一场关于地球的讨论。

英文释义: one of the four that are not the thumb
例句: These finger puppets are so funny!
例句释义: 这些手指人偶真是太有趣了！

英文释义: a piece of land next to or around your house where you can grow flowers, fruit, vegetables, etc., usually with a lawn
例句: There are many flowers in the garden.
例句释义: 花园里有许多花。

英文释义: information that tells you or warns you about something that is going to happen
例句: The girl puts the notice on the board.
例句释义: 女孩把告示张贴在公告栏上。

英文释义: a group of objects, often of the same sort, that have been collected; a group of objects or people
例句: He has a fine collection of stamps.
例句释义: 他收集了一些精美的邮票。

英文释义: of the present time or recent times
例句: Smart phones are common tools of modern life.
例句释义: 在现代生活中，智能手机是常用工具。

英文释义: a piece of work that has been given to someone; a job for someone to do
例句: I'm so happy―there isn't a single task on my to-do list!
例句释义: 我很高兴，我的任务列表上已经没有任务了！

详细释义: n.伙伴，搭档；配偶，伴侣；  v.成为……的合伙人
英文释义: a person that you are doing an activity with, such as dancing or playing a game
例句: We are all partners here. Let's work together to finish the job.
例句释义: 我们是好搭档，让我们齐心协力完成工作吧。

英文释义: thinking about what is good in a situation: feeling confident and sure that something good will happen; completely sure that something is correct or true; directed at dealing with something or producing a successful result; showing clear evidence that a particular substance or medical condition is present
例句: You'd better be positive rather than negative about things.
例句释义: 你最好积极地看待事物，不要消极。

英文释义: connected with the people who live in a country
例句: A civil aircraft is for taking passengers.
例句释义: 民用飞机用于载客。

英文释义: a room in which meals are cooked or prepared
例句: The kitchen is clean and modern.
例句释义: 这个厨房整洁而现代。

英文释义: a person who buys goods or uses services
例句: The consumers buy many goods from the supermarket.
例句释义: 消费者从超市里购买许多商品。

详细释义: n.击球；影片，镜头；  v.射击；  adj.杂色的
英文释义: the action of hitting, kicking or throwing the ball in order to score a point or goal in a game
例句: "Nice shot!" I said as he hit the ball.
例句释义: “好球！”我在他击球时说道。

详细释义: n.预算；  v.预算，安排；  adj.廉价的
英文释义: the money that is available to a person or an organization and a plan of how it will be spent over a period of time
例句: I don’t have much money for the budget.
例句释义: 我的钱不够预算。

详细释义: v. 渴望；  n. 希望得到的东西；  v. 希望，想要
英文释义: (not usually used in the present progressive tense) to want something to happen or to be true even though it is unlikely or impossible
例句: The couple wish that they would have their own house and car.
例句释义: 这对夫妇希望拥有自己的房子和车子。

英文释义: a picture that has been painted; the act or art of using paint to produce pictures
例句: There is a famous painting on the wall.
例句释义: 墙上有一幅名画。

英文释义: a person who is trained in a science and whose job involves doing scientific research or solving scientific problems
例句: They are distinguished scientists in the fields of biology and physics.
例句释义: 他们是生物和物理领域杰出的科学家。

详细释义: n.保险箱；冷藏箱；  adj.有把握的；可靠的，稳妥的
英文释义: a strong metal box or cupboard with a complicated lock, used for storing valuable things in, for example, money or jewelery
例句: By using the safe, your money will be safer.
例句释义: 有了保险箱，你的钱会更安全。

英文释义: an arrangement, a promise or a contract made with somebody
例句: The two businessmen signed a long-term agreement to cooperate.
例句释义: 这两名商人签署了长期合作协议。

详细释义: n.首都；大写（字母）；  adj.大写的
英文释义: the most important town or city of a country, usually where the central government operates from
例句: Big Ben is a famous landmark in the capital city of the UK.
例句释义: 大本钟是英国首都的著名地标性建筑。

英文释义: the opening in the face used for speaking, eating, etc.; the area inside the head behind this opening
例句: The kid has such a big mouth!
例句释义: 这个小孩的嘴巴真大！

英文释义: and not; used as a function word to introduce and negate a following clause or phrase
例句: Neither smoking nor drinking is allowed here.
例句释义: 在这儿既不能抽烟也不能喝酒。

英文释义: a person who has been attacked, injured or killed as the result of a crime, a disease, an accident, etc.
例句: The family are victims of the flood, and are now homeless.
例句释义: 这一家人是这次洪灾的受害者，现在他们无家可归了。

英文释义: a set of large sheets of paper that have news stories, information about local events, advertisements, etc., and that are folded together and sold every day or every week
例句: This clever little dog can read a newspaper!
例句释义: 这只聪明的小狗竟然在看报纸！

英文释义: the possibility that something bad or harmful could happen
例句: The big guy is making a threat to the man in blue.
例句释义: 这个大块头正在威胁那个穿蓝衣服的人。

英文释义: a duty to deal with or take care of somebody/something, so that you may be blamed if something goes wrong; blame for something bad that has happened
例句: We have a responsibility to take care of our parents.
例句释义: 我们有责任照顾父母。

详细释义: n. 微笑；  v. 微笑
英文释义: an expression on your face that makes the corners of your mouth turn up and that shows happiness, amusement, pleasure, affection, etc.
例句: The beautiful girl is smiling in the sunshine.
例句释义: 美丽的女孩在阳光下微笑。

英文释义: a lawyer, especially one who can act for somebody in court; a person who is given the power to act on behalf of another in business or legal matters
例句: The attorney is defending his client in the courtroom.
例句释义: 律师在法庭上为他的当事人辩护。

详细释义: n.得分；刻痕；二十；  vt.在……上刻痕
英文释义: to win points, goals, etc. in a game or competition
例句: Our team won by a score of two to one.
例句释义: 我们队以二比一的比分赢了这场比赛。

详细释义: n.账户；  v.做出说明（或解释）；认为是
英文释义: n arrangement that somebody has with a bank, etc. to keep money there, take some out, etc.
例句: I have no money in my bank account.
例句释义: 我的银行账户里没钱啦。

英文释义: attracting your attention because it is special, exciting or unusual
例句: Watching cartoons is more interesting for the little boy than doing his homework.
例句释义: 对这个小男孩来说，看动画片比做作业更有趣。

英文释义: the group of people who have gathered to watch or listen to something (a play, concert, somebody speaking, etc.)
例句: The audience in the conference hall stayed quiet during his speech.
例句释义: 他讲话时，会议厅里的听众都很安静。

英文释义: having a lot of money or property
例句: The rich old couple decided to sail around the world after they retired.
例句释义: 这一对富裕的老年夫妻决定在退休后去环游世界。

详细释义: n. 正餐，（现通例指）晚餐
英文释义: the main meal of the day, eaten either in the middle of the day or in the evening
例句: The family enjoyed a big dinner.
例句释义: 全家人享受了丰盛的晚餐。

英文释义: to show formally by marking a paper or raising your hand which person you want to win an election, or which plan or idea you support; to choose somebody/something for a position or an award by voting; to say that something is good or bad; to agree to give somebody/yourself something by voting
例句: Voting is a fair way for selection.
例句释义: 投票是一种公平的选举方式。

详细释义: adj.有西方特征的；  n.西部影片
英文释义: located in the west or facing west; connected with the west part of the world, especially Europe and N America
例句: I decided to wear a Western style wedding dress.
例句释义: 我决定穿西式婚礼裙。

英文释义: show or make a connection between two or more things
例句: The family tree shows everyone I’m related to.
例句释义: 这个家谱显示了和我有关联的所有人。

详细释义: v.旅行；走过，驶过；  n.旅行，旅游
英文释义: to go on a trip or journey :to go to a place and especially one that is far away
例句: Where should I travel next?
例句释义: 我接下来应该去哪儿旅行呢？

详细释义: n.辩论；讨论，争论；  v.辩论；议论
英文释义: In a debate two or more speakers express opposing views and then there is often a vote on the issue; a formal discussion of an issue at a public meeting or in a parliament
例句: The debate between the man and the woman is so fierce.
例句释义: 这个男人和这个女人之间的辩论太激烈了。

英文释义: to stop somebody from doing something; to stop something from happening
例句: The mother prevented her child from eating sweets.
例句释义: 妈妈不让她的小孩吃糖。

英文释义: a person who has the legal right to belong to a particular country
例句: All of these people are citizens of the city.
例句释义: 所有这些人都是这座城市的市民。

英文释义: (law) the age at which you are legally considered to be an adult
例句: The majority thinks it's a good plan, but I don't think so.
例句释义: 大多数人认为这是个好主意，但我不觉得。

详细释义: pron. 没有（一人或一物）；  adv. 毫不
英文释义: not one of a group of people or things; not any
例句: I wish I could offer you some cake but there's none left.
例句释义: 我很想请你吃蛋糕，但是没有了。

详细释义: adj.前面的，正面的；  n.前面，正面
英文释义: the part or side of something that faces forward; the side of something that you look at first
例句: The front seats in the classroom are usually for the most hardworking students.
例句释义: 教室的前排座位通常坐着最勤奋的学生。

详细释义: v. 出世；  adj. 天生的
英文释义: brought into life by the process of birth
例句: The couple were so happy when the baby was born.
例句释义: 孩子出生时，夫妻俩非常高兴。

英文释义: to say that you have done something wrong or illegal
例句: His mother made him admit that he broke the vase.
例句释义: 他妈妈让小男孩承认是他把花瓶打碎了。

详细释义: adj. 年长的；资格老的，地位较高的；  n. （大学或高中）毕业生
英文释义: for senior citizens (= older people, especially those who have retired from work)
例句: The senior citizens in the community often have fun talking to each other.
例句释义: 社区里的老年人们经常在一起愉快地聊天。

英文释义: to take or begin to have power or responsibility
例句: I don't know who you are, but I can assume you're my wife.
例句释义: 我不知道你是谁，但我猜你是我的妻子。

英文释义: a natural movement of air outside; breath as needed in physical exertion or in speech
例句: The wind is blowing the tree's leaves.
例句释义: 风正吹着树叶。

详细释义: n. 钥匙；  adj. 关键的
英文释义: a specially shaped piece of metal used for locking a door, starting a car, etc.
例句: The man in the white T-shirt is holding his keys.
例句释义: 穿白色T恤的男人拿着他的钥匙。

英文释义: connected with a job that needs special training or skill, especially one that needs a high level of education; (of people) having a job which needs special training and a high level of education
例句: My parents want me to have a professional career―but which profession should I choose?
例句释义: 父母希望我步入职业生涯，但是我应该选什么职业呢？

详细释义: n.重要任务，使命；  vi.派遣……执行任务
英文释义: a group of people doing such a job; the place where they work
例句: The soldiers advance to complete the mission.
例句释义: 士兵们前进完成任务。

详细释义: adj. 迅速的，动作敏捷的；  adv. 迅速地
英文释义: moving or able to move quickly
例句: The car was driving so fast; I could hardly see it!
例句释义: 那辆车开得太快了！我几乎看不见它了。

英文释义: without help from anyone or anything else; and nothing or no one else
例句: Seesaws are not very fun when you're alone.
例句释义: 当你孤身一人时，跷跷板就不那么有趣了。

英文释义: a person or an organization that buys something from a shop/store or business
例句: Would the customer buy this pair of blue jeans?
例句释义: 这个顾客会买这条蓝色的牛仔裤吗？

英文释义: to be badly affected by a disease, pain, sadness, a lack of something, etc.; to experience something unpleasant, such as injury, defeat or loss;  to become worse
例句: She would suffer from intense pain every month.
例句释义: 她每个月都要忍受剧痛。

英文释义: a spoken expression of ideas, opinions, etc., that is made by someone who is speaking in front of a group of people
例句: The public speaker looks confident during his speech.
例句释义: 这位发言人在演讲时看上去胸有成竹。

例句: He was a successful businessman and brought great changes to our phones.
例句释义: 他是一位成功的商人，大大改变了我们的手机。

英文释义: something that you can choose to have or do; the freedom to choose what you do
例句: You have two options for lunch, pasta or pizza.
例句释义: 午饭你有两种选择：要么吃意面，要么吃比萨。

英文释义: a person who is taking part in an activity or event
例句: Every participant focused on the lecture.
例句释义: 每个参与者都聚精会神地听了演讲。

英文释义: located in or toward the south
例句: He lives in the southern part of the city.
例句释义: 他住在城市的南边。

详细释义: adj.新鲜的；清新的；新来的，无经验的
英文释义: newly produced, made, gathered, etc. :not preserved by being frozen, canned, etc.
例句: We enjoy fresh fruit from the tree and fresh fish from the river.
例句释义: 我们喜欢树上新鲜的水果和河里新鲜的鱼。

英文释义: at some later time; in the end
例句: After weeks of hard study, he eventually got a satisfying result.
例句释义: 经过几周的刻苦学习，他终于得到了令人满意的结果。

英文释义: a large area of land that is thickly covered with trees
例句: The forest looked beautiful when the sun shone through the trees.
例句释义: 当阳光穿过树木时，整个森林看起来美极了。

详细释义: n. 视频，录像；  v. 制作……的录像；  n. 录像带
英文释义: a short film or recording of an event, made using digital technology and viewed on a computer, especially over the Internet; a short film made by a pop or rock band to be shown with a song when it is played on television or online
例句: His job was to record the show on video.
例句释义: 他的工作是制作演出的录像。

英文释义: covering or affecting the whole world
例句: With the Internet, we can have a global network of friends.
例句释义: 有了互联网，我们便可以和全世界的朋友联系了。

英文释义: ne of the two groups of elected politicians who make laws in some countries, for example in the US, Australia, Canada and France. The Senate is smaller than the other group but higher in rank. Many state parliaments in the US also have a Senate.
例句: Several politicians are talking in front of the United States Senate.
例句释义: 几个政治家在美国参议院前面交谈。

详细释义: v.改革，革新；改良，改进；  n.改革，革新；改良，改进
英文释义: to improve a system, an organization, a law, etc. by making changes to it
例句: The company decided to reform its management structure.
例句释义: 公司决定要改革管理结构。

详细释义: n.进入；通道；  v.（计算机）访问
英文释义: a way of entering or reaching a place
例句: The ramp gives access to disabled people.
例句释义: 这个斜坡使残障人士可以自由进入。

英文释义: a place where you can buy and eat a meal
例句: It is expensive to eat at this fancy restaurant.
例句释义: 在这家高档餐厅吃饭很贵。

详细释义: n.法官；裁判员；  v.判决，审判
英文释义: a person in a court who has the authority to decide how criminals should be punished or to make legal decisions
例句: The judge will decide whether you are guilty or not.
例句释义: 法官会决定你到底有没有罪。

英文释义: to produce a book, magazine, CD-ROM, etc. and sell it to the public; to print a letter, an article, etc. in a newspaper or magazine
例句: She hopes that her book will be published so everyone can buy it.
例句释义: 她希望自己的书能够出版，这样每个人都可以购买。

英文释义: the way in which two people, groups or countries behave towards each other or deal with each other; the way in which two or more things are connected
例句: They have built a business relation; they're partners from now on.
例句释义: 他们建立了商业关系；从现在开始，他们就是合作伙伴了。

英文释义: to let somebody/something come out of a place where they have been kept or trapped; to stop holding something or stop it from being held so that it can move, fly, fall, etc. freely
例句: The prisoner was released after completing his sentence.
例句释义: 这名囚犯服完刑后被释放了。

英文释义: a creature that is covered with feathers and has two wings and two legs
例句: These birds all have bright colors.
例句释义: 这些鸟的颜色都很鲜艳。

详细释义: n.意见，看法，观点；专家意见
英文释义: your feelings or thoughts about somebody/something, rather than a fact; the beliefs or views of a group of people; advice from a professional person
例句: Different people have different opinions about the same thing.
例句释义: 不同的人对于同样的东西有不同的看法。

详细释义: n.信用；学分；借款；称赞；  v.归因于
英文释义: an arrangement that you make, with a shop/store for example, to pay later for something you buy
例句: Personal credit can determine whether bank loans will be granted.
例句释义: 个人信用可以决定银行是否同意贷款。

英文释义: serious, uncertain and possibly dangerous
例句: The injured man is in a critical condition, so doctors rush him to the emergency room.
例句释义: 这位伤者情况危急，医生们赶紧把他送到急诊室。

英文释义: a part of something where two or more sides, lines or edges join; the place inside a room or a box where two sides join; the area around this place
例句: The little boy unhappily sat in the corner of the room.
例句释义: 小男孩不高兴地坐在房间的角落里。

英文释义: worried and feeling concern about something
例句: She's concerned about her daughter who is sick at home.
例句释义: 她很担心家里生病的女儿。

英文释义: to make somebody think of something; to remember something
例句: Looking at the photo, she recalled their time together.
例句释义: 看着这张照片，她回忆起了她们在一起的时光。

英文释义: a form of something that is slightly different from an earlier form or from other forms of the same thing
例句: This book has many different versions.
例句释义: 这本书有很多不同的版本。

英文释义: to look at somebody/something for a long time
例句: Don't stare at my food, you little dog.
例句释义: 不要盯着我的吃的看了，你这只小狗狗。

详细释义: n.安全；安全设备，保险装置
英文释义: freedom from harm or danger :the state of being safe
例句: Safety is important when cycling. Remember to wear a helmet!
例句释义: 骑车的时候安全很重要，记得戴上头盔！

英文释义: producing the result that is wanted or intended; producing a successful result
例句: The medicine she took was effective for treating colds.
例句释义: 她吃的药对治疗感冒很有效。

英文释义: a district or an area of a town; the people who live there; the area that you are in or the area near a particular place
例句: The houses in this neighborhood all look the same.
例句释义: 这个社区的房子都一模一样。

英文释义: existing at the beginning of a particular period, process or activity; new and interesting in a way that is different from anything that has existed before; able to produce new and interesting ideas; painted, written, etc. by the artist rather than copied
例句: I gave her a copy and kept the original document myself.
例句释义: 我给了她一份复印件，并自己保存了原件。

详细释义: n.军队，部队；  vi.结队而行
英文释义: soldiers, especially in large groups; one group of soldiers, especially in tanks or on horses
例句: The statues of the ancient troop are great historic heritage.
例句释义: 这支古老军队的雕像是伟大的历史遗迹。

英文释义: the money that a person, a region, a country, etc. earns from work, from investing money, from business, etc.
例句: The man feels happy when receiving his monthly income.
例句释义: 收到当月工资时，这个男人非常开心。

英文释义: in a direct line or manner
例句: Why take the long way while you can walk directly to the company?
例句释义: 既然能径直走去公司，为什么还要绕远路呢？

A dozen eggs now cost twenty 
dollars―how expensive!

英文释义: the coldest season of the year that is after autumn and before spring
例句: It always snows heavily here in winter.
例句释义: 这儿冬天经常下大雪。

英文释义: a very small town located in a country area
例句: I lived in a remote mountain village.
例句释义: 我住在一个遥远的小山村里。

详细释义: adj. 苏维埃的；  n. 苏维埃
英文释义: connected with the former USSR
例句: The little boy in the Soviet uniform is holding a bunch of flowers.
例句释义: 这个穿着苏维埃军装的小男孩手里拿着一束鲜花。

英文释义: to say that you will not do something that somebody has asked you to do;  to say that you do not want something that has been offered to you
例句: The man refuses to eat these desserts.
例句释义: 这个男人拒绝吃这些甜点。

英文释义: to turn over and over and move in a particular direction; to make a round object do this
例句: The kid is rolling the snowball to make it bigger.
例句释义: 小孩正在滚雪球，使它变得更大。

详细释义: n.通信，交流；沟通方式；信息
英文释义: the activity or process of expressing ideas and feelings or of giving people information
例句: They like to use cell phones for communication.
例句释义: 他们喜欢用手机来交流。

英文释义: the flat surface at the front of a television, computer, or other electronic device, on which you see pictures or information; the large flat surface that films/movies or pictures are shown on
例句: The movie theater's screen is so large!
例句释义: 这个电影院的银幕好大！

详细释义: v.获得；  n.（财富、重量的）增加；利益
英文释义: to obtain or win something, especially something that you need or want; to gradually get more of something; to obtain an advantage or benefit from something or from doing something; to increase in value
例句: We can gain valuable knowledge by reading books.
例句释义: 我们能通过阅读获得宝贵的知识。

详细释义: n.居民；住院实习医师；  adj.居住的
英文释义: a person who lives in a particular place or who has their home there
例句: I'm a US citizen and a California resident.
例句释义: 我是美国公民，居住在加利福尼亚。

英文释义: to go to or stay at a place where you cannot be seen or found
例句: The boy is hiding inside the big box.
例句释义: 男孩藏在这个大箱子里。

英文释义: a chemical element. Gold is a yellow precious metal used for making coins, jewellery, decorative objects, etc.; money, jewellery, etc. that is made of gold
例句: Every pirate dreams of finding a chest of gold.
例句释义: 每个海盗都梦想找到一箱黄金。

详细释义: n.社团，俱乐部；夜总会；球棒
英文释义: (especially in compounds) a group of people who meet together regularly, for a particular activity, sport, etc.
例句: People are having fun in the night club.
例句释义: 人们在夜店里玩得很开心。

详细释义: n.农场，饲养场；  v.种田，经营农牧业
英文释义: an area of land, and the buildings on it, used for growing crops and/or keeping animals
例句: The farmer keeps a lot of animals on his farm.
例句释义: 这个农民在农场里养了很多动物。

详细释义: n. 潜力，潜能；  adj. 潜在的，可能的
英文释义: a chance or possibility that something will happen or exist in the future
例句: He has the potential to be very strong.
例句释义: 他有变得非常强壮的潜力。

详细释义: adj.欧洲的；欧洲人的；  n.欧洲人
英文释义: of, relating to, or characteristic of the continent of Europe or its people
例句: These are some of the famous European landmarks.
例句释义: 这是欧洲的一些地标性建筑。

英文释义: the fact of being in a particular place; the state of being present
例句: Every morning the teacher checks the presence in class.
例句释义: 老师每天早上都在课堂上检查我们的出勤情况。

详细释义: adj.独立的，自立的；  n.无党派者
英文释义: confident and free to do things without needing help from other people
例句: He is learning to be independent in the face of a challenge.
例句释义: 他在学习独立面对挑战。

英文释义: one of the areas which a country, town or state is divided into for purposes of organization, with official boundaries (= borders)
例句: The city has four districts.
例句释义: 这座城市由四个区域组成。

详细释义: n.外形，形状，轮廓；  vt.使形成，塑造
英文释义: the form or outline of an object
例句: Put your hands together to make a heart shape.
例句释义: 把你的手放在一起比个心形。

英文释义: a person who reads, especially one who reads a lot or in a particular way; a person who reads a particular newspaper, magazine, etc.
例句: The little girl is a keen reader of fiction.
例句释义: 这个小女孩是个狂热的小说读者。

详细释义: n.合同，契约；  v.感染（疾病）；订合同
英文释义: an official written agreement
例句: We signed the contract and I bought the house.
例句释义: 我们签了合同，我买下了这栋房子。

详细释义: v.挤满；聚集在……周围；涌入（人的脑海）；  n.人群，观众；民众；朋友
英文释义: a large number of people gathered together in a public place, for example in the streets or at a sports game
例句: Many people are crowding on the train.
例句释义: 许多人正挤在这趟列车上。

详细释义: n. 基督教徒；  adj. 基督教的，基督教徒的
英文释义: a religious person who believes Jesus is the Christ and who is a member of a Christian denomination
例句: Everyone in this family is a Christian.
例句释义: 这一家人都是基督教徒。

详细释义: vt.表达；用快递寄出；  adj.明确的；快速的；  n.快递；快车
英文释义: travelling very fast; operating very quickly
例句: The boy got down on one knee and expressed his love for her.
例句释义: 男孩单膝跪地，向她表达自己的爱意。

英文释义: a set of rooms for living in, usually on one floor of a building; a set of rooms used for a holiday/vacation
例句: This apartment is so bright with these windows.
例句释义: 这套公寓窗户多，很明亮。

详细释义: adj. 愿意的，心甘情愿的
英文释义: ready or pleased to help and not needing to be persuaded; done or given in an enthusiastic way
例句: I am willing to marry you!
例句释义: 我愿意嫁给你！

英文释义: the quality or state of being physically strong
例句: The man is flipping a heavy tire to build his strength.
例句释义: 那个男人正通过推起一个沉重的轮胎来增强体力。

英文释义: happening or existing before the event or object that you are talking about
例句: People no longer use the old fashioned devices used in previous times.
例句释义: 人们不再使用以前的老式设备。

详细释义: n.乐队；帮伙；带；  v.用带捆扎；联合
英文释义: a small group of musicians who play popular music together, often with a singer or singers
例句: The Beatles' live band performance fascinated their fans.
例句释义: 甲壳虫乐队的现场表演让他们的粉丝为之疯狂。

英文释义: unmistakably (`plain' is often used informally for `plainly')
例句: He's obviously far taller than me.
例句释义: 他明显比我高。

英文释义: a large animal that is used for riding and for carrying and pulling things
例句: The black horse is running on the beach.
例句释义: 这匹黑马正在沙滩上奔跑。

详细释义: adj.感兴趣的；有利害关系的
英文释义: giving your attention to something because you enjoy finding out about it or doing it; showing interest in something and finding it exciting
例句: The baby seems to be interested in the globe.
例句释义: 小宝宝似乎对这个地球仪很感兴趣。

英文释义: an object that people practise shooting at, especially a round board with circles on it
例句: Yes! I hit the target, right in the center!
例句释义: 太好了！我击中了靶子，正中红心！

英文释义: a building where people are kept as a punishment for a crime they have committed, or while they are waiting for trial
例句: This prison has been abandoned for many years.
例句释义: 这座监狱已被废弃多年了。

英文释义: to sit on a horse, etc. and control it as it moves
例句: When I ride my bike, I always wear a helmet for safety.
例句释义: 当我骑自行车时，为了安全我总会戴安全帽。

详细释义: n.哨兵，警卫员；  vi.警惕；  vt.保卫，守护
英文释义: a person, such as a soldier, a police officer or a prison officer, who protects a place or people, or prevents prisoners from escaping
例句: The guard stood outside and defended the palace gates.
例句释义: 哨兵站在外面看守宫殿的大门。

英文释义: a very firm request for something; something that somebody needs; things that somebody/something makes you do, especially things that are difficult, make you tired, worried, etc.; the desire or need of customers for goods or services which they want to buy or use
例句: He has always demanded some unreasonable requests from his children.
例句释义: 他总是要求子女们满足他的无理需求。

英文释义: a person who collects and reports news for newspapers, radio or television
例句: The reporter wants to interview you.
例句释义: 这个记者想要采访你。

英文释义: to take goods, letters, etc. to the person or people they have been sent to; to do what you promised to do or what you are expected to do
例句: The man delivers the packages to the woman.
例句释义: 男人把包裹送到了这位女士的手上。

详细释义: n.正文，原文，课文；课本；  v.发送短信
英文释义: the main printed part of a book or magazine, not the notes, pictures, etc.; any form of written material; the written form of a speech, a play, an article, etc.
例句: Mary is reading the text before answering the exam question.
例句释义: 在回答考试问题前，玛丽正在阅读正文。

英文释义: something (such as a hammer, saw, shovel, etc.) that you hold in your hand and use for a particular task
例句: We have all kinds of useful tools.
例句释义: 我们有各种各样的实用工具。

详细释义: adj.野生的；野性的；狂热的；荒芜的；疯狂的
英文释义: living or growing in natural conditions; not kept in a house or on a farm
例句: The wild kid is making a big mess in the dining room.
例句释义: 这个孩子太野了，把餐厅搞得一团糟。

英文释义: a thing that is used for transporting people or goods from one place to another, such as a car or lorry/truck
例句: The vehicle drives off while carrying a container.
例句释义: 那辆车载着一个集装箱开走了。

英文释义: to watch somebody/something carefully, especially to learn more about them
例句: She observes the liquid very carefully.
例句释义: 她观察液体时十分仔细。

英文释义: a journey made by air, especially in a plane
例句: The flight information is shown on the big screen.
例句释义: 航班信息显示在大屏幕上。

英文释义: buildings, services, equipment, etc. that are provided for a particular purpose; a special feature of a machine, service, etc. that makes it possible to do something extra
例句: This facility contains many different kinds of products.
例句释义: 这间车间有很多不同种类的产品。

详细释义: n.理解；（非正式）协议；  adj.体谅的，谅解的
英文释义: the knowledge that somebody has about a particular subject or situation
例句: It's impossible to get an understanding when he talks that way.
例句释义: 他那样说话，我完全无法理解。

详细释义: n.平均数；  adj.通常的；  vt.平均为
英文释义: the result of adding several amounts together, finding a total, and dividing the total by the number of amounts
例句: His height equals the average of his parents' heights.
例句释义: 他的身高等于他父母身高的平均数。

英文释义: (of facts, ideas, etc.) to become known
例句: A little rabbit emerged from the hole to look for food.
例句释义: 一只小兔子从洞口钻出来找吃的。

英文释义: a thing that helps you to be better or more successful than other people
例句: The rocket gives him an unfair advantage!
例句释义: 火箭给了他优势，这不公平！

英文释义: fast in moving or reacting
例句: The rescue team were quick to save people from the earthquake.
例句释义: 搜救队迅速救援地震中的人们。

详细释义: n. 领导，领导地位；领导能力
英文释义: the leaders of a group, organization, or country
例句: Under his leadership, they made it to the top!
例句释义: 他们在他的领导下登上了山顶！

英文释义: to get money for work that you do
例句: She earns some extra money by working a part-time job.
例句释义: 她通过做兼职赚了些外快。

详细释义: n.磅（重量单位）；英镑；  v.（连续）猛击，捣碎
英文释义: the unit of money in the UK, worth 100 pence; a unit for measuring weight, equal to 0.454 of a kilogram
例句: Pound sterling is the national currency of the United Kingdom.
例句释义: 英镑是英国的国家货币。

英文释义: the important facts, ideas or events that support something and that it can develop from
例句: The basis of his teaching is taken from this book.
例句释义: 他的教义基于这本书。

英文释义: full of light; shining strongly
例句: He opened the window and the room became bright.
例句释义: 他打开窗户，房间就变得明亮起来。

英文释义: to cut open somebody’s body in order to remove a part that has a disease or to repair a part that is damaged
例句: The doctors are operating on the patient.
例句释义: 医生们正在给病人做手术。

英文释义: a person that you have invited to your house or to a particular event that you are paying for
例句: We are waiting at the door for the arrival of our guests.
例句释义: 我们在门口等待客人的到来。

详细释义: n. (用于检验、分析的) 试样，样品；  adj.样品的，作为例子的；  vt.抽样检查；抽取……的试样
英文释义: a small amount of a substance taken from a larger amount and tested in order to obtain information about the substance
例句: I'll need a sample of your blood to see if you're sick.
例句释义: 我需要你的血样来确定你是不是生病了。

英文释义: to give something, especially money or goods, to help somebody/something
例句: Many people contribute money to help people in need.
例句释义: 很多人捐钱来帮助有需要的人们。

详细释义: adj. 矮小的；很少的；微小的
英文释义: very small in size or amount
例句: The kitten is so tiny that it could be held in one hand.
例句释义: 这只猫咪好小，一只手就可以把它托起。

详细释义: v.阻挡，妨碍，阻塞；  n.块状物；街区；阻碍；大厦
英文释义: to stop somebody from going somewhere or seeing something by standing in front of them or in their way
例句: The fallen tree blocks the way.
例句释义: 这棵倒地的树阻挡了去路。

英文释义: the act of protecting somebody/something; the state of being protected
例句: Everyone should get involved in environmental protection.
例句释义: 每个人都应该投身到环境保护工作中来。

详细释义: v.定居，安顿；结束（争论）；解决（纠纷）；调停
英文释义: to make yourself or somebody else comfortable in a new position; to put something carefully in a position so that it does not move; to become or make somebody/something become calm or relaxed The baby wouldn't settle.
例句: He built himself a house and decided to settle there.
例句释义: 他给自己建了一所房子，并决定在那里安顿下来。

英文释义: to give food to a person or an animal;  (of a baby or an animal) to eat food
例句: I used to nurse my baby; now I just feed him out of the bottle.
例句释义: 我过去要亲自给宝宝喂奶，现在只要用瓶子喂他就行了。

英文释义: to buy or find things of a particular type and keep them as a hobby
例句: I collect old stamps for fun.
例句释义: 我因为好玩而收集旧邮票。

英文释义: more than was first mentioned or is usual
例句: Each additional scoop made the ice cream taste even more delicious.
例句释义: 每多一个球都让这个冰激凌变得更好吃了。

英文释义: very
例句: I highly recommend you today's special dish―snail and goose liver with red wine!
例句释义: 我强烈向你推荐今天的特别菜品，蜗牛、鹅肝配红酒！

英文释义: who or what somebody/something is
例句: He took out his identity card to show who he was.
例句释义: 他掏出身份证来表明自己是谁。

英文释义: the name of a book, poem, painting, piece of music, etc.
例句: That title is more attractive than the content.
例句释义: 那个标题比内容更加吸引人。

例句: The cake is mostly cream.
例句释义: 这个蛋糕大部分是奶油。

英文释义: a period of time in which somebody is taught something; something that is intended to be learned; an experience, especially an unpleasant one, that somebody can learn from so that it does not happen again in the future
例句: The girl is taking a tennis lesson.
例句释义: 女孩正在上网球课。

英文释义: strong religious belief
例句: Many people go on an annual pilgrimage to this sacred place to express their faith.
例句释义: 很多人每年会到这个神圣的地方来参拜，以表达他们的信仰。

英文释义: a natural flow of water that continues in a long line across land to the sea/ocean
例句: This river brings fresh water from the mountains.
例句释义: 河流从山里带来了淡水。

英文释义: to move somebody to a higher rank or more senior job
例句: She worked hard and was soon promoted.
例句释义: 她工作勤奋，不久就要得到提升了。

英文释义: alive now
例句: Most living things can't live without sunlight and water.
例句释义: 大多数生物都离不开阳光和水。

详细释义: v. 计算；认为；  n. 计算
英文释义: to add (people or things) together to find the total number
例句: I try to count sheep when I want to fall asleep.
例句释义: 当我想睡觉的时候，我就尝试着数绵羊。

英文释义: used to say that something can only happen or be true in a particular situation
例句: I won't buy you that toy unless you get a full mark.
例句释义: 我不会给你买玩具的，除非你得了一百分。

英文释义: to become the husband or wife of somebody; to get married to somebody; to perform a ceremony in which a man and woman become husband and wife
例句: They finally get married. The story has a happy ending!
例句释义: 最终，他们结婚了。结局皆大欢喜！

英文释义: the day after today
例句: Today is the 11th, so tomorrow will be the 12th.
例句释义: 今天是11日，所以明天是12日。

英文释义: the way that a person performs basic physical movements or skills
例句: The musician combines different techniques in the performance.
例句释义: 这位音乐家在表演中结合了不同的演奏技巧。

英文释义: a way or track that is built or is made by the action of people walking
例句: Follow the path through the forest and you won't get lost.
例句释义: 沿着这条森林小径走，你就不会迷路。

英文释义: either of the organs on the sides of the head that you hear with
例句: The dog's ears are up.
例句释义: 这只狗竖起了耳朵。

英文释义: a building or part of a building where you can buy goods or services
例句: I often shop at the supermarket with my family.
例句释义: 我经常和家人一起去超市购物。

详细释义: adj.民间的，民俗的；  n.人们
英文释义: (of art, culture, etc.) traditional and typical of the ordinary people of a country or community
例句: Many Chinese folk arts are still enjoyed today.
例句释义: 许多中国民间艺术在今天依然为人所热爱。

英文释义: a moral rule or a strong belief that influences your actions; a general or scientific law that explains how something works or why something happens
例句: Our business success is based on four fundamental principles.
例句释义: 我们生意的成功基于四项基本原则。

详细释义: vt.幸存；艰难度过；  vi.生存，活着
英文释义: to continue to live or exist
例句: The girl survived the shipwreck.
例句释义: 这个女孩在海难中幸存了下来。

详细释义: v. （使）升起，举起；  n. 免费搭车
英文释义: to raise somebody/something or be raised to a higher position or level
例句: She's lifting her baby up above her head.
例句释义: 她把宝宝举过了头顶。

详细释义: n.边界；边沿；  v.近似；为……镶边
英文释义: the line that divides two countries or areas; the land near this line
例句: There is a distinct border between the urban and the rural areas.
例句释义: 城市与农村之间有一条明显的边界。

英文释义: an event in which people compete with each other to find out who is the best at something
例句: Who is going to win this competition?
例句释义: 谁会赢得这场比赛呢？

英文释义: to move quickly off the ground or away from a surface by pushing yourself with your legs and feet
例句: She was so happy that she jumped for joy.
例句释义: 她高兴得都跳起来了。

英文释义: to come together, or bring people together, in one place to form a group; to collect plants, fruit, etc. from a wide area; to reach a conclusion often intuitively from hints or through inferences
例句: The students are gathering for the flag-raising ceremony.

英文释义: to produce tears from your eyes often while making loud sounds because of pain, sorrow, or other strong emotions

英文释义: having a value in money, etc.

详细释义: v.联系，联想；联合；  n.伙伴；同事，合作人；  adj.副的

例句: He can't reach the other side of the river anyway.
