英文释义: located in the north or facing north; connected with or typical of the north part of the world or a region
例句: Canada is located in northern North America.
例句释义: 加拿大位于北美洲北部。

英文释义: to move your head up and down as a way of answering “yes” or of showing agreement, understanding, or approval
例句: The little bird is nodding its head.
例句释义: 这只小鸟在点头。

英文释义: to cover a surface or object with paint
例句: The woman is painting the wall blue.
例句释义: 这个女人正在把墙刷成蓝色的。

详细释义: n. 燃料；  v. 给……加燃料
英文释义: a thing that is said or done that makes something, especially an argument, continue or get worse
例句: We use many different types of fuel in everyday life.
例句释义: 日常生活中，我们会使用到多种不同类型的燃料。

英文释义: one of the flat and typically green parts of a plant that grow from a stem or twig
例句: The picture shows different kinds of leaves.
例句释义: 图片里展示了各种各样的树叶。

英文释义: not wet, damp or sticky; without water or moisture
例句: These flowers are dry but still beautiful.
例句释义: 这些花干了也挺漂亮。

详细释义: adj.俄罗斯的，俄语的；  n.俄罗斯人，俄语
英文释义: from or connected with Russia
例句: This poster consists of Russian cultural icons.
例句释义: 这张海报由俄罗斯文化象征构成。

英文释义: the action or process of teaching; the act of instructing someone
例句: She follows the instructions to take her medicine.
例句释义: 她按照说明书的指示服药。

详细释义: n.泳池，水塘；  v.集中资源（或材料）
英文释义: [countable] a small area of still water, especially one that has formed naturally freshwater pools; a small amount of liquid or light lying on a surface; a group of people available for work when needed; a supply of things or money that is shared by a group of people and can be used when needed;
例句: There is a big swimming pool in the park.
例句释义: 公园里有个超大的游泳池。

英文释义: to go up something towards the top; to move somewhere, especially with difficulty or effort; to go up mountains or climb rocks as a hobby or sport; to go higher in the sky
例句: I don't think I could climb that mountain.
例句释义: 我觉得我攀不上这座山。

详细释义: adj.甜的；可爱的，美好的；芳香的；  n.糖果，甜食
英文释义: containing, or tasting as if it contains, a lot of sugar; having a pleasant smell; having a pleasant sound; (especially of children or small things) attractive; having or showing a kind character
例句: Most kids love sweet food such as candy.
例句释义: 大多数小孩都喜欢吃甜食，比如糖。

英文释义: the part of a vehicle that produces power to make the vehicle move
例句: The engine at the front of the car produces power to make the car move.
例句释义: 汽车前部的引擎为其提供前进的动力。

详细释义: n.盐；  adj.含盐的，腌制的；  v.加盐于，用盐腌
英文释义: a white substance that is added to food to give it a better flavour or to preserve it
例句: Adding salt gives the dish more flavor.
例句释义: 加盐可以让菜肴更有滋味。

英文释义: to become greater in size, number or importance; if a business expands or is expanded, new branches are opened, it makes more money, etc.
例句: Our business is expanding across the whole country.
例句释义: 我们的业务正在全国范围内扩大。

英文释义: the quality of being important
例句: Wi-Fi is of great importance to people as it becomes a basic need.
例句释义: Wi-Fi对人们很重要，它已经成了一项基本需求。

详细释义: n.金属，合金，金属制品；  vt.（以金属）覆盖，装配
英文释义: a substance (such as gold, tin, or copper) that usually has a shiny appearance, is a good conductor of electricity and heat, can be melted, and is usually capable of being shaped
例句: Wow, these roses are made of metal.
例句释义: 哇，这些玫瑰花是金属做的。

英文释义: (of a person’s or an animal’s body) having too much flesh on it and weighing too much
例句: You'll become fat if you eat too much junk food.
例句释义: 如果你吃很多垃圾食品的话，你会长胖的。

英文释义: a printed piece of paper that gives you the right to travel on a particular bus, train, etc. or to go into a theatre, etc.
例句: They got two tickets to fly back.
例句释义: 他们有两张返程的机票。

英文释义: the programs, etc. used to operate a computer
例句: You can download the softwares onto your computer.
例句释义: 你可以把这些软件下载到电脑上。

英文释义: to become impossible to see; to be lost or impossible to find
例句: How amazing it is that he can make a bird disappear!
例句释义: 他能把一只鸟变没了，真是太神奇了！

详细释义: adj.公司的；全体的；共同的；（法人）团体的
英文释义: connected with a corporation
例句: She works for a large corporate company. He works for a small independent one.
例句释义: 她在一家大型公司工作。他为一家小型独立公司工作。

英文释义: unusual or surprising, especially in a way that is difficult to understand
例句: I met a guy wearing strange clothes on the subway.
例句释义: 我在地铁上遇到了一个衣着奇怪的男人。

英文释义: either one of the two soft parts that surround the mouth; having the type of lips mentioned
例句: Her lips are the most beautiful part of her face.
例句释义: 她的嘴唇是她脸上最漂亮的部位。

英文释义: the activity of somebody who reads; an act of reading something
例句: The girl enjoys reading at home.
例句释义: 女孩很享受在家里读书。

详细释义: adj. 城市的，城镇的，都市的
英文释义: connected with a town or city; connected with types of music such as rhythm and blues and reggae that are played by black musicians
例句: I like to party so I prefer urban environments.
例句释义: 我喜欢派对，所以我更喜欢城市的环境。

英文释义: connected with the state of health of the mind or with the treatment of illnesses of the mind
例句: He takes pills as candy out of his mental sickness.
例句释义: 这个人精神出问题了，才会把药当作糖。

英文释义: more and more; to an increasing degree
例句: Snow increasingly accumulated on the ground.
例句释义: 地上的积雪越来越多。

英文释义: a light meal eaten in the middle of the day
例句: When we make a big sale, our boss invites us all to lunch.
例句释义: 当我们做成一单大生意时，我们老板会请我们去吃午餐。

详细释义: adj. 教育的；有教育意义的
例句: Well, this is the whole educational process.
例句释义: 好吧，这就是教育的全过程。

详细释义: pron.某个地方；  adv.到某处，在某处
英文释义: in, at or to a place that you do not know or do not mention by name
例句: He is searching for somewhere to take a holiday.
例句释义: 他正在寻找度假的地方。

英文释义: a person who owns or manages a farm
例句: Without farmers, we would have no food.
例句释义: 没有农民，我们就会没有食物。

详细释义: n.糖；食用糖；  vi.糖化；  vt.加糖于
英文释义: a sweet substance usually in the form of white or brown crystals or white powder that comes from plants and is used to make foods sweeter
例句: I like two lumps of sugar in my cup of coffee.
例句释义: 我想在我的咖啡里放两块糖。

英文释义: a large, round object in space (such as the Earth) that travels around a star (such as the sun)
例句: There are 8 major planets in our solar system.
例句释义: 太阳系中有八大行星。

详细释义: adj.最爱的；  n.最喜爱的人或物
英文释义: liked more than others of the same kind
例句: Apples are the little girl’s favorite fruit.
例句释义: 苹果是那个小女孩最爱的水果。

英文释义: to travel to or around an area or a country in order to learn about it
例句: They will explore the dark cave.
例句释义: 他们即将探索这个漆黑的洞穴。

英文释义: to get something, especially by making an effort
例句: The policeman is obtaining evidence from the crime scene.
例句释义: 这个警察正在犯罪现场取证。

英文释义: a person who hates somebody or who acts or speaks against somebody/something
例句: The man who holds the pan is her last enemy.
例句释义: 拿着平底锅的男人是她的最后一个敌人。

详细释义: adj. 复杂的，难解的；  n. 建筑群；情结
英文释义: made of many different things or parts that are connected; difficult to understand
例句: He has no clue about how to solve this complex case.
例句释义: 他对如何解决这个复杂的案件毫无头绪。

详细释义: vt.围绕；包围；  n.围绕物；  adj.环绕立体声的
英文释义: to be all around something/somebody
例句: The green plants surround the windows.
例句释义: 绿色植被把窗户围了起来。

英文释义: a person who competes in sports; a person who is good at sports and physical exercise
例句: He was a great athlete who ran really fast.
例句释义: 他以前是个优秀的运动员，跑得非常快。

英文释义: to ask (someone) formally or politely to do something
例句: The agent invited us in to have a look at the house.
例句释义: 房屋中介邀请我们进去看一下这栋房子。

详细释义: v.重复；重做；  n.复制；重奏
英文释义: to say or write something again or more than once
例句: Sorry, I couldn't hear you―could you please repeat what you said?
例句释义: 抱歉，我听不到你说的话，你可以重复一下刚才说的话吗？

英文释义: with a lot of attention or thought, so that you avoid hurting yourself, damaging something or doing something wrong
例句: He pulled out the block very carefully.
例句释义: 他小心地抽出了这个木块。

详细释义: n.灵魂；中心人物；  adj.熟悉黑人的
英文释义: the spiritual part of a person, believed to exist after death
例句: Piano and drum are the core musical instruments in soul music.
例句释义: 钢琴和鼓是灵乐的核心乐器。

英文释义: involving science; connected with science; (of a way of doing something or thinking) careful and logical
例句: Be very careful when doing scientific experiments.
例句释义: 做科学实验时一定要小心。

详细释义: adj.不可能的；  n.不可能的事
英文释义: that cannot exist or be done; not possible
例句: It's almost impossible for her to push that massive rock.
例句释义: 她要推动那块巨大的石头几乎不可能。

详细释义: n.讨论小组；仪表板；面板；  v.镶嵌
英文释义: a group of specialists who give their advice or opinion about something; a group of people who discuss topics of interest on television or radio
例句: The candidate was selected by the panel.
例句释义: 候选人是由讨论小组选出的。

英文释义: the thing or idea that a sound, word, sign, etc. represents; the things or ideas that somebody wishes to communicate to you by what they say or do
例句: This word has so many different meanings.
例句释义: 这个单词有很多不同的意思。

英文释义: having a husband or wife; connected with marriage;
例句: We're getting married today! We're so happy!
例句释义: 我们今天结婚，幸福极了！

英文释义: an object used for producing musical sounds, for example a piano or a drum
例句: Guitar, violin, drum, and piano are all musical instruments.
例句释义: 吉他、小提琴、鼓和钢琴都是乐器。

英文释义: to say that something will happen in the future
例句: He predicted this stock will experience an increase in a few days.
例句释义: 他预测这只股票过几天会涨。

详细释义: n.天气；  v.风化，受风蚀，经受风雨
英文释义: the state of the air and atmosphere at a particular time and place :the temperature and other outside conditions (such as rain, cloudiness, etc.) at a particular time and place
例句: The weather this week has been mostly cloudy.
例句释义: 这周的天气以多云为主。

英文释义: connected with the position or activities of a president
例句: Mount Rushmore and the White House both remind us of presidential governments.
例句释义: 拉什莫尔山和白宫都会让我们联想到总统制。

详细释义: adj.情绪激动的，感情冲动的
英文释义: connected with people’s feelings (= with the emotions); showing strong emotions, sometimes in a way that other people think is unnecessary
例句: Sometimes he is calm but sometimes he is really emotional.
例句释义: 他有时候很平静，但有时候也很情绪化。

英文释义: a promise to do something or to behave in a particular way; a promise to support somebody/something; the fact of committing yourself
例句: They made a commitment to each other at their wedding ceremony.
例句释义: 在婚礼上，他们相互做出承诺。

详细释义: n.熊；（股市）看跌的人；  vt.忍受，容忍；带有；生育
英文释义: a heavy wild animal with thick fur and sharp claws (= pointed parts on the ends of its feet). There are many types of bear.
例句: Look, the bear is eating honey!
例句释义: 看，那只熊在吃蜂蜜！

详细释义: n.口袋，兜，衣袋；  adj.袖珍的
英文释义: a small piece of material like a small bag sewn into or onto a piece of clothing so that you can carry things in it
例句: I put my phone into my pocket.
例句释义: 我把手机放进我的口袋里。

详细释义: adj.瘦的；稀薄的，淡的；  v.变薄，变少
英文释义: (sometimes disapproving) (of a person or part of the body) not covered with much flesh
例句: My personal trainer told me that I could stay thin by exercising every day.
例句释义: 我的私人教练告诉我，我可以通过每天锻炼保持苗条。

英文释义: the measurement in degrees of how hot or cold a thing or place is
例句: The weather forecast tells us today's minimum temperature will be 35°C.
例句释义: 天气预报告诉我们，今天的最低温度会是35摄氏度。

详细释义: n.惊喜；惊奇，诧异；  vt.出其不意地袭击；使惊奇，使诧异，使感到意外
英文释义: an event, a piece of news, etc. that is unexpected or that happens suddenly
例句: She had a look of surprise as she opened her gift.
例句释义: 拆开礼物后，她露出了惊喜的表情。

详细释义: n. 投票站；民意测验；  v. 获得（票数）
英文释义: the number of votes given in an election
例句: The voters will head to the polls and wait in line to vote.
例句释义: 选民们会前往投票站排队投票。

英文释义: an act of formally asking somebody to marry you
例句: That guy made a proposal to his girlfriend with a diamond ring.
例句释义: 那位男士手拿钻戒，向他的女朋友求婚。

英文释义: a result of something that has happened
例句: The consequence of eating too much junk food is getting fat.
例句释义: 吃太多垃圾食品的后果就是长胖。

英文释义: an amount of air that you take into your lungs
例句: She took a deep breath to smell the flowers.
例句释义: 她深吸了一口花香。

英文释义: someone or something that is seen
例句: My dog's sight is better with these binoculars.
例句释义: 用了望远镜，我的狗视力更好了。

详细释义: n.平衡；  v.保持平衡；平衡
英文释义: a situation in which different things exist in equal, correct or good amounts
例句: Look, he can keep balance on that rope!
例句释义: 看啊，他能在那根绳索上保持平衡！

英文释义: to take somebody else’s child into your family and become its legal parent(s)
例句: The couple adopted a child from the orphanage.
例句释义: 这对夫妻从孤儿院收养了一个孩子。

详细释义: n.少数民族；  adj.构成少数的
英文释义: a small group within a community or country that is different because of race, religion, language, etc.
例句: The two ladies of an ethnic minority group wear colorful clothes.
例句释义: 这两位少数民族妇女穿着鲜艳的服饰。

详细释义: adj.直的；坦诚的；  adv.直接地
英文释义: without a bend or curve; going in one direction only
例句: The road is very straight.
例句释义: 这条路很直。

详细释义: v.连接；与……有同感；把……联系起来
英文释义: to join together two or more things; to be joined together
例句: My phone is connected to the computer.
例句释义: 我的手机正连接着电脑。

英文释义: a thing or things that are produced as a result of work; a book, piece of music, painting, etc.
例句: On the desk are the great writer's works of literature.
例句释义: 桌子上放着这位伟大作家的文学作品。

英文释义: to be in the right or suitable place
例句: You belong to our group―please join us.
例句释义: 你属于我们的团队，请加入我们。

英文释义: help that is given to a person
例句: The blind man walks with the aid of a guide dog.
例句释义: 那个盲人在导盲犬的帮助下走路。

英文释义: an opinion or a suggestion about what somebody should do in a particular situation
例句: The doctor is giving her some good advice.
例句释义: 医生正给予她一些好的建议。

详细释义: n.照片；  vt.为……拍照；  vi.上镜
英文释义: a picture that is made by using a camera that stores images in digital form or that has a film sensitive to light inside it
例句: Here are all of my travel photographs.
例句释义: 这些都是我旅行拍的照片。

英文释义: with no people or things inside; (of something that somebody says or does) with no meaning; not meaning what is said
例句: The meeting room had many seats, but they were all empty.
例句释义: 会议室有很多座位，但是都是空的。

英文释义: characteristic of a region
例句: The regional accents of Beijing can be confusing sometimes.
例句释义: 有时候，北京当地的口音不太好懂。

详细释义: n. 小径，路径；记号，痕迹，线索；  v. （烟等）袅袅升起
英文释义: a path through the countryside
例句: The cyclist is riding on the forest trail.
例句释义: 自行车手正在森林小径上骑行。

详细释义: n.小说，长篇故事；  adj.新奇的，新颖的，与众不同的
英文释义: a long written story usually about imaginary characters and events
例句: He loves reading novels and these two are his favorites.
例句释义: 他喜欢读小说，这两本是他最喜欢的。

英文释义: a system of computer programming instructions
例句: The programmer is writing code for the new software on his computer.
例句释义: 这位程序员正在电脑上为一款新软件写代码。

详细释义: adv.出于某种原因，不知怎么地
例句: He looked different somehow.
例句释义: 不知怎么的，他看上去变了。

英文释义: to arrange something or the parts of something into a particular order or structure
例句: He is trying to organize the paper.
例句释义: 他在努力整理文件。

英文释义: a group of members of the public who listen to the facts of a case in a court and decide whether or not somebody is guilty of a crime
例句: The lawyer is showing the evidence to the jury.
例句释义: 律师正在向陪审团展示证据。

英文释义: either one of the two soft parts on a woman's chest that produce milk when she has a baby
例句: She held her baby to her breast to give some milk.
例句释义: 她把宝宝抱在胸前哺乳。

详细释义: v.告知收到；致意；答谢；承认
英文释义: to tell somebody that you have received something that they sent to you
例句: "Acknowledged. We will bake the bread soon."
例句释义: “已收到。我们会马上烤面包。”

详细释义: n. 主题；  adj. 主题的
英文释义: the subject or main idea in a talk, piece of writing or work of art
例句: These guys held a party with a pirate theme.
例句释义: 这些人办了个海盗主题的派对。

详细释义: n.暴风雨，暴风雪；  v.横冲直撞；突袭
英文释义: very bad weather with strong winds and rain, and often thunder and lightning
例句: The ship was hit by a storm at sea.
例句释义: 这艘船在海上遭遇了暴风雨的袭击。

英文释义: an organization of workers formed to protect the rights and interests of its members
例句: The union is trying to protect their rights as workers.
例句释义: 工会在努力保护他们作为劳动者的权利。

详细释义: n. 书桌，办公桌；服务台
英文释义: a piece of furniture like a table, usually with drawers in it, that you sit at to read, write, work, etc.
例句: There is an empty desk right here.
例句释义: 这儿有一张空的桌子。

详细释义: n.水果；成果，产物；  v.结果实
英文释义: (of a tree or plant) to produce fruit
例句: A basket of fresh fruits is on the wooden table.
例句释义: 木桌上放了一篮新鲜水果。

英文释义: costing a lot of money
例句: These are so expensive! You shouldn't have bought them for me! (Actually, yes, you should have.)
例句释义: 这太贵重了！你不该买给我的。（好吧，其实我想要。）

详细释义: adj.黄色的；胆小的；  n.黄色
英文释义: having the colour of lemons or butter
例句: Look at this big yellow sunflower.
例句释义: 瞧这朵黄色的大向日葵。

英文释义: something that you decide when you have thought about all the information connected with the situation
例句: I finally drew a conclusion from these facts.
例句释义: 我终于从这些事实中得出了一条结论。

详细释义: adj.首要的，主要的；最好的，一流的；  n.青春，全盛期，青壮年时期
英文释义: main; most important; basic
例句: "Our prime task is to reduce the pollution," said the mayor.
例句释义: “我们的首要任务是减少污染。” 市长说道。

详细释义: n.影子；阴影；  v.把影子投在……
例句: The shadow of her hand looks just like a bird!
例句释义: 她手的影子看起来就像一只鸟！

详细释义: n.奋斗；斗争；  vi.挣扎，抗争
英文释义: something that is difficult for you to do or achieve
例句: She's struggling to reach the top of the cliff.
例句释义: 她为了自己登顶的目标而奋斗。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to decide or believe something as a result of what you have heard or seen
例句: They conclude the successful meeting with a high five.
例句释义: 他们以击掌来结束这次会议。

英文释义: a person whose job involves examining facts or materials in order to give an opinion on them
例句: The analyst is explaining the trend of the stock market.
例句释义: 分析员正在解说股市走向。

英文释义: to move your body in a way that goes with the rhythm and style of music that is being played
例句: They had a dance battle as they were waiting for the traffic jam to end.
例句释义: 在等待通车的过程中，他们在斗舞。

英文释义: an official rule made by a government or some other authority
例句: The traffic police is introducing traffic rules and regulations to us.
例句释义: 交警在向我们介绍交通法规。

英文释义: a living thing
例句: The universe came into being as a result of a big bang.
例句释义: 宇宙的出现是大爆炸的结果。

详细释义: n.戒指；集团，团伙；  v.打电话
英文释义: a piece of jewellery that you wear on your finger, consisting of a round band of gold, silver, etc.
例句: The design of her rings is very interesting and unique.
例句释义: 她戒指的样式非常有趣和特别。

英文释义: to a great extent; mostly or mainly
例句: The users of this product are largely female.
例句释义: 这个产品的用户大多数为女性。

详细释义: v.换挡；移动；改换，替换；  n.轮值
英文释义: to change the gears when you are driving a vehicle
例句: You have to shift gears as you drive around the corner.
例句释义: 你开车驶过拐角时要换挡。

详细释义: n.税收，（公司或组织的）收益
英文释义: the money that a government receives from taxes or that an organization, etc. receives from its business
例句: Tourism contributes a large part of the local government's revenue.
例句释义: 旅游业收入在地方政府的收入中占很大一部分。

英文释义: to write or draw a symbol, line, etc. on something in order to give information about it
例句: I'm going to mark our meeting on the calendar.
例句释义: 我打算在日历上把我们开会的日子标记出来。

详细释义: v.使……坐落于，位于，处于；找出……的位置
英文释义: to find the exact position of somebody/something
例句: Some important cities are located in the places marked on the map.
例句释义: 一些重要的城市位于地图上面标出来的地方。

英文释义: an area of Britain, Ireland or the US that has its own government
例句: This state is divided into several counties.
例句释义: 这个国家被分为了若干个郡。

详细释义: n. 外貌，外表；公开露面
英文释义: the way that somebody/something looks on the outside; what somebody/something seems to be
例句: Many of his fans comment on his physical appearance.
例句释义: 他的很多粉丝都在讨论他的外表。

英文释义: a box, bag, etc. in which things are wrapped or packed; the contents of a box, etc.
例句: I wonder what could be in the package.
例句释义: 我想知道包裹里装的是什么。

英文释义: a problem; a thing or situation that causes problems
例句: The little boy is experiencing some difficulties in math.
例句释义: 小男孩遇到了一些数学上的问题。

详细释义: n.桥，桥梁；起连接作用的东西，纽带；  v.把……连接起来；架桥
英文释义: a structure that is built over a road, railway/railroad, river, etc. so that people or vehicles can cross from one side to the other
例句: There is a small wooden bridge crossing the stream in the woods.
例句释义: 树林里的小溪上有一座木制小桥。

英文释义: to say that (someone or something) is good and deserves to be chosen
例句: The owner of the hotel recommended a good steak house to the tourists.
例句释义: 旅馆老板向游客们推荐了一家不错的牛排店。

英文释义: easy to see or notice
例句: "2+2=4" should be pretty obvious to you.
例句释义: "2+2=4"对你来说是显而易见的吧。

英文释义: used when you are giving your opinion or stating what is important about a situation
例句: Basically, all the students are depressed during a hard English examination.
例句释义: 在这场困难的英语考试中，基本上所有学生都很郁闷。

英文释义: to produce or create something
例句: This plant generates electricity for the entire city.
例句释义: 这间工厂产出电力供全城使用。

英文释义: at the present or from now on; usually used with a negative
例句: He was afraid to sleep alone when he was young, but not anymore!
例句释义: 他小的时候害怕一个人睡觉，但现在不再怕了！

英文释义: to ask someone to marry you
例句: Daniel proposed marriage by getting down on one knee.
例句释义: 丹尼尔单膝跪地求婚。

详细释义: n.思考，思维；想法，见解；  adj.有头脑的，有见识的
英文释义: the process of thinking about something; ideas or opinions about something
例句: There's a lot of thinking going on in his young brain.
例句释义: 他稚嫩的大脑里有很多想法萦绕。

英文释义: used to say something might happen, exist, or be true but is not certain
例句: Possibly, I can really get a surprise!
例句释义: 也许我真的可以得到一个惊喜！

详细释义: n. 时尚；趋势；  v. 转向；使趋向
英文释义: a general direction in which a situation is changing or developing
例句: The new trend is for girls to wear very colorful clothing.
例句释义: 女孩儿们现在流行穿多彩的服饰。

英文释义: a person who visits a person or place
例句: I think we have a visitor at the door.
例句释义: 我想我们有客人来了。

英文释义: the act of lending something; the state of being lent
例句: He is applying for a loan so that he can afford to buy the house.
例句释义: 他正在申请一笔贷款，这样他就买得起房子了。

英文释义: at this time or period; now
例句: Five years ago, he was just a waiter; but currently, he is a successful businessman.
例句释义: 五年前，他只是个服务员，但现在他已经成了一位成功的商人。

英文释义: not having any physically unpleasant feelings; experiencing physical comfort
例句: The man looked so comfortable lying in the chair.
例句释义: 这个男人躺在椅子上，看起来非常舒适。

英文释义: a person or an organization that invests money in something
例句: This investor is always keen to fund new businesses with innovative ideas.
例句释义: 这位投资者一直热衷于为有创新想法的新企业提供资金。

详细释义: n.利润，盈利；益处；  v.得益，有益于
英文释义: the money that you make in business or by selling things, especially after paying the costs involved
例句: The girl made a profit by selling the dress.
例句释义: 这个女孩靠卖掉这件裙子赚了一笔。

英文释义: having strong feelings about something that you dislike very much or about an unfair situation
例句: The phone call makes him very angry.
例句释义: 这通电话让他非常生气。

详细释义: n. （飞机、轮船等的）全体工作人员
英文释义: all the people working on a ship, plane, etc.; all the people working on a ship, plane etc. except the officers who are in charge
例句: This is a picture of the crew and the aircraft.
例句释义: 这是一张机组人员与客机的合影。

英文释义: an unpleasant event, especially in a vehicle, that happens unexpectedly and causes injury or damage
例句: An accident happened, and the egg was broken.
例句释义: 一场事故发生了，然后鸡蛋被打碎了。

英文释义: the food that is eaten at a meal
例句: The family enjoyed a tasty meal.
例句释义: 这家人享受了一顿美餐。

详细释义: n.听力；听证会；申辩的机会
英文释义: the sense through which a person or animal is aware of sound; the ability to hear
例句: His hearing is not so good.
例句释义: 他的听力不是很好。

英文释义: the vehicles that are on a road at a particular time; the movement of ships, trains, aircraft, etc. along a particular route
例句: The cars are hardly moving in the traffic jam.
例句释义: 车子在交通堵塞中艰难地移动。

详细释义: n.肌肉；体力；  v.用强硬手段获得
英文释义: a piece of body tissue that you contract and relax in order to move a particular part of the body; the tissue that forms the muscles of the body
例句: I can see every muscle on the man's arm.
例句释义: 我可以看到这个男人手臂上的每块肌肉。

英文释义: an idea, a belief or an understanding of something
例句: The experiment supported his notion that heavy and light objects fall at the same speed.
例句释义: 这次实验支持了他的观点，即重物和轻物会以相同的速度下落。

详细释义: vt.捕获，抓住；捕捉，留存；  n.战利品
英文释义: to make somebody interested in something
例句: The boy captured a butterfly with his net.
例句释义: 小男孩用网兜捉了只蝴蝶。

英文释义: to like one thing or person better than another; to choose one thing rather than something else because you like it better
例句: The girl prefers vegetables to cake.
例句释义: 比起蛋糕，小女孩更喜欢蔬菜。

英文释义: used to emphasize that a particular statement, feeling, etc. is sincere or genuine
例句: The undefeated boxer is truly one of the greatest of all time.
例句释义: 这位不败的拳击手真的是有史以来最伟大的拳击手之一。

英文释义: the world; the planet that we live on
例句: We only have one earth, so we should do all we can to protect her.
例句释义: 我们只有一个地球，所以我们应该竭尽所能去保护她。

详细释义: adj. 日本的，日本人的，日语的；  n. 日本人，日语
英文释义: (a person) from Japan
例句: They wear clothes of Japanese style.
例句释义: 他们穿着日本风格的服饰。

英文释义: the top part of the front of the body, between the neck and the stomach
例句: He likes to show off his chest muscles.
例句释义: 他喜欢炫耀自己的胸肌。

英文释义: having a larger distance between opposite sides or surfaces than other similar objects or than normal
例句: This book is very thick.
例句释义: 这本书非常厚。

详细释义: n. 现金；  v. 付（或收）现款
英文释义: money in the form of coins or notes/bills
例句: The woman behind the counter said they take cash only.
例句释义: 柜台后面的女人说只接受现金。

英文释义: a building in which objects of artistic, cultural, historical or scientific interest are kept and shown to the public
例句: We can go to the museum to look at art.
例句释义: 我们可以去博物馆参观艺术品。

英文释义: a person or thing that is beautiful
例句: This beauty has blue eyes and golden hair.
例句释义: 那个美人有蓝的眼睛和金色的头发。

英文释义: a sudden serious and dangerous event or situation which needs immediate action to deal with it T
例句: It's an emergency; get her to the hospital as soon as possible.
例句释义: 情况紧急，尽快送她去医院。

英文释义: being the only one of its kind
例句: This square apple looks unique in a pile of round ones.
例句释义: 这个方苹果在一堆圆苹果中显得独一无二。

详细释义: adj. 体内的，内部的；  n. 内部器官
例句: The picture shows humans' major internal organs.
例句释义: 这张图展示了人类主要的内脏。

英文释义: connected with or belonging to a nation, race or people that shares a cultural tradition; typical of a country or culture that is very different from modern Western culture and therefore interesting for people in Western countries
例句: The three people come from different ethnic groups.
例句释义: 这三个人来自不同的少数民族。

英文释义: to make a physical or electronic connection between one object, machine, place, etc. and another
例句: Click the link and buy the backpack from our online store.
例句释义: 点击链接来百词斩商城买个双肩包吧。

详细释义: n.压力；节拍；  v.加压力于
英文释义: a state of mental tension and worry caused by problems in your life, work, etc.
例句: She is under a lot of stress with her work.
例句释义: 她在工作中承受着很大的压力。

详细释义: n.目录；  adj.满足的；  v.使满意
英文释义: the things that are contained in something
例句: You can get a brief idea of a book from the table of contents.
例句释义: 你可以从目录页了解一本书的大致内容。

详细释义: v.选择，挑选；  adj.精选的，选择的
英文释义: to choose somebody/something from a group of people or things, usually according to a system; to mark something on a computer screen; to choose something, especially from a menu
例句: Which dress do you think I should select?
例句释义: 你觉得我应该选哪条裙子？

英文释义: the part of a plant that grows under the ground and absorbs water and minerals that it sends to the rest of the plant; the origin or basis of something; the part of a word that has the main meaning and that its other forms are based on; a word that other words are formed from
例句: This tree's roots are above the ground.
例句释义: 这棵树的树根露出了地面。

英文释义: the part of the face that sticks out above the mouth, used for breathing and smelling things
例句: Look! The elephant is drinking water with its long nose.
例句释义: 看！大象正在用它的长鼻子喝水。

详细释义: v.宣布，宣告；表明；（在击球员还未全部出局时）宣布结束赛局
英文释义: to state something firmly and clearly
例句: The priest declared the couple husband and wife.
例句释义: 这个牧师宣布这对男女正式结成夫妻。

英文释义: (not usually used in the progressive tenses) to be grateful for something that somebody has done; to welcome something
例句: Grandma appreciated the gift of flowers on her birthday.
例句释义: 外婆为她生日那天收到的鲜花礼物表示感谢。

英文释义: used to emphasize something that is real or exists in fact
例句: The actual fact is that crocodiles walk underwater instead of swimming.
例句释义: 事实上，鳄鱼在水下是靠走而不是（人们通常以为的）游泳。

英文释义: a glass or plastic container, usually round with straight sides and a narrow neck, used especially for storing liquids
例句: I hope someone find my message in this bottle.
例句释义: 我希望有人能发现瓶子里我的留言。

英文释义: almost no; almost not; almost none
例句: There is hardly any water coming out of the tap.
例句释义: 水龙头几乎不出水了。

英文释义: the place on a computer or other electronic device where you can choose the way that it works or looks; the particular choices that you make
例句: You can adjust your smartphone settings in the settings menu.
例句释义: 您可以在设置菜单中调整手机的设置。

详细释义: v.发射；创办，开始从事；  n.（游艇、汽艇）下水
英文释义: to send something such as a spacecraft, weapon, etc. into space, into the sky or through water
例句: The space shuttle was launched into the sky in a cloud of smoke.
例句释义: 航天飞机在一片烟雾里被发射到天空中。

英文释义: a collection of information stored together in a computer, under a particular name; a box or folded piece of card for keeping loose papers together and in order
例句: Click here to open the file.
例句释义: 单击此处以打开文件。

详细释义: adj.生病的；  n.病人；  v.呕吐
英文释义: affected with a disease or illness
例句: The sick boy fell asleep in the bed.
例句释义: 这个生病的男孩在床上睡着了。

英文释义: something that happens as a result of an activity or process
例句: The final outcome of the football game is 0:0.
例句释义: 这场足球比赛的最后结果是0 : 0。

详细释义: n. 广告；促销活动；公元
英文释义: a public promotion of some product or service
例句: AD indicates any year after the supposed birth year of Jesus Christ.
例句释义: “公元”表示耶稣基督公认诞生之年以后的年份。

英文释义: to protect somebody/something from attack
例句: Our anti-virus software will defend your computer against attacks.
例句释义: 我们的杀毒软件会帮助你的电脑抵御攻击。

英文释义: something that you feel you have to do because it is your moral or legal responsibility
例句: Everyone should carry out his duty conscientiously when at work.
例句释义: 每个人在工作时都应该认真履行自己的职责。

英文释义: a piece of paper for writing or printing on, etc. usually in a standard size
例句: Please write your name on this sheet of paper.
例句释义: 请在这张纸上写下你的名字。

英文释义: used to say what is the right thing to do; used to say what you advise or recommend
例句: You ought to wipe your butt after pooping.
例句释义: 拉完??应该擦屁股。

英文释义: to make sure that something happens or is definite
例句: Please ensure my grammar is correct.
例句释义: 请确认我的语法是对的。

详细释义: adj.天主教的；  n.天主教徒
英文释义: connected with all Christians or the whole Christian Church; including many or most things
例句: The new couple hold their wedding at a Catholic church.
例句释义: 这对新婚夫妇在天主教堂举办了他们的婚礼。

英文释义: to an extreme degree
例句: Wow, his mouth is extremely big!
例句释义: 哇塞，他的嘴太大了！

英文释义: how large, important, serious, etc. something is
例句: The extent of my property is marked by a fence.
例句释义: 围栏以内都是我的财产范围。

详细释义: n. 零件；  adj. 组成的
英文释义: one of several parts of which something is made
例句: These are the components of a car.
例句释义: 这些是一辆车的零部件。

英文释义: a combination of things that you need to make something, often sold as a powder to which you add water, etc.
例句: The cookbook tells you to mix all of these up.
例句释义: 菜谱让你把这些都混合起来。

详细释义: adj.缓慢的；  adv.缓慢地；  v.（使）慢下来，（使）减速
英文释义: not moving, acting or done quickly; taking a long time; not fast
例句: The snail moved on the ground at a slow pace.
例句释义: 蜗牛以很缓慢的速度在地上爬行。

英文释义: to compare two things in order to show the differences between them; to show a clear difference when close together or when compared
例句: In chess, the contrast between black and white is easy to see.
例句释义: 在国际象棋里，黑白两棋的差异显而易见。

详细释义: n.地带，空间，地区，区域，范围
英文释义: one of the sections in a city or town that is used for a particular purpose
例句: Our school is in this zone.
例句释义: 我们学校在这个区域。

英文释义: to stop sleeping; to make somebody stop sleeping
例句: My mum waked me up with her rude manner.
例句释义: 妈妈粗鲁地叫我起床。

英文释义: a place where planes land and take off
例句: The plane landed at the airport.
例句释义: 飞机降落在机场。

详细释义: adj. 褐色的，棕色的；  n. 褐色，棕色
英文释义: having the colour of earth or coffee
例句: Her hair is brown, whereas her friend's is black.
例句释义: 她的头发是棕色的，然而她朋友的头发是黑色的。

英文释义: a piece of clothing for the upper body that has sleeves and usually a collar and buttons down the front
例句: He always has to wear a shirt and tie to work.
例句释义: 他总是穿衬衫打领带去工作。

详细释义: n.飞行员；  adj.试验性的；  v.给……领航
英文释义: a person who operates the controls of an aircraft, especially as a job
例句: He dreamed of being a pilot since he was a little boy.
例句释义: 他从小就梦想成为一名飞行员。

英文释义: to tell somebody about something, especially something dangerous or unpleasant that is likely to happen, so that they can avoid it; to strongly advise somebody to do or not to do something in order to avoid danger or punishment
例句: The sign warned the bone about the danger of being eaten.
例句释义: 这个标牌警告骨头有被吃掉的危险。

英文释义: as the end result of a succession or process
例句: Ultimately, he decided to go to the university close to his home.
例句释义: 最终，他决定去离家近的那所大学。

英文释义: a small animal with soft fur that people often keep as a pet. Cats catch and kill birds and mice.
例句: I prefer dogs, but this cat is so cute!
例句释义: 我更喜欢狗，但是这只猫真可爱！

详细释义: n.贡献；捐款，捐赠；投稿稿件
英文释义: something that is given to help a person, a cause, etc.
例句: Thanks to all of you for making a contribution to our charity.
例句释义: 感谢各位对我们慈善机构的捐赠。

英文释义: the number of things or people that a container or space can hold
例句: The capacity of this cup is 2 liters.
例句释义: 这个杯子的容量是两升。

英文释义: the reflexive form of we; used when you and another person or other people together cause and are affected by an action; used to emphasize we or us; sometimes used instead of these words
例句: We took this picture of ourselves.
例句释义: 我们给自己拍了这张照片。

英文释义: a large area of land, usually in the country, that is owned by one person or family; an area of land with a lot of houses or factories of the same type on it; all the money and property that a person owns, especially everything that is left when they die
例句: My estate includes my house and part of the forest.
例句释义: 我的地产包括我的房子和这片森林的一部分。

详细释义: vt.给……领路；给……做导游，带领；  n.导游
英文释义: to direct or influence somebody’s behaviour; to help somebody to move in a particular direction; to move something in a particular direction
例句: I am blind, but my dog can guide me home.
例句释义: 虽然我失明了，但是我的狗狗可以领着我回家。

英文释义: the conditions and facts that are connected with and affect a situation, an event or an action
例句: Success depends on many different circumstances.
例句释义: 成功取决于许多不同的条件。

英文释义: small soft white pieces (called flakes ) of frozen water that fall from the sky in cold weather; this substance when it is lying on the ground
例句: Children are playing in the snow.
例句释义: 孩子们正在雪地里玩。

英文释义: a person whose job is concerned with politics, especially as an elected member of parliament, etc.
例句: The female politician is giving an election speech.
例句释义: 女政治家正为竞选做演讲。

英文释义: to take (something that does not belong to you) in a way that is wrong or illegal; to move secretly and quietly so that other people do not notice you
例句: The thief is trying to steal his wallet.
例句释义: 小偷正试图偷他的钱包。

英文释义: to follow or chase somebody/something, especially in order to catch them
例句: The police were pursuing the two thieves who had stolen a woman's purse.
例句释义: 警察正在追赶两个小偷，他们偷了一个女人的钱包。

英文释义: to slide a short distance by accident so that you fall or nearly fall
例句: He slipped on the wet floor and fell.
例句释义: 他在湿地板上滑倒了。

英文释义: the number, amount, rate of something, expressed as if it is part of a total which is 100; a part or share of a whole; a share of the profits of something
例句: The percentage of the green part is 60 percent.
例句释义: 绿色部分的百分比占到了60%。

英文释义: the flesh of an animal used as food
例句: Vegetables are OK, but I prefer eating meats.
例句释义: 蔬菜是不错，但是我还是更喜欢吃肉。

详细释义: adj. 有趣的，好玩的；  n. 反常的怪事
英文释义: making you laugh; amusing
例句: It was so funny that he cried with laughter.
例句释义: 这太好笑了，他都笑出眼泪了。

详细释义: pron.两者都不；  conj.既不；  adj.两者都不的；  adv.既不……也不……
英文释义: not one nor the other of two things or people
例句: He tasted both dishes and decided neither was delicious.
例句释义: 他两盘菜都尝了尝，觉得两个都不好吃。

详细释义: n.泥土；国土；  vt.弄脏；污损
英文释义: the top layer of the earth in which plants, trees, etc. grow
例句: He held some soil in his hands.
例句释义: 他手里捧着一些泥土。

英文释义: medical treatment of injuries or diseases that involves cutting open a person’s body and often removing or replacing some parts; the branch of medicine connected with this treatment
例句: The surgeons are performing surgery on a patient.
例句释义: 外科医生们正在给病人做手术。

详细释义: adj.正确的；恰当的；  v.改正；矫正；批改
英文释义: accurate or true, without any mistakes
例句: Only one in four people know the correct answer to the question.
例句释义: 只有四分之一的人知道这个问题的正确答案。

英文释义: connected with Jews or Judaism; believing in and practising Judaism
例句: Both Marx and Einstein were Jewish.
例句释义: 马克思和爱因斯坦都是犹太人。

详细释义: n.责备，过失；  v.责备，把……归咎于
英文释义: responsibility for doing something badly or wrongly; saying that somebody is responsible for something
例句: I always get all the blame, but I never do anything wrong.
例句释义: 我总是受到所有的责备，但我从没做错过任何事。

详细释义: v.估价，估计；  n.估价，估计
英文释义: a judgement that you make without having the exact details or figures about the size, amount, cost, etc. of something; a statement of how much a piece of work will probably cost
例句: The worker estimates the cost of the repairs.
例句释义: 这个工人估算了一下维修的花费。

详细释义: adj.预期的，到期的；适当的，充分的；  adv.直接地，确切地；  n.应有的权利，应得到的东西
英文释义: owed something; deserving something
例句: The holiday is due tomorrow so the student is busy.
例句释义: 放假截止到明天，因此这位学生很忙碌。

英文释义: the ball used in this game of basketball
例句: Let's play basketball sometime.
例句释义: 让我们找个机会一起打篮球吧。

英文释义: a game played over a large area of ground using specially shaped sticks to hit a small hard ball (a golf ball) into a series of 9 or 18 holes, using as few strokes as possible
例句: I spend my morning playing golf.
例句释义: 早上我在打高尔夫球。

英文释义: to carefully examine the facts of a situation, an event, a crime, etc. to find out the truth about it or how it happened; to try to find out information about somebody’s character, activities, etc.; to find out information and facts about a subject or problem by study or research
例句: He's investigating the footprints, searching for clues to help solve the case.
例句释义: 他正在研究脚印，寻找线索来帮助破案。

英文释义: (often in compounds) very enthusiastic or excited about something; liking somebody very much; in love with somebody
例句: The fan went crazy when he saw the actor.
例句释义: 当这个影迷看到那个演员时，他变得疯狂起来。

英文释义: in a way that is large or important enough to be noticed or have an effect
例句: The company's profits have significantly increased in the last two years.
例句释义: 这家公司的利润在过去两年里显著增加了。

详细释义: vt.用链条拴住；束缚；  n.链子；项圈；连锁；一系列
英文释义: to fasten or secure with chains
例句: The dog is chained up so as not to hurt people.
例句释义: 狗狗被拴起来了，免得伤到人。

英文释义: a part of a tree that grows out from the main stem and on which leaves, flowers and fruit grow
例句: A bird is resting on the tree branch.
例句释义: 一只小鸟在树枝上休息。

详细释义: n.（保险锁等的）组合码；结合，联合
英文释义: two or more things joined or mixed together to form a single unit; the act of joining or mixing together two or more things to form a single unit
例句: A combination is a series of numbers or letters used to open a combination lock.
例句释义: 组合码是用来开密码锁的一系列数字或字母。

英文释义: many times at short intervals
例句: He went to the bathroom frequently after drinking too much water.
例句释义: 喝了太多水后，他频繁地去上厕所。

详细释义: n.总督；统治者；主管，负责人
英文释义: a person who is chosen to be in charge of the government of a state in the US
例句: Now the state governor has to sign this law.
例句释义: 现在州总督必须签署这条法律。

英文释义: the feeling of happiness that you have when something unpleasant stops or does not happen
例句: To the relief of the patient, the doctor told him everything is fine.
例句释义: 令这位病人感到安慰的是，医生告诉他一切正常。

英文释义: a person or thing that uses something
例句: Users of all ages can learn English with this app.
例句释义: 各个年龄段的用户都可以用这个应用来学英语。

英文释义: to hit somebody/something with your foot; (in sports such as football (soccer ) and rugby) to score points by kicking the ball
例句: The soccer player kicked the ball into the net. Goal!
例句释义: 这个足球运动员踢进了球，得分！

详细释义: n.（复数）礼仪，礼貌；态度，举止
英文释义: the way that somebody behaves towards other people
例句: It's bad manners to speak while you are eating.
例句释义: 一边吃饭一边说话是不礼貌的举止。

英文释义: belonging to a period of history that is thousands of years in the past; very old; having existed for a very long time; the people who lived in ancient times, especially the Egyptians, Greeks and Romans
例句: These ancient statues are over 2,000 years old.
例句释义: 这些古代雕像有2 000多年的历史。

英文释义: a complete lack of noise or sound; a situation when nobody is speaking
例句: They sat face to face in silence.
例句释义: 他们默然对坐。

详细释义: n.评价；等级，级别；额定功率
英文释义: a set of figures that show how many people watch or listen to a particular television or radio programme, used to show how popular a programme is
例句: We received an excellent rating for our customer service.
例句释义: 我们的客户服务得到了超赞的评价。

详细释义: adj.金黄色的；特别的，美好的
英文释义: having the deep yellow color of gold
例句: This is a golden egg.
例句释义: 这是一枚金蛋。

英文释义: the act or process of moving or the way something moves
例句: The slow motion clearly shows how he dodges the bullets.
例句释义: 慢动作清楚地展现了他躲过子弹的全过程。

英文释义: from or connected with Germany
例句: German cars and beer are famous products of the country.
例句释义: 德国的车和啤酒是该国著名的产品。

例句: These two babies are of different genders: male and female.
例句释义: 这两个婴儿是不同的性别：男性和女性。

英文释义: to find a way of dealing with a problem or difficult situation
例句: He helped the girl to solve the math problem.
例句释义: 他帮女孩解答了这道数学题。

英文释义: an amount of money that you pay for professional advice or services
例句: He was shocked by the huge amount of hidden fees behind such a haircut.
例句释义: 他被这个发型背后巨额的隐形费用惊呆了。

详细释义: n.风景，景观；风景画；  vt.美化……的环境
英文释义: a painting of a view of the countryside; this style of painting
例句: As I look at the beautiful landscape, I feel so calm and relaxed.
例句释义: 我看着美丽的风景，感到十分平静与放松。

英文释义: having been used before
例句: My phone is used, but I don't plan to buy a new one.
例句释义: 我的手机用旧了，但我不打算换新的。

详细释义: n.碗；（保龄球等运动使用的）木球
英文释义: a deep round dish with a wide open top, used especially for holding food or liquid
例句: The four bowls are in four different colors.
例句释义: 这四个碗分别有四种不同的颜色。

详细释义: adj.平等的；相等的；  v.比得上；  n.同等的人
英文释义: having the same rights or being treated the same as other people, without differences such as race, religion or sex being considered
例句: Today, men and women are equal in the eyes of the law.
例句释义: 如今，男女在法律面前是平等的。

英文释义: towards a place; forwards
例句: The car is going forth.
例句释义: 车在往前开。

英文释义: to put or make a frame or border around something
例句: The picture looks nice in this picture frame.
例句释义: 这幅画在这面画框里看起来很漂亮。

英文释义: happening in the usual way; showing what something is usually like
例句: She prepared a typical French meal for her friend.
例句释义: 她为她的朋友准备了一顿典型的法国餐。

英文释义: used before you mention the only thing or person about which a statement is not true
例句: Everyone was feeling upset, except for one guy.
例句释义: 除了他之外，每个人都很沮丧。

详细释义: adj.保守的；保守党的；  n.保守主义者
例句: The man has such a conservative attitude; he even despises the couple holding hands.
例句释义: 他的态度如此保守，连情侣牵手都看不惯。

详细释义: vt.消除，根除；消灭，铲除；（在比赛中）淘汰
英文释义: to remove or get rid of something/somebody
例句: This device helps me eliminate the weeds in my garden.
例句释义: 这个装置帮助我除掉花园里的杂草。

详细释义: n.主人，东道主；  v.主持，主办
英文释义: a person who invites guests to a meal, a party, etc. or who has people staying at their house
例句: The hosts had cooked food for us, so we brought some wine for them.
例句释义: 主人们为我们做了饭菜，所以我们给他们带了一些红酒。

英文释义: a building or large room for public meetings, meals, concerts, etc.
例句: The conference hall with red chairs is empty.
例句释义: 这个配有红色椅子的会堂空空荡荡的。

详细释义: v. 信任；盼望，希望；  n. 委托
英文释义: to have confidence in somebody; to believe that somebody is good, sincere, honest, etc.; to believe that something is true or correct or that you can rely on it
例句: My boss trusts me so much. I can't let him down.
例句释义: 我的老板那么信任我，我不能让他失望。

英文释义: (especially North American English) the mass of salt water that covers most of the earth’s surface
例句: Oceans are large areas of water between continents.
例句释义: 海洋是各大洲之间的大片水域。

英文释义: a line of seats in a theater, stadium, etc.
例句: There are four rows of seats.
例句释义: 这里有四排座位。

英文释义: a person, a company or a country that grows or makes food, goods or materials
例句: This country is a producer of high-quality wines.
例句释义: 这个国家出产优质葡萄酒。

英文释义: (usually used with can, could or be able to, especially in negative sentences or questions) to have enough money or time to be able to buy or to do something
例句: Finally, I can afford this car.
例句释义: 我终于买得起这辆车了。

详细释义: adv. 同时，与此同时；  n. 其间
英文释义: at or during the same time; in the meantime
例句: The turtle finishes the race; meanwhile, the rabbit is still sleeping.
例句释义: 乌龟完成了比赛，这个时候兔子还在睡觉。

英文释义: a method or system of government, especially one that has not been elected in a fair way
例句: Constantin was the ruler of the regime of the Rome Empire.
例句释义: 君士坦丁是古罗马帝国政权的统治者。

英文释义: the process or result of dividing into separate parts; the process or result of dividing something or sharing it out
例句: He finished the division of the cake.
例句释义: 他已把蛋糕分好了。

英文释义: to make somebody feel or believe something even more strongly
例句: The X-ray picture confirmed that he had broken his finger.
例句释义: X光片证实他的手指已经骨折。

详细释义: vt.修理；  n.方位确定，定位
英文释义: to make (something) whole or able to work properly again :to repair (something)
例句: He is fixing the car.
例句释义: 他在修车。

详细释义: v.呼吁，请求；申诉；对...有吸引力；  n.呼吁；吸引力；恳求； 筹款努力
英文释义: an urgent and deeply felt request for money, help or information, especially one made by a charity or by the police
例句: The animal rights group launched an appeal to stop commercial whaling.
例句释义: 动物权益保护组织呼吁停止商业捕鲸。

英文释义: a piece of special flat glass that reflects images, so that you can see yourself when you look in it
例句: The old woman is looking into the mirror.
例句释义: 这个老奶奶正在照镜子。

英文释义: one of the hard white objects inside the mouth that are used for biting and chewing
例句: Every tooth was straight and white.
例句释义: 每颗牙齿都整齐洁白。

详细释义: adj.聪明的；时髦的，衣着讲究的；  vi.难过，烦恼
英文释义: (especially North American English) intelligent
例句: The girl is so smart that she can solve very difficult math problems.
例句释义: 这个女孩很聪明，她能解很难的数学题。

英文释义: the size or measurement of something from one end to the other; the amount of time that something lasts; the distance from one end of a swimming pool to the other; the size of a horse or boat from one end to the other, when it is used to measure the distance between two horses or boats taking part in a race
例句: The ruler is 15 cm in length.
例句释义: 这把尺子长15厘米。

英文释义: to a complete degree or to the full or entire extent (`whole' is often used informally for `wholly')
例句: The audience consists entirely of children.
例句释义: 观众全部都是小孩子。

英文释义: to need or depend on somebody/something
例句: I often rely on ready-made food, because I am so bad at cooking!
例句释义: 我经常依赖于现成的食物，因为我不擅长做饭！

英文释义: a subject that you talk, write or learn about
例句: He wrote down a topic for us to discuss.
例句释义: 他写下一个主题供我们讨论。

英文释义: to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about somebody/something
例句: She is complaining about the wrong product sent by the seller.
例句释义: 她抱怨商家给她发错了货。

详细释义: adj. 易变的，可变的；  n. 变量，可变物
英文释义: often changing; likely to change; able to be changed
例句: You can't predict the weather here―it's too variable.
例句释义: 你不能预测这里的天气，它实在是太多变了。

详细释义: n. 电话（机）；  v. 打电话
英文释义: a system for talking to somebody else over long distances, using wires or radio; a machine used for this; the part of the telephone that you hold in your hand and speak into
例句: There's a telephone call for you.
例句释义: 有人打电话找你。

英文释义: the way you notice things, especially with the senses; the ability to understand the true nature of something; an idea, a belief or an image you have as a result of how you see or understand something
例句: Perception is the reflection of intelligence.
例句释义: 洞察力是智力的体现。

英文释义: if you are attracted by something, it interests you and makes you want it; if you are attracted by somebody, you like or admire them; to make somebody/something come somewhere or take part in something; to make people have a particular reaction
例句: This dog attracts many people to the fruit stall.
例句释义: 这只狗吸引了很多人来这个水果摊。

英文释义: the feeling that you are certain about something
例句: The student raised her hand with confidence to answer the question.
例句释义: 这个学生自信地举起手回答问题。

英文释义: a room for sleeping in
例句: There is a double bed and a dresser in the bedroom.
例句释义: 卧室里有一张双人床和一个梳妆台。

详细释义: n. 秘密；  adj. 秘密的，机密的
英文释义: something that is known about by only a few people and not told to others
例句: The little girl is telling her mother a secret.
例句释义: 这个小女孩正在告诉她的妈妈一个小秘密。

英文释义: a sum of money that somebody owes; the situation of owing money, especially when you cannot pay
例句: The man is burdened with the housing debt.
例句释义: 这个男人背负着房债。

英文释义: existing only in small numbers and therefore valuable or interesting
例句: He likes eating rare steak, which is bloody and red in the middle.
例句释义: 他喜欢吃那种中间呈血红色的半熟牛排。

英文释义: a container for holding a liquid or gas; the contents of a tank or the amount it will hold
例句: The train carried large tanks of oil.
例句释义: 这列火车运载着大罐的石油。

详细释义: n.护士；  v.护理，照顾；哺乳
英文释义: a person who is trained to care for sick or injured people and who usually works in a hospital or doctor's office
例句: The nurse is looking after her patient.
例句释义: 护士正在照顾病人。

英文释义: the reporting of news and sport in newspapers and on the radio and television; the range or quality of information that is included in a book or course of study, on television, etc.
例句: All of the media coverage is just about the lottery winner.
例句释义: 所有的新闻报道都是关于那个中彩票的人的。

英文释义: the action of opposing something that you disapprove or disagree with
例句: They both have shown their opposition to the other direction.
例句释义: 他们同时表示了对去往另一个方向的反对。

英文释义: to one side; out of the way
例句: I pushed the hamburger aside because I'm on a diet.
例句释义: 我把汉堡推到了一边，因为我正在节食。

英文释义: used in negative sentences and in questions instead of somewhere
例句: In the game, he could point anywhere on the globe.
例句释义: 在这个游戏中，他可能会指到地球仪上的任何地方。

详细释义: n. 联系；束缚物，联结物；  vi. 团结一致
英文释义: a uniting or binding element or force
例句: Everyone has a bond with another person in this web.
例句释义: 在这张网络中，每个人都与其他人有关系。

英文释义: a state of feeling or being happy or satisfied
例句: The little girl takes pleasure in eating cakes.
例句释义: 这个小女孩从吃蛋糕中获得快乐。

详细释义: n.主人；  adj.精通的；主要的；  v.掌握，精通
英文释义: the male owner of a dog
例句: The dog and its master are close to each other.
例句释义: 这条狗和它的主人很亲密。

英文释义: a period of time that is associated with a particular quality, event, person, etc.
例句: These kinds of costumes were quite prevalent in the Victorian era.
例句释义: 这些装束在维多利亚时代非常流行。

英文释义: something that is you need or want
例句: This company's requirements for their employees are unusual.
例句释义: 这家公司对雇员的要求不同寻常。

详细释义: n.娱乐，乐趣；  adj.有趣的，供娱乐使用的；  vi.开玩笑，嬉戏
英文释义: amusing or enjoyable
例句: They're all having fun at the party.
例句释义: 他们在派对上玩得很开心。

英文释义: a belief that something will happen because it is likely
例句: My parents have high expectations for me.
例句释义: 我的父母对我抱有很高的期望。

英文释义: one of the parts of the body of a bird, insect or bat that it uses for flying
例句: Mommy, I want the doll with the butterfly wings!
例句释义: 妈妈，我想要那个有蝴蝶翅膀的洋娃娃！

详细释义: adj.分开的；独立的；  v.使分开；分割；分配，划分
英文释义: to divide into different parts or groups; to divide things into different parts or groups;  to move apart; to make people or things move apart; to be between two people, areas, countries, etc. so that they are not touching or connected; to stop living together as a couple with your husband, wife or partner
例句: The couple face to separate directions.
例句释义: 这对夫妻朝着不同的方向。

详细释义: adv.有点儿，稍微；  pron.某物；一些
英文释义: to indicate that something is the case to a limited extent or degree.
例句: I'm somewhat bored with this problem.
例句释义: 我对这个问题有点厌烦了。

英文释义: to make a liquid or other substance flow from a container in a continuous stream, especially by holding the container at an angle; (of liquid, smoke, light, etc.) to flow quickly in a continuous stream; to serve a drink by letting it flow from a container into a cup or glass
例句: I poured a glass of milk.
例句释义: 我倒了一杯牛奶。

英文释义: to mix something by making circular movements in it with a spoon or similar object
例句: The lady is stirring the coffee.
例句释义: 这位女士正在搅拌咖啡。

英文释义: an opinion or decision that is based on careful thoughts
例句: The court will make fair judgments.
例句释义: 法院会做出公平的判决。

英文释义: an alcoholic drink made from malt and flavoured with hops. There are many types of beer.; a glass, bottle or can of beer
例句: Two glasses of beer are on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上有两杯啤酒。

英文释义: books are ones that you look at when you need specific information or facts about a subject
例句: The student working on his paper is taking references from books.
例句释义: 这个写论文的学生正在翻书作为参考。

详细释义: v. 撕裂，撕碎；  n. 眼泪
英文释义: to damage something by pulling it apart or into pieces or by cutting it on something sharp; to become damaged in this way
例句: The hands tear the wall wide open.
例句释义: 一双手撕裂了这面墙。

英文释义: a feeling of being uncertain about something or not believing something
例句: I really doubt whether aliens exist.
例句释义: 我很怀疑外星人是否真的存在。

英文释义: to agree to give somebody what they ask for, especially formal or legal permission to do something
例句: They finally granted us permission to take out the loan.
例句释义: 最终，他们同意我们贷款。

英文释义: in a serious way
例句: He took training very seriously.
例句释义: 他对待训练非常认真。

英文释义: a senior member of the government who is in charge of a government department or a branch of one
例句: These two environment ministers are shaking hands at an official meeting.
例句释义: 两位环境部部长在一场正式会议上握手。

英文释义: completely or entirely
例句: The moon is totally blocking the sun's light.
例句释义: 月球完全阻挡了射到地面的阳光。

英文释义: a person who is admired for great or brave acts or fine qualities
例句: He was praised as a hero for saving the child from the river.
例句释义: 他从河里救出了孩子，被大家称赞为英雄。

英文释义: connected with industry; used by industries; having many industries
例句: There are many factories in this industrial zone.
例句释义: 这个工业园区内有很多工厂。

英文释义: a white or gray mass in the sky that is made of many very small drops of water
例句: Don't you think the cloud looks like a heart?
例句释义: 你不觉得这朵云看起来像一颗心吗？

详细释义: v.伸展，延伸，张开；  n.伸展，张开
英文释义: to make something longer, wider or looser, for example by pulling it; to become longer, etc. in this; (of cloth) to become bigger or longer when you pull it and return to its original shape when you stop; to put your arms or legs out straight and contract your muscles; to put out an arm or a leg in order to reach something;
例句: The cat is stretching its body.
例句释义: 猫咪在舒展它的身体。

英文释义: a person, a team, an animal, etc. that wins something;  a thing or person that is successful or likely to be successful; a goal or point that causes a team or a person to win a game
例句: Hell yeah, I'm the winner!
例句释义: 没错，我就是获胜者！

英文释义: the amount of sound that is produced by a television, radio, etc.
例句: I turned the volume up to hear the radio.
例句释义: 我把收音机音量调大来听广播。

英文释义: a small object produced by a plant from which a new plant can grow
例句: The bowl is filled with pumpkin seeds.
例句释义: 碗里装满了南瓜种子。

详细释义: adj. 感到惊讶的，惊喜的
例句: Jenna was very surprised!
例句释义: 珍娜感到很惊喜！

详细释义: n.时髦，风尚；  vt.制作，塑造
英文释义: a popular style of clothes, hair, etc. at a particular time or place; the state of being popular; a popular way of behaving, doing an activity, etc.; the business of making or selling clothes in new and different styles
例句: He is trying to keep up with the latest fashion trend.
例句释义: 他在努力追随最新的时尚潮流。

英文释义: a powder made from dried berries (called peppercorns ), used to give a hot flavour to food
例句: The cook used many different kinds of peppers in his recipe.
例句释义: 这个厨师在他的食谱里用了很多不同种类的胡椒。

详细释义: adj.忙碌的，正被占用的；  v.使忙于
英文释义: having a lot to do; perhaps not free to do something else because you are working on something
例句: I'm too busy to get anything useful done!
例句释义: 我忙得都没时间做正事了！

英文释义: action taken to improve or help a situation
例句: The man's intervention helped the couple reconcile with each other.
例句释义: 通过他的调解，这对夫妻和好如初了。

英文释义: to make a version of (something) that is exactly or almost exactly like the original; to make a copy or duplicate of (something)
例句: He is copying the picture from the book.
例句释义: 他正在临摹这本书上的图画。

详细释义: n.小费；尖端；诀窍，建议；  v.给小费
英文释义: a small amount of extra money that you give to somebody, for example somebody who serves you in a restaurant
例句: He gave the porter a 5-dollar tip.
例句释义: 他给了那名行李员五美元作为小费。

详细释义: adj. 便宜的；低劣的，不值钱的
英文释义: costing little money or less money than you expected
例句: You won't find cheaper carrots than this anywhere!
例句释义: 你再也找不到比这更便宜的胡萝卜了！

详细释义: v.瞄准；力求达到，力争做到；  n.目标；对准
英文释义: to point or direct a weapon, a shot, a kick, etc. at somebody/something
例句: The man aims at the center of the target.
例句释义: 这位男士瞄准了靶子的中心。

英文释义: to mention something as a reason or an example, or in order to support what you are saying
例句: He cited a sentence said by a famous writer to start his speech.
例句释义: 他在演讲开头引用了一位著名作家说过的一句话。

英文释义: the general health, happiness and safety of a person, an animal or a group
例句: The organization aims to improve the welfare of animals.
例句释义: 这个组织旨在提升动物福利。

详细释义: n.蔬菜；  adj.蔬菜的，植物的
英文释义: a plant or plant part that is eaten as food
例句: These are just a few of the fresh, ripe vegetables in my garden.
例句释义: 这只是我花园里一部分新鲜成熟的蔬菜。

详细释义: adj. 灰色的；暗淡的；  n. 灰色，暗淡
英文释义: having a color between black and white; having a color that is like the color of smoke; dull; full of clouds
例句: My grandmother has a full head of gray hair.
例句释义: 我奶奶满头银发。

英文释义: food that is prepared in a particular way
例句: Add a slice of lemon to flavor the dish.
例句释义: 加上一片柠檬为这道菜肴调味。

英文释义: an area of sand or small stones (called shingle), beside the sea or a lake
例句: We spent a wonderful day at the beach.
例句释义: 我们在海滩上度过了美妙的一天。

英文释义: an addition or change that makes something better or more valuable
例句: I hope our sales show some improvement soon.
例句释义: 我希望我们的销售很快会有所改善。

英文释义: in, to or at every place; all places
例句: The world is so big. I just want to go everywhere.
例句释义: 世界那么大，我想到处去看看。

详细释义: n. 开口；孔；开始；开幕；职位空缺
英文释义: a space or hole that somebody/something can pass through
例句: We can escape the cave through this opening.
例句释义: 我们可以从这个开口逃出洞穴。

详细释义: n.罩衫，工装服；  adj.全面的，全部的

例句: In old factory photos, all the steel workers wore overalls.

英文释义: to separate or make something separate into parts; to separate something into parts and give a share to each of a number of different people, etc.; to use different parts of your time, energy, etc. for different activities, etc.; to separate two people or things
例句: The apple is divided into two equal parts.
例句释义: 这个苹果被平分成了两半。

英文释义: happening at the beginning; first
