例句释义: 这个单词的首字母是“a”。

详细释义: adj.非常严重的，糟糕的；病得很重的，心情很糟的
英文释义: very serious or very unpleasant
例句: Thousands of eggs were destroyed in the terrible traffic accident.
例句释义: 在这场糟糕的车祸中，几千个蛋碎了一地。

英文释义: to disagree strongly with somebody’s plan, policy, etc. and try to change it or prevent it from succeeding
例句: The boy opposes his father's smoking and tells him to stop.
例句释义: 男孩反对父亲吸烟，告诉他不要抽了。

详细释义: adj.当代的，现代的；同时代的；  n.同龄人，同时代的人
英文释义: belonging to the same time
例句: They are two popular contemporary singers of the 21st century.
例句释义: 他们是21世纪很受欢迎的两位当代歌手。

详细释义: n. 路线；途径；固定路线
英文释义: a way that you follow to get from one place to another; a fixed way along which a bus, train, etc. regularly travels or goods are regularly sent
例句: This blue line is the quickest route to get there.
例句释义: 这条蓝色的线是到那儿最快的路线。

英文释义: many in number; involving many different people or things
例句: Which of our multiple colors do you prefer?
例句释义: 我们有很多种颜色，你喜欢哪一个？

详细释义: adj.必不可少的，极其重要的；  n.必需品
英文释义: completely necessary; extremely important in a particular situation or for a particular activity
例句: Water, food and air are essential to life.
例句释义: 水、食物和空气对于生命而言是必不可少的。

详细释义: n. 社团；联盟；  v. 使……结盟，与……联合
英文释义: a group of sports teams who all play each other to earn points and find which team is best
例句: You are so good! You should join our soccer league!
例句释义: 你很厉害！你应该加入我们的足球社团！

详细释义: n.罪犯；  adj.犯罪的，犯法的
英文释义: a person who commits a crime
例句: The convicted criminal is having his mug shot taken.
例句释义: 那个已定罪的罪犯正在拍面部照片。

英文释义: giving attention or thought to what you are doing so that you avoid hurting yourself, damaging something or doing something wrong
例句: Pay careful attention to each piece so you don't choose the wrong one.
例句释义: 每一块拼图都要仔细观察，这样你就不会选错。

详细释义: n.果心，核；核心，要点；  v.去核
英文释义: the hard central part of a fruit such as an apple, that contains the seeds
例句: My mom gives me apples with the cores cut out.
例句释义: 妈妈把切掉了果核的苹果给我。

详细释义: adj.较高的，上面的；  n.鞋面
英文释义: at or near the top of something; located above something else, especially something of the same type or the other of a pair
例句: The upper floor is the working area, while the lower floor is the reception.
例句释义: 楼上是办公区域，楼下是接待处。

详细释义: v.冲，奔；匆忙做；  n.冲，急速行进；（交通）繁忙时段
英文释义: to move or do something very quickly or in a way that shows you are in a hurry
例句: I'll have to rush to the canteen; otherwise there'll be nothing left.
例句释义: 我得冲向食堂，不然什么吃的都没有了。

英文释义: used to say that something cannot be avoided
例句: The biggest diamond in the shop necessarily commands the highest price.
例句释义: 这家店里最大的这颗钻石必定售价最贵。

英文释义: feeling that you would like to sleep or rest; needing rest
例句: He was extremely tired because he had worked all night.
例句释义: 他非常疲惫，因为他工作了一个通宵。

详细释义: vt.雇用；使忙于，使从事；应用
英文释义: to give somebody a job to do for payment
例句: She employed a babysitter to look after her children.
例句释义: 她雇了个保姆来照顾她的孩子。

英文释义: a period of time when you are not at work or school
例句: People are enjoying their holiday from work.
例句释义: 人们享受着他们的假日。

英文释义: extremely large in area, size, amount, etc.
例句: This vast desert looks impossible to pass.
例句释义: 这片辽阔的沙漠看上去不可能穿越。

英文释义: a formal statement of an opinion agreed on by a committee or a council, especially by means of a vote; the act of solving or settling a problem, disagreement, etc.; the quality of being resolute or determined; a firm decision to do or not to do something; the power of a computer screen, printer, etc. to give a clear image, depending on the size of the dots that make up the image
例句: She made a resolution to read all of these English novels in just one week.
例句释义: 她下定决心要在一周内读完所有这些英文小说。

详细释义: n.家庭；  adj.家庭的，一家的
英文释义: all the people living together in a house or flat/apartment
例句: I grew up in a large household.
例句释义: 我生长在一个大家庭中。

英文释义: a medical procedure used to end a pregnancy and cause the death of the fetus
例句: She wants an abortion because she doesn’t want the baby.
例句释义: 她想堕胎，因为她不想要宝宝。

详细释义: adv.分离地，分开地；  adj.分隔的，拆开的，撇开的
英文释义: separated by a distance, of space or time; not together; separate or separately
例句: They set one man apart from the rest.
例句释义: 他们把一个人从人群里分离出来了。

详细释义: n.目击者；  v.目击，亲眼看见
英文释义: a person who sees something happen and is able to describe it to other people
例句: The little girl is the only witness of the accident.
例句释义: 小女孩是这场事故的唯一目击者。

详细释义: n.比赛；婚姻，配偶；  v.（使）相配
英文释义: a contest between two or more players or teams
例句: No. 10 is a real fan-favorite who works tirelessly every match.
例句释义: 10号球员是球迷的最爱，每场比赛他都不知疲倦地踢球。

英文释义: in a way that almost does not happen or exist
例句: I could barely hear what he was saying.
例句释义: 我几乎听不见他在说什么。

英文释义: a part of an area of activity, especially of a country’s economy
例句: This country's economy has three different sectors: manufacturing, agriculture, and services.
例句释义: 这个国家的经济有三个不同的部分：制造业、农业和服务业。

详细释义: n. 代表；  adj. 典型的，有代表性的
英文释义: a person who has been chosen to speak or vote for somebody else or on behalf of a group
例句: They chose her as their representative to speak for them.
例句释义: 他们选她作为代表为他们发声。

详细释义: prep. 在……下方；  adv. 在下方
英文释义: in or to a lower position than somebody/something; under somebody/something
例句: Most of the iceberg is beneath the surface.
例句释义: 冰山的大部分在海面之下。

英文释义: next to or at the side of somebody/something
例句: The loyal dog is lying beside her master.
例句释义: 这只忠诚的狗正趴在主人旁边。

英文释义: something that happens, especially something unusual or unpleasant
例句: The headmaster is speaking to the two boys about the classroom incident.
例句释义: 校长正在和这两个男孩谈论教室事件。

英文释义: not very great in amount or extent
例句: On this diet, you can only eat a very limited amount of food.
例句释义: 在这项饮食计划中，你只能吃一点点东西。

英文释义: feeling pleased and satisfied about something that you own or have done, or are connected with
例句: He's proud of himself because everyone thinks he did a great job!
例句释义: 他为自己感到骄傲，因为大家都觉得他很棒！

详细释义: v.流动；来自……的结果；  n.流动
英文释义: (of liquid, gas or electricity) to move steadily and continuously in one direction; (of people or things) to move or pass continuously from one place or person to another, especially in large numbers or amounts
例句: The river is flowing through the rocks.
例句释义: 河水在岩石间流动。

详细释义: n.教职工，全体教员；院系；能力
英文释义: all the teachers of a particular university or college
例句: The official website of the Law School shows a profile for each faculty.
例句释义: 法学院的官方网站上列有学院全体教师的个人简介。

详细释义: n.浪费；废物；  vt.浪费；消耗；  adj.无用的；废弃的
英文释义: the act of using something in a careless or unnecessary way, causing it to be lost or destroyed
例句: What a waste to throw the food away!
例句释义: 把这些食物扔掉真是太浪费了！

英文释义: used meaning ‘only’ or ‘simply’ to emphasize a fact or something that you are saying
例句: At first he was scared of it, but later he found it was merely a cat.
例句释义: 起初他很害怕，但后来他发现那只是一只猫。

详细释义: n.大量，一堆；群众；  v.聚集
英文释义: a large amount or quantity of something; a large number or amount of something
例句: A mass of people are waiting.
例句释义: 一大群人在等待。

英文释义: to give special importance to (something); to place emphasis on (something)
例句: I want to emphasize the importance of teamwork.
例句释义: 我想强调团队合作的重要性。

英文释义: a scientific test that is done in order to study what happens and to gain new knowledge
例句: There are many scientists doing experiments to find a cure.
例句释义: 为了找到治愈该病的方法，许多科学家在进行实验。

英文释义: a way of emphasizing that something is true and that there is no doubt about it
例句: The sun rises definitely from the east.
例句释义: 太阳毫无疑问是从东方升起。

英文释义: a device that is designed to explode in order to injure or kill people or to damage or destroy property
例句: This bomb will explode any minute!
例句释义: 这个炸弹随时都会爆炸！

详细释义: adj.巨大的；极大的，极大量的；庞大的
英文释义: very great in size or amount
例句: The little girl was shocked by the enormous dog.
例句释义: 小女孩被这只巨大的泰迪犬震惊了。

英文释义: the quality of somebody’s voice, especially expressing a particular emotion
例句: The little boy learned to use a more polite tone when speaking to his mother.
例句释义: 这个小男孩学会用更礼貌的语气和母亲说话。

英文释义: a person who understands and respects other people’s opinions and behaviour, especially when they are different from their own; a person who supports political, social and religious change
例句: The new king is a liberal who accepts different behaviors and opinions.
例句释义: 新国王是一位开明的人，可以接受不同的行为和观念。

英文释义: very large and heavy
例句: The massive statue is a very popular tourist attraction in Sichuan Province.
例句释义: 这座巨大的雕像是四川有名的旅游景点。

详细释义: n.工程师；技师；火车司机；  vt.设计；建造
英文释义: a person whose job involves designing and building engines, machines, roads, bridges, etc.; a person who is trained to repair machines and electrical equipment
例句: The two engineers are discussing their new building plans.
例句释义: 这两个工程师正在讨论新的建筑计划。

英文释义: one of the round objects under a car, bicycle, bus, etc. that turns when it moves
例句: The wheels of these bicycles are the same size.
例句释义: 这些自行车的轮子大小相同。

详细释义: n. 衰退；  v. 【语】使发生词尾变化，使变格
英文释义: to become smaller, fewer, weaker, etc.
例句: The world economy is on the decline.
例句释义: 世界经济日趋低迷。

英文释义: to use money to earn more money; to use your money to purchase stock in a company, to buy property, etc., in order to make future profit
例句: He invests all his money in property.
例句释义: 他将他的钱都投资到了房地产。

英文释义: a set of wires, covered in plastic or rubber, that carries electricity, telephone signals, etc.; thick strong metal rope used on ships, for supporting bridges, etc.
例句: Many birds are standing on the cables for a rest.
例句释义: 许多小鸟正停在电缆上休息。

英文释义: move, look, or point in a certain direction
例句: He is running towards his goal.
例句释义: 他正向着他的目标奔去。

英文释义: to leave (something) without covering or protection
例句: Some cement fell from the wall, leaving the bricks exposed.
例句释义: 墙上的水泥掉下来后，砖块露了出来。

英文释义: of or relating to the country and the people who live there instead of the city
例句: Rural areas are so much prettier than cities.
例句释义: 乡村地区比城市美多了。

详细释义: abbr.艾滋病，获得性免疫缺陷综合征
例句: The red ribbon is the symbol for the solidarity of people living with AIDS.
例句释义: 这条红丝带象征着艾滋病患者的团结一致。

详细释义: adj.狭窄的；  n.海峡；  v.变窄
英文释义: measuring a short distance from one side to the other, especially in relation to length
例句: The fat man is wondering how to pass through the narrow road.
例句释义: 那个胖子正在纠结如何才能走过那条窄巷。

英文释义: a soft substance or thick liquid used on your skin to protect it or make it feel soft; a similar substance used for cleaning things
例句: She always applies face cream after showering.
例句释义: 她洗完澡后总会涂面霜。

英文释义: a person who works in an office, working for another person, dealing with letters and telephone calls, typing, keeping records, arranging meetings with people, etc.
例句: The secretary takes phone calls, arranges meetings and takes care of general affairs.
例句释义: 这个秘书负责接听电话、安排会议和处理一般性事务。

英文释义: a place in a wall or a fence that has a movable part which can be opened or closed like a door
例句: The gate with beautiful patterns is made of iron.
例句释义: 这道有着美丽花纹的大门是铁制的。

详细释义: adj. 结实的；坚固的；固体的；  n. 固体
英文释义: strong and made well
例句: This safe is very solid!
例句释义: 这个保险箱非常结实！

英文释义: an area of land that is higher than the land around it, but not as high as a mountain
例句: There is a red house on the top of that green hill.
例句释义: 在那绿色小山的山顶上有一所红房子。

英文释义: a sound, especially when it is loud, unpleasant or disturbing; extra electrical or electronic signals that are not part of the signal that is being broadcast or transmitted and which may damage it; information that is not wanted and that can make it difficult for the important or useful information to be seen clearly
例句: The machines outside are making a loud noise.
例句释义: 外面的机器发出了巨大的噪声。

英文释义: an area of ground covered with grass
例句: It feels great to lie down on the grass.
例句释义: 躺在草地上感觉真好。

英文释义: used to say that a particular situation or fact makes you sad or disappointed, or gets you into a difficult position
例句: My mom bought me an ice cream, but unfortunately I dropped it.
例句释义: 我妈给我买了个冰淇淋，不幸的是，我把它掉地上了。

详细释义: n. 帽子（一般指有边的）
英文释义: a covering made to fit the head, often with a brim (= a flat edge that sticks out), and worn out of doors a straw/w
例句: She wears a black hat.
例句释义: 她戴着一顶黑色的帽子。

英文释义: a law or a set of laws passed by a parliament; the process of making and passing laws
例句: The Congress voted in favor of the new legislation.
例句释义: 国会投票赞成新的立法。

英文释义: to achieve something that you have been trying to do or get; to have the result or effect that was intended; to be successful in your job, earning money, power, respect, etc.
例句: I succeeded in shooting three arrows in the center of the target.
例句释义: 我成功地将三支箭都射中了靶心。

英文释义: to show that a day or an event is important by doing something special on it
例句: The graduates are celebrating by throwing their hats up in the air.
例句释义: 毕业生们把帽子扔向天空来庆祝毕业。

详细释义: n. 成绩，成就；实现，完成
英文释义: a thing that somebody has done successfully, especially using their own effort and skill
例句: He is known for his great achievements in the sport of tennis.
例句释义: 他在网球运动上的成就令人瞩目。

英文释义: to say that somebody has done something wrong or is guilty of something
例句: They accused each other of being wrong.
例句释义: 他们相互指责对方做错了。

英文释义: that can help you to do or achieve what you want; good; of the right standard
例句: A Swiss Army knife contains many different useful tools.
例句释义: 一把瑞士军刀有许多不同且实用的工具。

英文释义: to refuse to accept or consider something; to refuse to love, care for, or give attention to (someone)
例句: She directly rejected marrying him.
例句释义: 她直接拒绝嫁给他。

英文释义: a special ability that allows someone to do something well;  people or a person with a natural ability to do something well
例句: This baby showed great talent as he was playing the piano.
例句释义: 这个宝宝弹钢琴的时候展现出超强的天赋。

详细释义: v.品尝，尝起来；品鉴；  n.味道；鉴赏力
英文释义: to test the flavour of something by eating or drinking a small amount of it
例句: She always tastes the soup before serving it to others.
例句释义: 她上汤之前总要先尝一尝。

英文释义: a typical feature or quality that something/somebody has
例句: Spiciness is a characteristic of Sichuan cuisine.
例句释义: 辣，是川菜的一大特色。

英文释义: the white liquid produced by cows, goats and some other animals as food for their young and used as a drink by humans
例句: Drinking one glass of milk each day is good for your bones.
例句释义: 每天喝一杯牛奶有益于你的骨骼。

英文释义: to get away from a place where you have been kept as a prisoner or not allowed to leave; to get away from an unpleasant or dangerous situation; to avoid something unpleasant or dangerous;
例句: The mooncake managed to escape from the rabbit.
例句释义: 月饼逃脱了月兔的追赶。

详细释义: v.投，掷；投射（光）；  n.演员表，演员阵容
英文释义: to throw one end of a fishing line into a river, etc.
例句: He's going to cast that rock by the seaside.
例句释义: 他在海边准备把石块投掷出去。

英文释义: to say officially in court that somebody is to receive a particular punishment
例句: The judge sentenced him to life in prison.
例句释义: 法官判决他终身监禁。

详细释义: adj. 不寻常的，不常见的
英文释义: different from what is usual or normal
例句: That guy has an unusual ability! He can fly!
例句释义: 这个男人有不寻常的能力！他会飞！

英文释义: in a close relation or position in time or space
例句: This is a closely contested basketball game.
例句释义: 这场篮球比赛比分很接近。

英文释义: to make somebody/yourself believe that something is true
例句: The footprints convinced the wife that the cat made the mess.
例句释义: 这些脚印使这位太太确信是猫把一切弄乱的。

英文释义: a measurement of how tall a person or thing is :the distance from the bottom to the top of a person or thing
例句: The woman is measuring her daughter's height.
例句释义: 这个女人正在给她女儿量身高。

英文释义: a doctor, especially one who is a specialist in general medicine and not surgery
例句: My physician told me to eat more fruits and vegetables.
例句释义: 我的内科医生告诉我要多吃水果和蔬菜。

英文释义: to make a judgement about the nature or quality of somebody/something; to calculate the amount or value of something
例句: How do you assess the risk level of this investment? Low, medium or high?
例句释义: 你对这次投资的风险评估是怎样的？低风险、中风险，还是高风险？

英文释义: a large number or amount of something; a number or amount of something that is enough for a particular purpose
例句: She has received plenty of messages.
例句释义: 她收到了很多消息。

英文释义: almost or very nearly, so that any slight difference is not important
例句: The screen is so vivid that the pictures were virtually right there in front of me.
例句释义: 屏幕里的东西那么栩栩如生，仿佛那些画面（实际上）就在我的眼前。

英文释义: the process of adding two or more numbers together to find their total
例句: Simple addition is the easiest part of math class.
例句释义: 简单加法是数学课中最容易的部分。

英文释义: having a fine edge or point, especially of something that can cut or make a hole in something
例句: This knife is so sharp that it can easily slice the apple.
例句释义: 这把刀好锋利啊，切苹果超级容易。

英文释义: involving the use of skill and the imagination to produce something new or a work of art; having the skill and ability to produce something new, especially a work of art; showing this ability
例句: She is a very creative person, especially when she is drawing.
例句释义: 她是一个很有创造性的人，尤其是画画的时候。

详细释义: adj.下方的，底部的；  v.降低，减少
英文释义: located below something else, especially something of the same type, or the other of a pair; at or near the bottom of something
例句: The old lady sits on the lower deck of the bus.
例句释义: 这位老太太坐在公交车的下层。

英文释义: to think that somebody/something is good, acceptable or suitable; to officially agree to a plan, request, etc.; to say that something is good enough to be used or is correct
例句: They all approve of my good performance.
例句释义: 他们都称许我良好的表现。

英文释义: a statement, fact, or situation that tells you why something happened; a reason given for something; a statement or piece of writing that tells you how something works or makes something easier to understand
例句: The boy is giving his explanation for why he arrived late for school.
例句释义: 男孩正在解释他上学迟到的原因。

英文释义: a person who is homosexual, especially a man
例句: Gay people also have the right to love.
例句释义: 同性恋也有权利相爱。

英文释义: the area and buildings around a university, college, school, etc.
例句: A college campus is a great place to meet new friends.
例句释义: 大学校园是遇上新朋友的好地方。

详细释义: adj.得体的；适合的，适用的；独特的；真正的；完全的
英文释义: right, appropriate or correct; according to the rules
例句: You should wear something proper when having an interview.
例句释义: 面试时，你应当穿着得体。

英文释义: feeling ashamed because you have done something that you know is wrong or have not done something that you should have done
例句: The dog looked very guilty for destroying the living room.
例句释义: 这只狗因为破坏了客厅而感到很内疚。

详细释义: v.（尤指靠自己的努力、行动或经过一个过程）获得
英文释义: to obtain something by buying or being given it
例句: The little boy acquired knowledge of the universe from reading.
例句释义: 小男孩通过阅读学到了很多关于宇宙的知识。

英文释义: to try to be more successful or better than somebody else who is trying to do the same as you
例句: We compete against each other to see who's the fastest rider.
例句释义: 我们相互竞争，想看看谁才是最快的骑手。

英文释义: connected with the practical use of machinery, methods, etc. in science and industry; connected with the skills needed for a particular job, sport, art, etc.; connected with a particular subject and therefore difficult to understand if you do not know about that subject
例句: If you have any problems, please call me to get technical support.
例句释义: 如果你有任何问题，请打电话给我寻求技术支持。

详细释义: prep.加，加上；  n.加号；有利因素；  adj.正的
英文释义: used to indicate that one number or amount is being added to another
例句: One plus one equals two. Hopefully you knew that.
例句释义: 一加一等于二，希望你知道这个。

详细释义: n.移民，外侨；  adj.移民的；迁入的
英文释义: a person who has come to live permanently in a country that is not their own
例句: The deer immigrants can permanently live in the zebra country since they hold green cards.
例句释义: 这些鹿移民者持有绿卡，所以可以永久生活在斑马国。

英文释义: having little physical power or ability :not strong
例句: He's so weak that he can't even lift this tiny weight.
例句释义: 他真的是太虚弱了，竟然这么轻的重量都举不起来。

英文释义: not allowed by the law
例句: Occupying a bus lane is illegal.
例句释义: 占用公交车道是违法行为!

详细释义: n.可供选择的事物；  adj.可供选择的
英文释义: a thing that you can choose to do or have out of two or more possibilities
例句: He has the alternative of either riding or driving.
例句释义: 他可以在骑车或开车中选择一种。

英文释义: if one thing has an interaction with another, or if there is an interaction between two things, the two things have an effect on each other
例句: The singer wants to create more interaction with his fans.
例句释义: 这个歌手想要与歌迷有更多的互动。

英文释义: a thing shaped like a column
例句: Only a few columns of the old building are still standing.
例句释义: 这栋老建筑只有几根柱子还立在那儿。

英文释义: the various aspects of a person’s character that combine to make them different from other people; the qualities of a person’s character that make them interesting and attractive
例句: I thought she was nice, but her real personality is much meaner.
例句释义: 我以为她人很好，但是原来她真实的性格讨厌得多。

英文释义: a movement or sound that you make to give somebody information, instructions, a warning, etc.; a series of electrical waves that carry sounds, pictures or messages, for example to a radio, television or mobile/cell phone; a piece of equipment that uses different coloured lights to tell drivers to go slower, stop, etc., used especially on railways/railroads and roads
例句: The ship sent out a signal for help.
例句释义: 这艘船发出了求救信号。

详细释义: n. 课程，（学校或专业的）全部课程
英文释义: the courses that are taught by a school, college, etc.
例句: The curriculum includes math, science and English.
例句释义: 这些课程包含数学、科学和英语。

英文释义: something that you are very pleased or proud to do because people are showing you great respect
例句: She got an honor for her excellent grades.
例句释义: 她因出色的学习成绩而获得了这项荣誉。

英文释义: a person who is traveling from one place to another in a car, bus, train, ship, airplane, etc., and who is not driving or working on it
例句: All the passengers are seated and ready for the trip.
例句释义: 乘客们已经坐好了，准备开始旅程。

英文释义: help or support
例句: The doctor provided medical assistance for the old lady.
例句释义: 医生为老太太提供了医疗帮助。

英文释义: used to say that a particular situation or state will always exist; a very long time
例句: They turned into butterflies and stayed together forever.
例句释义: 他们变成了蝴蝶，会永远在一起。

详细释义: v.把……视为；  n.尊敬；问候；关注
英文释义: to think about somebody/something in a particular way
例句: The boy regards his angry mother as a female tiger!
例句释义: 男孩把发怒的妈妈看作一只母老虎！

详细释义: n. 联想；联系，协会，联盟，社团
英文释义: an official group of people who have joined together for a particular purpose
例句: What association do you have with the color green?
例句释义: 绿色会使你联想到什么?

英文释义: to hit something (such as a door) with the knuckles of your hand or with a hard object (such as a knocker) in order to get people's attention
例句: Before entering, you should knock the door.
例句释义: 进去之前，你应该先敲门。

英文释义: to cover something completely in paper or other material, for example when you are giving it as a present; to cover something/somebody in material, for example in order to protect it/them
例句: He wrapped up all the Christmas presents by himself.
例句释义: 他亲手包装了所有的圣诞礼物。

英文释义: a laboratory; a room or building equipped for scientific experimentation or research
例句: This lab has lots of equipment for experiments.
例句释义: 这间实验室有许多实验仪器。

详细释义: vt.展示；显示；陈列；  n.表现，流露；显示；陈列
英文释义: to put something in a place where people can see it easily; to show something to people
例句: The salesman displayed the latest laptop.
例句释义: 销售人员展示了最新型的笔记本电脑。

英文释义: the act of expressing disapproval and of noting the problems or faults of a person or thing; the act of criticizing someone or something
例句: The girl receives some criticism for her appearance from old ladies.
例句释义: 女孩因为她的外表受到了老太太们的批评。

英文释义: a thing of value, especially property, that a person or company owns, which can be used or sold to pay debts; a person or thing that is valuable or useful to somebody/something
例句: My house is an important part of my assets.
例句释义: 我的房子是我的财产中重要的一部分。

详细释义: n.抑郁，沮丧；不景气，萧条（期）
英文释义: a period when there is little economic activity and many people are poor or without jobs
例句: After the divorce she sank into a deep depression; she barely ate or slept.
例句释义: 离婚后她沉浸在极度的抑郁中，几乎不吃不睡。

英文释义: of or relating to a person's spirit
例句: Living a simple life, she devoted herself to the pursuit of spiritual world.
例句释义: 她过着简朴的生活，致力于追求自己的精神世界。

详细释义: adj.音乐的；有音乐才能的，喜欢音乐的；  n.音乐剧
英文释义: connected with music; containing music
例句: The guitar is a musical instrument which is hard to learn.
例句释义: 吉他是一种难学的乐器。

英文释义: a person whose job is to collect and write news stories for newspapers, magazines, radio or television
例句: The journalist is carrying a microphone and a camera.
例句释义: 这位记者带着一个话筒和一台相机。

英文释义: words that you say to God giving thanks or asking for help
例句: Christians usually say a prayer before eating a shared meal.
例句释义: 基督教徒有饭前祷告的习俗。

详细释义: n.犯罪嫌疑人，可疑分子；  v.怀疑，猜疑；  adj.可疑的
英文释义: a person who is suspected of a crime or of having done something wrong
例句: The suspect is talking with his lawyer.
例句释义: 犯罪嫌疑人正在和他的律师谈话。

详细释义: n.学者；公费生，有奖学金的学生
英文释义: a person who knows a lot about a particular subject because they have studied it in detail
例句: She's so young, but she's quite a little scholar.
例句释义: 她很年轻，但是已经是一个小小的学者了。

英文释义: a statement, an event, etc. telling somebody that something bad or unpleasant may happen in the future so that they can try to avoid it
例句: You should be careful when you see that warning sign.
例句释义: 看到那个警告标示时，你应该小心一点。

详细释义: n.气候；（社会思想等的）趋势
英文释义: the usual weather conditions in a particular place or region
例句: Climates differ from place to place, and from season to season.
例句释义: 气候随着地域和季节的不同而变化。

英文释义: a type of food made from milk that can be either soft or hard and is usually white or yellow in colour; a particular type of this food
例句: I love eating cheese.
例句释义: 我喜欢吃奶酪。

英文释义: the act of watching somebody/something carefully for a period of time, especially to learn something
例句: Telescope observation revealed many secrets about the star.
例句释义: 望远镜观测揭开了关于这颗恒星的许多秘密。

英文释义: the period of time when a person is a child
例句: We have been good friends since childhood.
例句释义: 我们从小就一直是好朋友。

英文释义: the act of paying somebody/something or of being paid
例句: The picture shows different payment methods.
例句释义: 这张图片显示了不同的付款方式。

英文释义: used as a polite way of addressing a man whose name you do not know, for example in a shop/store or restaurant, or to show respect
例句: Please call me "Sir" when you talk to me!
例句释义: 当你跟我说话时，请称呼“先生”。

详细释义: vt. 允许，许可；  n. 执照
英文释义: to allow somebody to do something or to allow something to happen
例句: Only the invited are permitted to enter the room.
例句释义: 只有受邀人士才被允许进入这个房间。

英文释义: a small roll of paper that is filled with cut tobacco and smoked
例句: Cigarettes are bad for your health.
例句释义: 香烟对你的身体健康有害。

详细释义: n. 定义，释义；（轮廓等）清晰
英文释义: an explanation of the meaning of a word or phrase, especially in a dictionary; the act of stating the meanings of words and phrases
例句: This word has been given a new definition.
例句释义: 这个词被赋予了一个新的定义。

英文释义: something that you think is more important than other things and should be dealt with first
例句: My priority is to finish my homework then dinner.
例句释义: 我得先做完作业才能吃晚餐。

英文释义: a type of food made from flour, water and usually yeast mixed together and baked
例句: There is nothing more delicious than freshly baked bread.
例句释义: 没有什么能比刚烤出来的面包更美味的了。

详细释义: n. 创造物，作品；创造，创作
英文释义: the act or process of making something that is new, or of causing something to exist that did not exist before
例句: No, I did not copy the design; this is my own creation.
例句释义: 不，我没有抄别人的设计，这都是我自己的作品。

详细释义: v.毕业；渐渐变为；取得学位；授予学位；  n.毕业生；学位获得者；  adj.毕业的；研究生的
英文释义: to get a degree, especially your first degree, from a university or college
例句: She graduated from university after four years' unforgettable life.
例句释义: 经过四年难忘的大学生活，她毕业了。

英文释义: an act of politely or formally asking for something
例句: His father agreed to his request for a Superman costume.
例句释义: 他父亲同意了他想要一套超人服装的请求。

英文释义: a strong feeling (such as love, anger, joy, hate, or fear)
例句: She expressed different emotions when watching this TV series.
例句释义: 她看这部电视剧的时候表现出了不同的情绪。

英文释义: to give a loud, high cry, because you are hurt, frightened, excited, etc.
例句: The woman screamed when she found a mouse in her slipper.
例句释义: 当这个女人发现拖鞋里的老鼠时，她尖叫了起来。

英文释义: (of a change, an event, etc.) sudden, very great and often surprising; exciting and impressive
例句: The dramatic decline of the stock value was a big blow for him.
例句释义: 这次股价的戏剧性下跌对他来说是一个沉重的打击。

英文释义: the whole of space and everything in it, including the earth, the planets and the stars; a system of stars, planets, etc. in space outside our own; a particular area of experience or activity
例句: There are a lot of stars in the universe.
例句释义: 宇宙中有很多星星。

英文释义: a space between two people or things
例句: Please mind the gap between the train and the platform!
例句释义: 请当心列车与站台之间的间隙！

英文释义: extremely good
例句: He's an excellent student who always gets excellent scores.
例句释义: 他是个优秀的学生，总是得高分。

英文释义: in a way that is very complete, extreme, strongly felt, etc. :in a deep way
例句: He slept so deeply that it was impossible to wake him up.
例句释义: 他睡得太熟了，根本叫不醒。

英文释义: having good luck
例句: She is such a lucky dog! She just won the jackpot in the lottery.
例句释义: 她真是个幸运儿！买彩票中了头奖。

详细释义: v.拖，拉，拽，扯；（时间或事件）拖沓；  n.拖
英文释义: to pull somebody/something along with effort and difficulty
例句: You can drag this picture from this folder to the other.
例句释义: 你可以把图片从这个文件夹拖进另一个文件夹。

详细释义: n.航空公司；  adj.航空公司的，航线的
英文释义: a company that provides regular flights to take passengers and goods to different places
例句: This airline operates on these flight routes.
例句释义: 这家航空公司运营这些航线。

英文释义: a place where books, magazines, and other materials (such as videos and musical recordings) are available for people to use or borrow
例句: She likes reading in the library.
例句释义: 她喜欢在图书馆看书。

英文释义: a plan of things to be done, or problems to be addressed; a list of items to be discussed at a meeting
例句: The meeting's agenda still needs to be written.
例句释义: 会议议程还需要写下来。

详细释义: v.痊愈，恢复健康；恢复；重新获得
英文释义: to become healthy after an illness or injury; to return to normal health
例句: He has recovered well from his foot injury.
例句释义: 他的脚伤已经痊愈了。

英文释义: a building or group of buildings where goods are made
例句: The local factory is causing smog.
例句释义: 当地工厂正在制造烟雾污染。

英文释义: a number of people or things that have been chosen from a larger group; a collection of things from which something can be chosen
例句: Our nursery offers a selection of spring flowers of many different colors.
例句释义: 我们的苗圃里有各种颜色的春季花卉可供挑选。

英文释义: at first; originally; mainly; principally
例句: The human body is primarily made up of water.
例句释义: 人体主要是由水分组成的。

英文释义: the structure that covers or forms the top of a building or vehicle
例句: There's a window and a chimney on this roof.
例句释义: 屋顶上有一扇窗户和一个烟囱。

英文释义: not able to do something
例句: The man in the wheelchair is unable to go up.
例句释义: 这位坐轮椅的男士没法往上爬。

英文释义: the money that you spend on something
例句: Buying a car can be a great expense.
例句释义: 买车是笔大花销。

详细释义: n.主动权，主动性；首创精神；（重要的）法案，倡议
英文释义: the ability to decide and act on your own without waiting for somebody to tell you what to do
例句: Her boyfriend took initiative and cleaned up after they all had dinner.
例句释义: 她男朋友在他们吃完晚饭后主动打扫了卫生。

详细释义: n.（病人或减肥者的）规定饮食；日常饮食；大量；  vi.节食
英文释义: a limited variety or amount of food that you eat for medical reasons or because you want to lose weight
例句: I'm trying to eat a diet of only fruits and vegetables.
例句释义: 我在努力节食，只吃水果和蔬菜。

详细释义: v.逮捕，拘留；  n.逮捕，拘留
英文释义: if the police arrest somebody, the person is taken to a police station and kept there because the police believe they may be guilty of a crime
例句: He was arrested for breaking the law.
例句释义: 他因为犯法被抓起来了。

英文释义: money for a particular purpose; the act of providing money for such a purpose
例句: They plan to help children living in poverty through extra funding.
例句释义: 他们计划用额外的基金帮助贫困儿童。

英文释义: the treatment of a physical problem or an illness
例句: The man tried a number of different Chinese therapies.
例句释义: 这个男人尝试了一些不同的中医理疗。

英文释义: to make something/somebody clean using water and usually soap
例句: He washes his car every week to keep it clean.
例句释义: 为了保持车子的整洁，他每个星期都洗车。

英文释义: to include something in an official list of things
例句: According to my schedule, I will go shopping on Monday afternoon.
例句释义: 根据我的日程表，星期一下午我会去购物。

详细释义: adj. 难过的，悲伤的，忧愁的
英文释义: unhappy or showing unhappiness
例句: The lonely dog is sad because the owner is on holiday.
例句释义: 因为主人外出度假，所以这只孤独的狗很悲伤。

详细释义: adj.简短的，简洁的；  n.摘要，概要；职责；  v.做……的摘要
英文释义: the instructions that a person is given explaining what their job is and what their duties are; a legal case that is given to a lawyer to argue in court; a piece of work for a barrister; a written summary of the facts that support one side of a legal case, that will be presented to a court
例句: The brief letter explains why she wants to quit.
例句释义: 这封简短的信解释了她为何想辞职。

英文释义: the job of providing houses, flats/apartments, etc. for people to live in
例句: We support the construction of more public housing.
例句释义: 我们支持建设更多的公共房屋。

英文释义: to send a letter, etc. to somebody by post/mail
例句: She is posting the letter.
例句释义: 她正在寄信。

详细释义: v. 购买；  n. 购买；所购之物
英文释义: to buy something
例句: The shirt is so cheap that I really want to purchase it!
例句释义: 这件T恤太便宜了，我想买。

英文释义: existing＝found or used now.
例句: These two Hawaiian Poo-uli birds could be the only existing ones left in the world.
例句释义: 夏威夷的这两只婆欧里鸟，可能是世界上仅存的两只婆欧里鸟了。

详细释义: n.钢，钢铁，钢制品；  v.下决心应对（不愉快的事）；  adj.钢的，与钢有关的
英文释义: a strong hard metal that is made of a mixture of iron and carbon; the industry that produces steel; a long thin straight piece of steel with a rough surface, used for rubbing knives on to make them sharp
例句: Steel can be used to reinforce concrete in the construction of buildings.
例句释义: 在建造房屋时，钢铁可以用于加固混凝土。

英文释义: concerning somebody/something; about somebody/something
例句: His speech would address important issues regarding environmental pollution.
例句释义: 他的演讲将涉及关于环境污染的重要问题。

英文释义: to say something in a loud voice; to speak loudly/angrily to somebody
例句: He cupped his hands around his mouth and shouted loudly.
例句释义: 他将双手拢在嘴边，大声呼喊。

英文释义: being the remaining one or ones of severa
例句: The meter will tell you how much power is remaining.
例句释义: 那个仪表会告诉你还剩下多少电。

英文释义: of or connected with seeing or sight
例句: The color of this dress is just a visual trick.
例句释义: 这条裙子颜色只是一个视觉游戏罢了。

英文释义: in a fair and reasonable way; honestly
例句: Justice means deciding fairly in accordance with the law.
例句释义: 正义意味着依据法律公平地进行判决。

详细释义: n.木屑，碎片；  v.使碎裂；切下，削下，凿下（碎片、屑片）
英文释义: a small piece of wood, glass, etc. that has broken or been broken off an object
例句: There are many wood chips on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上有很多木屑。

详细释义: adj.暴力的，粗暴的；强烈的，猛烈的
例句: Some violent pictures in this cartoon will have a negative effect on the boy.
例句释义: 这部动画片中的一些暴力画面会对这个男孩产生负面影响。

详细释义: adj.沉默的，安静的；  n.无声电影
英文释义: not speaking or making noise
例句: We should keep silent in the library.
例句释义: 在图书馆里我们应当保持安静。

英文释义: to think or believe that something is true or possible (based on the knowledge that you have)
例句: I suppose I should probably find a part-time job.
例句释义: 我在想，也许我该找份兼职。

英文释义: the type of person you are, especially the way you normally behave, look or feel; a person’s personality or character that makes them different from other people; used to refer to a person
例句: She's looking like her confident old self again.
例句释义: 她看起来又像从前那个自信的自己了。

详细释义: n. 自行车；  v. 骑自行车
英文释义: a bicycle
例句: I like riding my bike around the city.
例句释义: 我喜欢骑自行车环绕城市。

英文释义: a hot drink made by pouring boiling water onto tea leaves. It may be drunk with milk or lemon and/or sugar added.
例句: Would you like a cup of tea?
例句释义: 你要来杯茶吗？

英文释义: to notice or become aware of (something)
例句: Hearing a strange noise from the bush, he perceived danger and prepared to fight.
例句释义: 听到灌木丛里奇怪的声音，他意识到了危险并准备战斗。

英文释义: the process of comparing two or more people or things
例句: By comparison, her Valentine's gift is not as good as the gift her friend got.
例句释义: 相比之下，这个女孩的情人节礼物不如她朋友的好。

英文释义: an official agreement that ends an argument between two people or groups
例句: The two sides shook hands on the settlement.
例句释义: 双方握手言和。

英文释义: a level or part within a system or set of ideas
例句: Wow, look at how many layers that sandwich has!
例句释义: 哇，看看那个三明治有多少层！

详细释义: n. 规划；计划编制；  v. 预期
例句: Planning for the married life will help the couple have clear goals in the future.
例句释义: 规划婚后生活能帮助这对夫妻在未来有明确的目标。

英文释义: a piece of writing or speech that says what somebody/something is like; the act of writing or saying in words what somebody/something is like
例句: The policeman asked the girl to give a description of the criminal.
例句释义: 警察让女孩描述一下犯罪嫌疑人的样子。

详细释义: v.滑落；使滑动；  n.幻灯片
英文释义: to move easily over a smooth or wet surface; to make something move in this way
例句: The little girl is having fun sliding down quickly into the water.
例句释义: 小女孩快速滑落到水中，玩得很开心。

英文释义: by a lot of people; in or to many places
例句: The color red is widely used during the Spring Festival celebrations.
例句释义: 欢度春节时，处处可见红色。

英文释义: a marriage ceremony, and the meal or party that usually follows it
例句: The couple held their wedding ceremony on the grass.
例句释义: 这对夫妻在草地上举行了他们的婚礼。

英文释义: to give information to (someone)
例句: She excitedly informed us that she was getting married next week.
例句释义: 她兴奋地告诉我们她下周就要结婚了。

详细释义: n.一部分；份额；分担的责任；  vt.把……分成份额
英文释义: one part of something larger; an amount of food that is large enough for one person; a part of something that is shared with other people
例句: Every month the couple manage to save a small portion of their salaries.
例句释义: 这对夫妇每个月都设法从工资里省下一小部分钱。

英文释义: an area that one person, group, animal, etc. considers as their own and defends against others who try to enter it
例句: The dog's pee helps to mark its territory.
例句释义: 狗狗通过撒尿来标记领土。

英文释义: happening or done without delay
例句: This letter demands my immediate response.
例句释义: 这封信需要我立即回复。

详细释义: n. 对手，敌手，对抗者；  adj. 对立的；敌对的
英文释义: a person, team, group, etc., that is competing against another in a contest
例句: The boxer punched his opponent severely！
例句释义: 这个拳击手痛击对手！

英文释义: to stop doing something, especially before it is finished; to stop having something
例句: He abandoned his car in the desert.
例句释义: 他在沙漠中抛弃了车子。

英文释义: a large area of water that is surrounded by land
例句: The lake lies in the pretty, green valley.
例句释义: 这个湖位于美丽的绿色山谷中。

英文释义: to completely change the appearance or character of something, especially so that it is better; to change the form of something
例句: You will transform into a beautiful butterfly one day.
例句释义: 总有一天，你会变成漂亮的蝴蝶。

详细释义: n.（精神上的）紧张，不安；紧张局面
英文释义: a feeling of nervousness that makes you unable to relax; a situation in which people do not trust each other, or feel unfriendly towards each other, and which may cause them to attack each other
例句: The writer is feeling great tension because of the coming deadline.
例句释义: 截止日期就要到了，这位作家十分紧张。

英文释义: ahead of others in a race or contest; most important or most influential
例句: The leading cyclist was starting to pull away from the rest.
例句释义: 领先的骑手渐渐甩开了其他人。

英文释义: to annoy, worry or upset somebody; to cause somebody trouble or pain
例句: He plays music at night, which really bothers me!
例句释义: 他总在晚上玩音乐，这真的打扰到我了！

英文释义: to be formed or composed (of)
例句: A bicycle consists of many parts.
例句释义: 自行车由许多部分组成。

英文释义: a clear liquid that has a strong smell, that is used in some medicines and other products, and that is the substance in liquors (such as beer, wine, or whiskey) that can make a person drunk
例句: I avoid alcohol because it weakens my judgment.
例句释义: 我不喝酒，因为它会削弱我的判断力。

英文释义: to cause (a feature or capability of a computer) to be active or available for use
例句: Standing on the box enables him to look out the window.
例句释义: 站在箱子上让他能够看到窗外。

详细释义: v.（使）弯曲；  n.弯曲，弯曲处
英文释义: a curve or turn, especially in a road or river; severe pain and difficulty in breathing experienced by a diver who comes back to the surface of the water too quickly
例句: She is bending her waist to do some exercise.
例句释义: 她弯下她的腰，来做运动。

详细释义: n.（复数）储蓄金，存款；节省，节约；储蓄
英文释义: an amount of something that is not spent or used
例句: I put all of my money into savings instead of spending it.
例句释义: 我把我所有的钱都放在储蓄金里，而不是花掉。

英文释义: a large area of land that has very little water and very few plants growing on it. Many deserts are covered by sand.
例句: I finally found water in the desert.
例句释义: 我终于在沙漠里找到水了。

详细释义: aux.表示提供建议或征求意见
英文释义: used in questions with I and we for making offers or suggestions or asking advice
例句: Shall we dance together?
例句释义: 我们一起跳个舞吧？

英文释义: a mistake, especially one that causes problems or affects the result of something
例句: He is marking the errors on the document.
例句释义: 他正在标出文件上有错误的地方。

详细释义: n. 【口语】警察；  v. 抓住、发现（某人）在干坏事；获得；遭受；握住
英文释义: to receive or suffer something unpleasant; to notice something
例句: "You! Stop, immediately!" Shouted the cop.
例句释义: “你！站住！立刻！”警察喊道。

详细释义: adj. 两倍的，双的；  v. 使……翻倍
英文释义: twice as much or as many as usual; having or made of two things or parts that are equal or similar
例句: The burger in the middle is a double cheeseburger.
例句释义: 中间的汉堡是一个双层芝士堡。

英文释义: a substance that consists of very small fine grains of rock; a large area of sand on a beach
例句: The kids are playing in the sand.
例句释义: 孩子们在沙地里玩。

英文释义: the Romance language spoken in most of Spain and the countries colonized by Spain
例句: Bullfighting, paella and flamenco dancing are all closely related to Spanish culture.
例句释义: 斗牛、海鲜饭和弗拉门科舞这些都与西班牙文化息息相关。

英文释义: to produce letters, pictures, etc. on paper using a machine that puts ink on the surface
例句: This machine can print any pattern.
例句释义: 这台机器可以印刷出任何图案。

英文释义: to keep something in its original state in good condition
例句: It's our duty to preserve our environment together.
例句释义: 齐心协力保护环境是我们的责任。

详细释义: n.通道，走廊；（法案的）通过；段落；（时间的）推移；旅程
英文释义: a long narrow area with walls on either side that connects one room or place with another
例句: People with suitcases are walking through the passage.
例句释义: 人们提着箱子正从通道里走过。

英文释义: official; following an agreed or official way of doing things
例句: Please wear formal clothes to the event―don't embarrass me again!
例句释义: 请穿正装来参加宴会，别再让我难堪了！

英文释义: the process or a period of changing from one state or condition to another
例句: As the seasons transition, so does the color of the maple leaf.
例句释义: 随着季节的变换，枫叶的颜色也发生了转变。

英文释义: the state or fact of being real or living or of being present
例句: These fossils prove the existence of dinosaurs.
例句释义: 这些化石证明了恐龙的存在。

详细释义: n. 相册；唱片集，专辑；集邮册
英文释义: a book in which you keep photographs, stamps, etc.
例句: The father is looking at the photo album of him and his son.
例句释义: 父亲正在看他和儿子的相册。

英文释义: the act of taking part in an activity or event
例句: Classroom participation will be a big part of your grade, so pay attention!
例句释义: 课堂参与将是你们成绩考核里很重要的一项，所以要注意！

英文释义: to write or change a piece of music so that it is suitable for a particular instrument or voice
例句: It's time to arrange the pile of clothes in the wardrobe.
例句释义: 是时候把衣柜里的这堆衣服整理一下了。

英文释义: the mixture of gases that surrounds the earth
例句: The atmosphere can protect the earth from solar rays.
例句释义: 大气层可以保护地球免受太阳射线的伤害。

详细释义: n.关节；接合处；（尤指廉价的）公共场所；  adj.连接的，共同的
英文释义: a place where two bones are joined together in the body in a way that enables them to bend and move; a place where two or more parts of an object are joined together, especially to form a corner; a place where people meet to eat, drink, dance, etc., especially one that is cheap
例句: She felt a sudden pain in her knee joint.
例句释义: 她感到膝关节突然一阵疼痛。

英文释义: an act of replying to something/somebody in speech, writing or by some action
例句: She replied to the boy on the phone by confirming her name.
例句释义: 她确认了自己的名字，回答了电话那头男孩的问题。

详细释义: n. 周期，循环；  v. <英> 骑自行车
英文释义: the fact of a series of events being repeated many times, always in the same order
例句: The diagram shows the water cycle process.
例句释义: 这张图展示了水循环过程。

详细释义: adj.相反的；对立的；对面的；  adv.对立地；反面地；  n.反面；对立物
英文释义: as different as possible from something
例句: She is running in the opposite direction of all the others.
例句释义: 她正朝着与其他人相反的方向跑。

英文释义: to fasten something with a lock; to be fastened with a lock
例句: The door is locked; we can't get in!
例句释义: 这扇门锁上了，我们进不去！

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) if somebody/something deserves something, it is right that they should have it, because of the way they have behaved or because of what they are
例句: She deserves such a high ranking because of her popularity.
例句释义: 以她的高人气，她应该得到这样的名次。

英文释义: always behaving in the same way, or having the same opinions, standards, etc.; happening in the same way and continuing for a period of time; in agreement with something; not contradicting something; (of an argument or a set of ideas) having different parts that all agree with each other
例句: Her dream of becoming a nurse remained consistent throughout her life.
例句释义: 在她的一生中，成为一名护士的愿望始终没有变。

英文释义: the act of using force to oppose somebody/something
例句: Running with added resistance can be a good way to train runners.
例句释义: 增加阻力跑步可能是一种训练跑步者的好方法。

英文释义: a thing, fact or person that is found or learned about for the first time
例句: The discovery of water on Mars is exciting to us!
例句释义: 在火星上发现液态水真是一件激动人心的事！

英文释义: the state of being in a place or situation where there is no protection from something harmful or unpleasant
例句: Because of exposure to the sun, Mr. corn is burnt.
例句释义: 因为暴露在太阳下，玉米先生都晒伤了。

详细释义: n. 姿势；装腔作势，伪装；  vi. 摆造型；  vt. 主张，提出；引起，导致
英文释义: a particular position in which somebody stands, sits, etc., especially in order to be painted, drawn or photographed
例句: The beautiful model made a pose for the camera.
例句释义: 这个漂亮的模特在镜头前摆出了一个姿势。

英文释义: a small narrow river
例句: There was a small stream running through the forest.
例句释义: 有一条小溪从森林中流过。

英文释义: the act of selling something :the exchange of goods, services, or property for money
例句: All the clothes are on sale.
例句释义: 所有衣服都在打折。

英文释义: a deep round container used for cooking things in; a container made of glass, clay or plastic, used for storing food in; (especially in compounds) a container of various kinds, made for a particular purpose; a bowl, etc. that is made by a potter
例句: Hot pot is a speciality in Sichuan province.
例句释义: 火锅是四川省的一大特色。

详细释义: adj.壮丽的，宏伟的；重大的；  n.一千美元；大钢琴
英文释义: impressive and large or important
例句: The hotel lobby was very impressive and grand.
例句释义: 这家酒店的大厅非常宏伟壮观。

详细释义: n. 矿，矿山；  v. 开采，采矿；  pron. 我的（所有物）
英文释义: a deep hole or holes under the ground where minerals such as coal, gold, etc. are dug
例句: Will he find any gold in the mine?
例句释义: 他能在矿里找到金子吗？

英文释义: a government formed by two or more political parties working together
例句: We had to form a coalition to win the election.
例句释义: 我们必须结盟以赢得选举。

英文释义: a story about imaginary events :an exciting or dramatic story
例句: Most little kids love to read fairy tales.
例句释义: 很多小孩都喜欢读童话故事。

英文释义: a usually sharp blade attached to a handle that is used for cutting or as a weapon
例句: A knife is used to cut things up.
例句释义: 刀是用来切东西的。

英文释义: strong determination to achieve something
例句: Nothing shakes his resolve of being a fluent English speaker!
例句释义: 没有什么能动摇他想说一口流利的英语的决心！

英文释义: happening or existing between people of different races
例句: Racial origin has nothing to do with making friends.
例句释义: 种族背景毫不影响结交朋友。

英文释义: the shape of the part of the moon that is visible at different times during a month
例句: The moon will pass through all of its phases in about one month.
例句释义: 在大约一个月的时间里，月亮会呈现出所有的月相变化。

详细释义: n. 笑话；  v. 说笑话
英文释义: something that you say or do to make people laugh, for example a funny story that you tell
例句: His jokes always make people laugh.
例句释义: 他讲的笑话总是使人哈哈大笑。

英文释义: a piece of outdoor clothing that is worn over other clothes to keep warm or dry. Coats have sleeves and may be long or short.
例句: He wore a thick coat to keep warm in the winter.
例句释义: 大冬天他穿了一件厚外套来保暖。

详细释义: adj.墨西哥的；  n.墨西哥人

例句: The Mexican man sold delicious Mexican food such as tacos.
例句释义: 这个墨西哥人售卖好吃的墨西哥食物，比如墨西哥玉米卷。

英文释义: a change in your body or mind that shows that you are not healthy
例句: Flu symptoms include a headache, a sore throat, and a fever.
例句释义: 流感的症状包括头痛、嗓子痛和发烧。

英文释义: a company that makes a product
例句: Our company is a large manufacturer of household goods.
例句释义: 我们公司是一家大型日用品制造商。

英文释义: the study of the nature and meaning of the universe and of human life; a particular set or system of beliefs resulting from the search for knowledge about life and the universe
例句: I often think about the meaning of life and other questions of philosophy.
例句释义: 我常常思考生命的意义以及其他哲学问题。

英文释义: a round root of a plant that has brown, yellow, or red skin and white or yellow flesh and that is eaten as a vegetable
例句: Let's cut these potatoes and fry them into chips.
例句释义: 我们把这些土豆切了然后炸薯片吧。

英文释义: a layer of bricks, concrete, etc. that forms the solid underground base of a building
例句: A strong building needs a solid foundation.
例句释义: 一座坚固的建筑需要有稳固的地基。

英文释义: to repeat the exact words that another person has said or written
例句: I quoted Albert Einstein in my essay about world peace.
例句释义: 在那篇关于世界和平的论文中，我引用了阿尔伯特・爱因斯坦的话。

详细释义: adj.在线的，联网的；  adv.联机地，线上地
英文释义: controlled by or connected to a computer or to the Internet
例句: Online shopping provides a more convenient way of shopping.
例句释义: 网络购物是一种更方便的购物途径。

英文释义: formal discussion between people who are trying to reach an agreement
例句: They closed the deal after a day of negotiation.
例句释义: 经过一天的谈判，他们的生意成交了。

详细释义: vt.鞭策，鼓动；敦促，催促；  n.冲动，欲望
英文释义: to advise or try hard to persuade somebody to do something
例句: During the race the rider urged the horse to go faster so he could win.
例句释义: 在比赛中，骑手为了赢得胜利，不断鞭策他的马加快速度。

详细释义: n. 场合，时候；活动；时机，机会
英文释义: a particular time when something happens; a special event, ceremony or celebration
例句: In China, New Year's Eve is a great family occasion.
例句释义: 在中国，除夕夜是重要的家庭团聚时刻。

英文释义: a fine powder that consists of very small pieces of sand, earth, etc.

英文释义: to move air into and out of your lungs: to inhale and exhale

例句释义: 她做瑜伽时用深呼吸的方式来放松自己。

英文释义: to select (someone) for a position, job, etc., by voting; to choose to do something
例句: We elect our next leader by voting.
例句释义: 我们通过投票来选举下一任领导。

详细释义: n. 短上衣，夹克衫；（书籍的）护封
英文释义: a piece of clothing worn on the top half of the body over a shirt, etc. that has sleeves and fastens down the front; a short, light coat
例句: These four jackets are different in both color and style.
例句释义: 这四件夹克衫的颜色和风格都不同。

英文释义: pleased; happy
例句: I am glad to be sharing my speech with you today.
例句释义: 很高兴今天能给大家做演讲。

英文释义: not unusual or different in any way
例句: I'm just an ordinary man.
例句释义: 我只是一个再平常不过的男人。

英文释义: an act of making something less or smaller; the state of being made less or smaller; an amount of money by which something is made cheaper; a copy of a photograph, map, picture, etc. that is made smaller than the original one; the fact of adding one or more electrons to a substance or of removing oxygen from a substance

例句释义: 由于生意不景气，他不得不考虑裁员。

英文释义: not very often
例句: It rarely snows in Chengdu.
例句释义: 成都很少下雪。

详细释义: v.收拾，打包；包装；塞满，挤满；  n.一伙，一群
英文释义: to put clothes, etc. into a bag in preparation for a trip away from home; to put something into a container so that it can be stored, transported or sold
例句: He is packing his clothes.
例句释义: 他正在打包他的衣服。

英文释义: a course of action that is likely to ruin your career, position in society, etc.
例句: To avoid being cooked, the egg committed suicide by jumping off the edge.
例句释义: 为了不被做成食物，鸡蛋从边上跳下去自杀了。

英文释义: existing in large numbers
例句: The stadium is filled with numerous sports fans.
例句释义: 体育场里坐满了体育爱好者。

英文释义: a type of solid, liquid or gas that has particular qualities
例句: A substance like water can exist in solid, liquid or gaseous form.
例句释义: 像水这样的物质可以以固态、液态或者气态的形式存在。

英文释义: an activity that is done regularly as a way of training yourself to do something or to improve your behavior
例句: These soldiers are showing great discipline.
例句释义: 这些士兵展现出良好的纪律。

英文释义: in, at or to another place
例句: I want to move elsewhere because it's too noisy here.
例句释义: 我想搬到别处去，因为这儿太吵了。

详细释义: v.熨烫（衣物）；  n.熨斗；  adj.刚强的
英文释义: to use a heated iron to make clothing or fabric smooth
例句: I have an interview tomorrow, so I need to iron my shirt.
例句释义: 明天我有一个约会，所以要把衬衣熨一熨。

详细释义: adj.实用的，可行的；实际的，实践的
英文释义: (of a person) good at making or repairing things
例句: Sneakers are more practical than boots for runners.
例句释义: 对于跑步者来说，运动鞋比靴子更实用。

英文释义: used to introduce some new information that adds to or supports what you have said previously
例句: His work is busy; moreover, an interview and a call are waiting for him.
例句释义: 他工作很忙，此外，还有一个面试和一通电话在等着他。

英文释义: a very strong feeling of liking something; a hobby, an activity, etc. that you like very much
例句: The teacher delivered his speech with great passion.
例句释义: 这位老师以极大的激情发表了演讲。

详细释义: v.自愿做；自愿加入；  n.志愿者
英文释义: to offer to do something without being forced to do it or without getting paid for it
例句: "Will anybody volunteer to clean the park?" "I'll do it!"
例句释义: “有没有人自愿打扫公园？”“我愿意！”

详细释义: n.工具，器具；  vt.实施，执行
英文释义: a tool or an instrument, often one that is quite simple and that is used outdoors
例句: I use these implements to take care of my garden.
例句释义: 我用这些工具来打理我的花园。

英文释义: a part of a cell that controls or influences the appearance, growth, etc., of a living thing
例句: DNA consists of a large number of genes.
例句释义: DNA包含大量的基因。

英文释义: the act of enforcing; insuring observance of or obedience to
例句: The police are responsible for the enforcement of the law.
例句释义: 警察负责法律的执行。

英文释义: a thick liquid that is eaten with food to add flavour to it
例句: Wow! The tomato sauce in the bowl looks so delicious.
例句释义: 哇！碗里的番茄酱看起来很好吃的样子。

详细释义: n.（国家的）独立；（人的）自立，独立
英文释义: (of a country) freedom from political control by other countries
例句: America gained its independence from Britain in the 18th century!
例句释义: 18世纪，美国脱离英国取得独立！

英文释义: the activity of presenting, advertising and selling a company’s products or services in the best possible way
例句: They have created a marketing plan which should increase the sales of the product.
例句释义: 他们制定了一份市场营销计划，应该能提高这个产品的销售额。

英文释义: a person who is qualified to perform religious duties and ceremonies in the Roman Catholic, Anglican and Orthodox Churches; a person who performs religious ceremonies in some religions that are not Christian
例句: The priest is wearing a black gown.
例句释义: 这名神父身着一袭黑色长袍。

英文释义: very surprising, especially in a way that makes you feel pleasure or admiration
例句: The sunrise is so amazing!
例句释义: 日出美得惊人！

详细释义: adj. 强烈的，激烈的；认真的
英文释义: serious and often involving a lot of action in a short period of time; very great; very strong
例句: Wow, that was an intense thunderstorm!
例句释义: 哇，那是一次强烈的风暴。

详细释义: n.预先；增长；  v.提升；  adj.预先的
英文释义: a group of people who go somewhere first, before the main group
例句: He finished his homework in advance.
例句释义: 他提前做完了作业。

英文释义: a person or company that pays people to work for them
例句: The girl is hired by the employer.
例句释义: 女孩被雇主录用了。

详细释义: v.使...震惊；使...震动；  n.震惊；震动
英文释义: a strong feeling of surprise as a result of something happening, especially something unpleasant; the event that causes this feeling; a serious medical condition, usually the result of injury in which a person has lost a lot of blood and they are extremely weak; a violent shaking movement that is caused by an explosion, earthquake, etc.
例句: She was shocked to see how much her stock value had fallen.
例句释义: 看到股票跌了这么多，她真是惊呆了！

英文释义: to give somebody the desire, confidence or enthusiasm to do something well
例句: His speech inspired so many people to fight for equality.
例句释义: 马丁・路德金的演讲激励了很多人为平等为奋斗。

详细释义: v. 调整，调节；改变……以适应
英文释义: to change something slightly to make it more suitable for a new set of conditions or to make it work better
例句: "It's too hot in here; I'll adjust the temperature."
例句释义: “这里太热了，我调节一下温度。”

英文释义: older people leave their job and usually stop working completely.
例句: The retired couple are traveling together.
例句释义: 这对已经退休的夫妻正在一起旅行。

英文释义: that can be seen
例句: The cake in the right box is visible.
例句释义: 右边盒子里的蛋糕是可见的。

详细释义: v. 吻，接吻；  n. 吻
英文释义: to touch somebody with your lips as a sign of love, affection, sexual desire, etc., or when saying hello or goodbye; to gently move or touch something
例句: The newly married couple are sharing a kiss.
例句释义: 这对新婚夫妇正在接吻。

英文释义: the state of being physically or mentally ill
例句: He has an illness, but he still has to work.
例句释义: 他生病了，但仍然要工作。

英文释义: a type of soft flat hat with a peak; a soft hat that fits closely and is worn for a particular purpose
例句: This is a blue police cap.
例句释义: 这是一顶蓝色的警帽。

英文释义: a thing that you do often and almost without thinking, especially something that is hard to stop doing
例句: Make a habit of washing your hands after using the bathroom!
例句释义: 要养成上完厕所就洗手的习惯。

详细释义: adj. 竞争的；有竞争力的
英文释义: having a strong desire to win or be the best at something
例句: The soccer game was really competitive.
例句释义: 这场足球赛真的很有竞争性。

英文释义: the liquid that comes from fruit or vegetables; a drink made from this
例句: Fresh orange juice tastes better than the kind you can buy in a store.
例句释义: 新鲜的橙汁比商店买的好喝多了。

英文释义: of or relating to congress
例句: Congressional representatives from each state attended the national meeting.
例句释义: 来自各州的国会代表们参加了此次全国会议。

英文释义: the act of sharing in the activities of a group
例句: The teacher encouraged students' active involvement in the sporting activities.
例句释义: 老师鼓励学生们积极参加体育活动。

详细释义: v.支配，统治，控制；在……中占首要地位；耸立于，俯视

例句释义: 在这个家里，猫似乎占据着支配地位。

英文释义: at any time that; on any occasion that
例句: You can call customer service whenever you want.
例句释义: 无论何时，你都可以呼叫客服。

英文释义: to move from one place to another; to move something/somebody from one place to another

例句释义: 我要把这些文件从一个文件夹转移到另一个文件夹。

英文释义: to examine the nature or structure of something, especially by separating it into its parts, in order to understand or explain it
例句: She is carefully analyzing the data on the paper.
例句释义: 她正在仔细地分析文件上的数据。

英文释义: to fasten or join one thing to another
例句: The card player has several pieces of paper attached to his face.
例句释义: 这个打牌的人脸上被贴了好多张纸条。

英文释义: something (such as a flood, tornado, fire, plane crash, etc.) that happens suddenly and causes much suffering or loss to many people
例句: The unexpected disaster destroyed the whole city.
例句释义: 这场意料不到的灾难摧毁了整座城市。

英文释义: a space or an area for leaving vehicles

例句释义: 开车最烦人的就是找停车位。

详细释义: n. 前景，展望；  v. 有前途；对……进行仔细调查

详细释义: n.老板，上司；  v.发号施令

例句释义: 老板看着他工作的时候他很紧张。

英文释义: a reason for not being satisfied; a statement that somebody makes saying that they are not satisfied

例句释义: 这个顾客在向经理抱怨。

英文释义: the position of being a champion

例句释义: 谁要是赢了这场比赛，就意味着他荣获了锦标赛冠军。

详细释义: n.基本原理；  adj.至关重要的

英文释义: extremely bad or serious

例句释义: 在如此严酷的天气下，人们行走得很艰难。

详细释义: vt.提高（强度、力量、数量等）；增加，加强

例句: Clicking this icon can enhance the image.
例句释义: 点这个图标可以提高画质。

英文释义: (often used as an adjective) a person or thing that is strange and interesting because you do not know much about them or it
例句: The green light from the box gives me a sense of mystery.
例句释义: 盒子里发出的绿光给我一种神秘感。

详细释义: v.把……强加给；强制实行，强迫接受

例句释义: 我妈妈总是给我施加压力！

英文释义: the act of recording information in a computer, book, etc.

例句释义: 他走进了会议室。

英文释义: the act of spending or disbursing money

例句释义: 公共支出是指政府在教育、医疗和交通等方面的支出。

英文释义: the male ruler of an independent state that has a royal family

英文释义: to form an opinion of the amount, value or quality of something after thinking about it carefully

例句释义: 老师评估完我的作品，给了我满分。

英文释义: a person, an object, an event, etc. that represents a more general quality or situation

例句释义: 鸽子是和平的象征。

英文释义: a person who makes things

例句释义: 咖啡机非常适合在家煮美味的咖啡！

英文释义: to succeed in doing or completing something

英文释义: a covering usually of leather or rubber for the entire foot and the lower part of the leg

详细释义: n.显示器；监视器；班长；  vt.监视；监督；监测
英文释义: a device that shows information or images on a screen
例句: I want a new flat-screen computer monitor.
例句释义: 我想要一台新的纯平电脑显示器。

英文释义: a seed, or pod containing seeds, of a climbing plant, eaten as a vegetable. There are several types of bean and the plants that they grow on are also called beans.
例句: Coffee is made from coffee beans.
例句释义: 咖啡由咖啡豆制成。

英文释义: the act of forming an opinion of the amount, value or quality of something after thinking about it carefully

例句释义: 客户可以在线评估他们接受的服务。

英文释义: a living thing, real or imaginary, that can move around, such as an animal

例句释义: 你最喜欢的动物是狗、猫还是兔子？

英文释义: a person who is in charge of something, especially an officer in charge of a particular group of soldiers or a military operation; an officer of fairly high rank in the British or American navy; (in Britain) a London police officer of high rank
例句: The commander was thinking about possible strategies.

详细释义: adj.数字显示的；数码的，数字的

英文释义: the way things are done or organized

例句: He is concentrating on making his bread look perfect.
例句释义: 他正在专心地做面包，使其看起来完美。

例句释义: 教授正在向学生们解释一个著名的心理学实验。

详细释义: adv.重重地，沉重地，沉闷地，猛烈地

例句释义: 那个女人闭上眼睛开始祈祷。

例句释义: 那两个家伙在庆祝他们的成功。

详细释义: adj.光滑的；平稳的；  vt.使光滑；使平稳

例句: She said the taste of the chocolate is as smooth as silk. Give me some!
例句释义: 她说这种巧克力的口感如丝绸般柔滑，给我一点儿尝尝！

详细释义: adj.附近的，邻近的；  adv.在附近
英文释义: near in position; not far away
例句: My bluetooth phone can exchange information with any similar phone that is nearby.
例句释义: 我的蓝牙手机可以跟附近任何相似的手机交换信息。

详细释义: n.同龄人；  v.仔细看，费力地看
英文释义: a person who is the same age or who has the same social status as you
例句: He looks much younger than his peers.
例句释义: 他看起来比同龄人小得多。

详细释义: n.设计师；  adj.由著名设计师设计的
英文释义: a person whose job is to decide how things such as clothes, furniture, tools, etc. will look or work by making drawings, plans or patterns
例句: I am a fashion designer; I design clothes for women.
例句释义: 我是一个服装设计师，专门设计女装。

英文释义: the people who work for an organization or one of the armed forces
例句: Only company personnel have this card.
例句释义: 只有公司职员才有这张卡。

英文释义: a person (such as a teacher or a school administrator) who has a job in the field of education
例句: Confucius is a famous educator in ancient China.
例句释义: 孔子是中国古代著名的教育家。

详细释义: n.亲戚，家人；同类事物；  adj.相对的
英文释义: a person who is in the same family as somebody else
例句: The family tree shows all my relatives.
例句释义: 这张家谱展示了我所有的亲戚。

英文释义: the process of coming to live permanently in a country that is not your own; the number of people who do this
例句: Immigration to Germany has risen in recent times.
例句释义: 如今，向德国的移民越来越多了。

英文释义: a long narrow piece of leather, cloth, etc. that you wear around the waist
例句: My pants are so loose that I need to wear a belt.
例句释义: 我的裤子太宽松了所以我需要系一条腰带。

英文释义: the day in each year which is the same date as the one on which you were born
例句: This little girl is happy on her birthday.
例句释义: 这个过生日的女孩很开心。

英文释义: something that is suggested without being said directly; something that is implied
例句: She expressed her desire for the cookie by implication.
例句释义: 她含蓄地表达了想吃饼干的想法。

英文释义: without errors, mistakes, or flaws; in a perfect way
例句: The white shoes fit her perfectly.
例句释义: 那双白鞋和她完美搭配。

详细释义: n.海岸，海滨；  vi.沿海航行
英文释义: the land along or near a sea or ocean
例句: The view of the coast is amazing.
例句释义: 这片海岸的景色棒极了。

英文释义: a person who backs a politician or a team etc.
例句: These guys are supporters of the same soccer team.
例句释义: 他们都是同一支足球队的支持者。

详细释义: v. 陪伴；为……伴奏（或伴唱）
英文释义: to travel or go somewhere with somebody; to happen or appear with something else
例句: I always accompany my children to their school.
例句释义: 我总是陪着我的小孩们去学校。

英文释义: a soft grayish-white metal that is very valuable and is used to make jewelry, coins, knives, forks, etc.
例句: I got a silver medal, meaning that I came in second place.
例句释义: 我得了一枚银牌，这意味着我拿了第二名。

英文释义: a person who is between 13 and 19 years old
例句: Teenagers are always full of energy.
例句释义: 青少年总是充满了能量。

英文释义: the act of accepting that something exists, is true or is official
例句: I received this medal in recognition of my sports skills.
例句释义: 这枚奖牌是对我运动技能的认可。

英文释义: the fact of stopping work because you have reached a particular age; the time when you do this; the period of your life after you have stopped work at a particular age
例句: Some people look forward to retirement but I'm afraid it will be boring.
例句释义: 有些人期待着退休，但我觉得那会很无聊。

英文释义: a piece of cloth with a special design that is used as a symbol of a nation or group
例句: There are many flags flying in the air.
例句释义: 许多旗帜在空中飘扬。

英文释义: the process of becoming well again after an illness or injury
例句: I'm so happy I can walk again after my foot's recovery.
例句释义: 太高兴了！脚伤恢复之后我又可以走路了。

详细释义: v.低声低语地讲，悄悄地说；悄声说，耳语，低语；  n.私语
英文释义: to say or suggest something about somebody/something in a private or secret way
例句: My friend whispered a secret in my ear.
例句释义: 我的朋友在我耳边悄悄地告诉了我一个秘密。

英文释义: a man who treats other people in a proper and polite way
例句: "Thank you. You really are a gentleman."
例句释义: “谢谢。您真是位绅士。”

英文释义: a tall plant grown for its large yellow grains that are used for making flour or eaten as a vegetable; the grains of this plant
例句: Sweet corn tastes best with salt and butter.
例句释义: 吃甜玉米的时候加上盐和黄油味道最好。

英文释义: the large round object that circles the Earth and that shines at night by reflecting light from the sun
例句: The moon rises so big and bright over the sea.
例句释义: 月亮在海面上升起，它又大又亮。

详细释义: adj.内部的，里面的；内心的；  n.内部，里面
英文释义: inside; towards or close to the centre of a place
例句: The inner core of the Earth is made up of iron and nickel.
例句释义: 地球内部的核心由铁和镍组成。

详细释义: n.（美国四年制大学）三年级学生；  adj.（年级、职位、级别等）低的，低下的
英文释义: a person who is younger than another person;  a student in the year before the last year at high school or college
例句: “Junior” means young or younger children.
例句释义: ”少年“是指年少或者更小的孩子。

英文释义: the tube inside the neck that leads to the stomach and lungs
例句: The man has a pain in his throat.
例句释义: 这个人的喉咙疼。

英文释义: money that employees receive for doing their job, especially professional employees or people working in an office, usually paid every month
例句: They are receiving their monthly salaries from Lord Bao.
例句释义: 他们正在包大人那儿领每月工资。

详细释义: v.摇荡，来回摆动，转动，转向；使摇摆，使转动，使转向；  n.秋千
英文释义: to move backwards or forwards or from side to side while hanging from a fixed point; to make something do this
例句: He swings in the forest from tree to tree.
例句释义: 他在丛林的树间荡来荡去。

英文释义: a person who watches somebody/something; a person who watches and studies particular events, situations, etc. and is therefore considered to be an expert on them; a person who attends a meeting, lesson, etc. to listen and watch but not to take part
例句: The little boy wants to become a star observer in the future.
例句释义: 这个小男孩以后想成为一名观星者。

英文释义: the act of printing a book, a magazine, etc. and making it available to the public; a book, a magazine, etc. that has been published
例句: Once the publication process is complete, the book will be available to buy.
例句释义: 出版流程一完成，这本书就可以被买到了。

英文释义: a plant that is grown in large quantities, especially as food
例句: The main crops in this area are rice, corn and beans.
例句释义: 这个地区的主要农作物是水稻、玉米和大豆。

英文释义: to make a hole in the ground or to move soil from one place to another using your hands, a tool or a machine
例句: The dog is digging a hole.
例句释义: 这只狗正在挖洞。

英文释义: lasting for a long time or for all time in the future; existing all the time
例句: He hopes to find a permanent job.
例句释义: 他希望找到一份长久的工作。

英文释义: a fact or an event in nature or society, especially one that is not fully understood
例句: The northern lights are a breathtaking natural phenomenon.
例句释义: 北极光是令人叹为观止的自然现象。

英文释义: the state of feeling nervous or worried that something bad is going to happen
例句: It is difficult to disguise her great anxiety.
例句释义: 很难掩饰她严重的焦虑。

详细释义: prep. 不像；和……不同；  adj. 不同的
英文释义: different from a particular person or thing; used to contrast somebody/something with another person or thing; not typical of somebody/something
例句: One of these men is unlike the others.
例句释义: 这些男人中，有一个和其他人不同。

英文释义: covered or soaked with water or another liquid；not dry
例句: He got wet because of the rain.
例句释义: 因为下雨，他被淋湿了。

英文释义: to refuse to accept something and try to stop it from happening
例句: The overweight girl managed to resist the temptation of hamburgers.
例句释义: 这个胖女孩抵制住了汉堡的诱惑。

英文释义: a large meeting of the members of a profession, a political party, etc.
例句: This is an annual convention of barbers.
例句释义: 这是一场理发师的年会。

英文释义: to put your arms around somebody as a sign of love or friendship
例句: The two friends are warmly embracing each other.
例句释义: 这两个朋友正热情地拥抱着对方。

英文释义: to give support or help; to make it easier for someone to do something or for something to happen
例句: They assisted each other to the top of the mountain.
例句释义: 他们互相帮助，登上了山顶。

详细释义: n.展览（会）；陈列；(技能的) 展示
英文释义: an event at which objects (such as works of art) are put out in a public space for people to look at; a public show of something
例句: The teacher took the students to an art exhibition.
例句释义: 老师带学生们去参观了一个艺术展。

英文释义: to build or make something such as a road, building or machine
例句: The workers are constructing a tall building.
例句释义: 工人们正在建造一座高楼。

英文释义: a person who watches television
例句: He's a daily viewer of his favorite TV show.
例句释义: 他每天都要看他喜欢的电视节目。

英文释义: a container, usually made of metal, with a handle or handles, used for cooking food in; a metal container used for cooking food in
例句: This chef is pouring oil into the pan.
例句释义: 厨师在平底锅中倒了点油。

英文释义: a person who knows a lot about a particular subject and is employed to give advice about it to other people
例句: The consultant will explain how we should run our business.
例句释义: 顾问将会解释我们应该如何经营我们的事业。

英文释义: a person whose job is to manage and organize the public or business affairs of a company or an institution, or a person who works in an office dealing with records, accounts, etc.
例句: I am the administrator of the QQ group.
例句释义: 我是这个QQ群的管理员。

英文释义: sometimes but not often
例句: He only goes to the gym occasionally, about 3 times a month.
例句释义: 他只是偶尔去健身房，大约一个月三次。

英文释义: an official who is elected to be the head of the government of a city or town
例句: The duty of a mayor is to wisely govern the city.
例句释义: 一个市长的职责应该是明智地管理这个城市。

详细释义: n.体贴，体谅，顾及；考虑，思考
英文释义: the quality of being sensitive towards others and thinking about their wishes and feelings
例句: She shows a lot of consideration for her mother.
例句释义: 她很体贴她的母亲。

详细释义: adj.安全的；有把握的，确切的；  v.使安全；（经过努力）实现，获得
英文释义: that cannot be affected or harmed by something
例句: It's secure to put money into the safe.
例句释义: 将钱放进保险箱是非常安全的。

详细释义: adj. 粉红色的；  n. 粉红色
英文释义: pale red in colour
例句: The princess wore a pink dress.
例句释义: 公主穿着一条粉色的裙子。

详细释义: n. 雄鹿；  v. 马弓背踢后腿挑起
英文释义: a male deer, hare or rabbit (also called a buck rabbit)
例句: The buck is standing in the snow.
例句释义: 这只雄鹿站在雪地上。

详细释义: adj.有历史意义的，历史上著名的
英文释义: famous or important in history
例句: He is reading this book which recounts the historic victory of his country years ago.
例句释义: 他正在看的这本书记录了多年前他的国家取得的历史性胜利。

英文释义: a piece of writing in which the words are chosen for their sound and the images they suggest, not just for their obvious meanings. The words are arranged in separate lines, usually with a repeated rhythm, and often the lines rhyme at the end.
例句: This great poem was written by Li Bai.
例句释义: 这首名诗是李白写的。

详细释义: n. 祖母，外祖母；  v. 当祖母；当……的祖母
英文释义: the mother of your father or mother
例句: My grandmother gave me a candy cane.
例句释义: 我祖母给了我一个拐杖糖。

详细释义: v. 捆绑；装订；约束；结合
英文释义: to make (someone) have to do something because of a promise, agreement, etc.
例句: This contract is binding-if you sign it, you must do what it says.
例句释义: 这份合约会捆绑住你，如果你签了，你就必须按照它说的做。

英文释义: all the time; repeatedly
例句: She is constantly annoyed by the noise outside.
例句释义: 她不断地被外面的噪声所打扰。

英文释义: a company or business
例句: This small enterprise specializes in milk and dairy products.
例句释义: 这家小企业专营牛奶和乳制品。

详细释义: vt.偏爱；支持；有利于；长得像；  n.偏爱；特权；赞成；帮助
英文释义: to prefer one system, plan, way of doing something, etc. to another
例句: I need to be more healthy, so I would favor an apple over a burger.
例句释义: 我需要生活得更健康，所以比起汉堡，我更偏好苹果。

英文释义: the organ inside the body where food goes when you swallow it; the front part of the body below the chest
例句: We should eat healthy food if we want a strong stomach.
例句释义: 想拥有健康的胃，我们就应该健康饮食。

详细释义: adj.显然的；表面上的，貌似（真实）的
英文释义: easy to see or understand
例句: It is apparent that these shoes don't fit you.
例句释义: 很明显，这双鞋并不适合你。

英文释义: to measure how heavy somebody/something is, usually by using scales
例句: Please weigh the apples and pears for me.
例句释义: 请替我称一下苹果和梨的重量。

英文释义: to fix equipment or furniture into position so that it can be used; to put a new program onto a computer; to put somebody in a new position of authority, often with an official ceremony; to make somebody/yourself comfortable in a particular place or position
例句: The man installs a ceiling fan.
例句释义: 这男人把吊扇装上了。

英文释义: easily offended or upset; reacting quickly or more than usual to something
例句: Her teeth are sensitive to ice cream.
例句释义: 她的牙齿对冰激凌很敏感。

英文释义: an idea or a plan that you mention for somebody else to think about
例句: The shopping guide gives her some suggestions about the skirt.
例句释义: 导购给了她一些选裙子的建议。

详细释义: n. 邮件；  v. 邮寄
英文释义: to send (something, such as a letter or package) by mail
例句: She is going to check her inbox for any new mail.
例句释义: 她准备查看邮箱是否有新邮件。

英文释义: a set of instructions that tells you how to cook something and the ingredients (= items of food) you need for it
例句: She is following the recipe on the website to make an apple pie.
例句释义: 她正在照着网上的食谱做苹果派。

详细释义: adj. 合理的；通情达理的；（价格）公道的
英文释义: fair and sensible; (of prices) not too expensive; acceptable and appropriate in a particular situation
例句: He bought the apples at a reasonable price.
例句释义: 他用合理的价格买了苹果。

英文释义: the act or process of getting ready for something or making something ready
例句: When cooking, cutting the vegetables is important preparation.
例句释义: 做饭的时候，切菜是重要的准备工作。

英文释义: made of wood
例句: All of the kitchenware in this set is wooden.
例句释义: 这套厨具全都是木制的。

英文释义: in or connected with the first stages of a course of study
例句: Most people receive their elementary school education from the age of 6 to 12.
例句释义: 大多数人在6岁到12岁之间接受小学教育。

英文释义: a public performance of music
例句: The animals are holding a concert in the forest!
例句释义: 动物们正在森林里开演唱会呢！

详细释义: adj.有侵略性的；积极进取的
英文释义: angry, and behaving in a threatening way; ready to attack
例句: I was terrified by this aggressive dog.
例句释义: 我被这只攻击性很强的狗吓到了。

英文释义: wrong; not correct or true; not genuine, but made to look real to cheat people; wrong or mistaken, because it is based on something that is not true or correct
例句: Is this question true or false?
例句释义: 这道题是对还是错？

英文释义: what you intend or plan to do; your aim
例句: I have every intention of buying a house, so I must start saving now.
例句释义: 我一心想买房，所以现在必须开始存钱了。

英文释义: a television or radio station
例句: We can use the remote control to change the channel.
例句释义: 我们可以用遥控器来换频道。

详细释义: adj. 极限的；极端的；  n. 极端
英文释义: not ordinary or usual; serious or severe
例句: While youngsters enjoy extreme sports, old people think it's courting death.
例句释义: 年轻人喜欢极限运动，老年人却认为这是在自取灭亡。

英文释义: a long, hollow object that is used especially to control the flow of a liquid or gas
例句: These tubes are made of steel.
例句释义: 这些管子都是钢做的。

英文释义: a picture made using a pencil or pen rather than paint; the art or skill of making pictures, plans, etc. using a pen or pencil
例句: That's a simple drawing of a big head man.
例句释义: 那是一张画有一个大头男人的简笔画。

英文释义: a substance found in foods (such as meat, milk, eggs, and beans) that is an important part of the human diet
例句: Eggs, beans and meat are all excellent sources of protein.
例句释义: 鸡蛋、大豆和肉类都是很好的蛋白质来源。

英文释义: to stop doing (an action or activity)
例句: The office worker was so happy after he quit his job.
例句释义: 这名员工辞掉工作后感到很开心。

英文释义: the fact of somebody being away from a place where they are usually expected to be; the occasion or period of time when somebody is away
例句: My boss noticed my co-worker's absence in the meeting.
例句释义: 老板注意到我同事没来开会。

详细释义: n. 拉丁语；  adj. 拉丁的
英文释义: the language of ancient Rome and the official language of its empire
例句: Latin is a language which the ancient Romans used to speak.
例句释义: 拉丁语是古罗马人使用的语言。

例句: High speed trains run so rapidly.
例句释义: 高铁开起来真的很快。

详细释义: n. 监狱；看守所；  v. 监禁；拘留
英文释义: a prison
例句: The prisoner can do nothing but sleep in his jail cell.
例句释义: 这名犯人在监狱里除了睡觉之外什么事都不能做。

英文释义: a range of many people or things that are very different from each other; the quality or fact of including a range of many people or things
例句: We can see a great ethnic diversity from these kids.
例句释义: 从这些孩子身上，我们可以看到种族多样性。

英文释义: always telling the truth, and never stealing or cheating
例句: "Wow, the emperor is naked!" shouted an honest boy.
例句释义: “哇哦，这个皇帝没穿衣服！” 一个诚实的小男孩大叫道。

英文释义: the speed at which somebody/something walks, runs or moves
例句: They were walking at a fast pace.
例句释义: 他们正在快步走。

英文释义: the act of employing someone or something
例句: She found employment as an English teacher.
例句释义: 她找到了一份英语老师的工作。

英文释义: the part of a radio, television, computer, etc., that changes electric signals into sound; a person who gives a talk or makes a speech
例句: She's a talented speaker and enjoys talking to a large audience.
例句释义: 她是一位才华横溢的演讲者，喜欢对众多听众讲话。

英文释义: an idea, a feeling or an opinion that you get about somebody/something, or that somebody/something gives you; the effect that an experience or a person has on somebody/something
例句: He left a good impression on the interviewer.
例句释义: 他给这位面试官留下了好印象。

英文释义: a short piece of writing on a particular subject, written in order to be published
例句: The girl is busy writing her essay right now.
例句释义: 这个女孩正忙着写她的论文。

详细释义: n. 答卷者，应答者，【法】被告；  adj. 回答的，应答的
英文释义: a person who answers questions, especially in a survey; (law) a person who is accused of something
例句: "Thank you for being a respondent for our survey."
例句释义: “感谢你帮助我们完成调查。”

英文释义: very large; much larger or more important than similar things usually are
例句: The giant rock is naturally balanced.
例句释义: 这块巨大的石头保持着天然的平衡。

英文释义: a sweet food made from a mixture of flour, eggs, butter, sugar, etc. that is baked in an oven. Cakes are made in various shapes and sizes and are often decorated, for example with cream or icing.; a food mixture that is cooked in a round flat shape
例句: Would you like some chocolate cake?
例句释义: 你想来点儿巧克力蛋糕吗？

详细释义: n. 历史学家，史学工作者
英文释义: a person who studies or writes about history; an expert in history
例句: This historian kept a record of historical events and people.
例句释义: 这位史学家记录了很多历史事件和人物。

英文释义: to try to reach an agreement by formal discussion; to arrange or agree something by formal discussion
例句: The two businessmen are negotiating in an office.
例句释义: 两个商人在办公室里谈判。

英文释义: to bring somebody/something back to a former condition, place or position; to bring back a situation or feeling that existed before
例句: We hope to restore the garden to its former beauty.
例句释义: 我们希望把花园恢复到它原来的美丽模样。

例句: The clothing store offered substantial discounts on all items to boost sales.
例句释义: 这家服装店对店内所有的商品进行大幅度打折以促进销售。

详细释义: v.发出（砰的响声）；  n.砰的一声爆破声；  adj.流行的，大众的
英文释义: to make a short explosive sound; to cause something to make this sound; to burst, or make something burst, with a short explosive sound; to suddenly appear, especially when not expected; to put something/somebody somewhere quickly, suddenly or for a short time
例句: Let's pop open the champagne!
例句释义: 让我们砰的一声开启这瓶香槟吧！

详细释义: n. 专科医生；专家；  adj. 专家的

例句: They are the specialists in our hospital.
例句释义: 他们是我们医院的专家。

英文释义: the point from which something starts; the cause of something
例句: The origin of humankind is still mysterious, but we think our ancestors lived in the trees.
例句释义: 虽然人类的起源仍然是谜，但是我们认为我们的祖先生活在树上。

英文释义: agreement to, or permission for something, especially a plan or request
例句: My boss showed his approval by his hand gesture.
例句释义: 老板用他的手势表达了他的赞同。

英文释义: with low volume
例句: She walked quietly because she didn't want to wake her friend up.
例句释义: 因为不想吵醒她的朋友，她安静地走着。

英文释义: to give somebody help and information on a subject that you know a lot about

例句释义: 我的英语考试不及格，老师建议我用这个应用程序。

详细释义: adj.依照惯例的，依照传统的

例句: Although we can now pay online, some people still prefer the conventional method of cash.
例句释义: 尽管我们现在可以线上支付了，部分人仍然喜欢传统的现金支付手段。

英文释义: the distance from the top or surface to the bottom of something
例句: These fish dived into a depth of 150 meters.
例句释义: 这些鱼潜至水下150米深处。

英文释义: a large amount of money, property, etc. that a person or country owns
例句: Save your wealth in case you need it later.
例句释义: 储存你的财富，以备不时之需。

英文释义: a physical or mental condition that means you cannot use a part of your body completely or easily, or that you cannot learn easily
例句: His disability didn't stop him from running.

详细释义: v. 批评，评论，挑剔，责难
