例句: The candy stopped the baby from crying very effectively.
例句释义: 糖果非常有效地让小宝宝停止了哭泣。

英文释义: of or relating to biology or to life and living things
例句: Biological science is concerned with research of animals, plants and micro-organisms.
例句释义: 生物科学涉及对动物、植物和微生物的研究。

英文释义: a round vegetable with many layers inside each other and a brown, red or white skin. Onions have a strong smell and flavour.
例句: She is slicing the onion with a knife.
例句释义: 她正在用刀切洋葱。

例句释义: 这家药品公司的医药代表正在和医生聊天。

详细释义: adj.平坦的；扁平的；  n.公寓；平面；  adv.平直地

英文释义: a type of product made by a particular company

详细释义: adj.异常狂暴的；蠢笨的；精神错乱的；生气的，狂怒的；  n.狂怒

英文释义: (often in names of particular awards) a prize such as money, etc. for something that somebody has done

英文释义: by means of a particular person, system, etc.; through a place

例句: This device can precisely measure the diameter of the bolt.

英文释义: the area at either side of the body between the top of the leg and the waist; the joint at the top of the leg

英文释义: a small device that you press or move up and down in order to turn a light or piece of electrical equipment on and off

英文释义: a substance obtained by or used in a chemical process

英文释义: to put a word or name on something to describe or identify it :to attach a label to (something)

英文释义: being of the age 13 through 19

英文释义: a person who supports or speaks in favour of somebody or of a public plan or action

例句释义: 她的小女儿在音乐方面天赋异禀。

例句释义: 这个农民的手很粗糙。

例句释义: 他对着手机喊得好大声！他肯定很生气！

英文释义: (of a woman or female animal) having a baby or young animal developing inside her/its body

例句释义: 这个怀孕的女人正在喝水。

英文释义: a device that shows what time it is and that is usually placed in a room or attached to a wall

例句释义: 好吃！这巧克力真好吃！

详细释义: adj.意大利的；  n.意大利人

详细释义: adj.普遍存在的；全体的；通用的；  n.普遍原则

例句释义: “看，我能让篮球在我的手指上转动！”小女孩说。

英文释义: extremely good
例句: Superman has all kinds of super powers, like flying and super strength!
例句释义: 超人有各种各样的超能力，比如飞行和超级力量。

详细释义: v. 出产；弯曲；屈服；让行；  n. 收益
英文释义: to produce or provide something, for example a profit, result or crop
例句: The fields yielded many carrots for harvest this year.
例句释义: 这块田今年产出了很多胡萝卜。

详细释义: n. 篱笆，围栏，栅栏；  v. 击剑；用篱笆围住；束缚
英文释义: a structure like a wall built outdoors usually of wood or metal that separates two areas or prevents people or animals from entering or leaving
例句: The school is surrounded by a large fence.
例句释义: 学校被很大的围栏围住。

英文释义: a painting, drawing or photograph of a person, especially of the head and shoulders; a detailed description of somebody/something
例句: This is a portrait of a man.
例句释义: 这是一幅男子的肖像。

英文释义: the state of continuing to live or exist, often despite difficulty or danger
例句: He taught me survival skills, like how to start a fire in the forest.
例句释义: 他教我野外求生技能，比如如何在森林里生火。

英文释义: approximately but not exactly
例句: Pi roughly equals 3.14.
例句释义: 圆周率约等于3.14。

英文释义: a process by which a court of law makes a decision to end a disagreement between people or organizations
例句: They have filed a lawsuit against the property dispute.
例句释义: 他们已经就房产纠纷问题提起了诉讼。

详细释义: n. 证据，证词；见证，证明
英文释义: a formal written or spoken statement saying what you know to be true, usually in court
例句: The witness gave the testimony that the criminal was a strong man.
例句释义: 目击者给出证言，罪犯是个强壮的男性。

详细释义: n.束，串，群，伙；  v.使成一束（或一群等）
英文释义: a group of things of the same kind that are held or tied together or that grow together
例句: This bunch of flowers is so beautiful.
例句释义: 这束花真漂亮呀！

例句: These two businessmen founded a new company together.
例句释义: 这两个商人一起创办了一家新公司。

详细释义: n.负担，重担；  vt.使负重，装载；烦扰
英文释义: a duty, responsibility, etc. that causes worry, difficulty or hard work; a heavy load that is difficult to carry
例句: Our burden is too heavy, because we have too much homework.
例句释义: 我们的负担太重了，因为每天都有很多作业。

英文释义: to change or behave in a particular way as a result of or in response to something
例句: Different people react differently when shown a horror movie.
例句释义: 看恐怖电影时不同的人有不同的反应。

英文释义: a hall in a public building that is used for formal meetings
例句: The chamber has enough seats for a meeting.
例句释义: 这个会议室有足够的座位来开会。

英文释义: objects that can be moved, such as tables, chairs and beds, that are put into a house or an office to make it suitable for living or working in
例句: All of his furniture came as a set.
例句释义: 他的所有家具都是成套的。

英文释义: the fact of doing something together or of working together towards a shared aim
例句: Cooperation between team members will be necessary to finish the task.
例句释义: 小组成员间的合作对于完成任务是很必要的。

英文释义: a tightly stretched piece of wire, nylon, or catgut on a musical instrument, that produces a musical note when the instrument is played
例句: Normally, a guitar has six strings.
例句释义: 正常情况下，一把吉他有六根弦。

英文释义: a public or religious occasion that includes a series of formal or traditional actions
例句: The student was awarded her certificate during the graduation ceremony.
例句释义: 这位毕业生在毕业典礼上被授予毕业证书。

详细释义: v. 沟通，交流；传达，传递
英文释义: to exchange information, news, ideas, etc. with somebody
例句: The police communicate with each other by radio.
例句释义: 警察通过无线电进行沟通。

详细释义: n.面颊，脸蛋；  vt.（口语）无礼地说
英文释义: either side of the face below the eyes
例句: My little brother has cute cheeks.
例句释义: 我弟弟有着可爱的脸蛋。

英文释义: unable to find your way; not knowing where you are
例句: The hikers are lost walking in the forest.
例句释义: 在森林中行走，这两个旅行者迷失了。

详细释义: n.侧面像；外形，轮廓；  v.描绘……的轮廓，扼要描述
英文释义: the outline of a person’s face when you look from the side, not the front
例句: This woman's profile is so charming.
例句释义: 这个女人的侧颜是如此迷人。

英文释义: a method or a system for achieving something; a system of parts in a living thing that together perform a particular function
例句: A watch's mechanism is very complicated.
例句释义: 手表内部的机械装置是很复杂的。

英文释义: if two people disagree or one person disagrees with another about something, they have a different opinion about it
例句: She disagreed with his advice.
例句释义: 她不赞同他提出的建议。

详细释义: n.惩罚，处罚；不利结果；点球
英文释义: a punishment for breaking a law, rule or contract
例句: You used your hands! The other side can take a penalty kick!
例句释义: 你用手了！对方可以罚一个点球！

详细释义: vi.（在别无办法的情况下）诉诸，采用；  n.诉诸，凭借；度假胜地
英文释义: (resort to) to make use of something, especially something bad, as a means of achieving something, often because there is no other possible solution; to seek aid, relief, or advantage
例句: He had to resort to selling his house because of the high medical costs.
例句释义: 高昂的医疗费用使他不得不卖掉房子。

英文释义: the act or process of damaging something so badly that it no longer exists or cannot be repaired :the act or process of destroying something
例句: The war caused the destruction of the city.
例句释义: 这场战争毁了整座城市。

英文释义: a piece of soft paper that absorbs liquids, used especially as a handkerchief; a collection of cells that form the different parts of humans, animals and plants; very thin paper used for wrapping and packing things that break easily
例句: The little girl uses a tissue when she sneezes.
例句释义: 打喷嚏时，小女孩用了张纸巾。

详细释义: adj. 宪法的；合乎宪法的；体质的；  n. 保健运动
英文释义: connected with the constitution of a country or an organization
例句: The U.S.A has a constitutional system to protect its citizens.
例句释义: 美国有一个宪法体系来保护美国公民。

详细释义: v.喘气，喘息；气喘吁吁地说
英文释义: to breathe quickly with short breaths, usually with your mouth open, because you have been doing some physical exercise, or because it is very hot
例句: Dogs pant with their mouths when they are tired.
例句释义: 狗累了的时候会张嘴喘气。

英文释义: someone who you have not met before or do not know
例句: Kids, be careful of strangers offering candy!
例句释义: 小朋友，小心拿糖给你吃的陌生人！

英文释义: the act or process of causing or getting a disease
例句: This poor guy has a really terrible lung infection.
例句释义: 这个可怜的家伙受到了很严重的肺部感染。

英文释义: a piece of furniture with doors, drawers and/or shelves, that is used for storing or showing things
例句: She keeps her beauty products in the bathroom cabinet.
例句释义: 她把护肤品放在浴室橱柜里。

英文释义: that has been damaged or injured; no longer whole or working correctly
例句: My heart was broken when my girlfriend left me.
例句释义: 当我女朋友离开我时，我的心都碎了。

英文释义: a round fruit with shiny red or green skin and firm white flesh
例句: I had an apple for breakfast today.
例句释义: 我今天早餐吃了一个苹果。

英文释义: connected with electricity; using, produced by or producing electricity
例句: Don't touch these wires; they will give you an electric shock.
例句释义: 不要碰这些电线，它们会让你触电。

详细释义: vi.前进，行进；  n.收入，获利
英文释义: to continue doing something that has already been started; to continue being done
例句: The girl proceeded only after the traffic light turned green.
例句释义: 绿灯亮起之后，这个小女孩才开始往前走。

英文释义: an arrangement to risk money, etc. on the result of a particular event; the money that you risk in this way
例句: The man made a bet on the score of a game.
例句释义: 这个人在比分上赌了一把。

详细释义: adj. 文学的，文学上的；以写作为职业的
英文释义: connected with literature
例句: She put many famous literary books on her bookshelf.
例句释义: 她在书架上放了很多文学名著。

英文释义: a living thing, too small to be seen without a microscope, that causes infectious disease in people, animals and plants
例句: This virus is really dangerous.
例句释义: 这种病毒很危险。

英文释义: not intelligent :having or showing a lack of ability to learn and understand things
例句: The stupid donkey couldn’t even work out this easy math problem.
例句释义: 这只蠢驴连这么简单的数学问题都算不出来。

详细释义: n.争论，争端；  v.争执，驳斥
英文释义: an argument or a disagreement between two people, groups or countries; discussion about a subject where there is disagreement
例句: They had a dispute over who should be his dance partner.
例句释义: 谁该成为他的舞伴，她们在这个问题上发生了争执。

英文释义: chance or luck, especially in the way it affects people’s lives
例句: What a good fortune! I won the first prize.
例句释义: 运气真好！我中了一等奖。

详细释义: adj.战略（上）的，对全局有重要意义的，关键的
英文释义: done as part of a plan that is meant to achieve a particular purpose or to gain an advantage; connected with getting an advantage in a war or other military situation
例句: Shanghai is of strategic importance to the international trade of China.
例句释义: 上海这座城市对中国的国际贸易具有重要的战略意义。

详细释义: n.助理，助手；  adj.助理的，辅助的
英文释义: a person who helps or supports somebody, usually in their job
例句: The businessman has an assistant to help him with his work every day.
例句释义: 这个商人有一名每天协助他工作的助理。

英文释义: to succeed in dealing with or controlling a problem that has been preventing you from achieving something; to defeat somebody
例句: The passenger overcame his fear of flying.
例句释义: 这位乘客克服了他对飞行的恐惧。

英文释义: unusual or surprising in a way that causes people to take notice
例句: Alex's performance has been remarkable in recent months!
例句释义: 亚历克斯这几个月的业绩非常出色！

英文释义: to fill or use a space, an area or an amount of time
例句: These desks were occupied in different kinds of ways.
例句释义: 这些桌子被以各种方式占据。

英文释义: a piece of information shown in numbers
例句: I use facts and statistics to prove my point.
例句释义: 我用事实和统计数字来证明我的观点。

英文释义: the activity of going to shops/stores and buying things
例句: Meow Meow went shopping for some fish.
例句释义: 喵喵为了买鱼去购物。

英文释义: a child of your uncle or aunt
例句: The boy likes to play with his little cousin.
例句释义: 男孩喜欢和他的小表妹一起玩。

详细释义: vt.邂逅，偶遇；  n.偶然碰见，遭遇
英文释义: to meet somebody, or discover or experience something, especially somebody/something new, unusual or unexpected; to experience something, especially something unpleasant or difficult, while you are trying to do something else
例句: I've never thought that I'd encounter my favorite star one day!
例句释义: 我从没想过有一天可以遇到我最喜欢的明星！

英文释义: to remove dirt, liquid, etc. from something by using a cloth, your hand, etc.
例句: The woman is wiping the mirror with a rag.
例句释义: 这个女人正在用抹布擦拭镜子。

英文释义: at the beginning
例句: People initially lived in caves; now they live in houses.
例句释义: 人们最初住在山洞里，现在住在房子里。

详细释义: adj.失明的；  v.使失明；  n.卷帘
英文释义: unable to see
例句: The blind woman is crossing the street with her guide dog.
例句释义: 这位失明的女士正和她的导盲犬一起过街。

英文释义: a place where ships load and unload goods or shelter from storms
例句: There are hundreds of containers in the port.
例句释义: 港口有成百上千的集装箱。

英文释义: a form of energy from charged elementary particles, usually supplied as electric current through cables, wires, etc. for lighting, heating, driving machines, etc.
例句: He touched the socket with a wet finger and the electricity gave him a shock.
例句释义: 他用湿手碰到了墙上的插座，被电到了。

英文释义: connected with genes (= the units in the cells of a living thing that control its physical characteristics) or genetics (= the study of genes )
例句: Once I saw her mother, I realized that her blonde hair must be genetic.
例句释义: 一看到她母亲，我就明白了她的金发是遗传的。

英文释义: someone who speaks for or represents a person, company, etc.
例句: The basketball player's spokesman said he could not play next year.
例句释义: 这个篮球运动员的发言人称他明年不能再打球了。

英文释义: to keep something; to continue to have something; to continue to hold or contain something;
例句: Hot water can retain its heat for hours in the vacuum cup.
例句释义: 热水能在保温杯里保持温度好几个小时。

英文释义: the second of two things or people mentioned
例句: When asked which he would prefer, an apple or a pizza, the boy chose the latter.
例句释义: 当被问到更喜欢苹果还是比萨时，男孩选择了后者。

英文释义: something that encourages you to do something; a payment or concession (= a reduction in the amount of money that has to be paid) that encourages somebody to do something
例句: The carrot serves as an incentive to drive the horse.
例句释义: 胡萝卜激励着马前行。

详细释义: n.奴隶；  vi.奴隶般地工作，苦干
英文释义: a person who is owned by another person and is forced to work for them; a person who is so strongly influenced by something that they cannot live without it, or cannot make their own decisions; a device
例句: These slaves are chained together.
例句释义: 这几个奴隶被锁在了一起。

英文释义: to express the meaning of speech or writing in a different language; to be changed from one language to another
例句: The girl used a phone app to translate this phrase into English.
例句释义: 女孩用手机应用把这个短语翻译成了英文。

详细释义: adj. 精确的；正确的；符合标准的
英文释义: an accurate throw, shot, weapon, etc. hits or reaches the thing that it was aimed at; conforming exactly or almost exactly to fact or to a standard or performing with total accuracy
例句: I never miss my target because my aim is so accurate.
例句释义: 我从未失手，因为我瞄得很准。

英文释义: used to compare or contrast two facts
例句: The line chart shows one thing, whereas the bar chart shows another.
例句释义: 折线图显示的是一回事，而柱状图显示的则是另一回事。

英文释义: a feeling of extreme fear; a person, situation or thing that makes you very afraid
例句: They shouted in terror when they saw the spider.
例句释义: 当看见蜘蛛时，他们吓得尖叫起来。

英文释义: an act of increasing or making something increase in size, amount or importance
例句: Our company has undergone steady expansion for the last ten years.
例句释义: 在过去的十年中，我们公司实现了稳定的扩大发展。

英文释义: a small group of people in a society, etc. who are powerful and have a lot of influence, because they are rich, intelligent, etc.
例句: Only a few elites can make it to the top of the pyramid.
例句释义: 只有少数精英能到达金字塔顶端。

英文释义: connected with the Olympic Games
例句: The five rings are the symbol of the Olympic Games.
例句释义: 五环是奥运会的象征。

英文释义: any substance that makes something dirty, for example dust, soil or mud
例句: The vacuum cleaner helps me to get rid of the dirt.
例句释义: 真空吸尘器帮我除去灰尘。

英文释义: strange or unusual
例句: It is so odd of him to be like this.
例句释义: 他这样看起来很奇怪。

英文释义: short, narrow white or brown grain grown on wet land in hot countries as food; the plant that produces this grain
例句: I'll cook rice for dinner.
例句释义: 晚餐我会煮米饭。

英文释义: a small piece of metal or another material that is shot out of a gun
例句: Here are several different types of bullets.
例句释义: 这里是几种不同种类的子弹。

详细释义: adj.紧身的，紧的；紧贴的，牢固的；  adv.紧紧地，牢牢地
英文释义: fitting closely to your body and sometimes uncomfortable
例句: Oh no, these clothes are too tight for me.
例句释义: 哦不，这衣服对我来说太紧了。

英文释义: the holy book of the Christian religion, consisting of the Old Testament and the New Testament
例句: The Bible is the holy book of the Christian religion.
例句释义: 《圣经》是基督教的圣书。

详细释义: n.图表，表格；  vt.制成图表
英文释义: a page or sheet of information in the form of diagrams, lists of figures, etc.
例句: This chart shows that annual sales have continued to rise.
例句释义: 这张图显示年度销售额持续上升。

英文释义: of or connected with the sun; produced by or using the sun's light or heat
例句: Solar energy is from the sun.
例句释义: 太阳能来自太阳。

详细释义: n.正方形；广场；  adj.正方形的
英文释义: an open area in a town, usually with four sides, surrounded by buildings
例句: This square is a nice, quiet place to take a walk.
例句释义: 这个广场安静宜人，是个散步的好地方。

英文释义: the ability to direct all your effort and attention on one thing, without thinking of other things
例句: Repairing watches requires a great deal of concentration.
例句释义: 修理手表需要注意力非常集中。

英文释义: made of many different things or parts that are connected; difficult to understand
例句: The aged professor is explaining a complicated math problem.
例句释义: 年迈的教授在解释一个复杂的数学问题。

英文释义: With a mild, kind, or tender manner
例句: Children treat their toys gently.
例句释义: 孩子们对他们的玩具很温柔。

详细释义: n.冠军，优胜者；  adj.夺得第一名的
英文释义: a person, team, etc. that has won a competition, especially in a sport
例句: The French football team became the champion of the 2018 World Cup!
例句释义: 法国足球队成为2018年世界杯冠军！

详细释义: n.情况，情节；剧情梗概；设想
英文释义: a description of how things might happen in the future
例句: He is thinking about the worst case scenario as he is late for work.
例句释义: 他正在预想迟到后会发生的最糟糕的情况。

详细释义: n.望远镜；  v.缩短，精简；（使）套入；  adj.套筒的，伸缩式的
英文释义: a piece of equipment shaped like a tube, containing lenses, that you look through to make objects that are far away appear larger and nearer
例句: You can see many distant stars through the telescope.
例句释义: 通过望远镜，你可以看到许多遥远的星星。

英文释义: an image in a mirror, on a shiny surface, on water, etc.
例句: Look at the reflection of those dancers in the water!
例句释义: 看舞者们在水中的倒影！

英文释义: an attempt, by a large number of people, to change the government of a country, especially by violent action; a great change in conditions, ways of working, beliefs, etc. that affects large numbers of people
例句: A revolution in science and technology has changed the way that we communicate.
例句释义: 科技革命改变了我们的通信方式。

详细释义: v.脱衣服；  n.长条形土地
英文释义: to take off all or most of your clothes or another person’s clothes
例句: Please strip off your clothes for the medical exam.
例句释义: 请脱掉你的衣服配合体检。

详细释义: v. 口译；解释；把……理解为
英文释义: to translate one language into another as you hear it
例句: I interpreted his words into English.
例句释义: 我把他的话口译成了英文。

英文释义: having or showing the feelings that friends have for each other
例句: Tom and his buddy are very friendly with each other.
例句释义: 汤姆和他的伙计互相很友好。

英文释义: a sports competition involving a number of teams or players who take part in different games and must leave the competition if they lose. The competition continues until there is only the winner left.
例句: A tournament is a sports competition which continues until only the winner is left.
例句释义: 锦标赛是一种体育竞赛，其赛事会一直持续到只剩下冠军为止。

英文释义: a thing that is invented or imagined and is not true
例句: I like science fiction movies with spaceships.
例句释义: 我喜欢有太空飞船的科幻片。

英文释义: to discover or notice the presence of (something that is hidden or hard to see, hear, taste, etc.)
例句: The detective detected a few clues about who committed the crime.
例句释义: 侦探发现了一些关于罪犯的线索。

详细释义: adj.巨大的；精彩的，出色的；惊人的
英文释义: very great
例句: I feel the tremendous pressure of car and house loans on my shoulders.
例句释义: 我感觉肩上扛着巨大的车贷和房贷压力。

英文释义: the length of time that somebody lives or that something lasts
例句: They remained close friends throughout their whole lifetime.
例句释义: 她们是一生一世的好朋友。

英文释义: an official suggestion about the best thing to do; the act of telling somebody that something is good or useful or that somebody would be suitable for a particular job, etc.; a formal letter or statement that somebody would be suitable for a particular job, etc.
例句: He accepted the waiter's recommendation and ordered dumplings.
例句释义: 他接受了服务员的建议，点了饺子。

英文释义: a member of a senate
例句: These two senators met in front of the Congress building.
例句释义: 这两位参议员在国会大厦前见面。

英文释义: the pursuit and killing or capture of wild animals regarded as a sport
例句: He went hunting with his hound.
例句释义: 他带着猎犬去打猎。

英文释义: a mixture of raw vegetables such as lettuce, tomato and cucumber, usually served with other food as part of a meal
例句: I'm on a diet, so I'll just have a salad. Thanks!
例句释义: 我正在减肥，所以我只吃沙拉，谢谢！

英文释义: a written promise given by a company that something you buy will be replaced or repaired without payment if it goes wrong within a particular period
例句: We guarantee to deliver your package within three days.
例句释义: 我们保证在三天内将您的包裹送达。

英文释义: lacking experience with the world and the bad things that happen in life
例句: The newborn baby looks innocent when he smiles.
例句释义: 这个新生儿笑的时候看起来好单纯。

英文释义: a real or imagined line that marks the limits or edges of something and separates it from other things or places; a dividing line
例句: Many students will draw a line on the desk as the boundary.
例句释义: 许多学生会在课桌上画一条线作为分界。

详细释义: v.暂停播放；暂停，中止；  n.中止，暂停
英文释义: to stop talking or doing something for a short time before continuing
例句: The video was paused for a moment.
例句释义: 视频暂停了一下。

详细释义: n. 遥控器；  adj. 关系远的
英文释义: [countable] a device that allows you to operate a television, etc. from a distance
例句: You need a remote to turn on the air conditioner.
例句释义: 你需要遥控器才能打开空调。

英文释义: the good feeling that you have when you have achieved something or when something that you wanted to happen does happen; something that gives you this feeling
例句: I gave their service a good rating to show my satisfaction.
例句释义: 我给了好评来表示我对他们的服务很满意。

详细释义: n.日志，日记；定期刊物，杂志
英文释义: a written record of the things you do, see, etc. every day
例句: Every night I write about my day in my journal.
例句释义: 每天晚上我都要写一篇关于我的一天的日记。

英文释义: a long seat for two or more people, usually made of wood
例句: The boy is sitting on the bench with his mother.
例句释义: 小男孩正和他的妈妈坐在长凳上。

英文释义: a partner in a romantic or sexual relationship
例句: The lovers embraced each other tightly.
例句释义: 这对恋人紧紧相拥在一起。

详细释义: adj. 生的，未煮过的；未加工的
英文释义: not cooked
例句: The beef on the wooden board is raw.
例句释义: 木板上的牛肉是生的。

英文释义: knowing something; knowing that something exists and is important; being interested in something
例句: He tries to raise people's awareness of the importance of recycling.
例句释义: 他试图增强人们对回收利用的重要性的意识。

详细释义: adj.令人惊讶的，令人惊喜的
英文释义: causing surprise
例句: The cat's spot on its mouth is a surprising feature.
例句释义: 这只猫嘴上的斑点是个非常令人惊讶的特征。

英文释义: to take money out of a bank account
例句: The woman is withdrawing money from the ATM with her two bodyguards.
例句释义: 这个女人正带着她的两个保镖从自助取款机取钱。

英文释义: the top outside floor of a ship or boat; one of the floors of a ship or a bus; a complete set of 52 playing cards
例句: The couple are relaxing on the deck of the ship.
例句释义: 这对情侣在甲板上休息。

英文释义: in almost the same way; used to say that two facts, actions, statements, etc. are like each other
例句: The group of teenagers are dressed similarly.
例句释义: 这群年轻人的穿着很相似。

英文释义: (usually before a past participle) recently
例句: The newly born baby sleeps most of the day.
例句释义: 新出生的婴儿一天中大部分时间在睡觉。

英文释义: a long thin straight piece of wood or metal, especially one with the end placed in the ground, used as a support
例句: The telephone pole holds the cables.
例句释义: 电线杆支撑着电缆。

详细释义: v.作证；证实；证明；声明；见证（上帝的存在）
英文释义: to make a statement that something happened or that something is true, especially as a witness in court
例句: The man who witnessed the crime testified before the jury.
例句释义: 这场犯罪的目击者在陪审团面前出庭作证。

英文释义: the way in which a piece of equipment is set to perform a particular task; a particular way of doing something
例句: The camera has many different modes.
例句释义: 这台照相机有很多种不同的拍摄模式。

英文释义: a conversation between two or more people
例句: These two women are having a dialogue over their babies .
例句释义: 这两个女人在谈论她们的小孩。

英文释义: to express (something) in an indirect way :to suggest (something) without saying or showing it plainly
例句: The little boy implied his craving for this cherry.
例句释义: 小男孩暗示了他对这颗樱桃的渴望。

英文释义: in a way that shows or uses abilities or qualities that a person or an animal is born with
例句: Some people have naturally frizzy hair.
例句释义: 有的人天生卷发。

英文释义: shared by two or more people
例句: The two sides established a mutual understanding.
例句释义: 双方达成一致。

英文释义: a person who starts an organization, institution, etc. or causes something to be built
例句: He is widely regarded as the founder of modern physics.
例句释义: 他被广泛认为是现代物理学的奠基者。

英文释义: having the most modern and recently developed ideas, methods, etc.
例句: The robot is so advanced that it can cook many different meals.
例句释义: 这个机器人很先进，能做各式各样的佳肴。

英文释义: a feeling of pleasure or satisfaction that you get when you or people who are connected with you have done something well or own something that other people admire
例句: Our manager wants us to feel pride in the quality of our work.
例句释义: 我们的经理想让我们为自己工作的质量而感到骄傲。

详细释义: v.开除；解散；摒除，不再考虑
英文释义: to officially remove somebody from their job; to send somebody away or allow them to leave; to put thoughts or feelings out of your mind
例句: The boss dismissed the employee.
例句释义: 老板开除了那个员工。

英文释义: any vehicle that can fly and carry goods or passengers
例句: Aircraft are meant to be in the sky.
例句释义: 飞机注定要飞上天空。

英文释义: the act of taking goods, letters, etc. to the people they have been sent to; the process of giving birth to a baby
例句: I waited all day for the delivery of books to arrive.
例句释义: 我等这些书的快递送来等了一整天。

英文释义: for the most part
例句: He spends his money on many things, but mainly on food and drink.
例句释义: 他把钱花在很多东西上，但主要是饮食方面。

英文释义: to cook food in an oven without extra fat or liquid; to be cooked in this way
例句: This pizza is oven-baked and 100% delicious.
例句释义: 这个比萨是用炉子烤的，百分之百好吃。

详细释义: v.冻结，结冰；使冻僵；  n.严寒，冻结
英文释义: to become hard, and often turn to ice, as a result of extreme cold; to make something do this
例句: Water freezes at 0°C.
例句释义: 水在零摄氏度时会结冰。

英文释义: the raised flat area beside the track at a train station where you get on or off the train
例句: The train is passing platform 4.
例句释义: 列车正在经过4号站台。

详细释义: v. 资金供给，筹措资金；  n. 金融，财政，资金
英文释义: to provide money for a project
例句: The old man financed the poor student's education.
例句释义: 老人资助那个贫困学生上大学。

详细释义: n.水槽，洗碗池；  v.（使）下沉，（使）降低
英文释义: a large open container in a kitchen that has taps/faucets to supply water and that you use for washing dishes in
例句: I wash the dishes in the sink.
例句释义: 我在水槽里洗碗。

详细释义: adj.（事物）有吸引人的，诱人的；有魅力的，性感的；引起兴趣的
英文释义: (of a thing or a place) pleasant; (of a person) pleasant to look at, especially in a sexual way
例句: With such a low price, the hotel room is really attractive.
例句释义: 这间旅馆的房间价格如此低廉，真的很吸引人。

英文释义: very different from each other and of various kinds
例句: A diverse team can cooperate with each other and achieve a common goal.
例句释义: 多元化的团队可以相互协作，实现共同的目标。

英文释义: having ideas that are valuable and useful to people in their lives and work
例句: Before you write this essay, you should read some books relevant to the subject.
例句释义: 在写这篇论文之前，你应该阅读一些和主题相关的书籍。

详细释义: adj. 理想的；  n. 理想
英文释义: existing only in your imagination or as an idea; not likely to be real
例句: A couch potato's ideal weekend is to lay on the sofa, watching TV and eating snacks.
例句释义: 一个电视迷的理想周末是躺在沙发上看电视、吃零食。

英文释义: a feeling of great happiness
例句: The father and son had some joy together.
例句释义: 这对父子在一起很开心。

例句: We meet regularly to discuss the progress of the project.
例句释义: 我们定期会面，讨论工程进展情况。

例句: His working conditions are very poor.
例句释义: 他的工作环境很差。

英文释义: a person who sings, or whose job is singing, especially in public
例句: The singer is recording a song in the recording studio.
例句释义: 歌手正在录音棚里录歌。

英文释义: to change or develop slowly often into a better, more complex, or more advanced state :to develop by a process of evolution
例句: Even today,the human race continues to evolve - or maybe devolve.
例句释义: 即使在今天，人类仍然在不断进化，或者说退化。

英文释义: the activity or sport of killing wild animals with a gun
例句: She wore protective gear for her eyes and ears during shooting practice.
例句释义: 射击训练中，她戴着保护眼睛和耳朵的防护装备。

详细释义: adv. 部分地，在一定程度上
英文释义: to some extent; not completely
例句: This droid is partly functional having lost an arm.
例句释义: 失去了一只手臂，这个机器人只有部分功能可用了。

详细释义: adj. 不知道的，未知的，不知名的
英文释义: not known or identified; not famous or well known
例句: It's unknown where the flying object came from.
例句释义: 不明飞行物从何而来仍是未知的。

详细释义: n. 犯罪，冒犯，过错，触怒，犯规，进攻
英文释义: an illegal act; the act of upsetting or insulting somebody; the members of a team whose main aim is to score points against the other team; a method of attack
例句: The dog gets an offense from its host and looks angry.
例句释义: 狗狗被主人惹恼了，看起来十分生气。

详细释义: n.柜台；回击，反击；  v.抵制；  adv.相反地
英文释义: a long flat surface over which goods are sold or business is done in a shop/store, bank, etc.
例句: Customers pay money at the counter.
例句释义: 顾客在柜台付钱。

英文释义: to show that somebody/something is right or reasonable
例句: He is trying to justify his rude behavior.
例句释义: 他正试图为自己粗鲁的行为辩解。

英文释义: to say or do something to show that you disagree with or disapprove of something, especially publicly
例句: Raising fists and flags is a symbol of protesting something.
例句释义: 举起拳头和旗帜是抗议的一种标志。

详细释义: v.碰撞；坠落；崩溃；  n.撞车；坠落；轰隆声
英文释义: an accident in which a vehicle hits something, for example another vehicle, usually causing damage and often injuring or killing the passengers
例句: The car behind crashed into the car in front!
例句释义: 后面的车撞上前面那辆了！

英文释义: an activity involving a special skill at making things with your hands; all the skills needed for a particular activity; skill in making people believe what you want them to believe; a boat or ship; an aircraft or spacecraft
例句: Crafts usually involve making things skillfully with one's hands.
例句释义: 手工艺品中往往包含了熟练的手工制作。

英文释义: a formal agreement between two or more countries
例句: The two countries ceased fire and signed the peace treaty.
例句释义: 两个国家停战并签订了和平条约。

英文释义: a person who takes part in terrorism
例句: The durian terrorist is trying to attack other fruits.
例句释义: 榴恐怖分子正试图攻击其他水果。

英文释义: the ability to see and understand the truth about people or situations; an understanding of what something is like
例句: He really has an insight into math.
例句释义: 他对数学真的有很深刻的见解。

详细释义: v. 拥有，占有；缠住，迷住
英文释义: to have or own something; to have a particular quality or feature
例句: Individuals who possess a luxury yacht must have a lot of money.
例句释义: 拥有豪华游艇的人一定很有钱。

详细释义: n.水龙头；  v.监听，窃听 (电话)
英文释义: a device for controlling the flow of water from a pipe into a bath/ bathtub or sink; a device for controlling the flow of liquid or gas from a pipe or container
例句: Water flows from the tap.
例句释义: 水从水龙头流出来。

英文释义: large in size or amount :very full or complete
例句: The flood lead to extensive flooding of the area.
例句释义: 洪水导致该地区大面积泛滥。

英文释义: one part of a story that is broadcast on television or radio in several parts
例句: Episode 1 of this TV series is being shown now.
例句释义: 现在正在播放该电视剧的第一集。

详细释义: v. 游泳；眩晕；  n. 游泳
英文释义: (of a person) to move through water in a horizontal position using the arms and legs
例句: She can swim like a fish! Look at her!
例句释义: 看看她！她能像鱼一样游泳！

英文释义: a thick rubber ring that fits around the edge of a wheel of a car, bicycle, etc.
例句: The tires are arranged in order on the shelves.
例句释义: 轮胎被整齐摆放在货架上。

详细释义: n.过失；【地质学】断层；  v.责备，挑错
英文释义: the responsibility for something wrong that has happened or been done
例句: It's the boy's fault that the window was broken.
例句释义: 窗户破了是这个男孩的错。

详细释义: adj.宽松的；（指言行等）不严谨的；  v.松开
英文释义: not fitting closely; not firmly fixed where it should be; able to become separated from something; not tied together; not held in position by anything or contained in anything; free to move around without control; not tied up or shut in somewhere
例句: "I've lost so much weight that my old pants are too loose to wear!"
例句释义: “我瘦了好多，以前的裤子都松得不能穿了！”

详细释义: adv.不久，立刻；生气地，不耐烦地
英文释义: a short time; not long; soon
例句: The note on the door said that they would be back shortly.
例句释义: 门上的纸条写着他们不久就会回来。

例句: Originally, there was merely a piece of waste land.
例句释义: 最初，这里只是一块荒地。

详细释义: adj.相当大的；重要的；可观的
英文释义: great in amount, size, importance, etc.
例句: Students have considerable pressure in their final year of university.
例句释义: 学生在大学的最后一年有相当大的压力。

英文释义: existing earlier in time
例句: She had to refuse the invitation because of a prior arrangement.
例句释义: 由于事先有安排了，她不得不拒绝这个邀请。

详细释义: adj. 智力的；需用智力的；  n. 知识分子
英文释义: of or relating to the ability to think in a logical way
例句: Newton's intellectual mind had been inspired by an apple.
例句释义: 牛顿的智力思维受到了苹果的启发。

详细释义: n. 攻击，袭击；  v. 攻击，袭击，殴打
英文释义: the crime of attacking somebody physically; (by an army, etc.) the act of attacking a building, an area, etc. in order to take control of it; an act of criticizing somebody/something severely
例句: The troops are conducting an assault on the enemy lines.
例句释义: 军队正在对敌方防线展开袭击。

英文释义: to rest while you are doing something enjoyable, especially after work or effort
例句: Taking a bath is a good way to relax yourself.
例句释义: 泡澡是很好的放松方式。

英文释义: a series of steps that go from one level or floor to another
例句: The stairs ascend in a graceful curve.
例句释义: 这个楼梯呈优美的曲线上升。

英文释义: an unusual, exciting or dangerous experience, journey or series of events
例句: The boy went on an adventure in the jungle.
例句释义: 这个男孩到丛林里冒险了。

详细释义: adj. 外面的，外部的；外国的
英文释义: connected with or located on the outside of something/somebody
例句: This medicine is just for external use so we can't spray it to our mouth.
例句释义: 这种药只能外用，我们不能往嘴里喷。

英文释义: information, documents, etc. that show that something is true; the process of testing whether something is true or a fact; a way of proving that a statement is true or that what you have calculated is correct; a copy of printed material which is produced so that mistakes can be corrected
例句: We have proof that you're sick.
例句释义: 我们有证据表明你生病了。

英文释义: feeling sure about your own ability to do things and be successful
例句: The cat felt confident; in his mind, he was a powerful beast.
例句释义: 这只猫很有自信；在他的心目中，自己是一只强大的野兽。

详细释义: n. 总部，总局；司令部，指挥部
英文释义: a place from which an organization or a military operation is controlled
例句: The building is the headquarters of the family firm.
例句释义: 这座大楼是该家族公司的总部。

英文释义: happening or done quickly and unexpectedly
例句: The boy was scared by the sudden burst of the balloon.
例句释义: 气球突然爆了，吓了男孩一跳。

详细释义: adj.肮脏的，有灰尘的；  v.弄脏，玷污；  adv.不公平地，不诚实地
英文释义: not clean
例句: His hands are very dirty.
例句释义: 他的手很脏。

英文释义: the act of going against or refusing to obey a law, an agreement, etc.
例句: The?violation?of the rules of the road may?result?in?a terrible injury.
例句释义: 违反道路安全规则可能会使你受伤。

英文释义: the soft part in the mouth that moves around, used for tasting, swallowing, speaking, etc.
例句: The boy sticks out his tongue to make a face to me.
例句释义: 男孩伸出了舌头来对我做鬼脸。

详细释义: n.执照；许可；  v.发许可证
英文释义: an official document that shows that permission has been given to do, own or use something
例句: You should obtain a license before driving on the road.
例句释义: 开车上路前，你要先有驾照。

详细释义: n. 隐蔽处，躲避处（常用来指住处）；  v. 遮蔽，掩护，庇护
英文释义: a building, usually owned by a charity, that provides a place to stay for people without a home, or protection for people or animals who have been badly treated
例句: Someone used branches to make a shelter in the woods.
例句释义: 有人用树枝在树林里搭了个躲避处。

英文释义: to move your hand, or something such as a cloth, backwards and forwards over a surface while pressing firmly
例句: The little girl is rubbing her left eye.
例句释义: 这个小女孩正在揉她的左眼。

英文释义: public discussion and argument about something that many people strongly disagree about, disapprove of, or are shocked by
例句: Which kind of flavor is more delicious? There was controversy over the result.
例句释义: 哪种味道更美味？关于这个问题的讨论结果引起了争议。

英文释义: a door, gate, passage, etc. used for entering a room, building or place
例句: Children are gathering at the entrance of the park.
例句释义: 孩子们在公园的入口处集合。

英文释义: in a way that is acceptable or suitable
例句: It's important to sit properly at your desk.
例句释义: 正确地坐在桌前很重要。

详细释义: vi.逐渐消失；  vt.使褪色；  adj.乏味的
英文释义: to disappear gradually
例句: The trees were fading away into the mist.
例句释义: 树渐渐消失在薄雾中。

详细释义: adj. 防御用的；  n. 防御
英文释义: protecting somebody/something against attack
例句: The army's defensive formation offered very good protection from arrows.
例句释义: 军队的防御队形保护其免受箭矢的射击。

英文释义: a very sad event or situation, especially one that involves death; a serious play with a sad ending, especially one in which the main character dies; plays of this type
例句: They are performing a classic tragedy at the theatre.
例句释义: 他们正在剧院里表演一出经典悲剧。

详细释义: n. 网，网状物；  adj. 纯利的，净值的，净的
英文释义: a type of material that is made of string, thread or wire twisted or tied together, with small spaces in between; (especially in compounds) a piece of net used for a particular purpose, such as catching fish or covering something; (in sports) the frame covered in net that forms the goal
例句: The football was kicked into the net.
例句释义: 足球被踢进了网内。

英文释义: to give somebody/something its typical or most noticeable qualities or features
例句: They two are characterized by the sexy lips.
例句释义: 他们两个的特点在于其性感的嘴唇。

英文释义: a ceremony, usually a religious one, for burying or cremating (= burning) a dead person
例句: They were really sad during their father's funeral.
例句释义: 他们在父亲的葬礼上悲痛不已。

英文释义: a type of job that needs special training or skill, especially one that needs a high level of education
例句: Whatever profession you choose, work hard to be the best!
例句释义: 无论你选择什么职业，努力做到最好吧！

英文释义: to make changes to a piece of clothing so that it will fit you better
例句: The boy altered the setting of the light.
例句释义: 这个男孩改变了灯的设置。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to be the parts that together form something; to form a group legally or officially; (not used in the progressive tenses) to be considered to be something
例句: Bread, beef, cheese and salad constitute the perfect burger.
例句释义: 面包、牛肉、芝士和沙拉组成了一个完美的汉堡。

英文释义: a place or organization where people live or do business
例句: He cut the ribbon at the grand opening of the establishment.
例句释义: 在这场盛大的开幕仪式上，他负责剪彩。

详细释义: v.(常指用手)挤压；挤进，塞进；用力挤压榨取；  n.挤压
英文释义: to get liquid out of something by pressing or twisting it hard
例句: She squeezes the toothpaste onto the toothbrush.
例句释义: 她把牙膏挤到牙刷上。

英文释义: the ability to create pictures in your mind; the part of your mind that does this; the ability to have new and exciting ideas
例句: It's fun to use your imagination to find pictures in the clouds.
例句释义: 靠你的想象在云朵中找图画很有趣。

详细释义: n.面具；  vt.隐藏；掩盖，掩饰；伪装
英文释义: a covering for part or all of the face, worn to hide or protect it
例句: When he took his mask off, I saw that he looked very different.
例句释义: 当他摘下面具时，我看见了他完全不同的面貌。

详细释义: v. 可转变为，可变换成；改变，转变，转化；使改变信仰
英文释义: to be able to be changed from one form, purpose, or system to another
例句: Cool! The sofa can be easily converted into a bed.
例句释义: 真棒！这张沙发轻轻松松就能变成一张床。

详细释义: adj. 全面的，完整的；详尽的；综合的；广泛的，无所不包的；广义的
英文释义: includes everything that is needed or relevant; including all, or almost all, the items, details, facts, information, etc., that may be concerned
例句: She's making a comprehensive consideration of all her options.
例句释义: 她正在全面考虑她所做的选择。

英文释义: important and well-known; easily seen; sticking out from something
例句: A single tree in a field will appear to be more prominent.
例句释义: 田地里一棵孤零零的树会更显眼。

英文释义: the act of showing something or of giving something to somebody
例句: The student is giving a presentation about how to roll the dough scientifically.
例句释义: 这个学生正在做一个关于如何擀面的报告。

详细释义: adv.不顾一切地；  adj.不顾的，不管的
英文释义: paying no attention, even if the situation is bad or there are difficulties
例句: She goes for running regardless of the cold weather.
例句释义: 尽管天气很冷，她仍然去跑步了。

详细释义: v.装载；使担负；装填（弹药、胶卷或磁带等）；  n.承载量，容纳量
英文释义: to put a large quantity of things or people onto or into something
例句: The worker is loading the goods into the truck.
例句释义: 这个工人正在将货物装进卡车。

详细释义: adj.稳定的；  n.马厩；  vt.使（马）入厩
英文释义: firmly fixed; not likely to move, change or fail
例句: The cards placed this way are stable.
例句释义: 这样放置的扑克牌处于稳定状态。

英文释义: the act of making one person formally known to another, in which you tell each the other’s name
例句: The girl is making an introduction of her boyfriend to her parents.
例句释义: 这个女孩正在向父母介绍她的男朋友。

英文释义: to behave in a particular way, in order to make other people believe something that is not true; (especially of children) to imagine that something is true as part of a game;  (usually used in negative sentences and questions) to claim to be, do or have something, especially when this is not true
例句: I pretended to study hard, but actually I chatted on my phone.
例句释义: 我假装很努力地学习，但是实际上我在手机上聊天。

英文释义: people who are old
例句: This elderly couple are happy in their old age.
例句释义: 这对老夫妇在老年时也很幸福。

英文释义: the fact of having representatives who will speak or vote for you or on your behalf
例句: All the animal representations have attended this international conference.
例句释义: 动物代表们都出席了此次国际会议。

英文释义: an animal with long legs, that eats grass, leaves, etc. and can run fast. Most male deer have antlers
例句: The girl with food was immediately surrounded by deer.
例句释义: 拿着食物的小女孩被小鹿们迅速围住了。

英文释义: to tear, or to make something tear, along a straight line
例句: They split up after their love was broken.
例句释义: 他们感情破碎后就分开了。

英文释义: to go against or refuse to obey a law, an agreement, etc.
例句: The bird's behavior violated the sign's rules.
例句释义: 鸟儿的行为违反了这个标牌上的规定。

英文释义: the state of being a partner in business
例句: Their companies are working together in a partnership for the project.
例句释义: 他们的公司正在为这个项目合作。

英文释义: substances that make air, water, soil, etc. dirty
例句: Pollution from the factories made the sky turn gray.
例句释义: 工厂带来的污染物使天空变成了灰色。

英文释义: the production or sending out of light, heat, gas, etc.
例句: The emissions from the coal power station pollute the air.
例句释义: 燃煤发电站排放的废气会污染空气。

详细释义: adj.坚定的，扎实的；稳定的，不变的；  v.（使）稳固
英文释义: developing, growing, etc. gradually and in an even and regular way
例句: The stone house is quite steady under the extreme weather.
例句释义: 石屋在极端天气中非常稳固。

详细释义: adj.必不可少的，至关重要的；有活力的
英文释义: connected with or necessary for staying alive
例句: Water is vital to living beings.
例句释义: 水对生物来说是必不可少的。

英文释义: the things, especially bad things, that will happen or have happened to somebody/something; the power that is believed to control everything that happens and that cannot be stopped or changed
例句: Let this coin decide my fate!
例句释义: 就让这个硬币来决定我的命运吧！

英文释义: the money that you earn for the work that you do
例句: A rise in his online business earnings made him excited.
例句释义: 网络业务收入的增长让他兴奋不已。

英文释义: the part of a cooker/stove shaped like a box with a door on the front, in which food is cooked or heated
例句: The woman likes to bake bread in the oven.
例句释义: 这位女士喜欢在烤箱中烤面包。

英文释义: the quality of being excellent or important
例句: I completed my final year exam with distinction.
例句释义: 我以优异的成绩完成了期末考试。

英文释义: a part of something that is separate from the other parts or can be considered separately
例句: Our company dominates a small segment of the market.
例句释义: 我们公司占有一小部分市场。

英文释义: a place that is nonexistent, unknown, remote, etc.
例句: He looked everywhere in the room, but the key was nowhere to be found.
例句释义: 他在房间里到处找，但哪里都找不到钥匙。

英文释义: a person who writes poems
例句: He is one of the most famous poets in Chinese history.
例句释义: 他是中国历史上最著名的诗人之一。

英文释义: used when you want to emphasize how small, unimportant, etc. somebody/something is
例句: He was late by mere seconds, yet he was fined 200 yuan.
例句释义: 他迟到了仅仅几秒钟，就被罚了200元。

详细释义: adj.令人兴奋的；使人激动的
英文释义: causing feelings of interest and enthusiasm; causing excitement
例句: How exciting! Our team won!
例句释义: 太令人激动了！我们队赢了！

英文释义: a change, especially in the amount or level of something
例句: The temperature in the desert shows great variation throughout the day.
例句释义: 沙漠中一天内的气温变化很大。

详细释义: v. 安慰；使舒适；  n. 舒适
英文释义: to make somebody who is worried or unhappy feel better by being kind and sympathetic towards them
例句: The woman tries to comfort her crying daughter.
例句释义: 那个女人在安慰正在哭泣的女儿。

详细释义: n. 激进分子；  adj. 激进的；重大的，彻底的
英文释义: a person with radical opinions
例句: Some radicals insist that every animal should eat grass.
例句释义: 一些激进分子认为所有动物都应该吃草。

英文释义: to change your behavior so that it is easier to live in a particular place or situation
例句: This animal changes its color to adapt to its new surroundings.
例句释义: 这只动物为适应新环境改变了身体颜色。

详细释义: adj. 爱尔兰的，爱尔兰人的，爱尔兰语的
英文释义: of or connected with Ireland, its people or its language
例句: The Irish people are known for their beer and dancing.
例句释义: 爱尔兰人以他们的啤酒和舞蹈而出名。

英文释义: a sweet sticky yellow substance made by bees that is spread on bread, etc. like jam
例句: I want to put some honey on my apple.
例句释义: 我想放一点蜂蜜在苹果上。

英文释义: (used with an adjective) a person who writes letters to another person
例句: After the earthquake, a news correspondent was on the scene within an hour.
例句释义: 地震发生了以后，新闻记者在一小时之内就赶到了现场。

详细释义: adj.苍白的，灰白的；  vi.变苍白
英文释义: (of a person, their face, etc.) having skin that is almost white; having skin that is whiter than usual because of illness, a strong emotion, etc.; light in colour; containing a lot of white; (of light) not strong or bright
例句: Her pale face shows that she is very sick.
例句释义: 我们可以从她苍白的脸色看出她病得很严重。

英文释义: a person who plays a musical instrument or writes music, especially as a job
例句: The musician plays beautiful music.
例句释义: 这位音乐家在演奏美妙的音乐。

英文释义: the meaning of something
例句: The wedding anniversary is of great significance to the couple.
例句释义: 结婚纪念日对这对夫妻来说意义重大。

英文释义: a large ship or boat; a container used for holding liquids, such as a bowl, cup, etc.; a tube that carries blood through the body of a person or an animal, or liquid through the parts of a plant
例句: This supply vessel is sailing across the calm sea.
例句释义: 这艘补给舰航行在平静的海面上。

英文释义: the process of keeping something in a particular place until it is needed; the space where things can be kept; space where you put things when they are not being used
例句: We put all the paper boxes in storage.
例句释义: 我们把所有纸箱存放在仓库里。

英文释义: to leave a person or place very quickly, especially because you are afraid of possible danger
例句: The soldier fled the war.
例句释义: 这个士兵逃离了战争。

英文释义: material made by removing the hair or fur from animal skins and preserving the skins using special processes
例句: The sofa and pillow are covered in real leather.
例句释义: 沙发和枕头都是真皮做的。

英文释义: to give things to a large number of people; to share something between a number of people; to send goods to shops/stores and businesses so that they can be sold
例句: The presents were distributed to everyone at the party.
例句释义: 礼物派发给了派对上的所有人。

英文释义: (biology) the gradual development of plants, animals, etc. over many years as they adapt to changes in their environment
例句: This picture shows the evolution of the mobile phone.
例句释义: 这张图片展示了手机的演变过程。

详细释义: adj.生病的，不适的；  adv.不充分地
英文释义: not well or healthy; sick or unhealthy
例句: The girl is ill; she is resting on the sofa.
例句释义: 这个女孩生病了，她正在沙发上休息。

英文释义: (in developing countries) a group of people of the same race, and with the same customs, language, religion, etc., living in a particular area and often led by a chief; a large number of people
例句: The primal tribe people make the fire with wood.
例句释义: 原始部落的人用木柴生火。

英文释义: a flat board which is attached to a wall, frame, etc., and on which objects can be placed
例句: There are many books on the shelf.
例句释义: 架子上放了很多书。

英文释义: the father of your father or mother
例句: "Grandfather is the father of your parent," the boy said.
例句释义: “祖父就是你爸爸或你妈妈的父亲。”男孩说道。

详细释义: n. 草坪；草地；（衣服用）细麻
英文释义: an area of ground covered in short grass in a garden/yard or park, or used for playing a game on
例句: I take care of my lawn to keep it nice and green.
例句释义: 我精心打理我的草坪，让它看起来美观而又葱郁。

英文释义: to eat dinner
例句: The couple enjoyed dining under candlelight.
例句释义: 这对情侣很享受在烛光下进餐。

详细释义: n.智慧，学问；明智，正确判断
英文释义: the ability to make sensible decisions and give good advice because of the experience and knowledge that you have; the knowledge that a society or culture has gained over a long period of time
例句: Zhuge Liang is an example of wisdom.
例句释义: 诸葛亮是智慧的榜样。

英文释义: a group of people who are elected to govern an area such as a city or county
例句: All the members of the council were given equal importance.
例句释义: 理事会所有成员都同等重要。

英文释义: weak and easily hurt physically or emotionally
例句: The chain looks very vulnerable because of the paper clip.
例句释义: 因为是回形针串的，所以这条链子看起来很脆弱。

例句: Earthquakes, in some instances, can be devastating, whereas in others they might be quite mild.
例句释义: 地震在一些情况下是毁灭性的，但在另一些情况下则影响较小。

英文释义: a vegetable of the onion family with a very strong taste and smell, used in cooking to give flavour to food
例句: Garlic makes any meal taste better.
例句释义: 大蒜让所有菜肴更好吃了。

英文释义: the ability or qualities necessary to do something; the power or weapons that a country has for war or for military action
例句: He has the capability to handle multiple tasks at the same time.
例句释义: 他具有同时处理多项工作的能力。

英文释义: a collection of poems; poems in general
例句: I like reading poetry from the Tang Dynasty.
例句释义: 我很喜欢读唐朝的诗歌。

详细释义: n.名人；名流；  adj.有名望的
英文释义: a famous person
例句: The celebrity got the attention of photographers and fans.
例句释义: 名人受到了摄影师和粉丝的关注。

英文释义: slowly, over a long period of time
例句: Gradually, he becomes stronger and stronger.
例句释义: 渐渐地，他变得越来越强壮。

英文释义: the quality or state of being steady and not changing or being disturbed in any way (= the quality of being stable)
例句: Walking a tightrope requires extreme stability.
例句释义: 走钢丝需要极强的稳定性。

英文释义: a pleasant situation that you imagine but that is unlikely to happen; the act of imagining things; a person’s imagination
例句: She is lost in a fantasy, dreaming of her wedding day.
例句释义: 她沉浸在对婚礼的幻想中。

英文释义: frightened of something or afraid that something bad might happen
例句: Why don't you come out? Are you scared?
例句释义: 你怎么不出来？你害怕吗？

英文释义: the series of events that form the story of a novel, play, film/movie, etc.; a secret plan made by a group of people to do something wrong or illegal; a small piece of land that is used or intended for a special purpose
例句: This story has a romantic plot.
例句释义: 这个故事有一个浪漫的情节。

英文释义: the parts of a building or an object that support its weight and give it shape
例句: You can see the framework of the building so well at the moment.
例句释义: 你现在可以清楚地看见房屋的框架。

详细释义: n.手势，姿势；  v.做手势，用动作示意
英文释义: a movement of your body (especially of your hands and arms) that shows or emphasizes an idea or a feeling
例句: The girl believes that this gesture can bring her good luck.
例句释义: 女孩相信这个手势能带来好运。

详细释义: adj.仍在进行的；  n.进行，前进，发展
英文释义: continuing to exist or develop
例句: They are having an ongoing argument.
例句释义: 他们正争论不休。

详细释义: n.心理学；心理特征，心理状态
英文释义: the scientific study of the mind and how it influences behaviour
例句: I study psychology to learn about how people think.
例句释义: 我学心理学是为了了解人们如何思考。

英文释义: a separate section of a book, usually with a number or title
例句: Please open your books to the first chapter.
例句释义: 请把书翻到第一章。

详细释义: n. 离婚，离异；  v. 离婚
英文释义: the legal ending of a marriage; a separation; the ending of a relationship between two things
例句: The couple have agreed to get a divorce.
例句释义: 这对夫妻已经同意离婚了。

英文释义: to exist or be successful because of the help or influence of somebody/something
例句: I owe my full mark to this phone app!
例句释义: 我把我的满分归功于这个手机应用！

英文释义: a tube through which liquids and gases can flow
例句: These pipes are made of plastic, so they are very light.
例句释义: 这些管子是塑料做的，所以它们非常轻。

英文释义: physically strong, fit and active
例句: He is an athletic person who is good at most sports.
例句释义: 他是个运动型的人，擅长多项运动。

详细释义: adj. 轻微的，微小的；纤细的，瘦弱的；少量的；  n. 轻视，蔑视
英文释义: very small in degree or amount
例句: There's a slight imperfection on this antique teapot.
例句释义: 这个古董茶壶上面有一个小瑕疵。

英文释义: mathematics, especially as a subject in school
例句: The teacher is writing math equations on the blackboard.
例句释义: 老师正在黑板上写一些数学方程式。

详细释义: n.树荫，阴凉处；遮光物；  vt.遮蔽；险胜
英文释义: an area that is dark and cool under or behind something, for example a tree or building, because the sun’s light does not get to it
例句: I am standing in the shade of a tree. It's cooler here.
例句释义: 我站在树荫下，这儿凉快些。

英文释义: the part that sticks out and can be moved at the back of the body of a bird, an animal or a fish
例句: The horse's long tail lifted up into the air as it ran.
例句释义: 马的长尾巴随着其奔跑的步伐被甩向空中。

英文释义: to support a weight without breaking or falling
例句: These four columns sustain the entire building.
例句释义: 这四根柱子支撑着整座建筑物。

详细释义: v. 骑上；登上；爬上；增长；  n. 山；峰
英文释义: to seat yourself on a horse, bicycle, etc.
例句: She mounted her horse and rode away.
例句释义: 她飞身上马，疾驰而去。

英文释义: the state of being forced to do something because it is your duty, or because of a law, etc.; something which you must do because you have promised, because of a law, etc.
例句: If you want to own a pet, you must fulfill all the associated obligations.
例句释义: 如果你想拥有一只宠物，你就必须履行所有的相关义务。

英文释义: the direction that something is leaning or pointing in when it is not in a vertical or horizontal line
例句: The angle of each corner is 60 degrees.
例句释义: （这个三角形）每个角都是60度。

英文释义: a straight tree with a mass of long leaves at the top, growing in tropical countries. There are several types of palm tree, some of which produce fruit.
例句: Some people believe the shape of your palms will tell your future.
例句释义: 有些人相信手掌的形状可以预测未来。

英文释义: to be different from somebody/something
例句: The red guy differs from the others.
例句释义: 这个红色的人和其他人不同。

详细释义: n. 风俗；  adj. 定制的

例句: It's our custom to have dragon boat racing at this festival.
例句释义: 在这个节日里赛龙舟是我们的习俗。

英文释义: an expert in the science of economics
例句: This famous economist is often referred to as "the Father of Economics."
例句释义: 这位著名的经济学家常被称作“经济学之父”。

英文释义: a food made by cooking vegetables, meat, or fish in a large amount of liquid
例句: This is a bowl of chicken soup.
例句释义: 这是一碗鸡汤。

英文释义: a special event that people organize in order to celebrate something; the act of celebrating something
例句: Many people gathered together for the New Year celebration.
例句释义: 很多人聚在一起欢庆新年。

详细释义: adj. 效率高的；能胜任的
英文释义: doing something well and thoroughly with no waste of time, money or energy
例句: The mother is very efficient; she can watch her kids and do her work at the same time.
例句释义: 这位母亲效率非常高，她可以一边照看孩子一边做自己的工作。

详细释义: n.（文章或音乐的）创作，作品

例句: Beethoven's compositions are great works.
例句释义: 贝多芬的创作是伟大的作品。

详细释义: v.满足；（使）满意；符合……的标准
英文释义: to make somebody pleased by doing or giving them what they want
例句: The boy went to a fast food restaurant to satisfy his desire for a hamburger.
例句释义: 小男孩去快餐店满足了自己想吃汉堡的欲望。

英文释义: a number of things that have been placed on top of each other

例句释义: 多么高的一摞书！

例句: She briefly worked as a photographer before becoming a journalist.
例句释义: 在成为记者之前，她曾短暂地做过摄影师。

详细释义: n. 碳；复写纸；  adj. 碳的

例句释义: 煤炭主要由碳构成。

英文释义: to use something, especially fuel, energy or time

例句释义: 我们把从超市买来的厕纸都用完了。

详细释义: n.方案，计划；阴谋，诡计；  v.图谋，密谋
英文释义: a clever and often dishonest plan to do or get something
例句: The man is explaining the investment scheme to his colleagues.
例句释义: 这名男士正在向同事讲解投资方案。

详细释义: v.（使）破裂，打碎；断裂，折断；  n.破裂声；  adj.优秀的，一流的

例句释义: 土地因为缺水而裂开。

英文释义: the rate at which a sound or electromagnetic wave vibrates (= moves up and down)

例句释义: 这声音的频率很高。

英文释义: the dried leaves of the tobacco plant that are used for making cigarettes, smoking in a pipe or chewing

例句释义: 烟草是一种晒干的叶片，大多数人抽的就是雪茄和香烟里的烟草。

英文释义: a person who continues to live after an accident, illness, war, etc.

例句释义: 泰坦尼克号沉没事件中大多数幸存者是女人和孩子。

例句: As the winner, I received lots of money besides the cup.
例句释义: 作为胜利者，我除了得到奖杯外，还获得了一大笔钱。

详细释义: n.心理学家，心理学研究者
英文释义: a scientist who specializes in the study and treatment of the mind and behavior :a specialist in psychology
例句: The psychologist is using colored cubes to test the girl.
例句释义: 这位心理学家正在用彩色方块对女孩做测试。

英文释义: having a lot of money, possessions, etc.
例句: I'm so wealthy that I bathe in money.
例句释义: 我在钞票里沐浴，我太有钱了！

英文释义: any of the large systems of stars, etc. in outer space; the system of stars that contains our sun and its planets, seen as a bright band in the night sky; a group of famous people, or people with a particular skill
例句: There are countless stars and planets in this beautiful galaxy.
例句释义: 在这个美丽的星系里有数不清的恒星和行星。

英文释义: to move over snow on skis, especially as a sport
例句: The couple are skiing in the mountains.
例句释义: 这对情侣在山里滑雪。

英文释义: a limit on what somebody/something can do or how good they or it can be; a rule, fact or condition that limits something

英文释义: to find or discover somebody/something by looking carefully for them/it

例句释义: 这只警犬循着气味找到了被偷走的钱款。

英文释义: a formal arrangement to meet or visit somebody at a particular time, especially for a reason connected with their work
例句: I have an appointment with my doctor tomorrow .
例句释义: 我和医生约了明天见面。

英文释义: a greater interest in or desire for somebody/something than somebody/something else

英文释义: a unit for measuring length; a hundred centimetres

英文释义: in a manner accessible to or observable by the public; openly

例句释义: 他公开发表演讲来传播信息。

英文释义: impossible or very difficult to believe

例句释义: 他用牙齿拉动了卡车！真是令人难以置信！

详细释义: n. 战士；战斗机，歼击机
英文释义: a person who fights; a person who does not give up hope or admit that they are defeated

例句释义: 这个拳击手击中了对手的脸。

英文释义: happening in a short period of time rapid change/expansion/grow
例句: The train is traveling at a rapid pace.
例句释义: 火车正在急速行驶。

英文释义: a statement in which somebody admits that something is true, especially something wrong or bad that they have done
例句: The card gives me admission to enter the building.
例句释义: 这张卡使我能够进入这栋建筑。

英文释义: a person who hunts wild animals

例句释义: 这个带着猎犬的男人是个经验丰富的猎人。

英文释义: to teach somebody over a period of time at a school, university, etc.; to teach somebody about something or how to do something

英文释义: a relationship between friends

例句释义: 这俩孩子有着深厚的友谊。

英文释义: an officer who acts as military assistant to a more senior officer

例句: The infant in the duck towel is laughing happily.
例句释义: 裹在鸭子毛巾里的小婴儿笑得真开心。

英文释义: to use numbers to find out a total number, amount, distance, etc.

例句释义: 这个女孩为她的数学作业做计算。

英文释义: to make yourself free of somebody/something that is annoying you or that you do not want; to throw something away

例句释义: 谢天谢地！我终于摆脱了全部债务！

英文释义: a small area at the entrance to a building, such as a house or a church, that is covered by a roof and often has walls; a platform with an open front and a roof, built onto the side of a house on the ground floor

例句释义: 我喜欢坐在前门廊吹风。

英文释义: if somebody/something has a particular tendency, they are likely to behave or act in a particular way

英文释义: a particular arrangement or pattern

英文释义: the quality of doing something well with no waste of time or money; ways of wasting less time and money or of saving time or money

英文释义: to come or develop from something

例句: This is your new PC for studying.

英文释义: if a person or thing impresses you, you feel admiration for them or it; to make somebody understand how important, serious, etc. something is by emphasizing it; to have a great effect on something, especially somebody’s mind, imagination, etc.

英文释义: (of food, farming methods, etc.) produced or practised without using artificial chemicals

例句释义: 我讨厌学有机化学，但如果我想成为一个医生的话，我就必须学。

英文释义: a shelter made of a large sheet of canvas, nylon, etc. that is supported by poles and ropes fixed to the ground, and is used especially for camping

例句释义: 那对夫妇在河边支起了帐篷。

英文释义: inquiry; a close and careful study of someone or something to find signs of illness or injury

例句释义: 学生们正在参加考试。

英文释义: a person or company that produces books, magazines, etc.

例句释义: 经过出版商几个月的努力，这本书得以在书店里出售。

英文释义: to become stronger; to make somebody/something stronger

例句释义: 她每天坚持锻炼来使手臂变强壮。

例句: We feed a cow to get milk for breakfast.
例句释义: 我们养了一头奶牛为我们的早餐提供牛奶。

例句释义: 喵星人和汪星人在一张床上睡着了。

例句释义: 我父亲教我怎样打网球。

详细释义: n.神经；胆量，勇气；  v.给……以力量，使振作
英文释义: any of the long threads that carry messages between the brain and parts of the body, enabling you to move, feel pain, etc.

英文释义: a large round container, usually made of wood or metal, with flat ends and, usually, curved sides

例句释义: 这些木桶都用来储存啤酒。

例句释义: 她喜欢照相并且想要成为一名摄影师。

英文释义: an aircraft without wings that has large blades on top that go round. It can fly straight up from the ground and can also stay in one position in the air

英文释义: not talking much about your own abilities or possessions
例句: These two businessmen may be rich, but they're still very modest!
例句释义: 这两位企业家也许非常富有，但他们仍然很谦虚！

英文释义: to not do something until a later time or to make something happen at a later time
例句: The flight was delayed, so I'll have to wait until tomorrow.
例句释义: 航班延误了，所以我不得不等到明天。

英文释义: connected with the science or practice of farming
例句: Agricultural land is important for growing crops.
例句释义: 农田（质量）对于种庄稼来说很重要。

英文释义: to burst or make something burst loudly and violently, causing damage; to increase suddenly and very quickly in number; to suddenly express an emotion;
例句: The fireworks exploded in the air.
例句释义: 烟花在空中爆炸开来。

英文释义: to move your hand gently and slowly over a surface, somebody’s hair or an animal’s fur or hair, etc.
例句: He hit the ball cleanly with a beautiful stroke.
例句释义: 他利落地击球，打出漂亮的一击。

详细释义: n.瞄准镜；范围；眼界，见识；余地
英文释义: an instrument (such as a telescope or microscope) for looking through or watching something with
例句: A scope helps the shooter search at great distances.
例句释义: 瞄准镜有助于射手进行远距离搜索。

英文释义: the act of punishing someone or a way of punishing someone
例句: The student was given punishment for doing something wrong.
例句释义: 这个学生因为做错事受到了惩罚。

详细释义: n.一把；难管的人（尤指孩子）
英文释义: the amount of something that can be held in one hand
例句: He holds a handful of rice in his hand.
例句释义: 他捧了一把米在手里。

英文释义: used to emphasize how serious a situation or an event is
例句: The boy was badly injured in school.
例句释义: 男孩在学校里受了很严重的伤。

英文释义: the furthest that you can see, where the sky seems to meet the land or the sea
例句: I can see the horizon behind the hills.
例句释义: 我可以看到小山后面的地平线。

英文释义: having a strong desire to know about something
例句: The cat is curious about the black mouse.
例句释义: 这只猫对这个黑色鼠标感到好奇。

详细释义: adj.市中心的，商业区的，闹市区的；  adv.在市中心
英文释义: to, toward, or in the main or central part of a city or town
例句: There are a lot of skyscrapers in the downtown area.
例句释义: 市中心有很多摩天大楼。

详细释义: v.敦促，促使，激励；  adj.迅速的，及时的；准时的
英文释义: to encourage somebody to speak by asking them questions or suggesting words that they could say; to make somebody decide to do something; to cause something to happen;
例句: My phone prompts me to get out of bed and finish my paper!
例句释义: 我的手机敦促我起床写论文！

英文释义: a substance found in blood, fat and most tissues of the body. Too much cholesterol can cause heart disease.
例句: Too many fatty foods will cause cholesterol to block your blood vessels.
例句释义: 摄入过多的高脂肪食物会导致胆固醇阻塞血管。

英文释义: to take in a liquid, gas or other substance from the surface or space around
例句: Plants absorb water from the soil.
例句释义: 植物从土壤中汲取水分。

详细释义: n.调节；（行为、思想的）调整，适应
英文释义: a small change made to something in order to correct or improve it
例句: I made an adjustment to my chair so I can sit comfortably.
例句释义: 我调整了座椅，以便能坐得更舒服一点。

英文释义: a person who pays tax to the government, especially on the money that they earn
例句: The taxpayer checks the amount of tax with a calculator.
例句释义: 纳税人在用计算器检查税费金额。

详细释义: adj. 热切的，渴望的，急不可耐的
英文释义: very interested and excited by something that is going to happen or about something that you want to do
例句: The kids are eager to eat the cake on the table.
例句释义: 孩子们急不可耐想要吃掉桌上的蛋糕。

详细释义: n.校长；  adj.主要的，首要的
英文释义: the person who is in charge of a college or a university; a teacher who is in charge of a school
例句: The principal is the head of the school.
例句释义: 校长是学校的主要负责人。

英文释义: developed or executed with care and in minute detail
例句: This is a detailed roadmap.
例句释义: 这是一份详细的路线图。

英文释义: the act or process of giving someone a reason for doing something
例句: Money is his motivation for boxing.
例句释义: 金钱是他拳击的动力。

英文释义: a task or piece of work that somebody is given to do, usually as part of their job or studies
例句: My teacher gave me a lot of homework assignments for the weekend.
例句释义: 老师给我布置了很多周末的家庭作业。

英文释义: a rule or law that limits what you can do or what can happen; the act of limiting or controlling somebody/something; a thing that limits the amount of freedom you have
例句: There is a restriction on fishing here.
例句释义: 这里限制垂钓。

英文释义: a room or building used for scientific research, experiments, testing, etc.
例句: The male chemist works around the clock in the laboratory.
例句释义: 这位化学家整日整夜地在实验室里工作。

详细释义: n.车间，工场，工作室；研讨会
英文释义: a room or building in which things are made or repaired using tools or machinery; a period of discussion and practical work on a particular subject, in which a group of people share their knowledge and experience
例句: I left my car at the workshop for repair.
例句释义: 我把我的车留在车间修理。

英文释义: in another and different manner
例句: Now, I look at vegetables differently.
例句释义: 现在，我对蔬菜的看法不同了。

英文释义: a car
例句: These autos are parked in good order.
例句释义: 这些车停的很整齐。

英文释义: connected or concerned with love or a sexual relationship;
例句: On Valentine's Day, couples often go for a romantic dinner.
例句释义: 情人节这天，情侣们通常会出去吃一顿浪漫的晚餐。

英文释义: a soft, white material that grows on the seeds of a tall plant and that is used to make cloth
例句: Cotton feels soft and can be used to make clothes.
例句释义: 棉花摸起来很柔软，可以用来制作衣服。

英文释义: a device that uses electricity, petrol/gas, etc. to produce movement and makes a machine, a vehicle, a boat, etc. work
例句: This is the motor of the four-wheel drive.
例句释义: 这是这辆四驱车的马达。

详细释义: v. 控告，提起诉讼；起诉
英文释义: to make a claim against somebody in court about something that they have said or done to harm you; to formally ask for something, especially in court
例句: The worker is suing his boss for failing to pay his salary.
例句释义: 这名工人起诉老板拖欠工资。

详细释义: n. 味，风味；调味品；  v. 给……调味
英文释义: a particular type of taste
例句: The yoghurt has a strawberry flavor.
例句释义: 这个酸奶是草莓味的。

详细释义: v. 忽视，未注意到；  n. 忽视，远眺
英文释义: if a building, etc. overlooks a place, you can see that place from the building
例句: She's so busy on her tablet that she's totally overlooking her daughter.
例句释义: 她忙着玩平板，全然忽视了她的女儿。

详细释义: vi.浮动，漂流，漂浮；  vt.使浮动，使漂浮；  n.浮标，漂浮物，漂浮
英文释义: to move slowly on water or in the air
例句: It's so relaxing to just stay still and float in the water.
例句释义: 静止不动地飘在水面上，真是相当放松啊。

英文释义: to experience something, especially a change or something unpleasant
例句: He underwent rigorous training before he officially became armed police.
例句释义: 他在正式成为武警之前接受了严格的训练。

详细释义: n.顺序，次序；一系列，一连串
英文释义: the order that events, actions, etc. happen in or should happen in

例句释义: 按照这样的顺序，分三步把大象放进冰箱。

英文释义: a public meeting or march at which people show that they are protesting against or supporting somebody/something
例句: He gave a demonstration of how to use the new smartphone.
例句释义: 他对如何使用新的智能手机进行了演示。

详细释义: n.喷气式飞机；  vi.乘坐喷气式飞机
英文释义: a fast airplane that has one or more jet engines
例句: Nowadays most long-distance travel is by jet plane.
例句释义: 现在，大多数长途旅行会使用喷气式飞机。

英文释义: a round citrus fruit with thick reddish-yellow skin and a lot of sweet juice

例句释义: 一天一个橘子可以补充你所需的维生素C。

英文释义: a serious infectious disease of the lungs
例句: Our water consumption is quite high this month.
例句释义: 我们这个月的耗水量非常高。

详细释义: v. 坚持；断言；肯定地说；维护
英文释义: to state clearly and firmly that something is true
例句: He continued to assert that he was innocent.
例句释义: 他坚持声称自己是无辜的。

英文释义: the flat cutting part of a knife, sword, or other cutting tool or weapon
例句: He is sharpening the blade of the knife.
例句释义: 他正在磨刀。

英文释义: lasting or intended to last or be used only for a short time; not permanent

例句: Too much medication is not recommended.
例句释义: 不推荐过度药物治疗。

详细释义: n.（简陋的）小屋；  v.住在小屋里
英文释义: a small house or shelter, usually made of wood
例句: We like to go to our small log cabin in the woods.

例句释义: 这本字典现在是第三版，于2017年出版。

英文释义: an area of low land between hills or mountains, often with a river flowing through it; the land that a river flows through
例句: A small stream flows through the valley.
例句释义: 一条小溪流过山谷。

详细释义: v.投掷，扔；用沥青覆盖；【音】为……定音高；扎营；搭帐篷；  n.投掷；球场；沥青；音高
英文释义: to throw the ball to the person who is batting
例句: The player pitched the ball to me.
例句释义: 球员把球向我掷了过来。

英文释义: an evergreen forest tree with leaves like needles; the pale soft wood of the pine tree, used in making furniture, etc.
例句: The pine tree is a symbol of Mount Huangshan.

详细释义: adj.聪颖的；卓越的，有才气的
英文释义: extremely clever or impressive; very intelligent or skillful
例句: The brilliant girl can solve the math problems easily.
例句释义: 这个聪明的女孩可以轻松解决这些数学难题。

详细释义: prep.以……为对手；与……相对，与……相比
英文释义: used to show that two teams or sides are against each other
例句: Man A versus Man B is a good fight to watch.
例句释义: 甲男对乙男，可有看头了。

英文释义: total and complete
例句: Motion is absolute, while stillness is relative.
例句释义: 运动是绝对的，静止是相对的。

英文释义: a professional cook, especially the most senior cook in a restaurant, hotel, etc.

例句释义: 主厨是指在饭店或酒店里掌管厨房的熟练的厨师。

英文释义: the practice of treating somebody or a particular group in society less fairly than others; the ability to judge what is good, true, etc.; the ability to recognize a difference between one thing and another; a difference that is recognized
例句: This little duck suffers a lot of discrimination because it looks very different from others.
例句释义: 这只小鸭子因为长得与其他鸭子很不一样而受到了严重的歧视。

英文释义: rude in a way that causes you to feel upset, insulted or annoyed; extremely unpleasant; connected with the act of attacking somebody/something; connected with the team that has control of the ball; connected with the act of scoring points
例句: She found his words very offensive, which made her really upset.
例句释义: 她因为他的无礼言辞感到非常心烦。

英文释义: a loud deep sound
例句: The bombs went off with a loud boom.
例句释义: 炸弹爆炸的时候发出隆隆的一声巨响。

英文释义: to record your/somebody’s/something’s name on an official list
例句: The athletes are registering for a half-marathon around the park.
例句释义: 运动员们正在登记，报名参加环绕公园的半程马拉松。

英文释义: to choose (someone) to have a particular job; to give (someone) a position or duty
例句: My boss has appointed me to manage this project.
例句释义: 我的老板任命我来管理这个项目。

英文释义: the history, traditions and qualities that a country or society has had for many years and that are considered an important part of its character
例句: The building is the symbol of their cultural heritage.
例句释义: 这个建筑是他们文化遗产的象征。

英文释义: (in some religions) a being or spirit who is believed to have power over a particular part of nature or who is believed to represent a particular quality

例句释义: 波塞冬是古希腊神话中的海神。

英文释义: more important, powerful or noticeable than other things

例句释义: 这家公司占有80%的市场份额，在市场上具有举足轻重的地位。

英文释义: in a successful manner
例句: The rocket was launched successfully.
例句释义: 火箭成功发射了。

英文释义: a yellow citrus fruit with a lot of sour juice. Slices of lemon and lemon juice are used in cooking and drinks.
例句: I can't eat a whole lemon―can you?
例句释义: 我吃不了一整个柠檬，你能吗？

英文释义: feeling that you want to eat something
例句: I'm not really hungry, just a small piece of pizza would be fine for me.
例句释义: 我不是很饿，给我一小块比萨就好。

详细释义: v. 漫游；迷路；  n. 闲逛
英文释义: to move around or go to different places usually without having a particular purpose or direction
例句: The young couple is wandering in the park.
例句释义: 这对年轻的夫妇正在公园里漫步。

英文释义: to give a document, proposal, etc. to somebody in authority so that they can study or consider it
例句: The man is submitting the report to his boss.
例句释义: 这个男人正在把报告递交给他的老板。

英文释义: the study of how a society organizes its money, trade and industry
例句: We should have a deep knowledge of economics to understand changes in the global market.
例句释义: 我们应该有深厚的经济学知识，这样才能理解全球市场的变化（形势）。

英文释义: not wearing any clothes; without the usual covering
例句: The naked baby is crawling and smiling on the floor.
例句释义: 那个光着身子的婴儿正在地上边爬边笑。

英文释义: to expect something

例句释义: 我期待他能得第一！因为他真的很棒！

英文释义: (often in compounds) a small hard fruit with a very hard shell that grows on some trees

例句释义: 坚果是人体所需维生素E的一个来源。

英文释义: money or property that is given to you by somebody when they die
例句: The house is a legacy left by his grandfather.
例句释义: 这座房子是他祖父留下的遗产。

例句释义: 我们计划扩建我们的房子。

详细释义: v. （为表示厌恶、轻漠、冷淡、怀疑等）耸肩；  n. 耸肩
英文释义: to raise your shoulders and then drop them to show that you do not know or care about something

例句释义: 他耸耸肩，作为对母亲的唠叨的回应。

英文释义: a device that is placed inside a car engine, clock, radio, etc. and that produces the electricity that makes it work
例句: Here are some batteries of different sizes.
例句释义: 这里有些不同规格的电池。

英文释义: the act of coming to or reaching a place; the act of arriving
例句: Passengers on the platform are waiting for the train's arrival.
例句释义: 站台上的乘客正在等候火车到站。

英文释义: allowed and acceptable according to the law
例句: Fishing is legitimate there.
例句释义: 在这里钓鱼是合法的。

例句释义: 这些公司明确他们的应用的定位。

详细释义: n.通货膨胀；（充气后）膨胀；自负

例句: Because of the inflation, we could buy less fruit with the same money.

例句: The experienced captain can cope with the dangerous situation and find a solution.
例句释义: 这位经验丰富的机长能应付危险情况并找到解决方法。

英文释义: the hot, glowing gas that can be seen when a fire is burning

例句释义: 房子烧毁了，我们失去了一切。

详细释义: n. 一串；一簇；  v. 群集；丛生
英文释义: a group of things of the same type that grow or appear close together

例句释义: 我想摘那一串可口的葡萄，然后把它们全吃光。

例句释义: 她膝盖上有一个小伤口。

详细释义: adj.依赖的；  n.依赖他人者
英文释义: needing somebody/something in order to survive or be successful

例句释义: 那场车祸后，她的行动就一直依赖她儿子。

详细释义: n.淋浴，淋浴器；阵雨；  v.洗淋浴，淋湿
英文释义: the act of washing your body with a shower

例句释义: 小猫在快乐地洗淋浴。

英文释义: a place where vehicles are repaired and where you can buy a car or buy petrol/gas and oil
