例句释义: 接线员们的日常工作是接电话。

英文释义: a person whose job is to teach somebody a practical skill or sport; a teacher below the rank of assistant professor at a college or university
例句: The driving instructor is helping his student learn how to back a car.
例句释义: 驾校教练正在指导他的学生学习倒车。

英文释义: to fall down or fall in suddenly, often after breaking apart; to fail suddenly or completely
例句: He went crazy, watching the markets collapse.
例句释义: 看到市场崩溃，他变得抓狂起来。

英文释义: to take and use (something that belongs to someone else) for a period of time before returning it
例句: He borrowed money from his friend and promised to pay it back next week.
例句释义: 他向朋友借了钱并承诺下周还。

英文释义: in addition to what has just been stated
例句: He broke his leg in the forest; furthermore, some strange creatures were watching him.
例句释义: 他在森林中摔断了腿，此外，他还被某些奇怪的生物盯上了。

英文释义: a play, movie, television program, novel, etc., that is meant to make people laugh
例句: This TV comedy show is quite interesting.
例句释义: 这个电视喜剧节目十分有趣。

英文释义: a legal agreement by which a bank or similar organization lends you money to buy a house, etc., and you pay the money back over a particular number of years; the sum of money that you borrow
例句: He took out a mortgage, meaning he borrowed money to buy his home.
例句释义: 他办理过抵押贷款，这意味着他是借钱买的房子。

详细释义: n.批准；  v.批准；支持；对……实施制裁
英文释义: official permission or approval for an action or a change
例句: The installation of air conditioners received sanction from the boss.
例句释义: 老板批准了空调的安装。

详细释义: n. 平民，百姓；  adj. 平民的，百姓的，民用的
英文释义: a person who is not a member of the armed forces or the police
例句: The soldiers guarantee the safety of civilians.
例句释义: 士兵们保证了平民的安全。

详细释义: adv. 一周一次地；  adj. 每周的，一周一次的；  n. 周报，周刊
英文释义: once a week; every week
例句: This TV show is updated weekly.
例句释义: 这个电视节目每周更新一次。

英文释义: the place where a particular type of animal or plant is normally found
例句: Here are two deer in their natural habitat.
例句释义: 两只鹿在它们的自然栖息地里。

详细释义: n.谷物，谷粒；  v.使成粒状
英文释义: the small hard seeds of food plants such as wheat, rice, etc.
例句: There is a bag of grains on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上有一袋谷物。

英文释义: an object made of short stiff hairs (called bristles ) or wires set in a block of wood or plastic, usually attached to a handle. Brushes are used for many different jobs, such as cleaning, painting, writing and tidying your hair.
例句: Brushes of different sizes may be applied in different situations.
例句释义: 不同尺寸的画笔用于不同的情况。

英文释义: the ideas and opinions of a person or group
例句: He suddenly has the consciousness of being late.
例句释义: 他突然意识到自己迟到了。

详细释义: vt.献身于，专心致力于，奉献
英文释义: to give entirely to a specific person, activity, or cause
例句: The chicken jumped into the pot and devoted his life to us.
例句释义: 这只鸡跳进锅里，为我们献出了生命。

英文释义: the act or the process of finding the size, quantity or degree of something; a size, length, or amount known by measuring something
例句: The woman wanted to know her measurement of waist.
例句释义: 这个女人想知道自己腰的尺寸。

英文释义: any of the main divisions of some countries, and forms a separate whole for purposes of government control
例句: Chengdu is the capital of Sichuan Province.
例句释义: 成都是四川省的省会。

详细释义: v.缓解；顺利进出；  n.不拘束
英文释义: to become or to make something less unpleasant, painful, severe, etc.
例句: To ease her daily stress, she likes to practice yoga.
例句释义: 她喜欢通过练瑜伽来缓解日常压力。

英文释义: to take somebody/something in your hand suddenly and using force; to arrest or capture somebody; to be quick to make use of a chance, an opportunity, etc.; to take control of a place or situation, often suddenly and violently
例句: They seized one another by the wrist.
例句释义: 他们抓住了对方的手腕。

英文释义: a system of moral principles or rules of behaviour
例句: Confucius described a system of ethics for everybody to follow.
例句释义: 孔子描述了一套行为准则，并让每个人都遵守它。

例句: They all received nominations for the Nobel Prize, but nobody was sure who would win.
例句释义: 他们都获得了诺贝尔奖的提名，但没人能肯定谁会得奖。

英文释义: the act of allowing somebody to do something, especially when this is done by somebody in a position of authority
例句: My mother gave me her permission to go to the party.
例句释义: 我母亲允许我去参加聚会。

详细释义: adj.有智慧的，博学的；明智的
英文释义: having or showing wisdom or knowledge usually from learning or experiencing many things
例句: They are both extremely wise.
例句释义: 他们都很有智慧。

英文释义: a woman who performs on the stage, on television or in films/movies, especially as a profession
例句: The princess in the film was played by a famous actress.
例句释义: 这部电影里的公主由一个著名的女演员扮演。

详细释义: n.山顶，顶点；（政府间的）峰会
英文释义: the highest point of something, especially the top of a mountain
例句: They climbed to the summit of the mountain and gave a huge cheer.
例句释义: 他们攀上了这座山的顶峰，然后尽情欢呼。

详细释义: n.【化学】酸；  adj.含酸过多的
英文释义: that contains acid or has the essential characteristics of an acid; that has a pH of less than seven
例句: Make sure not to touch the acid―it will burn.
例句释义: 千万不要去碰酸，它会灼伤你的皮肤。

英文释义: the degree to which something is likely to happen
例句: The odds of winning the prize draw is extremely low, around a million to one.
例句释义: 抽中奖的概率极低，大概是百万分之一。

详细释义: adj. 有天赋的；有才华的
英文释义: having great natural ability
例句: This gifted child could be the next Einstein.
例句释义: 这个有天赋的小孩也许可以成为下一个爱因斯坦。

英文释义: a feeling of anger or annoyance caused by being unable to do something :the state of being frustrated
例句: The boy falls in great frustration because of his poor learning ability.
例句释义: 男孩因自己学习能力差而深感沮丧。

详细释义: adj.中等的；适中的；  n.媒介
英文释义: in the middle between two sizes, amounts, lengths, temperatures, etc.
例句: I'd like a medium-sized television.
例句释义: 我想要一台中等尺寸的电视机。

英文释义: to recognize the difference between two people or things; to be a characteristic that makes two people, animals or things different; to be able to see or hear something
例句: It's easy to distinguish the blue man from the gray men.
例句释义: 我们很容易就能把这个小蓝人从一群小灰人中辨别出来。

英文释义: the land along the edge of an area of water (such as an ocean, lake, etc.)
例句: There is a big "2017" on the shore.
例句释义: 在海岸上有一个大大的“2017”。

英文释义: several time
例句: He repeatedly refused his son's request for candy.
例句释义: 他屡次拒绝儿子吃糖的要求。

英文释义: either of the two organs in the chest that you use for breathing
例句: Lungs are the organs responsible for breathing.
例句释义: 肺是负责呼吸的器官。

英文释义: easily or clearly heard, seen, felt, etc.
例句: The red umbrella is distinct among the black ones.
例句释义: 这把红色的伞在这些黑色的伞中显得与众不同。

英文释义: connected with art or artists
例句: You're never too old to discover your artistic side.
例句释义: 发掘自己作为艺术家的那一面，永远都不会晚。

详细释义: n. 交谈，演讲，论述，讲道；  v. 演讲，谈论
英文释义: a long and serious treatment or discussion of a subject in speech or writing; the use of language in speech and writing in order to produce meaning; language that is studied, usually in order to see how the different parts of a text are connected
例句: We had a long discourse about our views on life.
例句释义: 我们讨论了很久各自对生活的看法。

英文释义: a container for holding or carrying things. Baskets are made of thin strips of material that bends and twists easily, for example plastic, wire or wicker.
例句: I always use this basket to pack food for a picnic.
例句释义: 我经常用这个篮子来装野餐的食物。

英文释义: making a strong impression; deserving attention, admiration, or respect
例句: Big buildings are an impressive part of a city.
例句释义: 高楼大厦是城市中令人印象深刻的一部分。

英文释义: a person or an organization that competes against others, especially in business; a person who takes part in a competition
例句: Over 200 competitors entered the race.
例句释义: 200多名参赛者参加了跑步比赛。

英文释义: unpleasant to look at
例句: I have never seen such an ugly dog as this.
例句释义: 我从未见过如此丑的狗。

详细释义: adj. 发愁的，担心的，烦恼的
英文释义: thinking about unpleasant things that have happened or that might happen and therefore feeling unhappy and afraid
例句: Her face looks worried. She must be in some trouble.
例句释义: 她看起来愁容满面。她一定有什么麻烦。

英文释义: to show somebody/something in a picture; to describe somebody/something in a piece of writing
例句: I like to portray beautiful flowers in my paintings.
例句释义: 我喜欢画美丽的花。

详细释义: n. 粉；火药；  v. 抹粉
英文释义: a dry mass of very small fine pieces or grains
例句: The white powder is flour which can be used to make bread.
例句释义: 这种白色的粉末是面粉，可以用来做面包。

英文释义: the soul of a dead person thought of as living in an unseen world or as appearing to living people
例句: There are ghosts in movies and stories, but I don't think they are real.
例句释义: 电影和故事里有鬼魂，但我认为它们（在现实生活中）不是真的。

英文释义: to make somebody do something by giving them good reasons for doing it
例句: He is trying to persuade his friend to go on a roller coaster with him.
例句释义: 他正试图说服他的朋友和他一起坐过山车。

英文释义: that is neither very good, large, hot, etc. nor very bad, small, cold, etc.; having or showing opinions, especially about politics, that are not extreme; staying within limits that are considered to be reasonable by most people
例句: The yellow area indicates moderate power output.
例句释义: 黄色区域表示中等功率输出。

英文释义: happening or coming after something else
例句: The collision with the giant wave was responsible for the subsequent sinking of the ship.
例句释义: 与巨浪相撞是船随后沉没的主要原因。

英文释义: a small flat sweet cake for one person, usually baked until crisp
例句: Chocolate cookies are my favorite.
例句释义: 巧克力饼干是我的最爱。

英文释义: someone or something that carries something; a company that carries goods or passengers from one place to another, especially by air; a military vehicle or ship that carries soldiers or equipment from one place to another
例句: The carrier takes the goods towards his truck.
例句释义: 搬运工把货物搬去他的货车那儿。

英文释义: happening or doing something often
例句: There are frequent trains running between the two cities.
例句释义: 这两个城市间的火车班次很频繁。

英文释义: to order somebody not to do something, go somewhere, etc., especially officially
例句: Smoking is banned in public places.
例句释义: 公共场所禁止吸烟。

详细释义: adj.糟糕的，讨厌的；可怕的，极坏的
英文释义: extremely unpleasant, shocking, or bad
例句: This fish smells awful. Take it away!
例句释义: 这条鱼的气味太糟糕了，快把它拿走！

英文释义: to respect somebody for what they have done or to respect their qualities
例句: The little boy admires the firemen and salutes them.
例句释义: 小男孩很钦佩消防员叔叔并向他们敬礼。

详细释义: n.宠物；  adj.宠爱的，钟爱的；  v.宠爱，爱抚
英文释义: an animal (such as a dog, cat, bird, or fish) that people keep mainly for pleasure
例句: She likes her pet dog very much.
例句释义: 她非常喜欢她的宠物狗。

英文释义: an unusual or wonderful event that is believed to be caused by the power of God
例句: This mystic light swirling over my hands is a miracle.
例句释义: 这束在我手掌间萦绕的神秘光线是一个奇迹。

英文释义: to do more than the law or an order, etc. allows you to do
例句: This is dangerous―we're exceeding the maximum safe speed.
例句释义: 这很危险，我们已经超过了安全速度的最大值。

英文释义: a strong regular repeated pattern of sounds or movements
例句: Only with a good sense of rhythm can he play this game well.
例句释义: 想玩好这个游戏，他必须要有很强的节奏感。

详细释义: adj.分布广的；普遍的，广泛的
英文释义: existing or happening over a large area or among many people
例句: My love story quickly became widespread through the Internet.
例句释义: 通过网络，我的爱情故事很快就传开了。

详细释义: adj.美丽的，可爱的；令人愉快的
英文释义: attractive or beautiful especially in a graceful way
例句: The baby had lovely eyes.
例句释义: 宝宝有一双可爱的眼睛。

详细释义: n.罪孽，罪过；错误，过失；  v.违反戒律；犯过失
英文释义: an offence against God or against a religious or moral law
例句: There are seven deadly sins in early Catholic teachings.
例句释义: 天主教早期教义中有七宗罪。

英文释义: an organization for helping people in need
例句: The charity aims to help people in need.
例句释义: 这个慈善机构旨在帮助有需要的人。

英文释义: a written text of a play, film/movie, broadcast, talk, etc.; writing done by hand
例句: The actor is reading a line of the movie script.
例句释义: 这名演员正在读电影剧本里的一句台词。

详细释义: n.（为达到目的采取的）手段，战术，策略
英文释义: an action or method that is planned and used to achieve a particular goal
例句: The coach is explaining tactics for the following soccer game.
例句释义: 教练正在讲解接下来的足球赛中要用的战术。

英文释义: official papers or a document that can prove who you are
例句: Please bring your identifications when you travel abroad.
例句释义: 当你要出国旅游时，请带上你的各种身份证明。

英文释义: a complete change in somebody/something; used in South Africa to describe the process of making institutions and organizations more democratic
例句: She went through a significant transformation in the last four years.
例句释义: 她在过去的四年里经历了巨大的变化。

英文释义: used or happening every day or regularly; ordinary
例句: Doing exercise and keeping a healthy diet have become my everyday life.
例句释义: 做运动和坚持健康的饮食已经成了我的日常生活。

英文释义: the title of a newspaper article printed in large letters, especially at the top of the front page
例句: I didn't read the story; I only saw the headline.
例句释义: 我没看这个故事，我只看了眼标题。

详细释义: v.冒险；  n.（商业）冒险；投机，风险投资
英文释义: to go somewhere even though you know that it might be dangerous or unpleasant
例句: The boys venture deep into the forest.
例句释义: 男孩们深入森林冒险。

英文释义: the act of an army entering another country by force in order to take control of it
例句: An alien invasion would be a nightmare to human beings.
例句释义: 对于人类而言，外星人入侵将是一个噩梦。

英文释义: despite anything to the contrary (usually following a concession)
例句: He hates vegetables but, due to their health benefits, eats them nonetheless.
例句释义: 尽管他讨厌蔬菜，但因为蔬菜有益健康，他还是得吃它们。

详细释义: adj.足够的，充分的；尚可的，过得去的
英文释义: enough in quantity, or good enough in quality, for a particular purpose or need
例句: I have prepared an adequate amount of food for 5 people.
例句释义: 我为五个人准备了充足的食物。

详细释义: n.钢琴；  adv.轻柔地（弹或唱）
英文释义: a large musical instrument with a keyboard that you play by pressing black and white keys and that produces sound when small hammers inside the piano hit steel wires
例句: I love music and piano.
例句释义: 我喜欢音乐和钢琴。

英文释义: a shop/store that sells food and other things used in the home. In American English ‘grocery store’ is often used to mean ‘supermarket’.
例句: The man works happily in this grocery store.
例句释义: 这个男人在这家杂货店工作得很开心。

英文释义: the strength of something, for example light, that can be measured
例句: High intensity of light may blind your eyes.
例句释义: 强光线可能会闪瞎你的双眼。

详细释义: n. 展览会，陈列品；  v. 展览，陈列
英文释义: a collection of things, for example works of art, that are shown to the public
例句: Let's go to see the Picasso exhibit tomorrow.
例句释义: 我们明天去看毕加索的展览吧。

详细释义: n.毯子；覆盖层；  adj.综合的；  vt.使覆盖
英文释义: a large cover, often made of wool, used especially on beds to keep people warm
例句: The baby is covered with a blanket to keep it warm.
例句释义: 为了保暖，宝宝盖上毛毯。

英文释义: the empty space at the side of a written or printed page
例句: I often make notes in the margin.
例句释义: 我经常在页边空白处做笔记。

英文释义: a very small animal that has a pointed nose and a long, thin tail
例句: The mouse lives in a hole in the wall.
例句释义: 这只老鼠住在一个墙洞里。

详细释义: n.绳索；  v.用绳捆（或扎等）
英文释义: very strong thick string made by twisting thinner strings, wires, etc. together
例句: How thick a rope do we need?
例句释义: 我们需要多粗的绳子？

详细释义: n.混凝土；  adj.具体的；  v.给 (道路等) 浇混凝土
英文释义: building material that is made by mixing together cement, sand, small stones and water
例句: Concrete is a very useful substance for making buildings.
例句释义: 在修建建筑时，混凝土是一种非常有用的材料。

英文释义: an official piece of paper on which a doctor writes the type of medicine you should have, and which enables you to get it from a chemist’s shop/drugstore
例句: The doctor passed the prescription to the patient.
例句释义: 医生把处方递给了病人。

详细释义: v. 追赶；驱逐；  n. 追逐
英文释义: to run, drive, etc. after somebody/something in order to catch them
例句: The children are chasing the butterflies in the field.
例句释义: 孩子们在田野里追赶蝴蝶。

英文释义: baked clay used for building walls, houses and other buildings; an individual block of this
例句: Builders are using bricks to build the wall.
例句释义: 建筑工人在用砖块砌墙。

详细释义: v. 招募（新兵），招收（新成员）；  n. 新兵，新成员
英文释义: to find suitable people and get them to join a company, an organization, the armed forces, etc.
例句: Student clubs recruit new members every year.
例句释义: 学生社团每年都会招收新成员。

英文释义: a small piece of material that is used to cover a hole in something or to make a weak area stronger, or as decoration
例句: I tore a hole in my pants, so I sewed a patch over it.
例句释义: 我的裤子撕破了一个洞，所以我打了一个补丁在上面。

英文释义: an opinion that all members of a group agree with
例句: They reached a consensus about what to eat for dinner.
例句释义: 大家就聚餐吃什么的问题达成了一致。

详细释义: n.惊恐，震惊；令人惊恐的事
英文释义: a feeling of great shock, fear or disgust
例句: He screamed in horror when he saw the monster.
例句释义: 看到怪物时，他惊恐地尖叫起来。

详细释义: n.录像，录音；  adj.记录的，记录用的
英文释义: music, sounds, or images that have been stored on a record, CD, computer, etc., so that they can be heard or seen again
例句: We can transfer your old sound recording onto a CD so you can listen to it at home.
例句释义: 我们能把你老唱片上的音乐转存到光盘上，以便你在家也能听。

英文释义: a person whose job is painting buildings, walls, etc.; an artist who paints pictures
例句: The painter is painting a picture.
例句释义: 画家正在画画。

详细释义: n. 殖民地居民；  adj. 殖民地的，关于殖民的
英文释义: connected with or belonging to a country that controls another country; typical of or connected with the US at the time when it was still a British colony

例句: He wears the helmet for safety's sake.

例句: A log is a piece of wood that has been cut or has fallen from a tree.
例句释义: 原木就是从树上砍下来或掉下来的一块木头。

英文释义: if a sound echoes, it is reflected off a wall, the side of a mountain, etc. so that you can hear it again
例句: If you shout in this valley, you'll hear an echo.
例句释义: 在这个山谷里大喊，你就可以听见回声。

英文释义: a small flat round piece of medicine that you swallow without chewing it
例句: The woman took some pills when she was ill.
例句释义: 这个女人生病了，就吃了一些药。

英文释义: feeling or showing happiness and enthusiasm
例句: He was excited to win the computer game.
例句释义: 他因为玩电脑游戏获胜而兴奋不已。

英文释义: a work of art that is a solid figure or object made by carving or shaping wood, stone, clay, metal, etc.
例句: The lion sculpture is made of stone.
例句释义: 狮子雕塑是用石头刻的。

详细释义: n. 【化学】化合物；  vi. 妥协；  adj. 多功能的；  vt. 使恶化
英文释义: a substance created when the atoms of two or more chemical elements join together
例句: The compound is underground.
例句释义: 这种化合物是地下工厂做的。

例句: Our department's four teams must integrate together to work on new projects.
例句释义: 我们部门的四个小组必须合力推进新项目。

英文释义: a fine white or brown powder made from grain, especially wheat, and used in cooking for making bread, cakes, etc.
例句: There is a bag of flour.
例句释义: 这里有一包面粉。

详细释义: adj.味苦的；带来痛苦的；严寒的
英文释义: having a strong and often unpleasant taste; not sweet
例句: The medicine is so bitter that she can't drink it without adding sugar!
例句释义: 这药太苦了，她不加糖就喝不下去！

英文释义: not covered by any clothes; (of trees or countryside) not covered with leaves; without plants or trees; (of surfaces) not covered with or protected by anything; (of a room, cupboard, etc.) empty
例句: She walked on the beach in bare feet.
例句释义: 她赤着脚走在沙滩上。

英文释义: a surface or piece of land that slopes (= is higher at one end than the other); an area of land that is part of a mountain or hill
例句: This little slope is for people in wheelchairs.
例句释义: 这个小斜坡是供坐轮椅的人使用的。

英文释义: money that you pay in return for being able to use property and especially to live in an apartment, house, etc. that belongs to someone else
例句: I have to pay rent on my house every month.
例句释义: 我得每月支付我的房租。

详细释义: n.（供一人食用、饮用的）一份
英文释义: an individual quantity of food or drink taken as part of a meal
例句: She's making individual servings of soup for people to take.
例句释义: 她正把汤分成单人份供人们自取。

详细释义: adj.不明显的，微妙的；敏锐的；精细的；狡猾的
英文释义: not very noticeable or obvious
例句: There is a subtle change in his weight.
例句释义: 他的体重有细微的变化。

英文释义: to a great extent or degree
例句: The number of people in the streets greatly decreased because of the flu.
例句释义: 因为一场流感，街上的人变少了很多。

英文释义: a senior priest in charge of the work of the Church in a city or district
例句: The bishop is in charge of our church.
例句释义: 主教负责我们的教堂。

英文释义: the act or process of accepting; the state of being accepted or acceptable
例句: I was excited that my proposal found general acceptance among my colleagues.
例句释义: 我很兴奋，因为我的提议得到了同事们的广泛接纳。

详细释义: v. 抽水，抽取；  n. 打气筒；泵，抽水（机）
英文释义: to make water, air, gas, etc. flow in a particular direction by using a pump or something that works like a pump
例句: The man is going to pump some water.
例句释义: 这个男人打算抽点水出来。

英文释义: sweet food made of sugar and/or chocolate, eaten between meal
例句: I love to eat all kinds of candy.
例句释义: 我喜欢吃各种糖果。

详细释义: adj.邪恶的；  n.邪恶，罪恶，恶行
英文释义: (of people) enjoying harming others; morally bad and cruel
例句: This devilish monster has an evil stare.
例句释义: 魔鬼的眼中闪过一丝邪恶的光。

详细释义: adj. 高兴的，满意的；  v. 使高兴
英文释义: feeling happy about something
例句: She is very pleased with her cola and chips.
例句释义: 她对可乐和薯片感到非常满意。

英文释义: a flat piece of metal, usually shaped like a coin, that is given to the winner of a competition or to somebody who has been brave, for example in war
例句: These gold medals are symbols of honor.
例句释义: 这些金牌是荣誉的象征。

英文释义: to ask (someone) in a very serious and emotional way for something needed or wanted very much; to ask somebody for money, food, etc., especially in the street
例句: The little dog is begging his master for food.
例句释义: 这只小狗正在向主人乞求食物。

详细释义: vt. 赞助；做……的保人；  n. 赞助人
英文释义: a person or company that pays for a radio or television programme, or for a concert or sporting event, usually in return for advertising
例句: This TV program is sponsored by a number of companies.
例句释义: 这个电视节目由多家企业赞助。

详细释义: adj. 道德的；凭处方出售的；  n. 处方药
英文释义: connected with beliefs and principles about what is right and wrong
例句: Putting rubbish into the correct bins is environmentally ethical.
例句释义: 分类扔垃圾是一种环保且道德的行为。

详细释义: adj.第二的；(疾病、感染等) 继发性的
英文释义: less important than something else
例句: He took the silver medal, which is secondary in importance.
例句释义: 他获得了银牌，位列第二。

详细释义: v.砰地关上；砰地放下；  n.砰的一声
英文释义: to shut, or to make something shut, with a lot of force, making a loud noise
例句: He slams the door as he leaves.
例句释义: 他走的时候，砰的一声把门关上了。

详细释义: v.出口，输出；  n.出口，输出；出口商品
英文释义: to sell and send goods to another country
例句: Our company exports products to many different countries.
例句释义: 我们公司向许多国家出口货物。

英文释义: based on new ideas, forms or methods that are used to find out what effect they have
例句: Scientists aim at finding experimental evidence from experiments.
例句释义: 科学家们致力于从实验中找到证据。

英文释义: to become or make something become liquid as a result of heating
例句: Ice melts and turns into water if it's hot enough.
例句释义: 如果温度足够高，冰就会融化变成水。

英文释义: 12 o’clock at night
例句: When the clock shows 12 at night, it is midnight.
例句释义: 当时钟在晚上显示12点时，那便是午夜。

英文释义: to move or make something move in the shape of a curve; to be in the shape of a curve
例句: There are several curves in this mountain road.
例句释义: 这条山路有很多弯道。

英文释义: the quality of being honest and having strong moral principles
例句: The judge has a strong sense of integrity.
例句释义: 这位法官有强烈的正直感。

详细释义: v. 给（书）题名；给予…权利
英文释义: to give a title to a book, play, etc.
例句: The book is entitled: The Journey Westward.
例句释义: 这本书被题名为《西游记》。

详细释义: adj. 显然的，明显的，明白的
英文释义: clear; easily seen
例句: It's evident that the salesman is lying.
例句释义: 很明显这个推销员在说谎。

英文释义: a way of thinking or explaining something
例句: Speaking with clear logic allows people to understand your ideas better.
例句释义: 逻辑清晰的演讲可以让人们更好地理解你的想法。

英文释义: a liquid taken from a plant, etc. that contains its smell and taste in a very strong form
例句: Some people think that the essence of Indian food is curry.
例句释义: 一些人认为印度菜的精髓是咖喱。

英文释义: to prevent (someone) from doing something or being a part of a group; to decide or prove that it is wrong and not worth considering.
例句: He was excluded by other teenagers.
例句释义: 他被其他青少年排挤。

英文释义: unpleasant to listen to
例句: Stop scratching the blackboard! The harsh noise is driving them crazy.
例句释义: 别刮黑板了！这刺耳的声音快把他们逼疯了。

详细释义: n. 橱，壁橱，小储藏室；  v. 把……引进密室会谈；  adj. 私下的，秘密的
英文释义: a small room or a space in a wall with a door that reaches the floor, used for storing things
例句: My clothes are all hanging in the closet.
例句释义: 我的衣服都挂在衣橱里。

英文释义: living in or relating to a suburb or to suburbs in general

英文释义: to say hello to somebody or to welcome them
例句: This gentleman takes his hat off to greet people.
例句释义: 这位绅士摘下他的帽子，向人们问好。

英文释义: connected with the inside part of something
例句: The interior furnishing of the living room is very delicate.
例句释义: 客厅的内部装潢十分精致。

例句: The doctors and nurses are talking in the corridor.

详细释义: adj.零售的；  n.零售；  v.零售，以零售价销售；  adv.以零售方式，以零售形式

例句: The retail price of watermelon is two yuan per jin.

英文释义: march in a procession

例句释义: 每年的三月八日是妇女节。

英文释义: a reptile with a very long thin body and no legs. There are many types of snake, some of which are poisonous
例句: Don't be afraid of my pet snake; it's very friendly.
例句释义: 不用害怕我的宠物蛇，它很友好。

英文释义: a reason, either true or invented, that you give to explain or defend your behaviour
例句: He made up a stupid excuse for not doing homework.
例句释义: 他为没做作业编了个愚蠢的借口。

例句释义: 多可爱的小猪！

详细释义: adj. 古典的；  n. 古典音乐
英文释义: connected with or influenced by the culture of ancient Greece and Rome
例句: I love classical music.
例句释义: 我热爱古典音乐。

英文释义: a state of human society that is very developed and organized; a society, its culture and its way of life during a particular period of time or in a particular part of the world; all the people in the world and the societies they live in, considered as a whole
例句: They are all outstanding achievements of human civilization.
例句释义: 它们都是人类文明中的伟大成就。

详细释义: v.折叠；彻底失败；合拢；  n.折叠；褶皱
英文释义: to bend something, especially paper or cloth, so that one part lies on top of another part

英文释义: to change something completely so that it is the opposite of what it was before; when a vehicle or its driver reverses or the driver reverses a vehicle, the vehicle goes backwards

例句释义: 他正将车倒进私家车道里。

英文释义: that cannot be found or that is not in its usual place, or at home
例句: "My discus is missing. Where is it?" the statue wondered.
例句释义: “诶，我的铁饼丢了，去哪儿了？” 这个雕塑疑惑道。

英文释义: a connection between two things in which one thing changes as the other does
例句: There is a strong correlation between stock price and profits.
例句释义: 股票价格和利润之间有很明显的相关性。

英文释义: the quality of being kind to people and animals by making sure that they do not suffer more than is necessary; the quality of being humane
例句: Mankind exists because of those common humanity.
例句释义: 人类之所以存在，是因为有这些共同的人道精神。

英文释义: a sudden bright light that shines for a moment and then disappears
例句: The lightning flashed across the sky.
例句释义: 一道闪电划过天空。

英文释义: someone who develops real estate (especially someone who prepares a site for residential or commercial use)
例句: The developer bought the land with plans to build a shopping mall on it.
例句释义: 开发商买下了这块地，打算在上面修建购物商场。

英文释义: that can be trusted to do something well; that you can rely on
例句: My mobile phone is very reliable!
例句释义: 我的手机相当靠得住！

详细释义: n. 牛肉；  v. 抱怨
英文释义: meat that comes from a cow
例句: This is a pack of beef steaks.
例句释义: 这是一盒牛肉。

详细释义: adj.罗马的，罗马文字的，罗马人的；  n.罗马天主教的

例句: This is a Roman historical relic that is still standing in Rome.
例句释义: 这处古罗马遗迹依然伫立于罗马。

英文释义: the design or style of a building or buildings;  the art and study of designing buildings
例句: Our professor is explaining the theory of architecture in class.
例句释义: 我们的教授正在课堂上讲解建筑学理论。

英文释义: happening or done sometimes but not often
例句: I only work on an occasional basis - I come when they need me.
例句释义: 我只是偶尔工作，他们需要帮忙的时候我就来。

英文释义: connected with organizing the work of a business or an institution
例句: She was busy with administrative work all day.
例句释义: 她一整天都忙于行政工作。

详细释义: n. 手肘；衣服肘部；  v. 用肘推、挤

例句: My elbow hurts really bad!
例句释义: 我的胳膊肘伤得很重！

英文释义: causing or likely to cause death; extreme; complete
例句: The mouse died after eating the deadly bread, which had been poisoned.
例句释义: 那只老鼠吃了带毒药的面包后死了。

英文释义: to think wrongly that somebody/something is somebody/something else; to make somebody unable to think clearly or understand something
例句: I always confuse the girl with her twin sister.

英文释义: a flying vehicle with wings and one or more engines
例句: You can go through the clouds by taking airplanes. It feels so amazing!
例句释义: 坐飞机可以穿过云层，那感觉太神奇了！

详细释义: adj. 每月的；  adv. 每月一次，按月；  n. 月刊
英文释义: happening, done, or made every month
例句: I have to keep up with my monthly house payments.
例句释义: 我必须按时付清我房屋的月供。

例句: Ducks are swimming happily in the water.
例句释义: 鸭子们在水中欢快地游着。

英文释义: the amount of a medicine, drug, or vitamin that is taken at one time
例句: The doctor is telling the patient the recommended dose of his medicine.
例句释义: 医生正在告诉病人药物的推荐剂量。

英文释义: (a person) from North Korea or South Korea
例句: This box reminds me of something Korean.
例句释义: 这个盒子让我想起一些和韩国有关的东西！

英文释义: to ask somebody for something in a very strong and serious way; to state in court that you are guilty or not guilty of a crime
例句: The girl pleaded with her mom to allow her to go to the party.
例句释义: 女孩恳求她的妈妈允许她去参加聚会。

详细释义: v. 开始，发动；  n. 新加入组织的人
例句: The boy initiated the war by launching a missile.
例句释义: 小男孩发射导弹发动了这场战争。

详细释义: n.演讲；讲课；  v.演讲；向……演讲
英文释义: a talk that is given to a group of people to teach them about a particular subject, often as part of a university or college course
例句: He gave a lecture in front of many people.
例句释义: 他在很多人面前发表了演讲。

详细释义: n. 厢式货车；（火车的）货车车厢
英文释义: a covered vehicle with no side windows in its back half, usually smaller than a lorry/truck, used for carrying goods or people
例句: The large van could hold many boxes.

英文释义: a part of the sea, or of a large lake, partly surrounded by a wide curve of the land
例句: The bay cuts into the land and makes a perfect place to go swimming.
例句释义: 这片海湾嵌入陆地, 使之成为绝佳的游泳场所。

详细释义: adj.主流的；  n.主流，主要倾向
英文释义: considered normal because it reflects what is done or accepted by most people

英文释义: an area where people live that is outside the centre of a city

例句释义: 这片郊区离城市大约有一小时车程。

详细释义: n. 三明治，夹肉面包；  vt. 夹入，挤进
英文释义: two pieces of bread with something (such as meat, peanut butter, etc.) between them
例句: The kids were really happy when I made them each a sandwich for lunch.
例句释义: 当我给孩子们每人做了一个三明治当午餐时，他们好开心。

英文释义: the long, flexible nose of an elephant
例句: The bird is feeding on the trunk of the tree.
例句释义: 小鸟正在树干上进食。

英文释义: information or a story that is passed from person to person but has not been proven to be true
例句: Rumor can be spread very quickly on the Internet.
例句释义: 网络上的谣言可以传播得很快。

英文释义: the act of accomplishing some aim or executing some order
例句: The implementation of the project will begin once they have agreed terms.
例句释义: 双方达成协议后，即可落实该项目。

详细释义: v.吞咽；  n.燕子；  vi.做吞咽动作，咽口水
英文释义: to make food, drink, etc. go down your throat into your stomach
例句: She always lifts her head when swallowing pills.
例句释义: 她总是会在吞药片的时候抬起头。

英文释义: to give (someone) a reason for doing something
例句: Praise from a teacher can always motivate students.
例句释义: 来自老师的夸赞经常能激励学生。

详细释义: v.提供，给予；使成为，致使，使处于（某种状态）；粉刷，往（墙上）抹灰
英文释义: to cause somebody/something to be in a particular state or condition
例句: The kind teacher rendered a lot of financial assistance to her poor students.
例句释义: 善良的老师为贫困生提供了很多经济援助。

英文释义: a clever plan designed to trick somebody, either by capturing them or by making them do or say something that they did not mean to do or say
例句: The man is about to fall into the trap!
例句释义: 这个男人就要陷入圈套了！

英文释义: to stop somebody/something from moving or acting freely; to control something with rules or laws
例句: This sign board indicates that all vehicles are restricted to enter.
例句释义: 这个标志表示所有机动车禁止通行。

英文释义: material made by weaving or knitting cotton, wool, silk, etc.
例句: The shop sells different kinds of cloth.
例句释义: 这家商店出售各式各样的布料。

英文释义: from appearances alone
例句: He was seemingly happy, but we didn't know how sad he really was.
例句释义: 他表面上很开心，但我们都不知道他其实有多难过。

详细释义: adj. 立法的，有立法权的；  n. 立法权，立法机构
英文释义: connected with the act of making and passing laws
例句: The legislative branch of government passes laws.
例句释义: 政府的立法机构制定法律。

英文释义: to make sure that people obey a particular law or rule
例句: The new parking restrictions will be strictly enforced.
例句释义: 新的停车规定将被严格执行。

英文释义: a curved piece of glass or plastic that makes things look larger, smaller or clearer when you look through it
例句: These camera lenses cost a lot.
例句释义: 这些相机镜头很贵。

详细释义: n. 检查员，督察员；视察者，检阅者；<英>查票员
英文释义: a person whose job is to visit schools, factories, etc. to check that rules are being obeyed and that standards are acceptable
例句: This inspector is examining the machinery in the factory.
例句释义: 该检查员正在检查工厂里的机器。

英文释义: to give something to somebody or allow them to use something that belongs to you, which they have to return to you later
例句: She lent him a pen in the exam.
例句释义: 考试的时候，她借给他一支钢笔。

英文释义: not decorated or complicated; simple; without marks or a pattern on it
例句: I like plain T-shirts as they are simple and cheap.
例句释义: 我喜欢朴素的T恤，因为它们简单又便宜。

英文释义: a person who pretends to have qualities, abilities, etc. that they do not really have in order to cheat other people
例句: The fraud obtains money by deception through the phone.
例句释义: 骗子通过电话诈骗获取钱财。

详细释义: n.同伴，志同道合的人；指南
英文释义: a person or an animal that travels with you or spends a lot of time with you
例句: Dogs are good companions.
例句释义: 狗狗是很好的伙伴。

详细释义: v. 搏斗；争辩；坚决主张
英文释义: to compete against somebody in order to gain something
例句: The two knights are contending for the love of the princess.
例句释义: 两位骑士正在为得到公主的爱而搏斗。

详细释义: n.指甲，爪；  v.将……钉牢，钉住
英文释义: thin hard layer covering the outer tip of the fingers or toes
例句: I got diverse patterns on my nails from the salon.
例句释义: 我去美甲沙龙给指甲做了不同的图案。

详细释义: n.排；陈列；编队；  v.排列；部署
英文释义: a set of numbers, signs or values arranged in rows and columns
例句: I was lecturing to an array of empty seats!
例句释义: 我对着一排空座位讲课！

详细释义: adj.（条例、法规等）严格的；严厉的
英文释义: demanding that rules, especially rules about behaviour, should be obeyed
例句: Students must obey these strict school rules.
例句释义: 学生必须遵守这些严格的校规。

英文释义: to fit together all the separate parts of something, for example a piece of furniture
例句: The factory assembles cars.
例句释义: 这家工厂负责装配车辆。

英文释义: a small animal with a long tail, that looks like a large mouse, usually considered a pest (= an animal which is disliked because it destroys food or spreads disease)
例句: Look! The three rats are waving to us.
例句释义: 看，这三只老鼠在跟我们挥手。

详细释义: v.爆炸；  n.迸发；  vi.突然出现；  vt.使胀满
英文释义: to break open or apart, especially because of pressure from inside; to make something break in this way
例句: The red balloon burst, and it scared the child.
例句释义: 这个红色的气球爆炸了，吓到了这个孩子。

英文释义: an interior passage or corridor onto which rooms open
例句: The hallway is totally empty; where is everybody?
例句释义: 走廊空无一人，大家都去哪了？

英文释义: a large hole in the side of a hill or under the ground
例句: He went into the dark cave by himself.
例句释义: 他独自一人走进了漆黑的山洞。

英文释义: that you cannot avoid or prevent
例句: An accident seems inevitable driving so dangerously!
例句释义: 如此危险驾驶，一场车祸似乎已不可避免！

英文释义: the direction or region at an equal distance between south and west
例句: We live to the southwest of our school.
例句释义: 我们住在学校的西南方。

详细释义: n.怪物；巨兽，巨大的东西；极其残酷的人，恶人，恶魔；  adj.巨大的
英文释义: (in stories) an imaginary creature that is very large, ugly and frightening
例句: The blue monster is both scary and funny.
例句释义: 这个蓝色的怪兽既可怕又好笑。

英文释义: if something is unexpected, it surprises you because you were not expecting it
例句: Something unexpected happened when they were posing.
例句释义: 当他们在摆造型的时候，意想不到的事情发生了。

英文释义: an object that is in your way and that makes it difficult for you to move forward
例句: The bunny jumps over the obstacles.
例句释义: 小兔子跳过了这些障碍物。

英文释义: to make an action or a process possible or easier
例句: The supermarket bought self-checkout machines to facilitate quicker payment.
例句释义: 这家超市购入自助结账机，以方便快捷支付。

详细释义: v. 撕开，扯破，裂开，敲诈；  n. 裂缝，裂口
英文释义: to tear something or to become torn, often suddenly or violently; to remove something quickly or violently, often by pulling it; to copy sound or video files from a website or CD on to a computer; to change text or images into a form in which they can be displayed on a screen or printed
例句: Oh no! I ripped both the red envelop and the money!
例句释义: 不！我把钱连同红包一起撕破了！

英文释义: a plant or a part of a plant that is used as medicine or to give flavor to food
例句: Herbs can be made into medicine.
例句释义: 药草可以用来制药。

详细释义: adj.压倒性的，势不可当的；巨大的
英文释义: very great or very strong; so powerful that you cannot resist it or decide how to react
例句: The red team won an overwhelming victory against the blue team in the election.
例句释义: 红队在选举中战胜了蓝队，取得了压倒性的胜利。

英文释义: the action of incorporating a racial or religious group into a community
例句: The integration of AI will revolutionize the automotive industry.
例句释义: 与人工智能的融合将会改变汽车行业。

详细释义: n. 水晶，晶体；结晶；水晶做成的东西
英文释义: a clear mineral, such as quartz, used in making jewellery and decorative objects
例句: She is holding a purple crystal in her hand.
例句释义: 她正拿着一块紫水晶。

英文释义: a difficult time for the economy of a country, when there is less trade and industrial activity than usual and more people are unemployed
例句: During a recession, there's less money in the economy to spend on goods or investments.
例句释义: 在经济衰退期间，用于购买商品或投资的资金减少了。

英文释义: set down in writing in any of various ways
例句: They have to take a written test before the interview.
例句释义: 在面试之前，他们要先做一个笔试。

详细释义: n.动机，目的；  adj.发动的，运动的；  v.引发，促进，激发
英文释义: a reason for doing something
例句: His motive in the competition was to win the championship.
例句释义: 他参加比赛的动机是拿冠军。

英文释义: a large amount of water covering an area that is usually dry
例句: The flood submerged the village and the farm.
例句释义: 这场洪水淹没了村庄和农场。

详细释义: n. 笔，钢笔；  v. 关押，监禁
英文释义: (often in compounds) an instrument made of plastic or metal used for writing with ink
例句: Sign this with a pen, please.
例句释义: 请用钢笔在这儿签字。

英文释义: the fact of owning something
例句: The couple have the certificate to prove their ownership of this house.
例句释义: 房产证可以证明这对夫妻拥有这栋房子的所有权。

英文释义: a dream that is very frightening or unpleasant; an experience that is very frightening and unpleasant, or very difficult to deal with
例句: The boy had a nightmare that he was chased by a mad dog.
例句释义: 这个男孩做了一个噩梦，梦见他被一条恶犬狂追。

英文释义: an official visit to a school, factory, etc. in order to check that rules are being obeyed and that standards are acceptable; the act of looking closely at something/somebody, especially to check that everything is as it should be
例句: The mechanic gave the car a thorough inspection according to the check list.
例句释义: 技工根据检查清单对汽车进行了一次全面检查。

英文释义: a person who supervises somebody/something
例句: The supervisor is overseeing the construction progress.
例句释义: 监督员正在督查施工进度。

英文释义: to go to somebody for information or advice; to ask for the professional opinion of someone
例句: She is consulting the doctor about her illness.
例句释义: 她正向医生咨询她的病情。

详细释义: n.竞技场，角斗场；（活动、斗争或竞争的）场所，战场，（竞争）舞台
英文释义: a place with a flat open area in the middle and seats around it where people can watch sports and entertainment
例句: The Rome Colosseum was an arena built in ancient times.
例句释义: 罗马斗兽场是古时候修建的竞技场。

英文释义: the act of discovering or identifying the exact cause of an illness or a problem
例句: My diagnosis is that you have a minor heart problem.
例句释义: 我的诊断结果是：你的心脏有个小毛病。

英文释义: the state of having control of the ball
例句: My house is my most expensive possession.
例句释义: 我的房子是我最贵重的财产。

英文释义: to stop feeling angry with somebody who has done something to harm, annoy or upset you; to stop feeling angry with yourself; used to say in a polite way that you are sorry if what you are doing or saying seems rude or silly
例句: The kitty has forgiven its master for hugging other cats.
例句释义: 小猫原谅主人抱了别的猫。

英文释义: with consistency or congruency
例句: I consistently hit the target.
例句释义: 我持续射中了目标。

英文释义: a room or rooms in a building, partly or completely below the level of the ground
例句: Many workers in Beijing live in the basement.
例句释义: 在北京，很多打工的人都住在地下室里。

详细释义: v. 漂流；使漂流；  n. 漂流物
英文释义: to move along smoothly and slowly in water or air
例句: The boat is drifting down the river.
例句释义: 船顺着河流漂下。

详细释义: v.沥干；喝光；  n.下水道，排水管
英文释义: to make something empty or dry by removing all the liquid from it; to become empty or dry in this way
例句: Let the water drain off the vegetables before you cook them.
例句释义: 烹饪蔬菜前要把水沥干。

英文释义: a person or an organization that prosecutes somebody in court, together with the lawyers, etc.
例句: The cat is facing prosecution over his attack on the poor rabbit.
例句释义: 这只猫因为攻击那只可怜的兔子而面临起诉。

英文释义: as large, fast, etc. as is possible, or the most that is possible or allowed
例句: Oh no! My weight has reached the maximum!
例句释义: 哦不！我的体重达到了量程的最大值！

英文释义: a spoken or written statement that informs people about something; the act of publicly informing people about something
例句: The famous couple made an official announcement about their marriage.
例句释义: 这对明星夫妻正式宣布了他们的婚事。

英文释义: a statement that says what you think will happen; the act of making such a statement
例句: The manager showed his predictions for the year to his team.
例句释义: 经理向他的团队展示了他对今年情况的预测。

英文释义: (microbiology) single-celled or noncellular spherical or spiral or rod-shaped organisms lacking chlorophyll that reproduce by fission; important as pathogens and for biochemical properties; taxonomy is difficult; often considered plants
例句: You can't see bacteria without a microscope.
例句释义: 细菌只有在显微镜下才能被看到。

英文释义: a written list of questions that are answered by a number of people so that information can be collected from the answers
例句: Please fill out this questionnaire so that we can improve our service.
例句释义: 请填写这份调查问卷，这样可以帮助我们改善服务。

英文释义: wet earth that is soft and sticky
例句: Oh no! I think our car is stuck in the mud!
例句释义: 哦，不！我想我们的车被卡在泥里了！

英文释义: the basic systems and services that are necessary for a country or an organization to run smoothly, for example buildings, transport and water and power supplies
例句: A good infrastructure includes transport, communications, etc.
例句释义: 完善的基础设施包括交通、通信等。

详细释义: n.匆忙；  v.赶紧（做某事）；催促
英文释义: the need or wish to get something done quickly
例句: He is often in a hurry to eat his breakfast and get ready.
例句释义: 他总是匆忙地吃早饭和准备出门。

英文释义: the rights and advantages that rich and powerful people in a society have; a special right or advantage that a particular person or group of people has
例句: He enjoys the privilege of being able to fast check in the airport he owns.
例句释义: 他享有在他的机场里快速登机的特权。

英文释义: a building used for the worship of a god or gods, especially in religions other than Christianity
例句: The old temple was beautiful at night.
例句释义: 这个古老的庙宇在晚上十分漂亮。

英文释义: used, happening or located outside rather than in a building
例句: Many people enjoy outdoor activities in their leisure time.
例句释义: 很多人喜欢在空闲时间进行户外活动。

英文释义: to take liquid, air, etc. into your mouth by using the muscles of your lips; to keep something in your mouth and pull on it with your lips and tongue; to take liquid, air, etc. out of something
例句: The baby always sucks his fingers.
例句释义: 宝宝总是很喜欢吸手指。

详细释义: n.广播或电视节目；  v.播放，广播
英文释义: to tell a lot of people about something; to send out programmes on television or radio
例句: A broadcast is a program, a performance, or a speech on the radio or on television.
例句释义: 广播电视节目是指在收音机里或在电视上播放的节目、表演或演说。

英文释义: to jump high or a long way
例句: The man leaped from a cliff to another cliff on the sea.
例句释义: 这个男人在海上从一个悬崖跳向另一个悬崖。

英文释义: done, chosen, etc. without somebody deciding in advance what is going to happen, or without any regular pattern
例句: It's just a random series of numbers.
例句释义: 这就是一系列随机的数字。

英文释义: the joint between the hand and the arm
例句: The basketball player injured his wrist.
例句释义: 这个篮球运动员的手腕受伤了。

英文释义: a piece of cloth that hangs down from above a window and can be used to cover the window; a piece of thick, heavy cloth that hangs in front of the stage in the theatre
例句: The purple curtains make my living room look so elegant.
例句释义: 这紫色的窗帘让我的客厅看起来很优雅。

英文释义: a small area of still water, especially one that is artificial
例句: The duck dived into the pond.
例句释义: 鸭子一头扎进了池塘。

英文释义: lands owned or ruled by a particular person, government, etc., especially in the past
例句: Don't cross the line. This is my domain!
例句释义: 别越过这条线。这是我的地盘！

英文释义: the unhappy feelings caused by knowing or thinking that you have done something wrong
例句: The boy is filled with guilt because he has broken the glass.
例句释义: 那个小男孩很内疚，因为他打碎了玻璃杯。

英文释义: cows and bulls that are kept as farm animals for their milk or meat
例句: The man is rounding up the cattle.
例句释义: 这人正在赶牛。

详细释义: adj.最少的，最低程度的；  n.最低限度，最小量
英文释义: the smallest or lowest amount that is possible, required or recorded; an extremely small amount
例句: In theory, the minimum temperature is minus 273.15 degrees Celsius.
例句释义: 理论上说，最低温度是零下273.15摄氏度。

英文释义: connected with government or public money, especially taxes
例句: The pie chart shows the educational, military and medical fiscal expenditure in 2009.
例句释义: 这个饼状图展示了2009年的教育、军事和医疗财政支出情况。

英文释义: a piece of clothing worn by women and girls that hangs from the waist down
例句: Her red skirt matches well with her red sunglasses.
例句释义: 她的红色裙子和红色太阳镜很搭。

详细释义: vt.倾倒，丢弃；  n.垃圾场，废物堆
英文释义: to get rid of something you do not want, especially in a place which is not suitable
例句: The big truck is dumping waste materials.
例句释义: 这辆大卡车正在倾倒废料。

例句: There is always someone stealing the crops, hence they build a fence.
例句释义: 老有人来这里偷玉米，因此他们修了篱笆。

英文释义: an organized set of data that is stored in a computer and can be looked at and used in various ways
例句: He works in the data center and maintains the database.
例句释义: 他在数据中心工作，负责维护数据库。

英文释义: anxious, embarrassed or afraid and unable to relax; making you feel like this; not feeling physically relaxed, warm, etc.; unpleasant or difficult to deal with
例句: My stomach feels really uncomfortable all the time.
例句释义: 我肚子一直不舒服。

详细释义: v. 处决；完成（动作）；实行；执行（计划）
英文释义: to kill somebody or something, especially as a legal punishment
例句: This pathetic bird is going to be executed by the cruel hunter.
例句释义: 这只可怜的小鸟将要被残酷的猎人处决了。

详细释义: n. 肢体；臂；枝干；树枝；  v. 肢解
英文释义: an arm or a leg; a similar part of an animal, such as a wing
例句: She lost a limb from an illness, but she can still run!
例句释义: 她因为疾病失去了一条腿，但她还可以跑步。

详细释义: n. 意识形态，思想（体系）
英文释义: a set of ideas that an economic or political system is based on; a set of beliefs, especially one held by a particular group, that influences the way people behave
例句: The animals formed two opposite ideologies based on what they eat.
例句释义: 动物根据它们吃的东西形成了两种相反的意识形态。

英文释义: a series of musical notes that are sung or played in a particular order to form a piece of music
例句: Musicians can play wonderful tunes on the violin.
例句释义: 音乐家能用小提琴弹奏出美妙的曲子。

详细释义: n. 伤害，损害；  v. 伤害
英文释义: damage or injury that is caused by a person or an event
例句: This kind of drug may cause serious harm to the heart.
例句释义: 这种药物可能对心脏造成严重损害。

详细释义: n. 铁路；  v. 迫使某人做某事
英文释义: a system of tracks, together with the trains that run on them, and the organization and people; a track with rails on which trains run
例句: I’m afraid to fly, so I use the railroad for long distance travel.
例句释义: 我怕坐飞机，所以我长途旅行都选择坐火车。

英文释义: to experience and deal with something that is painful or unpleasant, especially without complaining
例句: It is very hard to endure the toothache.
例句释义: 牙痛是难以忍受的。

英文释义: a type of dangerous and powerful energy that is produced by radioactive substances and nuclear reactions
例句: Don't get closer to radiation if you are not in a protective suit.
例句释义: 没有穿防辐射服就不要靠近辐射物。

英文释义: a hard pointed part that grows, usually in pairs, on the heads of some animals, such as sheep and cows.
例句: This animal's horns are very long and curly.
例句释义: 这只动物的角又长又弯。

详细释义: adj.（疾病）慢性的；积习难改的；（问题）顽固的
英文释义: (especially of a disease) lasting for a long time
例句: He's suffering from chronic neck and back pain.
例句释义: 他有慢性脖子痛和背痛。

英文释义: quiet and calm; not worried or disturbed in any way
例句: She sits by the lake in a peaceful way.
例句释义: 她平静地坐在湖边。

详细释义: n.创新，革新；新事物，新方法
英文释义: the introduction of new things, ideas or ways of doing something; a new idea, way of doing something, etc. that has been introduced or discovered
例句: The age of innovation is upon us! Hurry up with my dinner!
例句释义: 我们正在步入一个创新的时代！赶快把我的晚餐做好端上来！

详细释义: n.负担；  v.拉紧；劳累；过度使用
英文释义: pressure on somebody/something because they have too much to do or manage, or something very difficult to deal with; the problems, worry or anxiety that this produces
例句: Her kid's summer course fees put her under great financial strain.
例句释义: 孩子的暑假班费用使她承受着很大的经济负担。

英文释义: a musical instrument that is held against the front of your body and that has usually six strings which are played with your fingers or with a pick
例句: I have always wanted to play music on the guitar.
例句释义: 我一直希望能用吉他弹奏歌曲。

英文释义: a person or thing that replaces someone or something else
例句: She threw away the worn curtain and found a replacement.
例句释义: 她扔掉了破旧的窗帘，找到了一个替代品。

英文释义: to do things in a way that people think is correct or polite
例句: The boy's mother asked him to behave himself and not be rude.
例句释义: 男孩的妈妈让他守规矩些，不要粗鲁。

详细释义: v. 管理；执行；实施；给予；用（药）
英文释义: to manage and organize the affairs of a company, an organization, a country, etc.
例句: His job as manager is to administer many departments within the company.
例句释义: 作为经理，他的工作是管理公司内部的许多部门。

英文释义: a small change or improvement that is made to a law or a document; the process of changing a law or a document
例句: I made an amendment to my homework and corrected my mistake.
例句释义: 我对家庭作业做了些改正，修改了其中的错误。

详细释义: n.便笺簿；（动物的）脚；  v.填塞
英文释义: a number of pieces of paper for writing or drawing on, that are fastened together at one edge
例句: You can use an iPad to write notes instead of a pad of paper.
例句释义: 你可以不用纸质的便签簿，而用iPad来记笔记。

英文释义: the act or process of passing something from one person, place or thing to another; the act or process of sending out an electronic signal or message or of broadcasting a radio or television programme; a radio or television message or broadcast; the system in a vehicle by which power is passed from the engine to the wheels
例句: This tower was built for mobile phone signal transmission.
例句释义: 这座塔是用来传输手机信号的。

英文释义: to wait for somebody/something
例句: People awaited in a line to get on the bus.
例句释义: 人们站成一排等候上车。

英文释义: no longer active in your work or profession
例句: The retired people are playing chess together.
例句释义: 这些退休老人正在一起下棋。

详细释义: n.（枪等的）扳机；  vt.触发，引起，激发
英文释义: the part of a gun that you press in order to fire it; something that is the cause of a particular reaction or development, especially a bad one
例句: Pulling the gun's trigger causes it to fire.
例句释义: 扣动枪的扳机开火。

详细释义: v.使流出；（人群）涌出；  n.溢出，溅出
英文释义: to cause or allow (something) to fall, flow, or run over the edge of a container usually in an accidental way
例句: Oh no, I've spilled the green nail polish.
例句释义: 哦不，我把这瓶绿色的指甲油弄洒了。

英文释义: feeling or showing thanks because somebody has done something kind for you or has done as you asked
例句: Everyone was so grateful to the medical team that they lined the road, waving thankfully.
例句释义: 每个人都非常感谢医疗队。他们站在路边，满怀谢意地与医疗队员们挥手告别。

详细释义: n.优美；慈悲，善意，宽厚，仁慈；  vt.使……增光
英文释义: an attractive quality of movement that is smooth, elegant and controlled
例句: These athletes performed with much grace in the competition.
例句释义: 这些运动员在竞技时表现得非常优美。

英文释义: made to appear to exist by the use of computer software, for example on the Internet
例句: His girlfriend only appears when he wears the virtual reality glasses.
例句释义: 只有在他戴上虚拟现实眼镜的时候，他的女朋友才会出现。

英文释义: an area that is controlled by or belongs to a country and is usually far away from it
例句: A colony on another planet might look like this!
例句释义: 在另一个星球，殖民地可能是这样的！

英文释义: the act of adopting a child; the decision to start using something such as an idea, a plan or a name; the act of choosing somebody as a candidate for an election
例句: They were already looking into adoption.
例句释义: 他们已经在考虑领养一个小孩了。

详细释义: adj. 土生土长的，本土的
英文释义: produced, living, or existing naturally in a particular region or environment
例句: The giant panda is an animal which is indigenous to China.
例句释义: 大熊猫是中国土生土长的动物。

详细释义: n. 犯人；  v. （经审讯）证明……有罪，使……知罪
英文释义: a person who has been found guilty of a crime and sent to prison
例句: The convict is in prison for some pretty terrible crimes.
例句释义: 这个犯人因为一些很严重的罪行而入狱。

详细释义: n.毛巾，手巾；  v.用毛巾擦干
英文释义: a piece of cloth or paper used for drying things, especially your body
例句: She uses a blue towel to dry her hair.
例句释义: 她用一条蓝色的毛巾擦头发。

英文释义: to change something slightly, especially in order to make it more suitable for a particular purpose
例句: This car has been modified to make it even faster.
例句释义: 这辆车已经被改装过，以便它跑得更快。

详细释义: n. 粒子，微粒；【语】小品词
英文释义: a very small piece of something
例句: Atoms are very small particles.
例句释义: 原子是非常小的粒子。

详细释义: n.奖品，奖赏；  adj.得奖的；  v.珍视
英文释义: an award that is given to a person who wins a competition, race, etc. or who does very good work
例句: The man won first prize in the competition.
例句释义: 那个男人获得了比赛的一等奖。

详细释义: n.登陆，着陆；码头；降落；楼梯平台
英文释义: an act of bringing an aircraft or a spacecraft down to the ground after a journey; the area at the top of a set of stairs where you arrive before you go into an upstairs room or move onto another set of stairs; an act of bringing soldiers to land in an area that is controlled by the enemy; a flat wooden platform on the water where boats let people get on and off, and load and unload goods
例句: Air traffic controllers' instructions are crucial for the safe landing of aircrafts.
例句释义: 空中交通管制员的指挥对飞机的安全着陆至关重要。

英文释义: to make something increase, or become better or more successful
例句: The turtle uses a rocket to boost his speed.
例句释义: 这个乌龟使用火箭来增加自己的速度。

英文释义: an animal like a mouse with wings, that flies and feeds at night (= it is nocturnal). There are many types of bat.
例句: Bats hang themselves upside down when they sleep.
例句释义: 蝙蝠睡觉的时候会将身体倒挂起来。

详细释义: n.警报器，警报；  v.使惊恐，使忧虑
英文释义: a device that warns people of a particular danger; a loud noise or a signal that warns people of danger or of a problem
例句: The police car turned on the alarm as it passed by here.
例句释义: 警车路过时，打开了警报器。

英文释义: a day or period of the year when people stop working to celebrate a special event, often a religious one; a series of performances of music, plays, films/movies, etc., usually organized in the same place once a year; a series of public events connected with a particular activity or idea
例句: Traditionally people spend time with their families during the Chinese Spring Festival.
例句释义: 人们历来在春节期间与家人共度时光。

详细释义: n. 紧握，握力；  v. 握紧，抓牢
英文释义: to hold something tightly; to hold onto or to move over a surface without slipping
例句: You'd better not lose your grip on the mountain for your safety.
例句释义: 安全起见，你最好攀岩时别撒手。

详细释义: adj.奇异的，不寻常的；古怪的，诡异的
英文释义: very strange or unusual and difficult to explain
例句: These root vegetables look so weird.
例句释义: 这些根茎类蔬菜看起来非常奇怪。

详细释义: vt.暗中破坏；逐渐削弱；侵蚀……的基础
英文释义: to make something, especially somebody’s confidence or authority, gradually weaker or less effective
例句: Cyber-criminals undermine the Internet's security.
例句释义: 网络罪犯破坏互联网的安全。

英文释义: a first-year student at a university or college; a first-year student at high school (1) or junior high school
例句: Freshmen always have lots of things to do in their first few days at college.
例句释义: 在入学的头几天，新生们通常有很多事要做。

英文释义: when you sweat, drops of liquid appear on the surface of your skin, for example when you are hot, ill/sick or afraid
例句: I sweat a lot on the way to work.
例句释义: 在去上班的路上，我出了很多汗。

英文释义: on the outside of something; furthest from the inside or centre of something
例句: The outer part of this ball is green.
例句释义: 这个球的外部是绿色的。

详细释义: adj.喝醉了的；陶醉的，兴奋的；  n.醉汉，酒鬼
英文释义: having drunk so much alcohol that it is impossible to think or speak clearly
例句: A drunk man passed out on the sofa.
例句释义: 一个喝醉的男人在沙发上昏睡过去。

英文释义: the act of separating people or things; the state of being separate
例句: Their separation made them both extremely sad.
例句释义: 与对方分离让他们伤心欲绝。

详细释义: v. 统治，管理；居支配地位
英文释义: to legally control a country or its people and be responsible for introducing new laws, organizing public services, etc.
例句: The boss governs his business empire.
例句释义: 老板统治着他的商业帝国。

详细释义: n.东南（方）；  adv.向东南；  adj.东南方的
英文释义: the direction or region at an equal distance between south and east
例句: There is a log cabin in the southeast of the forest.
例句释义: 树林的东南方有一个小木屋。

英文释义: good at learning, understanding and thinking in a logical way about things; showing this ability; (of an animal, a being, etc.) able to understand and learn things
例句: She can do very difficult math ― what an intelligent girl!
例句释义: 她能解出非常难的数学题，真是个聪明的女孩儿！

英文释义: in any place; in all places that; in all cases that
例句: Wherever you want your package to go, we can deliver it.
例句释义: 无论你想让你的包裹去哪儿，我们都能送达。

详细释义: n. 投票表决；选票；投票总数；  vi. 通过投票决定；  vt. 使投票表决
英文释义: the system of voting in writing and usually in secret; an occasion on which a vote is held
例句: He voted on the ballot.
例句释义: 他在表决中投了票。

英文释义: language that is used to persuade or influence people, especially language that sounds impressive but is not actually sincere or useful
例句: Rhetoric is the study of how to use words to convince people.
例句释义: 修辞学是研究如何用言语说服人的学说。

英文释义: a pill containing vitamins
例句: Vitamin pills make up what we lack in our diet.
例句释义: 维生素片可以弥补我们饮食中微量元素的不足。

英文释义: a strong feeling of excitement and interest in something and a desire to become involved in it
例句: Little kids always have so much enthusiasm about life!
例句释义: 小孩子总是对生活充满热情。

详细释义: v.容纳；为……提供住处（或膳宿）
英文释义: to provide enough space for somebody/something
例句: The hostel accommodates travellers from all over the world.
例句释义: 这家青年旅舍为来自全球各地的游客提供住宿。

详细释义: vt.表扬，称赞；赞扬，歌颂；  n.赞美的话
英文释义: to express your approval or admiration for somebody/something
例句: She was happy because her boss praised her.
例句释义: 她很开心，因为她的老板表扬了她。

英文释义: to harm yourself or somebody else physically, especially in an accident
例句: I injured my knee playing football. Ouch!!
例句释义: 踢足球的时候我把膝盖伤着了。哎哟！

英文释义: a large area of land that has never been developed or used for growing crops because it is difficult to live there; a place that people do not take care of or control
例句: The wilderness is an area unoccupied by humans, where nature has grown wild.
例句释义: 荒野是指无人居住的地方，大自然中的生物在那里无拘无束地生长。

英文释义: continuing for a long time and seeming to have no end
例句: The princess is tired of the endless social activities and banquets.
例句释义: 公主厌倦了无休止的社交活动和宴会。

详细释义: n. 受命进行的工作；  v. 授权
英文释义: the power to act that voters give to their elected leaders
例句: The policeman had a mandate to search his house.
例句释义: 这个警察受命搜查他的家。

英文释义: in the same order as the people or things already mentioned
例句: The twins, Kate and Kimberley, received gifts of a toy car and a doll respectively.
例句释义: 凯特和金伯莉这对双胞胎姐妹分别收到了玩具车和洋娃娃作为礼物。

英文释义: the state of being uncertain; something that you cannot be sure about; a situation that causes you to be or feel uncertain
例句: Investing in company stocks will always come with some kind of uncertainty.
例句释义: 投资公司股票总是伴随着某种不确定性。

英文释义: a state of complete confusion and lack of order
例句: This kitchen is in chaos!
例句释义: 厨房里一片狼藉！

详细释义: adj. 机械的，机械学的，机械性的
英文释义: operated by power from an engine; connected with machines and engines; (of people’s behaviour and actions) done without thinking, like a machine
例句: We can use this mechanical claw to pick up the doll.
例句释义: 我们可以用这个机械爪来抓娃娃。

英文释义: a piece of canvas used for painting on; a painting done on a piece of canvas, using oil paints; a strong heavy rough material used for making tents, sails, etc. and by artists for painting on
例句: The artist is painting on the canvas.
例句释义: 艺术家正在油画布上作画。

详细释义: n.门厅，大厅；游说团；  vt.向（议员、政府官员等）进行游说（或疏通）
例句: The lobby of this building was recently furnished, adding new sofas and tables.
例句释义: 这栋楼的大厅刚装修过，添了新沙发和桌子。

详细释义: adj. 深刻的；  n. 深海
英文释义: very great; felt or experienced very strongly
例句: The relationship between parents has a profound impact on a child's behavior.
例句释义: 父母的关系对于孩子的行为有着深刻的影响。

详细释义: n.版式；  v.设计一个版式，设计……的版面
英文释义: to arrange text in a particular way on a page or a screen
例句: The editor couldn't decide the best format for the magazine.
例句释义: 编辑决定不了这期杂志哪款版式最佳。

英文释义: a particular quality in your personality
例句: The most obvious trait of his appearance is his big nose.
例句释义: 他最明显的外貌特征就是他的大鼻子。

英文释义: the fact that something is used or accepted by a lot of people
例句: In different countries, we must use a different currency to buy things.
例句释义: 在不同的国家，我们得用不同的货币来买东西。

英文释义: large gallinaceous bird with fan-shaped tail; widely domesticated for food
例句: The man is holding a big roast turkey.
例句释义: 这个男人手里拿着一只大的烤火鸡。

英文释义: to ask for a seat, table, room, etc. to be available for you or somebody else at a future time
例句: He has an emergency reserve of food stored at home.
例句释义: 他在家里有一个存放食物的紧急储备库。

详细释义: n.光线；（房屋等的）大梁，(横)梁；  v.发光，照射
英文释义: a line of light, electric waves or particles
例句: A sun beam reaches down through the clouds.
例句释义: 一束阳光穿过云层照射下来。

英文释义: a scientist who studies astronomy
例句: The astronomer watches the stars.
例句释义: 天文学家在观测星星。

英文释义: dishonest or illegal behaviour, especially of people in authority; the act or effect of making somebody change from moral to immoral standards of behaviour
例句: He gives money to his partner for corruption, but rejected.
例句释义: 他用钱贿赂合作伙伴，但遭到了拒绝。

英文释义: a person who is hired to perform work or to provide goods at a certain price or within a certain time
例句: The contractor and his team have been hired to complete the project.
例句释义: 承包人和他的团队被雇来完成这个项目。

英文释义: to say that you are sorry for doing something wrong or causing a problem
例句: The cat apologized to its owner for breaking the vase.
例句释义: 这只猫为打碎花瓶而向主人道歉。

详细释义: n. 教条，学说，信条，原则
英文释义: a belief or set of beliefs held and taught by a Church, a political party, etc.; a statement of government policy
例句: The girl is transcribing the doctrine from that book.
例句释义: 这个女孩正在抄写那本书中的教义。

英文释义: real; exactly what it appears to be; not artificial
例句: Which one is?the?genuine painting?of the famous artist?
例句释义: 哪一幅才是这位著名画家的真迹？

详细释义: n.拇指；  vt.以拇指示意；  vi.<口语>做手势要求搭车
英文释义: the short thick finger at the side of the hand, slightly apart from the other four
例句: We gave our thumbs up to show our agreement.
例句释义: 我们竖起拇指以表赞同。

英文释义: the state of being in agreement and working together; the state of being joined together to form one unit
例句: Our group's strength lies in our unity.
例句释义: 我们队伍的力量来源于我们的团结！

详细释义: n.妥协，折中；  v.使遭受危险

例句: The seller made a compromise and sold the dress at 50 yuan.
例句释义: 商家做出了妥协，以50元的价格卖出了那条裙子。

英文释义: making you feel very shocked and frightened
例句: I did not expect to see such a horrible scene on the phone.
例句释义: 我没料到会在手机上看到这么恐怖的场景。

英文释义: connected with behaviour; connected with the scientific study of human and animal behaviour
例句: These two children have different behavioral responses to the same news.
例句释义: 这两个孩子对同一个消息有不同的行为反应。

详细释义: adj. 排外的；  n. 独家新闻
英文释义: (of a group, society, etc.) not very willing to allow new people to become members, especially if they are from a lower social class
例句: Sorry, this club is very exclusive: VIPs only.
例句释义: 对不起，这家俱乐部只接受VIP会员。

英文释义: to throw or drop things in different directions so that they cover an area of ground; to move or to make people or animals move very quickly in different directions
例句: The kid's room has toys scattered all over the ground.
例句释义: 儿童房里的玩具散落满地。

英文释义: to take, carry or transport somebody/something from one place to another
例句: The belt conveys the luggage out.
例句释义: 传送带将行李运出来。

英文释义: to bend or turn something into a particular shape; to bend or turn something into a shape or position that is not normal or natural; to be bent or turned in this way; to turn something around in a circle with your hand; to injure part of your body, especially your ankle, wrist or knee, bending it in an awkward way
例句: The right way to eat this biscuit: twist it, lick it, then dip it.
例句释义: 吃这种饼干的正确方式是扭一扭，舔一舔，再泡一泡。

英文释义: the state of being formed of many parts; the state of being difficult to understand; the features of a problem or situation that are difficult to understand
例句: He is facing a math problem with great complexity.
例句释义: 他正面临着一个复杂的数学问题。

英文释义: a small tool with two or more pointed parts (called prongs or tines) used for picking up and eating food
例句: The fork is usually placed on the left side of the plate.
例句释义: 餐叉通常被放在餐盘的左侧。

英文释义: a thin round piece of plastic on which music, etc. is recorded; a piece or collection of music released as a record, or on CD, the Internet, etc.
例句: Music was recorded on this compact disk(CD).
例句释义: 音乐被刻录在这张光盘上。

英文释义: to remove or reduce an unpleasant feeling or pain; to make a problem less serious
例句: A nice massage will relieve your back pain.
例句释义: 舒服的按摩可以缓解你背部的疼痛。

英文释义: a feeling that somebody has done something wrong, illegal or dishonest, even though you have no proof; the feeling that you cannot trust somebody/something
例句: The two men raised the suspicion of the policeman.

英文释义: to say in an advertisement that you use and like a particular product so that other people will want to buy it

英文释义: a hollow place or structure that a bird makes or chooses for laying its eggs in and sheltering its young
例句: Most birds lay their eggs in their nests.
例句释义: 大多数鸟儿把蛋生在它们的巢穴里。

英文释义: a narrow road in the country; (especially in place names) a street, often a narrow one with buildings on both sides; a section of a wide road, that is marked by painted white lines, to keep lines of traffic separate
例句: There is a narrow bicycle lane beside the lake.
例句释义: 湖边有一条窄窄的自行车道。

英文释义: a person in your family who lived a long time ago
例句: It's said that the ancestors of whales may have had four limbs.
例句释义: 据说鲸鱼的祖先可能有四肢。

英文释义: to express very strong disapproval of somebody/something, usually for moral reasons
例句: This dog is condemned for its bad behavior.
例句释义: 这只狗因其坏行为（随地便便）而受到谴责。

详细释义: n.蒸汽；  v.冒水汽，冒热气
英文释义: the hot gas that is created when water is boiled
例句: Steam is coming from the pot. Turn off the stove!
例句释义: 水蒸气正在往锅外冒，关火吧！

详细释义: n.口音，腔调；重音符号；  v.强调
英文释义: a way of pronouncing the words that shows which country, area or social class a person comes from
例句: He has such a funny accent!
例句释义: 他的口音太搞笑了!

英文释义: expecting good things to happen or something to be successful; showing this feeling
例句: She stays optimistic, despite her condition.
例句释义: 即使身体很差，她也始终保持乐观。

英文释义: to join together with other people in order to do something as a group
例句: Humans across the globe should unite in their efforts to fight the virus.
例句释义: 全人类应该团结起来共同抗击病毒。

英文释义: an enclosure resembling a cage in form or purpose
例句: The bird is in the cage.
例句释义: 笼子里有只鸟。

英文释义: to provide yourself/somebody/something with the things that are needed for a particular purpose or activity
例句: The worker equips himself with several items.
例句释义: 这名工人身上装备了好几样东西。

英文释义: the country where someone was born or grew up
例句: Earth is our shared homeland for all human beings.
例句释义: 地球是我们人类共同的家园。

详细释义: n. 挂架，搁架；  v. 使痛苦
英文释义: a piece of equipment, usually made of metal or wooden bars, that is used for holding things or for hanging things on
例句: We can use these racks to hang our clothes.
例句释义: 我们可以用这些架子来挂衣服。

英文释义: the clothes worn by actors in a play or film/movie, or worn by somebody to make them look like somebody/something else; the clothes worn by people from a particular place or during a particular historical period
例句: The three kids are each wearing different costumes.
例句释义: 这三个孩子分别穿着不同的戏服。

详细释义: n.狼；贪婪的人；  v.狼吞虎咽地吃
英文释义: a large wild animal that is similar to a dog and that often hunts in groups
例句: Even though a wolf looks a bit like a dog, it is actually much more dangerous.
例句释义: 尽管狼看起来有点儿像狗，但其实它们要危险得多。

英文释义: a room in which trials or other legal cases are held
例句: The courtroom has emptied after the trial finished.
例句释义: 审判结束后，法庭里空无一人。

英文释义: a written law that is formally created by a government
例句: The government will pass this statute.
例句释义: 政府将通过这条法令。

英文释义: a film/movie made by photographing a series of gradually changing drawings or models, so that they look as if they are moving
例句: Almost every kid loves to watch cartoons!
例句释义: 几乎所有小孩子都喜欢看卡通片！

英文释义: the rate at which a worker, a company or a country produces goods, and the amount produced, compared with how much time, work and money is needed to produce them
例句: A worker's productivity depends on how he balances time, costs and quality.
例句释义: 一个工人的生产力取决于他如何平衡时间、成本和产品质量。

详细释义: v. 露齿而笑，咧嘴一笑；  n. 龇牙笑
英文释义: to smile widely
例句: The horse grinned when I told the joke.
例句释义: 听了我的笑话，马儿咧嘴一笑。

英文释义: a fault in a machine, especially in a computer system or program
例句: The programmer is trying to fix the bug in the software.
例句释义: 程序员正在努力修复软件的故障。

详细释义: vt.保佑，祝福，赐福；  vi.有幸具有
英文释义: to ask God to protect somebody/something; to make something holy by saying a prayer over it; to call God holy; to praise God; used to express surprise
例句: I hope that I am blessed by the gods for this exam.
例句释义: 我希望我在这场考试中被考神保佑。

详细释义: n. 小姨，姑妈，伯母，舅妈
英文释义: the sister of your father or mother or the wife of your uncle
例句: The woman with yellow hair is the boy's aunt.
例句释义: 黄头发的女人是这个男孩的小姨。

英文释义: the science or occupation of farming
例句: We depend on agriculture to give us food.
例句释义: 我们依靠农业给我们提供食物。

详细释义: adj. 怀敌意的；敌对的，敌方的
英文释义: very unfriendly or aggressive and ready to argue or fight
例句: He is hostile to everyone.
例句释义: 他对每个人都充满敌意。

英文释义: when a woman conceives or conceives a child, she becomes pregnant
例句: The pregnancy test proved that she had conceived a baby.
例句释义: 验孕测试显示她怀了一个宝宝。

详细释义: adv. 立即地；  conj. 一…就…
英文释义: immediately
例句: The beauty of this camera is that the photo is ready instantly.
例句释义: 这台相机的优点是照片立即可得。

英文释义: the state of being bankrupt
例句: A number of different debts drove the company into bankruptcy.
例句释义: 许多不同的债务迫使这家公司破产了。

英文释义: a substance that is put into the blood and that protects the body from a disease
例句: The little girl takes a vaccine every fall to protect herself from the flu.
例句释义: 这个小女孩每年秋天都会接种疫苗来预防流感。

英文释义: an extra amount of money that is added to a payment, especially to somebody’s wages or salary as a reward; anything pleasant that is extra and more or better than you were expecting
例句: My boss gave me a bonus this month for doing extra work.
例句释义: 我的老板这个月给我发了奖金，因为我做了额外的工作。

英文释义: the act of working with another person or group of people to create or produce something; a piece of work produced by two or more people or groups of people working together
例句: They wrote a book in collaboration with each other.
例句释义: 他们合作写完了一本书。

详细释义: vt.沿轨道运行，环绕……运行；  n.轨道
英文释义: to move in an orbit (= a curved path) around a much larger object, especially a planet, star, etc.
例句: All of our planets orbit the sun.
例句释义: （在太阳系里）所有行星都环绕太阳运行。

详细释义: vt.抓住；领会，理解；  n.紧握
英文释义: to take a firm hold of somebody/something
例句: The baby grasped his mother's finger.
例句释义: 婴儿抓住了母亲的手指。

英文释义: the ability to stay calm and accept a delay or something annoying without complaining
例句: Fishing is a sport that requires a lot of patience.
例句释义: 钓鱼是一项很需要耐心的运动。

详细释义: v. 刁难，欺侮；  n. 恶意，怨恨
英文释义: to deliberately annoy or upset somebody
例句: He's flirting with my best friend - I'm sure it's just to spite me.
例句释义: 他在勾搭我最好的朋友，我敢肯定这是在欺辱我。

英文释义: coming from, found in or typical of the tropics
例句: Schools of tropical fish are swimming around in the sea.
例句释义: 成群的热带鱼在海里四处游动。

详细释义: n. 巡逻兵；  v. 巡逻
英文释义: to go around an area or a building at regular times to check that it is safe and that there is no trouble
例句: The patrols are searching the ruins after the war.
例句释义: 战后，巡逻兵正在搜寻废墟。

英文释义: the quality of being happy and ready to do something
例句: The student raised his hand to show his willingness to clean the blackboard.
例句释义: 这位学生举手表示自愿去擦黑板。

详细释义: n.揭露；（出乎意料的）被揭示的真相
英文释义: the act of making people aware of something that has been secret
例句: The revelation that he stole from his company was exposed.
例句释义: 他盗窃公司财物的事情被揭露了。

详细释义: adj.冷静的，平静的；  n.平静，安宁；  v.（使）平静，（使）镇定
英文释义: not excited, nervous or upset; (of the sea) without large waves
例句: She is so calm although the endless work bothers her.
例句释义: 尽管工作不胜其烦，但她依然十分冷静。

英文释义: objects such as rings and necklaces that people wear as decoration
例句: My husband gave me a box of jewelry as a wedding gift.
例句释义: 我的丈夫送给我一盒子珠宝当作结婚礼物。

详细释义: v. 拖，拉，拽；  n. 一次获得；  v. 硬拖，硬拉，用力拖
英文释义: to pull something/somebody with a lot of effort
例句: It is pointless for him to attempt to haul the truck barehanded.
例句释义: 对他而言，赤手空拳地拉卡车是徒劳的。

英文释义: to admit that something is true, logical, etc.
例句: In the fight with this crazy kangaroo, I had no choice but to concede.
例句释义: 在与这只疯狂的袋鼠的战斗中，我除了认输，别无选择。

英文释义: a vehicle with four wheels that is used for carrying heavy loads or passengers and that is usually pulled by animals (such as horses)
例句: The horses are pulling the wagon along the forest path.
例句释义: 马儿们正拉着马车经过林间小路。

英文释义: at a later time; after an event that has already been mentioned
例句: Be sure to clean up the dog waste afterward!
例句释义: 之后要记得清理狗狗的排泄物！

详细释义: adj. 壮观的，引人入胜的；  n. 壮观的场面，精彩的表演
英文释义: very impressive
例句: Waterfalls are among the most spectacular sights that nature has given to us.
例句释义: 瀑布是大自然赐予我们的最壮观的景观之一。

详细释义: v.毁灭，毁坏；（使）破产；  n.废墟
英文释义: to damage (something) so badly that it is no longer useful, valuable, enjoyable, etc.; to spoil or destroy (something)
例句: These buildings were ruined by a powerful earthquake.
例句释义: 一场大地震摧毁了这些建筑。

详细释义: adj.陡峭的；  vi.（off）紧急转向，偏离；  n.透明薄纱
英文释义: very steep
例句: The rocky cliff over the ocean is so sheer!
例句释义: 海上的石崖很陡峭！

详细释义: adj. 免疫的，有免疫力的；免除的
英文释义: that cannot catch or be affected by a particular disease or illness
例句: People who exercise often are proven to have stronger immune systems.
例句释义: 经常锻炼的人被证实会有更强的免疫系统。

英文释义: the quality of being able to be trusted to do what somebody wants or needs
例句: The reliability of the safe is very high.
例句释义: 这个保险箱的可靠性很高。

详细释义: prep.在旁边，和……并排；  adv.在旁边，并排地，并肩地
英文释义: next to or at the side of something
例句: My dogs ran alongside me the entire way.
例句释义: 狗狗一路上都跟着我一起跑步。

英文释义: an area of wild land that has not been cleared, especially in Africa and Australia
例句: There is a row of bushes in front of the house.
例句释义: 房子前面有一排灌木。

详细释义: adj. 奇异的，珍奇的，来自异国的
英文释义: from or in another country, especially a tropical one; seeming exciting and unusual because it is connected with foreign countries
例句: I have never seen those exotic flowers before.
例句释义: 我过去从未见过这些奇异的花朵。

详细释义: adj. 迷人的，有极大吸引力的
英文释义: extremely interesting and attractive
例句: There are a lot of fascinating things to be found on the internet.
例句释义: 互联网上有很多吸引人的东西。

详细释义: n. 回形针，夹子；  v. 夹住
英文释义: (often in compounds) a small metal or plastic object used for holding things together or in place
例句: Use this paper clip to hold the sheets together.
例句释义: 用回形针把这些纸夹在一起。

英文释义: the top part of the leg between the knee and the hip
例句: The man has a cramp in his thigh.
例句释义: 那人的大腿抽筋了。

详细释义: n. 公牛，雄性的鲸、象等大动物
英文释义: the male of any animal in the cow family; the male of the elephant, whale and some other large animals;  a person who buys shares in a company, hoping to sell them soon afterwards at a higher price; an official order or statement from the Pope (= the head of the Roman Catholic Church)
例句: The black bull is angry and ready to attack.
例句释义: 这头愤怒的黑色公牛准备进攻了。

英文释义: a box that slides into and out of a piece of furniture (such as a desk) and that is used to store things
例句: Remember to keep all your files in the drawer.
例句释义: 记得把你的所有文件都放在抽屉里。

详细释义: n.绵羊（单复数同形）；胆小鬼
英文释义: an animal with a thick coat, kept on farms for its meat (called mutton or lamb ) or its wool
例句: Sheep are raised to produce wool.
例句释义: 人们养羊是为了产羊毛。

英文释义: to try to prevent something or to prevent somebody from doing something, especially by making it difficult to do or by showing that you do not approve of it
例句: The bad weather discouraged her from having a picnic.
例句释义: 这糟糕的天气使她不能外出野餐。

英文释义: concerned with or suggestive of ideas
例句: Different ideological beliefs during the Spring and Autumn Period arose from Confucianism, Taoism, and Mohism.
例句释义: 春秋时期涌现了许多思想意识形态，大多起源于儒家、道家和墨家。

英文释义: a person who runs as part of a sport, for exercise, or in a race
例句: These runners are running on the road.
例句释义: 这些跑步者们正在路上跑步。

例句: The monk left the temple and resumed secular life.
例句释义: 和尚离开了寺庙，重新过上了世俗的生活。

详细释义: adj.亲密的，密切的；详细的；  vt.宣布，通知；  n.密友，知己
英文释义: (of people) having a close and friendly relationship; private and personal, often in a sexual way
例句: Nothing is sweeter than being with intimate lovers.
例句释义: 没什么比和亲密的恋人在一起更幸福了。

英文释义: a group of countries or states that are controlled by one ruler or government; a group of commercial organizations controlled by one person or company
例句: This was built during the Roman empire.
例句释义: 这是在罗马帝国时期修建的。

英文释义: a taxi; the part of a truck, tractor, etc., in which the driver sits
例句: He uses his mobile phone to call a cab.
例句释义: 他用手机预订了一台出租车。

英文释义: a formal written, spoken or practical test, especially at school or college, to see how much you know about a subject, or what you can do
例句: The students are taking an exam.
例句释义: 学生们正在考试。

详细释义: n.纪录片；  adj.纪实的；文献的
英文释义: a film or a radio or television programme giving facts about something
例句: This documentary shows us the life of a panda.
例句释义: 这部纪录片向我们展现了熊猫的生活状态。

详细释义: adj. 中立的；  n. 中立国
英文释义: not supporting or helping either side in a disagreement, competition, etc.
例句: He remained neutral in the disagreement, not taking either side.
例句释义: 他在这场争吵中保持中立，不偏袒任何一方。

英文释义: the scientific study of the life and structure of plants and animals
例句: Biology?is the study of life and living things.
例句释义: 生物学是研究生命和生物的学科。

英文释义: able to change to suit new conditions or situations; able to bend easily without breaking
例句: The pencil is flexible enough to be knotted.
例句释义: 这支铅笔非常柔软，甚至可以打结。

详细释义: adj. 逐步的，渐进的；  n. 进步人士
英文释义: happening or developing steadily
例句: He has made progressive progress in his grade.
例句释义: 他在学习成绩上步步高升。

英文释义: a fine net of threads made by a spider to catch insects
例句: The spider makes a beautiful web.
例句释义: 蜘蛛织了张漂亮的网。

英文释义: a secret plan by a group of people to do something harmful or illegal
例句: Their conspiracy is to assassinate the king.
例句释义: 他们密谋刺杀国王。

详细释义: n. 伤亡人员，死伤者，受害人
英文释义: a person who is killed or injured in war or in an accident
例句: We suffered one casualty at work today.
例句释义: 在今天的工作中，有一人不幸遇难。

英文释义: a country that is governed by a president and politicians elected by the people and where there is no king or queen
例句: The United States is a republic.
例句释义: 美国是一个共和国。

英文释义: the act of killing somebody, especially as a legal punishment
例句: The wolf faces the execution of beheading for committing murder.
例句释义: 这匹狼因犯谋杀罪而面临死刑。

详细释义: adj.极好的；可怕的；（尺寸或程度）极其巨大的，大得惊人的
英文释义: excellent; wonderful
例句: I feel terrific today! What a nice day!
例句释义: 我今天感觉棒极了！天气真好！

英文释义: a very large animal that lives in the sea and looks like a very large fish. There are several types of whale, some of which are hunted.
例句: Did you see the whale jump out of the sea?
例句释义: 你看见鲸跃出水面了吗？

例句: The storage boxes are very functional and can hold all kinds of things.
例句释义: 这些收纳箱功能性很强，可以装各种东西。

详细释义: n.本能，天性；天分，天资；直觉
英文释义: a feeling that makes you do sth or believe that sth is true, even though it is not based on facts or reason
例句: Squirrels have the natural instinct to store nuts for winter.
例句释义: 松鼠有贮藏坚果过冬的天性。

例句: The teammates are in joyous celebration after scoring a goal.
例句释义: 进球后，队友们都在开心地庆祝。

英文释义: a chemical element. Aluminium is a light, silver-grey metal used for making pans, etc.
例句: Aluminum drink cans are light and convenient.
例句释义: 铝制饮料罐又轻又方便。

英文释义: a government department or the building in which it is located
例句: Governments have many different ministries, such as the Ministry of Health.
例句释义: 政府设有许多不同的部门，比如卫生部。

英文释义: a decision that is made by a jury in court, stating if somebody is considered guilty of a crime or not
例句: The?judge?is?making?his?final?verdict.
例句释义: 法官在进行最后的裁决。

英文释义: to teach somebody something, especially a practical skill
例句: My mom instructs me how to play golf.
例句释义: 我妈妈教我怎么打高尔夫球。

英文释义: the bone structure that forms the head and surrounds and protects the brain
例句: The human skull protects the organs in our head.
例句释义: 人类的头骨保护着头部内的器官。

英文释义: involving two or more people or groups working together to do something
例句: The cooperative witness provided the police officers valuable information about the suspect.
例句释义: 这名目击者非常配合，向警察提供了有价值的嫌疑人信息。

英文释义: to control or influence somebody/something, often in a dishonest way so that they do not realize it
例句: The man on the stage expertly manipulates the puppets using strings.
例句释义: 舞台上的这个男人熟练地用线操纵木偶。

英文释义: a black and yellow flying insect that can sting and that is often kept in hives for the honey that it produces
例句: There's a bee on the yellow flower.
例句释义: 这朵黄花上有一只蜜蜂。

详细释义: n.（医生或律师等）从业者，从事者
英文释义: a person who works in a profession, especially medicine or law
例句: The medical practitioners are preparing for whatever challenge they are faced with.
例句释义: 医疗工作者们做好了应对一切挑战的准备。
