详细释义: n.（用线、绳、带等打成的）环；  v.使成环，绕成圈；  vt.打成环状
英文释义: a round shape made by something like string or rope
例句: We made a loop out of rope for future use.
例句释义: 我们用绳子做了个环以供日后使用。

例句: I edit the story using a pencil.
例句释义: 我用铅笔编辑故事。

详细释义: v.鞭打，抽打；猛地移动，急走，急冲；  n.组织秘书
英文释义: to hit a person or an animal hard with a whip, as a punishment or to make them go faster or work harder
例句: The guy whips his horses to make them run faster.
例句释义: 那人鞭打他的马儿让它们跑得更快。

详细释义: n.拼图；难题；  v.使迷惑，迷惑
英文释义: a game, etc. that you have to think about carefully in order to answer it or do it
例句: He puts in the last piece of puzzle to complete the picture.
例句释义: 他把拼图的最后一块放进去，这幅图就完整了。

英文释义: a fungus with a round flat head and short stem
例句: "Give me back my hat," said the mushroom sadly.
例句释义: "把帽子还给我! " 蘑菇难过地说道。

英文释义: money that is paid by a government or an organization to reduce the costs of services or of producing goods so that their prices can be kept low
例句: The government provided a subsidy for the startups.
例句释义: 政府为创业者提供了补贴。

英文释义: when a liquid boils or when you boil it, it is heated to the point where it forms bubbles and turns to steam or vapour
例句: The water in the small pot is boiling.
例句释义: 小锅里的水正在沸腾。

英文释义: making you feel very sad, usually because somebody has died or suffered a lot
例句: There was a news report about the tragic accident on the highway.
例句释义: 新闻报道了这起发生在高速公路上的悲惨的交通事故。

英文释义: the science of numbers, quantities, and shapes and the relations between them
例句: My favorite subject in school was mathematics.
例句释义: 在学校，我最喜欢的课是数学。

英文释义: a person whose job is repairing machines, especially the engines of vehicles
例句: The mechanic is repairing something at the bottom of the car.
例句释义: 这个机修工在修理车底的某个部位。

详细释义: n.罐子，瓶子，坛子；  v.震动
英文释义: a round glass container, with a lid, used for storing food, especially jam, honey, etc.; a jar and what it contains; a tall container with a wide mouth, with or without handles, used in the past for carrying water, etc.; an unpleasant shock, especially from two things being suddenly shaken or hit
例句: The five jars contain two kinds of jam.
例句释义: 这5个罐子中装着两种果酱。

英文释义: a sudden, violent shaking of the earth’s surface
例句: The rescue team went to rescue the victims of the earthquake.
例句释义: 营救小组去营救地震的受害者。

英文释义: meat from a pig that has not been cured (= preserved using salt or smoke)
例句: I bought some pork from the supermarket.
例句释义: 我从超市买了些猪肉。

英文释义: the ability to create
例句: His creativity made him famous on the internet.
例句释义: 他的创造力让他火遍全网。

英文释义: with safety; in a safe manner
例句: The horse crossed the river safely.
例句释义: 小马安全地穿过了这条河。

英文释义: existing under the surface of something else
例句: The underlying part of the iceberg is much bigger than the visible part.
例句释义: 冰山在海面下的部分比海面上可见的部分大得多。

英文释义: sweet food eaten at the end of a meal
例句: I’d like to have some dessert with a cup of tea after dinner.
例句释义: 吃完晚饭后，我还想吃些甜点、喝杯茶。

英文释义: the feeling that you care about and are sorry about someone else's trouble, grief, misfortune, etc.
例句: He felt a lot of sympathy for the dog and gave it a bone.
例句释义: 他很同情那条小狗并给了它一根骨头。

英文释义: a person (especially a man) who catches fish
例句: The fisherman hoped that his net would be full of fish.
例句释义: 渔夫希望他的渔网满是鱼。

例句: That's an incredibly strange design!
例句释义: 那是一个令人难以置信的奇怪设计！

详细释义: n. 孤独，孤立状态；【化学】离析
英文释义: the state of being alone or lonely
例句: He experienced a feeling of isolation due to his skin disease.
例句释义: 由于皮肤病，他倍感孤独无助。

详细释义: n. 短袜，重击；  v. 重击
英文释义: a piece of clothing that is worn on your foot and that covers your ankle and sometimes the lower part of your leg
例句: She is wearing two different color socks on her feet.
例句释义: 她脚上穿着两只不同颜色的袜子。

英文释义: a person who makes money by starting or running businesses, especially when this involves taking financial risks
例句: Entrepreneurs start new businesses.
例句释义: 企业家开始新的生意。

英文释义: a set of physical conditions that show you have a particular disease or medical problem
例句: Many people suffer from post-holiday syndrome after a long vacation.
例句释义: 很多人在长假后患上了“节后综合征”。

英文释义: an office or organization that provides information on a particular subject; (in the US) a government department or part of a government department
例句: The Federal Bureau of Investigation is a government agency in the United States investigating crimes.
例句释义: 联邦调查局是美国调查犯罪的政府机构。

英文释义: the office, factory, etc. where people work
例句: I spend five days a week at my workplace.
例句释义: 一周我花五天在工作场所。

英文释义: the desire or determination to be successful, rich, powerful, etc.; something that you want to do or achieve very much
例句: This powerful man's political ambition was to unify the three kingdoms.
例句释义: 这个有权势的男人的政治野心是一统三国。

英文释义: to use something, especially for a practical purpose
例句: It's better to utilize waste than to throw it away.
例句释义: 废物再利用总比把它扔掉要好。

英文释义: a light wind
例句: She smiled when a gentle breeze blew her hair.
例句释义: 当一阵温和的微风拂过她的头发的时候，她笑了。

英文释义: costing a lot of money, especially more than you want to pay
例句: Actually, holding a wedding ceremony is much more costly than I thought.
例句释义: 实际上，举行婚礼比我想象中要贵得多。

英文释义: having a great desire (for something or to do something)
例句: The boy is ambitious and wants to be a successful businessman one day.
例句释义: 男孩很有抱负，未来想成为一个成功的商人。

英文释义: used to say that you think that sth is probably true
例句: "The murderer is presumably a man who wears glasses and smokes."
例句释义: “凶手大概是个戴眼镜且会抽烟的男人。”

英文释义: having a lot of influence on somebody/something
例句: He is such an influential star that many people copy his look.
例句释义: 他是一位很有影响力的明星，许多人都在模仿他的穿着。

英文释义: the process of changing something that is written or spoken into another language
例句: The little boy is trying to do some translation exercises.
例句释义: 这个小男孩正尝试着做一些翻译练习。

详细释义: adj.不确定的；多变的，难预料的
英文释义: feeling doubt about something; not sure
例句: He was uncertain of the correct answer to the multiple choice question.
例句释义: 他不确定这道选择题的正确答案是哪个。

英文释义: (of a solid) to mix with a liquid and become part of it; to make a solid become part of a liquid
例句: This tablet dissolves in water.
例句释义: 这片药在水中会溶解。

英文释义: connected with or based on statistics
例句: The statistical data shows that most people cannot afford a house.
例句释义: 这项统计数据表明大多数人买不起房子。

详细释义: n.（幽门到直肠间的）肠子；  adj.直觉的，本能的；  vt.取出内脏
英文释义: the tube in the body through which food passes when it leaves the stomach; the organs in and around the stomach, especially in an animal
例句: Gut is the tube in the body where food passes when it leaves the stomach.
例句释义: 肠子就是食物在人体内离开胃时通过的管道。

详细释义: adj. 大城市的，大都会的
英文释义: connected with a large or capital city
例句: There are a lot of tall buildings in metropolitan New York.
例句释义: 纽约这种大都会有很多高楼。

详细释义: adj.美学的；审美的；美的；艺术的
英文释义: concerned with beauty and art and the understanding of beautiful things
例句: The oil painting has great aesthetic value.
例句释义: 这幅油画具有非常高的美学价值。

英文释义: to say or write the letters of a word in the correct order; to form words correctly from individual letters; to form words when they are put together in a particular order
例句: The teacher is teaching the students how to spell.
例句释义: 老师正在教学生如何拼写。

英文释义: to put something into something else or between two things
例句: I am inserting my USB flash drive into the laptop.
例句释义: 我正在将我的闪存盘插入笔记本电脑中。

英文释义: a small confined place where you can do something privately, for example make a telephone call, or vote
例句: I haven’t seen a telephone booth for years.
例句释义: 我好多年都没见过电话亭了。

详细释义: n.头盔；盔形物；  vt.给……戴头盔
英文释义: a type of hard hat that protects the head, worn, for example, by a police officer, a soldier or a person playing some sports
例句: He is wearing an orange helmet.
例句释义: 他正戴着一顶橘色头盔。

英文释义: the area around the middle of the body between the ribs and the hips, often narrower than the areas above and below
例句: The man put the measuring tape around his waist.
例句释义: 这个人在腰上围了一条软尺。

英文释义: a large powerful animal of the cat family, that hunts in groups and lives in parts of Africa and southern Asia. Lions have yellowish-brown fur and the male has a mane
例句: The lion is standing proudly, facing the sun.
例句释义: 这头狮子面向太阳骄傲地站着。

英文释义: something done, achieved, or accomplished successfully
例句: His winning the Nobel Prize for Literature was a great accomplishment.
例句释义: 他获得诺贝尔文学奖是一项极大的成就。

详细释义: adj.王室的，皇家的；盛大的，高贵的
英文释义: connected with or belonging to the king or queen of a country
例句: The king wears his royal clothes.
例句释义: 国王穿着他的御用衣服。

英文释义: a sudden feeling of great fear that cannot be controlled and prevents you from thinking clearly
例句: After she fell, she reached for her shoes in a panic.
例句释义: 跌倒之后她慌张地捡起了鞋子。

详细释义: v.压扁，压坏；镇压；  n.拥挤的人群
英文释义: to press or squeeze something so hard that it is damaged or injured, or loses its shape; to push or press somebody/something into a small space
例句: The can was crushed and put into the recycling bin.
例句释义: 易拉罐被压扁并扔进了可回收垃圾桶中。

英文释义: a high area of rock with a very steep side, often at the edge of the sea or ocean
例句: The steep white cliffs surrounded the bay.
例句释义: 陡峭的白色悬崖包围着海湾。

英文释义: very small in size or amount; as small as possible
例句: The advertisement emphasizes that the risk involved in the surgery is minimal.
例句释义: 广告强调这个手术的风险微乎其微。

英文释义: strong thick string or thin rope; a piece of this
例句: I can't believe that I was tripped by this cord!
例句释义: 我不敢相信我居然被这根细绳绊倒了！

英文释义: by good luck
例句: Fortunately, he actually won the lottery! One million dollars!
例句释义: 太幸运了，他中了彩票，那可是100万啊！

英文释义: a powerful drug that some people take illegally for pleasure and can become addicted to. Doctors sometimes use it as an anaesthetic.
例句: Doing cocaine will ruin your life.
例句释义: 吸食可卡因会毁了你的人生。

详细释义: n. 假象，幻象；幻想；错误观念
英文释义: something that looks or seems different from what it is :something that is false or not real but that seems to be true or real
例句: The feeling that the picture is moving is just an illusion.
例句释义: 感觉图片在动只是一种错觉。

详细释义: adj.匿名的；无名的；不具名的；无特色的；无个性特征的
英文释义: written, given, made, etc. by somebody who does not want their name to be known or made public
例句: I received an anonymous letter. I did not know who wrote it.
例句释义: 我收到了一封匿名信，我不知道是谁写的。

英文释义: to accept somebody/something that is annoying, unpleasant, etc. without complaining
例句: They have to tolerate the smell in the elevator.
例句释义: 他们不得不忍受电梯里的臭味。

英文释义: pleasure that you have when you recognize and enjoy the good qualities of somebody/something; a piece of writing or a speech in which the strengths and weaknesses of somebody/something, especially an artist or a work of art, are discussed and judged
例句: Appreciation of paintings always pleases her.
例句释义: 欣赏画作总是使她感到愉快。

详细释义: n. 委员，专员，理事；行政长官
英文释义: a member of a commission :one of a group of people who have been given the official job of finding information about something or controlling something
例句: The horse is speaking as the commissioner of the vegetarian committee.
例句释义: 这匹马作为素食动物特别委员会的委员之一，正在发言。

英文释义: the ability to bend easily without breaking; (approving) the ability to change to suit new conditions or situations
例句: She practices yoga to improve her flexibility.
例句释义: 她通过练习瑜伽来提高身体灵活性。

英文释义: to move quickly, especially with difficulty, using your hands to help you; to push, fight or compete with others in order to get or to reach something
例句: He quickly scrambled up the tree to escape from the bull.
例句释义: 他迅速爬上树，躲避那头牛。

英文释义: a building or room that has games (such as roulette or blackjack) for gambling
例句: There are many gambling games in casino.
例句释义: 在赌场中，有很多种赌博游戏。

英文释义: to make something more attractive by putting things on it
例句: We decorate the tree to celebrate Christmas.
例句释义: 我们装饰了这棵树来庆祝圣诞节。

详细释义: n.脉搏；（电子）脉冲；  vi.（使）跳动，搏动，震动；（感情等）洋溢，充满
英文释义: the regular beat of blood as it is sent around the body, that can be felt in different places, especially on the inside part of the wrist; the number of times the blood beats in a minute
例句: The doctor takes the patient's pulse to determine her illness.
例句释义: 医生通过把脉来判断病人的病情。

详细释义: adj. 相等的；等值的；  n. 同义词；等价物
英文释义: equal in value, amount, meaning, importance, etc.
例句: The price of the luxury car is equivalent to ten times his annual salary.
例句释义: 这辆豪车的价格等于他十倍的年薪。

英文释义: placed or attached in a way that does not move easily
例句: The restaurant offers an all-you-can-eat buffet at a fixed price!
例句释义: 这家餐厅供应价格固定的不限量自助餐！

英文释义: having knowledge or skill in a particular job or activity
例句: He is an experienced, older driver with 30 years of driving experience.
例句释义: 他是一位经验丰富的老司机，有30年驾龄。

英文释义: something that is given to a person or an organization such as a charity, in order to help them; the act of giving something in this way
例句: I gave a 10 euro donation to the homeless man.
例句释义: 我为那个无家可归的人捐了10欧元。

英文释义: a book in which you can write down the experiences you have each day, your private thoughts, etc.
例句: The girl keeps a diary every day.
例句释义: 女孩儿每天都写日记。

详细释义: n. 具有讽刺意味的事；反语；冷嘲
英文释义: the amusing or strange aspect of a situation that is very different from what you expect; a situation like this
例句: I slipped right next to the "do not slip" sign, and we all laughed at the irony.
例句释义: 我恰好在“小心滑倒”的牌子旁摔了一跤，这一讽刺场景让我们都笑了。

详细释义: n. 匙，调羹；  vt. 用匙舀
英文释义: a tool that has a handle with a shallow bowl at the end, used for stirring, serving and eating food
例句: There is a wooden spoon in the bowl.
例句释义: 碗里有一只木勺子。

英文释义: (used after a preposition) the middle part of something
例句: I saw her in their midst, standing and laughing.
例句释义: 我看见她站在他们中间，笑容灿烂。

英文释义: a narrow street or passage between buildings
例句: The narrow alley winds through the old town.
例句释义: 这条窄巷弯弯曲曲地穿过古老的小镇。

详细释义: v.交流，互动；互相作用，互相影响
英文释义: to talk or do things with other people
例句: During the performance, the beautiful dancer interacted with the audience hand in hand.
例句释义: 表演过程中，这位美丽的舞者与观众牵手互动。

英文释义: a substance that you use with water for washing your body
例句: There is a piece of soap in her hand.
例句释义: 她手里拿着一块肥皂。

英文释义: pretty and attractive
例句: Awww, that kitten is so cute!
例句释义: 啊，这小猫真可爱！

详细释义: n.竞争对手；  v.与………竞争，与………匹敌
英文释义: a person, company or thing that competes with another in sport, business, etc.
例句: The two rivals compete to see who's better.
例句释义: 这两个对手相互竞争，想一决高下。

英文释义: to hit somebody/something hard with your fist (= closed hand)
例句: The boxer punched the sandbag really hard.
例句释义: 拳击手用拳头狠狠地打在了沙袋上。

详细释义: v. 别住，钉住，固定住；  n. 别针，饰针
英文释义: to hold fast or prevent from moving
例句: The note paper was pinned to the wall.
例句释义: 墙上钉了张便笺纸。

英文释义: a game resembling ice hockey that is played on an open field; two opposing teams use curved sticks try to drive a ball into the opponents' net
例句: Ice hockey's played on ice, field hockey on field; both have sticks.
例句释义: 冰上曲棍球在冰上进行，陆上曲棍球在陆地上进行，两种运动都使用曲棍球棒。

英文释义: to continue to do something despite difficulties or opposition, in a way that can seem unreasonable
例句: Although the water is cold, we persist in going forward.
例句释义: 尽管水很凉，我们还是坚持前进。

英文释义: a person or company that supplies goods
例句: This farm is a supplier providing food to the restaurant.
例句释义: 这座农场是那家餐厅的食品供应商。

英文释义: apprehended with certainty
例句: Australia is known for its kangaroos and koalas.
例句释义: 澳大利亚以袋鼠和考拉闻名。

英文释义: a force that is gained by movement
例句: His momentum caused him to go up into the air.
例句释义: 动量让他高高跃起。

详细释义: n. 钱包（尤指女用的），小钱袋，手袋
英文释义: a small bag made of leather, plastic, etc. for carrying coins and often also paper money, cards, etc., used especially by women; the amount of money that is available to a person, an organization or a government to spend
例句: This purse holds some coins.
例句释义: 这个钱包装了一些硬币。

详细释义: v.摆脱；流出（眼泪）；蜕皮；使清晰；流下；  n.棚屋
英文释义: to cry
例句: The city is trying to shed its bad image from the past.
例句释义: 该城市试图摆脱其过去糟糕的形象。

详细释义: n. 液体；  adj. 液体的
英文释义: a substance that flows freely and is not a solid or a gas, for example water or oil
例句: Liquid, like water, can flow freely.
例句释义: 液体，比如说水，可以自由地流动。

英文释义: a small symbol on a computer or smartphone screen that represents a program or a file; a famous person or thing that people admire and see as a symbol of a particular idea, way of life, etc.; (in the Orthodox Church) a painting or statue of a holy person that is also thought of as a holy object
例句: The icons have been interestingly arranged onto the desktop.
例句释义: 电脑屏幕上的图标以一种有趣的方式排列着。

英文释义: a very large animal with thick grey skin, large ears, two curved outer teeth called tusks and a long nose called a trunk. There are two types of elephant, the African and the Asian.
例句: The elephant is drinking water.
例句释义: 这头大象正在喝水。

英文释义: as a result; therefore
例句: His wife found the money he hid and he was consequently punished.
例句释义: 老婆发现了他藏的私房钱，他因此收到了惩罚。

详细释义: n.特许（经营权）；公民权；选举权；  v.赋予特权；赋予公民权
英文释义: formal permission given by a company to somebody who wants to sell its goods or services in a particular area; formal permission given by a government to somebody who wants to operate a public service as a business
例句: I gained the franchise of the restaurant, so I can sell food!
例句释义: 我获得了这家餐厅的特许经营权，我可以出售食品啦！

英文释义: in a way that is accurate or true, without any mistakes; in a way that is right and suitable, so that something is done as it should be done; in a way that follows the accepted standards or rules
例句: He answered the teacher's question correctly.
例句释义: 他正确地回答了老师的问题。

详细释义: adv. 精神上，智力上，心理上
英文释义: connected with or happening in the mind
例句: She looks as if she is mentally tired.
例句释义: 她看起来精神疲惫。

英文释义: to take another person’s child into your home for a period of time, without becoming his or her legal parents
例句: This foster child will now be a part of their family.
例句释义: 这个收养的孩子现在将成为他们家庭中的一部分。

英文释义: a road vehicle with two wheels that you ride by pushing the pedals with your feet
例句: We are riding bicycles for a trip.
例句释义: 我们正在骑自行车旅行。

英文释义: causing a hopeful feeling
例句: It was encouraging to hear his boss say, "Well done!"
例句释义: 听到老板说“做得好”让他非常受鼓舞。

详细释义: v.作弊；欺骗，哄骗；  n.骗子
英文释义: to act in a dishonest way in order to gain an advantage, especially in a game, a competition, an exam, etc.
例句: I always cheat when I play cards.
例句释义: 我在打牌时总是作弊。

英文释义: to become healthy again; to make something healthy again
例句: The doctor's treatment healed my hand back to full health!
例句释义: 医生的治疗让我的手痊愈了！

英文释义: a medical condition in which a person has a temperature that is higher than normal
例句: The girl is sick and has a high fever.
例句释义: 这个女孩生病了并且发高烧。

英文释义: a device containing paper, sand, chemicals, etc. that a liquid or gas is passed through in order to remove any materials that are not wanted; a device that allows only particular types of light or sound to pass through it
例句: The water filter is used to purify the water.
例句释义: 净水器用以净化水。

英文释义: a small animal with soft fur, long ears and a short tail. Rabbits live in holes in the ground or are kept as pets or for food.
例句: Would you like a pet rabbit?
例句释义: 你想要一只宠物兔吗？

详细释义: n. 硬币；  v. 铸造（硬币）
英文释义: a small, flat, and usually round piece of metal issued by a government as money
例句: This coin is worth ten cents.
例句释义: 这枚硬币值10美分。

详细释义: vt.剥削，利用；开发，开拓；  n.辉煌功绩
英文释义: (disapproving) to treat somebody unfairly by making them work and not giving them much in return; to treat a person or situation as an opportunity to gain an advantage for yourself
例句: The greedy employer exploits his workers for his own profits.
例句释义: 这个贪婪的老板为了自己的利益剥削工人。

详细释义: adj. 可进入的；可使用的
英文释义: that can be reached, entered, used, etc. by somebody who has problems walking
例句: The secret garden is only accessible with the secret key.
例句释义: 这个秘密花园要用秘密钥匙才能进入。

英文释义: a living thing, especially one that is extremely small
例句: Many living organisms can only be seen using a microscope.
例句释义: 许多有机体只有用显微镜才能看到。

英文释义: a feeling that you get when something affects your body; a general feeling or impression that is difficult to explain; an experience or a memory
例句: The hot sun is causing a burning sensation on her shoulders.
例句释义: 炙热的太阳让她的肩膀产生了灼热感。

英文释义: partly; not completely
例句: The sun is only partially visible during a solar eclipse.
例句释义: 日食发生时，只有一部分太阳可见。

详细释义: adv.往楼上，在楼上；往高处；  adj.楼上的
英文释义: the floor or floors in a building that are above the ground floor
例句: The dog ran upstairs to eat his food.
例句释义: 狗狗上楼去吃食物。

英文释义: the protection of the natural environment
例句: Conservation of our environment is very important.
例句释义: 保护环境很重要。

详细释义: v. 推；猛推；  n. 推搡
英文释义: to push somebody/something in a rough way
例句: I don't think you'll move that brick wall no matter how hard you shove it.
例句释义: 无论你用多大力气去推那堵墙，我都觉得你推不动它。

例句: We mowed the lawn in the backyard and planted some flowers beside it.
例句释义: 我们修剪了后院的草坪，并在旁边栽了一些花。

详细释义: n. 宪章；特权，豁免权；租赁；  v. 包，租（汽车等）
英文释义: an official document stating that a ruler or government allows a new organization, town or university to be established and gives it particular rights
例句: The American Constitution is a charter that outlines a system of government.
例句释义: 美国宪法是一个概述政府系统的章程。

英文释义: a large piece of equipment for cooking food, containing an oven and gas or electric rings on top
例句: Turn off the stove, or the food will be overcooked.
例句释义: 快把炉子关掉，不然食物要烧焦了。

详细释义: n.同意，准许；赞成；  v.同意
英文释义: permission to do something, especially given by somebody in authority
例句: I give you my consent; you can do it if you want.
例句释义: 我赞成你的想法；如果你想做，你就做吧。

英文释义: to have somebody/something as parts or members
例句: These animals comprise most of the cat family.
例句释义: 这些动物构成了猫科动物的大部分。

英文释义: a letter or note informing somebody that they have not done something
例句: I made a reminder in the calendar to send an important email.
例句释义: 为了发一封重要的电子邮件，我在日历上做了提醒。

英文释义: very similar
例句: The two dogs are a lot alike.
例句释义: 这两只狗长得很像。

英文释义: a mixture of flour, water, and other ingredients that is baked to make bread, cookies, etc.
例句: Dough is a mixture of flour and water.
例句释义: 生面团是面粉和水的混合物。

英文释义: to build a dam across a river, especially in order to make an artificial lake for use as a water supply, etc.
例句: The dam keeps the river from flooding the town.
例句释义: 大坝阻止河水淹没城镇。

英文释义: known about by a lot of people; (of a fact) generally known and accepted
例句: This is a well-known painting.
例句释义: 这幅画世界闻名。

英文释义: that is near or around something
例句: The surrounding river of the house looks so blue!
例句释义: 房子周围的河水看起来真蓝呀！

英文释义: connected with the relation of plants and living creatures to each other and to their environment; interested in and concerned about the ecology of a place
例句: We need to maintain an ecological balance between humans and nature.
例句释义: 我们需要在人与自然间保持生态平衡。

详细释义: n.装备，装束，全套服装；组织，团队；  v.提供装备
英文释义: a set of clothes that you wear together, especially for a particular occasion or purpose; a group of people working together as an organization, business, team, etc.; a set of equipment that you need for a particular purpose
例句: When it comes to their outfits, they have totally different taste.
例句释义: 她们对于穿搭有着完全不同的品位。

详细释义: adj. 前所未有的，空前的，无前例的
英文释义: that has never happened, been done or been known before
例句: In 1903, the Wright Brothers made an unprecedented airplane flight.
例句释义: 1903年，莱特兄弟进行了一次前所未有的飞行。

英文释义: a journalist who writes editorials
例句: He is one of the magazine's most popular columnists.
例句释义: 他是该杂志最受欢迎的专栏作家之一。

详细释义: adj. 初步的，预备的；  n. 预赛；预考，初试；初步措施
英文释义: happening before a more important action or event
例句: The preliminary drawings of the building are already finished.
例句释义: 建筑的初步图稿已经完成。

详细释义: n.专利；  adj.显然的，明显的；有专利的；  v.取得专利权
英文释义: an official right to be the only person to make, use or sell a product or an invention; a document that proves this
例句: He held a patent for his newly made spicy sauce.
例句释义: 他持有他最新研制的辣椒酱的专利。

英文释义: feeling nervous and uncomfortable about meeting and talking to people; afraid of doing something or being involved in something
例句: They are both shy on the first date.
例句释义: 第一次约会时，他们俩都很害羞。

详细释义: n. 垃圾；拙劣的文学（或艺术）作品；  v. 捣毁；贬低
英文释义: things that you throw away because you no longer want or need them
例句: Please take out the trash now. It stinks!
例句释义: 请马上把垃圾拿出去，好臭！

英文释义: having a physical or mental disability; unable to perform one or more natural activities (such as walking or seeing) because of illness, injury, etc.
例句: These two young people are disabled but can still play basketball.
例句释义: 这两个年轻人虽然残疾了，但仍能打篮球。

详细释义: adj.总的，毛重的；  n.总量，总额；  adv.总共地
英文释义: being the total amount of something before anything is taken away; very unpleasant; very rude
例句: The gross cost for all these things is very high.
例句释义: 这些东西的总成本很高。

详细释义: excl. 该死，讨厌；  v. 诅咒；  n. 诅咒；  adv. （表示厌烦）该死
英文释义: (informal) a swear word that people use to show that they are annoyed, disappointed, etc.
例句: Damn it! Why do I keep getting fired!
例句释义: 该死的！为什么我老是被开除！

英文释义: a chemical substance produced in the body or in a plant that encourages growth or influences how the cells and tissues function; an artificial substance that has similar effects
例句: A high level of male hormones makes him look masculine.
例句释义: 大量的男性荷尔蒙使他看上去男人味十足。

详细释义: n. 纹理，质地；结构；口感；【音】谐和统一感；肌理
英文释义: the way a surface, substance or piece of cloth feels when you touch it, for example how rough, smooth, hard or soft it is
例句: She loves the smooth texture of silk.
例句释义: 她爱丝绸的光滑质地。

英文释义: a narrow piece of wood, or a metal or plastic case, containing a black or coloured substance, used for drawing or writing
例句: This is a black pencil.
例句释义: 这是一支黑色的铅笔。

详细释义: n.边境，国界；边远地区，边界地区
英文释义: a line that separates two countries, etc.; the land near this line
例句: People from different countries are playing volleyball over the frontier.
例句释义: 来自不同国家的人们在跨边境打排球。

详细释义: n. 喷雾；浪花；  vi. 飞溅，喷；  vt. 向……扫射
英文释义: (especially in compounds) a substance that is forced out of a container such as an aerosol, in very small drops
例句: We can use this spray to make the house smell better.
例句释义: 我们可以用这个喷雾让室内更好闻。

英文释义: to make (something) known to the public
例句: He disclosed the classified secret to the public.
例句释义: 他把机密公之于众了。

详细释义: n. 【法】抚养权，监护权；【法】拘留
英文释义: the legal right or duty to take care of or keep somebody/something
例句: The divorced couple are arguing over custody of their child.
例句释义: 这对离了婚的夫妻正在为孩子的监护权而吵架。

英文释义: a person who owns a bank or has an important job at a bank
例句: I trust my banker to keep my money safe.
例句释义: 我相信我的银行家能保障我钱的安全。

英文释义: an animal, especially one that is large or dangerous, or one that is unusual
例句: Lions, tigers, wolves and leopards are examples of dangerous, wild beasts.
例句释义: 狮子、老虎、狼和豹子都是危险的野兽。

英文释义: to get involved in and try to influence a situation that does not concern you, in a way that annoys other people
例句: Let it fall! Don't interfere with the process.
例句释义: 让它倒下去！别去干涉这个过程。

英文释义: a large tree that produces small nuts called acorns. Oaks are common in northern countries and can live to be hundreds of years old.; the hard wood of the oak tree
例句: There is a bench under the grand oak tree.
例句释义: 巨大的橡树下有一条长凳。

详细释义: n. 笔记本；笔记本电脑
英文释义: a book with blank pages that is used for writing notes
例句: I like to use colorful stickers to mark the important pages in my notebook.
例句释义: 我喜欢用彩色便利贴在笔记本的重要页面上做标记。

详细释义: n.外形，轮廓；大纲，概要；  v.描绘，画出……的轮廓
英文释义: a description of the main facts or points involved in something
例句: The girl drew an outline of the model.
例句释义: 这个女孩画出了模特的轮廓。

详细释义: n. 出席；出席人数；出席者；随员
英文释义: the act of being present at a place, for example at school
例句: The register kept a record of people's attendances at the conference.
例句释义: 登记簿记录了人们出席会议的情况。

英文释义: the activity of buying and selling goods or shares in a company in the hope of making a profit, but with the risk of losing money
例句: His risky speculation made him a lot of money.
例句释义: 他的冒险投机让他赚了一大笔钱。

详细释义: v. 移去……的覆盖物，发现
英文释义: to remove something that is covering something
例句: She uncovered the pot to see whether the food was cooked.
例句释义: 她打开盖子看食物是不是已经煮好了。

详细释义: n. 代表（某人），因为某人；利益；赞同，支持
英文释义: as the representative of somebody or instead of them
例句: Lord Bao attended the conference on behalf of Baicizhan.
例句释义: 包大人代表百词斩参加了这次会议。

英文释义: introducing or using new ideas, ways of doing something, etc.
例句: This girl always comes up with new and innovative ideas!
例句释义: 这女孩儿总能想出一些具有创新意义的新点子！

英文释义: a large sea fish with very sharp teeth and a pointed fin on its back. There are several types of shark, some of which can attack people swimming.
例句: The diver is swimming with sharks.
例句释义: 潜水员在和鲨鱼一起游泳。

详细释义: n. 磨坊，碾磨机，制造厂；  v. 碾，磨，（毫无目的地）乱转
英文释义: a building fitted with machinery for grinding grain into flour; (often in compounds) a factory that produces a particular type of material
例句: The wind mill works by using wind power.
例句释义: 风车磨坊是利用风能工作的。

英文释义: the act of fixing equipment or furniture in position so that it can be used;  a piece of equipment or machinery that has been fixed in position so that it can be used
例句: The installation of the new air conditioner is almost complete.
例句释义: 这台新空调基本安装好了。

英文释义: to make somebody interested and excited about something; to make something develop or become more active; to encourage something
例句: The globe can be used to stimulate discussion among the kids.
例句释义: 地球仪可用来鼓励孩子们相互讨论。

详细释义: n. 标签；附加语；  v. 装包头于（鞋带等）
英文释义: a small piece of cloth, paper, metal, etc., that is attached to something and that has information written on it
例句: I always look for a sale tag to get a lower price.
例句释义: 我总是在寻找降价标签以得到更低的价格。

英文释义: (of a line, pole, etc.) going straight up or down from a level surface or from top to bottom in a picture, etc.
例句: The boy found the only vertical tree in the woods.
例句释义: 这个男孩找到了树林里唯一一棵与地面垂直的树。

英文释义: the sport or activity of swimming
例句: Swimming is the boy's favorite outdoor activity.
例句释义: 游泳是这个男孩最喜欢的户外活动。

详细释义: n. 舰队，船队；  adj. 迅速的；  n. 车队
英文释义: a group of military ships commanded by the same person; all the military ships of a particular country
例句: The big fleet of ships always stay together.
例句释义: 这支舰队的舰船总是一起行动。

详细释义: n. 目录，目录册，商品目录；  v. 为……编目录，登记
英文释义: a complete list of items, for example of things that people can look at or buy
例句: There is a variety of clothes on the catalog for us to select.
例句释义: 我们可以在商品目录上选择各式各样的衣服。

英文释义: a publicly stated opinion
例句: The correct stance can significantly improve a golfer's swing.
例句释义: 正确的站姿能明显改善高尔夫球手的挥杆效果。

详细释义: vt.强迫；迫使屈服；（使）不得已
英文释义: to force somebody to do something; to make something necessary
例句: He was compelled to stay in the circle.
例句释义: 他被迫待在一个圆圈里。

英文释义: a tendency to be easily offended or upset by something
例句: She showed great sensitivity about what others thought about her appearance.
例句释义: 她很在意别人对于她外貌的评价。

详细释义: n. 瞬间；  adj. 立即的
英文释义: a very short period of time; a particular point in time
例句: The mother caught her baby the instant he fell.
例句释义: 那位母亲在孩子掉下的瞬间接住了他。

详细释义: n. 初次登台，在社交场合的初次露脸；  v. 初次露面，初次表演
英文释义: the first public appearance of a performer or sports player
例句: The young player made his debut after signing a contract with the club.
例句释义: 这位年轻的运动员跟俱乐部签订合同后，首次亮相赛场。

详细释义: v. 宣告；声明，声称；表明
英文释义: to publicly and officially tell people about something important
例句: He proclaimed on social media that his team had won the world gaming championship.
例句释义: 他在社交媒体上宣告他的战队获得了这项电竞游戏的冠军。

详细释义: adv.在世界各地；  adj.全世界的
英文释义: affecting all parts of the world
例句: The Internet connects users worldwide.
例句释义: 互联网连接的用户遍布世界各地。

详细释义: v.徒步旅行；使高涨，提高（价格）；  n.（数量、价格等）增加，上升
英文释义: to go for a long walk in the country, especially for pleasure
例句: A group of old people are going hiking on a sunny day.
例句释义: 天气晴朗，一群老年人在远足。

英文释义: a situation in which there is an angry disagreement between people or groups who have different opinions
例句: They felt confrontation was the only way to solve their disagreement.
例句释义: 他们觉得对抗是解决他们之间的分歧的唯一办法。

详细释义: adj.多彩的，华美的，色彩的；有趣的
英文释义: full of bright colours or having a lot of different colours
例句: Many colorful stickers are on the wall.
例句释义: 墙上贴了很多彩色的贴纸。

详细释义: n. 组成，结构；宪法，章程
英文释义: the system of laws and basic principles that a state, a country or an organization is governed by
例句: The chemical constitution of vitamin B6 seems quite complex.
例句释义: 维他命b6的化学构造看起来很复杂。

英文释义: a person who teaches people or animals to perform a particular job or skill well, or to do a particular sport
例句: His personal trainer is teaching him how to use the fitness equipment correctly.
例句释义: 他的私人教练正在教他如何正确使用健身器材。

英文释义: a public holiday in the US (on the fourth Thursday in November) and in Canada (on the second Monday in October), originally to give thanks to God for the harvest and for health; the expression of thanks to God
例句: Roast turkey is a traditional food served on Thanksgiving.
例句释义: 烤火鸡是感恩节的传统食物。

详细释义: n.气味；香味；迹象；  v.嗅到；察觉
英文释义: the pleasant smell that something has
例句: She loves the scent of the sunflower.
例句释义: 她喜欢向日葵的味道。

详细释义: n. 堆，一大堆；  v. 堆积，堆放
英文释义: a pile of something, usually neatly arranged; a large number or amount of something; a lot of something
例句: I've bought this entire stack of goods through e-shopping!
例句释义: 这一大堆东西都是我从网上买的！

英文释义: the line of hair that grows over your eye
例句: The woman is correcting her eyebrow shape with a brush.
例句释义: 这个女人正在用小刷子来修正她的眉形。

详细释义: n. 一袋；麻袋；  v. 掠夺
英文释义: a large bag with no handles, made of strong rough material or strong paper or plastic, used for storing and carrying, for example flour, coal, etc.
例句: They filled the sacks with potatoes.
例句释义: 他们在麻布袋子里装满了土豆。

详细释义: v.停止，结束；  n.停止，停息
英文释义: to stop happening or existing
例句: The rain ceased and the rainbow showed up.
例句释义: 雨停了，彩虹出现在天边。

详细释义: v. 经遗传而得（特性等）
英文释义: to have qualities, physical features, etc. that are similar to those of your parents, grandparents, etc.
例句: The baby inherited his father's curly hair.
例句释义: 小宝宝遗传了父亲的卷发。

英文释义: a flat piece of wood, metal or plastic with raised edges, used for carrying or holding things, especially food; a shallow plastic box, used for various purposes
例句: He brought three glasses of water on a tray.
例句释义: 他用托盘拿过来了三杯水。

详细释义: n.先锋，先驱；  vt.开辟，首倡
英文释义: a person who is the first to study and develop a particular area of knowledge, culture, etc. that other people then continue to develop; one of the first people to go to a particular area in order to live and work there
例句: He's a pioneer in climbing, that is, the first man to reach the summit.
例句释义: 他是登山的先锋，即第一个到达山顶的人。

英文释义: a book about a particular subject that is used in the study of that subject especially in a school
例句: This textbook demonstrates how to be a cat person.
例句释义: 这本教科书教你怎样做一个“猫奴”。

英文释义: unkind; unpleasant
例句: Her brother is so nasty to her―he's always fighting with her and pulling her hair.
例句释义: 她觉得弟弟很讨厌――他总是和她打架，拉扯她的头发。

英文释义: to become or to make something smaller in size or amount
例句: My sweater shrank in the wash.
例句释义: 我的毛衣在洗涤后缩水了。

英文释义: a small round mark, especially one that is printed
例句: Ladybugs have several black dots on their backs.
例句释义: 瓢虫的背上有一些黑色圆点。

英文释义: a plant grown for its grain that is used to produce the flour for bread, cakes, pasta, etc.; the grain of this plant
例句: The wheat here has turned yellow.
例句释义: 这儿的小麦已经变黄了。

英文释义: (especially of people or animals) angry and aggressive in a way that is frightening
例句: The tiger showing its sharp teeth looks so fierce.
例句释义: 这只露出锋利牙齿的老虎看上去真凶猛。

详细释义: adj. 理性的；理智的；合理的
英文释义: (of behaviour, ideas, etc.) based on reason rather than emotions
例句: The mother tried to remain rational when her son smashed the bowl.
例句释义: 儿子打碎碗时，母亲试着保持理智。

英文释义: a country whose ruler is a king or queen
例句: The lion rules the animal kingdom with the help of his friends.
例句释义: 狮子在朋友们的帮助下统治动物王国。

英文释义: a passage between rows of seats in a church, theatre, train, etc., or between rows of shelves in a supermarket
例句: The stewardess is walking down the aisle of the airplane.
例句释义: 这位空姐在飞机的过道上行走。

英文释义: to make something less physically strong; to become less physically strong; to make somebody/something less strong or powerful; to become less strong or powerful
例句: His eating disorder and insufficient food intake obviously weakened him.
例句释义: 饮食失调和摄入不足明显使他变得虚弱了。

详细释义: n.外交礼节；外交议定书；  vi.拟定议定书；  vt.把……写入议定书
英文释义: a system of rules that explain the correct conduct and procedures to be followed in formal situations
例句: When presidents meet, protocol requires that they shake hands.
例句释义: 当总统们会面的时候，外交礼节规定他们必须握手。

英文释义: for only one particular person, group or use
例句: The toilet is for the mother and baby exclusively.
例句释义: 这个房间专供母婴使用。

详细释义: adj. 声音的；畅言无忌的
英文释义: connected with the voice
例句: The singer is good at both vocal and facial expressions!
例句释义: 这位歌手擅长声乐和面部表情的表现！

英文释义: in an open way
例句: He held a press conference to openly express his opposition to the new chemical plant.
例句释义: 他召开新闻发布会，公开反对新建化工厂。

英文释义: not right or fair according to a set of rules or principles; not treating people equally
例句: This is unfair! Why is he more important than us!
例句释义: 这不公平！凭什么他比我们更重要！

英文释义: used to refer to an area of land when you are mentioning its natural features, for example, if it is rough, flat, etc.
例句: From grasslands to deserts, there are many different types of terrain around the world.
例句释义: 从草原到沙漠，世界上有很多种不同的地形。

英文释义: to move soldiers or weapons into a position where they are ready for military action
例句: Forces and tanks were deployed at strategic locations.
例句释义: 军队和坦克已部署在各个战略位置。

英文释义: involving the possibility of something bad happening
例句: Walking on the ice to get his ball is quite risky.
例句释义: 他走在冰上去捡球是很危险的。

英文释义: a food made from a mixture of flour, water, and sometimes eggs that is formed into different shapes (such as thin strips, tubes, or shells) and usually boiled
例句: There are various kinds of pasta on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上放着各种各样的意大利面食。

详细释义: n.体裁；类型；流派；  adj.（艺术）风俗的，以日常情景为主题的
英文释义: a particular type or style of literature, art, film or music that you can recognize because of its special features
例句: Books in the bookstore are arranged according to different genres.
例句释义: 这家书店的书是按体裁来分类排放的。

详细释义: v. 使分心，转移（注意力），分散（思想）
英文释义: to take somebody’s attention away from what they are trying to do
例句: The cat tried to distract his friend's attention and took his fish.
例句释义: 小猫试图转移他朋友的注意力，伺机拿走他的小鱼干。

详细释义: n.优点；价值；功绩；  v.值得；应得
英文释义: the quality of being good and of deserving praise, reward or admiration; the quality of being deserving
例句: A merit of this phone is that the excellent camera can clearly capture the moon.
例句释义: 这款手机的优点之一是它出色的拍照功能可以清晰地捕捉月亮的样子。

英文释义: a person who makes plans; a chart for recording future appointments, tasks.
例句: The two planners are looking at the city map.
例句释义: 两位规划者正看着城市地图。

英文释义: very sad and without hope
例句: He felt very depressed when he got fired.
例句释义: 被解雇时，他感到非常沮丧。

详细释义: n.大块；矮而厚的木块；大量
英文释义: a thick solid piece that has been cut or broken off something
例句: I will just cook this big chunk of meat for dinner.
例句释义: 晚饭我只烹饪这一大块肉。

详细释义: n.（价格、债款等的）折扣；  v.打折
英文释义: an amount of money that is taken off the usual cost of something
例句: These clothes are sold at a 70% discount.
例句释义: 这些衣服正在三折甩卖。

英文释义: a device used for climbing that has two long pieces of wood, metal, or rope with a series of steps or rungs between them
例句: I climbed up the ladder to change the light bulb.
例句释义: 我爬上梯子换灯泡。

英文释义: an area of tropical forest where trees and plants grow very thickly
例句: The boy explored through the jungle.
例句释义: 这个小男孩在丛林里探险。

英文释义: the movement of large numbers of people, birds or animals from one place to another
例句: Lack of food caused the migration of the elephants.
例句释义: 食物匮乏导致了象群的迁徙。

英文释义: to enter a country, town, etc. using military force in order to take control of it
例句: The wolves invaded the goat family.
例句释义: 狼群入侵了咩咩村。

英文释义: a violent storm with very strong winds, especially in the western Atlantic Ocean
例句: Run! The hurricane is coming！
例句释义: 快跑！飓风来了！

英文释义: a person or business that sells goods to the public
例句: This retailer sells many kinds of products.
例句释义: 这个零售商销售各种各样的商品。

英文释义: to arrange something in groups according to features that they have in common; to decide which type or group somebody/something belongs to
例句: Please classify the garbage when throwing them away.
例句释义: 扔垃圾的时候请进行分类。

详细释义: n. 政变；出乎意料的行动或胜利
英文释义: a sudden change of government that is illegal and often violent
例句: A group of people staged a coup and dethroned the dictator.
例句释义: 一群人发动政变，废黜了那个独裁者。

英文释义: an official who lives in a foreign country as the senior representative there of his or her own country
例句: Each cellphone company sent an ambassador to the conference.
例句释义: 每个手机厂商都派了代表来参加这个会议。

英文释义: the quality of being dense; the degree to which something is dense
例句: The high density of buildings makes the city so crowded.
例句释义: 这个城市的建筑密度很高，所以城市也非常拥挤。

英文释义: giving help, encouragement or sympathy to sb
例句: My family was supportive of my dream to be a singer.
例句释义: 对于我想要成为歌唱家的梦想，我的家人持肯定态度。

英文释义: a strong desire to know about something
例句: Curiosity drives the cat to see what it is in the box.
例句释义: 好奇心驱使这只猫去看盒子里是什么。

详细释义: v. 跳过；遗漏；  n. 跳跃
英文释义: to move forwards lightly and quickly making a little jump with each step
例句: The children are skipping rope during their break.
例句释义: 孩子们在课间跳绳。

英文释义: angry or violent behavior or feelings
例句: This cat looks full of aggression.
例句释义: 这只猫看起来充满了攻击性。

英文释义: something that helps somebody/something to develop better or more quickly
例句: A big red flower means a stimulus to her.
例句释义: 对她而言大红花意味着一种鼓励。

英文释义: the work of collecting and writing news stories for newspapers, magazines, radio, television or online news sites; the news stories that are written
例句: They work in journalism and broadcast news as anchors.
例句释义: 他们从事新闻行业，作为主播播报新闻。

英文释义: a machine that is made to look like a human and that can do some things that a human can do
例句: In the future, we all will have robot assistants.
例句释义: 未来，我们都会有机器人助手。

英文释义: to put something quickly into a liquid and take it out again
例句: I like to dip the cookie into the milk.
例句释义: 我喜欢把饼干蘸一下牛奶再吃。

英文释义: the same; in a similar way; also
例句: The big man hates the small man; likewise, the small man hates the big man.
例句释义: 这个大个子讨厌这个小个子。同样地，这个小个子也讨厌这个大个子。

英文释义: casual；without formality or ceremony;
例句: The man on the right is wearing more informal clothing.
例句释义: 右边的男人穿得更随便一点。

英文释义: one of the many soft light parts covering a bird’s body
例句: This beautiful hat is made of feathers.
例句释义: 这顶漂亮的帽子是羽毛做的。

英文释义: any object that is completely round, for example a ball
例句: The world is not flat; it is a sphere.
例句释义: 世界不是平的，而是一个球体。

英文释义: to become or make something become tight or tighter
例句: She tightened up her belt before the karate match.
例句释义: 空手道比赛前，她系紧了她的腰带。

英文释义: to talk with too much pride about something that you have or can do
例句: The man is boasting of his muscle.
例句释义: 这个男人在吹嘘自己的肌肉。

详细释义: v. 轻拍，抚摸；  n. 轻拍，抚摸
英文释义: to lightly touch (someone or something) with your hand usually several times in order to show affection or approval or to provide comfort
例句: He patted the dog affectionately.
例句释义: 他亲切地拍了拍那只狗。

详细释义: n.脚底，鞋底，袜底；  adj.独有的；  v.给……装鞋底
英文释义: the bottom surface of the foot
例句: She is having the sole of her foot massaged.
例句释义: 她正在按摩足底。

详细释义: n.公开（性），公众的关注；宣传
英文释义: the attention that is given to somebody or something by newspapers, television, etc.
例句: He gets a lot of publicity; he's always on TV.
例句释义: 他总是上电视，得到了很多公众的注意。

英文释义: to spread open or flat something that has previously been folded; to become open and flat
例句: I've unfolded this piece of paper.
例句释义: 我展开了这张纸。

英文释义: the state of being legally or officially acceptable
例句: Nobody questioned the validity of the judge's ruling.
例句释义: 没有人质疑法官判决的有效性。

英文释义: all the plants and living creatures in a particular area considered in relation to their physical environment
例句: Plants, fishes, and the sun make up the ecosystem of this lake.
例句释义: 植物、鱼类和太阳构成了这个湖泊的生态系统。

详细释义: adj. 不完全的；偏爱的，特别喜欢的；偏袒的，不公平的，有偏见的；部分的
英文释义: showing or feeling too much support for one person, team, idea, etc., in a way that is unfair
例句: The partial eclipse obscured less than half the moon's surface.
例句释义: 月偏食遮盖了月球不到一半的面积。

英文释义: the part around the neck of a shirt, jacket or coat that usually folds down
例句: The collar of this shirt is too tight.
例句释义: 这件衬衣的衣领太紧了。

英文释义: any wild plant without flowers that grows in water and forms a green floating mass
例句: The worker is cutting the weeds.
例句释义: 工人正在除草。

英文释义: the act or process of doing what you have been asked or ordered to do :the act or process of complying
例句: Compliance with the law is expected of all citizens.
例句释义: 全体公民都有义务遵守法律。

详细释义: n. 条纹，条痕，色线；  v. 成条纹
英文释义: a long thin mark or line that is a different colour from the surface it is on; a part of a person’s character, especially an unpleasant part; a series of successes or failures, especially in a sport or in gambling
例句: She drew several black streaks on the paper using the writing brush.
例句释义: 她用毛笔在纸上画了几条黑色条纹。

英文释义: believed or reputed to be the case
例句: There are supposedly foxes around here, but they haven't seen any yet.
例句释义: 据说这附近可能有狐狸，但他们还没看到。

英文释义: a substance added to soaps or detergents to increase their cleansing action
例句: The builder is working on the roof.
例句释义: 这个建筑工人正在盖房顶。

详细释义: n. 一瞥；  v. 一瞥，瞥见
英文释义: a look at somebody/something for a very short time, when you do not see the person or thing completely
例句: Alice caught a quick glimpse of Wonderland through the tiny door.
例句释义: 爱丽丝透过小小的门匆匆瞥见了仙境。

详细释义: n. 前提；房屋地基；  v. 假定
英文释义: a statement or an idea that forms the basis for a reasonable line of argument
例句: This is the movie's premise: two people are trapped on an island and they end up falling in love!
例句释义: 在电影的前情假定中，两个被困在荒岛上的人迟早要相爱！

英文释义: a type of food or product that a restaurant or place is famous for because it is so good
例句: These are several kinds of specialties in our restaurant.
例句释义: 这是我们饭店的几样特色菜。

详细释义: v. 认为，视为；知道，相信
英文释义: (not usually used in the progressive tenses) to have a particular opinion about something
例句: He deemed the music beautiful.
例句释义: 他觉得音乐悦耳。

英文释义: an object that is made by a person, especially something of historical or cultural interest
例句: These ancient artifacts are of great historical and cultural value.
例句释义: 这些古代手工艺品都极具历史和文化价值。

详细释义: vi.鬼鬼祟祟地走；打小报告；  vt.潜行；偷窃；  adj.偷偷的；  n.行为鬼祟的人
英文释义: to go somewhere secretly, trying to avoid being seen
例句: The boy took off his shoes so he could sneak around.
例句释义: 这个男孩脱掉了鞋子，这样就能偷偷地溜出去了。

英文释义: an animal with a long tail, that climbs trees and lives in hot countries. There are several types of monkey and they are related to apes and humans.
例句: Monkeys are very clever animals.
例句释义: 猴子是十分聪明的动物。

英文释义: someone who teaches or gives help and advice to a less experienced and often younger person
例句: My mentor in college gave me lots of advice on how to revise my paper.
例句释义: 我的大学导师在修改论文方面给了我很多意见。

英文释义: someone who listens attentively
例句: She's a good listener who always hears you out when you have problems.
例句释义: 她是个很好的倾听者。当你遇到问题时，她总是愿意听你把话说完。

英文释义: a flash, or several flashes, of very bright light in the sky caused by electricity;  a sudden stroke of fortune
例句: Oh my God! A bolt of lightning is striking my house.
例句释义: 我的天哪！一道闪电击中了我的房子！

英文释义: the part of a shirt, jacket, etc. that covers all or part of your arm
例句: In winter, I prefer shirts with long sleeves.
例句释义: 冬天，我比较喜欢穿长袖衬衫。

英文释义: the state or feeling of being disappointed
例句: The birthday cake was a big disappointment to him.
例句释义: 这个生日蛋糕让他非常失望。

英文释义: to interrupt somebody when they are trying to work, sleep, etc.
例句: His snoring really disturbs me at night!
例句释义: 晚上，他的呼噜声真的很打扰我！

英文释义: any of the curved bones that are connected to the spine and surround the chest; a piece of meat with one or more bones from the ribs of an animal
例句: The pork ribs on the plate seem delicious！
例句释义: 这盘排骨看上去很美味！

英文释义: greater than what seems reasonable or appropriate
例句: Excessive food intake made the cat overweight.
例句释义: 贪食使得这只猫超重了。

例句: She is wearing a pair of high-tech VR glasses.
例句释义: 她戴着一副高科技虚拟现实眼镜。

英文释义: pieces of wood, metal, brick, etc. that are left after something has been destroyed; rubbish/garbage or pieces of material that are left somewhere and are not wanted
例句: The debris from buildings can be seen everywhere after the earthquake.
例句释义: 地震后，房屋的残骸随处可见。

英文释义: a straight, thin stick or bar
例句: I hope this fishing rod is strong enough to catch a big fish.
例句释义: 但愿这鱼竿足够结实，可以钓起来大鱼。

详细释义: adj. 有逻辑的；推理正确的
英文释义: following or able to follow the rules of logic in which ideas or facts are based on other true ideas or facts
例句: Logical thinking requires a step-by-step thought process.
例句释义: 逻辑思维需要循序渐进的思维过程。

英文释义: the grey or black powder that is left after something, especially tobacco, wood or coal, has burnt
例句: These backpackers left nothing here but a pile of ashes.
例句释义: 这些背包客只在这儿留下一堆灰烬。

英文释义: the group of people who go to the church in a particular area
例句: Priests and nuns both live and work in a parish.
例句释义: 牧师和修女们都在教区生活和工作。

英文释义: the system by which people are owned by other people as slaves
例句: Lincoln announced the slavery should be abolished.
例句释义: 林肯宣布奴隶制应被废除。

详细释义: adj.（纸等）空白的；  n.空白，空白处
英文释义: an empty space on a printed form or document for you to write answers, information, etc. in
例句: Your notepad is blank; write some notes about the meeting!
例句释义: 你的笔记本是空白的，写点会议记录吧！

英文释义: a product or a raw material that can be bought and sold; a thing that is useful or has a useful quality
例句: You can find many commodities in supermarkets.
例句释义: 你可以在超市看到各种各样的商品。

英文释义: to make a person or an animal healthy again after an illness; to make an illness go away
例句: These pills will cure your sickness.
例句释义: 这些药丸能治好你的病。

详细释义: adj.矿物的；  n.矿物，矿物质
英文释义: of, relating to, containing, or resembling minerals
例句: We should drink more mineral water―it's good for our health.
例句释义: 我们应该多喝矿泉水，这对我们的健康有好处。

英文释义: the state of not having enough food to eat, especially when this causes illness or death
例句: He wants a hamburger to satisfy his hunger.
例句释义: 他想吃个汉堡来缓解饥饿。

英文释义: connected with or happening at the time of somebody’s death
例句: The fish is dying from lack of water.
例句释义: 因为缺水，这只鱼就快要死了。

详细释义: adj.备用的；多余的，闲置的；  n.备用品；  vt.抽出，腾出
英文释义: to save somebody/yourself from having to go through an unpleasant experience
例句: I have a spare tire for my car.
例句释义: 我的车有一个备胎。

例句: He is halfway up the stairs.
例句释义: 他上楼梯上到一半。

英文释义: the fact of being equal in rights, status, advantages, etc.
例句: The law ensures equality for all.
例句释义: 法律保障人人平等。

英文释义: an area of land used for burying dead people, especially one that is not beside a church
例句: Many?tombstones?lie?in?this?cemetery.
例句释义: 这片墓地里有许多墓碑。

英文释义: the act of annoying or worrying somebody by putting pressure on them or saying or doing unpleasant things to them
例句: Harassment from bullies can be very depressing.
例句释义: 来自恶霸的骚扰很让人沮丧。

英文释义: done in a way that was planned, not by chance
例句: Why does he deliberately try to make other people fall over?
例句释义: 他为什么故意绊倒别人？

详细释义: n.名望，名声，声誉；  vt.使有名，使著名
英文释义: the condition of being known or recognized by many people
例句: The actor enjoys fame and loves the attention it brings him.
例句释义: 这位男演员沉浸在名望中，并享受着由此带来的关注度。

英文释义: a feeling of sadness or disappointment that you have because of something that has happened or something that you have done or not done
例句: The woman regrets buying too much clothing.
例句释义: 这个女人后悔买了那么多衣服。

详细释义: adj.吸引人的，容貌出众的；显著的，突出的
英文释义: interesting and unusual enough to attract attention
例句: The most striking feature of this cat is its long snow-white hair.
例句释义: 这只猫最吸引人的是它雪白的长毛。

英文释义: the chance of something happening; how likely something is to happen
例句: In all likelihood, the lion will win the boxing match.
例句释义: 狮子很可能会赢得拳击比赛。

英文释义: the long orange root of a plant that is eaten as a vegetable
例句: Look! I have collected so many carrots!
例句释义: 瞧！我已经采了这么多胡萝卜！

详细释义: n. （道路等的）通行费；伤亡人数；  v. 敲钟
英文释义: an amount of money that you are required to pay for the use of a road or bridge
例句: You have to pay the toll if you ride the freeway.
例句释义: 如果你走高速路的话得付通行费。

详细释义: n.（圆形物体的）边缘；轮缘，轮圈；  v.形成边缘
英文释义: the metal edge of a wheel onto which the tyre is fixed
例句: I just bought a cup with gold rim.
例句释义: 我刚买了一个带有金边的杯子。

详细释义: adj.尴尬的，窘迫的，觉得难堪的
例句: The student is very embarrassed about being disciplined in front of his classmates.
例句释义: 这名学生因为在同学面前受到训诫而感到十分尴尬。

详细释义: vi.紧紧抓住；黏着，挨近；依恋，依附；坚持，墨守，忠实于
英文释义: to hold on tightly to somebody/something
例句: The koala clings to the tree.
例句释义: 考拉紧紧地抓着树。

详细释义: v. 眨眼睛；闪亮；闪烁；  n. 眨眼睛
英文释义: when you blink or blink your eyes or your eyes blink, you shut and open your eyes quickly
例句: She blinked as the photo was taken.
例句释义: 拍照的时候她眨眼睛了。

英文释义: feeling that somebody has done something wrong, illegal or dishonest, without having any proof; making you feel that something is wrong, illegal or dishonest
例句: The policeman found the woman's behavior suspicious.
例句释义: 警察发现这个女人的行为很可疑。

详细释义: n.（军队的）班，小队，小组；  v.编成班
英文释义: a section of a police force that deals with a particular type of crime
例句: Our squad moved out to find the enemy.
例句释义: 我们的小分队出去搜寻敌人了。

详细释义: adj.符合条件的；（尤指婚姻等）合适的，合意的
英文释义: a person who is eligible for something or to do something, is able to have or do it because they have the right qualifications, are the right age, etc.
例句: Children under 1.2m tall are eligible for free tickets.
例句释义: 身高在一米二以下的儿童符合免票条件。

英文释义: a business engaged in processing agricultural products and preparing them for market
例句: The processor turns apples into juice.
例句释义: 这台加工机把苹果制成了果汁。

详细释义: v.跳进，（使）投入；使陷入；暴跌；  n.卷入，参与；暴跌，骤减
英文释义: to move or make somebody/something move suddenly forwards and/or downwards; to move up and down suddenly and violently
例句: The sportswoman plunged into the water. Splash!
例句释义: 女运动员跳入水中，水花四溅。

详细释义: adj. 人口学的；人口统计学的
英文释义: of or relating to the study of changes that occur in large groups of people over a period of time :of or relating to demography
例句: The demographic charts show the aging population in four of these countries.
例句释义: 人口统计图表显示了其中四个国家的人口老龄化情况。

详细释义: n. 寒冷；  v. （使）感到冷，使变冷；  adj. 扫兴的
英文释义: a feeling of being cold
例句: I feel a chill coming on. The temperature is set too low.
例句释义: 我感觉有点冷。温度调得太低了。

详细释义: n.保护区；避难所，收容所；  v.避难，寻求庇护；给以庇护，提供庇护
英文释义: shelter or protection from danger, trouble, etc.
例句: This is a wetland refuge for birds.
例句释义: 这是一个鸟类湿地保护区。

英文释义: to control the direction in which a boat, car, etc. moves; (of a boat, car, etc.) to move in a particular direction; to take control of a situation and influence the way in which it develops
例句: Be cautious when you steer a car.
例句释义: 驾驶时，请务必谨慎。

详细释义: n. 集会；公路汽车赛；  v. 恢复（健康等），重新振作
英文释义: a large public meeting, especially one held to support a particular idea or political party
例句: He has organized a public rally.
例句释义: 他组织了一场群众集会。

详细释义: v. 欢呼；鼓劲，使振作；  n. 鼓励，振奋
英文释义: to shout loudly, to show support or praise for somebody, or to give them encouragement
例句: The sports fans cheered for their team.
例句释义: 球迷们为他们的球队加油喝彩。

详细释义: n.出口；表现机会，发泄方法
英文释义: a pipe or hole through which liquid or gas can flow out
例句: Water came out of the wall through several outlets.
例句释义: 水从墙上的几个出口中排了出来。

详细释义: adj.完好无缺的，原封未动的
英文释义: complete and not damaged
例句: The glass remained intact after it was dropped.
例句释义: 这个玻璃杯掉了下来，但依然完好无缺。

英文释义: to become, and continue to be, successful, strong, healthy, etc.
例句: Plants thrive if they get enough sunlight.
例句释义: 如果有足够的阳光，植物便会茁壮成长。

英文释义: a nut that grows underground in a thin shell
例句: There are some peanuts in the bowl.
例句释义: 碗里有一些花生。

英文释义: to bite food into small pieces in your mouth with your teeth to make it easier to swallow; to bite something continuously, for example because you are nervous or to taste it
例句: The boy is chewing the rice.
例句释义: 这个男孩在咀嚼米饭。

详细释义: adj. 精心设计的，精巧的；  v. 详细说明，详尽阐述
英文释义: very complicated and detailed; carefully prepared and organized
例句: This elaborate wood carving features delicate flowers.
例句释义: 这件精巧的木雕上有精致的花朵。

详细释义: n.怀孕；构想，设想；思想，观念
英文释义: the process of forming an idea or a plan; an understanding or a belief of what something is or what something should be; the process of an egg being fertilized inside a woman’s body so that she becomes pregnant
例句: This baby will come into the world nine months after conception.
例句释义: 怀孕九个月后，宝宝会来到这个世上。

详细释义: n. 拍卖；  v. 拍卖
英文释义: a public event at which things are sold to the person who offers the most money for them
例句: Although about five of us were bidding on the house at the auction, I finally won.
例句释义: 在拍卖会上，虽然我们五个都为这栋房子竞价，但最终还是我赢了。

英文释义: a thick slice of good quality beef
例句: There are two pieces of delicious steak on the fork.
例句释义: 叉子上叉了两块美味的牛排。

英文释义: to obey a rule, an order, etc.
例句: We should comply with traffic regulations.
例句释义: 我们应该遵守交通规则。

详细释义: n.胜利，凯旋；  vi.成功，获胜
英文释义: a great success, achievement or victory
例句: "I win!" he shouted in triumph.
例句释义: “我赢了！” 他在胜利时喊道。

英文释义: an owner of shares in a company or business
例句: Shareholders are expecting rapid market growth by next month.
例句释义: 股东们期望下个月市场快速增长。

详细释义: adj.类似的，比得上的，可比较的
英文释义: similar to somebody/something else and able to be compared
例句: The two dogs are comparable in size and strength.
例句释义: 这两条狗在大小和强壮程度方面都不相上下。

详细释义: vt.运输，运送；  v.使产生身临其境的感觉；  n.运输工具
英文释义: to take something/somebody from one place to another in a vehicle
例句: This ship can transport hundreds of containers.
例句释义: 这艘船能运输几百个集装箱。

英文释义: the part of the mind that makes you aware of your actions as being either morally right or wrong
例句: My conscience always tells me to do something right.
例句释义: 我的良心经常告诉我要做对的事情。

英文释义: the act or process of using numbers to find out an amount
例句: The little girl is doing calculations on the blackboard.
例句释义: 小女孩正在黑板上做计算题。

详细释义: n. 中场休息，幕间休息；间隔
英文释义: a period of time between events
例句: They have 15 minutes' interval.
例句释义: 他们有15分钟的中场休息时间。

详细释义: n.抓痕，擦伤；  v.抓破，划破
英文释义: a mark, a cut or an injury made by scratching somebody’s skin or the surface of something
例句: The cat leaves some scratches on the wall.
例句释义: 猫在墙上留下了一些抓痕。

详细释义: adj.醒着的；  v.（使）醒来；唤起，被唤起
英文释义: not asleep (especially immediately before or after sleeping)
例句: It's already 3:22 a.m., but she is still awake.
例句释义: 现在已经是凌晨3点22分了，但她还醒着。

英文释义: the power or right to make judgments about the law, to arrest and punish criminals, etc.
例句: The thief escaped into Germany which wasn't within the French police's jurisdiction.
例句释义: 盗贼逃到了德国，已不在法国警察的管辖范围内了。

详细释义: n.男女平等主义者，女权扩张论者；  adj.主张男女平等的，女权主义的
英文释义: a person who supports the belief that women should have the same rights and opportunities as men
例句: Feminists call for equal rights for women and girls.
例句释义: 女权主义者呼吁女性应当享有平等的权利。

英文释义: a thing that limits or restricts something, or your freedom to do something
例句: Money constraints prevented the boy travelling the world.
例句释义: 金钱的限制使这个男孩无法环游世界。

英文释义: the people who go on an expedition
例句: They went on a mountain expedition.
例句释义: 他们去山上探险了。

英文释义: the state of being like somebody/something but not exactly the same; a feature that things or people have that makes them like each other
例句: There are many similarities between a Husky and a wolf.
例句释义: 哈士奇和狼有许多相似之处。

英文释义: the thick end of a weapon or tool; the part of a cigarette or cigar that is left after it has been smoked; the part of the body that you sit on
例句: Corgis have the cutest butts of all kinds of dogs.
例句释义: 柯基有着所有狗狗中最可爱的屁股。

英文释义: a cover over a container that can be removed or opened by turning it or lifting it
例句: My mouth watered when the waiter took the lid off the plate.
例句释义: 当服务员把盘子上的盖子拿起来时，我流口水了。

详细释义: adj. 哑的，暂不说话的，愚笨的；  v. 使沉默
英文释义: unable to speak; temporarily not speaking or refusing to speak; stupid
例句: It‘s dumb to row on the cracked soil.
例句释义: 在龟裂的土地上划船是件很蠢的事情。

详细释义: n.大批；容量；体积；  adj.大量的；散装的；  v.膨胀；显得重要
英文释义: the (large) size or quantity of something
例句: Buying tomatoes in bulk is more economical than buying in small quantities.
例句释义: 批量采购番茄比少量购买实惠很多。

详细释义: v. 撒，洒；下稀疏的雨；  n. 少量
英文释义: to shake small pieces of something or drops of a liquid on something
例句: To finish his cupcakes, the baker sprinkled some sugar on the top.
例句释义: 为了完成他的纸杯蛋糕，烘焙师在上面撒了一些糖粉。

英文释义: the state of being human and not living for ever
例句: Seeing a dead body reminds us of our mortality.
例句释义: 看到尸体总会让我们想到自己也必然会死。

英文释义: connected with philosophy
例句: This old man likes to think about philosophical questions.
例句释义: 这位长者喜欢思考哲学问题。

详细释义: n. 【经济学】兑换；转变，转换；宗教、信仰上的转变
英文释义: the act or process of changing from one form, state, etc., to another
例句: There are different conversion rates among those currencies.
例句释义: 这些货币之间有不同的汇率。

详细释义: n. 老主顾；赞助人；支持者
英文释义: a person who uses a particular shop/store, restaurant, etc.
例句: He is one of the restaurant's oldest patrons; he has been eating there for years.
例句释义: 他是这家餐馆最久的主顾之一，他已经光顾这里很多年了。

英文释义: connected with or belonging to a town, city or district that has its own local government
例句: This beautiful building is home to the municipal government of San Francisco.
例句释义: 这个漂亮的建筑是旧金山市政府所在地。

英文释义: a large organ in the body that cleans the blood and produces bile
例句: The largest internal organ in a human body is the liver.
例句释义: 人体最大的内脏是肝脏。

英文释义: a state of peaceful existence and agreement
例句: They live together in perfect harmony.
例句释义: 他们和睦地住在一起。

英文释义: only; not involving somebody/something else
例句: The girl wants to stay solely instead of communicating with her friends.
例句释义: 这个女孩想独自待着，不想和朋友们交流。

英文释义: the ability to suffer something, especially pain, difficult conditions, etc. without being harmed
例句: I've had to develop a tolerance for loud noise at the place where I work.
例句释义: 在我上班的地方，我不得不养成耐受巨大噪声的能力。

英文释义: an animal with horns and a coat of hair, that lives wild in mountain areas or is kept on farms for its milk or meat
例句: I love my pet goat even though it eats everything.
例句释义: 我爱我的宠物山羊，尽管它什么都吃。

详细释义: n. 祝福；幸事；  v. 使幸福
英文释义: God’s help and protection, or a prayer asking for this
例句: Mother gave her daughter a blessing by kissing on her forehead.
例句释义: 妈妈亲吻女儿额头以示祝福。

英文释义: the official home of a king, queen, president, etc.; any large impressive house
例句: The first snow this winter covered the palace in a blanket of white.
例句释义: 今冬的初雪给这座宫殿盖上了一层雪白的毯子。

详细释义: n. 农民；农夫；庄稼人；小耕农
英文释义: a person who is rude, behaves badly, or has little education
例句: The peasants are working on the farm land.
例句释义: 农民在地里劳作。

英文释义: not messy; clean and orderly
例句: The folded clothes look very neat in the drawer.
例句释义: 抽屉里叠好的衣服看起来很整洁。

详细释义: n.祖父或祖母，外祖父或外祖母
英文释义: the father or mother of your father or mother
例句: The little boy is having his picture taken with his grandparents.
例句释义: 小男孩正在和他的祖父母拍照片。

英文释义: a large shop/store that sells food, drinks and goods used in the home, where people choose what they want from the shelves and pay for it as they leave
例句: You can buy a lot of things from the supermarket.
例句释义: 你可以在超市买到很多东西。

详细释义: n. 旅行；漫游；  v. （出租车、船等）缓慢巡行
英文释义: a journey by sea, visiting different places, especially as a holiday/vacation
例句: He and his wife are so excited about going on a cruise.
例句释义: 他和他的妻子对乘船旅行感到很兴奋。

英文释义: a telephone that does not have wires and works by radio, that you can carry with you and use anywhere
例句: The doctor will show you how to use the mobile phone.
例句释义: 这位博士会给你演示如何使用手机。

英文释义: a document, chart, etc., that shows the days, weeks, and months of a year
例句: The month is over, so it's time to flip to the next month on the calendar.
例句释义: 这个月结束了，是时候翻到日历的下一个月了。

详细释义: n.寡妇，遗孀；  v.使成为寡妇
英文释义: a woman whose husband has died and who has not married again
例句: The poor woman became a widow after her husband's death.
例句释义: 那个可怜的女人在她丈夫死后就成了寡妇。

英文释义: to put money into a bank account; to put or lay somebody/something down in a particular place
例句: I deposit money in my piggy bank when I can.
例句释义: 当我有钱我会往我的存钱罐里存钱。

英文释义: hair that grows on the chin and cheeks of a man’s face; similar hair that grows on some animals
例句: He likes to touch his beard when he thinks.
例句释义: 他思考的时候喜欢摸自己的胡子。

英文释义: to go slower or make a vehicle go slower using the brake
例句: Not again?! I hate having to brake my car for cows!
例句释义: 不要吧，又来？！我讨厌为了牛刹车！

英文释义: a sudden strong wish or need to do something, without stopping to think about the results; a force or movement of energy that causes something else to react; something that causes somebody/something to do something or to develop and make progress
例句: These things were an impulse buy on November 11th by him.
例句释义: 这些东西是他在“双十一”那天一时冲动买下来的。

英文释义: to order somebody not to do something; to order that something must not be done
例句: We forbid smoking in the restaurant.
例句释义: 餐厅内禁止吸烟。

英文释义: the soft thick mass of hair that grows on the body of some animals; the skin of an animal with the fur still on it, used especially for making clothes; a piece of clothing, especially a coat or jacket, made of real or artificial fur; an artificial material that looks and feels like fur
例句: A fur coat is very warm, but very expensive!
例句释义: 毛皮外套很温暖，但也很昂贵！

详细释义: adj. 残忍的，粗鲁的；严酷的，难以忍受的
英文释义: violent and cruel
例句: This terrorist attack was incredibly brutal!
例句释义: 这次恐怖袭击真的太残忍了！

英文释义: an animal that kills and eats other animals
例句: Tigers, eagles and wolves are all predators.
例句释义: 老虎、鹰和狼都是捕食者。

英文释义: to leave a place, especially to start a trip

英文释义: a thin stick with a sharp point at one end, which is shot from a bow

详细释义: n.同时；其间；  adv.同时；当时；在那当中

英文释义: to send an electronic signal, radio or television broadcast, etc.

详细释义: v.收割（庄稼）；  n.收获，收成

详细释义: v.暗中监视（或侦察）；当间谍；  n.间谍，密探

详细释义: n.（投硬币的）狭缝，狭槽；  v.把……放入狭长开口中，把……纳入
英文释义: a long narrow opening, into which you put or fit something; a position, a time or an opportunity for somebody/something, for example in a list, a programme of events or a series of broadcasts

英文释义: a narrow area of high land along the top of a line of hills; a high pointed area near the top of a mountain; a raised line on the surface of something; the point where two sloping surfaces join; a long narrow area of high pressure in the atmosphere

例句释义: 当管道压力过大时，压力传感器会显示出来。

英文释义: clothes, sheets, etc. that need washing, that are being washed, or that have been washed recently
例句: Doing laundry is part of my housework.
例句释义: 我的家务之一是洗衣服。

详细释义: adj.手工的；手的；手动的；  n.手册；指南
英文释义: operated or controlled by hand rather than automatically or using electricity, etc.
例句: Wow, you can drive a manual transmission car?
例句释义: 哇，你能驾驶手动挡汽车？

详细释义: n. 手枪，信号，发令枪；  v. 用手枪杀死，用手枪伤害
例句: The heroine in this comic book hides a pistol in her handbag.
例句释义: 这本漫画书的女主角把手枪藏在手提包里。

英文释义: connected with the navy of a country
例句: The man in the white uniform is a naval officer.
例句释义: 这个穿着白色制服的人是一名海军军官。

英文释义: a person who makes a formal complaint against somebody in court
例句: The plaintiff accused the defendant of intentional injury.
例句释义: 原告以故意伤害罪控告被告。

英文释义: a word or statement saying sorry for something that has been done wrong or that causes a problem; information that you cannot go to a meeting or must leave early
例句: He is making an apology to his boss.
例句释义: 他在向老板道歉。

例句: The man's endless talking has bored his colleagues to sleep.
例句释义: 这个男人冗长的讲话让同事们都厌烦得想睡觉了。

详细释义: n. 爱人；  adj. 心爱的，所钟爱的
英文释义: somebody you love very much
例句: You are my beloved.
例句释义: 你是我的爱人。

英文释义: a place connected to the Internet, where a company or an organization, or an individual person, puts information
例句: Users visit this website to search for the information they want.
例句释义: 用户访问这个网站来搜索他们想要的信息。

英文释义: to interest and amuse somebody in order to please them
例句: Clowns entertained us at the circus.
例句释义: 在马戏团里，小丑逗我们开心。

英文释义: very strange or unusual
例句: This bizarre creature among the other fish really caught my eye.
例句释义: 在其他鱼当中，这种奇怪的生物引起了我的注意。

详细释义: adv. 在海外；  adj. 海外的
英文释义: to or in a foreign country, especially those separated from your country by the sea or ocean
例句: We export the goods overseas.
例句释义: 我们把货物出口到海外。

详细释义: n. 悼念；致敬；贡品；称赞
英文释义: an act, a statement or a gift that is intended to show your respect or admiration, especially for a dead person
例句: The little girl brought flowers to pay tribute to her grandmother's memory.
例句释义: 小女孩带来一些花，以表达对祖母的哀思。

英文释义: to bring or get something back, especially from a place where it should not be;  to find and get back data or information that has been stored in the memory of a computer; to make a bad situation better; to get back something that was lost
例句: The dog retrieves a ball.
例句释义: 小狗找回了一个球。

详细释义: v. 设计，想出；遗赠（不动产）；  n. 设计，发明，遗赠
英文释义: to invent something new or a new way of doing something
例句: They devised a plan for their company‘s future.
例句释义: 他们制定了公司未来发展计划。

英文释义: a plane that carries and drops bombs
例句: The military bomber dropped bombs on its targets.
例句释义: 军用轰炸机对目标进行狂轰滥炸。

英文释义: to formally suggest that somebody should be chosen for an important role, prize, position, etc.
例句: Five actors were nominated as Best Actor.
例句释义: 这五位男演员都被提名为最佳男主角。

详细释义: vi.讨价还价，谈判；  n.特价商品，便宜货；  vt.经讨价还价成交；  adj.（价格）低廉的
英文释义: something that is bought or sold for a price which is lower than the actual value :something bought or sold at a good price
例句: The old lady is trying to bargain with the seller.
例句释义: 那位老太太试图和商家砍价。

英文释义: having doubts that a claim or statement is true or that something will happen
例句: I'm skeptical that the weasel did not come here merely to extend his greetings.
例句释义: 我怀疑那只黄鼠狼不仅仅是来这里表达问候的。

详细释义: n.监视，细看，详细检查，仔细观察
英文释义: the act of carefully examining something especially in a critical way
例句: The exam was going on under the scrutiny of the teacher.
例句释义: 考试在老师的严格监视下进行。

英文释义: to prevent yourself from having or expressing a feeling or an emotion
例句: She is trying to suppress her anger.
例句释义: 她在努力抑制自己的愤怒。

详细释义: n. 黄铜；黄铜（器）；铜管乐器；【口语】厚脸皮；高级将领官员
英文释义: a bright yellow metal made by mixing copper and zinc; objects made of brass
例句: This tap is made of brass.
例句释义: 这个水龙头是用黄铜做的。

例句: Considering she's only three, she can draw pretty well.
例句释义: 考虑到她只有三岁，她已经画得很好了。

英文释义: having bad luck; caused by bad luck
例句: I’m so unfortunate―why does it only rain on me?
例句释义: 我真不幸，为什么雨只下在我头上？

详细释义: n.锚；（广播电视新闻节目的）主持人
英文释义: a heavy metal object that is attached to a rope or chain and dropped over the side of a ship or boat to keep it in one place
例句: The ship dropped the anchor and hit the shark on its head.
例句释义: 船抛出锚，打到了一只鲨鱼头上。

详细释义: num. 零；  n. 零，零度
例句: I have had zero problems.
例句释义: 我没有问题。

详细释义: v. 提取；取出；摘录；设法得到；  n. 摘录；  v. 索取；  n. 提出物
英文释义: to remove or obtain a substance from something, for example by using an industrial or a chemical process
例句: The rig extracts oil from the ocean floor.
例句释义: 钻探设备从海底提取石油。

英文释义: involving a lot of work or activity done in a short time; extremely thorough; done with a lot of care; (of methods of farming) aimed at producing as much food as possible using as little land or as little money as possible
例句: The intensive study for the college entrance exam made him exhausted.
例句释义: 高考强化训练让他精疲力竭。

英文释义: to give information about somebody/something to an enemy
例句: He betrayed his partner by selling the secret documents to others.
例句释义: 他背叛了合作伙伴，把这些秘密文件卖给了其他人。

英文释义: the quality of always behaving in the same way or of having the same opinions, standard, etc.; the quality of being consistent
例句: His consistency is remarkable, scoring points in every single game!
例句释义: 他的表现特别稳定，每场比赛都得分！

详细释义: n. 官僚主义；政府机构
英文释义: the system of official rules and ways of doing things that a government or an organization has, especially when these seem to be too complicated
例句: The bureaucracy always makes people go through unnecessary procedures.
例句释义: 官僚主义总是让人们走一些不必要的程序。

英文释义: quick at learning and understanding things
例句: The clever boy can figure out any difficult math problem.
例句释义: 这个男孩聪明极了，可以解出很难的数学题。

英文释义: that allows information to be passed continuously and in both directions between a computer and the person who uses it.
例句: This interactive robot is playing a game with the girl.
例句释义: 这个交互机器人正在和女孩玩游戏。

详细释义: adj.艰巨的，具有挑战性的；  v.挑战（challenge的现在分词）
英文释义: difficult in an interesting way that tests your ability
例句: He wants to try some challenging sports.
例句释义: 他想尝试一些具有挑战性的运动。

英文释义: the people who are attending a religious service
例句: The congregation of tourists are following the tour guide into the scenic area.
例句释义: 在导游的带领下，游客们正在进入景区。

英文释义: having a very pleasant taste or smell; extremely pleasant or enjoyable
例句: The rice noodles my brother is cooking look so delicious!
例句释义: 我哥哥煮的米粉看起来真美味！

详细释义: adv.在（船、飞机、火车、公共汽车）上；  prep.在（船、火车、公共汽车、飞机）上
英文释义: on or onto a ship, plane, bus or train
例句: In Thailand, fishers often cook and have meals aboard their boats.
例句释义: 在泰国，渔民们经常在船上做饭和用餐。

英文释义: if people, plants, animals, etc. reproduce or reproduce themselves, they produce young
例句: Crocodiles reproduce by laying eggs on land.
例句释义: 鳄鱼通过在陆地上产卵来繁殖后代。

英文释义: a strong feeling of sympathy for people who are suffering and a desire to help them
例句: The man gave the girl his shoes because he had great compassion.
例句释义: 男子把鞋给了小女孩，因为他富有同情心。

英文释义: a long thin creature with no bones or legs, that lives in soil; the young form of an insect when it looks like a short worm
例句: Worms make good fish food.
例句释义: 蠕虫能做很好的鱼食。

英文释义: improving a situation; having a helpful or useful effect
例句: Eating nutritious food and exercising are beneficial to our health.
例句释义: 吃有营养的食物和锻炼身体对我们的健康有益。

详细释义: adj.尴尬的；笨拙的；不方便的
英文释义: making you feel embarrassed
例句: It's so awkward when the boy tore a hole on his pants.
例句释义: 当男孩把裤子扯了个洞时，场面十分尴尬。

英文释义: mentioned in stories from ancient times
例句: According to one Chinese myth, human beings were created by the legendary Nuwa.
例句释义: 根据一个中国神话，人类是由传说中的女娲创造的。

详细释义: n. 并发症；（新出现的）困难，难题
英文释义: a thing that makes a situation more complicated or difficult
例句: Vomit is a common complication of pregnancy.
例句释义: 呕吐是妊娠期间一种常见的并发症。

英文释义: the work of repairing and cleaning an old building, a painting, etc. so that its condition is as good as it originally was
例句: The restoration of the temple to its former glory will take a long while.
例句释义: 要使这座寺庙恢复往日的辉煌还需要很长时间。

英文释义: a person who writes music, especially classical music
例句: The composer has difficulty writing this piece.
例句释义: 作曲家在写这首曲子时遇到了困难。

英文释义: the act of giving up something or doing something in order to reach agreement
例句: The mother made a concession and allowed the boy to continue watching TV.
例句释义: 妈妈让步了，同意让小男孩再多看一会儿电视。

英文释义: civilians trained as soldiers but not part of the regular army

例句释义: 民兵们为了国家而战。

英文释义: known to be real and genuine and not a copy
例句: This diamond isn't fake―I'm sure it's authentic.
例句释义: 这颗钻石不是假的――我敢保证它是真的！

英文释义: the period of time when somebody holds an important job, especially a political one; the act of holding an important job
例句: This CEO's tenure lasted 14 full years in the electronics company.
例句释义: 这家电子公司的CEO足足有14年的任期。

英文释义: the act of rejecting something
例句: I found her rejection of our food extremely rude.
例句释义: 我认为她拒绝我们的食物是非常无礼的。

英文释义: a person who steals something
例句: A thief is stealing the girl's phone.
例句释义: 一个小偷正在偷这个女孩的手机。

英文释义: a round roof with a circular base; a thing or a building shaped like a dome
例句: This building has a large glass dome at the top of it.
例句释义: 这个建筑的顶部有一个大大的玻璃圆顶。

详细释义: adj. 不足够的，不充分的，不适当的

例句: The small amount of food is inadequate for them.

详细释义: n. 有锁的橱柜，有锁的存物柜
英文释义: a small cupboard that can be locked, where you can leave your clothes, bags, etc. while you play a sport or go somewhere
例句: I unlock my locker with a key.
例句释义: 我用钥匙打开了柜子。

详细释义: adj.编辑的，编者的；  n.（报刊的）社论
英文释义: an important article in a newspaper, that expresses the editor’s opinion about an item of news or an issue; in the US also a comment on radio or television that expresses the opinion of the station or network
例句: The man is doing some editorial work for this book.
例句释义: 这个人在为这本书做一些编辑工作。

例句: Leaves turn yellow in the autumn.
例句释义: 秋天，叶子都变黄了。

英文释义: having or showing true and constant support or loyalty
例句: Dogs are the most faithful, loyal pets you can have.
例句释义: 狗是你最忠实的宠物。

详细释义: n.（企业等的）合并；吸收合并（如刑法中重罪吸收轻罪）
英文释义: the act of joining two or more organizations or businesses into one
例句: A merger between our companies will benefit all our shareholders.
例句释义: 我们企业之间的合并会使双方股东受益。

详细释义: v. （鬼，魂）常出没于；  n. 常去的地方
英文释义: if the ghost of a dead person haunts a place, people say that they have seen it there
例句: Ghosts are believed to haunt old places.
例句释义: 人们相信鬼魂经常出没于古旧的场所。

详细释义: n.原油；  adj.天然的；粗糙的；粗鲁的；简陋的
英文释义: oil in its natural state, before it has been treated with chemicals
例句: The Middle East is rich in crude oil.
例句释义: 中东是一个原油丰富的地区。

英文释义: not clear in a person’s mind; not having or giving enough information or details about something; (of a person’s behaviour) suggesting a lack of clear thought or attention; not having a clear shape
例句: He didn't understand her vague words.
例句释义: 他没有理解女孩含糊的话语。

英文释义: a person who buys and sells things as a job
例句: The market trader is selling some home-grown vegetables.
例句释义: 集市商贩正在卖自家种的蔬菜。

详细释义: v. 使人想起；唤起；引起
英文释义: to bring a feeling, a memory or an image into your mind
例句: This picture evokes feelings of summer.
例句释义: 这张照片唤起了夏天的感觉。

英文释义: the act or process of finishing something; the state of being finished and complete;  the formal act of completing the sale of property, for example the sale of a house
例句: The final piece of the jigsaw puzzle would see its completion.
例句释义: 把最后一块放上去，这幅拼图就完成了。

详细释义: n. 静脉；血管；叶脉；纹理；迹象
英文释义: any of the tubes that carry blood from all parts of the body towards the heart
例句: The doctor restricts the blood flow in order to see the patient's veins more clearly.
例句释义: 医生限制了血液的流动，以便更清楚地看到病人的静脉。

详细释义: n.伤疤，伤痕；内心创伤；  v.给……留下伤痕
英文释义: a mark that is left on the skin after a wound has healed
例句: He has a scar on his forehead.
例句释义: 他的前额有一道疤。
