英文释义: to admit that you have been defeated and want to stop fighting; to allow yourself to be caught, taken prisoner, etc.
例句: Under such huge pressure, she finally surrendered.
例句释义: 在巨大的压力下，她不得不投降。

详细释义: vi.汹涌；激增；  n.波涛汹涌
英文释义: to move very quickly and suddenly in a particular direction
例句: The water surges over the road.
例句释义: 水汹涌着淹没了路面。

详细释义: adj. 肯定的，积极的；  n. 肯定语，赞成的一方
英文释义: an affirmative word or reply means ‘yes’ or expresses agreement
例句: "Can you do the job, penguin?" "Affirmative, captain."
例句释义: ”你能完成这项工作吗，企鹅？“ “肯定的，船长。”

英文释义: to look closely at something/somebody, especially to check that everything is as it should be
例句: He is here to inspect the shop for a health test.
例句释义: 他正在对店铺进行卫生检查。

详细释义: n.（广播员对球赛等的）实况报道，（电影的）解说词；评论，评论文章
英文释义: a spoken description of an event that is given while it is happening, especially on the radio or television
例句: People love this man's commentary on soccer games.
例句释义: 人们非常喜欢这个人对足球比赛的解说。

英文释义: a person who works on a ship as a member of the crew; a person who sails a boat
例句: The sailor has been out to sea for several months.
例句释义: 水手已经出海几个月了。

英文释义: a person who supports and admires a particular person or set of ideas; a person who does things after somebody else has done them first
例句: Followers walk behind and leaders stand in front.
例句释义: 追随者走在后面，领袖走在前面。

英文释义: connected with an empire; connected with the system for measuring length, weight and volume using pounds, inches, etc.
例句: The Forbidden City is an imperial palace.
例句释义: 紫禁城是一座帝王宫殿。

英文释义: the system by which a vehicle is supported on its wheels and which makes it more comfortable to ride in when the road surface is not even
例句: In outer space, things are in a state of suspension.
例句释义: 在外太空，东西处于悬浮状态。

英文释义: a social or business visitor
例句: He doesn't know who the caller is.
例句释义: 他不知道打电话来的人是谁。

英文释义: to provide something good to balance or reduce the bad effects of damage, loss, etc.; to pay somebody money because they have suffered some damage, loss, injury, etc.
例句: He should be compensated for his work-related injury.
例句释义: 他应该得到工伤赔偿。

英文释义: the action or process of producing or making something
例句: The making of cakes is a complicated process.
例句释义: 蛋糕的制作是一个复杂的过程。

英文释义: the remains of an animal or a plant which have become hard and turned into rock
例句: There is a fossil of an ancient fish embedded in the ground.
例句释义: 地里有一块古代鱼类的化石。

详细释义: adj.极美妙的，令人印象深刻的
英文释义: extremely attractive or impressive
例句: This house has a stunning view of the sunset.
例句释义: 这栋房子可以看到极美妙的日落。

详细释义: v.（鸟、直升机）盘旋，翱翔；（人）逗留在附近，徘徊
英文释义: (of birds, helicopters, etc.) to stay in the air in one place
例句: The spaceship is hovering over the water.
例句释义: 宇宙飞船正在水面上盘旋。

英文释义: not suitable or appropriate in a particular situation
例句: It seems both fish tanks are inappropriate for the fish.
例句释义: 似乎两个鱼缸对于鱼来说都不太合适。

英文释义: capable of doing what it is intended to do
例句: She deemed the subway a viable alternative option for when the traffic was bad.
例句释义: 她认为在交通拥挤的时候，乘地铁是一个可行的选择。

详细释义: n. 光线；射线；  v. 放射，照射
英文释义: one of the lines of light that you can see coming from an object
例句: A single ray of light illuminates the stage.
例句释义: 一束光照亮舞台。

英文释义: a man who rides a horse and whose job is to take care of cows or horses especially in the western U.S.
例句: The three men riding on their horses are cowboys.
例句释义: 这三个骑马的男人是牛仔。

英文释义: a simple picture that is drawn quickly and does not have many details; a short report or story that gives only basic details about something; a short funny scene on television, in the theatre, etc.
例句: The artist is doing a sketch of the living room.
例句释义: 这位画家正在画一幅客厅的素描。

英文释义: to make something, especially butter, pure by heating it
例句: The son has to clarify what he wrote for his father.
例句释义: 儿子需要把他写的东西给爸爸阐明。

详细释义: n. 闲谈，聊天；  v. 闲谈，聊天
英文释义: to talk in a friendly informal way to somebody
例句: They usually have a chat while drinking coffee.
例句释义: 他们通常在喝咖啡时闲聊。

英文释义: too many to be counted :very many
例句: There are countless stars in the night sky.
例句释义: 夜空中有无数的星星。

英文释义: brown coins that do not have much value
例句: Chinese ancient coins were made of copper.
例句释义: 中国古代钱币是铜做的。

英文释义: going to happen soon
例句: The beach is empty due to the upcoming storm.
例句释义: 由于风暴将至，海滩空无一人。

英文释义: a person who is being taught, especially a child in a school
例句: The pupils are walking to school.
例句释义: 小学生们走路去学校。

英文释义: to try very hard to achieve something
例句: They are all striving for a good future and life.
例句释义: 他们都在为美好的未来和生活而奋斗。

英文释义: to fail to take care of somebody/something
例句: The parents neglect their child and keep fighting.
例句释义: 那对父母忽视了他们的孩子，只顾着一直吵架。

英文释义: a separate room or area in a hospital for people with the same type of medical condition
例句: The patients lie on the beds in the ward.
例句释义: 病人躺在病房的床上。

英文释义: the activity of fighting a war, especially using particular weapons or methods
例句: Violent warfare is taking place in this area.
例句释义: 这个地区正爆发着一场激烈的战争。

详细释义: adj. 中世纪的，中古（时代）的
英文释义: connected with the Middle Ages (about AD?1000 to AD?1450)
例句: Castles and knights were symbols of the medieval times.
例句释义: 城堡和骑士是中世纪的象征。

英文释义: to steal money or property from a person or place
例句: A thief just robbed her in the park.
例句释义: 小偷刚在公园打劫了她。

英文释义: someone (especially a child) who learns (as from a teacher) or takes up knowledge or beliefs
例句: This man is a language learner―he loves to learn languages!
例句释义: 这个男人是个语言学习者――他喜欢学习语言！

详细释义: n.巨响；重击；  v.发出砰的一声；重击；猛敲；砰地关上
英文释义: a sudden loud noise
例句: After a gust of wind, the door was suddenly shut with a bang.
例句释义: 一阵风过后，门突然关上，发出一声巨响。

详细释义: n. 绳结，结合，树的节；  v. 打结
英文释义: a join made by tying together two pieces or ends of string, rope, etc.; a hard round spot in a piece of wood where there was once a branch; a small group of people standing close together
例句: In the Stone Age people tied knots in ropes to count.
例句释义: 在石器时代人们曾在绳子上打结来计数。

英文释义: (in stories) a large aggressive animal with wings and a long tail, that can breathe out fire; a woman who behaves in an aggressive and frightening way
例句: Look! This dragon can breathe fire!
例句释义: 看，这条龙会喷火！

英文释义: the act or process of supporting a cause or proposal :the act or process of advocating something
例句: His advocacy of environmental protection is echoed by many people across the globe.
例句释义: 他的环保主张得到了全球范围内许多人的响应。

详细释义: v. （使）倾斜；  n. 倾斜，斜坡
英文释义: to move, or make something move, into a position with one side or end higher than the other
例句: The dog tilted its head to the side.
例句释义: 狗狗把头侧向一边。

详细释义: adj. 金钱的；货币的，金融的
英文释义: connected with money, especially all the money in a country
例句: He was very good with monetary matters and always saved his money.
例句释义: 他很会理财，总是把钱存起来。

英文释义: the state of being successful, especially in making money
例句: The prosperity of the city is evident from this busy nighttime scene.
例句释义: 这忙碌的夜景显示着这座城市的繁荣。

详细释义: n. 抗生素；  adj. 抗菌的
英文释义: a substance, for example penicillin, that can destroy or prevent the growth of bacteria and cure infections
例句: These pills are common antibiotics.
例句释义: 这些药是常见的抗生素。

英文释义: a person who has made or invented a particular thing
例句: This sculpture's creator is trying to present what she envisioned in her mind.
例句释义: 这座雕塑的创造者正试图呈现出她脑海中想象的画面。

详细释义: vt.积攒；  vi.聚积，（数量）逐渐增加
英文释义: to gradually get more and more of something over a period of time
例句: He accumulates wealth for future use.
例句释义: 他积累财富以供将来使用。

英文释义: a scientist who studies biology
例句: Zoologists, botanists and microbiologists are all kinds of biologists.
例句释义: 动物学家、植物学家和微生物学家都是生物学家。

英文释义: connected with elections
例句: The ballot, ballot box, and candidate are all associated with electoral activities.
例句释义: 选票、投票箱和候选人都与选举活动有关。

英文释义: a part of the sea or a river where fish are caught in large quantities
例句: The fishery is a part of the sea where fish are caught in large numbers.
例句释义: 渔场属于海的一部分，在那儿能捕获大量的鱼。

英文释义: to officially charge somebody with a crime in court
例句: He was prosecuted because of owing his friends' money.
例句释义: 他因为欠朋友钱而被起诉。

英文释义: to express or represent an idea or a quality
例句: The lotus flower embodies purity and integrity.
例句释义: 莲花象征着清白和正直。

英文释义: a piece of thick material like a small carpet that is used for covering or decorating part of a floor
例句: Wow, this black rug looks very soft!
例句释义: 哇，这张黑色的地毯看起来好柔软！

英文释义: not interesting or exciting
例句: The TV show is so dull that makes him want to sleep.
例句释义: 这档电视节目很无趣，让他想睡觉。

英文释义: to become involved in a situation in order to improve or help it; to exist between two events or places; to happen in a way that delays something or prevents it from happening
例句: They only stopped fighting when the teacher intervened.
例句释义: 当老师介入时，他们才停止打架。

详细释义: n.（警察）突击搜捕；袭击；  vt.突袭，偷袭；劫掠；攫取； 突击搜捕
英文释义: a surprise visit by the police looking for criminals or for illegal goods or drugs
例句: The policemen are going to launch a raid to find the suspect.
例句释义: 为了找到嫌疑人，警察准备展开突击搜捕。

详细释义: vi.发光；  n.喜悦，满足的心情
英文释义: (especially of something hot or warm) to produce a dull, steady light; (of a person’s body or face) to look or feel warm or pink, especially after exercise or because of excitement, embarrassment, etc.; to appear a strong, warm colour
例句: The burning coals glow in the dark.
例句释义: 燃烧的煤炭在黑暗中发出光亮。

详细释义: n. 王冠，冕；花冠；  v. 加冕
英文释义: an object in the shape of a circle, usually made of gold and precious stones, that a king or queen wears on his or her head on official occasions
例句: The man is about to put on his crown.
例句释义: 这个男人正要戴上他的王冠。

详细释义: adj.假的，伪造的；  n.假货，赝品；  v.冒充，假装
英文释义: not genuine; appearing to be something it is not
例句: Do you know which rabbit is the fake one?
例句释义: 你知道哪一只小兔子是假的吗？

英文释义: a picture or drawing in a book, magazine, etc.
例句: I need an illustration of a pirate ship for my children's book.
例句释义: 我写的儿童书需要一幅海盗船的插图。

英文释义: a sea creature with a hard shell, eight legs and two pincers (= curved and pointed arms for catching and holding things). Crabs move sideways on land.
例句: Crab is one of my favorite seafoods.
例句释义: 螃蟹是我最喜欢的海鲜之一。

详细释义: vi. 爬行；毛发直竖；  n. 毛骨悚然的感觉
英文释义: (of people or animals) to move slowly, quietly and carefully, because you do not want to be seen or heard
例句: The cat is slowly creeping towards her.
例句释义: 那只猫慢慢地悄悄爬向她。

英文释义: having the qualities that deserve somebody/something; having qualities that deserve your respect, attention or admiration
例句: You did a great job and are worthy of the prize you received.
例句释义: 你工作非常出色，值得你所获得的奖赏。

例句: The girl is very satisfied with the pizza.
例句释义: 这个女孩对披萨很满意。

英文释义: a chemical element. Hydrogen is a gas that is the lightest of all the elements. It combines with oxygen to form water.
例句: The balloons are filled with hydrogen in order to ascend to the air.
例句释义: 为了让气球飞到空中，我们给气球充的是氢气。

英文释义: an economic system in which a country’s businesses and industry are controlled and run for profit by private owners rather than by the government
例句: Capitalism works for making money, but it doesn't help the poor very much.
例句释义: 资本主义对赚钱有用，但却不能帮助穷人。

英文释义: the business of managing or working on a farm

英文释义: how likely something is to happen; (mathematics) a ratio showing the chances that a particular thing will happen

例句: Shanxi Province is famous for its vinegar.
例句释义: 山西省以醋闻名。

详细释义: adj.顾问的，咨询的；  n.报告

例句释义: 她以顾问的身份工作。如果你有任何问题，你可以向她寻求建议。

例句: The organizer must make sure that everything is well-prepared for the party.
例句释义: 组织者必须确保聚会中的所有事情都准备妥当。

详细释义: v. 治疗；恢复；补救；  n. 治疗；补救；矫正
英文释义: to relieve or cure (a disease, illness, etc) by or as if by a remedy
例句: He took some pills to remedy his cough.
例句释义: 他吃了些药来治疗咳嗽。

英文释义: a copy of a book, piece of music, etc. before it has been printed
例句: This is the manuscript of a famous writer.

英文释义: the condition of not being able to do something :lack of ability
例句: He has an inability to distinguish red from green.

英文释义: to break something, or to be broken, violently and noisily into many pieces; to move with a lot of force against something solid; to make something do this; to hit something very hard and break it, in order to get through it; to hit something/somebody very hard; to destroy, defeat or put an end to something/somebody; to crash a vehicle
例句: The football smashed the glass into pieces.
例句释义: 这个足球把玻璃撞成了碎片。

英文释义: (of a person) believing that something you want will happen

例句: They had a disagreement about what to build with their toys.
例句释义: 他们在用这些积木造什么上产生了分歧。

详细释义: adj.精致的，花哨的；  n.喜爱；  v.想象，幻想
英文释义: to believe or imagine something
例句: This fancy gold tableware must have been so expensive!
例句释义: 这套华丽的金色餐具肯定很贵！

例句释义: 统一发型是军训的强制性要求。

英文释义: principles concerning right and wrong or good and bad behaviour; the degree to which something is right or wrong, good or bad, etc. according to moral principles

例句: Is the water in this swimming pool deep enough to dive into?
例句释义: 这个游泳池的水深到能跳水吗？

例句释义: 苏打水搭配柠檬和薄荷，十分完美。

例句释义: 这家科技公司在电子广告牌上为他们最新款的手机做广告。

详细释义: n. 低音电吉他；鲈鱼；男低音；低音部分；低音符
英文释义: an electric guitar that plays very low notes
例句: I am the bass player in my band.
例句释义: 我是乐队里的低音电吉他手。

例句释义: 我把备忘录放得到处都是，以提醒自己必须做的事。

英文释义: to make a person or an animal unconscious for a short time, especially by hitting them on the head; to surprise or shock somebody so much that they cannot think clearly or speak; to impress somebody very much
例句: The man was wide-eyed and stunned.
例句释义: 这个男人眼睛睁得大大的，同时愣住了。

英文释义: things that are considered useless or of little value
例句: What a mess! Must get rid of all this smelly junk.
例句释义: 真是一团糟！必须把这些发臭的垃圾清扫出去。

例句: The two men are devoted to performing well in their careers.

详细释义: vt.生产，制造；  n.（复数）产品

例句: This factory uses machines to manufacture goods.
例句释义: 这家工厂用机器制造产品。

例句: The girl sent her mother a card and flowers to show her deep affection.
例句释义: 女孩送了妈妈一张卡片和鲜花来表达自己对她深深的感情。

详细释义: adj.成熟的；  vt.使成熟；  vi.成熟

例句: The lion is now mature enough to go hunting alone.
例句释义: 这头狮子现在已经成熟到可以独自捕猎了。

例句: The stamp on the pig shows the good quality of it.
例句释义: 猪身上盖的章表示猪的质量合格。

英文释义: a person who studies or writes about philosophy
例句: This is a statue of an ancient Greek philosopher.
例句释义: 这是一尊古希腊哲学家的雕塑。

详细释义: v. 紧握；抓住；  n. 抓住；离合器
英文释义: to hold somebody/something tightly

例句释义: 他紧紧抓住他的红包，保持警惕。

英文释义: an occasion when a vehicle or machine stops working
例句: His old car had a breakdown on the road.
例句释义: 他的旧车在路上出现了故障。

英文释义: to hide somebody/something
例句: I use this mask to conceal my face.
例句释义: 我用面具来隐藏我的脸。

英文释义: either of the two organs in the body that remove waste products from the blood and produce urine; the kidneys of some animals that are cooked and eaten
例句: Kidneys are vital organs in our bodies.
例句释义: 肾脏是我们体内的重要器官。

英文释义: a small bunch of hair that forms a curved or round shape; the tendency of hair to form curls
例句: Her blonde curls are very beautiful.
例句释义: 她金色的卷发十分好看。

英文释义: the quality of being good; the part of something that has a useful effect on somebody/something, especially somebody’s health

例句释义: 照顾受伤的小猫展现了她善良的一面。

英文释义: (uncountable) the scientific study of the earth's surface, physical features, divisions, products, population, etc.
例句: Geography can help us know the world better.
例句释义: 学习地理可以让我们更好地了解世界。

英文释义: what happens to somebody or what will happen to them in the future, especially things that they cannot change or avoid; the power believed to control events
例句: It was destiny that she would kiss the frog and it would become the prince.
例句释义: 公主亲了青蛙，然后它变成了王子，这一切都是宿命。

英文释义: to a remarkably degree or extent
例句: Remarkably, the food in the shabby restaurant was very good!
例句释义: 出乎意料的是，这家破旧餐馆的饭菜非常美味！

详细释义: n.读写能力；识字；有文化；教养
英文释义: the ability to read and write
例句: Chinese teachers mainly cultivate the students' literacy.
例句释义: 语文老师主要培养孩子的读写能力。

详细释义: n. 出租汽车；  v. (飞机) 缓慢滑行
英文释义: a car with a driver that you pay to take you somewhere. Taxis usually have meters which show how much money you have to pay.
例句: The man is waiting for a taxi.
例句释义: 这位男士正等着出租车。

详细释义: v. 漏；泄露；  n. 漏洞
英文释义: to allow liquid or gas to get in or out through a small hole or crack; (of a liquid or gas) to get in or out through a small hole or crack in something
例句: The pipe leaks and the water flows everywhere.
例句释义: 水管漏水，水流得到处都是。

详细释义: n. 独唱；  adj. 独奏的
英文释义: a piece of music, dance or entertainment performed by only one person
例句: The singer is performing a solo on the stage.
例句释义: 这位歌手正在舞台上独唱。

详细释义: adj.澳大利亚的；澳大利亚人的；  n.澳大利亚人
英文释义: belonging or relating to Australia, or to its people or culture
例句: Kangaroos are native Australian animals.
例句释义: 袋鼠是澳大利亚的本地动物。

例句: In this country, 50 trillion notes are commonly seen.
例句释义: 在这个国家，五十万亿面值的纸币是很常见的。

英文释义: the group of people who are responsible for making the laws in some kinds of their government
例句: These are the Houses of Parliament in London.
例句释义: 这是伦敦的议会大厦。

详细释义: n. 兽群，牧群；  v. 放牧，群集
英文释义: a group of animals of the same type that live and feed together
例句: Look! There is a herd of sheep!
例句释义: 看！这有一群羊！

详细释义: n. 温室；镶有玻璃的座舱
英文释义: a building with glass sides and a glass roof for growing plants in
例句: Greenhouses are the best place to grow plants quickly.
例句释义: 温室是快速栽种植物的最好地方。

英文释义: having or showing strong feelings of enthusiasm for something or belief in something
例句: He always gets so passionate while playing the guitar.
例句释义: 弹吉他的时候，他总是充满了激情。

详细释义: n. （时间、金钱等的）花费，支出，消耗

例句释义: 这张饼状图显示了我上个月的所有支出。

详细释义: v. 探测，探索；  n. 探针，探测器
英文释义: to touch, examine or look for something, especially with a long thin instrument; to ask questions in order to find out secret or hidden information about somebody/something
例句: He held a device to probe for the location of the gold.

详细释义: n. 管道；  vt. 用管道输送
英文释义: a series of pipes that are usually underground and are used for carrying oil, gas, etc. over long distances
例句: This pipeline will carry oil to another country.
例句释义: 管道将把石油运输到另一个国家。

详细释义: n. 精神病医生；精神病学家
英文释义: a doctor who studies and treats mental illnesses
例句: The psychiatrist is recording her patient's problems.
例句释义: 精神病医生正在记录病人的问题。

英文释义: the smallest particle (1) of a chemical element that can exist
例句: Two hydrogen atoms combine with one oxygen atom to form a water molecule.
例句释义: 两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合形成一个水分子。

英文释义: a small meal or amount of food, usually eaten in a hurry
例句: There are some snacks for you to eat after dinner.
例句释义: 这儿有一些零食供你晚餐后享用。

英文释义: the last part of a story, film/movie, etc.; the final part of something
例句: The film has a happy ending.
例句释义: 这部电影有一个完美的结局。

英文释义: a bird or an animal that moves from one place to another according to the season
例句: A wild goose is a kind of migrant bird which flies to different habitats in different seasons.
例句释义: 大雁是一种候鸟，它们在不同的季节飞向不同的栖息地。

英文释义: very pleasant or attractive
例句: The princess in that movie was very charming.
例句释义: 那部电影里的公主很迷人。

详细释义: n. 增补，补充物，保健品；  v. 补充
英文释义: a thing that is added to something else to improve or complete it; a pill that you take or a special kind of food that you eat in order to improve your health; a book or a section at the end of a book that gives extra information or deals with a special subject
例句: You should take these herbal supplements once a day.
例句释义: 你应该一天服用一次这些草本保健品。

英文释义: colored liquid that is used for writing or printing
例句: I used ink to write some nice Spring Festival wishes.
例句释义: 我用墨水写了些春节祝福。

详细释义: n.悲伤，痛苦，忧虑；  vt.使悲伤
英文释义: a feeling of great worry or unhappiness; great suffering
例句: He is in distress because of the stressful work.
例句释义: 充满压力的工作让他觉得痛苦。

英文释义: the ability to do something well; a skill that you need in a particular job or for a particular task
例句: The girl showed her competence on stage and received an award for her performance.
例句释义: 女孩在舞台上展现了自己的能力，并且获了奖。

详细释义: n.适应，适应性的变化；改编，改写本
英文释义: a change in a plant or animal that makes it better able to live in a particular place or situation
例句: Arctic foxes changing color seasonally is an example of adaptation to the environment.
例句释义: 北极狐季节性的变色是适应环境的一个例子。

英文释义: a strong and harmful need to regularly have something (such as a drug) or do something (such as gamble)
例句: His addiction to alcohol gradually deepened.
例句释义: 他的酒瘾越来越大了。

详细释义: v. 发誓，保证，以…抵押，向…祝酒；  n. 保证，誓言
英文释义: to formally promise to give or do something; to make somebody or yourself formally promise to do something; to leave something with somebody as a pledge (2)
例句: They pledge that they will dedicate themselves to their jobs.
例句释义: 他们保证自己会敬业。

英文释义: a theory or a group of ideas about how something should be done, made, or thought about
例句: This picture showed the basic paradigm of the family tree.
例句释义: 这张图展示了家系图的基本范例。

详细释义: n.纪念像，纪念物，纪念碑，纪念仪式；  adj.记忆的
英文释义: a statue, stone, etc. that is built in order to remind people of an important past event or of a famous person who has died; a thing that will continue to remind people of somebody/something
例句: The memorial of Confucius is built to remind us of his achievements.
例句释义: 修建孔子纪念像是为了让我们记住他的成就。

英文释义: a system, especially in a society or an organization, in which people are organized into different levels of importance from highest to lowest; the group of people in control of a large organization or institution
例句: There is usually a rigid hierarchy in most large corporations.
例句释义: 很多大公司都有严格的等级制度。

英文释义: to cause (someone or something) to become sick or affected by disease
例句: He was infected with the cold by his colleague.
例句释义: 他被同事传染了感冒。

详细释义: adv.向后地；  adj.落后的；向后的，倒行的
英文释义: towards a place or position that is behind
例句: The little boy went backward on the beach.
例句释义: 那个小男孩在沙滩上倒着走。

英文释义: to make somebody feel upset because of something you say or do that is rude or embarrassing; to seem unpleasant to somebody; to be against what people believe is morally right
例句: The boy's speculation about her age offended her.
例句释义: 男孩关于她年龄的猜想冒犯到了她。

英文释义: physical desire for food
例句: Wow, what a huge appetite you have!
例句释义: 天哪，你的胃口真大！

英文释义: feeling or showing concern about someone who is in a bad situation; having or showing feelings of sympathy; showing that you approve of somebody/something or that you share their views and are willing to support them; easy to like
例句: The boy was very sympathetic to his friend who just dropped her ice cream.
例句释义: 这个男孩非常同情刚刚弄掉自己冰激凌的朋友。

英文释义: the process of changing or improving the condition of something or the way it works; the process of putting something back into the state it was in before
例句: Reconstruction took place rapidly in the old city.
例句释义: 旧城改造进行得很快。

英文释义: a thin rubber covering that a man wears over his penis during sex to stop a woman from becoming pregnant or to protect against disease
例句: Don't forget to wear condoms before having sex.
例句释义: 进行性行为之前，请记得戴上安全套。

英文释义: unfriendly or aggressive feelings or behaviour
例句: The dog's fierce look shows its hostility.
例句释义: 狗狗一脸凶相，满是敌意。

英文释义: in a way that lasts or is intended to last or be used only for a short time; in a way that is not permanent
例句: She will live here temporarily before moving into her new house.
例句释义: 在搬进新家前她会在这里暂时住一段时间。

英文释义: a person who is watching an event, especially a sports event
例句: Thousands of spectators watched the tennis match.
例句释义: 成千上万的观众观看了这场网球比赛。

详细释义: v.流血；散开；使……抽干；  n.出血
英文释义: to lose blood, especially from a wound or an injury
例句: "I may bleed to death", the watermelon's last words.
例句释义: “我可能要流血身亡了”，西瓜哥的遗言。

英文释义: a mass of ice and dust that moves around the sun and looks like a bright star with a tail
例句: The comet is approaching the sun.
例句释义: 彗星正在向太阳靠近。

英文释义: a small group of musicians, dancers or actors who perform together
例句: This is an ensemble of young musicians.
例句释义: 这是一个由年轻音乐家组成的乐团。

详细释义: v.呛，噎，（使）窒息；  n.窒息，噎住
英文释义: to be unable to breathe because the passage to your lungs is blocked or you cannot get enough air; to make somebody unable to breathe
例句: She was choking while drinking water.
例句释义: 她喝水的时候呛着了。

英文释义: (abbreviation S, St) a person that the Christian Church recognizes as being very holy, because of the way they have lived or died
例句: Saints are often depicted with a circle of light above them to show their holiness.
例句释义: 圣人头上常常被画上光环来显示其神圣。

详细释义: n. 鸡尾酒；餐前开胃小吃；混合物
英文释义: a drink usually made from a mixture of one or more spirits (= strong alcoholic drinks) and fruit juice. It can also be made without alcohol
例句: Colorful cocktails are served on the table.
例句释义: 桌上摆满了五颜六色的鸡尾酒。

详细释义: adv.作为兼职；  adj.部分时间的
英文释义: for part of the day or week in which people work
例句: During the day I go to school; at night, I work part-time as a waiter.
例句释义: 白天我去学校；晚上我兼职做服务员。

英文释义: a small round green seed, eaten as a vegetable. Several peas grow together inside a long thin pod on a climbing plant also called a pea.
例句: Look how fresh and green these peas are!
例句释义: 看，这些豌豆多新鲜、多翠绿呀！

英文释义: a chemical used for killing pests, especially insects
例句: Farmers will spray pesticides to prevent crops from being eaten by insects.
例句释义: 农民会喷洒农药以防止昆虫侵害庄稼。

英文释义: a person who is chosen or elected to represent the views of a group of people and vote and make decisions for them
例句: Delegates from both nations signed the peace agreement.
例句释义: 两个国家的代表签订了和平协议。

详细释义: v.颤抖，哆嗦；颤动，摇晃；  n.颤抖，战栗
英文释义: to shake in a way that you cannot control, especially because you are very nervous, excited, frightened, etc.
例句: The boy is trembling in the cold weather.
例句释义: 这个男孩在寒冷的天气里冻得直发抖。

英文释义: the act of keeping something in its original state or in good condition; the act of making sure that something is kept; the degree to which something has not been changed or damaged by age, weather, etc.
例句: Putting food into a fridge is a good way to ensure food preservation.
例句释义: 把食物放进冰箱是一个保存食物的好方法。

英文释义: being careful about what you say or do, especially to avoid danger or mistakes; not taking any risks
例句: The maid is very cautious not to make a mistake in front of the empress.
例句释义: 这个丫鬟在皇后面前非常谨慎，不敢犯任何错误。

英文释义: the act or process of moving or turning around a central point; the act of regularly changing the thing that is being used in a particular situation, or of changing the person who does a particular job
例句: The fan's rotation is what creates a cool breeze in the room.
例句释义: 正是风扇的旋转给室内创造了凉爽的微风。

英文释义: cheap enough that people can afford to buy it or pay it
例句: I have 3,000 yuan, so this smartphone is affordable for me.
例句释义: 我有3000元钱，所以这款智能手机我买得起。

详细释义: n.偏见，成见；损害，侵害；  vt.使抱有偏见
英文释义: an unfair feeling of dislike for a person or group because of race, sex, religion, etc.
例句: The other elephants held a prejudice against him because of his giant ears.
例句释义: 其他大象因他的大耳朵而对其抱有偏见。

详细释义: n. 合格证书，文凭；证明，证明书
英文释义: an official document proving that you have completed a course of study or passed an exam; a qualification obtained after a course of study or an exam
例句: I got my graduation certificate after finishing college.
例句释义: 在完成大学教育后，我获得了毕业证书。

英文释义: a long loose outer piece of clothing, especially one worn as a sign of rank or office at a special ceremony
例句: It is a tradition for the crosstalk performers to wear robes.
例句释义: 相声演员穿长袍是一种传统。

详细释义: v.委任，任命，提名；  adj.已受委派而尚未上任的
英文释义: to choose or name somebody for a particular job or position
例句: After the interview, she is designated as a manager of the company.
例句释义: 面试结束后，她被任命为公司的经理。

英文释义: quickly and without warning
例句: The water stopped abruptly so I couldn't finish my shower.
例句释义: 水突然停了，所以我不能洗完澡。

英文释义: a kind or forgiving attitude towards somebody that you have the power to harm or right to punish
例句: The farmer shows mercy to the snake.
例句释义: 农夫向蛇展现了他的仁慈。

英文释义: a person who is or was in the same class as you at school or college
例句: All of my classmates are in this class photo.
例句释义: 我们全班同学都在这张班级照里。

详细释义: n. 异教；风尚，热潮；信徒；  adj. 流行的；风靡一时的
英文释义: a small group of people who have extreme religious beliefs and who are not part of any established religion
例句: Believers of this cult worship aliens.
例句释义: 这个异教的教徒崇拜外星人。

英文释义: very serious or severe
例句: When she was working, she felt an acute pain in her neck.
例句释义: 工作的时候，她感到脖子一阵剧痛。

英文释义: a hotel for people who are traveling by car, with space for parking cars near the rooms
例句: I drove all night until I found a motel where I could stay.
例句释义: 我开了一整晚的车，直到找到一个能下榻的汽车旅馆。

英文释义: a very strong feeling of dislike for somebody/something
例句: He has a lot of hatred to this terrible phone.
例句释义: 他对这个糟糕的手机有极大的怨恨。

英文释义: a straight line going from one side of a circle or any other round object to the other side, passing through the centre
例句: The worker was measuring the lumber's diameter.
例句释义: 工人正在测量木材的直径。

详细释义: n. 护理；看护；  adj. 喂奶的
英文释义: the job of taking care of people who are sick, injured, or old
例句: Nursing is the practice of caring for sick and injured people.
例句释义: 护理就是指照顾病人和伤者。

详细释义: n. 前辈；（被取代的）原有事物
英文释义: a person who did a job before somebody else
例句: He learned a lot from his experienced predecessor.
例句释义: 他从经验丰富的前辈那里学到了很多东西。

英文释义: to persuade or use influence on
例句: The leader gives a speech to induce his followers.
例句释义: 领导做了一场演讲来引导他的员工。

详细释义: v.得到……的赞助或帮助；应募，招募，参加，加入
英文释义: to persuade somebody to help you or to join you in doing something; to join or to make somebody join the armed forces
例句: He couldn't lift the rock alone so he enlisted the help of a few friends.
例句释义: 他一个人搬不动这块石头，所以他找了几个朋友来帮忙。

详细释义: n.【审计】披露；公开；被揭发出来的事情
英文释义: the act of making something known or public that was previously secret or private
例句: The full disclosure of annual financial statements is a requirement for most companies.
例句释义: 大多数公司都被要求全面公开年度财务报表。

详细释义: n. 青少年；雏鸟；  adj. 青少年的；幼稚的
英文释义: a young person who is not yet an adult
例句: This group of juveniles are taking a selfie together.
例句释义: 这群青少年在一起自拍。

详细释义: n. 女礼服；女裙服；长袍
英文释义: a woman’s dress, especially a long one for special occasions
例句: The bride wore a beautiful white wedding gown.
例句释义: 新娘穿着漂亮的白婚纱。

英文释义: to stop; to make somebody/something stop
例句: You should halt when you see a policeman make this gesture.
例句释义: 看到警察做出这个手势时，你应该要止步。

英文释义: determined to do something despite difficulties, especially when other people are against you and think that you are being annoying or unreasonable
例句: You'll learn to be persistent when climbing mountains.
例句释义: 在爬山的过程中，你会学会坚持不懈的精神。

英文释义: if two or more facts, figures, etc. correlate or if a fact, figure, etc. correlates with another, the facts are closely connected and affect or depend on each other; to show that there is a close connection between two or more facts, figures, etc.
例句: The chart shows that level of income correlates with the level of education.
例句释义: 这张图表显示，收入水平与教育水平相关联。

详细释义: n. 人道主义者；慈善家；博爱主义者；  adj. 人道主义者的；慈善的；博爱的
英文释义: a person who is concerned with reducing suffering and improving the conditions that people live in
例句: She's a well-known humanitarian who devotes her life to help the poor.
例句释义: 她是一位著名的人道主义者，奉献其一生来帮助穷人。

详细释义: vt.流亡，放逐；使离乡背井；  n.流放，充军
英文释义: to force somebody to leave their country, especially for political reasons or as a punishment; to send somebody into exile
例句: The man was exiled to the wilderness.
例句释义: 他被流放到了边疆。

详细释义: n.吼叫声，轰鸣声；  vi.咆哮；  vt.大声呼喊
英文释义: a loud deep sound made by an animal, especially a lion, or by somebody’s voice, or by a machine
例句: The tiger let out a mighty roar on the cliff.
例句释义: 这只老虎在山崖上发出威猛的怒吼。

英文释义: to cause severe physical pain as a form of punishment or as a way to force someone to do or say something
例句: My friend tortured us with her terrible singing.
例句释义: 我朋友用她糟糕的歌声折磨我们。

详细释义: adj. 建筑上的，建筑学的
英文释义: connected with architecture
例句: This old architectural style impresses me.
例句释义: 这种复古建筑风格让我很震撼。

英文释义: (often in names) a large group of singers; a group of performers who sing and dance in a musical show
例句: What a wonderful performance by the chorus!
例句释义: 合唱团的表演好精彩呀！

英文释义: a structure from which water is sent up into the air by a pump, used to decorate parks and gardens/yards
例句: The fountain becomes so colorful at night.
例句释义: 在晚上，喷泉变得五彩缤纷。

英文释义: to become, or to make somebody/something become, conscious or healthy and strong again
例句: She is using this device to revive the unconscious man.
例句释义: 她正在用这个设备让这位昏迷的男性苏醒。

英文释义: (used about groups of animals, plants, etc.) at risk of no longer existing
例句: This species is endangered with less than 70 left today.
例句释义: 此类物种濒临灭绝，如今只剩下不到70只了。

详细释义: adj.滑稽的，使人发笑的；  n.连环漫画杂志
英文释义: amusing and making you laugh; connected with comedy (= entertainment that is funny and that makes people laugh)
例句: His comic actions often make us laugh.
例句释义: 他滑稽的动作经常使我们大笑。

英文释义: to live in a particular place
例句: This type of crab resides inside shells.
例句释义: 寄居蟹住在贝壳里面。

详细释义: n.报复；报仇；  v.为……报仇，报……之仇
英文释义: something that you do in order to make somebody suffer because they have made you suffer
例句: They were taking revenge on the aliens who had attacked them before.
例句释义: 他们对曾经攻击过他们的外星人进行了报复。

例句: The little boy is unclear about how to work out the answer to the math problem.
例句释义: 这个小男孩不清楚如何算出数学题的正确答案。

英文释义: having a taste like that of a lemon or of fruit that is not ready to eat; (especially of milk) having an unpleasant taste or smell because it is not fresh
例句: The lemon has such a sour taste!
例句释义: 柠檬真酸啊！

英文释义: a warning or a piece of advice about a possible danger or risk
例句: Caution: the road is dangerous ahead.
例句释义: 警告：前方道路危险。

详细释义: vi. 起源；开始；  vt. 开创
英文释义: to happen or appear for the first time in a particular place or situation
例句: Humans originated from ape-like creatures.
例句释义: 人类起源于类人猿动物。

详细释义: adj.实证的，以观察或实验为根据的
英文释义: based on experiments or experience rather than ideas or theories
例句: Empirical studies focus more on observation rather than theory alone.
例句释义: 实证研究更强调观察而非理论本身。

详细释义: v. 以诱饵吸引；  n. 诱惑物
英文释义: to persuade or trick somebody to go somewhere or to do something by promising them a reward
例句: I lure fish by putting worms on my fishing pole.
例句释义: 我把蠕虫放到鱼钩上做诱饵来钓鱼。

英文释义: to produce a book, list, report, etc. by bringing together different items, articles, songs, etc.
例句: This book compiles thousands of love stories.
例句释义: 这本书汇集了成千上万个爱情故事。

详细释义: v. （火山、喷泉、蒸汽等）喷发；喷射出
英文释义: when a volcano erupts or burning rocks, smoke, etc. erupt or are erupted, the burning rocks, etc. are thrown out from the volcano
例句: This volcano erupts three times a day.
例句释义: 这座火山一天喷发三次。

英文释义: (of descriptions, etc.) very clear and full of details, especially about something unpleasant
例句: She gave a graphic description of the bloody battle.
例句释义: 她生动地描述了这场激烈的战争。

详细释义: n.织布机；  v.阴森地逼近；隐现；即将来临
英文释义: a machine for making cloth by twisting threads between other threads which go in a different direction
例句: The girl is operating the loom to weave the cloth.
例句释义: 这个女孩正在用织布机织布。

英文释义: a woman who is believed to have magic powers, especially to do evil things

详细释义: n. 服务员，侍者，随从；  adj. 伴随的，随之而产生的
英文释义: a person whose job is to serve or help people in a public place; a person who takes care of and lives or travels with an important person or a sick or disabled person
例句: The gas attendant filled up the car for the customer.
例句释义: 这个加油站服务员正在为顾客的汽车加油。

详细释义: v. 履行，实现，完成；满足（愿望、要求等），使满意
英文释义: to do or achieve what was hoped for or expected; to do or have what is required or necessary; to have a particular role or purpose
例句: She fulfilled her goals on the list.
例句释义: 她完成了清单上的目标。

英文释义: a person or thing that comes after somebody/something else and takes their/its place
例句: The old king hands over his throne to his successor.
例句释义: 国王把他的王位转交给了继承人。

英文释义: the murder of an important or famous person, especially for political reasons
例句: The weapon used for the assassination was a bow and arrow.
例句释义: 用来暗杀的武器是一副弓箭。

英文释义: related to the energy that is produced when atoms are split; related to weapons that use this energy
例句: A mushroom cloud formed after the atomic bomb went off.
例句释义: 原子弹爆炸后，天空中出现了蘑菇云。

英文释义: connected with the way in which the physical features of a place are arranged
例句: Mountains, deserts, plains, and rainforests have different geographic features.
例句释义: 山脉、沙漠、平原和雨林有着不同的地理特征。

详细释义: adj.轻便的，手提的，便携式的
英文释义: that is easy to carry or to move
例句: I prefer portable computers―they're more convenient.
例句释义: 我更喜欢手提电脑――它们更方便。

英文释义: a soft red fruit with very small yellow seeds on the surface, that grows on a low plant
例句: I want to buy one box of strawberries.
例句释义: 我想买一盒草莓。

详细释义: n. 持有者，占有者，（台，架等）支持物
英文释义: a person who has or owns the thing mentioned
例句: The runner is the holder of the 100 meter world record.
例句释义: 这位赛跑运动员是百米世界纪录的保持者。

英文释义: if a picture, substance or sound has clarity, you can see or hear it very clearly, or see through it easily
例句: The clarity of the water allows us to see all the fish clearly.
例句释义: 水很清澈，这样我们就能看清里面所有的鱼了。

英文释义: a person who works to protect the natural world from pollution and other threats
例句: A group of environmentalists are planting trees.
例句释义: 一群环保主义者正在植树。

英文释义: a deep valley with steep rock sides and often a stream or river flowing through it
例句: There is a river running through the canyon.
例句释义: 有一条河流经这道峡谷。

英文释义: writing that is arranged in lines, often with a regular rhythm or pattern of rhyme
例句: Li Bai’s poem is made up of four verses.
例句释义: 李白的诗有四句。

英文释义: very small drops of water that are present in the air, on a surface or in a substance
例句: The machine on the desk adds moisture to the air.
例句释义: 桌上的机器能增加空气中的水分。

详细释义: n. 奖品，战利品，胜利纪念物

例句: All I want is to win first place and have my name on a big trophy.
例句释义: 我只想赢得冠军，把我的名字印在大奖杯上。

详细释义: n.格格声；发出嘎嘎声的儿童玩具；（响尾蛇）音响器官；  v.（使）发出格格声；（人或车）疾驰；使烦扰
英文释义: a series of short loud sounds made when hard objects hit against each other; a baby’s toy that makes a series of short loud sounds when it is shaken; a wooden object that is held in one hand and makes a series of short loud sounds when you spin it round, used, for example, by people watching a sports game

例句释义: 这个婴儿喜欢咔嗒咔嗒的声音。

英文释义: a person that somebody works with, doing the same kind of job
例句: They watch their co-worker presenting his plan.
例句释义: 他们看着同事陈述计划。

例句: These two families have completely different parenting styles.
例句释义: 这两个家庭养育子女的方式完全不同。

详细释义: adj.非常漂亮的；（衣服或色彩）华丽的；令人愉快的，引人入胜的
英文释义: (of colours, clothes, etc.) with very deep colours; impressive
例句: A gorgeous woman is lying in the flowers.
例句释义: 一位美丽的女子躺在群花之中。

英文释义: to suddenly break into small pieces; to make something suddenly break into small pieces
例句: This bottle of essence hit the floor and shattered into pieces!
例句释义: 这瓶精华液在地上摔得粉碎！

英文释义: a slope going downwards
例句: You'd better drive carefully on such a descent.
例句释义: 在这样的下坡路段开车时，最好当心点。

英文释义: to become wider; to make something wider
例句: This road was too narrow, so now we have to widen it.
例句释义: 这条路太窄了，所以现在我们要把它加宽。

详细释义: v.取笑；挑逗；使……渴望；梳理；  n.爱戏弄别人的人

英文释义: to surprise somebody suddenly in a way that slightly shocks or frightens them
例句: The explosion of firecrackers startled the chicken.
例句释义: 鞭炮的爆炸声把鸡吓了一跳。

英文释义: one of the four books in the Bible about the life and teaching of Jesus
例句: The man was preaching the Gospel.
例句释义: 这个人在传布福音。

英文释义: a male member of a royal family who is not king, especially the son or grandson of the king or queen
例句: The prince looks more charming with his blue cape on.
例句释义: 穿上蓝色的斗篷，这位王子显得更加迷人了。

英文释义: a person whose job is to serve customers at their tables in a restaurant, etc.
例句: The young man is a waiter in a restaurant.
例句释义: 这个年轻的小伙子是一家餐馆的服务员。

详细释义: v.立誓，宣誓，发誓；  n.誓约

英文释义: (of a person) not willing to change their ideas or behaviour

英文释义: one of the two periods that the school or college year is divided into

例句释义: 一学年通常包含两个学期。

英文释义: a piece cut off a plant that will be used to grow a new plant；an article or a story that you cut from a newspaper or magazine and keep
例句: Many students in primary school save cuttings from newspapers.
例句释义: 许多小学生保存有剪报。

详细释义: n. 果酱；  v. （使）阻塞，使塞满

英文释义: the place where you were born or lived as a child
例句: He misses his hometown when he is looking at the moon.
例句释义: 他望着月亮，思念着自己的故乡。

英文释义: to fall downwards, often hitting the ground several times, but usually without serious injury; to make somebody/something fall in this way; to fall suddenly and in a dramatic way

英文释义: a piece of equipment for discovering the presence of something, such as metal, smoke, explosives or changes in pressure or temperature

例句释义: 这个金属探测器一靠近黄金就发出了响声。

英文释义: a pattern of straight lines, usually crossing each other to form squares; a pattern of squares on a map that are marked with letters or numbers to help you find the exact position of a place

例句: Every week the man would see the doctor about his psychiatric disorder.
例句释义: 每周这个男人都会去找医生治疗他的精神问题。

详细释义: v.以……轴转动，使旋转；轮流，轮换
英文释义: to move or turn around a central fixed point; to make something do this

例句释义: 跳舞时她旋转着身体。

英文释义: different from something; against something; completely different in nature or direction

例句: The patient was taken into the back of the ambulance.
例句释义: 患者被抬进救护车的后面。

英文释义: a person who has a lot of authority and manages and controls an activity, a place, a group of workers, etc.

例句释义: 我们的校长正在带主管参观学校。

详细释义: n.撞击；隆起物；（碰撞造成的）肿块；  v.颠簸地行驶；除名

例句释义: 我买了一个新的调制解调器让电脑能联网。

英文释义: a member of a group that works to put out fires

例句释义: 消防员没能把大火扑灭。

英文释义: not in a place because of illness, etc.; not present in something; showing that you are not really looking at or thinking about what is happening around you

英文释义: (in Christianity) the state of being saved from the power of evil

例句释义: 基督教徒们相信：如果你追随耶稣，你就可以获得拯救。

例句释义: 她今天上午上了两节课，即英语和数学。

英文释义: a stamp or mark put in your passport by officials of a foreign country that gives you permission to enter, pass through or leave their country

例句释义: 我拿到了我的签证，现在我可以环游世界啦！

英文释义: to change something that is old or damaged and replace it with something new of the same kind

例句释义: 我的房东在年底续签了我的租约。

详细释义: adv.在头顶，在上面；  adj.在头顶上的，上面的；  n.吊顶，天花板

例句释义: 看，有一架飞机正在头顶上飞！

英文释义: a round fruit with soft red and yellow skin, yellow flesh and a large rough seed inside

例句释义: 桃子是我最喜欢的水果。

英文释义: the act or process of changing something in order to improve it or make it more acceptable; a change that is made

例句: We can tell from the shape of its head that this is a male goose.

英文释义: an open space for a fire in the wall of a room

例句释义: 他们在壁炉前聊天。

例句: The plant needs to be carefully nurtured with water and fertilizer.

例句释义: 她穿的很鲜艳。

英文释义: to make somebody suddenly feel afraid

例句释义: 我的弟弟从衣柜里跳出来，吓到我了。

英文释义: very angry

详细释义: n.毒物，毒药，毒素；  v.毒死，毒害

例句释义: 这把尺子既有英寸刻度，又有厘米刻度。

详细释义: adj.岩石的，多岩石的；磐石般的

例句释义: 灯塔坐落在岩石海岸上。

英文释义: a person who pays rent for the use of a room, building, land, etc. to the person who owns it

例句释义: 我们带新租客去看了房。

例句释义: 他用钢琴弹奏了一段美妙的旋律。

英文释义: a very small piece of matter (= a substance) with a negative electric charge, found in all atoms
例句: An electron moves around an atom's nucleus.
例句释义: 电子绕着原子的原子核运动。

详细释义: n. 物理学者，物理学家
英文释义: a scientist who studies physics
例句: Einstein was a great physicist.
例句释义: 爱因斯坦是个伟大的物理学家。

详细释义: adj. 著名的，卓著的；高贵的
英文释义: very successful and admired by other people
例句: Einstein is a distinguished physicist and scientist.
例句释义: 爱因斯坦是一位杰出的物理学家和科学家。

英文释义: all the words in a particular language; all of the words known and used by a person
例句: There are plenty of words in the vocabulary which are related to business.
例句释义: 词汇表中的许多单词都与商业有关。

英文释义: a tall tree with leaves that have five points and turn bright red or yellow in the autumn/fall. Maples grow in northern countries.
例句: In autumn, maple leaves turn red.
例句释义: 枫树叶子在秋天变成红色。

英文释义: the soft fine hair that covers the body of sheep, goats and some other animals; long thick thread made from animal’s wool, used for knitting; cloth made from animal’s wool, used for making clothes, etc.
例句: Lend me your wool please. I'll make you a pretty sweater.
例句释义: 借我点儿你的羊毛，我要给你织一件漂亮的毛衣。

英文释义: a person (especially a man) whose job is to sell things
例句: The salesman is introducing the latest car to his customer.
例句释义: 这个推销员在向他的顾客介绍最新款汽车。

英文释义: an account written by somebody, especially somebody famous, about their life and experiences
例句: His memoir records the events of his whole life.
例句释义: 他的回忆录记录了他的一生中发生的事件。

英文释义: completely and without qualification; used informally as intensifiers
例句: The man was totally and utterly in love with his wife.
例句释义: 这个男人全心全意地爱着他的妻子。

英文释义: to prepare and use land for growing plants or crops; to grow plants or crops
例句: I'll need to cultivate my fields well if I want my crops to grow.
例句释义: 如果我想让我的作物生长，我就得把我的田地耕作好。

英文释义: a device that is used for recording sounds or for making your voice louder when you are speaking or singing to an audience
例句: The woman speaks with her microphone.
例句释义: 这位女士用麦克风讲话。

英文释义: a small soft round fruit with shiny red or black skin and a large seed inside; a tree on which cherries grow, or a similar tree, grown for its flowers
例句: Cherry juice is good for your skin.
例句释义: 樱桃汁对你的皮肤有好处。

详细释义: adj.奢侈的，豪华的；  n.奢侈，奢华
英文释义: the enjoyment of special and expensive things, particularly food and drink, clothes and surroundings
例句: This luxury car looks so expensive.
例句释义: 这辆豪华车看起来很贵。

英文释义: to give a summary of something (= a statement of the main points)
例句: I don’t want to read the whole thing. Could you just summarize the book for me?
例句释义: 我不想再看这个东西了，你能就帮我概括一下这本书吗？

英文释义: a field covered in grass, used especially for hay
例句: There are a flock of sheep wandering around the meadow.
例句释义: 草地上有一群羊在游荡。

英文释义: the act of throwing something away
例句: The cleaner handles trash disposal for us.
例句释义: 清洁工负责处理我们的垃圾。

英文释义: containing magic; used in magic
例句: He has a very magical hat.
例句释义: 他的帽子有魔力。

详细释义: v. 违背；违抗，藐视；使不可能 (理解或解释)；赌…也不能
英文释义: to refuse to obey or show respect for somebody in authority, a law, a rule, etc.
例句: Many people defied the warning sign of no scribbling on the wall.
例句释义: 许多人不顾墙上不准乱涂乱画的警告标志。

详细释义: n.插头；  vt.插入（插头），接通（电源）；补足
英文释义: a small plastic object with two or three metal pins that connects a piece of electrical equipment to the main supply of electricity
例句: He wants to pull out the plug.
例句释义: 他想把插头拔出来。

例句: Strip mining has destroyed the land here.
例句释义: 露天采矿破坏了这里的土地。

英文释义: a small flat folding case made of leather or plastic used for keeping paper money and credit cards in; a flat leather, plastic or cardboard case for carrying documents in
例句: My wallet holds all of my money and credit cards.
例句释义: 我的钱包里有我所有的钱和信用卡。

详细释义: adj.社会主义的；  n.社会主义者
英文释义: connected with socialism; governed by or belonging to a party that believes in socialism
例句: Do you know the core socialist values?
例句释义: 你知道社会主义核心价值观吗？

英文释义: a young sheep; meat from a young sheep
例句: Those two lambs are so cute!
例句释义: 那两只小羊如此可爱！

详细释义: n. 废金属；小块，小片；碎片；口角，吵架；  v. 报废；舍弃；打架
英文释义: a small piece of something, especially paper, cloth, etc.
例句: All these old cars will be used as scrap.
例句释义: 所有这些旧汽车都将当废金属利用。

英文释义: to attract somebody or make somebody want to do or have something, even if they know it is wrong
例句: The squirrel is easily tempted by the acorn.
例句释义: 这只松鼠很容易被一颗橡子引诱。

英文释义: to an extreme or greatly exaggerated degree
例句: The bear became wildly excited when he found all that honey.
例句释义: 当熊发现那一堆蜂蜜时，他变得极其兴奋。

详细释义: n. 宣言，声明书；宣布，宣告
英文释义: an official or formal statement, especially about the plans of a government or an organization; the act of making an official statement about something
例句: The leaders in the room drafted the Declaration of Independence.
例句释义: 屋子里的几位领导人拟定了《独立宣言》。

详细释义: n. 坐标轴；轴；中心线；基准线
英文释义: a fixed line against which the positions of points are measured, especially points on a graph
例句: The axis of the graph represents a different dimension: x, y, and z.
例句释义: 图表中每条轴线代表了不同的维度：X、Y、Z。

英文释义: a school that provides training in special subjects or skills
例句: This is an academy for soldiers to train.
例句释义: 这是一所训练士兵的学院。

英文释义: the noise made by a group of people clapping their hands and sometimes shouting to show their approval or enjoyment
例句: The audience broke into enthusiastic applause for the three boys.
例句释义: 观众们对三个男孩报以热烈的掌声。

英文释义: to put a drug or other substance into a person’s or an animal’s body using a syringe
例句: "Does this hurt?" the doctor asked as she injected her patient with antibiotics.
例句释义: “痛吗？”医生一边给患者注射抗生素一边问。

英文释义: in a smooth, regular or equal way; with equal amounts for each person or in each place
例句: The weight was evenly distributed to both sides.
例句释义: 两边重量相等。

英文释义: to happen or exist before something or someone, or to come before something else in a series
例句: Dinner was preceded by a short prayer.
例句释义: 吃饭前先进行一个简短的祈祷。

英文释义: having two parts or aspects
例句: His?computer?is?equipped?with?dual?screens.
例句释义: 他的电脑配有双屏幕。

英文释义: to be in charge of somebody/something and make sure that everything is done correctly, safely, etc.
例句: The teacher supervises the students doing the exam.
例句释义: 老师正在监督学生考试。

详细释义: n. 盾牌；防护物；  v. 保护
英文释义: a large piece of metal or leather carried by soldiers in the past to protect the body when fighting
例句: The knight fights with a sword and shield.
例句释义: 骑士挥舞着宝剑和盾牌战斗。

英文释义: a simple musical instrument that consists of a long piece of metal bent into the shape of a triangle, that you hit with another piece of metal
例句: She drew a triangle with a black pen.
例句释义: 她用黑笔画了一个三角形。

英文释义: a strong desire to have or do something
例句: My aspiration is to be the CEO of a company someday.
例句释义: 我的抱负是有一天成为一家公司的首席执行官。

英文释义: someone who tells a story
例句: Bill was a born narrator who loved to tell scary stories.
例句释义: 比尔是个天生的故事大王，非常喜爱讲恐怖故事。

英文释义: cooked in hot oil
例句: All I wanted was a plate of delicious fried foods.
例句释义: 我只是想要一盘美味的油炸食物。

英文释义: a case with flat sides and a handle, used for carrying clothes, etc. when you are travelling
例句: My suitcase looks too old.
例句释义: 我的手提箱看上去太旧了。

英文释义: having a slope
例句: They installed a new inclined access ramp for wheelchairs.
例句释义: 他们为了方便轮椅通行安装了一个新的斜坡道。

英文释义: a chemical element. Calcium is a soft silver-white metal that is found in bones, teeth and chalk.
例句: Milk and cheese are high in calcium.
例句释义: 牛奶和芝士都富含钙。

英文释义: the work or activity involved in being in charge of somebody/something and making sure that everything is done correctly, safely, etc.; a meeting between a student and their tutor or supervisor that involves teaching and discussion of the student's work
例句: The young staff member worked hard under the supervision of his boss.
例句释义: 这位年轻的职员在老板的监督下努力工作。

详细释义: vt.代替；  n.代替者，代替物
英文释义: to take the place of somebody/something else; to use somebody/something instead of somebody/something else
例句: You should substitute fruits for sweets.
例句释义: 你应该用水果代替甜食。

详细释义: n. 认识，领会，领悟，实现
英文释义: the process of becoming aware of something; the process of achieving a particular aim, etc.; the act of selling something that you own, such as property, in order to get the money that you need for something; the act of producing a sound, play, design, etc.; or the thing that is produced
例句: I suddenly had a realization that I forgot to lock the door.
例句释义: 我突然意识到我忘记锁门啦。

英文释义: an occasion when people pack a meal and take it to eat outdoors, especially in the countryside
例句: The family enjoyed a nice picnic outside.
例句释义: 这一家人在室外享用了一顿很好的野餐。

详细释义: n. 沙砾，小石，砾石；  adj. 粗重而沙哑的，刺耳的；  vt. 用砾石铺
英文释义: small stones, often used to make the surface of paths and roads
例句: There is lots of gravel along the road.
例句释义: 路上有许多碎石。

例句: Their belief in nationalism drove these rabbits to leave the union and live separately.
例句释义: 对民族主义的信仰驱使这些兔子退出联盟，单独居住。

英文释义: a fabric that is woven or knit
例句: They use colorful threads to make this textile.
例句释义: 他们用鲜艳的线来制作这块纺织品。

详细释义: n. 先例，范例；  adj. 在前的，前面的
英文释义: an official action or decision that has happened in the past and that is seen as an example or a rule to be followed in a similar situation later; a similar action or event that happened earlier
例句: These cases set the precedent for future intellectual property legal cases.
例句释义: 这些案子为未来的知识产权案件开创了先例。

详细释义: adj. 永恒的，永不改变的
英文释义: without an end; existing or continuing forever
例句: The lock and key symbolize the eternal love of the couple.
例句释义: 锁和钥匙象征着恋人之间永恒的爱。

英文释义: a person who translates the words that someone is speaking into a different language
例句: The interpreter helps the two people to communicate with each other.
例句释义: 口译员帮助这两个人相互交流。

英文释义: a formal document written for a prosecuting attorney charging a person with some offense
例句: She made an indictment against the company who sold her expired milk powder.
例句释义: 她起诉了那家卖给她过期奶粉的公司。

英文释义: an accident in which two vehicles or people crash into each other; a strong disagreement between two people or between opposing ideas, opinions, etc./ the meeting of two things that are very different
例句: Fortunately, no one was injured in the collision between the cars.
例句释义: 幸运的是，没人在两车碰撞中受伤。

英文释义: the muscular back part of the leg below the knee
例句: Your calf muscles will be sore after a long run.
例句释义: 经过长跑，你小腿肌肉会酸痛。

详细释义: n. 家族；氏族；部落；宗派；亲族
英文释义: a group of families who are related to each other, especially in Scotland; (informal, sometimes humorous) a very large family, or a group of people who are connected because of a particular thing
例句: The old man is the head of the family clan.
例句释义: 那个老人是一家之主。

英文释义: to prove, show, find out, or state that (something) is true or correct
例句: This card can verify the man's identity.
例句释义: 这个证件可以证实此人的身份。

英文释义: a place where children are cared for during the day while their parents are working
例句: I drop off my kids at the nursery before I go to work.
例句释义: 上班之前，我把孩子们送去了托儿所。

英文释义: the sport of fighting someone with your hands while wearing very thick gloves
例句: The two boxers are waiting for a chance to strike in the boxing match.
例句释义: 在这场拳击比赛中，两位拳击手都在等待时机进行攻击。

详细释义: n. 派别，小集团，小派系；派系斗争，内讧
英文释义: a small group of people within a larger one whose members have some different aims and beliefs to those of the larger group
例句: The leaders of two opposing factions had a talk.
例句释义: 这两个敌对派系的领导人进行了会谈。

详细释义: n.香料，调味品；  v.使增添趣味
英文释义: one of the various types of powder or seed that come from plants and are used in cooking. Spices have a strong taste and smell
例句: I added some spice to the recipe to make it taste better.
例句释义: 我在菜谱里加了些香料，这样料理就会更美味了。

详细释义: adj.困惑的；混乱的；  vt.使困惑
例句: I get confused when the two of you tell me different things.
例句释义: 你们俩对我讲不同的事，我开始迷糊了。

英文释义: a piece of thick material such as rubber or plastic used especially in some sports for people to lie on or fall onto
例句: The dog is sitting on the "welcome" mat.
例句释义: 狗狗坐在印有＂欢迎＂的垫子上。

详细释义: v.单脚跳，跳过；乘坐；  n.单脚跳跃；蛇麻草
英文释义: (of a person) to move by jumping on one foot
例句: This is a game where you hop to different spots drawn on the ground.
例句释义: 这种游戏需要你单脚跳到画在地面上的不同的区域。

英文释义: extremely large in size or amount
例句: Compared with the immense universe, our planet is so small.
例句释义: 与浩瀚无垠的宇宙相比，我们的星球是如此渺小。

英文释义: feeling shame or embarrassment about somebody/something or because of something you have done
例句: He was deeply ashamed to be caught cheating during the exam.
例句释义: 考试作弊被抓，他感到很羞愧。

英文释义: (in a college or university, especially at Oxford or Cambridge) a person who is responsible for the discipline of students
例句: The dean of our department is reading in his office.
例句释义: 我们学院的院长在办公室里看书。

英文释义: at a later or succeeding time
例句: They had a romantic dinner and decided to watch a movie afterwards.
例句释义: 他们吃了一顿浪漫的晚餐，然后决定去看电影。

详细释义: adj.乐器的；有帮助的；仪器的
英文释义: made by or for musical instruments
例句: They only play instrumental music; their band doesn't have a singer.
例句释义: 这个乐队只有乐器演奏，他们没有歌手。

详细释义: adj. 贵族的，高贵的；  n. 贵族
英文释义: belonging to a family of high social rank (= belonging to the nobility)
例句: The women in the expensive dresses come from a noble family.
例句释义: 这些穿着昂贵衣服的女人出身高贵。

详细释义: n. 不幸事件之后果，余波
英文释义: the period of time after a bad and usually destructive event
例句: In the aftermath of the war, these poor villagers were homeless.
例句释义: 在战争的余波中，这些可怜的村民无家可归。

英文释义: a period of a thousand years counted from the beginning of the Christian era
例句: The year 2000 was the beginning of a new millennium.
例句释义: 2000年是一个新千年的开始。

详细释义: v.喘气；气喘吁吁地说出；  n.喘气
英文释义: to take a quick deep breath with your mouth open, especially because you are surprised or in pain
例句: The old man is gasping while going upstairs.
例句释义: 在上楼梯时，老人大口喘着气。

英文释义: a person whose job involves travelling and working in a spacecraft
例句: I would love to be an astronaut and go to space.
例句释义: 我想成为一名宇航员进入太空。

详细释义: n. 外壳，面包皮，硬外皮
英文释义: the hard outer surface of bread; a layer of pastry, especially on top of a pie
例句: Everytime I eat bread, I always leave the crust.
例句释义: 每次我吃面包都不吃面包皮。

详细释义: adj. 无用的，无价值的，无效的
英文释义: not useful; not doing or achieving what is needed or wanted
例句: It's useless trying to use this bicycle.
例句释义: 这辆自行车已经没法用了。

英文释义: the act or process of producing babies, young animals or plants
例句: Cell reproduction can be very complicated sometimes!
例句释义: 有时候，细胞繁殖过程非常复杂。

英文释义: a common disease that is caused by a virus and that causes fever, weakness, body aches, and breathing problems
例句: It seems as though the whole family has the flu.
例句释义: 似乎全家人都得了流感。

英文释义: an object with a round folding frame of long straight pieces of metal covered with material, that you use to protect yourself from the rain or from hot sun
例句: This umbrella is yellow.
例句释义: 这把伞是黄色的。

详细释义: adj. 不省人事的；未察觉的
英文释义: in a state like sleep because of an injury or illness, and not able to use your senses
例句: We found him unconscious on the floor.
例句释义: 我们发现他倒在地上，不省人事。

英文释义: a flying insect that bites humans and animals and sucks their blood. One type of mosquito can spread the disease malaria.
例句: There are two mosquitos on her arm!
例句释义: 她的手臂上有两只蚊子！

详细释义: v. 使转向，使改道（或绕道）
英文释义: to make somebody/something change direction
例句: We're being diverted from the road, but we'll get back to it soon.
例句释义: 我们改道了，但很快会回到原路。

英文释义: a climbing plant that produces grapes; any climbing plant with long thin stems; one of these stems
例句: The monkey is swinging on the vine.
例句释义: 这个猴子在藤蔓上晃荡。

英文释义: a person who protects something
例句: The frontier soldiers are the guardians of national territory.
例句释义: 边防战士是国家领土的守护者。

英文释义: to do what you are told or expected to do
例句: The dog always obeys its master.
例句释义: 这只狗总是服从它主人的话。

英文释义: showing concern for the needs or feelings of other people
例句: Her boyfriend is very thoughtful.
例句释义: 她的男朋友非常体贴。

英文释义: a school teaching mechanical and industrial arts and the applied sciences
例句: The computer science graduate joined a leading tech firm.
例句释义: 这名计算机专业的毕业生加入了一家业内领先的科技公司。

详细释义: n. 方法论，方法学；（某一学科的）一套方法
英文释义: a set of methods and principles used to perform a particular activity
例句: Teaching methodologies vary according to the subject.
例句释义: 教学方法要随着科目而变。

英文释义: imitation or representation, as of a potential situation or in experimental testing
例句: Hopefully this driving simulation machine can help me pass my test!
例句释义: 真希望这个驾驶模拟器可以帮我通过考试！

英文释义: to wake up; to make somebody wake up
例句: She was awakened by the bird's song.
例句释义: 她被鸟儿的歌声唤醒了。

英文释义: tending not to take an active or dominant part
例句: Stop smoking! You are making your baby a passive smoker!
例句释义: 别抽烟啦！你正在让你的孩子成为被动吸烟者！

详细释义: n. 垄断；垄断商品；专卖商品
英文释义: the complete control of trade in particular goods or the supply of a particular service; a type of goods or a service that is controlled in this way
例句: The biggest company has a monopoly in the market!

例句: The company paid dividends to its investors.

英文释义: to change your opinions or plans, for example because of something you have learned; to change something, such as a book or an estimate, in order to correct or improve it
例句: She is revising her paper according to the advice given by her teacher.
例句释义: 她正在根据老师给的意见修改论文。

英文释义: when a dog barks, it makes a short loud sound
例句: It scares me when the dog barks.
例句释义: 这只狗叫的时候吓到我了。

英文释义: relatively low in price or charging low prices
例句: Living such a poor lifestyle, I can only use the inexpensive iron axe.
例句释义: 过着穷苦日子的我，只用得上便宜的铁斧子。

英文释义: to make somebody feel extremely frightened
例句: The boys were terrified by the horror movie.
例句释义: 男孩们被这部恐怖电影吓坏了。

英文释义: an open space that is partly or completely surrounded by buildings and is usually part of a castle, a large house, etc.
例句: The dog is having fun in the courtyard.
例句释义: 狗狗在院子里愉快地玩耍。

详细释义: v. 吸引注意；使神魂颠倒
英文释义: to attract or interest somebody very much
例句: The blonde boys are fascinated by the book.
例句释义: 金发男孩儿被这本书深深地吸引了。

英文释义: a machine that produces electricity
例句: The generator is providing electricity to the restaurant.
例句释义: 发电机正在为餐厅供电。

详细释义: v.刺伤；戳；  n.刺痛；尝试，努力
英文释义: to push a sharp, pointed object, especially a knife, into somebody, killing or injuring them
例句: I felt as if someone had stabbed me in the heart with a knife.
例句释义: 我感觉像有人拿了一把匕首刺入了我的心脏。

英文释义: a place where you can buy drinks and simple meals. Alcohol is not usually served in British or American cafes.; a small shop/store that sells sweets, newspapers, food, etc. and usually stays open later than other shops/stores
例句: I went for coffee with my friend in a cafe.
例句释义: 我和我朋友在咖啡馆喝了咖啡。

英文释义: the extent to which something happens or has an effect
例句: The incidence of heart disease goes up as people get older.
例句释义: 随着年龄增大，心脏病发生的概率也会增加。

详细释义: n.（小）道具；支柱；支持者；  v.支撑，维持
英文释义: small objects used by actors in a play or film; a person or thing that gives help or support to sb/sth that is weak
例句: Here are some props for the show.
例句释义: 这里有一些为演出准备的道具。

英文释义: ideas or statements that may be false or exaggerated and that are used in order to gain support for a political leader, party, etc.
例句: The political propaganda is posted onto the lampposts around the city.
例句释义: 政治宣传内容被张贴在了城里各处的灯柱上。

详细释义: v.强调，加强，划线于…下；  n.底线
英文释义: to emphasize or show that something is important or true
例句: The teacher underscored the key points from the lecture.
例句释义: 老师强调了课程的要点。

详细释义: vt.制定，规划（计划、方法等）；系统地阐述
英文释义: to create or prepare something carefully, giving particular attention to the details
例句: He is formulating a detailed plan for his trip.
例句释义: 他正在为自己的旅行制订一个详尽的计划。

英文释义: to have a bad effect on somebody and make them behave in an immoral or dishonest way
例句: The corrupt behavior of the rat is simply despicable.
例句释义: 那只老鼠的腐败行为是可鄙的。

英文释义: a large strong building with thick high walls and towers, built in the past by kings or queens, or other important people, to defend themselves against attack
例句: One day, I will be a king and live in a castle.
例句释义: 将来有一天，我会成为一位国王，住在城堡里。

详细释义: adv. 技术上，专门地，学术上，工艺上
例句: Smart phones are much more technically advanced than the first mobile phones.
例句释义: 智能手机在技术上比第一代手机先进得多。

详细释义: adv. 并行地，平行地；  adj. 相似的；  n. 相似物；  v. 与……相似
英文释义: to be similar to something; to happen at the same time as something
例句: These tracks run parallel to each other.
例句释义: 这些铁轨相互平行。

英文释义: to do or achieve what was hoped for or expected
例句: He has fulfilled his childhood dream of becoming an astronaut.
例句释义: 他实现了成为一名宇航员的童年梦想。

英文释义: a type of oven that cooks or heats food very quickly using electromagnetic waves rather than heat; an electromagnetic wave that is shorter than a radio wave but longer than a light wave
例句: The girl uses the microwave to heat up her milk.
例句释义: 这个女孩用微波炉来加热牛奶。

英文释义: done completely; with great attention to detail; (of a person) doing things very carefully and with great attention to detail; used to emphasize how bad or annoying somebody/something is
例句: We gave my car a thorough clean.
例句释义: 我们彻底地清洗了车子。

英文释义: a small amount or piece of something that can be tested or examined
例句: This exhibit contains various different specimens of butterfly.
例句释义: 这件展览品中包含了各种不同的蝴蝶标本。

详细释义: v. 隐藏，使……模糊；  adj. 难以理解的；不清楚的
英文释义: to make it difficult to see, hear or understand something
例句: The view from the bridge was obscured by mist.
例句释义: 从桥上看出去，视野被迷雾遮蔽。

英文释义: a sight or view that is very impressive to look at; an unusual or surprising sight or situation that attracts a lot of attention
例句: The tornado was very dangerous, but wow! What a spectacle!
例句释义: 虽然龙卷风十分危险，但场面太壮观了！

详细释义: n.兴奋，激动；  v.（使）非常兴奋，（使）非常激动
英文释义: a strong feeling of excitement or pleasure; an experience that gives you this feeling; a sudden strong feeling that produces a physical effect
例句: It gave me a real thrill to ride the rollercoaster!
例句释义: 坐过山车真是太刺激啦！

英文释义: a powerful illegal drug made from morphine, that some people take for pleasure and can become addicted to
例句: Heroin is a dangerous drug.
例句释义: 海洛因是一种危险的毒品。

详细释义: n. 景色，风光；观点，看法；前景
英文释义: a view from a particular place
例句: The outlook over the mountains is very grand.
例句释义: 群山的景色非常壮观。

英文释义: a short period of time during which something is done or happening
例句: These two boxers are both ready to begin the bout.
例句释义: 这两个拳击手都准备好开始比赛了。

英文释义: a small computer that can work with a battery and be easily carried
例句: The laptop is on the wooden table.
例句释义: 笔记本电脑在木桌子上。

英文释义: to breathe air in through your nose in a way that makes a sound, especially when you are crying, have a cold, etc.; to breathe air in through the nose in order to discover or enjoy the smell of something
例句: The girl leaned over to sniff the purple flower.
例句释义: 女孩俯身去闻那朵紫色的花。

英文释义: relating to or involved in the production of babies, young animals, or new plants
例句: This diagram shows the male and female reproductive organs.
例句释义: 这张图展示了男性与女性的生殖器官。

详细释义: n. 打印机；印刷机，印刷工
英文释义: a machine for printing text on paper, especially one connected to a computer
例句: Can you please fix my printer?
例句释义: 你可以帮我修理打印机吗？

英文释义: relating to space and the position, size, shape, etc. of things in it
例句: The Earth's spatial position can be shown using the three lines.
例句释义: 地球的空间位置可以用这三条线来展示。

详细释义: adj.不感兴趣的，感到厌烦的
英文释义: feeling tired and impatient because you have lost interest in somebody/something or because you have nothing to do
例句: They are bored of having a meeting.
例句释义: 他们开会开烦了。

英文释义: a shape that has a pointed top and sides that form a circle at the bottom
例句: A traffic cone is used to warn drivers.
例句释义: 交通锥筒是用来警告司机的。

例句: The plane went down the runway before takeoff.
例句释义: 飞机起飞前沿跑道滑行。

英文释义: special metal clothing that soldiers wore in the past to protect their bodies while fighting
例句: You should wear armor―enemies tend to hit back!
例句释义: 你必须穿上盔甲――因为敌人会回击你。

详细释义: n. 散步；漫步；闲荡；溜达；  vi. 散步；  vt. 溜达；游荡；在……散步；在……漫步
英文释义: a slow relaxed walk
例句: The couple went for a stroll on the beach at sunset.
例句释义: 那对夫妇黄昏时分在沙滩散步。

英文释义: a chemical element. Nitrogen is a gas that is found in large quantities in the earth’s atmosphere.
例句: Nitrogen makes up most of Earth's atmosphere.
例句释义: 组成地球大气层的绝大部分气体是氮气。

详细释义: v. 弹回，恢复，振作；  n. 弹回，重新振作，回应
英文释义: to bounce back after hitting something
例句: The ball rebounded from the tree and hit me.
例句释义: 球从树上回弹后打到了我。

英文释义: (of glass, plastic, etc.) allowing you to see through it
例句: These glasses are transparent.
例句释义: 这些玻璃杯是透明的。

详细释义: adj.必需的，必不可少的；基本的，作为组成部分的；整体的

例句释义: 派对结束后，我们回到了各自的房间。

例句释义: 我希望“没有付出，就没有收获”这句谚语说的不是真的。

英文释义: when a liquid, gas or air circulates or is circulated, it moves continuously around a place or system
例句: Use the fan to circulate the air in the room.
例句释义: 开风扇让空气在房间里循环起来。

详细释义: n.预言；预报，预测；  vt.预报，预测
英文释义: to say what you think will happen in the future based on information that you have now

例句释义: 天气预报说下周的天气会很糟糕。

例句释义: 在复活节的时候，基督教徒喜欢做彩蛋。

英文释义: the act or process of putting people or things into a group or class (= of classifying them)
例句: There is a classification for every type of car.
例句释义: 每种类型的汽车都有其分类。

例句释义: 请总结这一段的大意。

详细释义: vi.猛冲，猛推；  n.主要观点

例句释义: 火箭猛地冲上云霄。

英文释义: connected with countries that unite to fight a war together, especially the countries that fought together against Germany in the First and Second World Wars; (of two or more things) similar or existing together; connected with something
例句: Churchill, Roosevelt, and Stalin were the main leaders of the allied forces in World War II.
例句释义: 在第二次世界大战期间，丘吉尔、罗斯福和斯大林是同盟军的主要领导人。

例句: Old people like to play mahjong for recreation.
例句释义: 老年人喜欢玩麻将作为消遣。

详细释义: adj.可笑的，荒唐的；  n.荒唐的事
英文释义: completely ridiculous; not logical and sensible
例句: It's absurd for a grown man to ride such a small bike.
例句释义: 成年人骑这么小的自行车是很可笑的。

例句: He gave in to his temptation to try the desserts.
例句释义: 他没能抵抗住这些甜点的诱惑。

例句: The city must rely on safe drinking water from the reservoir.
例句释义: 这个城市肯定是靠这个水库供给安全饮用水的。

详细释义: n.盛宴；节日；  v.尽情地吃
英文释义: a large or special meal, especially for a lot of people and to celebrate something
例句: This special feast consists of meats, vegetables, bread, wine and more.
例句释义: 这场特别的盛宴上有肉、蔬菜、面包和葡萄酒以及其他食物。

详细释义: n.比拟，比喻；类比；相似，类似
英文释义: a comparison of one thing with another thing that has similar features; a feature that is similar
例句: People often make an analogy between a student and a flower.
例句释义: 人们经常把学生比作花朵。

英文释义: a person who stands in front of an orchestra, a group of singers etc., and directs their performance, especially somebody who does this as a profession
例句: The conductor is leading the band.
例句释义: 乐队指挥正在指挥乐队。

英文释义: a person or an animal that lives in a particular place

例句释义: 小镇上有很多居民。

详细释义: v. 捆扎；  n. 带子
英文释义: to fasten somebody/something in place using a strap or straps; to wrap strips of material around a wound or an injured part of the body
例句: Strap the safety belt before driving.
例句释义: 开车前先为自己系上安全带。

例句: He is really determined to stop his bad habits and get fit.
例句释义: 他非常坚决地要改正恶习、保持健康。

例句: The product has the brand's logo.
例句释义: 这个产品上有该品牌的标识。

英文释义: to increase in degree or strength; to make something increase in degree or strength
例句: The microphone intensifies the loudness of my voice.
例句释义: 麦克风能扩大我说话的音量。

英文释义: an electric current passing across a space between two terminals; a curved shape; (geometry) part of a circle or a curved line
例句: The ball traveled in a perfect arc through the sky.
例句释义: 球在天空中划出了一道完美的弧线。

详细释义: v. 摇摆，摇曳；动摇（某人）；  n. 摇摆
英文释义: to move slowly from side to side; to move something in this way
例句: The willow tree swayed gently in the breeze.
例句释义: 柳树在微风中轻轻摆动。

英文释义: a student in the second year of a course of study at a college or university
例句: I will be a sophomore this year.
例句释义: 今年我就大二了。

英文释义: to increase sth as much as possible
例句: Maximize the volume if you still can't hear the sound clearly.
例句释义: 如果你还听不清声音，就把音量最大化。

详细释义: v.升级；提高；  n.改善，提高；升级
英文释义: to make a piece of machinery, computer system, etc. more powerful and efficient
例句: The sewing machines in our factory have just been upgraded.
例句释义: 我们工厂的缝纫机刚进行了升级。

详细释义: adj.显然的，明白无误的，明了的；  v.使显现，使显露，表明
英文释义: (formal) easy to see or understand
例句: His nervousness was manifest to all the audience.
例句释义: 观众能明显看出他的紧张。

例句释义: 小男孩抱紧了双臂，坚决拒绝吃饭。

英文释义: the process by which the surface of something is gradually destroyed through the action of wind, rain, etc.

例句释义: 这块岩石的奇怪形状是风力侵蚀的结果。

详细释义: v. 冲掉；脸红；清除；赶出；  n. 发红；  adj. 完全齐平的
英文释义: when a toilet flushes or you flush it, water passes through it to clean it, after a handle, etc. has been pressed
例句: Don't forget to flush the toilet after using it.
例句释义: 方便过后要记得冲厕所哦。

英文释义: having had a high standard of education; showing a high standard of education
例句: He is a highly educated scholar.
例句释义: 他是一个受过高等教育的学者。

详细释义: v. 舔；使无法理解；轻轻拍打；  n. 舌头一次舔的量

例句释义: 小女孩开心地舔着冰激凌。

英文释义: to arrange things so that they form a line or are in proper position
例句: Every car in the lot should be aligned with each parking space.
例句释义: 所有车停放的位置都应与停车位对齐。

详细释义: adj.强大的，强有力的；  adv.非常

例句释义: 狮子是非洲大陆上最强大的动物。

英文释义: a very stupid person; a person with very low intelligence who cannot think or behave normally
例句: He is such an idiot that he cuts the branch he stands on.
例句释义: 他简直是个傻子，竟然锯掉自己站着的那根树枝。

英文释义: based on your own ideas or opinions rather than facts and therefore sometimes unfair
例句: How people may view this image is subjective.
例句释义: 人们如何看待这幅画具有主观性。

英文释义: a device for controlling the flow of a liquid or gas, letting it move in one direction only; a structure in the heart or in a vein that lets blood flow in one direction only; a device in some brass musical instruments for changing the note

例句释义: 松开阀门后，水就可以流动了。

例句释义: 你需要一个好会计来帮你把钱弄到手。

英文释义: the quality of being reasonable, right, and just.

例句释义: 这座雕像是公平的象征。

例句释义: 一旦蛋壳开始破裂，它就会变得十分脆弱。

英文释义: a bird of prey (= a bird that kills other creatures for food) with large round eyes, that hunts at night
例句: Every night I hear an owl on the tree outside my room.
例句释义: 每晚我都听见房间外的树上有一只猫头鹰在叫。

英文释义: a sharp movement made with a knife, etc. in order to cut somebody/something; a long narrow wound or cut
例句: A hooligan slashed the tires on people's cars with a blade.
例句释义: 一个小混混用刀在别人的汽车轮胎上划口子。

例句: The villagers signed a petition asking for a new school.
例句释义: 村民们签署了一份请愿书，希望开办新学校。

英文释义: a person eating a meal (especially in a restaurant)

例句: This advertisement is to promote a new product.
例句释义: 这则广告的目的是推广新产品。

详细释义: n. 信件，函件；通信，通信联系
