例句释义: 你想在三明治上涂点芥末吗？

详细释义: n.绰号；昵称；  vt.叫错……的名字
英文释义: an informal, often humorous, name for a person that is connected with their real name, their personality or appearance, or with something they have done
例句: If I call my dog's nickname, he'll come to me.
例句释义: 如果我叫狗狗的昵称，他就会向我跑来。

英文释义: a person who lives in a village
例句: The villagers are working on the fields.
例句释义: 村民们在地里干活。

详细释义: pron.任何；无论什么；  adv.任何
英文释义: any or every; anything or everything; used when you are saying that it does not matter what somebody does or what happens, because the result will be the same
例句: The man covers his ears when others say whatsoever.
例句释义: 无论别人说什么，他都把耳朵堵上。

详细释义: n. 冰雹；  v. 下冰雹；歌颂
英文释义: small balls of ice that fall like rain
例句: He lifts up the basin to protect his head from the hail.
例句释义: 他用脸盆保护头部来免受冰雹的袭击。

英文释义: a piece of clothing
例句: We have all kinds of garments for you to wear.
例句释义: 我们有各式各样的服装供你穿。

英文释义: in secrecy; not openly
例句: The boy secretly put a birthday card in his sister's backpack.
例句释义: 那个男孩偷偷地把一张生日贺卡放在了他姐姐的书包里。

英文释义: located, done or used inside a building
例句: Natural indoor lighting saves on energy costs.
例句释义: 利用室内的自然光线可以减少能源消耗。

英文释义: to tell (someone) officially about something
例句: The employee was notified that he was fired.
例句释义: 这个员工被告知他被解雇了。

详细释义: v. 使开始起作用；使活动起来
英文释义: to make something such as a device or chemical process start working
例句: Press the power button to activate the machine.
例句释义: 按下电源键来开启机器。

英文释义: to use power or influence to affect somebody/something; to make a big physical or mental effort
例句: I exerted all my strength to lift all the boxes.
例句释义: 我用尽全力抬起这些箱子。

英文释义: having or showing a lack of experience or knowledge :innocent or simple
例句: It is naive of the boy to believe that he could grow coins.
例句释义: 那个男孩认为自己可以种硬币，这太天真了。

英文释义: a school or class for very young children
例句: Children are playing games in the kindergarten classroom.
例句释义: 孩子们正在幼儿园教室里玩游戏。

英文释义: one of various types of grass that produce grains that can be eaten or are used to make flour or bread. Wheat, barley and rye are all cereals.
例句: Wild cereals like rice were among the first crops people farmed.
例句释义: 像水稻这样的谷物是人类种植的第一批农作物。

英文释义: a waterproof overshoe that protects shoes from water or snow
例句: This type of animal lives only in the Arctic.
例句释义: 这种动物只生活在北极。

英文释义: a decorative cover for a bed, made of two layers with soft material between them
例句: When the weather gets cold, I sleep with a heavy quilt to stay warm.
例句释义: 当天气变冷时，我会盖一床厚被子保暖。

英文释义: aware of something
例句: It's a sensible choice to take only a few things when going climbing.
例句释义: 轻装上阵去爬山是一个明智的选择。

详细释义: n. 营业收入；人员更替率
英文释义: the total amount of goods or services sold by a company during a particular period of time
例句: The café's turnover for September was in excess of one million yuan.
例句释义: 这家咖啡馆九月份的营业额超过了一百万元。

详细释义: v. 使骨折；使折断；  n. 骨折；折断；裂口
英文释义: to break or crack; to make something break or crack
例句: He has fractured the bone in his leg during training.
例句释义: 他在训练中弄断了自己的腿。

英文释义: a large building with a square or triangular base and sloping sides that meet in a point at the top. The ancient Egyptians built stone pyramids as places to bury their kings and queens
例句: Egypt is famous for its ancient pyramids.
例句释义: 埃及以其古老的金字塔而闻名。

英文释义: (biology) a system of connected organs or tissues along which materials or messages pass
例句: The digestive tract allows your body to use food for energy.
例句释义: 消化道可以让你的身体把食物转化成能量。

英文释义: a man who has never been married
例句: After four years of hard work, I finally got my bachelor's degree!
例句释义: 经过四年的努力学习，我终于拿到了学士学位！

详细释义: adj. 卑微的；谦逊的；  v. 使……谦逊，使……卑下
英文释义: to make somebody feel that they are not as good or important as they thought they were
例句: The general rose from humble beginnings.
例句释义: 那位将军出身卑微。

英文释义: connected with the way in which a business, machine, system, etc. works; ready to be used
例句: The screen of my phone is broken, but it is still operational.
例句释义: 尽管屏幕坏了，我的手机还是可以正常使用。

英文释义: causing someone to believe that something is true or certain
例句: The cream on the cat's face is convincing evidence that it ate the cake.
例句释义: 猫脸上的奶油是它吃了蛋糕的有力证据。

英文释义: a person’s descendants are their children, their children’s children, and all the people who live after them who are related to them
例句: These people are the grandparents' descendants.
例句释义: 这些人是祖父母的后代。

英文释义: in a proud manner
例句: The boy is proudly showing his gold medal to his friends.
例句释义: 这个男孩骄傲地向朋友们展示他的金牌。

英文释义: a piece of cloth that is worn around the neck, for example for warmth or decoration. Women also wear scarves over their shoulders or hair.
例句: My scarf is fashionable, and it also keeps me warm.
例句释义: 我的围巾既时尚又保暖。

详细释义: n. 肿块；粗笨的人；  v. 成团，成堆；使成块；  n. 一小方块 (糖)
英文释义: a swelling under the skin, sometimes a sign of serious illness
例句: There is a lump on his neck.
例句释义: 他脖子上有一个肿块。

英文释义: a thing that makes something look more attractive on special occasions
例句: They're putting decorations on the Christmas tree.
例句释义: 她们在往圣诞树上放装饰品。

英文释义: any animal that gives birth to live babies, not eggs, and feeds its young on milk. Cows, humans and whales are all mammals.
例句: Humans, whales, cats and cows are mammals.
例句释义: 人、鲸鱼、猫和牛都是哺乳动物。

英文释义: a large round vegetable with thick orange skin. The seeds can be dried and eaten and the soft flesh can be cooked as a vegetable or in sweet pies.
例句: There are many pumpkins on the field.
例句释义: 地里放着很多南瓜。

英文释义: an arrangement of the parts of something or a group of things; the form or shape that this arrangement produces; the equipment and programs that form a computer system and the way that these are set up to run
例句: Our new computer network has a star-shaped configuration.
例句释义: 我们新的计算机网络是星状的布局。

英文释义: a wide highway that is built for fast travel
例句: The cars are driving on the freeway.
例句释义: 汽车在高速公路上行驶。

详细释义: vi. 发生冲突；发出撞击声；不合，不一致，不调和；  n. 冲突；抵触；撞击声
英文释义: to hit together and make a loud ringing noise; to make two metal objects do this
例句: The couple clashed over who should wash the dishes.
例句释义: 这对情侣为谁该洗碗的问题发生了冲突。

详细释义: n. 时事通讯，业务通讯
英文释义: a short written report that tells about the recent activities of an organization and that is sent to members of the organization
例句: From our newsletter, you can learn about how to take good care of your pets.
例句释义: 从我们的时事简讯中，你能学会如何照顾好你的宠物。

英文释义: to copy the way a person speaks or behaves, in order to amuse people; to copy somebody/something
例句: The boy imitates his father by shaving in the mirror.
例句释义: 小男孩对着镜子模仿父亲刮胡子。

英文释义: to add a number to itself a particular number of times
例句: Ten multiplied by eight is 80.

详细释义: adv. 向上地；  adj. 向上的
英文释义: towards a higher place or position
例句: The pilot tried to pull the aircraft into an upward climb.
例句释义: 飞行员试着驾驶飞机向上爬升。

详细释义: v. 咳嗽；  n. 咳嗽
英文释义: to force out air suddenly and noisily through your throat, for example when you have a cold
例句: He coughed badly when he was ill.
例句释义: 他生病时咳嗽得厉害。

详细释义: adj.臭名昭著的，声名狼藉的
英文释义: well known for being bad
例句: He is a notorious emperor in Chinese history.
例句释义: 他在中国历史上是个臭名昭著的君主。

详细释义: adj. 立体声的；  n. 立体声（装置）
英文释义: using a sound system that has two separate speakers so that you hear different sounds from each; produced by a system of this type
例句: Music fans love listening to music in hi-fi stereo system.
例句释义: 音乐爱好者喜欢用立体声设备听歌。

详细释义: n. 天鹅绒；鹿茸的嫩皮
英文释义: a type of cloth made from silk, cotton or nylon, with a thick soft surface
例句: These velvet blankets are very comfortable to touch.
例句释义: 这些天鹅绒毯子手感很好。

详细释义: adj. 致命的，致死的；  n. 致死因子
英文释义: causing or able to cause death
例句: A bite from this kind of snake is lethal!
例句释义: 被这种蛇咬一口可是致命的！

详细释义: vt.使必需，限定继承；  n.限定继承权
英文释义: to involve sth that cannot be avoided.
例句: Being a professor entails giving lectures, marking papers and supervising exams.
例句释义: 作为一名教授，就必然要上课、改试卷以及监考。

英文释义: a cylinder that turns around in a machine or device
例句: Use the roller to paint the walls.
例句释义: 用滚筒来刷墙。

详细释义: n. 橄榄；橄榄树；  adj. 橄榄色的
英文释义: a small green or black fruit with a strong taste, used in cooking and for its oil
例句: The best cooking oil is made from olives.
例句释义: 最好的烹饪油是用橄榄制作的。

详细释义: n. 烤面包，吐司；敬酒；  v. 为……祝酒
英文释义: the act of a group of people wishing somebody happiness, success, etc. by drinking a glass of something, especially alcohol, at the same time
例句: There are two slices of toast and some butter on the table.
例句释义: 桌上有两片吐司和一些黄油。

详细释义: n. 尝试，努力，尽力；  v. 努力，尽力
英文释义: an attempt to do something, especially something new or difficult
例句: Climbing this mountain is a risky endeavor.
例句释义: 爬这座山是一次冒险的尝试。

详细释义: n.凭据；  v.提供证明书；  adj.信任的
英文释义: the abilities and experience that make someone suitable for a particular job or activity, or proof of someone's abilities and experience
例句: You need good credentials to be a trained psychologist.
例句释义: 你得有资格证才能当心理医生。

详细释义: v. 打旋；大口喝酒；  n. 涡状形
英文释义: to move in circles or to cause (something) to move in circles
例句: She is swirling the wine in the glass.
例句释义: 她正让杯子里的葡萄酒旋转。

英文释义: something that makes it difficult to think or pay attention
例句: Texting while driving is a serious distraction for drivers, and can have serious consequences.
例句释义: 开车时发短信是一件让驾驶员分心的事，可能引起严重的后果。

详细释义: n. 火腿；  adj. 做作的，蹩脚的
英文释义: meat from the leg of a hog that is often prepared by smoking or salting
例句: Ham is made of pork.
例句释义: 火腿是猪肉做的。

详细释义: v. 闲逛，漫步，徘徊；眼睛或手（缓慢地）扫遍
英文释义: to walk or travel around an area without any definite aim or direction
例句: I don't know where we're going; I'd just like to roam the city for a while.
例句释义: 我不知道我们要去哪里，我就是想在城里闲逛。

英文释义: a large round bowl for holding liquids or for preparing foods in
例句: The basin in our bathroom was very clean.
例句释义: 我们浴室的水池很干净。

详细释义: v. 掷，抛；猛烈地移动；  n. 尽情欢乐的一阵，一时的放纵
英文释义: to throw somebody/something somewhere with force, especially because you are angry
例句: He?flung?a?handful?of?brown?dirt.
例句释义: 他把一捧黄土抛了出去。

英文释义: the animals kept on a farm, for example cows or sheep
例句: Livestock refers to animals kept to be sold or traded, such as cattle or sheep.
例句释义: 家畜是指以出售或交易为目的而饲养的动物，如牛或羊。

英文释义: a chemical substance that forms or produces a soft mass of very small bubbles, used for washing, shaving, or putting out fires, for example
例句: I made a heart with the foam.
例句释义: 我用泡沫做了个爱心的图案。

英文释义: showing extreme courage and admired by many people; of or relating to heroes
例句: An ordinary man may also make a heroic move.
例句释义: 一个普通人也能做出英勇的举动。

英文释义: a person who has the legal right to receive somebody’s property, money or title when that person dies
例句: The baby is the heir of his family.
例句释义: 这个小婴儿是他家的继承者。

英文释义: a building or chamber above or below the ground in which a dead body is kept
例句: The tomb is full of treasure.
例句释义: 墓穴里满是宝藏。

英文释义: to use one cost, payment or situation in order to cancel or reduce the effect of another
例句: The positives offset the negatives.
例句释义: 正负相抵了。

英文释义: having little or no hair on the head; without any of the usual hair, marks, etc. covering the skin or surface of something
例句: Wait, why am I combing my hair?―I'm bald, I don't have any hair.
例句释义: 等等，我为什么要梳头？我是秃头，我根本没有头发。

英文释义: a feeling of excitement about something (usually something good) that is going to happen
例句: She is full of anticipation―her baby is almost due.
例句释义: 她充满了期待，因为她的宝贝就要出世了。

英文释义: easy to do or to understand; not complicated; (of a person or their behaviour) honest and open; not trying to trick somebody or hide something
例句: The straightforward employee asked his boss for a pay raise.
例句释义: 那个直率的员工向老板提出加工资。

英文释义: to buy insurance so that you will receive money if your property, car, etc. gets damaged or stolen, or if you get ill/sick or die
例句: He insures the cars against traffic accidents.
例句释义: 他为车投了交通事故险。

详细释义: n.界面；【地质】分界面，接触面
英文释义: the way a computer program presents information to a user or receives information from a user, in particular the layout of the screen and the menus
例句: The most important part of a tablet computer is its user interface.
例句释义: 平板电脑最重要的部分就是它的用户界面。

英文释义: a shop/store that sells books
例句: She’s buying books in the bookstore.
例句释义: 她正在书店里买书。

英文释义: the leader of the Roman Catholic Church, who is also the Bishop of Rome
例句: The Pope is the head of the Catholic church.
例句释义: 教皇是天主教教会的领袖。

详细释义: adj. 脆的，易碎的，霜冻的，干脆的；  n. 油炸马铃薯片；  v. （使）发脆
英文释义: (of food) (also crispy) pleasantly hard and dry; (of fruit and vegetables) (also crispy) firm and fresh; (of the air or the weather) pleasantly dry and cold
例句: He likes eating potato chips because they are very crisp.
例句释义: 他喜欢吃薯片，因为它们很脆。

英文释义: the act of encouraging somebody to do something; something that encourages somebody
例句: His encouragement made her run even faster.
例句释义: 在他的鼓励之下，她跑得更快了。

英文释义: the quality of being honest
例句: The boy shows honesty by saying that he broke the vase.
例句释义: 男孩说是他打碎了花瓶，体现了自己的诚实。

英文释义: a mixture of finely chopped meat, fat, bread, etc. in a long tube of skin, cooked and eaten whole or served cold in thin slices
例句: I could eat sausage for breakfast, lunch, or dinner.
例句释义: 我早、中、晚餐都可以吃香肠。

英文释义: very beautiful and impressive
例句: The sunrise in the countryside is quite glorious.
例句释义: 乡间的日出非常壮丽。

英文释义: causing feelings of anger and annoyance
例句: There is nothing more frustrating than the computer crash at present.
例句释义: 现在没有什么比电脑死机更令人沮丧的事情了。

英文释义: if something overturns, or if somebody overturns it, it turns upside down or on its side
例句: I was so angry that I overturned my ice cream cone.
例句释义: 我十分生气，以至于我把甜筒冰激凌打翻了。

详细释义: adj. 小巧的，小型的，袖珍的，体积小的；紧密的，紧凑的，密集的；  v. 把……压紧；变得坚实；  n. 带镜小粉盒
英文释义: smaller than is usual for things of the same kind; using or filling only a small amount of space
例句: Smartphones are the most compact computers; they're much smaller than laptops.
例句释义: 手机是最小巧的电脑，它们比笔记本电脑小多了。

英文释义: to prevent somebody from having or doing something, especially something important
例句: The baby cried as his friend deprived him of the toy.
例句释义: 这个婴儿哭了，因为他的朋友抢走了他的玩具。

英文释义: nervous and afraid
例句: The girl is fearful of the imaginary monsters under her bed.
例句释义: 女孩对那些床下面想象出的怪物感到害怕。

英文释义: tending to select; characterized by careful choice
例句: She is very selective about the pearls used to make necklaces.
例句释义: 她对用于制作项链的珍珠很挑剔。

英文释义: the practice of thinking deeply in silence, especially for religious reasons or in order to make your mind calm; serious thoughts on a particular subject that somebody writes down or speaks
例句: Meditation helps him to relax and escape from the stress of work.
例句释义: 他借助冥想来放松，逃离工作压力。

详细释义: v. 颤抖，打战；颤动；  n. 颤抖，打战
英文释义: (of a person) to shake slightly because you are cold, frightened, excited, etc.
例句: The man's hand is shivering violently.
例句释义: 这个男人的手剧烈地抖动着。

详细释义: n.（牛津或剑桥大学的）指导教师，大学教师；  vt.穿上
英文释义: to put on (a piece of clothing)
例句: They are both respected dons of this university.
例句释义: 他们是这所大学里受人尊敬的教师。

英文释义: to grow well; to be healthy and happy
例句: Plants flourish with enough sunlight.
例句释义: 植物有充足的阳光就会茂盛。

详细释义: v. 放电；  n. 释放
英文释义: to release force or power
例句: The electric eel can discharge and use its current against smaller fish.
例句释义: 电鳗可以放电并利用电流对付小鱼。

英文释义: the main area of land of a country, not including any islands near to it
例句: This map of Africa shows both the mainland and an island.
例句释义: 这张非洲地图展示了非洲大陆和一个岛屿。

英文释义: an opinion or a way of thinking about ideas or situations
例句: The two ministers held conflicting standpoints on war issue.
例句释义: 两位大臣在战争问题上持有相反的观点。

详细释义: v. 用力拖（或拉）；  n. 猛拉；牵引
英文释义: to pull something hard, often several times; to pull something hard in a particular direction
例句: They are tugging the rope in the game.
例句释义: 他们在比赛中拉着绳子。

英文释义: a sea creature with a hard shell, a long body divided into sections, eight legs and two large claws (= curved and pointed arms for catching and holding things). Its shell is black but turns bright red when it is boiled.
例句: Lobster is a delicious kind of seafood.
例句释义: 龙虾是种美味的海鲜哦！

英文释义: support by one person or group of people for another because they share feelings, opinions, aims, etc.
例句: They're marching together to show solidarity with their leader in their fight for environmental reform.
例句释义: 在环境改革的斗争中，他们一起游行，表现出与领袖的团结一致。

英文释义: a place where a road leads away from the one you are travelling on
例句: Slow down before turnings.
例句释义: 转弯前要减速。

英文释义: the process of detecting something; the fact of being detected
例句: Good eyes are required for detection of tiny objects.
例句释义: 对微小物体的侦查需要好眼力。

例句: Given that whale sightings are a rare occurrence, these guys are very lucky!
例句释义: 考虑到目睹鲸鱼的事件极少出现，这些人可真是幸运！

详细释义: n. 鞍；鞍部；  v. 给马装鞍具；使负重担
英文释义: a leather seat for a rider on a horse
例句: There is a leather saddle on the back of the horse.
例句释义: 马背上有一套皮质的鞍具。

例句: A variety of artworks are on display in the museum.
例句释义: 博物馆里陈列着各种各样的艺术品。

详细释义: n. 党羽；虔诚信徒；  adj. 偏袒的；盲目推崇的
英文释义: a member of an armed group that is fighting secretly against enemy soldiers who have taken control of its country
例句: These two partisans attempt to cooperate with each other rather than competing.
例句释义: 这两个党派尝试着合作而非竞争。

详细释义: adj. 俯卧的；易于……的；有……倾向的
英文释义: likely to suffer from something or to do something bad
例句: The little baby is lying prone on the ground.
例句释义: 这个小宝宝正俯卧在地上。

详细释义: n. 输水软管；  v. 用水管冲洗（汽车等）
英文释义: a long tube made of rubber, plastic, etc., used for putting water onto fires, gardens, etc.
例句: Firemen pointed the hose at the fire, hoping to put it out.
例句释义: 消防队员把水管对准着火处，希望把火扑灭。

英文释义: the act or process of freeing a country or a person from the control of somebody else
例句: The slave got his liberation at last.
例句释义: 这个奴隶最终得到了解放。

英文释义: existing in large quantities; more than enough
例句: The fish in this pond are abundant.
例句释义: 池塘里的鱼太丰富了。

英文释义: a tool with a handle and a heavy metal head, used for breaking things or hitting nails
例句: I used a big hammer to push in the nail.
例句释义: 我用锤子来把钉子敲进去。

详细释义: adj.令人畏惧的；可怕的；难以克服的
英文释义: if people, things or situations are formidable, you feel fear and/or respect for them, because they are impressive or powerful, or because they seem very difficult
例句: In ping-pong competition tournament, he was a formidable opponent.
例句释义: 在乒乓球比赛中，他是一位令人畏惧的对手。

英文释义: the act or ceremony of burying a dead body
例句: The burial was the saddest part of the funeral.
例句释义: 下葬是葬礼中最令人悲伤的部分。

详细释义: adj. 不愿意的，不情愿的，勉强的
英文释义: not wanting to do something and refusing to do it
例句: The dog is unwilling to follow its master.
例句释义: 小狗不想跟着它的主人走。

英文释义: a small, thin package
例句: This packet of potato chips has been opened.
例句释义: 这袋薯片已经被打开了。

详细释义: n. 被排除在外的事物
英文释义: a person or thing that is not included in something
例句: The girl was upset about her exclusion from the group.
例句释义: 这个女孩因被排除在小组之外而烦恼。

详细释义: v. 动员起来；动员；鼓动起
英文释义: to work together in order to achieve a particular aim; to organize a group of people to do this
例句: Our teacher mobilized us to study harder for the exam.
例句释义: 我们老师动员我们要为考试更努力地学习！

详细释义: adj. 强有力的，有活力的；精力充沛的；强健的
英文释义: very active, determined or full of energy
例句: Exercises can make us more vigorous.
例句释义: 锻炼能让我们更有活力。

英文释义: unwilling to work or be active; doing as little as possible
例句: I feel lazy today. I just want to sleep.
例句释义: 我今天懒洋洋的，我只想睡觉。

英文释义: an official document that identifies you as a citizen of a particular country, and that you may have to show when you enter or leave a country
例句: I had to show my passport to the immigration official.
例句释义: 我必须向移民局官员出示护照。

英文释义: connected with marriage or with the relationship between a husband and wife
例句: They are enjoying their happy marital life.
例句释义: 他们的婚姻生活很幸福。

英文释义: feeling affection for somebody, especially somebody you have known for a long time; finding something pleasant or enjoyable, especially something you have liked or enjoyed for a long time;  liking to do something which other people find annoying or unpleasant, and doing it often; kind and loving
例句: The man is very fond of his horse.
例句释义: 这位男士很喜欢他的马。

英文释义: connected with photographs or photography
例句: There is a lot of high-tech photographic equipment in the studio.
例句释义: 工作室里有许多高科技摄影器材。

英文释义: that you have doubts about because you think it is not accurate or correct; likely to be dishonest or morally wrong
例句: The story he gave to the police officers is questionable.
例句释义: 他对警察说的话很可疑。

详细释义: n. 泰然自若，信心；  v. 使相等，使平衡
英文释义: a calm, confident manner
例句: We were all impressed by her poise and confidence.
例句释义: 她的镇定、自信给我们留下了深刻的印象。

详细释义: adj. 自制的；本国制造的，本地制造的
英文释义: made at home, rather than produced in a factory and bought in a shop/store
例句: The mother teaches the daughter to make homemade cookies.
例句释义: 母亲教女儿做自制饼干。

详细释义: adj.过剩的，多余的；  n.过剩，盈余
英文释义: an amount that is extra or more than you need; the amount by which the amount of money received is greater than the amount of money spent
例句: He has some surplus cash every month.
例句释义: 他每个月都可以存下一些闲钱。

英文释义: everything that is around or near somebody/something
例句: The village's surroundings are mostly forests and green lands.
例句释义: 村庄的周围主要是森林和绿地。

英文释义: very violent and cruel
例句: Crocodiles are vicious animals. Stay away from them if you can.
例句释义: 鳄鱼是一种凶残的动物，请你尽可能地远离它们。

详细释义: n. 楔子；  v. 楔入
英文释义: a piece of wood, rubber, metal, etc. with one thick end and one thin pointed end that you use to keep a door open, to keep two things apart, or to split wood or rock
例句: I drove a wedge through a log to split it in two.
例句释义: 我把楔子插入木头，将它一分为二。

详细释义: n.鹰；（高尔夫球赛中）少击两杆入穴的成绩；  vt.（高尔夫球赛中）比标准杆数少击两杆入穴
英文释义: a large bird of prey (= a bird that kills other creatures for food) with a sharp curved beak and very good sight
例句: A huge eagle is flying high in the sky.
例句释义: 一只雄鹰在天上飞翔。

详细释义: n. 扰乱，打扰；骚乱，混乱
英文释义: the act of disturbing somebody/something or the fact of being disturbed; actions that make you stop what you are doing, or that upset the normal state that something is in
例句: The loud music was such a disturbance whilst I was trying to work.
例句释义: 在我工作时，如此大声的音乐简直是巨大的干扰！

英文释义: covered with or containing sand
例句: A pair of sunglasses has been left on the sandy beach.
例句释义: 一副太阳眼镜被落在了沙滩上。

详细释义: adj.（神经）紧张的；  v.使拉紧；拉紧；  n.时态
英文释义: (of a person) nervous or worried, and unable to relax; (of a situation, an event, a period of time, etc.) in which people have strong feelings such as worry, anger, etc. that often cannot be expressed openly
例句: I feel really tense about the coming exam.
例句释义: 我真的很紧张即将来临的考试。

英文释义: time that is spent doing what you enjoy when you are not working or studying
例句: The busy employee enjoys his leisure time only on the weekends.
例句释义: 这个忙碌的员工只在周末有些闲暇时光。

英文释义: to send out something such as light, heat, sound, gas, etc.
例句: The little boy emits a ray of light from his hands.
例句释义: 小男孩儿用双手发射出一束光。

详细释义: adj. 制药的，药物的；  n. 药物
英文释义: of or relating to the production and sale of drugs and medicine
例句: This ancient medical book introduces some pharmaceutical knowledge.
例句释义: 这本古代医学书介绍了一些药物知识。

英文释义: the first design of something from which other forms are copied or developed
例句: The prototype of a new type of car is being exhibited.
例句释义: 一种新型汽车的样车正在展览中。

详细释义: n. 相识的人，熟人；认识
英文释义: a person that you know but who is not a close friend
例句: He met an old acquaintance at his friend's wedding.
例句释义: 他在朋友的婚礼上遇见了一位老熟人。

英文释义: plants in general, especially the plants that are found in a particular area or environment
例句: Some remote forests are rich in vegetation.
例句释义: 某些偏远的森林有着丰富的植被。

详细释义: adj. 比较的，相对而言的；  n. 比较级
英文释义: connected with studying things to find out how similar or different they are
例句: I did a comparative study of which kind of car uses the least fuel, and decided on the smallest car.
例句释义: 我对哪种车花费更少的油做了比较研究，然后选择了最小的那辆。

英文释义: a piece of material (such as iron or steel) that is able to attract certain metals
例句: Magnet can attract paper clips.
例句释义: 磁铁能吸起回形针。

英文释义: happening or needed during a particular season; varying with the seasons
例句: He makes a living by doing seasonal part-time work.
例句释义: 他靠做季节性兼职来维持生计。

英文释义: the feeling that somebody/something is without value and deserves no respect at all
例句: Her facial expression fully shows her contempt.
例句释义: 她的表情明显就是鄙视。

详细释义: n. 组件，模件，（航天器的）舱；（组成一门课程的）独立单元
英文释义: a unit of a computer system or program that has a particular function; one of a set of separate parts or units that can be joined together to make a machine, a piece of furniture, a building, etc.; a unit of a spacecraft that can function independently of the main part
例句: These are the different modules inside a computer.
例句释义: 这些都是电脑内部的不同组件。

英文释义: the fact of being more important, powerful or noticeable than somebody/something else
例句: He has complete dominance in company matters, because he holds a 90% share.
例句释义: 他在公司中处于支配地位，因为他有这家公司百分之九十的股份。

英文释义: enough or more than enough; (of a person’s figure) large, often in an attractive way
例句: We're lucky to have an ample amount of food to eat.
例句释义: 我们非常幸运能吃到这么多食物。

英文释义: a place where many kinds of wild animals are kept for the public to see and where they are studied, bred and protected
例句: There are so many animals in the zoo!
例句释义: 动物园里有好多动物啊！

英文释义: something that causes problems and tends to stop somebody/something from succeeding or making progress; a bad or undesirable quality or feature
例句: Compared with the short boy, the tall boy was at a disadvantage when the books fell.
例句释义: 与矮个子男孩相比，高个子男孩在书掉下来时处于不利地位。

英文释义: a long narrow line of colour, that is a different colour from the areas next to it
例句: The woman by the pool is wearing a black and white striped skirt.
例句释义: 池子边的这位女士穿着一个黑白相间的短裙。

英文释义: the most important or famous; in a position at the front
例句: Tesla is regarded as one of the foremost inventors of his generation.
例句释义: 特斯拉被视为他那一代人里最棒的发明家之一。

详细释义: adj.强效力的，烈性的；强有力的；有说服力的
英文释义: very effective or strong
例句: Potent drugs might have twice the effect of normal ones.
例句释义: 强效药的效力可能是普通药的两倍。

英文释义: to say something suddenly and loudly, especially because of strong emotion or pain
例句: "Help!" the woman exclaimed as the man stole her bag.
例句释义: 这个男人偷了她的包，她大喊：“帮帮我！”

英文释义: a place where you can safely cross a road, a river, etc., or from one country to another
例句: The sign shows a man walking on the crossing.
例句释义: 这个标志显示了一个走在人行横道上的行人。

英文释义: a person whose job is to take care of people’s teeth
例句: The dentist cleaned my teeth.
例句释义: 牙医清洗了我的牙齿。

详细释义: adj.不利的；（方向上）逆的；在相反的方向上移动（或运转）；相反的
英文释义: negative and unpleasant; not likely to produce a good result
例句: Bad teeth are one of the adverse effects of drinking too many carbonated beverages.
例句释义: 蛀牙是过度饮用碳酸饮料的坏处之一。

详细释义: adj. 学者气质的，学者风度的，学术的
英文释义: (of a person) spending a lot of time studying and having a lot of knowledge about an academic subject; connected with academic study
例句: Her glasses and all the books on her desk gave her a scholarly appearance.
例句释义: 她的眼镜以及放在桌上的书籍让她学者气质外漏无疑。

详细释义: n.悲伤；伤心事；  v.感到悲伤；为……悲痛
英文释义: a feeling of great sadness because something very bad has happened
例句: Her tears are full of sorrow.
例句释义: 她的眼泪充满悲伤。

英文释义: a mixture of flour, fat and water or milk that is rolled out flat and baked as a base or covering for pies, etc.; a small cake made using pastry
例句: I love the pastry so much. I'll eat them all!
例句释义: 我特别喜欢这种糕点。我要把它们全部吃完！

详细释义: adj. 省的；地方性的；偏狭的；  n. 地方人民；乡下人；外地人
英文释义: connected with one of the large areas that some countries are divided into, with its own local government
例句: Toronto is the provincial capital of Ontario province.
例句释义: 多伦多是安大略省的省会城市。

英文释义: to make something seem larger, better, worse or more important than it really is
例句: The sheep exaggerated the size of the wolf when retelling the story to his friends.
例句释义: 这只羊在向朋友们复述这个故事时夸大了狼的体型。

英文释义: a large structure used for the controlled production of nuclear energy
例句: The scientists are observing the nuclear reactor from afar.
例句释义: 科学家正在远处观察核反应堆。

英文释义: very important for the final result of a particular situation; able to decide something quickly and with confidence
例句: The last judge has the decisive vote in deciding the winner.
例句释义: 最后一个评委拥有选出胜利者的决定性一票。

详细释义: n. 拱洞；拱起；拱门；  v. 做成拱形
英文释义: a curved structure that supports the weight of something above it, such as a bridge or the upper part of a building
例句: The bridge has five arches.
例句释义: 这座桥有五个拱洞。

英文释义: a mountain with a hole in the top or side that sometimes sends out rocks, ash, lava, etc. in a sudden explosion (called an eruption)
例句: Watch out―the volcano is about to erupt!
例句释义: 小心！火山要喷发了！

英文释义: something that you say or do to greet somebody
例句: He exchanged greetings with his neighbor.
例句释义: 他和邻居互相问候。

英文释义: feeling angry or unhappy because somebody you like or love is showing interest in somebody else; feeling angry or unhappy because you wish you had something that somebody else has
例句: The boy was jealous as the girl received more praise from the teacher.
例句释义: 男孩因为那个女孩得到老师更多的表扬而感到嫉妒。

详细释义: n.轻声笑；  vi.轻声笑，咯咯地笑
例句: She covered her mouth and gave a little chuckle.
例句释义: 她捂着嘴巴，轻声一笑。

英文释义: connected with molecules (= small units of matter consisting of a group of atoms, into which a substance can be divided without a change in its chemical nature)
例句: You can only see this process at the molecular level.
例句释义: 你只能在分子水平上看见这个过程。

英文释义: land covered with grass that is suitable for feeding animals on
例句: What a beautiful sight―cows grazing peacefully on a green pasture.
例句释义: 牛在牧场上安静地吃草，这是一片多么美丽的景色啊！

详细释义: n. 沼泽；  v. 使困惑，压倒
英文释义: an area of ground that is very wet or covered with water and in which plants, trees, etc. are growing
例句: Crocodiles in the swamp are desperate for food.
例句释义: 沼泽里的鳄鱼极度渴望食物。

英文释义: an attempt by some of the people in a country to change their government, using violence
例句: These oppressed mushrooms were waging a rebellion against the brutal ruler.
例句释义: 这些深受压迫的蘑菇们对残暴的头领发动了一场反叛。

英文释义: to go somewhere very quickly
例句: The woman is dashing forward.
例句释义: 这个女人朝前猛冲。

英文释义: the body of voters who elect a representative for their area
例句: A constituency is a district that elects its own spokesperson to the House of Representatives.
例句释义: 选区是指选举自己的发言人进入众议院的地区。

详细释义: n. 共产主义者，共产党员
英文释义: a person who believes in or supports communism; a member of a Communist Party
例句: Communists hope to create an equal society.
例句释义: 共产主义者希望建立平等的社会。

英文释义: extremely good
例句: His surfing skills are truly awesome!
例句释义: 他的冲浪技术实在是非常好。

英文释义: a woman who is sexually attracted to other women
例句: The two lesbians live happily together.
例句释义: 这两位女同性恋者幸福地生活在一起。

详细释义: adv. 显然地；证据确凿地
英文释义: clearly; that can be seen or understood easily
例句: Evidently, it was my cat who ate my dinner!
例句释义: 很显然，我的猫偷吃了我的晚餐！

详细释义: n. 饵，诱惑物；  v. 辱骂，欺侮
英文释义: food put on a hook to catch fish or in nets, traps, etc. to catch animals or birds; a person or thing that is used to catch somebody or to attract them, for example to make them do what you want
例句: There's no better bait for a cat than fish.
例句释义: 对于猫而言，没有比鱼更好的诱饵了。

详细释义: adj. 疼痛的，酸痛的；  n. 疮
英文释义: if a part of your body is sore, it is painful, and often red, especially because of infection or because a muscle has been used too much
例句: Ugh! My back feels so sore!
例句释义: 啊！我的背好酸啊！

详细释义: adj.故意的；沉着的，小心谨慎的
英文释义: done on purpose rather than by accident
例句: Your making me fall wasn't an accident―it was deliberate!
例句释义: 你害我跌倒不是意外，你就是故意的！

详细释义: n. 禁令；封港令；  v. 禁止或限制贸易
英文释义: a government order that limits trade in some way
例句: The country imposed an embargo on the import of oil.
例句释义: 该国对石油进口发出了禁令。

英文释义: a person who writes novels
例句: This novelist wrote a series of famous books.
例句释义: 这个小说家写了一系列著名的小说。

英文释义: not real or true; existing only in stories; connected with fiction
例句: These fictional characters are based on real animals.
例句释义: 这些虚构人物是基于真实的动物。

英文释义: the way in which words are used in a language; the fact of something being used; how much something is used
例句: The teacher wrote out the correct usage of the word on the board.
例句释义: 老师在黑板上写了这个单词的正确用法。

详细释义: v.搭建，竖起；建造，建立；  adj.直立的，垂直的
英文释义: to build something; to put something in position and make it stand vertical
例句: It took him a long time to erect the tent.
例句释义: 搭建这个帐篷用了他很长时间。

详细释义: n. 誓言；誓约；咒骂；咒语
英文释义: a formal promise to do something or a formal statement that something is true
例句: The doctor took an oath to treat the sick to the best of his ability.
例句释义: 这位医生立誓要竭尽全力治疗病人。

英文释义: the state of not having, or not having enough of, something that is essential
例句: Sleep deficiency may cause dark circles under the eyes.
例句释义: 睡眠不足可能会导致黑眼圈。

英文释义: the son of your brother or sister; the son of your husband’s or wife’s brother or sister
例句: I can't wait to meet my nephew!
例句释义: 我等不及去见我外甥了。

详细释义: n.眩目的光；  v.怒目而视
英文释义: a very bright, unpleasant light
例句: The sun's glare made it hard to see.
例句释义: 太阳强烈的光线让它无法直视。

英文释义: connected with or contained in the food that you eat and drink regularly
例句: Dietary changes can accelerate weight loss.
例句释义: 饮食改变有助于减肥。

详细释义: n. 污点，模糊；  v. 使…模糊
英文释义: a shape that you cannot see clearly, often because it is moving too fast; something that you cannot remember clearly
例句: Everything is a blur when I take my glasses off.
例句释义: 我摘下眼镜后，眼前一片模糊。

英文释义: a substance added to soil to make plants grow more successfully
例句: She has many bags of fertilizer in her storage room.
例句释义: 她的储藏室里有许多袋肥料。

英文释义: (in stories) a creature like a small person, who has magic powers
例句: The story was about a fairy with butterfly wings.
例句释义: 这是关于有着蝴蝶翅膀的小仙子的故事。

详细释义: adj.冰冻的，冰冷的；冷冻用的
英文释义: extremely cold
例句: Look at her face! It must be freezing cold outside.
例句释义: 看看她的脸！外面肯定像冰冻一样寒冷。

英文释义: the height above sea level; a place that is high above sea level
例句: The altitude of this mountain is 8,844 meters.
例句释义: 这座山的海拔为8 844米。

英文释义: the quality of needing to be dealt with or happen immediately
例句: She ran with a sense of urgency, afraid of being late for the meeting.
例句释义: 她急匆匆地跑着，生怕开会迟到。

英文释义: to move or copy (a file, program, etc.) from a usually larger computer system to another computer or device
例句: Click on the second icon and you can download and watch the movie.
例句释义: 点击第二个图标，你就可以下载并观看这部电影了。

英文释义: the act or process of finding new people to join a company, an organization, the armed forces, etc.
例句: The young male villagers queued for the military recruitment.
例句释义: 村里的青壮年们排队参加新兵招募。

详细释义: adj.手巧的；方便的；伸手可及的
英文释义: easy to use or to do
例句: The handy girl makes adorable woolen dolls.
例句释义: 这个手巧的女孩儿会做可爱的羊毛毡玩偶。

英文释义: a small electric light that can be carried in your hand and that runs on batteries
例句: She always reads books with a flashlight at night.
例句释义: 她经常在晚上用手电筒看书。

英文释义: to recognize or show that two things are not the same
例句: It is hard to differentiate between the two pictures.
例句释义: 这两张照片很难区分。

详细释义: n.种族主义者；  adj.种族主义的
英文释义: a person with a prejudiced belief that one race is superior to others
例句: These racist huskies constantly discriminate against the corgis and their little legs.
例句释义: 这几只哈士奇是种族主义者，他们总是歧视柯基和他们的小短腿。

详细释义: adj. 多变的，各种各样的
英文释义: of many different types; not staying the same, but changing often
例句: The table was covered with a varied assortment of tools.
例句释义: 桌上放满了各种各样的工具。

英文释义: to work together with somebody in order to produce or achieve something
例句: They collaborated to draw up a business plan.
例句释义: 他们合作起草了一个商业计划。

英文释义: a number of people or things that follow each other in time or order
例句: A succession of horses passed us in the forest.
例句释义: 森林中，一匹匹马从我们身边经过。

英文释义: difficult to deal with
例句: This is definitely one of the most tricky projects he's worked on.
例句释义: 这绝对是他在工作中遇到的最棘手的项目之一。

英文释义: a woman whose job is to serve customers at their tables in a restaurant, etc.
例句: The waitress brought us two plates of salad.
例句释义: 女服务员给我们端来两盘沙拉。

英文释义: a part of something that is left after the other parts have been used, removed, destroyed, etc.
例句: They are looking at the remnants of what was once a huge castle.
例句释义: 他们现在看到的是当年一座大城堡的遗迹。

详细释义: n. 水泥，混凝土；胶合剂
英文释义: a grey powder made by burning clay and lime that sets hard when it is mixed with water. Cement is used in building to stick bricks together and to make very hard surfaces.
例句: We pour the cement in before it dries.
例句释义: 我们趁水泥还没干，把它倒进去。

英文释义: to repeat (a poem, passage, etc) aloud from memory before an audience, teacher, etc.
例句: The boy is reciting a text to his teacher.
例句释义: 男孩正在向老师背课文。

英文释义: having no job :not employed

例句释义: 她被老板炒了鱿鱼，这意味着她失业了。

英文释义: the food served in a restaurant (usually an expensive one)

例句释义: 这家餐厅提供日式菜肴，并且有着日式的装修风格。

英文释义: the act of interfering
例句: We hated it when there was interference in our chess games!
例句释义: 我们讨厌在下象棋的时候被人干涉！

英文释义: to build or place something in a particular position; to consider how an idea, event, etc. is related to other things that influence your view of it
例句: Our compass helped us situate ourselves.
例句释义: 我们的指南针帮助我们定位。

英文释义: meat from the back or sides of a pig that has been cured (= preserved using salt or smoke), usually served in thin slices
例句: I like to have bacon and eggs for my breakfast.
例句释义: 早餐我想吃培根和鸡蛋。

详细释义: vt.溺爱；毁坏；  vi.（食物）变质

例句: The grandparents spoil their grandchild by doing everything for him.
例句释义: 爷爷奶奶太宠他们的孙子了，恨不得替他把所有事都做了。

详细释义: v.摔跤，角斗；努力斗争；  n.摔跤，角力，扭斗
英文释义: to fight somebody by holding them and trying to throw or force them to the ground, sometimes as a sport
例句: I loved to wrestle and fight in college.
例句释义: 上大学时，我喜欢玩摔跤搏斗。

详细释义: v. 摧毁；使垮掉，使不知所措，使陷于混乱

例句释义: 火灾摧毁了这栋大房子。

英文释义: to not realize how good, strong, determined, etc. somebody really is

例句释义: 这个拳击手低估了他对手的实力。

英文释义: to find your position or the position of your ship, plane, car etc. and the direction you need to go in, for example by using a map; to sail along, over or through a sea, river etc.; to find the right way to deal with a difficult or complicated situation; to find your way around on the Internet or on a particular website
例句: Nowadays a smartphone can help you navigate your way around cities.
例句释义: 现在，智能手机可以帮助你在城市中导航。

详细释义: adj.健壮的，强壮的；精力充沛的
英文释义: strong and healthy;
例句: Drinking?milk?helps?you?build?a?robust?body.
例句释义: 喝牛奶能帮你强身健体。

英文释义: an item in a legal document that says that a particular thing must or must not be done
例句: The tenant will sign the tenancy agreement after checking every clause.
例句释义: 房客核对完每条条款后才会签署租房合同。

详细释义: adj. 效忠的，忠于…的，坚信的
英文释义: willing to give your time, energy, etc., to something
例句: The engaged couple had agreed to stay committed to each other.
例句释义: 这对已订婚的情侣已经达成协议会忠于对方。

英文释义: a short news report on the radio or television

例句释义: 学生正在读公告栏上张贴的一些通知。

详细释义: n.【昵称】亲爱的，宝贝；  adj.惹人喜爱的，迷人的
英文释义: a person you love very much

英文释义: the relation of plants and living creatures to each other and to their environment; the study of this
例句: Ecology is the study of the relationships between creatures and their environment.
例句释义: 生态学是一门研究生物与环境之间的关系的学问。

英文释义: the distribution of forces in preparation for battle or work

例句释义: 这只狗下令派遣了100名狗士兵帮助小猫们与猴子作战。

英文释义: a flat, hard area, especially outside a house or restaurant, where you can sit, eat and enjoy the sun

例句释义: 这个地方因美丽的水稻梯田而出名。

详细释义: adj. 西北方的，来自西北的
例句: The supermarket is in the northwestern corner of the town.

英文释义: to feel bitter or angry about something, especially because you feel it is unfair
例句: After quarreling over and over, the couple resented each other.
例句释义: 在一次又一次的争吵之后，这对夫妻互相怨恨起来。

例句: My garden becomes so colorful in the springtime when all the plants blossom.

英文释义: if somebody has a temper, they become angry very easily
例句: Stuck in traffic for over an hour, the man began to lose temper.
例句释义: 堵车一个多小时了，这个男人控制不住，开始发火了。

英文释义: the fact of not stopping or not changing; a logical connection between the parts of something, or between two things
例句: This loop can clearly visualize continuity.

详细释义: n.配饰；附件；配件；同谋；  adj.附属的；辅助的；同谋的
英文释义: a thing that you can wear or carry that matches your clothes, for example a belt or a bag
例句: Some girls like various accessories, such as sunglasses, hats and lipsticks.

详细释义: adj. 价值不大的；小的；器量小的；琐碎的
英文释义: small and unimportant
例句: Any?petty?cash?can?be?stored?in?the?jar.

详细释义: adj. 迂回的，间接的，不坦率的

例句释义: 宇宙飞船是用来探索宇宙中的未知区域的。

英文释义: using or connected with many complicated rules and ways of doing things :of, relating to, or like a bureaucracy or bureaucrat

英文释义: to encourage a horse to go faster, especially by pushing the spurs on your boots into its side

例句释义: 牛津大学是世界上最有声望的大学之一。

英文释义: very cold; covered with ice

例句释义: 这个男人正在冰湖里游泳。

例句释义: 应用数学适用于众多领域，比如生物学和计算机科学。

英文释义: a type of heavy oil used as a fuel instead of petrol/gas; a vehicle that uses diesel fuel

例句释义: 那个男人正在加油站给柴油货车加油。

英文释义: the structure of bones that supports the body of a person or an animal; a model of this structure

英文释义: a meeting in which people are given instructions or information
例句: My boss gave us a briefing about the new strategy.
例句释义: 老板做了简报给我们讲解新战略。

英文释义: to use a needle and thread to make stitches in cloth
例句: She uses the machine to sew a new dress.
例句释义: 她用机器缝制新裙子。

详细释义: adj. 令人不快的，讨厌的
英文释义: not pleasant or comfortable; not kind, friendly or polite
例句: There's an unpleasant smell coming out from the refrigerator.
例句释义: 有股难闻的味道从冰箱里冒了出来。

例句释义: 他的病令他的胃部遭受着尖锐的疼痛。

英文释义: seriously mentally ill and unable to live in normal society

例句释义: 这个精神病人已经完全疯了，因为他把自己想象成一条狗。

例句: The police find valid evidence to indict the wolf for murder.
例句释义: 警察找到了起诉大灰狼谋杀的有效证据。

例句: She found the book very entertaining.
例句释义: 她觉得这本书很有趣。

详细释义: adj. 引人注目的；  v. 作记号

例句: The tallest boy is marked in the bus line.
例句释义: 这个最高的男生在等车的队伍里很引人注目。

详细释义: adj.泥泞的；浑浊的；  v.搅乱

例句释义: 下雨过后这条路非常泥泞。

详细释义: adj. 职业的，军事占领的
英文释义: connected with a person’s job or profession

例句释义: 注意安全，提防工伤！

详细释义: n. 渡船，渡轮；  v. 渡运（人、车或物等）

详细释义: n. 杠杆作用；杠杆效率
英文释义: the action, power, or use of a lever

英文释义: (of paper, labels, etc.) with glue on one side so that you can stick it to a surface; made of or covered in a substance that sticks to things that touch it
例句: The glue on her hand is so sticky.
例句释义: 她手上的胶水好黏啊。

英文释义: a state of great anxiety and confusion

例句释义: 董事长卷款失踪后，公司陷入了混乱。

英文释义: very surprising; difficult to believe

例句释义: 他以惊人的速度从他们身边跑过！

英文释义: the state of being perfect

例句释义: 这个小女孩在数学考试中取得了优异的成绩。

英文释义: the priests or ministers of a religion, especially of the Christian Church

英文释义: the act of extending the period of time when something is effective or valid :the act of renewing something

例句释义: 有些鸟会飞到南方过冬。

详细释义: adj.热衷的，渴望的；  v.恸哭

详细释义: v. 定……的方位；  n. 【the Orient】东方
英文释义: to find your position in relation to your surroundings
例句: I used a compass to orient myself.
例句释义: 我用指南针来帮我定位。

英文释义: existing only in your mind or imagination
例句: The child is serving his imaginary customer.
例句释义: 这孩子在为他想象中的顾客服务。

英文释义: connected with or involving mathematics
例句: She is good at solving mathematical puzzles.
例句释义: 她很擅长解答数学难题。

英文释义: a child of a particular person or couple; the young of an animal or plant
例句: The parents love their offspring more than anything else.
例句释义: 这对父母爱他们的子女超过一切。

详细释义: n. 档案室，档案；  vt. 把……收集归档
英文释义: a place in which public records or historical materials (such as documents) are kept
例句: The man is checking and counting files in the archive.
例句释义: 那位男生在档案室里面清点文件。

英文释义: a large round stone, metal or wooden post that is used to support a bridge, the roof of a building, etc., especially when it is also decorative; a strong supporter of something; an important member of something; a person who has a lot of a particular quality
例句: These pillars hold the roof up.
例句释义: 这些柱子支撑起屋顶。

详细释义: v.黏附；遵守；坚持；附着，粘在……上
英文释义: to stick firmly to something
例句: I used glue to adhere the poster to the wall.
例句释义: 我用胶水把海报贴在墙上。

英文释义: a piece of paper that shows that goods or services have been paid for
例句: You will get a receipt when you buy things in a store.
例句释义: 当你在店里买东西时，会得到一个收据。

英文释义: clothes that you wear under other clothes and next to the skin
例句: Underwear is what you wear under your normal clothes.
例句释义: 内衣是你穿在普通衣服里面的衣服。

英文释义: the process or fact of making a substance or place dirty or no longer pure by adding a substance that is dangerous or carries disease
例句: The contamination of the river was caused by the dumping of raw sewage.
例句释义: 这条河流的污染是由未经处理便被排入河中的污水造成的。

英文释义: feeling worried or unhappy about a particular situation, especially because you think that something bad or unpleasant may happen or because you are not sure that what you are doing is right; not certain to last; not safe or settled; that does not enable you to relax or feel comfortable
例句: The man playing Mahjong felt uneasy when he got a phone call from his wife.
例句释义: 这个正在打麻将的男人接到老婆的电话，感到心神不宁。

英文释义: the act of taking something that belongs to somebody else, especially without permission; a sum of money to be used for a particular purpose, especially by a government or company
例句: He made an appropriation of the money for food to pay for his shoes.
例句释义: 他挪用了买菜的钱来给自己买鞋。

英文释义: the action of keeping something rather than losing it or stopping it; the action of keeping liquid, heat, etc. inside something rather than letting it escape; the ability to remember things
例句: Water retention is vital for a cactus to survive in the desert.
例句释义: 仙人掌要想在沙漠中存活，保存水分很重要。

英文释义: the fact of being lost or impossible to find
例句: The little sheep's disappearance has baffled his companions.
例句释义: 这只小羊的失踪让他的同伴感到很困惑。

英文释义: a road vehicle, usually with four wheels, that is pulled by one or more horses and was used in the past to carry people
例句: The prince helped me out of the carriage.
例句释义: 王子扶我走下马车。

英文释义: large, heavy guns which are often moved on wheels; the section of an army trained to use these guns
例句: The old artillery has been put by the seaside for many years.
例句释义: 这门老旧的大炮放在海边很久了。

英文释义: a person who gives a message to somebody or who delivers messages to people as a job
例句: The messenger is on his way to deliver the documents.
例句释义: 信使小哥正在送信的路上。

详细释义: n. 基本图案，主题，中心思想，【音】乐旨
英文释义: a single or repeated design or pattern
例句: The green motif on the tomato shows that it is organic.
例句释义: 番茄上的绿色图案表明了它是有机食品。

英文释义: the particular attitude or way of thinking of a person or group
例句: To win the race, it certainly helps to have a competitive mentality.
例句释义: 运动员们想要赢得比赛，当然要有竞争心理咯。

英文释义: a flat part at the side of a road for people to walk on
例句: People should walk on the pavement at the side of the road.
例句释义: 行人应该走马路侧边的人行道。

英文释义: slightly wet
例句: The grass is moist due to last night's heavy rain.
例句释义: 因为昨晚的大雨，草地湿漉漉的。

英文释义: a powerful vehicle with two large and two smaller wheels, used especially for pulling farm machinery
例句: We use tractors to farm.
例句释义: 我们用拖拉机来耕地。

英文释义: to arrange for an event, etc. to take place at a later time or date
例句: I had to postpone the meeting until later.
例句释义: 我不得不把这个会议向后推迟。

详细释义: n. 【金融】受益人，受惠者；  adj. 拥有封地的
英文释义: a person who receives money or property when somebody dies
例句: My son is the beneficiary of my will.
例句释义: 儿子是我遗嘱的受益人。

英文释义: not protected :not able to defend yourself
例句: The helpless zebra is caught by a lion.
例句释义: 这匹无助的斑马被狮子抓住了。

英文释义: angry disagreement between people
例句: There were only two candidates for the job left in contention.
例句释义: 这个职位只剩下两个候选人在争夺。

英文释义: a style of dancing that tells a dramatic story with music but no talking or singing
例句: Miss Elephant's dream is to become a ballet dancer.
例句释义: 大象小姐的梦想是成为一个芭蕾舞者。

英文释义: an activity that a person does for pleasure when not working
例句: Fishing is my hobby, so I often go to the lake on weekends.
例句释义: 我的爱好是钓鱼，所以我周末常去湖边。

详细释义: n. 决策者，政策制定者
英文释义: a member of a government department, legislature, or other organization who is responsible for making new rules, laws, etc.
例句: Policymakers have issued a new policy to reduce carbon emissions.
例句释义: 决策者们出台了一项新政策以减少碳排放。

英文释义: (specialist) the speed of something in a particular direction
例句: The velocity of the free kick was over 100km/h!
例句释义: 这脚任意球的速度达到了惊人的100km/h以上。

英文释义: to find an acceptable way of dealing with two or more ideas, needs, etc. that seem to be opposed to each other; to make people become friends again after an argument or a disagreement
例句: They are desperate to reconcile and fix their broken hearts.
例句释义: 他们迫切地想要和解，修复两人受伤的心。

英文释义: full of noise
例句: It's so noisy outside. I can't stand this kind of environment!
例句释义: 外面太吵了。我受不了这样的环境了！

英文释义: a person whose job is to clean other people’s houses or offices, etc.
例句: The cleaner needs different tools to do her job.
例句释义: 清洁工需要用各种工具来完成工作。

详细释义: n. 分隔间，火车车厢的分隔间
英文释义: one of the separate sections which a coach/car on a train is divided into; one of the separate sections that something such as a piece of furniture or equipment has for keeping things in
例句: The four compartments contain four different candies.
例句释义: 四个隔间装了四种不同的糖果。

英文释义: extreme anger that often includes violent behaviour; a state of being extremely angry about something
例句: He was full of fury when he saw that message.
例句释义: 当看到那条信息时，他愤怒不已。

详细释义: vt.侮辱；  n.侮辱的言辞或行为
英文释义: to say or do something that offends somebody
例句: The customer insulted the ice cream seller by throwing the money to the ground.
例句释义: 这个顾客把钱丢在地上，以此来侮辱卖冰激凌的小贩。

详细释义: adj. 自发的，无意识的；自然的，天真率直的
英文释义: not planned but done because you suddenly want to do it; often doing things without planning to, because you suddenly want to do them
例句: The father made a spontaneous decision to take his family to the beach that day.
例句释义: 爸爸做了个心血来潮的决定，想在那天带着全家去海滩。

详细释义: v.开始，着手；上船，登机；从事
英文释义: to get onto a ship; to put something onto a ship
例句: She embarked on a new career as a writer after quitting as a doctor.
例句释义: 她放弃当医生后，开始了新的作家生涯。

详细释义: adj.使人产生误解的，误导的；  v.把……引入歧途
英文释义: tending to deceive or mislead either deliberately or inadvertently
例句: The leaves are very misleading; he's chosen the smallest carrot!
例句释义: 这些叶子太有误导性了，导致他选了最小的那根胡萝卜！

详细释义: v. 开花；  n. 青春时期；兴旺时期
英文释义: to produce flowers
例句: These purple flowers bloom in spring.
例句释义: 这些紫色的花在春天开放。

详细释义: adj. 苗条的，修长的，纤细的
英文释义: (of people or their bodies) thin in an attractive or elegant way; thin or narrow; small in amount or size and hardly enough
例句: Ever since you started exercising, you've become so much more slender!
例句释义: 自从你开始运动，你就变得苗条多了。

英文释义: an often somewhat formal shirt for women and girls
例句: She is wearing a white blouse.
例句释义: 那个女士穿着一件白色的衬衫。

详细释义: n. 表现，表示；示威运动
英文释义: an event, action or thing that is a sign that something exists or is happening; the act of appearing as a sign that something exists or is happening
例句: Language?is?both a manifestation and a carrier of national?culture.
例句释义: 语言既是民族文化的表现，又是民族文化的载体。

详细释义: adj.明显的；完全的；  adv.完全
英文释义: looking severe and without any colour or decoration; unpleasant; real, and impossible to avoid; very different to something in a way that is easy to see; complete and total
例句: The high-end houses stand in stark contrast to the slums next to them.
例句释义: 高级住宅区与旁边的贫民区形成明显对比。

英文释义: a piece of jewellery consisting of a chain, string of beads, etc. worn around the neck
例句: She likes to wear many necklaces.
例句释义: 她喜欢戴很多项链。

英文释义: the state of being near somebody/something in distance or time
例句: Seats in economy class are in very close proximity to each other.
例句释义: 经济舱里的座位都靠得很近。

英文释义: a small magazine or book containing pictures and information about something or advertising something
例句: Travel brochures contain many beautiful pictures.
例句释义: 旅行手册里有许多漂亮的图片。

英文释义: the total length of the outside edge of an area or a shape
例句: It's easy to calculate the perimeter of the rectangle.
例句释义: 很容易算出这个矩形的周长。

英文释义: a liquid, often made from flowers, that you put on your skin to make yourself smell nice
例句: She uses a refrigerator to store her perfumes.
例句释义: 她用一台冰箱来存放她的香水。

详细释义: n. 【医学】牙齿定位器；  v. 支柱；支撑；加固；使绷紧
英文释义: a metal device that people, especially children, wear inside the mouth to help their teeth grow straight
例句: The braces would help to straighten her teeth.
例句释义: 牙套能帮助她矫正牙齿。

英文释义: to be a symbol of (something)
例句: This white bird symbolizes world peace.
例句释义: 白鸽象征着世界和平。

详细释义: n.（鸟或羊的）群；一群人；（对牧师而言的）教徒；  vi.聚集，成群而行
英文释义: a group of birds or animals (such as sheep)
例句: A flock of sheep were grazing on the grassland.
例句释义: 一群羊在草地上吃草。

英文释义: to make a substance pure by taking other substances out of it; to improve something by making small changes to it
例句: She refines the design of the car to make it travel faster.
例句释义: 她改进了这辆车的设计，使它行驶得更快。

英文释义: a state in which two people, companies, etc. are competing for the same thing
例句: The business rivalry is very intense, like a tug of war at the edge of the cliff.
例句释义: 商业竞争非常激烈，就像悬崖上的拔河一样。

英文释义: easily becoming a gas at a fairly low temperature
例句: This stock is very volatile, and it always experiences sharp increases and decreases.?
例句释义: 这只股票非常不稳定，它经常暴涨或暴跌。

英文释义: done carefully and with a lot of attention to detail; demanding that particular rules, processes, etc. are strictly followed
例句: The standards of selecting pilots are extremely rigorous.
例句释义: 选飞行员的标准非常严格。

英文释义: an animal that has a horse and a donkey as parents
例句: Mules are used to carry heavy loads on their saddles.
例句释义: 人们把重物放在骡子的鞍上，让它们运送重物。

英文释义: extremely pleased and excited about something
例句: She was delighted by her excellent mark in the final exam.
例句释义: 她因为期末考试取得了好成绩而非常开心。

英文释义: shaped like an egg
例句: The mirror has a pleasing oval shape.
例句释义: 这镜子是很好看的椭圆形。

详细释义: n.跨栏用栏，障碍；  v.跨栏，跨过
英文释义: one of a series of barriers to be jumped over in a race
例句: The athletes are jumping over the hurdles.
例句释义: 运动员们正跨过栏架。

详细释义: adj.结实的，坚固的；强壮的，健壮的
英文释义: (of an object) strong and not easily damaged
例句: This sturdy box can easily hold the weight of many books.
例句释义: 这个结实的箱子能轻松承受许多书的重量。

详细释义: n. 独木舟，轻舟；  v. 乘独木舟
英文释义: a light narrow boat which you move along in the water with a paddle
例句: The red canoe is resting on the shallow water.
例句释义: 这只红色独木舟停靠在浅水滩上。

详细释义: n. 草地，草皮；  v. 覆草皮
英文释义: the upper layer of ground that is made up of grass and plant roots
例句: The green turf is nice to walk on.
例句释义: 这绿油油的草地十分适合散步。

英文释义: to become wider; to affect or make something affect more people or things; to increase your experience, knowledge, etc.
例句: This once narrow track has been broadened into a wider road.
例句释义: 这条曾经的狭窄小道被拓宽成了一条宽阔的马路。

英文释义: all the people who work for a particular company, organization, etc.; all the people in a country or an area who are available for work
例句: The city's workforce accounts for about 60 percent of the population.
例句释义: 这座城市的劳动力约占总人口的 60%。

英文释义: a long journey, especially by sea or in space
例句: The ship is on a voyage now.
例句释义: 这艘船正在航行中。

详细释义: adj. 明确的，可靠的，权威的
英文释义: considered to be the best of its kind and almost impossible to improve
例句: The second employee's request for a raise was answered with an angry and definitive rejection.
例句释义: 又一个员工请求加薪，但遭到了愤怒而明确的拒绝。

英文释义: to move, drive or push something forward or in a particular direction; to force somebody to move in a particular direction or to get into a particular situation
例句: He used a paddle to propel the boat.
例句释义: 他用桨来划动船只。

英文释义: to change the shape, appearance or sound of something so that it is strange or not clear
例句: The stockings-on-head game distorts her face.
例句释义: 头上套丝袜的游戏让她的脸部变形了。

详细释义: n.勺，铲子；独家新闻；  v.挖，掘
英文释义: a kitchen tool like a spoon that has a usually thick handle and a deep bowl for taking something from a container
例句: The amount contained in one scoop of ice cream is not much.
例句释义: 一勺冰激凌的量并不多。

详细释义: adj. 超重的；  n. 超重；  vt. 在重量上超过
英文释义: (of people) too heavy and fat
例句: The girl with yellow hair is overweight.
例句释义: 这个黄头发的女孩超重了。

英文释义: happening or done quickly and immediately; doing something quickly
例句: This is the swiftest land animal by far.
例句释义: 这是目前陆地上最敏捷的动物。

英文释义: to open something that is fastened, tied or wrapped
例句: At the end of the day, the man undoes his tie.
例句释义: 一天结束后，这个男人松了松领带。

英文释义: progress in a job, social class, etc.; the process of helping something to make progress or succeed; the progress that is made
例句: The man with suitcase is on the way to career advancement.
例句释义: 那个提着公文包的男人正处于事业上升期。

英文释义: a woman who is loved or admired very much by other people
例句: Artemis, the goddess of hunting, was one of the figures in ancient Greek mythology.
例句释义: 狩猎女神阿尔忒弥斯是古希腊神话中的人物之一。

详细释义: n.茎，梗；  v.隐伏跟踪，（为搜索而）走遍
英文释义: a thin stem that supports a leaf, flower or fruit and joins it to another part of the plant or tree; the main stem of a plant
例句: The stalk of a cherry is very long.
例句释义: 樱桃的茎很长。

英文释义: to frighten or threaten somebody so that they will do what you want
例句: The big tiger is intimidating the small one to leave his territory.
例句释义: 这只大老虎正在恐吓小老虎，想让它离开自己的领地。

英文释义: a son of your son or daughter
例句: The grandpa put his grandson on his shoulders.
例句释义: 这位爷爷把他的孙子放在肩膀上。

详细释义: n. 边缘；边界；  v. 接近；濒临
英文释义: an edge or rim; margin
例句: The verge of the road is covered with lovely blue flowers.
例句释义: 路的边缘长满了可爱的蓝色花朵。

详细释义: n.瘟疫；灾难；麻烦；  v.折磨；烦扰；造成麻烦
英文释义: any infectious disease that kills a lot of people; a disease spread by rats that causes fever, swellings on the body and usually death
例句: The Black Plague took thousands of lives away in Middle Ages.
例句释义: 在中世纪，黑死病夺走了成千上万条生命。

英文释义: a member of one of the middle ranks in the army and the air force, below an officer; (in Britain) a police officer just below the rank of an inspector; (in the US) a police officer just below the rank of a lieutenant or captain
例句: The soldiers follow the orders of the sergeant.
例句释义: 士兵们听从中士的命令。

详细释义: n.一批（人或物）；一批生产量
英文释义: an amount of food, medicine, etc. produced at one time
例句: I just finished this batch of cookies―would you like one?
例句释义: 我刚刚做好这一批饼干，你要来一块吗？

详细释义: n.花边；鞋带；  v.加以修饰
英文释义: a long thin piece of material like string that goes through the holes on a shoe and is used to fasten it
例句: The?dress?is?trimmed?with?lace.
例句释义: 这条裙子上有花边作为点缀。

英文释义: to prevent (something) from happening
例句: Scary sharks deter people from swimming in the sea.
例句释义: 凶猛的鲨鱼使人们不敢在海里游泳。

详细释义: n. 有爵位的贵族；  v. 逞威风；  vt. 称…为勋爵
英文释义: a powerful man in medieval Europe, who owned a lot of land and property
例句: He's an English lord honored by the King.
例句释义: 他是一个被国王册封的英国贵族。

英文释义: (of a document, an agreement, etc.) to be no longer valid because the period of time for which it could be used has ended; (of a period of time, especially one during which somebody holds a position of authority) to end
例句: This card is already expired, so let me cut it up for you.
例句释义: 这张卡已经到期了，让我帮你剪掉吧。

详细释义: adj. 邻接的，毗连的；邻近的
英文释义: (of an area, a building, a room, etc.) next to or near something
例句: The Mongolian yurt is adjacent to the trees.
例句释义: 蒙古包和几棵树相邻作伴。

英文释义: dirty and/or untidy
例句: The child made the room really messy.
例句释义: 小孩将房间弄得一团糟。

英文释义: a person who smokes cigarettes, cigars, etc.
例句: The man with glasses is a heavy smoker.
例句释义: 这个戴眼镜的男人是一个重度吸烟者。

英文释义: a sudden event that causes many people to suffer; an event that causes one person or a group of people personal suffering, or that makes difficulties
例句: The tsunami was a huge catastrophe.
例句释义: 这场海啸是一个巨大的灾难。

详细释义: v. 抑制，拒绝给某事物
英文释义: to refuse to give something to somebody
例句: The man withheld some information when questioned by police.
例句释义: 这个男人在被警察盘问时隐瞒了一些信息。

英文释义: a hard yellowish-white substance like bone that forms the tusks (= long teeth) of elephants and some other animals; an object made of ivory
例句: It is not very common to see ivory crossing with another like this.
例句释义: 像这样交叉的象牙比较少见。

英文释义: a young animal or plant in the very early stages of development before birth, or before coming out of its egg or seed, especially a human egg in the first eight weeks after fertilization
例句: Embryos take shape in the womb of a woman.
例句释义: 胚胎在女性的子宫里成形。

英文释义: (of two or more events) to take place at the same time; (of ideas, opinions, etc.) to be the same or very similar; (of objects or places) to meet; to share the same space
例句: My birthday coincides with my wedding anniversary.
例句释义: 我的生日和我的结婚纪念日碰巧是同一天。

详细释义: v.超越（经验、理性、信念等）的范围，超过
英文释义: to be or go beyond the usual limits of something
例句: This pianist's beautiful music can transcend through cultures and ages.
例句释义: 这位钢琴家奏出的美妙音乐超越了文化和年龄的界限。

英文释义: a musical instrument with strings, that you hold under your chin and play with a bow
例句: She can play the violin well.
例句释义: 她小提琴拉得很好。

详细释义: adj.合算的；获利的；有利可图的
英文释义: producing a large amount of money; making a large profit
例句: E-business is a lucrative industry which brings up many billionaires.
例句释义: 电商是一个很赚钱的行业，造就了很多亿万富翁。

英文释义: (of an object or a building) decorated in a way that makes it attractive; intended to look attractive or pretty
例句: The decorative flowers hung on the wall look lovely.
例句释义: 挂在墙上的装饰性花朵看起来很漂亮。

英文释义: not affected by something; able to resist something
例句: The fire fighters' uniforms were fire resistant.
例句释义: 消防队员的制服是防火的。

英文释义: to go with somebody to protect or guard them or to show them the way
例句: The black car on the highway is being escorted by the police.
例句释义: 警察护送着这辆黑色轿车行驶在高速公路上。

英文释义: a piece of old, often torn, cloth used especially for cleaning things
例句: She used a rag to clean the glass window.
例句释义: 她在用抹布擦玻璃窗。

详细释义: n.售货摊；  v.（因故障而）停止
英文释义: a table or small shop with an open front that people sell things from, especially at a market
例句: There are many stalls in the open-air market.
例句释义: 露天集市上有许多货摊。

英文释义: the state of being kept in a place, especially a prison, and prevented from leaving
例句: He was kept in detention by the police.
例句释义: 他被警察拘留了。

英文释义: a person who tells lies
例句: That politician is a liar! Don't believe him!
例句释义: 那个政客是个骗子！别相信他！

英文释义: situated in or oriented toward the southeast
例句: This city is in the Southeastern United States.
例句释义: 这个城市在美国东南部。

英文释义: a formal agreement between two or more people, groups or countries, especially one in which they agree to help each other
例句: These countries finally came into a climate change pact.
例句释义: 这些国家最终达成了气候变化协议。

英文释义: to get information or a reaction from somebody, often with difficulty
例句: The kid is trying to elicit information from his mother about his birthday gift.
例句释义: 这个小孩试图从妈妈的嘴里探出生日礼物的消息。

详细释义: n.汗衫，背心，马甲；  v.给……穿衣服
英文释义: a piece of underwear worn under a shirt, etc. next to the skin
例句: I put on my white vest to get ready for exercise.
例句释义: 我穿上我的白色背心准备锻炼。

英文释义: The state of being intensely interested or attracted
例句: These foreigners have a fascination for the pandas and hotpot.
例句释义: 这群外国人对熊猫和火锅很着迷。

英文释义: to ask somebody for some information
例句: The policeman inquired about the escaped prisoner's whereabouts.
例句释义: 警察正在询问逃犯的行踪。

详细释义: n.半身塑像；  v.打碎；搜捕；  adj.破产的
英文释义: a stone or metal model of a person’s head, shoulders and chest
例句: The bust of Pythagoras honors the great Greek mathematician.
例句释义: 这尊毕达哥拉斯半身像是用来纪念这位伟大的古希腊数学家的。

英文释义: to be a sign of something
例句: Traffic signs signify different things you must do on the road.
例句释义: 交通标志显示了你在公路上必须遵守的各种规则。

详细释义: v.支持，鼓励；增强；  n.枕垫
英文释义: to improve something or make it stronger
例句: The trainer gave words of encouragement to bolster the little boy's confidence.
例句释义: 教练说了一些鼓励的话来增加这个小男孩的信心。

详细释义: v.迫使，使感激，施恩于，帮忙，使…成为必要
英文释义: to force somebody to do something, by law, because it is a duty, etc.; to help somebody by doing what they ask or what you know they want
例句: Tax payers are obliged to pay tax accordingly.
例句释义: 纳税人有义务按规定缴税。

详细释义: n. 假释；特别口令；  v. 有条件释放，假释
英文释义: permission given to a prisoner to leave prison before the end of a sentence usually as a reward for behaving well
例句: When on parole, a released prisoner must not break the conditions.
例句释义: 在保释期，被释放的囚犯必须遵守相关条件。

详细释义: v. 泼洒，溅，使成斑驳状；  n. 飞溅的水
英文释义: (of liquid) to fall noisily onto a surface
例句: She splashes cold water onto her face.
例句释义: 她把冷水泼到脸上。

英文释义: the respect and admiration that somebody/something has because of their social position, or what they have done
例句: He has considerable prestige owed to his educational achievements.
例句释义: 由于在教育方面的成就，他享有很高的威望。

英文释义: the height of a place, especially its height above sea level
例句: The mountain is at an elevation of 3000 meters above sea level.
例句释义: 这座山的海拔高度是3000米。

英文释义: like or suggesting poetry, especially because it shows imagination and deep feeling
例句: The lotus pond under the moonlight painted a poetic picture, arousing feelings of homesickness.
例句释义: 月光下的荷塘构成了一幅富有诗意的图景，唤起了思乡之情。

英文释义: a sentence of inquiry that asks for a reply
例句: The suspect remained silent throughout the interrogation.
例句释义: 在审问过程中，嫌犯一直保持着沉默。

英文释义: connected with language or the scientific study of language
例句: Spanish, Portuguese, and French all have linguistic similarities.
例句释义: 西班牙语、葡萄牙语、法语具有语言上的相似性。

英文释义: connected with the way in which the physical features of a place are arranged
例句: A geographical feature of this area is that it's rocky.
例句释义: 这个地方的一个地理特征就是多山石。

详细释义: n. 污渍，污迹；  v. 弄脏；玷污；染色
英文释义: a dirty mark on something, that is difficult to remove
例句: These ink stains are really hard to clean up.
例句释义: 这些墨水污迹真的很难清理干净。

英文释义: to remove a covering like a curtain from a new structure at a formal ceremony in order to show the opening or finishing of a new building or work of art
例句: The groom unveiled the bride's face.
例句释义: 新郎揭开了新娘的红盖头。

详细释义: adj. 迫近的，紧迫的，即将来临的
英文释义: happening very soon
例句: The bomb's detonation is imminent.
例句释义: 炸弹马上就要爆炸了！

详细释义: adv. 向后；退步，每况愈下
英文释义: towards a place or position that is behind
例句: When we both bend backwards, we almost make a complete circle.
例句释义: 当我们都向后仰的时候，我们几乎组成了一个完整的圆。

详细释义: v.拍手，鼓掌，击掌；  n.轻拍（以示热情招呼），拍手（喝彩），鼓掌（欢迎），善意的拍打
英文释义: to hit your open hands together several times to show that you approve of or have enjoyed something
例句: In a show of support, they all began to clap their hands.
例句释义: 为了表示支持，他们开始鼓掌。

详细释义: n. 锡箔纸；衬托；  v. 挫败；使受挫折
英文释义: metal made into very thin sheets that is used for covering or wrapping things, especially food
例句: The dark chocolate cakes in foil cups are put on the table.
例句释义: 桌上放着装在锡箔纸杯中的黑巧克力蛋糕。

英文释义: a direction measured from a fixed point using a compass
例句: The colored arrow of compass points to the bearing of northeast.
例句释义: 指南针上的有色箭头指向东北方向。

英文释义: having or showing a lack of respect for other people and their feelings
例句: It's very rude to jump the queue.
例句释义: 插队是很不礼貌的行为。

英文释义: a game, an activity, etc. that provides entertainment and pleasure
例句: These are examples of what most youngsters do for amusement.
例句释义: 这些是大多数年轻人娱乐的方式。

详细释义: v. 挖深，使变深；使……更糟糕
英文释义: if colour or light deepens or if something deepens it, it becomes darker
例句: The pit has been deepened by the worker.
例句释义: 这个坑已经被工人挖深了。

详细释义: adj. 活泼的，充满生气的
英文释义: full of interest and energy
例句: My grandpa is very animated although he is aged.
例句释义: 虽然我爷爷已经上了年纪，但他仍充满活力。

英文释义: a person or company from whom you rent a room, a house, an office, etc.; a man who owns or manages a pub or a guest house
例句: My landlord is fierce; nobody dares to owe her money.
例句释义: 包租婆太凶猛，没人敢欠她钱。

详细释义: v. 勒住；抑制；控制；约束；  n. 路缘；控制；约束
英文释义: to control or limit something, especially something bad
例句: Curb your horse now before it runs off the cliff!
例句释义: 在你的马掉下悬崖前，快勒住它！

详细释义: adj. 合成的，复合的；  n. 合成物，复合材料
英文释义: made of different parts or materials
例句: She made a composite photo of herself at the beach.
例句释义: 她合成了一张自己在海滩的照片。

英文释义: to lower your body to the ground by bending your legs
例句: The blonde woman in the blue skirt crouches.
例句释义: 那个穿蓝色裙子的金发女士蹲下了。

英文释义: to defeat somebody, especially in a competition, race, etc.;  to succeed in dealing with or controlling something
例句: I managed to conquer the difficulties in my work.
例句释义: 我成功地克服了工作上的困难。

英文释义: lasting for a long time
例句: The most important feature of stainless steel is that it is enduring.
例句释义: 不锈钢最重要的特点就是持久耐用。

英文释义: suggested without being directly expressed
例句: These emojis have implicit meanings.
例句释义: 这些表情符号具有隐含意义。

英文释义: as much or as many as is possible; not limited in any way
例句: The sea appears to be unlimited, I can't see where it ends.
例句释义: 大海看上去总是无边无际的，我看不到它的尽头。

详细释义: n.独裁者，独裁政权执政者；口授令他人做笔录者
英文释义: a person who behaves as if they have complete power over other people, and tells them what to do; a ruler who has complete power over a country, especially one who has gained it using military force
例句: My boss acts like a dictator to his employees.
例句释义: 我的老板像一个独裁者那样对待员工。

详细释义: v. 吸入（空气，烟，气体等），吸气
英文释义: to take air, smoke, gas, etc. into your lungs as you breathe
例句: The boy is inhaling some medication to stop himself coughing.
例句释义: 这个小男孩在吸入一些止咳的药物。

详细释义: adj. 即将出现的，即将到来的
英文释义: going to happen, be published, etc. very soon
例句: The forthcoming movie looks awesome; I can't wait to watch it!
例句释义: 这部即将上映的电影看起来很赞，我简直等不及去看了！

英文释义: the measurement from one side of something to the other; how wide something is; the distance between the two long sides of a swimming pool
例句: The man's width is smaller than his height.
例句释义: 这人的宽度小于他的高度。

英文释义: to go to where somebody/something is and bring them/it back
例句: "Here doggy, fetch!" I shouted as I threw the ball.
例句释义: 我一边扔球一边喊道：“小狗，接住！”

英文释义: a strong desire for more wealth, possessions, power, etc. than a person needs
例句: He has an insatiable greed for money.
例句释义: 他对金钱贪得无厌。

详细释义: adj. 圆形的；环形的；  n. 通知
英文释义: shaped like a circle; round
例句: All the staff members were asked to stand in a circular manner.
例句释义: 所有员工被要求站成一个圆形。

英文释义: a device that makes a long loud sound as a signal or warning
例句: The sound of the siren from the ambulance is actually by a dog.
例句释义: 救护车传来的警报声实际上是狗叫的。

详细释义: adj.疲倦的，困乏的，令人厌倦的；  v.使疲倦
英文释义: very tired, especially after you have been working hard or doing something for a long time; making you feel tired or bored; no longer interested in or enthusiastic about something
例句: The matchsticks keep that weary student's eyes open.
例句释义: 这名学生昏昏欲睡，只能用火柴棍来撑开眼睛。

英文释义: (of a seat, hotel room, house, etc.) empty; not being used
例句: There is a vacant seat between those two people.
例句释义: 那两个人之间有一个空位。

详细释义: v. 与……相配；补充；  n. 补充；互为补充的东西；补语
英文释义: to add to something in a way that improves it or makes it more attractive
例句: She is delighted that her new belt complements her dress so well.
例句释义: 新腰带和她的裙子很配，她非常高兴。

英文释义: unable to hear anything or unable to hear very well
例句: The girl is completely deaf; she can't hear anything.
例句释义: 这个女孩失聪了，什么也听不见。

英文释义: a large wild animal of the cat family, that has yellowish fur with black lines (= stripes) and lives in parts of Asia
例句: A tiger is running in the snow.
例句释义: 一只老虎正在雪地上奔跑。

英文释义: an event in which the people of a county, state, etc., vote for or against a law that deals with a specific issue :a public vote on a particular issue
例句: A referendum requires all qualified citizens to vote.
例句释义: 全民公投要求所有选民参与投票。

英文释义: to give something officially to somebody/something for a particular purpose
例句: Allocate one piece of cake to each person.
例句释义: 给每个人都分一块蛋糕。

英文释义: a person who has a million pounds, dollars, etc.; a very rich person
例句: This millionaire has more cash than he knows what to do with.
例句释义: 这个百万富翁钱多得不知道怎么花了。

英文释义: the side of a hill
例句: The couple sat on the hillside to have a picnic.
例句释义: 这对夫妻坐在山坡上享用野餐。

英文释义: a person, thing or situation that has two opposite features and therefore seems strange
例句: I don't understand why she is doing exercises while eating junk food―it's a paradox.
例句释义: 我不懂她为什么在锻炼的同时还在吃垃圾食物，真是自相矛盾。

英文释义: to feel and show sadness because somebody has died; to feel sad because something no longer exists or is no longer the same
例句: The woman in black is mourning the death of a loved one.
例句释义: 黑衣女士在棺材旁哀悼死去的爱人。

详细释义: adj. 稀少的，罕见的；缺乏的，不足的
英文释义: if something is scarce, there is not enough of it and it is only available in small quantities
例句: Water is scarce in this area.
例句释义: 这个地区十分缺水。

英文释义: a military operation in which an army tries to capture a town by surrounding it and stopping the supply of food, etc. to the people inside
例句: The police placed the bank under siege, waiting for the criminal to surrender.
例句释义: 警察包围了银行，等待罪犯投降。

详细释义: adj.很可能的；大概的；  n.很有希望被选中的人
英文释义: likely to happen, to exist or to be true
例句: It's probable that he will turn left because he is pretty hungry now.
例句释义: 他很可能会朝左走，因为他现在非常饿。

英文释义: to cook (food) on a barbecue; to broil or roast (meat, fish, etc.) over hot coals or an open fire
例句: My favorite food is barbecued meat.
例句释义: 我最喜欢的食物是烤肉。

英文释义: in a strange way
例句: These two carrots are very strangely shaped.
例句释义: 这两个胡萝卜外形长得非常奇怪。

英文释义: sure or certain; unlikely to change
例句: The police found definite proof that he committed the crime.
例句释义: 警方已经掌握明确证据，可以证明是他实施了犯罪。

英文释义: a person who changes words written in one language into a different language
例句: The translator is converting the English news report into Chinese.
例句释义: 这名译者正在把英文新闻报道翻译成中文。

英文释义: an area of low land that is always soft and wet because there is nowhere for the water to flow away to
例句: Make sure to wear boots if you go to the marsh.
例句释义: 去湿地的时候一定要穿靴子。

英文释义: to lead or be in charge of a meeting, ceremony, etc.
例句: The head of the company presided over this business conference.
例句释义: 公司领导主持了本次商务会议。

英文释义: happening slowly over a long period; not sudden
例句: The graph shows a gradual increase.
例句释义: 图表显示出了逐步增长。

英文释义: at the present time, in contrast with the past
例句: Nowadays, phones are more advanced than this brick.
例句释义: 现今，人们用的手机比这种板砖大哥大先进多了。

详细释义: v.取代，替代，迫使（某人）离开家园，使离开原位
英文释义: to take the place of somebody/something; to move something from its usual position
例句: The man feels depressed after being displaced in his job by a machine.
例句释义: 在他的工作被机器取代后，这个男人感到十分难过。

英文释义: to treat one person or group worse/better than another in an unfair way
例句: Discriminating against others is a bad behavior.
例句释义: 歧视他人是不好的行为。

详细释义: v.登记…作为商标；  n.特征
英文释义: to register something as a trademark
例句: This is the trademark of a popular APP.
例句释义: 这是一款很火的应用的商标。

英文释义: done alone; without other people; (of a person or an animal) enjoying being alone; frequently spending time alone; (of a person, thing or place) alone, with no other people or things around; (especially in negative sentences and questions) only one
例句: A solitary man is standing in the cold wind alone.
例句释义: 一个孤独的男人正站在寒风之中。

英文释义: a complete list of things that you can look at, buy, or use, for example in a library or at an art show
例句: The girl got information about the clothes from the catalogue.
例句释义: 小女孩能从产品目录中得到更多关于衣服的信息。

详细释义: n. 同性恋；  adj. 同性恋的
英文释义: a person, usually a man, who is sexually attracted to people of the same sex
例句: Homosexuals only love members of the same sex.
例句释义: 同性恋者只爱同性。

例句: People of all backgrounds are welcome in our multicultural society.
例句释义: 我们的多文化社会欢迎拥有各种背景的人。

详细释义: adj.南极的，北极的；极地的；截然对立的，正好相反的
英文释义: connected with, or near the North or South Pole
例句: Penguins and polar bears live in polar regions.
例句释义: 企鹅和北极熊住在极地地区。

英文释义: a young dog
例句: The two puppies are good friends.
例句释义: 这两只小狗是好朋友。

英文释义: a law forbidding the sale of alcoholic beverages

英文释义: the large nut of a tropical tree called a coconut palm. It grows inside a hard shell and contains a soft white substance that can be eaten and juice that can be drunk

详细释义: adj. 中值的；中央的；  n. 中值，中位数

详细释义: v.发出嗡嗡声，哼（歌曲）；  n.轰鸣声，嗡嗡声

详细释义: adj. 合成的，人造的；  n. 合成物

详细释义: v. 模仿，戏弄；  n. 模仿者

英文释义: to stop somebody/something from doing something, especially by using physical force; to stop yourself from feeling an emotion or doing something that you would like to do

详细释义: adj. 反应积极的，反应敏捷的
