英文释义: an attitude of doubting the truth of something (such as a claim or statement)
例句: My skepticism of other people's motives has almost always been well-founded!
例句释义: 我对他人动机的怀疑基本都是有依据的！

详细释义: adj. 叹为观止的，令人惊奇的；非凡的
英文释义: extremely good; wonderful
例句: "It is the most marvelous fireworks show!" the girl exclaimed.
例句释义: “这是最叹为观止的烟花表演！”这个女孩惊叹道。

详细释义: v.供应伙食；为（集会、婚礼等）承办酒席
英文释义: to provide food and drinks for a social event
例句: We hired a fancy restaurant to cater for our party.
例句释义: 我们雇了一家很棒的饭店给我们的派对供应伙食。

英文释义: a person who does hard physical work for money
例句: The laborer looks very confident.
例句释义: 这位工人看起来很自信。

详细释义: n.信赖，依靠；信赖的人或物
英文释义: the state of needing somebody/something in order to survive, be successful, etc.; the fact of being able to rely on somebody/something
例句: Babies have a significant reliance on their parents.
例句释义: 婴儿十分依赖他们的父母。

英文释义: the body’s ability to avoid or not be affected by infection and disease
例句: The little boy has a strong immunity to viruses.
例句释义: 这个小男孩对病毒有很强的抵抗力。

英文释义: a violent storm with very strong winds which move in a circle. There is often also a long cloud which is narrower at the bottom than the top.
例句: The tornado destroyed the whole village.
例句释义: 龙卷风毁掉了整个村庄。

英文释义: a game for two people played on a board marked with black and white squares on which each playing piece (representing a king, queen, castle, etc.) is moved according to special rules. The aim is to put the other player’s king in a position from which it cannot escape (= to checkmate it).
例句: The girl is playing chess with her dad.
例句释义: 女孩正在和爸爸下棋。

详细释义: n.万圣节前夕（指10月31日夜晚）
例句: On Halloween, children dress up to play tricks.
例句释义: 万圣节前夕，孩子们都装扮好去捣蛋。

详细释义: n.水牛，野牛（产于北美）；水陆两用坦克
英文释义: large shaggy-haired brown bison of North American plains
例句: The buffaloes are grazing on the pasture.
例句释义: 水牛们正在牧场上吃草。

英文释义: an animal with a long neck and one or two humps on its back, used in desert countries for riding on or for carrying goods
例句: The camel is known as the ship of the desert.
例句释义: 骆驼被称作沙漠之舟。

详细释义: n. 原子核，核心，细胞核
英文释义: the central part of an atom that is made up of protons and neutrons
例句: The nucleus is the center of the atom.
例句释义: 原子核就是原子的中心。

详细释义: adj. （头发）亚麻色的，金色的；  n. 金（浅）发女郎
英文释义: (of hair) pale gold in colour; (of a person) having blonde hair
例句: The model has long blonde hair.
例句释义: 这个模特有一头金色长发。

详细释义: vi.遵照，顺从；相一致；  adj.一致的
英文释义: to obey a rule, law, etc.
例句: Even the donkeys conform to the traffic regulations!
例句释义: 就连驴子都遵守交通规则！

详细释义: adj.值得（花时间、精力）的，有意义的
英文释义: worth doing or getting :good enough, important enough, etc., to be worth spending time, effort, or money on
例句: Studying English words with this app is definitely worthwhile!
例句释义: 用这个应用学英语单词绝对超值哦！

详细释义: n. 装载的货物；装船；装运；装货量
英文释义: a load of goods that are sent from one place to another
例句: I'm waiting for the shipment coming from India.
例句释义: 我在等待从印度运来的货物。

英文释义: a small lump that grows on a plant and from which a flower, leaf or stem develops; a flower or leaf that is not fully open; used to speak to a man you do not know
例句: The flower has not bloomed yet, but I can see the bud.
例句释义: 这花虽然还没有开，但是我可以看到花蕾。

英文释义: a feeling of respect and liking for somebody/something
例句: His superb carving skills filled me with admiration.
例句释义: 他精湛的雕刻技艺令我钦佩不已。

英文释义: a tool or piece of equipment used for specific activities
例句: Various pieces of apparatus are required when doing an experiment.
例句释义: 做实验时需要各式各样的仪器。

英文释义: to be strong enough not to be hurt or damaged by extreme conditions, the use of force, etc.
例句: We all have to withstand our own pressures in life.
例句释义: 我们都不得不承受各自的生活压力。

详细释义: v. 罚出，开除；排出；开除；驱逐
英文释义: to officially make somebody leave a school or an organization
例句: The referee expels a player from the game for not playing by the rules.
例句释义: 裁判将一名选手罚下场，因为他没有遵守比赛规则。

英文释义: a situation in which a plant, an animal, a way of life, etc. stops existing
例句: The extinction of this animal occurred around 66 million years ago.
例句释义: 这类动物的灭绝发生在大约6 600万年前。

英文释义: a general description or an outline of something
例句: This booklet provides an overview of the company.
例句释义: 这本书概括介绍了公司的情况。

英文释义: the feeling of being unwilling to do something and hesitating before you do it, because you do not want to do it or because you are not sure that it is the right thing to do
例句: I can see her reluctance clearly.
例句释义: 我能看出她明显不情愿。

英文释义: that exists or is very common at a particular time or in a particular place
例句: It's prevalent to use this kind of mobile telephones in the 90s.
例句释义: 20世纪90年代很流行用这种手机。

英文释义: by a small margin
例句: His grandfather can scarcely hear his grandson speaking.
例句释义: 他祖父听力不好，几乎听不到他孙子说的话。

英文释义: supply water to (land or crops) to help growth, typically by means of channels
例句: Irrigation helps provide grassland with water.
例句释义: 灌溉可以给草地补充水分。

详细释义: adj.无害的；仁慈的，和善的；（病）良性的
英文释义: (of people) kind and gentle; not hurting anybody
例句: Responsible use of your smartphone is relatively benign.
例句释义: 合理使用手机对你的身体相对无害。

详细释义: v. 缓慢地移动；拖累，迫使担负；伐木；杂乱地堆积；隆隆地行进；  n. 木材；废旧家具，不用的大件物品；无用的杂物；隆隆声
英文释义: to move in a slow, heavy and awkward way
例句: The old bus lumbered up the hill.
例句释义: 这辆旧公交车吃力地在坡上缓慢行进。

英文释义: a round vegetable with large green, purplish-red or white leaves that can be eaten raw or cooked
例句: I am cutting up this cabbage to make a salad.
例句释义: 我正在切卷心菜来做沙拉。

详细释义: adj.松弛的；懈怠的；萧条的；  v.变松弛；逃避工作
英文释义: not stretched tight
例句: The rope was slack, so he was able to escape.
例句释义: 绳子松了，所以他得以逃脱。

英文释义: with self-possession (especially in times of stress)
例句: Despite her naughty children and messy room, she still somehow manages to work calmly.
例句释义: 尽管孩子们调皮捣蛋，房间内乱七八糟，她还是设法平静地工作。

英文释义: the hard work and effort that somebody puts into an activity or a purpose because they think it is important
例句: His dedication to finding the vaccine was very admirable.
例句释义: 他致力于疫苗研发，令人钦佩。

英文释义: the unfair difference between groups of people in society, when some have more wealth, status or opportunities than others
例句: There is an inequality in family status between cats, dogs and people.
例句释义: 猫、狗和人的家庭地位是不平等的。

例句: The coherent plan meant that everyone knew how to reach the target.
例句释义: 协调一致的计划意味着每个人都知道如何实现目标。

英文释义: to take somebody away illegally and keep them as a prisoner, especially in order to get money or something else for returning them
例句: The girl was kidnapped by a strong male.
例句释义: 女孩被一个强壮的男人绑架了。

英文释义: very serious and sincere
例句: "Thank you very much!" said the granny with an earnest expression on her face.
例句释义: “非常感谢你！”这位老奶奶真诚地说道。

详细释义: adj. 恰当的；有（做某事的）倾向
英文释义: suitable or appropriate in the circumstances
例句: What he said was an apt description of the situation.
例句释义: 他说的话是对这种情况恰如其分的描述。

英文释义: the best possible; producing the best possible results
例句: Chopsticks would be the optimal choice to serve noodles.
例句释义: 筷子是吃面的最佳选择。

英文释义: the quality of being easy to understand or use; the quality of being natural and plain
例句: I love the simplicity of the single flower floating on the water.
例句释义: 我很喜欢一朵花漂浮在水面上这样简单的画面。

详细释义: vt.用订书钉订；  n.订书钉；主食；主要产品；  adj.主要的，基本的
英文释义: to attach one thing to another using a staple or staples
例句: Please staple the two sheets of paper together.
例句释义: 请把这两张纸订在一起。

英文释义: the story of a person’s life, written by that person; this type of writing
例句: This scientist's autobiography inspired me a lot.
例句释义: 这位科学家的自传给了我很大的启发。

英文释义: meant to be kept secret and not told to or shared with other people
例句: He destroyed the confidential document as soon as he had finished reading it.
例句释义: 他一读完机密文件就把它销毁了。

英文释义: the state of having more than one possible meaning; a word or statement that can be understood in more than one way
例句: Ambiguities arose from the confusing picture.
例句释义: 这张图片模棱两可，容易让人产生误解。

英文释义: able to exist together without trouble or conflict :going together well
例句: He is compatible with his friend because of their similar interests and opinions.
例句释义: 他和他的朋友很合得来，因为他们有相似的兴趣和观点。

英文释义: the commercial enterprise of transporting goods and materials
例句: Shipping costs are much lower than air freight.
例句释义: 船运的成本比空运低很多。

详细释义: adj. 易受感染的；易受影响的；多情的
英文释义: very likely to be influenced, harmed or affected by somebody/something
例句: Young children are susceptible to disease.
例句释义: 小朋友容易感染疾病。

例句: There will be a 5% deduction of his salary because he's late for work.
例句释义: 因为他上班迟到，他的工资将被扣除5%。

英文释义: attractive or interesting; showing that you want people to help you or to show you pity or sympathy
例句: The kids found the smells from their mother's dinner quite appealing.
例句释义: 孩子们觉得母亲做的晚餐香味诱人。

英文释义: remaining strict or determined
例句: It's almost 4 p.m., but the sun is still relentless.
例句释义: 都下午四点了，可太阳光还那么强烈。

英文释义: a pair of glasses with dark glass in them that you wear to protect your eyes from bright light from the sun
例句: The sunglasses suit her so much.
例句释义: 这副太阳镜很适合她。

英文释义: connected with relationships between people
例句: We can use interconnected blue lines to illustrate interpersonal relationships.
例句释义: 我们可以用相互连接的蓝线来表现人与人之间的关系。

英文释义: a container that is used for holding flowers or for decoration
例句: Beautiful flowers were kept in the red vase.
例句释义: 红色的花瓶中插着漂亮的花。

详细释义: v. 弄碎；使破碎；崩溃；破灭；  n. 碎屑；面包屑
英文释义: to break or break something into very small pieces
例句: He crumbled the snack noodle into pieces before eating it.
例句释义: 他在吃干脆面之前，把它捏得碎碎的。

英文释义: a set of stairs inside a building including the posts and rails (= banisters) that are fixed at the side
例句: Just walk up the staircase to get to the second floor.
例句释义: 请走楼梯上二楼。

英文释义: a thing such as a bath/ bathtub or a toilet that is fixed in a house and that you do not take with you when you move house
例句: Bathtubs and toilets are common fixtures in bathrooms.
例句释义: 浴缸和马桶是浴室中常见的固定装置。

详细释义: adj.母亲的，母性的；母方的，母系的
英文释义: of or relating to a woman who is having a baby
例句: The crazy fans were showing their maternal love for the three boys.
例句释义: 狂热的粉丝们对三个男孩表达了母性般的爱。

英文释义: to state officially, especially in writing, that something is true
例句: He was certified dead by the doctor.
例句释义: 医生证明他已经去世。

详细释义: adj. 愤世嫉俗的；恶意的
英文释义: believing that people only do things to help themselves rather than for good or honest reasons
例句: With that cynical outlook, he feels disappointed about the society.
例句释义: 抱着那种愤世嫉俗的观点，他对这个社会感到非常失望。

例句: She experienced terrible loneliness after the loss of her husband.
例句释义: 丈夫去世后，她饱受孤独之苦。

详细释义: n.商品，货品；  v.推销，经营
英文释义: goods that are bought or sold; goods that are for sale in a shop/store; things you can buy that are connected with or that advertise a particular event or organization
例句: The merchandise in this store is neatly folded and well presented.
例句释义: 这家店里的商品叠得整整齐齐，展示得很清楚。

详细释义: vi. 胜出；  vt. 优于
英文释义: to be very good at doing something
例句: The red man excels in running.
例句释义: 红色的小人在跑步中胜出了。

详细释义: adj.钝的；直率的；  v.感觉或需求减弱；变钝
英文释义: without a sharp edge or point
例句: These blunt pencils are no good for writing with.
例句释义: 这些钝铅笔不适合写字。

英文释义: the activity of working in a garden, especially for pleasure
例句: The family is doing gardening work in the garden.
例句释义: 这家人正在花园里做园艺工作。

英文释义: the feeling of being grateful and wanting to express your thanks
例句: On Father's Day, we show our gratitude to our fathers for raising us.
例句释义: 父亲节那天，我们向父亲表达感激之情，感谢他们辛勤养育我们。

英文释义: the ruler of an empire
例句: In ancient China, the emperor was the most powerful man.
例句释义: 在中国古代，皇帝是最有权力的人。

例句: Each of these hospitals has an affiliation with the medical college.
例句释义: 这些医院都与这所医学院有从属联系。

英文释义: having three parts or involving three people or groups; three times as much or as many as something
例句: The triple cheeseburger is the largest burger you can buy here.
例句释义: 这个有普通汉堡三倍大的芝士汉堡是你在这儿能买到的最大的汉堡。

英文释义: a difference, especially one connected with unfair treatment
例句: There is great disparity between the rich and the poor in economy.
例句释义: 富人和穷人在经济状况上有很大差距。

英文释义: a chemical substance in animals and plants that helps to cause natural processes (such as digestion)
例句: Saliva contains enzymes that are capable of breaking down bread in order to digest.
例句释义: 唾液中含有能分解面包以便消化的酶。

英文释义: connected with the official system for sending and delivering letters, etc.
例句: Our postal service is pretty good, so we always receive our mail on time.
例句释义: 我们邮局的服务特别好，所以我们总是准时收到我们的信件。

详细释义: n.圆柱体，圆筒；汽缸，泵（或桶）体
英文释义: a solid or hollow figure with round ends and long straight sides; an object shaped like a cylinder, especially one used as a container
例句: Do you know how to calculate the volume of a cylinder?
例句释义: 你知道怎么计算圆柱体的体积吗？

英文释义: a restaurant where you choose and pay for your meal at a counter and carry it to a table. Cafeterias are often found in factories, colleges, hospitals, etc.
例句: We had our lunch in a cafeteria.
例句释义: 我们在一家自助餐厅吃了午饭。

详细释义: adj.含糊不清的，引起歧义的，模棱两可的
英文释义: able to be understood in more than one way :having more than one possible meaning
例句: Do you see a vase or two faces? It's pretty ambiguous.
例句释义: 你看到的是一个花瓶还是两张脸呢？这张图模棱两可。

英文释义: to take (something, such as a machine or structure) apart so that it is in separate pieces
例句: The building is being safely dismantled.
例句释义: 大楼正被安全地拆除。

英文释义: showing high moral standards; allowing somebody to keep their good name and the respect of others
例句: At this honorable moment, he got his master's degree.
例句释义: 在这个荣耀时刻，他获得了他的硕士学位。

详细释义: n. （一）堆；大量；  v. 堆积
英文释义: a lot of something
例句: A heap of files are waiting to be classified.
例句释义: 有一大堆文件要归类。

例句: I'm happy with my seat allocation next to the window.
例句释义: 被分到了飞机上靠窗的座位，我真高兴。

详细释义: vi.滑翔；滑动；  n.滑翔，滑行；滑音，过渡音
英文释义: to move smoothly and quietly, especially as though it takes no effort
例句: The birds glide over the open ocean.
例句释义: 鸟儿们在广阔的海面上滑翔。

英文释义: to cover a surface with flat stones or bricks
例句: The trail had been paved with stone.
例句释义: 这条小径用石子铺成。

详细释义: adj.传染的；具有感染力的；易传播的
英文释义: if a person or an animal is infectious, they have a disease that can be spread to others
例句: Her yawn was so infectious that everyone in the office yawned with her.
例句释义: 她的哈欠极具感染力，以至于办公室里的每个人都跟着她打起了哈欠。

英文释义: a political movement that believes in an economic system in which the state controls the means of producing everything on behalf of the people. It aims to create a society in which everyone is treated equally.
例句: The idea of communism was first introduced by Karl Marx.
例句释义: 共产主义思想最初是由卡尔・马克思提出的。

英文释义: to happen before something or come before something/somebody in order; to go in front of somebody
例句: Click this button to browse the preceding text.
例句释义: 点击这个按钮以浏览前文。

英文释义: something that is done in advance in order to prevent problems or to avoid danger
例句: We wear masks as a precaution against catching a cold.
例句释义: 我们戴口罩来预防感冒。

英文释义: to cook something in hot fat or oil; to be cooked in hot fat or oil
例句: It's easy to fry eggs; I can make two for you.
例句释义: 煎鸡蛋很容易，我可以给你做两个。

英文释义: the underground railway system in some cities
例句: The metro is empty.
例句释义: 地铁里空无一人。

英文释义: connected with what something is like or how good it is, rather than with how much of it there is
例句: Changes in temperature can lead to qualitative differences.
例句释义: 温度的变化引起了质的差异。

详细释义: adj. 红外线的；  n. 红外线
英文释义: having or using electromagnetic waves which are longer than those of red light in the spectrum, and which cannot be seen
例句: The thief tried to sneak through the infrared security system.
例句释义: 小偷试图溜过红外线安防系统。

详细释义: n.（由壮观的景象等引起的）惊叹，惊奇；  vt.使敬畏，使惧怕
英文释义: feelings of respect and slight fear; feelings of being very impressed by something/somebody
例句: He gazed in awe at the magnificence of the Egyptian pyramids.
例句释义: 他敬畏地凝视着宏伟壮丽的埃及金字塔。

详细释义: adj. 不稳定的，不稳固的；反复无常的
英文释义: likely to change suddenly
例句: The scoops of ice cream are so unstable and are about to fall.
例句释义: 冰淇淋球摇摇晃晃，快要掉落。

详细释义: adv. 不变地，永恒地；总是
英文释义: not changing or capable of change; staying the same; not variable
例句: The Moon invariably orbits the Earth.
例句释义: 月亮始终围绕着地球转。

英文释义: the beginning of something, especially something unpleasant
例句: The referee's whistle indicates the onset of the game.
例句释义: 裁判的哨声表示比赛开始。

详细释义: n. 无数；极大数量；  adj. 无数的
英文释义: a very large number
例句: There are a myriad of colored bars.
例句释义: 有无数个彩色柱子。

英文释义: made warm or hot (`het' is a dialectal variant of `heated')
例句: There's no need to wear a sweater in a well-heated room.
例句释义: 在暖气很足的房里不用穿毛衣。

英文释义: a part of your income that you do not have to pay tax on
例句: There is a tax exemption when you buy perfume at the duty-free store.
例句释义: 你在免税店买香水的时候，是不用付税的。

详细释义: v. 侦察；监视；  n. 童子军，侦察员，守卫
英文释义: to search an area or various areas in order to find or discover something
例句: The soldier scouts the enemy in the grass.
例句释义: 这名战士躲在草丛里侦查敌军。

英文释义: pots, dishes, etc. made with clay that is baked in an oven, especially when they are made by hand
例句: Pottery is one of my favorite hobbies.
例句释义: 陶艺是我最大的爱好之一。

英文释义: not large, strong or important enough for a particular purpose
例句: One pea?! This meal is totally insufficient.
例句释义: 只有一个豌豆？这顿饭完全不够吃。

英文释义: either of the two long thin parts on the heads of some insects and some animals that live in shells, used to feel and touch things with; a piece of equipment made of wire or long straight pieces of metal for receiving or sending radio and television signals
例句: My TV's antenna is broken, so it doesn't work anymore.
例句释义: 电视天线坏了，所以它也无法工作了。

英文释义: (of an excuse or explanation) reasonable and likely to be true
例句: The scientist's research shows it is plausible that aliens can exist.
例句释义: 这位科学家的研究表明外星人的存在是可信的。

英文释义: (of a plane or passengers) in the air;
例句: He is looking at the airplane that is airborne.
例句释义: 他正看着空中的那架飞机。

例句: Stop harassing me with your snoring! Go sleep in the other room!
例句释义: 不要再让你的鼾声打扰我了！去另一个房间睡觉！

详细释义: adj.精力充沛的，充满活力的
英文释义: having or showing a lot of energy
例句: These elementary school students are very energetic.
例句释义: 这群小学生精力非常充沛。

英文释义: the principles of right and wrong that are accepted by an individual or a social group
例句: Anti-doping is an important code of ethics in sports.
例句释义: 反兴奋剂是体育界的一条重要道德准则。

详细释义: v. 授予（奖项、学位、荣誉或权利）；商讨，协商
英文释义: to give somebody an award, a university degree or a particular honour or right
例句: The president conferred a degree onto the graduating student.
例句释义: 校长授予这个毕业生学位。

详细释义: vt. 使瘫痪；使麻痹；使不能活动
英文释义: to make somebody unable to feel or move all or part of their body; to prevent something from functioning normally
例句: The disease may paralyze his body, but not his thinking.
例句释义: 疾病可以让他的身体瘫痪，却不能麻痹他的思想。

英文释义: to put somebody/something in a situation in which they could be harmed or damaged
例句: Cutting down trees will endanger the habitats of many animals.
例句释义: 砍伐树木会危及许多动物的家园。

英文释义: to make somebody feel shy, awkward or ashamed, especially in a social situation
例句: He was embarrassed when he couldn't afford the bill.
例句释义: 当他付不起账单时，他很尴尬。

英文释义: a large board on the outside of a building or at the side of the road, used for putting advertisements on
例句: The billboard on this highway is blank.
例句释义: 这段高速公路上的广告牌是空白的。

详细释义: adj. 有实质的；独立存在的
英文释义: dealing with real, important or serious matters
例句: When a rock is turned into gold, substantive change happens.
例句释义: 当石头变成黄金，实质性的变化就发生了。

详细释义: adj. 保暖的；温泉的；  n. 保暖内衣裤
英文释义: (of clothing) designed to keep you warm by preventing heat from escaping from the body
例句: Gloves, scarfs and thermal underwear help keep you warm in winter.
例句释义: 手套、围巾和保暖内衣能让你在冬天也暖暖的。

详细释义: adj. 白天的，日间的；  n. 白天
英文释义: the period during the day between the time when it gets light and the time when it gets dark
例句: Lots of daytime sleep is crucial to owls, as they go out hunting at night.
例句释义: 猫头鹰晚上觅食，所以充足的日间睡眠对猫头鹰很重要。

英文释义: a large plant that is smaller than a tree and that has several stems of wood coming from the ground
例句: The shrubs in the park had been pruned into the shape of ball.
例句释义: 公园里的灌木被修剪成了球形。

英文释义: to join things together into one; to be joined into one
例句: The two private taxi companies have been consolidated into one.
例句释义: 这两家打车软件公司已经合并了。

英文释义: a type of court with the authority to deal with a particular problem or disagreement
例句: The tribunal is a place where justice and fairness should be applied.
例句释义: 法庭是一个申张正义和公平的地方。

英文释义: the act of pressing; the exertion of pressure
例句: He has a lot of pressing work which is keeping him busy.
例句释义: 他有很多紧迫的工作要忙。

例句: Being aroused from sleep is the beginning of his day.
例句释义: 他新的一天从被闹钟唤醒开始。

英文释义: connected with teeth
例句: The boy opened his mouth ready for his dental examination.
例句释义: 男孩张开了嘴巴接受牙科检查。

英文释义: compartment where the pilot sits while flying the aircraft
例句: Pilots were sitting in the cockpit when flying.
例句释义: 飞行员在飞行期间坐在驾驶舱里。

例句: Preparing for the college entrance exam is a very stressful time for most students.
例句释义: 对大多数学生来说，备战高考的时候压力很大。

详细释义: n. 纸巾，餐巾，（小孩用的）尿布
英文释义: a piece of cloth or paper used at meals for protecting your clothes and cleaning your lips and fingers; a piece of soft cloth or other thick material that is folded around a baby’s bottom and between its legs to absorb and hold its body waste
例句: You have something on your face. Here, take this napkin and wipe it off.
例句释义: 哎呀，你脸上沾了东西。来来来，快拿纸巾擦擦。

英文释义: to remove things from a vehicle or ship after it has taken them somewhere
例句: It's going to take all afternoon to unload these boxes.
例句释义: 要把这些箱子卸下来得花一个下午的时间。

英文释义: having a lot of money and a good standard of living
例句: The affluent man has a lot of money.
例句释义: 这位富人非常有钱。

详细释义: adj.温暖舒适的，安逸的；  v.取悦
英文释义: warm, comfortable and safe, especially because of being small or confined; easy and convenient, but not always honest or right
例句: The baby looked very cozy sleeping on the soft blanket.
例句释义: 小宝宝看起来在柔软的毯子上睡得很舒服。

英文释义: a man who has been given a special honour by the king or queen and has the title Sir before his name; (in the Middle Ages) a man of high social rank who had a duty to fight for his king. Knights are often shown in pictures riding horses and wearing armour.
例句: The knight protected our village from intruders.
例句释义: 骑士保护我们的村庄免于被入侵。

英文释义: the waste liquid that collects in the bladder and that you pass from your body
例句: The doctor is doing a urine test.
例句释义: 医生正在进行一个尿检。

英文释义: the quality or fact of being very fat, in a way that is not healthy
例句: The man suffers from obesity and lives an unhealthy lifestyle.
例句释义: 那个患有肥胖症的男人过着一种不健康的生活。

英文释义: to make (a bad situation, a problem, etc.) worse
例句: Breathing in cigarette smoke exacerbated her cough.
例句释义: 被动吸二手烟加剧了她的咳嗽。

详细释义: v. 呻吟；抱怨；  n. 呻吟
英文释义: to make a long deep sound because you are annoyed, upset or in pain, or with pleasure
例句: The woman loudly groaned due to her splitting headache.
例句释义: 这个女人因剧烈的头痛而大声呻吟起来。

详细释义: v.（尤指作为常住居民）居住
英文释义: to live somewhere
例句: After dwelling in the broken shell for years, the snail moves out.
例句释义: 在这破壳里住了多年后，蜗牛决定搬家。

详细释义: adj. 牛奶般的；乳白色的
英文释义: like milk
例句: She took great care of her milky skin.
例句释义: 她把她牛奶般的皮肤保养得真好。

例句: Property and machinery are tangible assets, whereas stocks and shares aren't.
例句释义: 房产和机器设备是有形资产，而股票和股份则不是。

英文释义: an action or a piece of work that needs skill, strength or courage
例句: Swallowing a solid steel sword is an amazing feat!
例句释义: 吞钢剑真是一门神奇的技艺！

详细释义: adj. 好战的，好暴力的；  n. 激进分子，斗士
英文释义: using, or willing to use, force or strong pressure to achieve your aims, especially to achieve social or political change
例句: The?two militant?puppies?love?to?fight.
例句释义: 这两只好斗的小狗喜欢打架。

详细释义: n. 潜伏，潜行；  vi. 鬼鬼祟祟地走
英文释义: to be in a hidden place
例句: The lion is lurking in the grass, stalking a herd of deer.
例句释义: 狮子潜伏在草里，悄悄接近一群鹿。

英文释义: a small electric lamp that uses batteries and that you can hold in your hand; a long piece of wood that has material at one end that is set on fire and that people carry to give light;
例句: It’s too dark out here―use your torch, please.
例句释义: 这里太暗了，请把你的火把用上吧。

英文释义: grass that has been cut and dried and is used as food for animals
例句: Farmers always roll up hay so it's easier to move around.
例句释义: 农民总是把干草卷起来方便运输。

详细释义: n.侏儒；  vt.发育不全；  adj.矮生动物或植物的；发育不全的
英文释义: an extremely small person, who will never grow to a normal size because of a physical problem; a person suffering from dwarfism
例句: The Seven Dwarves were happy when staying with Snow White.
例句释义: 七个小矮人和白雪公主在一起时非常开心。

详细释义: v. 使结束，终止；  adj. 终止的；可结尾的
英文释义: to end; to make something end
例句: We terminated the contract to end our cooperation.
例句释义: 我们终止了合同来结束合作。

详细释义: n. 甲虫；  v. 快速移动
英文释义: an insect, often large and black, with a hard case on its back, covering its wings. There are several types of beetle.
例句: The boy is looking at the beetle specimens on the wall.
例句释义: 这个小男孩正在看墙上的甲虫标本。

英文释义: connected with the particular method you use to achieve something; carefully planned in order to achieve a particular aim; connected with military tactics; (especially of weapons) used or having an effect over short distances or for a short time
例句: It takes a lot of tactical moves in order to win a game of chess.
例句释义: 要在国际象棋中获胜需要很多战略性的棋步。

英文释义: a time of training and testing when you start a new job to see if you are suitable for the work
例句: You're under probation until you prove you can do the job by yourself.
例句释义: 你现在还在试用期，直到证明你有能力担任这个工作为止。

详细释义: n. 情妇；女教师；女主人
英文释义: a woman who has a sexual relationship with a married man
例句: That white tigress was the tiger's mistress.
例句释义: 白老虎是这只老虎的情妇。

详细释义: v. 操纵；  n. 花招
英文释义: a movement performed with care and skill; a clever plan, action or movement that is used to give somebody an advantage
例句: The skilled pilot can maneuver the helicopter very well.
例句释义: 这位熟练的飞行员可以很好地操纵直升机。

详细释义: v.聚集在一起，挤作一团；把身子蜷成一团，蜷缩；  n.挤在一起的人，一堆杂乱的东西
例句: Baby penguins huddle together while their parents are not around.
例句释义: 当父母不在身边时，小企鹅们会挤作一团。

英文释义: (especially in the past) a person on a ship who attacks other ships at sea in order to steal from them
例句: We're going to dress up as pirates for the costume party.
例句释义: 我们在化装舞会中要打扮成海盗的样子。

详细释义: n. （事故中）遭严重损坏的汽车（飞机等）；沉船，失事船；  v. 破坏，使毁灭
英文释义: a car, plane, etc. that has been very badly damaged in an accident
例句: The wreck of the plane was left here.
例句释义: 飞机残骸被遗留在这里。

英文释义: of or belonging to the class of words (called a gender) that ordinarily includes most of the words referring to males
例句: His beard and suit are masculine enough to show his charm.
例句释义: 他的胡子和西装都很有男子气概，足以展示他的魅力。

英文释义: a person who pays money, usually once a year, to receive regular copies of a magazine or newspaper; a person who gives money regularly to help the work of an organization such as a charity
例句: He is a subscriber to the Daily News and receives messages every morning.
例句释义: 他是《每日新闻》的订阅者，每天早上都会收到消息。

英文释义: the act of producing letters, pictures, patterns, etc. on something by pressing a surface covered with ink against it
例句: Magazine printing is a complicated process.
例句释义: 杂志印刷是一个复杂的过程。

英文释义: a small hard shiny white ball that forms inside the shell of an oyster and is of great value as a jewel
例句: I like to go deep sea diving for pearls.
例句释义: 我喜欢深潜到海里去寻找珍珠。

英文释义: the time of day when the light has almost gone, but it is not yet dark
例句: I enjoy watching the sunset at dusk.
例句释义: 我很享受在黄昏看日落。

英文释义: known and admired by many people for some special quality or achievement
例句: The Eiffel Tower is renowned for its beauty and simplicity.
例句释义: 埃菲尔铁塔以其美丽简约而著名。

英文释义: a medical condition that causes someone to become sick after eating, touching, or breathing something that is harmless to most people
例句: She has an allergy to pollen and cannot help sneezing whenever getting near the flower.
例句释义: 她对花粉过敏，一靠近花就忍不住打喷嚏。

英文释义: a change from one state to the opposite state
例句: A true role reversal is when children take care of their elderly parents.
例句释义: 一种真实的角色转换表现为孩子照顾年迈的父母。

详细释义: adj.令人失望的；令人扫兴的
英文释义: not as good, successful, etc. as you had hoped; making you feel disappointed
例句: I found the contents of my gift to be very disappointing.
例句释义: 当我看到礼物是什么的时候，我感到非常失望。

英文释义: the natural qualities of a person’s character
例句: He has an unhealthy disposition; he gets angry so easily.
例句释义: 他的性情不好，很容易就会发火。

详细释义: n. （用鸡蛋、牛奶等调制的）面糊；  v. 连续猛击
英文释义: a mixture of eggs, milk and flour used in cooking to cover food such as fish or chicken before you fry it, or to make pancakes; a mixture of eggs, milk, flour, etc. used for making cakes
例句: The mother is teaching her daughter how to make pancake batter.
例句释义: 妈妈正在教女儿怎么制作摊煎饼的面糊。

详细释义: n. 飞镖；猛冲；标枪；  v. 快速投掷；突然移动
英文释义: a small pointed object, sometimes with feathers to help it fly, that is shot as a weapon or thrown in the game of darts
例句: We love to throw darts for fun.
例句释义: 我们喜欢玩投飞镖。

英文释义: a person’s continued support for a political party, religion, ruler, etc.
例句: He swore his allegiance to the king.
例句释义: 他宣誓效忠于国王。

详细释义: n. 蜡；蜡状物；  v. 给…上蜡；  adj. 蜡制的
英文释义: a solid substance that is made from beeswax or from various fats and oils and used for making candles, polish, models, etc. It becomes soft when it is heated.
例句: The wax of the red candle fell on the table.
例句释义: 红蜡烛的蜡油滴到了桌子上。

英文释义: the very end of a finger
例句: I like drawing faces on my fingertips.
例句释义: 我喜欢在自己的指尖上画脸。

详细释义: vi.呜咽，抽泣；发呜咽声；哭诉；  n.呜咽，哭泣
英文释义: to cry noisily, taking sudden, sharp breaths
例句: The little boy is sobbing because his dog passed away.
例句释义: 这个小男孩在抽泣，因为他的狗去世了。

英文释义: a piece of clothing that covers the body from the waist down and is divided into two parts to cover each leg separately
例句: She wears a pair of yellow trousers.
例句释义: 她穿了一条黄色的裤子。

详细释义: n.融合，合并；核聚变；熔合物
英文释义: the process or result of joining two or more things together to form one; the act or process of combining the nuclei (= central parts) of atoms to form a heavier nucleus, with energy being released
例句: The metal is formed by the fusion of copper and iron.
例句释义: 这金属是由铜和铁熔合制成的。

详细释义: n. 铁锨，铲；  v. 铲起
英文释义: a tool with a long handle and a broad blade with curved edges, used for moving earth, snow, sand, etc.
例句: The shovel stands at an inclined angle in a pile of soil.
例句释义: 那个铲子斜立在一堆泥土上。

英文释义: a set of political and economic theories based on the belief that everyone has an equal right to a share of a country’s wealth and that the government should own and control the main industries
例句: The hammer and sickle represents socialism. Workers, unite!
例句释义: 锤头和镰刀代表了社会主义。工人们，团结起来！

详细释义: adj. 优雅的，优美的，得体的
英文释义: moving in a controlled, attractive way or having a smooth, attractive form; polite and kind in your behaviour, especially in a difficult situation
例句: She is such a graceful and beautiful actress!
例句释义: 她是一个如此优雅美丽的演员！

英文释义: a model of a person or an animal that can be made to move, for example by pulling strings attached to parts of its body or by putting your hand inside it. A puppet with strings is also called a marionette.; a person or group whose actions are controlled by another
例句: The little girl had fun playing with puppet prince and puppet princess.
例句释义: 小女孩和木偶王子、木偶公主一起玩得很开心。

详细释义: n. 批发；  adj. 大规模的；批发的
英文释义: in large quantities, especially so they can be sold again to make a profit
例句: Retailers buy things in wholesale.
例句释义: 零售商通过批发方式采购东西。

英文释义: a device or room for freezing food or keeping it frozen
例句: Fresh food goes in the top; frozen foods go in the freezer.
例句释义: 新鲜食物放上面；冷冻食物放进冷藏室。

详细释义: n. 小教堂；私人祈祷室
英文释义: a small building or room used for Christian worship in a school, prison, large private house, etc.
例句: We go to the chapel to praise God.
例句释义: 我们去小教堂祷告。

英文释义: to help someone or something pay for the costs of (something)
例句: The government subsidizes housing costs for those with low income.
例句释义: 政府为低收入者提供住房补贴。

英文释义: causing great suffering or loss
例句: The fire was disastrous and caused great damage to the church.
例句释义: 这场大火是灾难性的，给这座教堂造成了巨大的损失。

英文释义: an enemy or opponent
例句: These two adversaries are locked in a heated public debate.
例句释义: 这两名对手正陷于激烈的公开辩论中。

英文释义: having a lot of different parts and small details that fit together
例句: The inside of this watch is quite intricate.
例句释义: 这只手表的内部构造十分复杂精细。

详细释义: n.代金券；教育补助金券；  vt.证实……的可靠性
英文释义: a printed piece of paper that can be used instead of money to pay for something, or that allows you to pay less than the usual price of something
例句: I won a voucher worth $5000, but only for purchasing the private jet.
例句释义: 我得了一张5000美元的代金券，但是只能用来买私人飞机。

例句: This delicious burger has two slices of meat.

详细释义: n.小鸡；【美俚】少妇；  adj.胆小的

详细释义: n. 胶水；  v. 用胶粘

例句释义: 要把东西粘在一起，胶水会十分有用！

英文释义: all humans, thought about as one large group; the human race

例句释义: 人类社会中需要合作。

英文释义: not accurate or true

英文释义: an engine that has a part with blades that are caused to spin by pressure from water, steam, or air

英文释义: the act of betraying somebody/something or the fact of being betrayed

详细释义: adj. 焦点的，中心的，在焦点上的

例句: Do you know the eventual outcome of this chemical reaction?

详细释义: v. 否决；投反对票；  n. 否决权；禁止

例句释义: 士兵们历经了战时的精神创伤，在战后依然饱受折磨。

详细释义: n. 叛乱分子；  adj. 叛乱的，起事的

英文释义: a box that has a glass top or sides and that is used for displaying objects in a store, museum, etc.
例句: The vase is showcased in a glass case.
例句释义: 这个花瓶被放在玻璃柜里展示。

详细释义: adj. 凄凉的；萧瑟的；阴郁的；无希望的

英文释义: a covering of very thin transparent material worn, especially by women, to protect or hide the face, or as part of a hat, etc.; a thin layer that stops you from seeing something

例句释义: 他给予了这个足球运动员更严厉的惩罚。

详细释义: n. 日出；朝霞；  adj. 新兴的

例句释义: 桌子上有一些双莓枫糖浆烤薄饼。

英文释义: a simple drawing using lines to explain where something is, how something works, etc.

详细释义: v. 梳理；  n. 梳理

英文释义: bags, cases, etc. that contain somebody’s clothes and things when they are travelling

英文释义: a person who uses their strength or power to frighten or hurt weaker people

例句释义: 那个瘦小的男孩正在被大块头欺负。

英文释义: to go in a circle around a central point

例句释义: 旋转木马正在以很快的速度转动着。

英文释义: a piece of jewellery worn around the wrist or arm

英文释义: to make a substance or place dirty or no longer pure by adding a substance that is dangerous or carries disease; to influence people’s ideas or attitudes in a bad way

例句: He and his comrades fight together.
例句释义: 他和他的战友们一起战斗。

详细释义: n. 彩虹；呈彩虹状；彩虹状的；使呈彩虹状
英文释义: a curved band of different colours that appears in the sky when the sun shines through rain
例句: A rainbow arched across the sky.
例句释义: 一道彩虹横跨天际。

详细释义: adj.对立的，相互矛盾的；  n.矛盾的事物
英文释义: containing or showing a contradiction
例句: The gestures he is making are contradictory to what he is saying.
例句释义: 他比出的手势与他所说的话是自相矛盾的。

英文释义: happy and cheerful; used at Christmas to say that you hope that somebody has an enjoyable holiday
例句: I wish you a merry Christmas!
例句释义: 祝你圣诞快乐！

英文释义: to become or make something become flat or flatter
例句: We can use the rolling pin to flatten the dough.
例句释义: 我们可以用擀面杖把面团擀平。

英文释义: belonging to or part of the real nature of something/somebody
例句: Confidence is a quality which is intrinsic to this man.
例句释义: 自信是这个人的内在品质。

详细释义: adj.相应的；符合的，一致的；通信的
英文释义: having the same characteristics as something else: matching something else
例句: Each medal winner should stand on the corresponding platform.
例句释义: 每一位奖牌得主都要站在相应的领奖台上。

英文释义: [countable] a short sleep, especially during the day
例句: I need to take a nap this afternoon.
例句释义: 今天下午我得小睡一会儿。

例句: He had been waiting for twenty minutes and he was getting impatient.
例句释义: 他已经等了二十分钟，有点不耐烦了。

英文释义: at the time you are speaking or writing; now; used to show that something happened after a short time; used to show that something will happen soon
例句: Don't worry. The doctors will be here presently.
例句释义: 别担心，医生马上就到。

英文释义: to suffer or die because you do not have enough food to eat; to make somebody suffer or die in this way
例句: The bear is starving; it doesn't have enough food to eat.
例句释义: 这只熊快饿死了；它没有食物吃。

英文释义: to damage something or make something worse
例句: She?was?born?with?impaired?hearing.
例句释义: 她天生听力不好。

详细释义: adj. 疯狂的；狂乱的；慌乱的
英文释义: unable to control your emotions because you are extremely frightened or worried about something
例句: The staff are greatly?frantic?before?the?deadline?for?the?project.
例句释义: 员工在项目日期截止前异常狂躁。

英文释义: a tool or device with a sharp edge that is used to shave or cut hair from the face, body, or head
例句: He shaved his face with a?razor.
例句释义: 他正在用刮胡刀刮胡子。

英文释义: having a useful and helpful effect rather than being negative or with no purpose
例句: My teacher made some constructive suggestions about how I could improve my work.
例句释义: 在改进工作方面，老师给了我一些建设性的建议。

英文释义: (of land or soil) that plants grow well in
例句: The dung of cows makes the land more fertile.
例句释义: 奶牛的粪便让土地更肥沃了。

详细释义: v. 取回；开拓，开垦；废物回收利用
英文释义: to get something back or to ask to have it back after it has been lost, taken away, etc.
例句: Many years later, he reclaimed the treasure he had buried.
例句释义: 许多年后，他取回了过去埋下的宝藏。

英文释义: writing that is not poetry
例句: This piece of prose is famous for its beautiful language.
例句释义: 这篇散文因其优美的语言而著称。

详细释义: v. 使作呕，使厌恶；  n. 恶心
英文释义: if something disgusts you, it makes you feel shocked and almost ill/sick because it is so unpleasant
例句: What really disgusts me isn't one worm, but a half one in an apple.
例句释义: 真正让我恶心的不是在苹果中发现一条虫，而是半条虫。

英文释义: a pipe that is usually underground and that is used to carry off water and sewage
例句: The city sewer system carries away waste to then be treated.
例句释义: 城市下水道系统将废水排走，然后再进行处理。

英文释义: happening at the correct or most useful time; not happening too late
例句: The arrival of this man was timely.
例句释义: 这个男人及时到达了。

英文释义: to hold something, ready to use it as a weapon or tool
例句: The warrior wields his two swords.
例句释义: 这个战士挥舞着两把剑。

英文释义: a thick, flat piece of a hard material (such as stone or wood)
例句: Workers are paving road with stone slabs.
例句释义: 工人们在用石板铺路。

英文释义: a food that is made when bacteria is added to milk and that is often flavored and chilled
例句: There is a cup of yogurt on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上放了一杯酸奶。

详细释义: n.狐狸；狡猾的人；  v.欺骗，迷惑
英文释义: a wild animal of the dog family, with reddish-brown fur, a pointed face and a thick heavy tail
例句: The fox gave the boy flowers and sat beside him.
例句释义: 狐狸给了男孩花，并坐在他身边。

详细释义: vt.注定，使在劫难逃；  n.厄运，劫数；宣告，判决
英文释义: to make somebody/something certain to fail, suffer, die, etc.
例句: One bad move doomed him to failure in the chess competition.
例句释义: 走错的那一步棋注定了他在比赛中的失败。

英文释义: having or bringing a lot of rain

例句释义: 带上你的雨伞。外面在下雨。

英文释义: the daughter of your brother or sister; the daughter of your husband’s or wife’s brother or sister
例句: My niece is my sibling's daughter.
例句释义: 我的侄女或外甥女就是我兄弟姐妹的女儿。

英文释义: the way in which the parts of something such as the page of a book, a garden or a building are arranged
例句: The paper shows the layout of the flat.
例句释义: 这张蓝图画着这套公寓的布局。

英文释义: the fact of continuing to try to do something despite difficulties, especially when other people are against you and think that you are being annoying or unreasonable
例句: Persistence is key to achieving your goals.
例句释义: 坚持不懈是获得成功的秘诀。

英文释义: finely chopped beef made into a flat round shape that is then fried, often served in a bread roll
例句: He often eats a hamburger for lunch.
例句释义: 他午餐一般会吃一个汉堡包。

详细释义: adv.直立地；  adj.垂直的；正直的
英文释义: in or into a vertical position
例句: To my surprise, my dog can walk upright on his hind legs!
例句释义: 让我惊讶的是，我的狗竟然可以用后腿直立行走！

英文释义: to officially end a law, a system or an institution
例句: In the mid 1800s, slavery was abolished in America.

详细释义: adj. 偶然的，意外的；非本质的

例句释义: 他因为踩到香蕉皮而意外摔倒了。

英文释义: connected with breathing
例句: This picture shows the human respiratory system.
例句释义: 这张图片展现了人类的呼吸系统。

英文释义: a small container which has a measured amount of a medicine inside and which dissolves when you swallow it
例句: The medicine can be taken in capsule form.
例句释义: 该药可以以胶囊的形式服用。

详细释义: adj.自动驾驶的；自治的，有自治权的
英文释义: (of a vehicle) that has the technology to drive itself without a person in control

英文释义: a large sailing boat, often also with an engine and a place to sleep on board, used for pleasure trips and racing

例句释义: 今天我们把游艇开到海里去吧。

详细释义: n. 控制杆；施加影响的手段；  v. 用杠杆移动
英文释义: a long piece of wood, metal, etc. used for lifting or opening something by somebody placing one end of it under an object and pushing down on the other end

英文释义: of, relating to, or concerned with the art of speaking or writing formally and effectively especially as a way to persuade or influence people
例句: The sentence employs a particular rhetorical device.
例句释义: 这个句子运用了特定的修辞手法。

英文释义: a type of make-up, usually black, that is put around the edge of the eyes to make them more noticeable and attractive

详细释义: n. 图书管理员，图书馆馆长

英文释义: to free a country or a person from the control of somebody else; to free somebody from something that restricts their control over and enjoyment of their own life
例句: She felt her heart liberated together with the birds.
例句释义: 她感到自己的心随着鸟儿一起被解放了。

英文释义: an enemy

例句释义: 这条狗是这只猫的宿敌。

例句释义: 狗、猫和鸭子喜欢在一起洗澡。

例句释义: 海啸给这座城市造成了灾难性的破坏。

例句释义: 当听到这个坏消息时，这个人陷入了极大的痛苦中。

other.

例句: Ripples have formed upon the water's surface.
例句释义: 水面荡起了涟漪。

英文释义: within reasonable limits; to an average extent; fairly but not very
例句: I bought a moderately priced car: it is not too expensive nor too cheap.
例句释义: 我买了一辆价格适中的车：既不太贵也不太便宜。

英文释义: a fault in somebody’s character, a plan, a system, etc.
例句: His main shortcomings are laziness and greed.
例句释义: 他的主要缺点是懒惰和贪婪。

英文释义: inside or into a building
例句: This golf course also allows you to play golf indoors.
例句释义: 这种高尔夫课程能让你在室内也能打高尔夫。

英文释义: a line along which two edges of cloth, etc. are joined or sewn together
例句: There are seams on this white cloth.
例句释义: 这条白布上有接缝。

英文释义: to make somebody feel that they do not belong in a particular group
例句: He was alienated by his friends just because he was different.
例句释义: 他因为与众不同而被他的朋友们疏远了。

详细释义: v. 叮；刺疼；使苦闷；  n. （因被刺而引起的）疼痛
英文释义: to feel, or to make somebody feel, a sharp pain in a part of their body
例句: A bee stung me on the arm and it really hurt!
例句释义: 一只蜜蜂叮了我的胳膊一下，真疼！

英文释义: (of people) not working hard
例句: The man is idle when he should be working.
例句释义: 这个男人在应该工作的时候非常懒散。

详细释义: n. 筋疲力尽；耗尽，枯竭

例句释义: 她感到筋疲力尽。

英文释义: the scientific study of the structure of human or animal bodies
例句: The students are learning about the anatomy of a human.
例句释义: 学生们正在学习人体解剖学。

详细释义: v. 准确地解释或说明；  adj. 精确的；  n. 针尖，极小之物，极不重要的事物
英文释义: to find and show the exact position of somebody/something or the exact time that something happened; to be able to give the exact reason for something or to describe something exactly
例句: I pinpointed the enemy's position with the flag.
例句释义: 我用旗子标明了敌人确切的位置。

英文释义: a building in which films/movies are shown

例句释义: 这家影院有一个巨幕。

英文释义: (of clothes) old and torn

例句释义: 那双旧鞋子破烂不堪，你不能再穿它们了！

英文释义: the state of being alone, especially when you find this pleasant
例句: I am in solitude. My shadow is my only friend.

英文释义: showing the effects of too much alcohol; involving people who are drunk
例句: The drunken woman is sleeping on the bench.
例句释义: 这个喝醉的女人正在长椅上睡觉。

详细释义: v.不同意；不信奉国教；  n.（Dissent）不信奉国教

详细释义: n.薄雾，雾气；烟雾；  vt.（使）变糊涂
英文释义: air that is difficult to see through because it contains very small drops of water, especially caused by hot weather
例句: A few rays of sunshine shone through the forest haze.

详细释义: adj.景色优美的；舞台背景的，舞台的；  n.风景名胜

例句: The phone company disconnected my phone service because I didn't pay my bill.

详细释义: adj.勇敢的，英勇的，有胆量的

英文释义: undisputed credibility

英文释义: a liquid that you put on your skin in order to make yourself smell nice

例句释义: 她的香水很好闻。

英文释义: （of two or more lines, paths,etc.) to move towards each other and meet at a point

英文释义: by good fortune

例句: This couple often quarrel with each other over trivial stuff.

详细释义: n. 指定，名称，指示，选派

英文释义: the act of deliberately making somebody believe something that is not true (= of deceiving them); a trick intended to make somebody believe something that is not true

英文释义: a device for examining something or recording something using light, sound or X-rays

英文释义: a wide and open area of something, especially land or water

英文释义: a device in a wall that you put a plug into in order to connect electrical equipment to the power supply of a building

详细释义: adj. 水生的，水栖的，水中的，水上的

英文释义: a situation in which many people do not have enough food to eat

英文释义: a place where a person lives

详细释义: adj.坦白的，直率的；清楚表明的，明显的

英文释义: not based on, or not using, clear logical thought

英文释义: different from what is usual or expected, especially in a way that is worrying, harmful or not wanted

英文释义: to walk

英文释义: of or relating to a monument

例句: The girl is memorizing words to prepare for the coming test.
例句释义: 为了准备即将到来的考试，这个女孩正在记单词。

英文释义: having the total cost, or the cost of something that is mentioned, contained in the price; including all the days, months, numbers, etc. mentioned; including a wide range of people, things, ideas, etc.

例句释义: 他们正在进行前往西藏布达拉宫的朝圣之旅。

英文释义: to smoke a cigarette, pipe, etc.

英文释义: a small animal or plant that lives on or inside another animal or plant and gets its food from it

例句释义: 臭虫是一种可怕的寄生虫，它们靠吸血生存。

英文释义: action taken in return for an injury or offense
例句: The boy pulled her hair, who kicked him in retaliation.
例句释义: 这个男孩扯了她的头发，她踢了男孩一脚作为报复。

英文释义: the parts of a town or city that are furthest from the centre
例句: The areas outside of the fifth ring road are outskirts.
例句释义: 五环外的区域就叫郊区。

英文释义: grow worse
例句: Wet weather worsens my grandpa's joint pain.
例句释义: 潮湿的天气加重了我爷爷的关节疼痛。

英文释义: to eat all of something quickly, especially because you are very hungry
例句: The bearded man is devouring a big burger.
例句释义: 这个大胡子男人正大口吃着巨型汉堡。

详细释义: adj. 年老的；老年人特有的
英文释义: very old
例句: We may be old and aged, but our lives are great. We’ve got it made!
例句释义: 我们可能年纪大了些，但生活得很好。我们做到啦！

详细释义: adj.好吃的；(尤指女子)迷人的，性感的
英文释义: having a strong and pleasant flavour
例句: Wow, this is a tasty orange! I give it the thumbs-up.
例句释义: 哇，这个橙子太好吃了！我要给它点个赞。

英文释义: to make something easier to do or understand
例句: The character of the left is complicated. Can we simplify it, like on the right?
例句释义: 左边的字很复杂，我们能不能简化它，像右边一样？

英文释义: the act of somebody cutting your hair
例句: This is the baby's first ever haircut.
例句释义: 这个宝宝第一次理发。

详细释义: n.妒忌；妒忌的对象；  v.嫉妒，羡慕
英文释义: the feeling of wanting to be in the same situation as somebody else; the feeling of wanting something that somebody else has
例句: The little puppy envies the big dog who has a ball to play with.
例句释义: 小狗嫉妒那只有球可以玩的大狗。

详细释义: adj.明显的，显著的；引人注目的
英文释义: easy to see or notice; clear or definite
例句: It was noticeable that the rabbit's friend was in the snake's stomach.
例句释义: 显而易见的是，小兔子的朋友在蛇的肚子里。

英文释义: to raise, move, or open (something) with a tool
例句: I'll have to pry the nails out with this tool.
例句释义: 我要用这个工具把钉子撬出来。

英文释义: the denomination of a banknote or coin is its official value
例句: These?banknotes?come?in?various?denominations.
例句释义: 这些钞票有着不同的面额。

详细释义: n. 公鸡；架子十足的人
英文释义: an adult male chicken
例句: The cock has a beautiful tail.
例句释义: 这只公鸡的尾巴很漂亮。

英文释义: a reference book that contains words listed in alphabetical order and that gives information about the words' meanings, forms, pronunciations, etc.
例句: Use this dictionary if there are any words you don't know.
例句释义: 如果有不认识的单词，用这本字典查查。

英文释义: a small piece of material or paper that you use for blowing your nose, etc.
例句: These handkerchiefs have flowers on them.
例句释义: 这些手帕上有绣花。

英文释义: two people or things that are complementary are different but together form a useful or attractive combination of skills, qualities or physical features
例句: These two people are complementary to each other. They are a perfect match.
例句释义: 这两个人彼此互补，他们在一起就是完美的搭档。

英文释义: if something radiates heat, light or energy or heat, etc. radiates from it, the heat is sent out in all directions
例句: The sun radiates light and heat towards the earth.
例句释义: 太阳向地球发出光和热。

英文释义: by which; because of which
例句: The famous singer runs several successful businesses whereby she has made a ton of cash!
例句释义: 这位著名歌手凭借成功地经营多种事业，赚了一大笔钱！

详细释义: adv. （形容不快或伤痛）极其，非常；伤心地，愤怒地
英文释义: in a way that shows feelings of sadness or ange
例句: This lemon has bitterly sour flavor.
例句释义: 这柠檬有股强烈的酸味。

详细释义: n. 抵制；  vt. 抵制
英文释义: an act of boycotting somebody/something
例句: The office workers are putting up a boycott.
例句释义: 员工们在举行抗议活动。

例句: The cat is looking curiously into the box.
例句释义: 猫咪正好奇地朝着箱子里面看。

英文释义: showing kindness towards people and animals by making sure that they do not suffer more than is necessary
例句: Volunteering to help the homeless is a very humane act.
例句释义: 自愿帮助无家可归的人是一种非常人道的行为。

详细释义: adj. 合乎习俗的；惯常的
英文释义: if something is customary, it is what people usually do in a particular place or situation
例句: In China, it's customary to eat food with chopsticks.
例句释义: 在中国，用筷子吃饭是种习俗。

详细释义: v. 掠过；浏览，略读；抹去
英文释义: to move quickly or lightly along, above, or near the surface of something; to read something quickly in order to find a particular point or the main points; to remove fat, cream, etc. from the surface of a liquid
例句: The sea bird skims the water's surface for a fish.
例句释义: 海鸟在捕鱼时轻轻掠过水面。

英文释义: made of or containing metal
例句: The metallic armor will protect me in the war!
例句释义: 在战斗中，这件金属盔甲可以保护我！

英文释义: a set of negative and often unfair beliefs that a society or group of people have about something
例句: He attracts unwanted attention from the crowd due to the stigma of being a prisoner.
例句释义: 坐牢的耻辱让他被人指指点点。

英文释义: dead
例句: A tag is tied to the foot of the deceased to indicate his identity.
例句释义: 死者脚上绑着标签来注明其身份。

详细释义: adj. 限制的；限制性的；  n. 限制词
英文释义: preventing people from doing what they want
例句: The rules about dogs in parks are quite restrictive.
例句释义: 公园里对狗的规定很严格。

英文释义: a sweet dish eaten at the end of a meal; a cold dessert (= a sweet dish) like cream flavoured with fruit, chocolate, etc.
例句: The blueberry pudding looks delicious.
例句释义: 这个蓝莓布丁看起来很美味。

英文释义: the ability to know something by using your feelings rather than considering the facts
例句: Her intuition told her that something was wrong.
例句释义: 她凭直觉意识到有什么不对劲。

详细释义: n. 壁炉，格栅；  v. 磨碎，使人烦燥
英文释义: a metal frame with bars across it that is used in a fireplace or to cover an opening
例句: There is a fire in the grate.
例句释义: 炉格里面燃着火。

英文释义: the official who controls the game in some sports; a person who is asked to settle a disagreement
例句: The soccer referee took out a Red card.
例句释义: 足球裁判拿出了一张红牌。

英文释义: a daughter of your son or daughter
例句: My granddaughter can help me cook now.
例句释义: 我孙女现在能帮我做饭了。

英文释义: (formal) usual
例句: He got accustomed to the food after 10 years of living here.
例句释义: 在这里住了十年之后，他习惯了这里的食物。

英文释义: a person who studies sociology
例句: Sociologists study the development of human society and human interactions.
例句释义: 社会学家研究人类社会的发展和人际交往。

英文释义: to calculate an amount, a number, etc.
例句: The agent reckoned the house was worth about 500,000 yuan.
例句释义: 房屋中介估算这房子价值50万元。

详细释义: adj. 古怪的，怪僻的；  n. 古怪的人，怪僻的人
例句: Dali is an eccentric artist of the surrealist movement.
例句释义: 达利是超现实主义运动中一位古怪的艺术家。

详细释义: v. 无意中听到，偷听到
英文释义: to hear, especially by accident, a conversation in which you are not involved
例句: This father overheard his children talking.
例句释义: 这位父亲偶然听到了他儿女的谈话。

英文释义: a person who feels enthusiasm for something :a person who enjoys something very much
例句: These football enthusiasts are watching the game together.
例句释义: 这些足球爱好者们在一起观看比赛。

英文释义: of, relating to, or produced by a volcano
例句: The sky was clouded with smoke after the volcanic eruption.
例句释义: 在火山喷发后，天空被浓烟笼罩。

详细释义: adj. 和善的；亲切的；优美的；奢华的
英文释义: (of people or behaviour) kind, polite and generous, especially to somebody of a lower social position
例句: The gracious queen hugged the boy in the crowd.
例句释义: 这位和善的皇后拥抱了人群中的这个男孩。

详细释义: n. 不满，不平；令人不满的事物
英文释义: a feeling that you are not pleased and satisfied
例句: The couple expressed dissatisfaction with the food to the waiter.
例句释义: 这对夫妇向服务员表达了对食物的不满。

英文释义: (of the earth or a building) to move or shake violently
例句: I can feel the floor quaking. Is it an earthquake?
例句释义: 我感觉地面在震动，是发生地震了吗？

英文释义: sports, games, and exercises that require strength and skill :athletic activities
例句: He is good at many kinds of athletics.
例句释义: 他擅长很多种运动。

英文释义: to effect the downfall or destruction of (a ruler, institution, etc), especially by force
例句: These oranges overthrew the government led by the cruel lemon.
例句释义: 这些橙子推翻了残酷柠檬所领导的政府。

英文释义: a building or buildings built in order to defend an area against attack
例句: The fort is on top of the mountain.
例句释义: 堡垒位于山顶。

英文释义: a disadvantage or problem that makes something a less attractive idea
例句: His short arms are his biggest drawback; he's struggling to reach the toilet paper!
例句释义: 他的小短手是他最大的缺点，他很努力地去够厕纸！

英文释义: the carrying of goods by some means of transport
例句: The freight train transports the goods.
例句释义: 货运列车用于运送货物。

详细释义: adj. 鲁莽的，不顾后果的
英文释义: showing a lack of care about danger and the possible results of your actions
例句: It is reckless for the driver to be driving while texting on the phone.
例句释义: 驾驶员一边开车一边用手机打字的行为是很不顾后果的。

英文释义: a large animal like a monkey, with no tail. There are different types of ape.
例句: Apes are different from monkeys; they have no tails.
例句释义: 类人猿和猴子不一样，它们没有尾巴。

详细释义: v. 发牢骚；  n. 抱怨，怨言
英文释义: to complain about somebody/something in a bad-tempered way; to make a deep continuous sound
例句: My mom always grumbles about the mess as she cleans my room.
例句释义: 我妈打扫卫生的时候，总会对着杂乱的房间一阵咕哝。

英文释义: the arrival or inward flow of a large amount of something (such as money)
例句: The?big?city?has?attracted?a?huge?influx?of?people.
例句释义: 这个大城市吸引了大量人群涌入。

英文释义: a person who introduces, or gives information about, programmes on the radio or television; a person who gives information about something in a station, an airport, etc., especially through a loudspeaker
例句: She works as an announcer for a radio station.
例句释义: 她是一名电台主播。

英文释义: the act of punishing or harming somebody in return for what they have done to you, your family or friends
例句: The cat decides to take vengeance on his friend.
例句释义: 这只猫决定报复他的朋友。

详细释义: v. 疾跑，冲刺；  n. 全速奔跑
英文释义: to run or go very fast for a short distance
例句: Both the athletes sprint to the finish line to try and win the race.
例句释义: 运动员们都向着终点线冲刺，想要赢得比赛。

英文释义: to damage or spoil something good
例句: The wedding was marred by the terrible weather.
例句释义: 婚礼被这糟糕的天气给毁了。

英文释义: to become or make something become brighter or lighter in colour
例句: That lamp really lightens the room!
例句释义: 台灯着实照亮了这个房间！

英文释义: the process of a liquid, gas or other substance being taken in
例句: I use the sponge for the absorption of liquid.
例句释义: 我用这块海绵来吸收液体。

英文释义: a woman who stays at home to cook, clean, take care of the children, etc. while her husband or partner goes out to work
例句: The housewife is ironing the clothes with her child.
例句释义: 这个家庭主妇正在和她的孩子一起熨衣服。

详细释义: n. 学徒；  v. 使当学徒
英文释义: a person who learns a job or skill by working for a fixed period of time for someone who is very good at that job or skill
例句: The young apprentice worked on a piece of wood under his teacher's guidance.
例句释义: 这名年轻的学徒在他老师的指导下做木匠活。

英文释义: a flying insect with a long thin body and four large wings, like a butterfly, but less brightly coloured. Moths fly mainly at night and are attracted to bright lights.
例句: The moth is flying directly towards the flame.
例句释义: 飞蛾正径直扑向火焰。

详细释义: adj. 外面的；  adv. 外面地，向外地
英文释义: going away from a particular place, especially one that you are going to return to
例句: We all enjoy this outward journey.
例句释义: 我们都很享受这次户外旅行。

英文释义: to speak of or mention (something or someone) in an indirect way
例句: She was alluding to Pinocchio when she told the man his nose was getting longer.
例句释义: 她告诉这个男人他的鼻子在变长，其实是在暗指他是匹诺曹。

英文释义: one half of the earth, especially the half above or below the equator
例句: A hemisphere is half of a sphere, or ball.
例句释义: 半球就是半个球体，或球形。

详细释义: n.残疾，生理缺陷；障碍；  vt.使不利，妨碍
英文释义: a permanent physical or mental condition that makes it difficult or impossible to use a particular part of your body or mind
例句: The soldier who has a handicap proudly stands with the others.
例句释义: 这位残疾士兵骄傲地和其他士兵站在一起。

例句: Catfish are a fish with spines around their mouths that resemble a cat's whiskers.
例句释义: 鲶鱼是一种嘴周围长有刺的鱼，它们嘴边的刺看起来像猫的胡须。

详细释义: n. 史诗般的作品；  adj. 史诗的，叙事诗的；壮丽的，宏大的
英文释义: telling a story about a hero or about exciting events or adventures
例句: An epic is a long poem or story usually depicting a hero's journey.
例句释义: 史诗是一则描写英雄旅程的长诗或故事。

英文释义: to make someone want to do something by making it seem very attractive or interesting to them
例句: The tourists were seduced by the beauty of the lake.
例句释义: 游客们被湖泊的美景吸引住了。

英文释义: to surprise and sometimes confuse (someone) very much; to fill (someone) with wonder
例句: This news really amazes me!
例句释义: 这条消息真的让我感到很吃惊！

详细释义: adj. 超自然的；  n. 超自然物，神奇人物，不可思议的事
英文释义: that cannot be explained by the laws of science and that seems to involve gods or magic
例句: Corn circles are widely believed to be made by supernatural powers.
例句释义: 大家认为麦田怪圈产生于超自然力量。

英文释义: to repair and paint an old building, a piece of furniture, etc. so that it is in good condition again
例句: The man, accompanied by his dog, is renovating his own home.
例句释义: 这个男人正在狗狗的陪伴下整修自己的家。

英文释义: to persuade somebody to do something by talking to them in a kind and gentle way
例句: The man coaxed his son into leaving the supermarket.
例句释义: 那个男人哄他的儿子离开了超市。

详细释义: v. （镜头）拉近（拉远）；  n. 车辆疾驰的声音，嗡嗡声，（摄影）变焦
英文释义: (of a camera) to show the object that is being photographed from closer/further away, with the use of a zoom lens
例句: The camera zoomed in on the child's face.
例句释义: 摄像机将孩子的脸拉近了。

详细释义: n. 缰绳；  v. 控制
英文释义: a long narrow leather band that is attached to a metal bar in a horse’s mouth (= a bit) and is held by the rider in order to control the horse
例句: You should hold the reins to lead your horse.
例句释义: 你应该握住缰绳来牵你的马。

英文释义: the people who can vote in an election
例句: He has the backing of almost two-thirds of the electorate.
例句释义: 他有将近三分之二选民的支持。

详细释义: prep. 减（去）；  adj. 负的；  n. 劣势
英文释义: used when you subtract (= take away) one number or thing from another one
例句: Seven minus one is six.
例句释义: 七减一等于六。

英文释义: a person who has seen a crime, accident, etc. and can describe it afterwards
例句: He was the only eyewitness of this robbery.
例句释义: 他是这次抢劫的唯一目击者。

英文释义: a serious illness affecting one or both lungs that makes breathing difficult
例句: Pneumonia leads to a reduction in breathing efficiency.
例句释义: 肺炎会降低呼吸效率。（肺炎会引起呼吸困难。）

英文释义: a book, play or film/movie with an exciting story, especially one about crime or spying
例句: The old couple went to see a thriller in the cinema.
例句释义: 老夫妇去电影院看了一场恐怖片。

详细释义: n. 果肉；果肉酱；  v. 去除果肉，捣成浆状
英文释义: the soft part inside some fruit and vegetables
例句: I squeeze the fruit's pulp into the juice.
例句释义: 我挤压水果的果肉，榨出了汁。

详细释义: n. 成年人；  adj. 成长的，成熟的，成人的
英文释义: (used especially by and to children) an adult person
例句: The boy is a grown-up now and no longer plays with the old toys.
例句释义: 这个男孩现在已是一个成年人，不再玩以前的旧玩具了。

英文释义: a person who rules a country, for example a king or a queen
例句: They bowed down before the monarch, who ruled the country.
例句释义: 他们在一国之君面前俯首称臣。

详细释义: n.摇篮；发源地；  v.轻轻地抱或捧
英文释义: a small bed for a baby which can be pushed gently from side to side
例句: The adorable baby is lying in the cradle.
例句释义: 这个可爱的婴儿正躺在摇篮里。

英文释义: an occasion when a volcano suddenly throws out burning rocks, smoke, etc.
例句: The eruption of this volcano destroyed the whole city.
例句释义: 火山爆发摧毁了整个城市。

例句: The forest ranger is preventing the man from cutting down the tree.
例句释义: 护林员正在阻止这个人砍树。

详细释义: v. 珍爱，珍视；抱有（希望）
英文释义: to love somebody/something very much and want to protect them or it
例句: I cherish my little darling.
例句释义: 我珍爱我的小宝贝。

详细释义: v. 品味；享受；  n. 调味品；乐趣
英文释义: to get great pleasure from something; to want very much to do or have something
例句: With a bottle of red wine and a movie ready, she was relishing her evening.
例句释义: 伴着一瓶红酒和一部电影，她正享受着这个夜晚。

英文释义: (of a room or building) large and with plenty of space for people to move around in
例句: Her house is quite spacious compared to her friend's.
例句释义: 与她朋友的房子相比，她的房子非常宽敞。

英文释义: the act or policy of censoring books, etc.
例句: A part of this image is blurred because of censorship guidelines.
例句释义: 因为审查制度，这幅图像的一部分被模糊了。

英文释义: to take, send or bring goods or people secretly and illegally into or out of a country, etc.
例句: He smuggled phones by hiding them underneath his coat.
例句释义: 他走私手机的方式是把它们藏在外套下面。

详细释义: adj.恼怒的，烦闷的；  v.使烦恼，打扰

例句释义: 他认为取得博士学位是他人生中的一个重要里程碑。

详细释义: adj.仪式的；礼仪的；  n.宗教仪式
英文释义: used in or done as part of a ceremony
例句: The queen was crowned in the ceremonial event.
例句释义: 皇后在仪式上加冕。

详细释义: v. 阻碍，妨碍，牵制；  n. （有盖的）大篮子
英文释义: to prevent somebody from easily doing or achieving something
例句: This huge ball hampered the man's progress on the obstacle course.
例句释义: 这个大球阻碍了男人的闯关之路。

英文释义: thinking about or connected with something that happened in the past
例句: The woman is in a retrospective mood while looking at old photos.
例句释义: 这位女士看着老照片缅怀过去。

例句: We laughed at her amusing story.
例句释义: 我们被她有趣的故事逗乐了。

英文释义: of or relating to herbs
例句: The ingredients of herbal medicine all come from plants.
例句释义: 草药的成分都来源于植物。

英文释义: a person who does not eat meat or fish
例句: He is a strict vegetarian and never eats any meat.
例句释义: 他是一个严格的素食主义者，从不吃任何肉类食品。

英文释义: a formal meal for a large number of people, usually for a special occasion, at which speeches are often made
例句: The banquet had many different kinds of food.
例句释义: 这场宴会里有很多不同种类的食物。

详细释义: n. 霜冻，严寒；  v. 结霜，冻死
英文释义: the thin white layer of ice that forms when the temperature drops below 0°C; a weather condition in which the temperature drops below 0°C
例句: The leaves were covered with frost.
例句释义: 树叶覆盖上一层薄霜。

英文释义: a short sentence or phrase that expresses the aims and beliefs of a person, a group, an institution, etc. and is used as a rule of behaviour
例句: There is a motto on the wall in our classroom.
例句释义: 我们教室的墙上有一句格言。

英文释义: high quality porcelain originally made only in China
例句: This is a beautiful china teacup and teapot.
例句释义: 这是一套精美的青花瓷茶杯与茶壶。

英文释义: very comfortable; containing expensive and enjoyable things
例句: My apartment cost me a lot―I hope you find it sufficiently luxurious.
例句释义: 这个公寓花了我一大笔钱――我希望你觉得它足够奢华。

英文释义: to make (a treaty, agreement, etc.) official by signing it or voting for it
例句: My cat has ratified the treaty and agreed to let me feed him.
例句释义: 我家猫批准了协议，同意让我来养他。

英文释义: having a pleasant smell
例句: The air is fragrant with the scent of coffee.
例句释义: 空气中弥漫着咖啡香。

英文释义: hot liquid rock that comes out of a volcano
例句: The lava flowed down the slope into the sea.
例句释义: 熔岩沿坡面而下，流进了海里。

英文释义: very good or great :unusual in a way that is very impressive
例句: These are the six phenomenal paintings of several great foreign artists.
例句释义: 这六幅现象级的画作出自几位伟大的国外画家之手。

英文释义: the property of being sustainable
例句: This factory has invested in environmental sustainability, adopting various green technologies.
例句释义: 这家工厂在环境的可持续性上做投资，采用了各种绿色技术。

英文释义: a serious infectious disease in which swellings appear on the lungs and other parts of the body
例句: Tuberculosis is a serious infectious disease that affects someone's lungs.
例句释义: 肺结核是一种严重感染人肺部的传染性疾病。

英文释义: impressive to look at; making a strong impression
例句: The castle is an imposing building.
例句释义: 这座城堡是座宏伟的建筑。

英文释义: a group of flowers that are picked and often tied together
例句: The bride held the bouquet in her hands.
例句释义: 新娘手上拿着一束捧花。

英文释义: a substance similar to chalk made into white or coloured sticks for writing or drawing; a type of soft white stone
例句: The student is writing the answer with a chalk.
例句释义: 学生在用粉笔写答案。

英文释义: (of a person) expecting a lot of work or attention from others; not easily satisfied
例句: All dresses they could find couldn't satisfy the demanding girl.
例句释义: 她们找的裙子都不能让这个苛刻的女孩满意。

详细释义: n.家庭教师，指导教师；  v.当……的家庭教师
英文释义: a private teacher, especially one who teaches an individual student or a very small group
例句: The tutor is helping the little boy with his homework.
例句释义: 这个家庭教师正在辅导小男孩的功课。

英文释义: a natural substance that gives color to animals and plants
例句: A pigment is a substance that gives something a particular color.
例句释义: 颜料是一种能使某物具有特定颜色的物质。

英文释义: a large tropical fruit with thick rough skin, sweet yellow flesh with a lot of juice and stiff leaves on top
例句: Pineapples are my favorite fruit in the summer.
例句释义: 菠萝是我在夏天最喜欢吃的水果。

英文释义: one for melting metals
例句: Be careful around the hot furnace.
例句释义: 熔炉很烫，小心点。

英文释义: a person or an organization that tries to get agreement between people or groups who disagree with each other
例句: When the two brothers have a quarrel, their good friend has to be a mediator.
例句释义: 当这两兄弟发生争执时，他们的好朋友就得担当调停者。

详细释义: n. 艰苦跋涉；  v. 拉（货车），搬运

详细释义: n.小装置，小机件，小玩意儿
英文释义: a small tool or device that does something useful

例句释义: 这台虚拟现实设备是一件很便于玩3D游戏的新装备。

例句: He has an intuitive sense that he should cut the blue wire to disarm the bomb.
例句释义: 他有一种直觉，剪断蓝色的线能够拆除炸弹。

详细释义: n. （图像的）说明文字；（报刊的）标题

英文释义: to increase the amount, value, size, etc. of something
例句: He augmented his income through freelance writing.
例句释义: 他通过自由撰稿来增加自己的收入。

英文释义: a very small difference in color, tone, meaning, etc.

例句释义: 这对孪生姐妹的外貌有些细微差别。

详细释义: n. 毁坏，荒废；荒芜，凄凉
英文释义: The act of devastating, or the state of being devastated; a laying waste.
例句: A tsunami caused mass devastation in this city.
例句释义: 海啸给这座城市造成了极大的破坏。

详细释义: v. 保护，维护；  n. 防卫措施，防范措施
英文释义: to protect something/somebody from loss, harm or damage; to keep something/somebody safe
例句: The job of the guards is to safeguard the money.
例句释义: 这些警卫的职责是保护财产安全。

英文释义: to destroy or get rid of something completely, especially something bad
例句: I have to eradicate the bugs from my apartment.
例句释义: 我必须消灭公寓里的这些虫子。

详细释义: adv.在水下；水下；  adj.吃水线以下的
英文释义: below the surface of water
例句: You can see a beautiful world underwater.
例句释义: 你可以在水下看到一个美丽的世界。

详细释义: n. 移位，位移，排水量；替代
英文释义: the act of displacing somebody/something; the process of being displaced

英文释义: a place where two roads meet and cross

英文释义: having an allergy to sth

例句释义: 看他的脸！这个可怜的家伙对海鲜过敏。

例句释义: 正午时分太热了，所以别出门啊。

英文释义: a person whose job is to cut men’s hair and sometimes to shave them; a shop where men can have their hair cut
例句: I asked my barber to give me a new style this time.
例句释义: 这一次我让我的理发师给我理一个新发型。

英文释义: not safe

例句释义: 湿手触碰开关是很不安全的。

详细释义: adj. 不足的，缺乏的；  v. 限制
英文释义: very small in size or amount
例句: There is scant fresh water on Earth; we should try to conserve it.
例句释义: 地球上的淡水很缺乏，我们应该努力保护它。

例句: If you gamble, you might win sometimes, but you will lose in the long run.
例句释义: 赌博，你也许有时会赢，但从长远来看，你一定会输。

例句释义: 我伤心的时候，男朋友总是想尽一切办法安慰我。

详细释义: adj.轻快的；活跃的；寒冷而清新的

例句释义: 他们年轻健康，在跑步训练中保持着轻快的步伐。

详细释义: v.用力举起；  n.举起；起伏
英文释义: to lift, pull or throw somebody/something very heavy with one great effort
例句: These people heave the big green ball together.

详细释义: n. 奖金；赠物；  vt. 发给…奖金
英文释义: good things that are given or provided freely and in large amounts
例句: Sometimes in video games, when you complete a mission you get a bounty.
例句释义: 有时候在游戏中，你完成一个任务就得到赏金。

英文释义: (formal) to agree

详细释义: n. 躲开，避开，逃避；使无效，废止
英文释义: not doing something; preventing something from existing or happening

英文释义: that you can trust and respect as true and correct
例句: He is a respected expert who gives clear and authoritative advice.
例句释义: 他是一位受人尊敬的专家，他给出的建议清晰且权威。

英文释义: willing to accept feelings, habits, or beliefs that are different from your own
例句: He is tolerant of his naughty cat.
例句释义: 他对他淘气的小猫很容忍。

英文释义: the state of being annoyed, especially by something that somebody continuously does or by something that continuously happens; the fact of your skin or a part of your body being sore or painful
例句: The big traffic jam brought great irritation to the drivers.
例句释义: 堵车让司机们很愤怒。

详细释义: n. 猎犬；  v. 追逼；烦扰；纠缠

例句释义: 我的小猎犬鼻子很灵。

例句释义: 这个家庭靠农场的农产品为生。

英文释义: a scientist who studies chemistry
例句: The chemist is working in a lab.
例句释义: 化学家正在实验室里工作。

详细释义: v.惧怕，害怕；  n.畏惧，恐惧；  adj.恐怖的，使人敬畏的
英文释义: to be very afraid of something; to fear that something bad is going to happen
例句: The child dreads the ghost so much that he couldn't fall asleep.
例句释义: 这个孩子很怕鬼，怎么都睡不着。

例句: The camper is looking at the lake in front of her.
例句释义: 这个露营者正看着面前的湖泊。

英文释义: to not consider something; to treat something as unimportant

例句释义: 这个粗鲁的吸烟者无视“禁止吸烟”的标牌。

英文释义: the amount of rain that falls on a particular area

详细释义: v. 用脚（手）划水，荡桨；  n. 桨
英文释义: to move a small boat through water using a paddle
例句: He paddles the dragon boat with a spoon.
例句释义: 他用勺子划龙舟。

例句释义: 黄色橡胶鸭的数量超过了黑色的。

例句释义: 老师正在数黑板上的单词的音节。

例句释义: 这个罪犯被剥夺了政治权利。

例句: He will vote by proxy, because he is sick.
例句释义: 他将由代理人投票，因为他病的很重。

英文释义: (of people and animals) moving or doing things in a very awkward way

例句释义: 她觉得瑜伽很难，因为她的身体不太灵活。

英文释义: a set of letters or symbols in a fixed order used for writing a language
例句: The English alphabet has 26 letters.
例句释义: 英语字母表有26个字母。

英文释义: pasta in the shape of long, thin strings
例句: Spaghetti with tomato sauce and grated cheese is my favorite.
例句释义: 加了番茄酱和芝士粉的意大利细面是我的最爱。

英文释义: very strict or severe
例句: Sara, your standards are too stringent for me to get anything done!
例句释义: 莎拉，你的标准太严厉了，我完全没法做到！

英文释义: a type of white stone that contains calcium, used in building and in making cement
例句: This is a block of limestone with a whitish color.
例句释义: 这块有点白的石头是石灰岩。

英文释义: to make (land, water, air, etc.) dirty and not safe or suitable to use
例句: Few fish can survive in this polluted river.
例句释义: 在这条受污染的河流里，很少有鱼能存活下来。

详细释义: v. 给予精力；使活跃；使兴奋
英文释义: to give somebody more energy, strength, etc.
例句: This sports drink helps to energize my body.
例句释义: 这个运动饮料能让我精力充沛。

例句: His beautiful handwriting is easy to read.
例句释义: 他漂亮的笔迹清晰易读。

详细释义: adj.单独的，单个的；非凡的，显著的
英文释义: connected with or having the singular form
例句: There is a singular red flower amongst a bed of yellow ones.
例句释义: 在黄色的花丛中有一朵红色的花。

英文释义: behaviour in which somebody pretends to have moral standards or opinions that they do not actually have

例句释义: 这个环卫工很伪善，他收集完垃圾后竟然朝海里倒。

详细释义: adj. 明显的；公开的；公然的
英文释义: done in an open way and not secretly

例句释义: 很明显，这只狗想吃那盘意大利面。

英文释义: black clothing that is worn to show that you are mourning for someone who has died
例句: The black armband showed the boy was in mourning.
例句释义: 手臂上的黑纱显示这个男孩正在服丧。

详细释义: adj.被捕获的；被俘虏的；  n.俘虏
英文释义: kept as a prisoner or in a confined space; unable to escape
例句: The poor tiger is kept captive in the cage.

详细释义: adj. 卷曲的，卷毛的，弯曲的
英文释义: having a lot of curls or a curved shape
例句: Her hair is so curly because she uses a special hair product.
例句释义: 她头发很卷，因为她用了特殊的美发产品。

例句释义: 他根据滚滚黑烟推断出这里发生了火灾。

英文释义: not fair; expecting too much

例句释义: 他不能接受他的老板的无理要求。

详细释义: n.直觉，预感；  vt.耸肩，弯腰驼背

英文释义: to make somebody/something seem less bad

例句释义: 他试图通过修篱笆来亡羊补牢。

详细释义: adj.歇斯底里的，情绪激动的

例句: His hysterical behavior like tearing the paper apart is really scary.

英文释义: a lack of good judgement; the fact of doing something stupid; an activity or idea that shows a lack of judgement
例句: It's folly to help the shoots grow by pulling them upward.
例句释义: 拔苗助长是愚蠢的行为。

英文释义: a very small living thing that can cause infection and disease
例句: The man sneezed and sprayed many germs into the air.

英文释义: a person whose job is cutting up and selling meat in a shop/store or killing animals for this purpose
例句: The butcher is cutting some fresh meat for sale.
