英文释义: following the current fashion or style :fashionable and appealing
例句: That dress is very chic―where'd you buy it?
例句释义: 这件连衣裙非常别致――你在哪里买的？

详细释义: adj. 走失的，迷路的；离了群的；  v. 走失；分心，走神；有外遇，在别处拈花惹草；  n. 流浪者；走失，迷路
英文释义: (of animals normally kept as pets) away from home and lost; having no home
例句: The stray dog can only sleep on the street.
例句释义: 这条流浪狗只能睡在街上。

英文释义: to kill (a person or animal) by squeezing the throat
例句: It appears that the victim was strangled with this rope.
例句释义: 看来受害者是被这根绳子勒死的。

详细释义: n. 四肢伸开的躺卧姿势；  v. 四肢伸开地坐（或卧）
英文释义: to lie or sit with your arms and legs spread wide apart
例句: The family sprawled on the beach and had a good time.
例句释义: 那家人四肢伸开躺在沙滩上，十分享受。

英文释义: a group of soldiers who come from a particular army and are working together with soldiers from other armies
例句: Each nation sent a contingent of athletes to the Olympic Games.
例句释义: 每个国家都派出了一队运动员参加奥运会。

英文释义: brave; willing to do dangerous or unusual things; involving danger or taking risks
例句: It's such a daring move to jump into the water from here!
例句释义: 从这里跳进大海是一个多么大胆的举动啊！

英文释义: a ship or lorry/truck that carries oil, gas or petrol/gas in large quantities
例句: I use this blue tanker to deliver gasoline to my customers.
例句释义: 我用这辆蓝色的油槽车运油给顾客。

详细释义: n. 友谊；伙伴关系；交情；团体；奖学金
英文释义: a feeling of friendship between people who do things together or share an interest
例句: These?young?sporty?women?had?a?strong?fellowship.
例句释义: 这些爱运动的年轻女孩们有很好的友谊。

详细释义: v.满得外溢，外流，泛滥；  n.容纳不下的物（或人）
英文释义: to be so full that the contents go over the sides; (of a place) to have too many people in it
例句: My glass is overflowing; pour less water next time!
例句释义: 我杯子里的水都满得溢出来了，下次少倒点儿。

详细释义: n.（尤指装食品和液体的）硬纸盒，纸板箱，塑料箱
英文释义: a light box or container usually made of cardboard or plastic
例句: Drinking a carton of milk per day is good for your health!
例句释义: 每天一盒牛奶，有助于身体健康！

例句: Any company who provided sponsorship is advertised on the show.
例句释义: 任何一家提供赞助的公司都能在这个节目中植入广告。

详细释义: n. 队列，大部队，旅；  v. 把……编成旅，把……编成队
英文释义: a large group of soldiers that is part of an army
例句: The fire brigade stood in front of the fire engine, all wearing their professional uniforms.
例句释义: 消防队员穿着专业的消防服，站在消防车前。

详细释义: v. 尖叫，发出尖锐的声音，尖声讲；  n. 尖叫，尖叫声
英文释义: to give a loud high shout, for example when you are excited, frightened or in pain; to say something in a loud, high voice
例句: She shrieked and grabbed her hair.
例句释义: 她一边尖叫一边抓头发。

英文释义: the quality of being attractive and showing a good sense of style
例句: We can see this lady's elegance from the way she holds her teacup.
例句释义: 我们可以从这位女士端茶杯的姿势看出她的优雅。

英文释义: very bad or unpleasant
例句: I?dreamt?that?I?was?being chased?by?something?dreadful.
例句释义: 我梦见我被一个可怕的东西追赶着。

详细释义: adj. 最高的，至上的，首要的；  n. 最高
英文释义: more important than anything else
例句: Our dog is of paramount importance in our family; far more so than my father.
例句释义: 在我们家，狗狗的地位是最高的，远远超过我爸。

英文释义: (not used in the progressive tenses) to be enough for somebody/something
例句: The girl believes that four eggs should suffice to make the cake.
例句释义: 这个女孩认为四个鸡蛋应该够做蛋糕了。

英文释义: physical beauty that also suggests wealth or success
例句: Her?glamour?impresses?me?every?time?I?see?her.
例句释义: 每次我看到她，她的魅力都让我印象深刻。

例句: Garden designs will use different ideas of aesthetics.
例句释义: 园林设计会运用不同的美学观点。

详细释义: n.海绵，多孔布丁，松蛋糕；  v.用湿海绵（或布）擦，揩
英文释义: a piece of artificial or natural material that is soft and light and full of holes and can hold water easily, used for washing or cleaning; artificial sponge used for filling furniture, cushions, etc.; a light cake made from eggs, sugar and flour, with or without fat
例句: The sponge gives the kitchen a brand-new, shiny look.
例句释义: 清洁海绵让厨房墙壁焕然一新。

英文释义: a long piece of writing about a particular subject that is done to earn an advanced degree at a university
例句: He tried to get some ideas for his dissertation from the old studies.
例句释义: 他试图从一些旧的研究中为自己的论文找到灵感。

英文释义: a piece of electrical equipment in which food is kept cold so that it stays fresh
例句: I opened the fridge to get some food.
例句释义: 我打开冰箱，拿点食物。

详细释义: n.具有危险性的人（或物）；  v.威胁，威吓
英文释义: a person or thing that causes, or may cause, serious damage, harm or danger
例句: A careless driver on the road is a menace to the public.
例句释义: 粗心的司机开车上路对于公众来说是个大威胁。

英文释义: (of glass, liquid, etc.) not clear enough to see through or allow light through
例句: The window is made of opaque glass.
例句释义: 这扇窗是用不透明的玻璃做的。

详细释义: adj. 有报酬的，有回报的
英文释义: producing a lot of money
例句: His hard work and effort are always rewarding.
例句释义: 他的勤奋努力终有回报。

英文释义: the feeling you have in your stomach when you think you are going to vomit
例句: I feel a little nausea today; maybe it was something I ate.
例句释义: 今天我感觉有点恶心；也许跟我吃的东西有关。

英文释义: in regard to academic matters
例句: She performed well academically but was poor at sports.
例句释义: 她在学业上表现出色，但在体育方面表现不佳。

详细释义: v. （为小事）烦恼，过于忧虑；  n. 大惊小怪，小题大做
英文释义: to be or become upset or worried
例句: The man is fussing over a small problem.
例句释义: 这男人正在为一件小事烦恼。

详细释义: v. 犹豫，踌躇；  n. 颤抖
英文释义: to walk or behave in a way that shows that you are not confident
例句: The explorer's confidence was faltering as he began to doubt the route he had taken.
例句释义: 探险家开始怀疑他所走的路线，他的信心在动摇。

英文释义: a plant with brightly coloured flowers of unusual shapes. There are many different types of orchid and some of them are very rare.
例句: Orchids are my favorite flowers.
例句释义: 兰花是我最喜欢的花。

英文释义: to make somebody feel ashamed or stupid and lose the respect of other people
例句: The?poor?boy?was?badly?humiliated?at?school.
例句释义: 那个可怜的男孩在学校遭受了严重的羞辱。

详细释义: adj. 多国之间的，多国（或多方）参加的
英文释义: in which three or more groups, nations, etc. take part
例句: There were many different nations present at the multilateral conference.
例句释义: 许多不同的国家出席了这场多边会议。

英文释义: very quickly, because you are in a hurry, especially when this has bad results
例句: She hastily ran to the train before it departed.
例句释义: 她在发车前慌忙地跑向火车。

详细释义: adj.麻木的，失去知觉的；  vt.使麻木，使失去知觉
英文释义: if a part of your body is numb, you cannot feel anything in it, for example because of cold; unable to feel, think or react in the normal way
例句: My hand was so numb that I could hardly move it.
例句释义: 我的手麻木了，几乎不能动。

英文释义: an official who is in charge of a prison
例句: The warden and two guards are checking the cells.
例句释义: 典狱长和两名警卫正一起检查牢房。

详细释义: adj. 不可思议的，奇迹般的；奇迹般的
英文释义: like a miracle; completely unexpected and very lucky
例句: It's miraculous that a newborn baby can speak like this!
例句释义: 一个刚出生的婴儿就能开口说话，简直不可思议！

英文释义: a piece of furniture with doors and shelves used for storing dishes, food, clothes, etc.; a space in a wall with a door that reaches the ground, used for storing things
例句: She is taking out a bowl from the cupboard.
例句释义: 她从碗橱里拿了个碗出来。

英文释义: severe action taken to restrict the activities of criminals or of people opposed to the government or somebody in authority
例句: The targets of a new crackdown include factories that pollute the air.
例句释义: 新一轮的打击对象包括污染空气的工厂。

英文释义: the distance or measurement from one side to the other; how broad or wide something is
例句: You can measure the breadth of the room with this measuring tool.
例句释义: 你可以用这个度量工具测量房间的宽度。

英文释义: a feeling of great surprise
例句: The cute cat stares at the mirror in amazement.
例句释义: 这只可爱的猫一脸惊愕地盯着镜子。

详细释义: adj.灭绝的；破灭了的，消亡了的
英文释义: (of a type of plant, animal, etc.) no longer in existence
例句: Dinosaurs have been extinct for millions of years.
例句释义: 恐龙在几百万年前就已经灭绝了。

英文释义: the condition of being a child without living parents
例句: He donated books and toys to the orphanage.
例句释义: 他向孤儿院捐赠了书籍和玩具。

英文释义: forming business connections and contacts through informal social meetings; computing the interconnection of two or more networks in different places meetings.
例句: Having skills in networking will help you find jobs or clients.
例句释义: 拥有建立人际网的技巧可以帮助你找到工作或是寻找客户。

英文释义: a type of very large ape that has black fur and that comes from Africa
例句: A gorilla family is living in the forest.
例句释义: 一个大猩猩家庭生活在森林中。

英文释义: a factory where a substance such as oil is refined (= made pure)
例句: The oil is made pure in the refinery.
例句释义: 油在炼油厂里被提纯。

英文释义: the force or energy with which something moves
例句: His boss's praise gives him the impetus to work harder.
例句释义: 老板的表扬给了他更加努力工作的动力。

英文释义: a boy or young man
例句: This group of lads all have a different style.
例句释义: 这群小伙子风格各异。

英文释义: having no purpose because there is no chance of success
例句: It was futile to mend the fence after all his sheep were lost.
例句释义: 羊都被偷光了才去补羊圈并没有什么用。

英文释义: a loving feeling
例句: The hospital aims to provide a caring environment.
例句释义: 这家医院以提供充满关怀的环境为目标。

英文释义: containing salt or too much salt
例句: Fish from the sea taste salty because of the salt in the sea water.
例句释义: 因为海水里有盐，所以海鱼吃起来是咸的。

英文释义: people of different backgrounds come to see themselves as part of a larger national family.
例句: Assimilation is the process when a group's culture comes to resemble those of another.
例句释义: 同化作用就是一个群体的文化变得和另一个群体一样的过程。

详细释义: adj. 显眼的；显著的；显而易见的
英文释义: easy to see or notice; likely to attract attention
例句: The red man is very conspicuous, since everyone else is blue.
例句释义: 红色的人非常显眼，因为其他的人都是蓝色的。

详细释义: adj. 颇胖的，丰满的；  v. 拍打使鼓起，突然坐下、倒下，
英文释义: having a soft, round body; slightly fat
例句: I may be plump now, but I am losing weight.
例句释义: 也许现在我还很胖，但我正在减肥。

英文释义: the tube along which food passes after it has been through the stomach, especially the end where waste is collected before it is passed out of the body

例句: The fans screamed when they saw their idol.
例句释义: 粉丝们在见到他们的偶像时尖叫了起来。

英文释义: the preparation and use of land for growing plants or crops
例句: We only use organic cultivation methods on our farm.
例句释义: 我们农场里只采用有机培育法。

英文释义: done by one member of a group or an organization without the agreement of the other members
例句: He made a unilateral announcement of his marriage to his favorite female star.
例句释义: 他单方面宣布和他最爱的女明星结婚了。

英文释义: a slow popular song that is typically about love
例句: I'll sing a ballad for you, baby.
例句释义: 我要为你唱一首歌谣，宝贝儿。

详细释义: adj. 成荫的，多荫的；可疑的，靠不住的
英文释义: protected from direct light from the sun by trees, buildings, etc.; (of a tree, etc.) providing shade from the sun
例句: It's nice to take a walk in the shady forest.
例句释义: 在成荫的森林里散步很惬意。

英文释义: (of people or their behaviour) hard and cruel; determined to get what you want and not caring if you hurt other people
例句: Instead of saving his friend, the ruthless lion tried to kill him.
例句释义: 这只残忍的狮子非但不救他的朋友，反而想杀了他。

详细释义: n. 善于变戏法的人，魔术师，术士
英文释义: a person who can do magic tricks; (in stories) a person who has magic powers
例句: The magician performed many magic tricks.
例句释义: 魔术师表演了许多魔术。

英文释义: to hesitate and be unable to make a decision or choice
例句: Her thoughts of what to eat for lunch continues to waver.
例句释义: 她对午饭吃什么仍然犹豫不决。

详细释义: n.跛子，不健全的人；  v.使跛；严重削弱
英文释义: a person who is unable to walk or move normally because of a disease or injury
例句: The cripple has to use a wheelchair to get around.
例句释义: 这个跛脚的人必须借助轮椅才能四处走动。

详细释义: n.歹徒，逃犯，丧失公权者；  v.将……放逐
英文释义: (used especially about people in the past) a person who has done something illegal and is hiding to avoid being caught; a person who is not protected by the law
例句: The?two?men?were?outlaws?in?the?wild?west.
例句释义: 这两个人是蛮荒西部的不法之徒。

英文释义: a straight line between the centre of a circle and any point on its outer edge; the length of this line
例句: The circle's radius is about 10 centimeters.
例句释义: 这个圆的半径大约是10厘米。

英文释义: a statement that something will happen in the future, especially one made by somebody with religious or magic powers; the power of being able to say what will happen in the future
例句: The prophecy said that the world would end in 2012.
例句释义: 预言书上说世界将在2012年毁灭。

英文释义: a brush on the end of a long handle, used for sweeping floors
例句: One of my duties is to sweep the floor with a broom.
例句释义: 我的任务之一是用扫帚扫地。

英文释义: made by people rather than by nature
例句: This park has a man-made lake.
例句释义: 这个公园里有一个人工湖。

详细释义: n.（衣服等的）衬里；衬料；里子
英文释义: a layer of material used to cover the inside surface of something
例句: The jacket was gray with a red inner lining.
例句释义: 这件灰色外套的内衬是红色的。

详细释义: n.忧郁，沮丧；  v.变忧郁，变忧愁
英文释义: a feeling of being sad and without hope
例句: The boy is filled with gloom after failing his exam.
例句释义: 男孩因为考试失利而倍感沮丧。

详细释义: adj. 突出的；跳跃的；  n. 突出部分
英文释义: most important or noticeable
例句: Mr.Giraffe's salient height made him stand out in the photograph.
例句释义: 长颈鹿先生显著的身高使他在照片里很突出。

英文释义: saying what you think openly and honestly; not hiding your thoughts
例句: She was very candid with her friends; she directly expressed her opinion.
例句释义: 她对自己的朋友很率直，有什么话都会直说。

详细释义: v. 升起，吊起；向上推；  n. 起重机
英文释义: to raise or pull something up to a higher position, often using ropes or special equipment
例句: We use the machine to hoist the huge stone off the ground.
例句释义: 我们用这个机器将大石从地面吊起。

详细释义: n. 绷带；  v. 用绷带绑扎
英文释义: a strip of cloth used for tying around a part of the body that has been hurt in order to protect or support it
例句: I hurt my hand, so I wrapped it in a bandage.
例句释义: 我把手弄伤了，所以包了绷带。

英文释义: a task or project, especially one that is important and/or difficult
例句: Having babies is a huge undertaking.
例句释义: 抚养孩子是一项很重大的事业。

英文释义: to become, or allow somebody to become, a part of a country or community rather than remaining in a separate group
例句: Growing up with the dogs, the cat had become totally assimilated into their pack.
例句释义: 那只猫咪和狗狗一起长大，已经被狗完全同化了。

详细释义: v. （使）缠结；（使）乱作一团；  n. 纠缠；纠结；复杂的问题；困惑
英文释义: to twist something into an untidy mass; to become twisted in this way
例句: That stupid dog got tangled up in our decorations.
例句释义: 那条愚蠢的狗被缠在了装饰品中。

英文释义: a formal written statement of relinquishment
例句: The girl has to sign the company's waiver before doing the bungee jump.
例句释义: 这个女孩在蹦极前必须签署这家公司的责任免除协议。

英文释义: to go or move somewhere quickly
例句: We must hasten our pace, or we'll miss our train!
例句释义: 我们必须加紧步伐，否则就会错过火车！

英文释义: to make something last longer
例句: The teacher said he would prolong the lesson by only one minute.
例句释义: 那位老师说他只拖堂一分钟。

详细释义: adj. 锯齿状的，参差不齐的
英文释义: having a sharp, uneven edge or surface
例句: The edges of this kind of leaf are jagged.
例句释义: 这种树叶的边缘是锯齿状的。

英文释义: when you digest food, or it digests, it is changed into substances that your body can use
例句: The food he ate was hard to digest.
例句释义: 他吃的食物很难消化。

详细释义: n. 甜甜圈；油炸圈饼；多纳滋
例句: There are some delicious doughnuts in the box.
例句释义: 盒子里有些美味的甜甜圈。

英文释义: slow to speak or act because you feel uncertain, embarrassed or unwilling
例句: She stands in front of the fridge, hesitant about what to eat.
例句释义: 她站在冰箱前，犹豫着要吃什么。

详细释义: v. 放弃，让出（权利，财产等），撤回
英文释义: to give up (something) :to give (something, such as power, control, or possession) to another person or group
例句: The army relinquished their control over the airport due to running out of food supplies.
例句释义: 因为食物耗尽，这支军队放弃了对机场的控制。

英文释义: deserving to be noticed or to receive attention because it is unusual, important or interesting
例句: This must be a noteworthy painting because so many people are crowded around it.
例句释义: 这一定是一幅值得注意的画，因为有这么多人都围着它。

英文释义: to begin to happen; to begin something
例句: We were about to commence the race.
例句释义: 我们就快开始比赛了。

详细释义: n. 忧虑，担心，疑惧；逮捕
英文释义: worry or fear that something unpleasant may happen
例句: I have some apprehensions about this business deal.
例句释义: 我对这个生意还有一点担心。

详细释义: v. 阻塞，阻碍；  n. 木底鞋
英文释义: to slowly form a block in (something, such as a pipe or street) so that things cannot move through quickly or easily
例句: The water is stuck! The pipe must be clogged.
例句释义: 水流不通了！水管一定是被堵住了。

英文释义: not married
例句: I'm the only one still unmarried out of my friends.
例句释义: 我是我朋友里唯一仍然未婚的。

英文释义: the quality of tasting or smelling sweet
例句: After all these years, I still love the sweetness of a lollipop.
例句释义: 这么多年以后，我还是很爱棒棒糖的甜味。

英文释义: rule against
例句: Health and well-being overrides the importance of work.
例句释义: 健康的身体比工作重要。

详细释义: v. 死去；脆裂，老化，腐烂
英文释义: (of people or animals) to die, especially in a sudden violent way
例句: A family of three ducks perished in the fire.
例句释义: 鸭子一家三口在火灾中去世了。

详细释义: adj.专心的，注意的；肯帮忙的
英文释义: listening or watching carefully and with interest; helpful; making sure that people have what they need
例句: He was very attentive in class, unlike his deskmate, who dozed off.
例句释义: 他上课非常认真，不像他的同桌在打瞌睡。

详细释义: n. 刻痕，凹口；  v. 在…上刻凹痕
英文释义: a small cut that is shaped like a V and that is made on an edge or a surface
例句: For each day he spent on the island, he marked a new notch on the tree.
例句释义: 每在岛上度过一天，他就在树上刻一个新的刻痕。

英文释义: an animal of the horse family, with short legs and long ears. People ride donkeys or use them to carry heavy loads.
例句: The donkey is trying to eat a carrot.
例句释义: 这头驴子正在努力吃一根胡萝卜。

英文释义: the area around a particular place
例句: These houses are in the vicinity of the hospital.
例句释义: 这些房子都在医院附近。

详细释义: adj.使人满意的；令人愉快的；讨人喜欢的
英文释义: that gives you pleasure or satisfaction
例句: She finds the bunch of flowers very pleasing.
例句释义: 她觉得这束花让她很满意。

英文释义: to move your fingers on a sensitive part of somebody’s body in a way that makes them laugh
例句: He laughs whenever his wife and daughter tickle him.
例句释义: 他妻子和女儿每次挠他痒痒，他都笑个不停。

英文释义: defeat someone in an expectation through trickery or deceit
例句: The two jockeys are competing to win the race.
例句释义: 两位赛马的骑师正为赢得比赛而互相竞争。

详细释义: n.跛行；  vi.一瘸一拐地走，跛行
英文释义: a way of walking in which one leg is used less than normal because it is injured or stiff
例句: Ever since he was hit by a car, he's walked with a limp.
例句释义: 自从他被车撞后，他走路就一瘸一拐的。

详细释义: adj. 瘦骨嶙峋的；骨的；多骨的；似骨的
英文释义: (of a person or part of the body) very thin so that the bones can be seen under the skin
例句: These kind-hearted animal protection staff rescued the bony stray dog.
例句释义: 这些善良的动物保护协会工作人员救助了这只瘦骨嶙峋的流浪狗。

英文释义: a song that has a special importance for a country, an organization or a particular group of people, and is sung on special occasions
例句: These sports fans are singing their national anthem before the match.
例句释义: 在比赛开始前，体育迷们唱起了国歌。

详细释义: n. 自负；（带镜子的）梳妆台
英文释义: too much pride in your own appearance, abilities or achievements
例句: It's clear that this man's level of vanity is far too high!
例句释义: 这个男人太自负了！

详细释义: v. 使变淡，稀释；使病弱
英文释义: to make a liquid weaker by adding water or another liquid to it
例句: Water dilutes the solution quickly.
例句释义: 水可以很快稀释溶液。

英文释义: (of a person) tall and heavy; (of a thing) large and difficult to move or carry
例句: To be a good wrestler, you have to be pretty bulky.
例句释义: 想要成为一个优秀的摔跤手，你的体型必须很庞大。

英文释义: a toy made of a light frame covered with paper, cloth, etc., that you fly in the air at the end of one or more long strings
例句: The little boy is running to fly his colorful kite.
例句释义: 这个小男孩正跑着放他的彩色风筝。

英文释义: of or using electromagnetic waves that are just shorter than those of violet light in the spectrum and that cannot be seen
例句: My hat protected me from the dangerous ultraviolet rays.
例句释义: 我的帽子保护我免于危险的紫外线。

详细释义: n. 男巫，奇才；  adj. 男巫的，有魔力的
英文释义: (in stories) a man with magic powers; a person who is especially good at something
例句: Beware! The wizard's magic is incredibly powerful!
例句释义: 小心！这个男巫的魔法十分强大。

英文释义: to rise; to go up; to climb up
例句: The walking group are ascending to the summit of the mountain.
例句释义: 这个徒步团队正在向山顶攀登。

例句: In this tourist spot children under 1.2 meters tall are exempt from paying entrance fee.
例句释义: 在这个旅游景点，身高在1.2米以下的儿童可以免票。

英文释义: to press or squeeze something together or into a smaller space; to be pressed or squeezed in this way; to reduce something and fit it into a smaller space or amount of time; to make computer files, etc. smaller so that they use less space on a disk, etc.
例句: The bags are much smaller after being compressed.
例句释义: 装被子的袋子在压缩后变小了很多。

详细释义: adj. 必有一死的；致命的；极端的
英文释义: that cannot live for ever and must die
例句: Man is mortal; we all must die.
例句释义: 人终有一死，我们都是如此。

英文释义: towards, onto or on land, having come from an area of water such as the sea or a river
例句: The bottle was finally washed ashore after many years.
例句释义: 多年以后，瓶子终于被冲上了岸。

英文释义: a play or performance made of scenes from a historical event or a legend
例句: There is a pageant going on the stage.
例句释义: 一场历史剧正在上演。

详细释义: adj. 最年长的，最老的；  n. 最年长者
英文释义: (of people, especially of three or more members of the same family) oldest
例句: My older brother is the eldest child in our family.
例句释义: 我的大哥是家里最大的小孩。

英文释义: shaped like a rectangle (= a flat shape with four straight sides, two of which are longer than the other two, and four angles of 90°)
例句: The shape of the photo frame is rectangular.
例句释义: 相框是长方形的。

详细释义: adj. 不健康的，对健康有害的
英文释义: harmful to your health :likely to make you sick
例句: It is unhealthy to stay up late, smoke cigarettes and drink alcohol.
例句释义: 熬夜、抽烟、酗酒都是不健康的。

英文释义: tall plant like grass with a hollow stem that grows in or near water
例句: My boat is stuck in the reeds. Please help me move it.
例句释义: 我的船卡在芦苇丛中了。请帮我移开它。

详细释义: v. 跟着发生，接踵而来
英文释义: to happen after or as a result of another event
例句: Landslide ensued after the storm.
例句释义: 风暴之后，随之而来的是泥石流。

详细释义: n.（天灾、战争等造成的）大破坏，大毁灭；  vi.损毁；  vt.严重破坏
英文释义: a situation in which there is much destruction or confusion
例句: The tornado has wreaked havoc on the city.
例句释义: 龙卷风对这座城市造成了极大的破坏。

英文释义: a chemical element. Sulphur is a pale yellow substance that produces a strong unpleasant smell when it burns and is used in medicine and industry.
例句: Sulfur can be used in the production of gunpowder.
例句释义: 硫磺可以被用于制造火药。

英文释义: very frightened
例句: The mouse was terrified of the cat.
例句释义: 这只老鼠非常怕猫。

英文释义: to escape from somebody/something or avoid meeting somebody
例句: She tried to evade the embarrassing questions that the journalists asked.
例句释义: 她尽力回避记者提出的令人尴尬的问题。

英文释义: the act or process of forming an opinion, based on what you already know; something that you can find out indirectly from what you already know
例句: The boy made an inference about love.
例句释义: 那个男孩推断了一下爱情。

英文释义: the act of persuading somebody to do something or to believe something
例句: I prefer to use persuasion with my daughter, rather than orders or physical force.
例句释义: 我倾向于用劝说的方式跟女儿交流，而不是命令或者体罚。

英文释义: a country that is ruled by a monarch (such as a king or queen)
例句: In a monarchy, the country is ruled by a king or a queen.
例句释义: 在君主政体中，国家由国王或女王所统治。

详细释义: v. 结婚；  vt. 密切地结合
英文释义: to marry
例句: We decided to wed as soon as we finished college.
例句释义: 我们决定大学一毕业就结婚。

详细释义: n. 殖民地居民，殖民者
英文释义: a person who settles in an area that has become a colony
例句: The native people have felt threatened ever since colonists invaded their land.
例句释义: 面对殖民者的侵略，土著人产生了强烈的危机感。

英文释义: a person who steals from a person or place, especially using violence or threats
例句: The robber tried to take the man's bag.
例句释义: 强盗想要抢这个人的包。

英文释义: professional wrongdoing that results in injury or damage.
例句: A quill was left in his body due to the doctor's malpractice.
例句释义: 因为医生的失职，有一根豪猪刺遗留在了他体内。

英文释义: to make something look bigger than it really is, for example by using a lens or microscope; to make something bigger, louder or stronger
例句: He needs to magnify the objects so he can see them better.
例句释义: 他需要放大物体以便能够看清它们。

详细释义: adj. 被引入歧途的；被误导的；  v. 使入歧途
英文释义: having wrong or improper goals or values
例句: In a misguided attempt at a shortcut, he drove straight into the cornfield.
例句释义: 他试图抄近路，但是他直接误入了一片玉米地。

英文释义: having an evil appearance :looking likely to cause something bad, harmful, or dangerous to happen
例句: I can't stand the clown, because he always looks so creepy and sinister.
例句释义: 我无法忍受这个小丑，因为他看上去既恐怖又凶险。

英文释义: the chemical processes in living things that change food, etc. into energy and materials for growth
例句: Increasing the metabolism of your body is helpful for weight loss.
例句释义: 提高身体的新陈代谢能力有助于减肥。

详细释义: v. 探知，弄清，查明（真相等）
英文释义: to find out the true or correct information about something
例句: The detective searched this room to ascertain the facts of the case.
例句释义: 侦探搜查了这个房间以便查明案情。

英文释义: a written statement that promises the good condition of a product and states that the maker is responsible for repairing or replacing the product usually for a certain period of time after its purchase
例句: The phone came with a one-year warranty, which entitles him to free repairs.
例句释义: 这个手机有一年的保修期，所以他有权享受免费维修。

英文释义: a large building or room in which public meetings, concerts, etc. are held
例句: Auditoriums are often used to hold speeches and lectures.
例句释义: 礼堂通常被用于举办演讲和讲座。

英文释义: to throw a set of three or more objects such as balls into the air and catch and throw them again quickly, one at a time
例句: He's amazing―how can he juggle so many balls at once?
例句释义: 他太棒了，他是如何同时耍这么多球的？

英文释义: to change direction or make something change direction, especially after hitting something; to succeed in preventing something from being directed towards you; to prevent somebody from doing something that they are determined to do
例句: He managed to deflect the arrow so it pointed upward.
例句释义: 他尝试着使箭头偏斜，这样它就指向上方。

详细释义: n. 蔑视；抗议，反抗；挑战
英文释义: the act of defying someone or something; a refusal to obey something or someone
例句: There's a look of defiance on his face.
例句释义: 他露出蔑视的神情。

英文释义: suffering or death caused by having nothing to eat or not enough to eat :the condition of someone who is starving
例句: The drought resulted in the starvation of many animals.
例句释义: 干旱使许多动物的挨饿。

英文释义: available or existing in large amounts or numbers
例句: The fruits and vegetables are plentiful!
例句释义: 水果和蔬菜好丰富啊！

英文释义: extremely small and difficult or impossible to see without a microscope
例句: The student is taking a microscopic examination of the cells.
例句释义: 这个学生正在用显微镜观察细胞。

英文释义: (of buildings, mountains, etc.) very high and impressive
例句: This mountain's lofty peak towers through the clouds.
例句释义: 这座巍峨的山峰高耸入云。

例句: The rusty old van was not fit to drive.
例句释义: 这辆生锈的旧货车不能再行驶了。

详细释义: v.放大（声音等）；扩大；增强；详述
英文释义: to increase something in strength, especially sound; to add details to a story, statement, etc.
例句: You can amplify your voice with a megaphone.
例句释义: 你可以用扩音器来扩大音量。

英文释义: to make somebody feel extremely shocked, disgusted or frightened
例句: Your costume will horrify many children.
例句释义: 你的服饰会吓到很多小朋友。

详细释义: v. 发怒；  n. 愤怒
英文释义: to be very angry about something
例句: I'm so upset; I just want to fume about it for a while.
例句释义: 我好心烦，我只想愤怒一阵子。

详细释义: vt. 剪羊毛；剪头发；  n. （复数）大剪刀
英文释义: (in the plural) a garden tool like a very large pair of scissors, used for cutting bushes and hedges
例句: The old farmer is shearing his sheep.
例句释义: 这位老农正在给他的羊剪毛。

详细释义: adj. 地球的，陆地的；  n. 陆地生物，地球上的人
英文释义: living or growing on land instead of in water or air
例句: I have learned a lot about the Earth's geography from this terrestrial globe.
例句释义: 我从地球仪上学到了许多关于地球的知识.

详细释义: adj. 下雪的；被雪覆盖的；洁白无瑕的
英文释义: when a lot of snow falls; covered with snow; very white, like new snow
例句: It was a snowy night and there was no one on the street.
例句释义: 那是一个下雪的夜晚，街上空无一人。

详细释义: adj. 发光的；鲜艳的；明亮的；夜光的
英文释义: shining in the dark; giving out light
例句: This jar of fireflies are luminous and glow at night.
例句释义: 装着萤火虫的罐子在晚上会发出点点亮光。

英文释义: the act of starting a new operation or practice
例句: The new king is taking an oath at his inauguration.
例句释义: 新任国王正在他的就职典礼上宣誓。

详细释义: adj. 海事的，海上的，沿海的，近海的
英文释义: located near or next to the sea
例句: A maritime nation should be aware of tsunami.
例句释义: 沿海的国家应警惕海啸。

英文释义: (especially in compounds) a machine for drying something
例句: I use a dryer to dry off my hands.
例句释义: 我用烘干机来烘干我的手。

英文释义: to decay, or make something decay, naturally and gradually
例句: The apple on the table is rotting.
例句释义: 桌子上的苹果正在腐烂。

英文释义: (of a liquid, gas, etc.) to spread to every part of an object or a place
例句: The sweet smell of the flowers permeated the entire room.
例句释义: 花的香气弥漫了整个房间。

英文释义: the feeling of being alienated from other people
例句: The little zebra among the horses faces alienation for its different stripes.
例句释义: 这匹小斑马因为与众不同的条纹而被小马们疏远了。

详细释义: n. 一壶，一罐（的量）；（有把手，小口的）大壶
英文释义: a container with a handle and a lip, for holding and pouring liquids; the amount of liquid contained in a jug
例句: I like drinking a jug of milk every day.
例句释义: 我喜欢每天喝一壶牛奶。

详细释义: v. 使认识；使熟悉；介绍
英文释义: to make somebody/yourself familiar with or aware of something
例句: I took the chance to get acquainted with my new work colleague.
例句释义: 我抓住机会和我的新同事熟悉起来。

详细释义: n. 统计数值；统计学；统计
英文释义: a number that represents a piece of information (such as information about how often something is done, how common something is, etc.)
例句: These statistics can help analyze the stock market.
例句释义: 这些数据有助于分析股市。

英文释义: to affect somebody/something in an unpleasant or harmful way
例句: She is afflicted by a bad headache.
例句释义: 头痛使她遭罪。

详细释义: vi. 聚集；  vt. 积累，积聚
英文释义: to gather or collect (something, such as a large amount of money) especially for yourself
例句: He has amassed a lot of money over the years.
例句释义: 这些年他攒了不少钱。

详细释义: n. 贫民窟，贫民区，陋巷
英文释义: an area of a city that is very poor and where the houses are dirty and in bad condition
例句: The living conditions in this slum are shockingly poor.
例句释义: 这个贫民窟的生活条件差得惊人。

英文释义: the action, process, or system of taxing people or things
例句: The system of taxation requires us to pay taxes.
例句释义: 税收制度要求我们缴纳税金。

英文释义: to look for or to look at information on a computer, especially on the Internet or a specific website
例句: He was just browsing through the pictures, not reading the content.
例句释义: 他只是在浏览图片，并没有看上面的内容。

英文释义: to cross an area of land or water
例句: It seemed impossible to traverse the entire Asian continent by car, but they did it!
例句释义: 驾车横越亚洲大陆看上去是不可能的，但他们做到了！

详细释义: n.晒成棕褐色或晒黑的皮肤；  v.硝制（皮革）
英文释义: the brown colour that somebody with pale skin goes when they have been in the sun
例句: I?can get?a?tan?while?lying?in the sun.
例句释义: 躺在阳光下，我就会晒黑。

英文释义: a person who rides a bicycle
例句: The cyclist stopped to enjoy the beautiful natural scenery.
例句释义: 骑自行车的人停了下来以欣赏这美丽的自然景色。

英文释义: weighing heavily on the senses or spirit
例句: Galileo faced an oppressive society which, at the time, considered his theories ridiculous.
例句释义: 伽利略所面对的是一个压迫性的社会，当时的人们认为他的理论是荒谬的。

英文释义: an instrument used for measuring the temperature of the air, a person’s body, etc.
例句: The man used a thermometer to take his temperature.
例句释义: 这个男人用一支温度计来测量体温。

英文释义: having a definite limit or fixed size
例句: The set is finite in size, since it only has four numbers.
例句释义: 这个集是有限的，因为它只有四个数字。

详细释义: v.刈，收割庄稼；  n.干草堆
英文释义: to cut (something, such as grass) with a machine or a blade
例句: With this machine, I can easily mow the lawn.
例句释义: 有了这台机器，我就可以轻松地修剪草坪了。

详细释义: n. 蔑视，鄙视；  vt. 鄙视
英文释义: a feeling of strong dislike or disapproval of someone or something you think does not deserve respect
例句: Her facial expression shows her disdain for the girl beside her.
例句释义: 她的表情表明了她很鄙视她旁边的女生。

英文释义: a loose outer piece of clothing that has no sleeves, fastens at the neck and hangs from the shoulders, like a cloak but shorter
例句: The little boy looks so cute in that red cape!
例句释义: 那个披着红色斗篷的小男孩看上去真可爱！

详细释义: v. 传授，给予，将（某性质）给予或赋予某事物
英文释义: to pass information, knowledge, etc. to other people; to give a particular quality to something
例句: A teacher's duty is to impart knowledge to students.
例句释义: 教师的职责就是向学生传授知识。

英文释义: a device that is attached to people or objects to make them fall slowly and safely when they are dropped from an aircraft. It consists of a large piece of thin cloth that opens out in the air to form an umbrella shape.
例句: The fox uses a parachute to descend.
例句释义: 这只狐狸用降落伞来下降。

英文释义: shake, quiver, or throb; move back and forth rapidly, usually in an uncontrolled manner
例句: I vibrate the pendulum of the metronome to set the rhythm.
例句释义: 我让节拍器的摇锤摇摆起来，以此来设置节奏。

详细释义: n. 不满；  adj. 不满的
英文释义: a feeling of being unhappy because you are not satisfied with a particular situation; something that makes you have this feeling
例句: From the look on their faces, you could see their discontent at the food they were given.
例句释义: 从他们表情可以看出他们对被提供的食物非常不满。

详细释义: adj. 法定的；可依法惩处的
英文释义: of or relating to formal laws or statutes
例句: There are seven statutory holidays in China, such as Spring Festival and Mid-Autumn Festival.
例句释义: 中国有七个法定节假日，如春节和中秋节等。

英文释义: to entertain (someone) in a light and pleasant way; to make someone laugh or smile
例句: Their talk show amused the audience.
例句释义: 他们的脱口秀把观众逗乐了。

英文释义: to draw a line under a word, sentence, etc.; to emphasize or show that something is important or true
例句: You should underline the most important points when you read.
例句释义: 阅读时，你应该在重要部分的下面画线。

英文释义: the act of intimidating a weaker person to make them do something
例句: The man was scared by his boss's intimidation.
例句释义: 这个男人被他老板的恐吓吓住了。

详细释义: n. 唱反调者；持不同政见者，意见不同的人；  adj. 持不同政见的，意见不同的
英文释义: someone who strongly and publicly disagrees with and criticizes the government
例句: The disillusioned dissident cat priest decided to convert to the dog religion.
例句释义: 这位持有不同意见的猫教士在幻想破灭后决定皈依狗教。

英文释义: a foot traveler; someone who goes on an extended walk (for pleasure)
例句: These three hikers are hiking in the mountains.
例句释义: 这三名远足者正在山上徒步旅行。

英文释义: a viewer who looks around casually without seeking anything in particular
例句: If you want to search for something online, a browser is needed.
例句释义: 如果你想在网上搜索东西，就需要一个浏览器。

英文释义: a specialist in geology
例句: The geologists are recording information about the rock.
例句释义: 地质学家正在记录岩石的信息。

英文释义: the part of the body below the chest that contains the stomach, bowels, etc.
例句: She touched her abdomen with both hands.
例句释义: 她将双手放在了腹部上。

英文释义: to secretly plan with other people to do something illegal or harmful
例句: The baby robbers are conspiring to steal the gold milk bottle.
例句释义: 宝宝强盗们正密谋对黄金奶瓶实施偷窃。

详细释义: n.隔开物，隔墙，隔板；  v.隔开
英文释义: a wall or screen that separates one part of a room from another
例句: Our meeting room is separated by a glass partition.
例句释义: 我们的会议室被一面玻璃隔墙给隔开了。

详细释义: adj. 朦胧的；多荫的，阴凉的
英文释义: dark and full of shadows
例句: I saw a shadowy figure disappearing into the sunset.
例句释义: 我看见一个朦胧的身影消失在日落黄昏里。

详细释义: v. 罢免，驱逐，剥夺，取代
英文释义: to force somebody out of a job or position of power, especially in order to take their place
例句: The traitor was ousted from the group.
例句释义: 背叛者被驱逐出了团队。

英文释义: something that prevents people from doing something by making them afraid of what will happen to them if they do it
例句: The armed guards are a deterrent to potential robbers.
例句释义: 这些武装警卫对潜在的劫匪来说具有威慑作用。

详细释义: adj.保留的，留作专用的；内向的，矜持的，缄默的
英文释义: kept for use only by a particular person or group
例句: This parking spot is reserved for cars with disabled people.
例句释义: 这是残疾人专用的停车位。

英文释义: acting or done in a secret or dishonest way, often intending to trick people
例句: He distracts my attention in order to steal from me. How sly!
例句释义: 他虚晃一枪转移我的注意力，来偷我的东西。太狡猾啦！

英文释义: to describe or express something as an amount or a number
例句: A measuring cup helps me quantify the ingredients that I need.
例句释义: 量杯帮我确定我需要的材料的用量。

英文释义: a chemical element. Silicon exists as a grey solid or as a brown powder and is found in rocks and sand. It is used in making glass and transistors.
例句: Silicon is a chemical element and its chemical symbol is "Si".
例句释义: 硅是一种化学元素，化学符号是Si。

英文释义: to mean something
例句: The red color is usually used to denote error.
例句释义: 红色一般用于指出错误。

详细释义: adj. 光芒四射的，绚丽的
英文释义: giving a warm bright light
例句: The sun warms the clouds to a radiant glow.
例句释义: 太阳为云层罩上了一层暖暖的绚丽光辉。

详细释义: v.缝，绣；  n.（肋部的）突然剧痛
英文释义: to use a needle and thread to repair, join, or decorate pieces of cloth; to sew the edges of a wound together
例句: The cobbler is stitching a part of the shoe using the sewing machine.
例句释义: 鞋匠正在用缝纫机缝合鞋的部件。

详细释义: v. 拆毁（建筑物等）；毁坏，破坏（组织等）
英文释义: to pull or knock down a building
例句: The excavator is demolishing the building.
例句释义: 挖掘机正在拆除这栋建筑。

英文释义: the row of small bones that are connected together down the middle of the back
例句: He illustrates the basic structure of the backbone.
例句释义: 他用图说明了脊柱的基本结构。

详细释义: n. 停泊处；【口语】职业；  v. 使停泊
英文释义: a place in the water near the shore where a ship stops and stays
例句: A large boat anchored at the berth.
例句释义: 一艘大船在停泊处停下来。

详细释义: n. 检查站，关卡，记录点
英文释义: a place, especially on a border between two countries, where people have to stop so their vehicles and documents can be checked
例句: These people are lining up to go through the security checkpoint.
例句释义: 这些人正排队通过安全检查站。

英文释义: a sense organ or nerve ending in the body that reacts to changes such as heat or cold and makes the body react in a particular way
例句: The cone receptors in our eyes are sensitive to different colors of light.
例句释义: 眼睛里的锥形感受器对不同颜色的光很敏感。

英文释义: containing an unusual amount of grease or oil
例句: This little boy loves eating greasy food, which makes him fatter.
例句释义: 这个小男孩很喜欢吃油腻的食物，这让他越来越胖。

英文释义: completely lacking in something
例句: The swimming pool is devoid of water.
例句释义: 这个游泳池里没有水。

英文释义: a comfortable chair with sides on which you can rest your arms
例句: A cat is sitting on the armchair.
例句释义: 扶椅上坐着一只猫。

例句: Plagiarism and smoking in non-smoking areas are both considered immoral behavior.
例句释义: 抄袭和在无烟区吸烟都是不道德的行为。

详细释义: v. 伤心，悲痛；  vi. 使悲伤，使伤心
英文释义: to feel very sad, especially because somebody has died
例句: She's been grieving ever since her husband died.
例句释义: 丈夫去世之后，她一直感到很悲伤。

英文释义: a large and long container in which people take baths or showers
例句: The white bathtub on the wooden floor is filled with water.
例句释义: 木地板上的白色浴缸装满了水。

英文释义: of various different sorts
例句: Look at this assorted array of healthy fruit juice!
例句释义: 看看这些种类丰富的健康果汁！

英文释义: willing to listen to or accept ideas, suggestions, etc.
例句: Her elderly mother was surprisingly receptive to her suggestion to go skydiving.
例句释义: 她年迈的母亲出人意料地欣然接受了去跳伞的建议。

英文释义: electrical force measured in volts
例句: “Be careful, this machine has a high voltage.”
例句释义: “小心，这台机器带高压电。”

英文释义: a title printed at the top of a page or at the beginning of a section of a book
例句: Heading is written or printed at the top of a page of writing.
例句释义: 标题通常书写或打印在一页文字的顶部。

英文释义: energy, force or enthusiasm
例句: The pupil is walking to school with such vigor.
例句释义: 这个充满活力的小学生走在上学路上。

英文释义: if there is a scarcity of something, there is not enough of it and it is difficult to obtain it
例句: Water scarcity is a big problem facing many people around the world.
例句释义: 水资源短缺是世界上很多人都面临的一个重大问题。

英文释义: to become more severe or strong or to make (something) more severe or strong
例句: The man stiffened his hair by applying some gel to it.
例句释义: 这个男人涂了些发胶，让头发更坚硬。

详细释义: n. 采石场；  v. 努力挖掘
英文释义: a place where large amounts of stone, etc. are dug out of the ground
例句: The quarry supplies rock for making buildings.
例句释义: 采石场提供建房所需的石材。

详细释义: n.挽具，马具；降落伞背带；  vt.治理（河流等）
英文释义: a set of strips of leather and metal pieces that is put around a horse’s head and body so that the horse can be controlled and fastened to a carriage, etc.; a set of strips of leather, etc. for fastening something to a person’s body or to keep them from moving off or falling
例句: A harness is fastened around the horse's head and body.
例句释义: 一套马具绑在马的头上和身上。

英文释义: to gradually become or make something become weaker until it disappears
例句: After the clouds dissipated, the sun shone through.
例句释义: 云雾消散后，阳光就穿透出来。

详细释义: n. 剩菜；残余物；  adj. 残余的
英文释义: food that has not been finished at a meal and that is often served at another meal
例句: The leftovers were thrown into the trash bin.
例句释义: 剩菜被倒进了垃圾桶。

英文释义: to make something known to the public; to advertise something
例句: He publicized their relationship to let everybody know that he's in love.
例句释义: 他公布了恋情，好让所有人知道他谈(bei)恋(cheng)爱(bao)了。

英文释义: a death that is caused in an accident or a war, or by violence or disease
例句: There were at least two fatalities as a result of the fire.
例句释义: 此次火灾有至少两起死亡。

英文释义: connected with sex in a way that most people find offensive; extremely large in size or amount in a way that most people find unacceptable and offensive
例句: The male monkey makes obscene display of his red buttock to attract the female.
例句释义: 这只公猴为了吸引母猴，下流地展示着它的红屁股。

例句: Oxygen in the air causes iron oxide to form on these bolts.
例句释义: 空气中的氧气使这些螺栓上形成了氧化铁。

详细释义: n. 凸出部分；  v. 凸出，膨胀
英文释义: a rounded lump on the surface of something
例句: He has a bulge in his stomach from drinking too much beer.
例句释义: 他由于喝啤酒太多，肚子已经突出来了。

英文释义: the fact of allowing fresh air to enter and move around a room, building, etc.
例句: The ventilation equipment in the ceiling keeps the air fresh.
例句释义: 天花板上的通风设备能让空气清新。

详细释义: n. 下属；部下；  adj. 次要的；  v. 使处于次要地位
英文释义: having less power or authority than somebody else in a group or an organization
例句: The boss thinks his subordinate is hard-working.
例句释义: 老板觉得他的部下很勤快。

详细释义: n. 肥料；  v. 施肥于
英文释义: the waste matter from animals that is spread over or mixed with the soil to help plants and crops grow
例句: The farmer adds manure to the crops to help them grow.
例句释义: 农民在庄稼上施肥料以帮助它们生长。

英文释义: expecting bad things to happen or something not to be successful; showing this
例句: The pessimistic man always expects the worst.
例句释义: 这个悲观的人总是把什么事情都想得很糟。

详细释义: adj.湍急的；混乱的，动荡的；骚动的
英文释义: (of air or water) changing direction suddenly and violently
例句: The man is struggling in the turbulent river.
例句释义: 那个男人在湍急的河水中挣扎着。

英文释义: of or relating to lines of longitude
例句: His trousers have longitudinal stripes, unlike his T-shirt.
例句释义: 跟他的T恤不同，他的裤子上有纵向条纹。

英文释义: a cynical feeling of distrust
例句: He can't hide his cynicism of the other man's reasons for proposing.
例句释义: 他掩饰不住对那个男人求婚目的的讥讽！

英文释义: a firm or public statement that something is true or that you support something strongly
例句: He was happy to receive the affirmations from his peers.
例句释义: 他很高兴受到同侪的肯定。

英文释义: making you want to do, try, taste, etc. something
例句: This bone looks rather inviting to the dog.
例句释义: 在汪星人看来，这根骨头相当诱人。

英文释义: an army or a country that enters another country by force in order to take control of it; a soldier fighting in such an army
例句: The soldiers are defending their land from the invaders.
例句释义: 士兵们正在抵御侵略者，保卫他们的土地。

英文释义: independent of other things of the same type
例句: The abacus is made up of discrete units.
例句释义: 算盘是由分开的单元组成的。

英文释义: to annoy somebody, especially deliberately
例句: The noise upstairs aggravates him.
例句释义: 楼上传来的噪声激怒了他。

英文释义: a stone at the corner of the base of a building, often laid in a special ceremony
例句: The number on the cornerstone represents the year the building was constructed.
例句释义: 奠基石上的数字代表了建筑物建造的年份。

详细释义: adj. 性感的；引人注意的
英文释义: sexually attractive
例句: The dog looks so seductive in those black silky stockings.
例句释义: 这只狗穿着黑丝袜，看上去真性感。

例句: A variety of dishes were served at the luncheon.
例句释义: 午宴提供了各种各样的菜式。

英文释义: an arrangement of flowers and/or leaves in the shape of a circle, traditionally hung on doors as a decoration at Christmas
例句: Wreaths are placed at war memorials.
例句释义: 花圈放置在战争纪念碑旁。

详细释义: adj. 令人烦恼的，讨厌的
英文释义: causing trouble, pain, etc. over a long period of time
例句: Frequently feeling the call of nature can be so troublesome for old people.
例句释义: 对老人来说，总想上厕所实在是令人烦恼。

详细释义: n.四周有篱笆（或围墙等）的场所，围场
英文释义: a piece of land that is surrounded by a fence or wall and is used for a particular purpose
例句: Animals can graze safely in the enclosure.
例句释义: 动物们在围场里可以安心地吃草。

详细释义: adj.愁容满面的，没有希望的；阴暗的
英文释义: nearly dark, or badly lit in a way that makes you feel sad; sad and without hope; without much hope of success or happiness in the future
例句: The little boy is in a really gloomy mood.
例句释义: 这个小男孩愁容满面。

英文释义: a machine that prints letters or figures on a sheet of paper when a person pushes its keys
例句: The author used a typewriter to write the novel.
例句释义: 作家用打字机来写小说。

英文释义: to cause (someone) to feel slightly angry
例句: Talking on your phone during a movie is likely to annoy others.
例句释义: 在看电影的时候打电话很可能会惹怒其他人。

英文释义: to harm (someone) through sexual contact :to touch (someone) in a sexual and improper way
例句: That dog tried to molest the kitty.
例句释义: 这只狗试图骚扰这只小猫.

英文释义: continuous movement and change; a flow; an act of flowing
例句: The shape of clouds is always in a state of flux.
例句释义: 云的形态总在不断地变化之中。

详细释义: n.质问，询问，怀疑；  v.询问，表示怀疑
英文释义: to ask questions or express doubt about (something)
例句: If you have a query, don't ask me―I don't know anything.
例句释义: 如果你有疑问，不要问我，我什么也不知道。

英文释义: an expression of very strong disapproval
例句: The criminal received widespread condemnation for committing the crime.
例句释义: 这名罪犯因所犯罪行受到了普遍的谴责。

详细释义: adj. 指示的；暗示的；陈述的；  n. 陈述语气
英文释义: showing or suggesting something
例句: The red numbers are indicative of danger.
例句释义: 红色的数字象征着危险。

例句: She's in a mid-level managerial position at the company.
例句释义: 她在这家公司担任一个中层管理职务。

英文释义: the act of putting somebody in a prison or another place from which they cannot escape; the state of being there
例句: Draven was sentenced to seven years' imprisonment.
例句释义: 德雷文被判处七年监禁。

英文释义: arranged neatly and with everything in order; keeping things neat and in order
例句: The living room looks so tidy after mom cleaned it.
例句释义: 妈妈打扫后，客厅变得如此干净整洁。

英文释义: funny and entertaining; showing a sense of humour
例句: This guy was so humorous and made everyone laugh.
例句释义: 这个人很幽默，把大家都逗笑了。

英文释义: a large fruit with hard green, yellow or orange skin, sweet flesh and juice and a lot of seeds
例句: They served different kinds of melon at the graduation party.
例句释义: 在毕业派对上，他们提供了不同种类的瓜。

英文释义: (of a thing) damaged or thinner than normal because it is old and has been used a lot
例句: Look at this pair of worn shoes, you need to buy a new pair.
例句释义: 看看你这双旧鞋，你得买双新的了。

英文释义: causing great surprise, excitement, or interest
例句: A piece of sensational  news spread over our company.
例句释义: 一则轰动性的消息传遍了我们公司。

英文释义: (used only in infinitives and in orders) if you tell somebody to beware, you are warning them that somebody/something is dangerous and that they should be careful
例句: Passers-by are warned to beware of the wet floor.
例句释义: 过路行人被提醒要小心地滑。

详细释义: adj. 有关的；适当的；中肯的
英文释义: appropriate to a particular situation
例句: I collected pertinent information of France before I traveled there.
例句释义: 在去法国旅行之前，我收集了跟当地有关的信息。

英文释义: something that is thought to be true or probable; the act of supposing that something is true, although it has not yet been proved or is not certain
例句: My presumption that he was dating with a girl turned out to be wrong.
例句释义: 我推测他在和女生约会，结果错了。

详细释义: n. 职业；行业；天职；使命
英文释义: a type of work or way of life that you believe is especially suitable for you
例句: These vocations play different roles in our society.
例句释义: 这些职业在我们的社会中扮演着不同的角色。

英文释义: the fact of doing what you are told to do or of being willing to obey
例句: Obedience is one of the most important qualities in a dog.
例句释义: 顺从是狗最重要的一个特点。

详细释义: vt. 资助，捐助，向……捐钱；认为……具有某种品质
英文释义: to give a large sum of money to a school, a college or another institution to provide it with an income
例句: The kind man endowed a million dollars to the school.
例句释义: 这位好心人向该校资助了一百万美元。

英文释义: fair and reasonable; treating everyone in an equal way
例句: The white rabbit proposed an equitable distribution of the carrots.
例句释义: 小白兔提议用一种公平的方式来分胡萝卜。

英文释义: the things that must be done to plan and organize a complicated activity or event that involves many people
例句: In ancient times, the logistics regarding food and supplies were key to winning wars.
例句释义: 在古代，要想赢得战争，粮草和其他补给的后勤保障十分重要。

详细释义: adj.机智幽默的；妙趣横生的

英文释义: a person who gives away secrets about their friends, their country, etc.

英文释义:

例句释义: 很多人喜欢白兰地胜于其他烈酒。

详细释义: adj. 雄伟的，崇高的，极端的，超群的；  n. 顶峰，崇高；  v. 使…纯化，使…升华，变高尚
英文释义: of very high quality and causing great admiration
例句: The sublime view brought him a magical feeling of awe.
例句释义: 壮丽的景色给他一种奇妙的敬畏感。

英文释义: the natural colour and condition of the skin on a person’s face
例句: They have different complexions but they formed a profound friendship.
例句释义: 虽然他们肤色不同，但是他们结下了深厚的友谊。

详细释义: n. 正派，体面，庄重，合乎礼仪，礼貌

例句: He has a strong sense of decency, so he can resist any temptation.
例句释义: 他为人正派，所以他能抵制住各种各样的诱惑。

详细释义: prep. 尽管，虽然；  adv. 尽管，虽然
英文释义: (also used following the noun it refers to) without being affected by something; despite something
例句: Notwithstanding the snow, the girl is still selling the matches.
例句释义: 尽管下雪了，小女孩仍然在卖火柴。

英文释义: the science or practice of planting and taking care of trees and forests
例句: Forestry is the science growing and taking care of trees in forests.
例句释义: 林学是养护和种植森林树木的科学。

详细释义: n. 扳手；痛苦，难受；  v. 使扭伤
英文释义: a metal tool with a specially shaped end for holding and turning things, including one which can be adjusted to fit objects of different sizes, also called a monkey wrench or an adjustable spanner
例句: The worker used a wrench to repair the sink.
例句释义: 这个工人在用扳手修水槽。

英文释义: to ask someone a lot of questions for a long time in order to get information, sometimes using threats
例句: The dog interrogated the kitten to find out the truth about his missing dinner.
例句释义: 狗狗在审问猫猫关于他消失的晚餐的事情。

英文释义: to choose not to demand something in a particular case, even though you have a legal or official right to do so
例句: The restaurant waived their fee because of the delay in serving the dishes.
例句释义: 餐馆因为延迟上菜而免单。

英文释义: to break into small parts or pieces and be destroyed
例句: The band that used to be so close, has now disintegrated.
例句释义: 这个曾经无比团结的乐队现在解散了。

详细释义: n. 拉链；  vt. 用拉链扣住；  vi. 拉上拉链
英文释义: a thing that you use to fasten clothes, bags, etc. It consists of two rows of metal or plastic teeth that you can pull together to close something or pull apart to open it.
例句: To get into this purse you need to open the zipper.
例句释义: 你得拉开拉链才能打开这个钱包。

英文释义: to remove something from something larger; to become separated from something; to leave or separate yourself from somebody/something
例句: I detach the screen protector from my phone.
例句释义: 我把保护膜从手机上撕了下来。

英文释义: spending a lot more money or using a lot more of something than you can afford or than is necessary; costing a lot more money than you can afford or is necessary; (of ideas, speech or behaviour) very extreme or impressive but not reasonable or practical
例句: The?extravagant?woman?spent?a?large amount?of?money?on?these?shoes.
例句释义: 那位奢侈的女士花了一大笔钱买这双鞋。

详细释义: v.（风暴、危机等）酝酿，即将来临；调制；酿造；冲泡 (茶），煮（咖啡)；  n.酿造的饮料；啤酒
英文释义: to make beer
例句: Trouble was brewing outside the stadium as rival fans were gathering.
例句释义: 球场外对立的粉丝们开始聚集，一场冲突正在酝酿之中。

详细释义: n. 锌；  vt. 镀锌于…
英文释义: a chemical element. Zinc is a bluish-white metal that is mixed with copper to produce brass and is often used to cover other metals to prevent them from rusting.
例句: Zinc is a very common metal.
例句释义: 锌是一种很常见的金属。

英文释义: not very good
例句: The quality of the wine is just mediocre; not bad, but not good.
例句释义: 这酒品质一般，不好也不坏。

英文释义: to make somebody responsible for doing something or taking care of somebody
例句: He entrusted his friend take care of a bank transaction for him.
例句释义: 他委托朋友帮他到银行办理业务。

英文释义: present only in small amounts :less than necessary or normal
例句: The desert's vegetation is sparse; there are hardly any plants here at all.
例句释义: 该沙漠植被稀少，几乎看不到任何植物。

英文释义: money that is given to a school, a college or another institution to provide it with an income; the act of giving this money
例句: People help the hospital through difficult times with generous endowments.
例句释义: 人们用慷慨的捐赠帮助这家医院度过困难时期。

英文释义: done to cure or treat someone
例句: This little boy is taking remedial action, repairing his damages to his neighbors' fence.
例句释义: 小男孩正在采取补救措施，修复被他弄坏的邻居家的篱笆。

详细释义: v. 叙述；给（电视或电影）作旁白；  vi. 讲故事
英文释义: to tell a story
例句: She used lively expressions to help her narrate her story.
例句释义: 她用生动活泼的表情来叙述故事。

英文释义: a sport in which athletes are judged on how well they perform various physical exercises on a mat or on special equipment
例句: These gestures are quite common in gymnastics.
例句释义: 这些姿势在体操中很常见。

英文释义: a law which says that people must not go outside after a particular time at night until the morning; the time after which nobody must go outside
例句: Due to the curfew, people must return to their houses by midnight.
例句释义: 因为宵禁，人们必须在12点之前回家。

详细释义: n. 表演，演奏；给予，提供
英文释义: the performance of something, especially a song or piece of music; the particular way in which it is performed
例句: Your rendition of Beethoven was fantastic!
例句释义: 你对贝多芬作品的演奏真是太棒了！

英文释义: a book or set of books giving information about all areas of knowledge or about different areas of one particular subject, usually arranged in alphabetical order; a similar collection of information on a website or CD-ROM
例句: This plant encyclopedia has many beautiful illustrations.
例句释义: 这本植物百科全书有很多漂亮的插图。

详细释义: adj.令人钦佩的，值得赞扬的
英文释义: having qualities that you admire and respect
例句: Her skills are very admirable.
例句释义: 她技能卓越。

英文释义: a way of criticizing a person, an idea or an institution in which you use humour to show their faults or weaknesses; a piece of writing that uses this type of criticism
例句: The cartoon depicts a satire of rich people's greed.
例句释义: 这幅漫画讽刺了富人的贪婪。

英文释义: the removal of a tooth
例句: I'm afraid the extraction of your tooth may be quite painful.
例句释义: 恐怕拔牙会很痛。

例句: Dinner is ready when she arrives at the restaurant, because she ordered beforehand by phone.
例句释义: 她到餐厅时，晚餐已经准备好了，因为她预先用手机点了菜。

英文释义: having a size, number, or amount that is directly related to or appropriate for something
例句: I'm eating a bigger burger because I'm bigger! It's proportional to my weight!
例句释义: 我吃大点儿的汉堡是因为我（体型）更大！这和我的体重是成比例的！

详细释义: adj. 沉闷的，冗长乏味的
英文释义: lasting or taking too long and not interesting
例句: It is really tedious to look at the screen all day long!
例句释义: 整天对着电脑屏幕，真是乏味极了！

英文释义: having or bringing a feeling of sadness mixed with pleasure and affection when you think of happy times in the past
例句: Sometimes, he gets very nostalgic for his hometown.
例句释义: 有时候，他非常思念故乡。

英文释义: the act of not including somebody/something or not doing something; the fact of not being included/done
例句: There was an omission of his name on the wedding invitation, which upset him deeply.
例句释义: 他对于他被疏忽邀请参加婚礼感到很沮丧。

详细释义: n.（空气或水的）乱流；骚乱，动荡
英文释义: a series of sudden and violent changes in the direction that air or water is moving in
例句: The plane is experiencing severe turbulence during the flight.
例句释义: 飞机在飞行时遇到了强烈的气流。

详细释义: n. 爬行动物，爬虫；  adj. 爬行的，爬虫类的
英文释义: any animal that has cold blood and skin covered in scales, and that lays eggs. Snakes, crocodiles and tortoises are all reptiles.
例句: These animals are reptiles.
例句释义: 这些动物都是爬行动物。

英文释义: not lasting :lasting for only a short time

例句释义: 即使是匆匆一眼，她可以看出这只狗狗很难过。

英文释义: the feeling of being slightly angry

例句释义: 令我恼火的是，我整晚都在试图杀死那只蚊子。

英文释义: a serious mental illness that causes you to falsely believe that other people are trying to harm you
例句: The man suffers from paranoia; he believes others are trying to harm him.
例句释义: 这个男人有妄想症，他总以为其他人想伤害他。

英文释义: a discrimination between things as different and distinct
例句: The differentiation between different colors is a very important ability for children.
例句释义: 对儿童来说，区分颜色是一种很重要的能力。

英文释义: a person who writes the story of another person’s life

例句释义: 这位传记作家写了很多关于名人生平的著作。

英文释义: large and impressively beautiful

例句释义: 这座宫殿在蓝天下看上去十分雄伟，我要是能住在里面就好啦！

英文释义: to make (someone or something) clean

英文释义: a liquid that is rubbed onto your skin or hair

详细释义: n.盗窃，夜盗，盗窃行为；  v.入室行窃

例句释义: 当他们到达犯罪现场时，很明显那里发生了入室盗窃。

英文释义: of or like water; containing a lot of water; (of food, drink, etc.) containing too much water; thin and having no taste
例句: The soup in this canteen is watery and had no flavor.
例句释义: 这个食堂的汤味道寡淡。

英文释义: to bring a dead person back to life
例句: The witch claimed that she could resurrect the dead.
例句释义: 那个女巫声称她可以使死人复活。

英文释义: Of or exhibiting electromagnetism
例句: Light, heat, X-rays and radio are all types of electromagnetic radiation.
例句释义: 光、热、X射线和无线电都是电磁辐射的形式。

详细释义: adj. 更可取的，更好的，更合适的（to）

例句: Consumers need some reassurance about returning goods bought online.
例句释义: 消费者需要一些网购退货的相关保证。

英文释义: cause to run off the tracks
例句: The toy train accidentally derailed and overturned.
例句释义: 这列玩具火车意外脱轨并翻了车。

英文释义: a man whose job is to take care of passengers on a ship, an aircraft or a train and who brings them meals, etc.
例句: A steward is looking after the passengers and serving them food.
例句释义: 这位男乘务员正在照顾乘客、分发餐食。

英文释义: involving two people or groups who agree to help each other or behave in the same way to each other
例句: Reciprocal relationships contribute to a good neighborhood.
例句释义: 互惠关系有助于建立好的邻里感情。

例句: Attach the electrodes to the battery to jump-start the car.
例句释义: 连接电池的电极，以启汽车引擎。

详细释义: vi. 闪耀；焕发，活跃，才华横溢；  n. 活力
英文释义: to shine brightly with small flashes of light
例句: The stars are beautiful as they sparkle in the sky.
例句释义: 星星在天空中闪耀时，看上去很美。

英文释义: able to control the way you behave and to make yourself do things that you believe you should do
例句: Mr. Bear, who is disciplined, has never broken the rules.
例句释义: 遵守纪律的熊先生从未违反过规则。

英文释义: fit or suitable to be eaten; not poisonous

详细释义: v. 消灭；宣布中立，使中立化

英文释义: a very tall building in a city

英文释义: a storm with thunder and lightning and usually very heavy rain

例句释义: 雷暴雨的巨响让我整晚没睡。

英文释义: a small thin book with a paper cover that contains information about a particular subject
例句: This little booklet will explain everything you want to know.
例句释义: 这个小册子解释了你想要知道的一切。

详细释义: n. 公告，声明，宣告，判决
英文释义: a formal public statement
例句: He delivered a pronouncement outlining the new rules.

详细释义: adj. 滑稽的；令人捧腹的

英文释义: a vegetable with shiny dark purple skin and soft white flesh

详细释义: vt. 宣布放弃，与...断绝关系；  n. 垫牌
英文释义: to state publicly that you no longer have a particular belief or that you will no longer behave in a particular way
例句: He has renounced his former associate for his crime.
例句释义: 因为合作伙伴犯罪，他宣布与其断绝关系。

详细释义: v. 包围，包上；  n. 信封（同“envelope”）
英文释义: to wrap somebody/something up or cover them or it completely

例句释义: 大海包围着这座小岛。

英文释义: to leave your own country to go and live permanently in another country
例句: The cat left its country and emigrated to the Giraffe Kingdom.
例句释义: 这只猫离开了自己的国家，移居到了长颈鹿王国。

详细释义: v. 向…行贿；买通；  n. 贿赂；行贿物
英文释义: to give somebody money or something valuable in order to persuade them to help you, especially by doing something dishonest

英文释义: to enlarge beyond bounds or the truth
例句: He is overstating what really happened to gain people's sympathy.
例句释义: 他为了博得大家的同情而夸大了事实。

详细释义: det.无论哪个；  pron.无论哪些

例句释义: 那个女孩不赞成晚餐吃比萨。

英文释义: to open your mouth wide and breathe in deeply through it, usually because you are tired or bored
例句: The cat yawned lying on the grass. So cute!
例句释义: 这只猫躺在草地上打哈欠，太可爱了！

详细释义: adv. 强调地，着重地，明显地，断然地
英文释义: in a very clear way that involves speaking with force

例句释义: “不能吃快餐”，她坚决地对她的孩子说。

详细释义: n. 高潮，最令人兴奋（或感兴趣）的部分
英文释义: the most exciting or important event or point in time; the most exciting part of a play, piece of music, etc. that usually happens near the end; the highest point of sexual pleasure

例句释义: 电影的高潮部分太感人了，大家都哭了。

例句释义: 狐狸当黄金走私者的日子正式结束了！

英文释义: an official statement about something important that is made to the public; the act of making an official statement

例句释义: 树林里面的空气尤为潮湿。

详细释义: adj. 唱诗班的，合唱队的
例句: The choral society is performing on the stage.

英文释义: to express great happiness about something

例句释义: 他为自己考试的好成绩感到高兴。

英文释义: capable of being attributed

例句释义: 小松鼠之所以无家可归，是因为森林面积的减少。

英文释义: a length equal to 1?100 meter

例句释义: 这把尺子的长度是15厘米。

例句释义: 他们来自两个不同的地区，所以他们说不同的方言。

英文释义: a house built all on one level, without stairs
例句: A bungalow is a house which has only one level, and no stairs.
例句释义: 平房是指只有一层楼,没有楼梯的房子。

详细释义: adj. 无言的，未说出口的，不言而喻的
例句: The fact that they love each other remains unspoken.
例句释义: 他们彼此爱着对方，这是心照不宣的事实。

详细释义: n. 代替，替换，替换物，代入
英文释义: an act of using one person or thing in the place of another
例句: Normally sugar is used in the recipe; in substitution, I used honey.
例句释义: 在这个菜谱里通常会用到糖；作为替代，我用蜂蜜。

英文释义: a container with a lid, handle and a spout, used for boiling water
例句: I boil water in my kettle to make tea.
例句释义: 我把壶里的水烧开来泡茶。

英文释义: a small shallow round dish that a cup stands on
例句: This delicate saucer is made of porcelain.
例句释义: 这个漂亮的小碟子是瓷做的。

详细释义: n.再发生，循环，重现，重新提起
例句: He has a recurrence of stomachache.
例句释义: 他的胃病复发了。

英文释义: to use a particular set of facts or ideas in order to form an opinion that is considered valid for a different situation; to make a general statement about something and not look at the details
例句: It's safe to generalize that most trees are green.
例句释义: 可以毫不夸张地说，概括起来所有的树都是绿色的。

详细释义: adj. 短暂的，路过的；转瞬即逝的；  n. 过客
英文释义: continuing for only a short time
例句: The transient beauty of a meteor is rarely seen.
例句释义: 流星转瞬即逝的美总是很少被看见。

详细释义: v.掠夺，洗劫；  n.掠夺品，赃物
英文释义: (usually of large numbers of people during a violent event) to steal from shops and houses
例句: After the looting, there was nothing left in the jewelry store.
例句释义: 一番掠夺之后，珠宝店里空空如也。

英文释义: to dress somebody/yourself; to provide clothes for somebody to wear
例句: After his bath, my dog likes me to clothe him in his own little bathrobe.
例句释义: 洗澡后，狗狗喜欢我给它穿上它自己的浴袍。

英文释义: the force that drives something forward
例句: The rocket's propulsion is largely created by the burning of fuel.
例句释义: 火箭的推动力主要是由燃料燃烧产生的。

详细释义: adj. 二手的，旧的，用过的
英文释义: if you buy something second-hand, it is not new but has been owned by somebody else before
例句: I bought these second-hand items at good prices!
例句释义: 我以好价钱买到了这些二手货。

详细释义: adj. 给予知识的，提供有用信息的；见闻广博的
英文释义: providing information
例句: History books can be very informative.
例句释义: 历史书能带给人丰富的知识。

详细释义: n.漏斗；烟囱；  v.（使）成漏斗形
英文释义: a device shaped like a hollow cone with a tube extending from the point
例句: A funnel is the best way to pour liquid into a small hole.
例句释义: 使用漏斗是将液体倒入一个小洞的最好办法。

英文释义: a person who is very enthusiastic about something
例句: They are football fanatics.
例句释义: 他们是足球的狂热爱好者。

详细释义: adj. 名义上的；象征性的，很少的；名词性的
英文释义: being something in name only, and not in reality
例句: The emperor is just a nominal ruler.
例句释义: 这个皇帝只是名义上的统治者。

英文释义: the state or condition of having gotten or done something difficult :the act of attaining something
例句: Landing on the moon is now very possible attainment.
例句释义: 现在，人们有可能登上月球了。

英文释义: extremely; very; very much
例句: He was running exceedingly fast!
例句释义: 他跑的真是过分的快了！

英文释义: a condition in which something has become separated from something else
例句: This picture illustrates the healthy eye and the detachment of the retina.
例句释义: 这张图描绘了健康的眼睛和视网膜的脱离。

详细释义: adj. 驯服的，温顺的；  v. 驯服
英文释义: (of animals, birds, etc.) not afraid of people, and used to living with them
例句: Don't worry, this lion is tame―it won't hurt you.
例句释义: 别担心，这只狮子很温驯，它不会伤害你的。

详细释义: n.艺术表现；翻译；透视图；抹灰底层
英文释义: the performance of a piece of music, a role in a play, etc; the particular way in which sth is performed
例句: Their rendering of this dance was simply exquisite.
例句释义: 他们对于这支舞蹈的表现精彩细腻。

英文释义: the feeling of needing or wanting a drink
例句: The precious water can satisfy his thirst.
例句释义: 这瓶宝贵的水能让他解渴。

英文释义: the family or the race of people that you come from
例句: It's interesting to look back at human ancestry.
例句释义: 回头研究人类的祖先是件有趣的事情。

详细释义: adj. 绘画的，形象化的；  n. 画报，画刊
英文释义: using or containing pictures; connected with pictures
例句: Internationally-recognized signs are pictorial representations of ideas.
例句释义: 国际公认的标志是思想形象化的表现。

详细释义: n. 卫生；卫生学；保健学
英文释义: the practice of keeping yourself and your living and working areas clean in order to prevent illness and disease
例句: Hands should be washed with soap to improve hygiene.
例句释义: 为了更卫生，洗手的时候应该用肥皂。

详细释义: adj. 临时的，暂时的，暂定的；  n. 临时邮票
英文释义: existing or accepted for the present time but likely to be changed
例句: He lost his ID card so used a provisional one to take the train.
例句释义: 他的身份证丢了，所以用了一张临时的身份证明来乘火车。

详细释义: vt. 打发走，把（外国人）驱逐出境
英文释义: to force somebody to leave a country, usually because they have broken the law or because they have no legal right to be there
例句: The tiger is being deported to his homeland because he broke the law.
例句释义: 老虎因触犯法律而被遣送回国。

英文释义: (especially in compounds) a person or an animal that lives in the particular place that is mentioned
例句: I'm an apartment dweller―we share this building with many others.
例句释义: 我住在公寓里――我们同其他许多人共享这栋楼。

英文释义: having or showing very strong feelings
例句: She is an ardent supporter of a creative application.
例句释义: 她是一款创意app的死忠粉。

详细释义: adj. 正直的，正当的，公正的
英文释义: morally good :following religious or moral laws
例句: Catching the thief was a righteous thing to do; he gained everyone's respect.
例句释义: 抓小偷是件正义的事情，他因此得到了人们的尊重。

英文释义: the act or process of telling a story, especially in a novel, a film/movie or a play
例句: Her narration of the story really brought the characters to life.
例句释义: 她对故事的叙述仿佛使得故事中的人物活了过来。

详细释义: n. 猛的一击，摇晃，震惊；  v. （使）颠簸，摇晃，使震惊
英文释义: a sudden, rough movement
例句: The truck jolted over the rough ground.
例句释义: 卡车在凹凸不平的地面上颠簸而行。

英文释义: to repair something that has been damaged or broken so that it can be used again; to repair a hole in a piece of clothing, etc.
例句: The man is trying to mend the damaged roof.
例句释义: 这个男人正在修补被损坏的的屋顶。

英文释义: an official appointed to count the votes (especially in legislative assembly)
例句: Tellers deal with customers face-to-face in the bank, including giving and receiving cash.
例句释义: 银行出纳员与客户面对面打交道，包括给出和收取现金。

英文释义: (formal) harmful
例句: Sweet food is detrimental to your teeth.
例句释义: 甜食对你的牙齿有害。

英文释义: well known because of a special skill or feature
例句: Sichuan is noted for being the home of pandas.
例句释义: 四川因为是熊猫故乡而著名。

英文释义: shocking; extremely bad
例句: Their fight in the movie was really appalling!
例句释义: 他们在电影中的打斗场景真是太可怕了！

详细释义: n. 估价，评价，鉴定；估定的价值，定价
英文释义: the act or process of making a judgment about the price or value of something
例句: The specialist conducted a valuation of the antique vase.
例句释义: 专家对古董花瓶进行了估价。

英文释义: a container in which water is heated to provide hot water and heating in a building or to produce steam in an engine
例句: The boiler provides hot water and heating for the building.
例句释义: 锅炉为大楼提供热水和暖气。

英文释义: having a lot of knowledge because you have studied and read a lot
例句: Aristotle is a very learned man in history.
例句释义: 历史上，亚里士多德是一位十分博学的人。

英文释义: a statement or description that makes something seem larger, better, worse or more important than it really is; the act of making a statement like this
例句: Saying he had caught a fish bigger than a man was a great exaggeration!
例句释义: 他极尽夸张之能事，声称自己钓到了一条比人还大的鱼！

英文释义: not fair or deserved
例句: It was an unjust trial!
例句释义: 这是一场不公平的审判！

英文释义: angry or violent disagreement between two people or groups of people; trouble or difficulty of any kind
例句: The couple's strife is mainly due to a money issue.
例句释义: 钱已经成为了许多婚姻当中引发冲突的原因。

英文释义: full of new, exciting or dangerous experiences
例句: He was an adventurous man who travelled far and wide!
例句释义: 他是一个爱冒险的人，他走遍了世界！

英文释义: a person who is being taught how to do a particular job
例句: Trainees must work under the guidance of their trainers.
例句释义: 受训者必须在施训者的指导下展开工作。

详细释义: n. 退款；  v. 退款
例句: Customers that are unhappy with the clothes are able to apply for a refund.
例句释义: 顾客如果对衣服不满意可以申请退款。

英文释义: a small strong vehicle used, especially by the army, for driving over rough ground
例句: This man is driving a jeep with luggage strapped to the roof.
例句释义: 这个人开着一辆吉普车，行李捆在车顶上。

英文释义: to produce a substance by means of chemical or biological processes
例句: A new drug has been synthesized in the laboratory.
例句释义: 一种新型药品在实验室里被合成了。

详细释义: adv. 轮流地，交替地，依次地
英文释义: if two things happen alternately, they follow each other in a regular way, one after the other
例句: The couple agree to alternately do the dishes.
例句释义: 这对夫妻约定轮流洗碗。

英文释义: unable to take enough air into your lungs :breathing very hard because you are trying to get more air
例句: The asthma attack left her breathless.
例句释义: 她哮喘犯了，喘不过气。

英文释义: to become solid; to make something solid; (of ideas, etc.) to become or to make something become more definite and less likely to change
例句: The yellow liquid in the mould soon solidified into jelly.
例句释义: 模具中的黄色液体很快凝固成了果冻。

例句: He is such a skilled craftsman! The plate looks so amazing!
例句释义: 他是一个手艺如此精湛的工匠！这个盘子画得太棒了！

英文释义: inclined or able to forgive and show mercy
例句: His mother was forgiving of his breaking the vase.
例句释义: 他妈妈对他打破花瓶这件事很宽容。

英文释义: a belief that is not true :a false idea
例句: He is under the delusion that someone is sitting next to him.
例句释义: 他有种有人坐在他旁边的错觉。

详细释义: vt.把……静音；  n.弱音器；  adj.缄默的
英文释义: to make the sound of something, especially a musical instrument, quieter or softer, sometimes using a mute
例句: The man answered the phone after muting the TV.
例句释义: 这个男人给电视静音后，接听了电话。

英文释义: the way in which a particular living thing functions
例句: The doctor is measuring patient's blood pressure to test human physiology while running.
例句释义: 医生正测量病人的血压，以测试人体跑步时的生理机能。

英文释义: to consider that something is caused by a particular thing or person
例句: We can ascribe his illness to undue work pressure.
例句释义: 我们可以把他的病归因于过度的工作压力。

英文释义: to wake (someone) from sleep
例句: My husband likes to rouse me with a gentle touch in the morning.
例句释义: 每天早上，我丈夫喜欢轻轻地推醒我。

英文释义: a room for several people to sleep in, especially in a school or other institution
例句: My dormitory is clean and tidy.
例句释义: 我的宿舍干净整洁。

英文释义: the quality of showing or saying what you really think or feel
例句: With all sincerity, I offer you my heart.
例句释义: 我诚意满满地将我的心奉献给你。

英文释义: to push something out suddenly and with a lot of force; when you eject a disk, tape, etc., or when it ejects, it comes out of the machine after you have pressed a button
例句: I eject the DVD from the DVD player.
例句释义: 我把DVD从DVD机里弹了出来。

详细释义: n. 元帅；  v. 整理，排列，集结
英文释义: an officer of the highest rank in the British army or air force
例句: The marshal held the highest rank in the army.
例句释义: 元帅享有军队最高军衔。

详细释义: v.规定；保证；要求以……为条件
英文释义: to state clearly and firmly that something must be done, or how it must be done
例句: The confidentiality agreements stipulate that moviegoers can not reveal any plot of the movie.
例句释义: 保密协议规定，所有观影人都不得透露影片的任何情节。

英文释义: a large, round fruit that has hard, green skin, sweet, red, juicy flesh, and black seeds
例句: Watermelon is a popular summer fruit.
例句释义: 西瓜是夏天很受欢迎的水果。

详细释义: adj. 令人不悦的；讨厌的
英文释义: not wanted or approved of; likely to cause trouble or problems
例句: Well, I certainly think it's undesirable to get fired from my job.
例句释义: 我当然认为我被解雇是件令人不悦的事。

英文释义: A memorandum is a written report that is prepared for a person or committee in order to provide them with information about a particular matter.
例句: Did you get the memorandum about the meeting tomorrow?
例句释义: 你拿到明天会议的便签了吗？

例句: Cupid is the embodiment of love and tenderness.
例句释义: 丘比特是爱情与温柔的化身。

英文释义: very much; extremely; with no limit
例句: The ocean seems to be infinitely vast.
例句释义: 大海好像无限广阔。

英文释义: not paid, done, returned, etc. by the required or expected time
例句: The boy needs to pay the fine on his overdue book.
例句释义: 这男孩需要为过期未还的书支付罚款。

例句: Regular exercise can improve your metabolic rate.
例句释义: 定期运动可以提高你的新陈代谢率。

英文释义: (of buildings, clothes, objects, etc.) in poor condition because they have been used a lot; (of a person) badly dressed in clothes that have been worn a lot; (of behavior) unfair or unreasonable
例句: Our plan was to buy and fix the shabby old house.
例句释义: 我们的计划是买下并整修这个破旧的老房子。

详细释义: n. 大修；彻底革新；  vt. 解体检修，大修
英文释义: an examination of a machine or system, including doing repairs on it or making changes to it
例句: His old car will need a complete overhaul after the accident.
例句释义: 这次事故过后，他的旧车需要彻底大修。

英文释义: producing a large amount of something
例句: He is a prolific athlete who has won many medals.
例句释义: 他是一位多产的运动员，赢得了许多奖牌。

英文释义: in a direction from lower to higher
例句: The roller coaster was going upwards along the track very fast.
例句释义: 过山车正沿着轨道向上飞驰。

英文释义: the psychological result of perception and learning and reasoning
例句: Developing moral cognition is as important as acquiring knowledge.
例句释义: 建立道德认知与获取知识一样重要。

英文释义: making it easy, possible, or likely for something to happen or exist
例句: Libraries provide an environment that is more conducive to learning than studying at home.
例句释义: 与在家学习相比，图书馆提供的环境更有利于学习。

英文释义: having a fault or faults; not perfect or complete
例句: The young woman received a parcel with defective goods.
例句释义: 这位年轻女子收到了一个商品有缺陷的包裹。

英文释义: living by killing and eating other animals
例句: We little fish can do nothing when faced with the predatory hawk.
例句释义: 我们这些小鱼面对捕食的老鹰真的无能为力。

英文释义: a person who is responsible for the money and accounts of a club or an organization
例句: A treasurer's main job is to deal with the finance of a company.
例句释义: 财务主管的主要工作是处理公司的财务问题。

详细释义: v. 使无效，使不能运转，使无能，使伤残，使丧失活动能力
英文释义: to injure or affect somebody permanently so that, for example, they cannot walk or cannot use a part of their body; to make something unable to work so that it cannot be used
例句: The thief disabled the security camera.
例句释义: 小偷破坏了监控摄像头。

详细释义: vt. 审查，检查；  n. 检查员
英文释义: to remove the parts of a book, film/movie, etc. that are considered to be offensive, immoral or a political threat
例句: Before releasing, all films should be censored.
例句释义: 在上映之前，所有电影都要经过审查。

详细释义: adj. 荒谬的，可笑的，滑稽的
英文释义: very foolish
例句: The idea of becoming rich overnight while just loafing around all day is ludicrous!
例句释义: 他终日游手好闲却幻想一夜暴富，真是太荒唐可笑了！

英文释义: the aspect of pronunciation that involves bringing articulatory organs together so as to shape the sounds of speech
例句: The teacher is showing how to have good articulation.
例句释义: 这位老师正在演示如何正确地发音。

英文释义: not completely, but as a most important part
例句: Students in a foreign studies university consist chiefly of girls.
例句释义: 外国语大学的学生主要都为女生。

详细释义: adj.最适宜的；最佳的；  n.最佳条件；最适宜
英文释义: the best possible result, set of conditions, etc.
例句: Do you know the optimum temperature for the fish?
例句释义: 你知道最适宜鱼儿生存的温度是多少吗？

英文释义: the place where the money of a government, club, etc., is kept
例句: The treasury announced the annual budget, announcing more for the education sector.
例句释义: 国库宣布了年度预算，将给教育部分配更多的预算。

详细释义: n. 左轮手枪；旋转式装置
英文释义: a small gun that has a container for bullets that turns around so that shots can be fired quickly without having to stop to put more bullets in
例句: The cowboy is holding two revolvers in his hands; you better stay clear!
例句释义: 这个牛仔手中拿着两把左轮手枪，你最好离他远点！

详细释义: n. 头脑清楚；心智健全，神智正常
英文释义: the condition of having a healthy mind :the condition of being sane
例句: He depends on coffee to maintain his sanity when working long hours.
例句释义: 长时间工作时，他靠咖啡保持头脑清醒。

英文释义: the belief that a perfect life, situation, etc. can be achieved, even when this is not very likely
例句: He was full of youthful idealism, believing all good things will come true.
例句释义: 他满脑子都是年轻人的理想主义，他觉得一切皆可以实现。

英文释义: a person who enters a building illegally in order to steal
例句: The burglar is trying to break into the house.
例句释义: 盗贼正试图闯进这个家。

详细释义: v.群集，蜂拥；  n.一大群人
英文释义: to go somewhere or be present somewhere in large numbers
例句: The crowds thronged into the mall.
例句释义: 人群涌进了大厅。

英文释义: edible seeds or roots or stems or leaves or bulbs or tubers or nonsweet fruits of any of numerous herbaceous plant
例句: There are different types of veggies on the table.
例句释义: 桌子上有不同种类的蔬菜。

英文释义: clever at understanding and making judgements about a situation
例句: He was a shrewd businessman who was careful with every penny.

The?wretched?old?lady?lives?in?poor?
conditions.
