英文释义: a place where you can play games on machines which you use coins to operate
例句: The young boy spent the whole day playing games at the arcade.
例句释义: 这个年轻的男孩在游戏厅玩了一整天了。

英文释义: the group of people who are members of the highest social class in some countries
例句: Look at their outfits! They must belong to the nobility.
例句释义: 看看他们的服装！他们一定是贵族。

详细释义: n. 疾驰，飞驰；  v. （马）飞奔，疾驰
英文释义: the fastest speed at which a horse can run, with a stage in which all four feet are off the ground together
例句: The horse's gallop is very graceful.
例句释义: 那匹马飞奔疾驰的姿势非常优美。

英文释义: a person who loves their country and who is ready to defend it against an enemy
例句: That patriot is saluting the national flag.
例句释义: 那位爱国者在向国旗敬礼。

详细释义: n. 手推车；电车；有轨电车；无轨电车；触轮
英文释义: a small vehicle with wheels that can be pushed or pulled along and is used for carrying things
例句: This trolley is the perfect size for this kitten to push.
例句释义: 这个手推车对这只小猫咪来说大小刚刚好。

英文释义: the fact of depending on each other; the fact of consisting of parts that depend on each other
例句: The disabled couple rely on interdependence to ride the bike.
例句释义: 这对残疾夫妇需要互相依赖才能骑走自行车。

详细释义: adj. 向前的；  adv. 向前
英文释义: continuing or moving forward
例句: Onward, my friend! Win the race for me!
例句释义: 朋友，冲啊！为我赢得比赛吧！

英文释义: able to do something well because of training and practice
例句: She's proficient in several languages.
例句释义: 她精通几门语言。

英文释义: not joined or connected :separate from another part or thing
例句: This beautiful detached house has a red front door and garage.
例句释义: 这座漂亮的独栋宅院有红色的正门和车库。

详细释义: adj. 充满深情的，挚爱的
英文释义: showing caring feelings and love for somebody
例句: The affectionate couple are smiling at each other.
例句释义: 这对深情的夫妇互相微笑。

详细释义: n. 峡谷；胃；暴食；咽喉；障碍物；  v. 拼命吃；吞下，狼吞虎咽；塞满，填满
英文释义: a deep, narrow area between hills or mountains
例句: This gorge is famous for its spectacular views.
例句释义: 这个峡谷以壮观的景色而闻名。

英文释义: act against (something) :to cause (something) to have less of an effect or to have no effect at all
例句: She applies eye cream to counteract the effects of tiredness.
例句释义: 她疯狂涂眼霜想要消除熬夜的后果。

英文释义: a silver-white metallic element that produces a very bright white light when it burns
例句: Magnesium is commonly used in fireworks.
例句释义: 镁在烟花中被广泛使用。

详细释义: v.（尤指为法律、社会状况的改变而）激烈争论，鼓动，煽动；搅动（液体）
英文释义: to argue strongly for something you want, especially for changes in a law, in social conditions, etc.
例句: He agitated the workers to go on strike.
例句释义: 他煽动工人们继续罢工。

详细释义: n. 【法律】少年犯罪，不法行为（青少年），行为不当
例句: School bullying is a kind of delinquency which will not be tolerated.
例句释义: 校园霸凌是少年犯罪的一种，对此不应有丝毫容忍。

英文释义: water or air is not moving and therefore smells unpleasant
例句: The stagnant pond is dirty, while the lake is replenished with fresh water.
例句释义: 这个不流动的池塘很脏，而这个湖泊不断有活水流动。

详细释义: adj. 紧张的，忙碌的；（因患肺病等）发烧的，有病态潮红的
英文释义: very busy and filled with activity
例句: She hopes to have more hands to end this hectic day!
例句释义: 她希望能多长几只手来终结这忙碌的一天！

详细释义: n. 必需品；  adj. 需要的，必不可少的，必备的
英文释义: something that you need for a particular purpose
例句: The USB cable is a requisite for charging my iPhone.
例句释义: 为了给iPhone充电，我必须有USB数据线。

详细释义: adj.弯曲的；  v.弯腰，弯曲（bend过去式）
英文释义: having a shape that is changed by bending :not straight
例句: The man is picking out the bent nails from the straight ones.
例句释义: 那个男人正在从一堆钉子中挑出弯曲的钉子。

详细释义: n. 弯路，绕行之路；  v. 绕道，迂回
英文释义: a longer route that you take in order to avoid a problem or to visit a place; a road or route that is used when the usual one is closed
例句: I had to take a detour to the destination because my usual shortcut was blocked off.
例句释义: 我不得不绕路前往目的地，因为我常用的捷径被阻断了。

英文释义: a very small piece of matter (= a substance) with a positive electric charge that forms part of the nucleus (= central part) of an atom
例句: Protons are positively charged particles in the center of an atom.
例句释义: 质子是原子核中带正电的粒子。

英文释义: a traditional short story that teaches a moral lesson, especially one with animals as characters; these stories considered as a group
例句: "The Fox and The Grapes" is one of the most famous fables.
例句释义: “狐狸与葡萄”是著名的寓言故事之一。

英文释义: polite behaviour
例句: Tipping one's hat to a lady is an old-fashioned gesture of civility.
例句释义: 向女士倾斜帽子是老式的礼仪手势。

英文释义: to decide that (something or someone) is wrong :to rule against (something or someone)
例句: I told them my decision, but my boss overruled me and made a different decision.
例句释义: 我告诉他们我的决定，但是我的老板否决了我，并做出了不同的决策。

英文释义: to relate
例句: Pots, stoves and chopping knives all pertain to cooking.
例句释义: 锅、炉子和菜刀都与烹饪有关。

英文释义: a special right or privilege that some people have
例句: Voting is everybody's prerogative; we should all do it.
例句释义: 投票是每个人都有的权利；我们应该去做。

英文释义: hard to handle or manage because of size or weight
例句: This gift box is too cumbersome; I'll never carry it home.
例句释义: 这个礼物盒太笨重了，我绝对没办法把它带回家。

详细释义: adj.容易发生的，免不了的；  n.附带事件，杂项
英文释义: happening by chance, or in connection with something of greater importance.
例句: Some incidental injuries are natural in such a violent sport.
例句释义: 在这样一项激烈的运动中，在所难免会伴随着受伤。

英文释义: a message sent by telegraph and then printed and given to somebody
例句: She sent a telegram upon her arrival in Beijing.
例句释义: 她一抵达北京就发了一封电报。

英文释义: the fact that the same thing happens again and again, and usually with the same length of time between each time it happens; the fact that something is arranged in an even way or in an organized pattern
例句: There is a regularity in wild geese's flying south every autumn.
例句释义: 大雁每年秋天南飞的行为存在规律性。

详细释义: adj. 应付的，未付的，欠着的，受恩惠的，感激的，负有义务的
英文释义: money that is owing has not been paid yet
例句: The National Debt is the total amount of money borrowed by the government that is still owing.
例句释义: 国家债务是由政府举借的、尚未偿还的金钱总额。

详细释义: adv. 无疑地；肯定地；  adj. 无疑的；肯定的
英文释义: almost certainly
例句: You will doubtless agree with me that 1 + 1 = 2?
例句释义: 1+1=2 这个公式你没有异议吧？

详细释义: adv. 忠实地；诚心诚意地
例句: This dog faithfully waits for its master to come home every day.
例句释义: 这只狗每天忠诚地等待他的主人回家。

详细释义: n. 文盲，目不识丁者；  adj. 缺乏（某方面）知识的
英文释义: (of a person) not knowing how to read or write
例句: Illiterates cannot read.
例句释义: 文盲无法阅读。

英文释义: stopping and starting often over a period of time, but not regularly
例句: The intermittent rain lasted for the entire day.
例句释义: 雨断断续续下了一整天。

详细释义: n. 海滨，海边；  adj. 海边的，海滨的
英文释义: an area that is by the sea, especially one where people go for a day or a holiday/vacation
例句: I hope we can take a vacation on the seaside.
例句释义: 我希望我们能去海边度假。

英文释义: showing strong feelings that are sincere
例句: Love is a heartfelt emotion.
例句释义: 爱是一种真挚的情感。

英文释义: very weak; not effective; not showing determination or energy
例句: The feeble old man found it difficult to climb the stairs.
例句释义: 这位虚弱的老人连爬楼梯都很困难。

英文释义: (of a tumour or disease) that cannot be controlled and is likely to cause death; (formal) having or showing a strong desire to harm somebody
例句: The tumor is malignant―we will have to remove it.
例句释义: 这是恶性肿瘤，我们必须切除它。

英文释义: that has fallen to the bottom of the sea or the ocean, or of a lake or river
例句: The sunken ship lies at the bottom of the ocean.
例句释义: 这艘船沉在了这片海的底部。

详细释义: adj. 公平的，不偏不倚的
英文释义: not supporting one person or group more than another
例句: A judge should guarantee that the trial is impartial.
例句释义: 法官应该保证审判是公平的。

详细释义: adj. 同时发生的；  n. 同时发生的事件
英文释义: existing or happening at the same time
例句: There are two concurrent football matches around the city.
例句释义: 有两场足球赛同时在市里举行。

详细释义: adj. 三角形的；三人间的
英文释义: shaped like a triangle
例句: Warning signs are often triangular in shape.
例句释义: 警示标志一般都是三角形的。

英文释义: a feeling of anger and surprise caused by something that you think is unfair or unreasonable
例句: She was filled with indignation at the news that many workers' wages were defaulted.
例句释义: 看到很多工人的工资被拖欠，她感到满心愤慨。

英文释义: having the training, knowledge, and experience that is needed to do something well; having a lot of skill
例句: They're very skillful skateboarders!
例句释义: 他们是技术极其娴熟的滑板运动员！

英文释义: to cut words or designs on wood, stone, metal, etc.
例句: The artist is engraving patterns into the wood.
例句释义: 艺术家在木头上雕刻图案。

英文释义: the quality of being new and interesting in a way that is different from anything that has existed before
例句: The originality of the painter's work was impressive.
例句释义: 这位画家的作品的独创性令人印象深刻。

英文释义: prolonged unfulfilled desire or need
例句: The kitten had a yearning to go out after weeks indoors.
例句释义: 在室内闷了好几个星期后，这只小猫十分渴望出门。

英文释义: the quality that allows someone to do things that are dangerous or frightening; the quality or state of being brave
例句: The man's bravery is to be admired!
例句释义: 这个男人的勇敢无畏应当得到赞扬！

英文释义: the passage from the nose and throat to the lungs, through which you breathe
例句: In an asthma attack, your airway narrows, making it difficult to breathe.
例句释义: 哮喘让你的呼吸管变窄，这会造成呼吸困难。

英文释义: the area around the South Pole
例句: This kind of animal lives in the Antarctic.
例句释义: 这种动物生活在南极。

详细释义: n. 边缘；  v. 充满，注满；  vt. 注满
英文释义: the top edge of a cup, bowl, glass, etc.
例句: All the beer glasses were full to the brim.
例句释义: 杯子里的酒都溢出了。

英文释义: the time in a man’s life when he is a boy
例句: The boy enjoyed his happy boyhood in the countryside.
例句释义: 这个男孩在乡下度过了快乐的童年。

英文释义: to force (someone) to leave a place
例句: That man was evicted from the house for not paying the rent.
例句释义: 这个男人因为没有付房租，所以被赶出来了。

英文释义: a coloured pencil or stick of soft coloured chalk or wax, used for drawing
例句: The child colored many pictures with crayons.
例句释义: 小孩子用蜡笔给许多图画上色。

英文释义: (psychology) the conscious exclusion of unacceptable thoughts or desires
例句: She was shy at first, but overcame her inhibitions once she got to know him.
例句释义: 一开始她很害羞，但跟他熟了以后她就克服了自己的拘谨。

英文释义:
?
the choice and meaning of the words used when you say or write something
例句: He paid close attention to the wording when writing poetry.
例句释义: 在写诗时，他密切注意自己的措辞。

英文释义: having many mountains
例句: Airplanes cannot land in this mountainous area.
例句释义: 飞机不能在这片山区着陆。

详细释义: n.拖把；  v.用拖把拖洗、擦抹
英文释义: a tool for washing floors that has a long handle with a bunch of thick strings or soft material at the end
例句: Use this mop to clean the floor.
例句释义: 用这个拖把来清洁地板。

英文释义: to make somebody feel less tired or less hot; to fill somebody’s glass or cup again
例句: He had a cup of coffee to refresh himself.
例句释义: 他喝了一杯咖啡来给自己提神。

英文释义: the act of persuading someone to have sex with you
例句: The peacock shows his powers of seduction by spreading his splendid tail.
例句释义: 这只孔雀开屏了，展现着他的魅力。

详细释义: adj. （植物）茂盛的，（人）充满活力的
英文释义: (of plants, etc.) strong and healthy; growing quickly and well; full of energy, excitement and happiness
例句: The trees are exuberant in the forest in spring time.
例句释义: 春天的时候，森林里的树木长得很茂盛。

英文释义: paying attention to what is happening in case of danger, accidents, etc.
例句: The cat is keeping a watchful eye on the newcomer.
例句释义: 这只猫对于新来的（猫）非常警惕。

详细释义: n. 荒谬，谬论，荒谬的言行
英文释义: a ludicrous folly
例句: Having dinner with a turkey is an absolute absurdity.
例句释义: 和一只火鸡共进晚餐实在是荒谬极了。

详细释义: v. 劫持，劫机，拦路抢劫
英文释义: to use violence or threats to take control of a vehicle, especially a plane, in order to force it to travel to a different place or to demand something from a government
例句: The airliner was hijacked by a masked man.
例句释义: 这架飞机被一个蒙面男子劫持了。

详细释义: v. 分开，隔离，进行种族隔离
英文释义: to separate people of different races, religions or sexes and treat them in a different way; to keep one thing separate from another
例句: The police segregated the two rival camps of protesters.
例句释义: 警察把两个对立的抗议者阵营隔离开来。

英文释义: to think deeply, usually in silence, especially for religious reasons or in order to make your mind calm; to plan something in your mind; to consider doing something
例句: The dog meditates in order to get peace of mind.
例句释义: 这只狗狗通过冥想来获得内心的平静。

英文释义: the act of positioning close together (or side by side)
例句: The juxtaposition of the old house and the new one is quite artistic.
例句释义: 老房子和新房子的并列很有艺术感。

英文释义: the process of developing industries in a country or an area
例句: Urban industrialization has given many people factory jobs.
例句释义: 城市的工业化给很多人提供了工厂的工作。

英文释义: a situation, feeling, system, etc. that is not as good or true as it seems to be
例句: It's a sham! Don't drink it!
例句释义: 这是假货！千万别喝！

英文释义: to make (a food or drink) by mixing different things together
例句: He is concocting an unusual drink.
例句释义: 他正在调和一种不寻常的饮料。

英文释义: a unit used to measure the power of engines
例句: The maximum output of this engine is two hundred horsepower.
例句释义: 这台发动机的最大输出功率是200马力。

英文释义: to end a pregnancy early in order to prevent a baby from developing and being born alive; to give birth to a child or young animal too early for it to survive; to end or cause something to end before it has been completed, especially because it is likely to fail.
例句: The captain aborted the mission when the huge storm hit.
例句释义: 风暴来袭时，上校中止了任务。

英文释义: having an important, often very bad, effect on future events
例句: The Qing government made the fateful decision to adopt a close-door policy.
例句释义: 清政府做出了一项重大的决定――闭关锁国。

详细释义: v. 扩散，弥漫；传播；  adj. 四散的，散开的
英文释义: to spread something or become spread widely in all directions
例句: The blue ink diffuses slowly in the water.
例句释义: 蓝色的墨水渐渐扩散到了水里。

详细释义: adj. 善良的，有德行的，贞洁的
英文释义: behaving in a very good and moral way; claiming to behave better or have higher moral standards than other people
例句: It's virtuous to help people in need.
例句释义: 帮助有需要的人是善良（的行为）。

详细释义: n. 弱势的一方，受害者，输家
英文释义: a person, team, etc., that is expected to lose a contest or battle
例句: I'm only able to give paper in this game, so I will always be the underdog.
例句释义: 我在这个游戏中只能出布，所以我永远都只能是输家啦。

英文释义: extreme enthusiasm for something that is usually shared by many people
例句: I have a mania for neatness. It's a problem inside my head.
例句释义: 我的有整洁的癖好，这算是我脑中的执念。

详细释义: v.使有生气，使活泼；  adj.有生命的
例句: The boy's special brush pen can animate anything he draws.
例句释义: 马良的神笔能使他画的任何东西都活过来。

详细释义: v.使眼花；使赞叹不已；  n.光辉；令人赞叹的东西
英文释义: if a strong light dazzles you, it is so bright that you cannot see for a short time
例句: He was dazzled by the car's headlights.
例句释义: 他被车前灯照花了眼。

英文释义: natural ability or skill at doing something
例句: He has an excellent aptitude for science.
例句释义: 他对科学展现出了优异的天资。

英文释义: sinking until covered completely with water
例句: The car gradually sank into the river until total immersion.
例句释义: 汽车逐渐沉入河里，直到完全沉没。

详细释义: n.欢呼，赞扬，称赞；  vt.欢呼，喝彩，鼓掌欢迎；推选
英文释义: praise and approval for somebody/something, especially an artistic achievement
例句: She was highly acclaimed for her wonderful performance.
例句释义: 她因自己出色的成绩受到了高度称赞。

英文释义: to make somebody calmer or less angry by giving them what they want
例句: The little dog often appeases the big one by offering up his bones.
例句释义: 这只小狗常常献上骨头来防止大狗动怒。

详细释义: n.移民，移民出境，移居外国
英文释义: Removal from one country or region to another for the purpose of residence
例句: A great tide of emigration from Europe to America happened in the 19th century.
例句释义: 19世纪发生了一场从欧洲到美洲的大型移民潮。

英文释义: good for your health
例句: Fresh fruits and vegetables are much more healthful than fast food.
例句释义: 新鲜水果和蔬菜比快餐更有益身体健康。

英文释义: words or expressions that are used by a particular profession or group of people, and are difficult for others to understand
例句: I didn't understand all the horse and riding jargon he was using.
例句释义: 我不懂他所说的关于马和骑马的行话。

详细释义: adj. 不省人事的；无知的；愚蠢的；无意义的；不理解的
英文释义: unconscious
例句: The girl saw a man lying senseless on the ground.
例句释义: 女孩看到一个男人躺在地上不省人事。

英文释义: the quality of being unclear or abstruse and hard to understand
例句: He's troubled by the obscurity of the book, which is written in Old English.
例句释义: 这本用古英语写的书晦涩难懂，使他感到烦恼。

详细释义: adj. 艰巨的；努力的；陡峭的
英文释义: involving a lot of effort and energy, especially over a period of time
例句: Cycling uphill is an arduous task.
例句释义: 骑车上坡是很艰难的任务。

例句: Graduating from university is an unforgettable experience for most students.
例句释义: 对于大多数学生来说，大学毕业是一次难忘的经历。

英文释义: wood that has been cut into pieces to be used for burning in fires
例句: Firewood is wood that has been cut into small pieces to be burned in fires.
例句释义: 木柴是指被砍成块以便在火中燃烧的木头。

英文释义: in an excited manner
例句: He screamed excitedly when he received the job offer.
例句释义: 他接到任职通知时兴奋地大叫起来。

英文释义: extremely valuable or important
例句: This antique which is being exhibited is priceless.
例句释义: 这件正在展览的古董是无价的。

详细释义: adj. 温和的；适度的，有节制的

例句: Many kinds of flowers bloom in temperate climates.
例句释义: 很多种类的花都要在温和的气候才能开花。

英文释义: used as decoration rather than for a practical purpose
例句: The wall was decorated with an ornamental design.
例句释义: 墙上有装饰性的图案。

英文释义: the state or act of having or doing whatever you want; the state of allowing sb to have or do
例句: Whenever he feels stressed, he allows himself the indulgence of cake or two.
例句释义: 每当感到有压力时，他就放纵自己吃一两块蛋糕。

详细释义: adj. 刺激的，使人烦恼的
英文释义: annoying, especially because of something somebody continuously does or something that continuously happens
例句: The irritating customer succeeds in enraging him.
例句释义: 那位恼人的顾客成功激怒了他。

英文释义: to make a law affecting something
例句: The congress is responsible for legislating, or making laws.
例句释义: 国会负责立法或制定法律。

详细释义: vi. 猛扑，突然袭击；  n. 猛扑，飞扑；  vt. 扑过去抓住
英文释义: to suddenly jump toward and take hold of someone or something
例句: "Ahhh!" I screamed as the cat pounced on to me.
例句释义: “啊！”我在喵星人突袭我时大叫一声。

详细释义: v. 闪烁；发微光；  n. 闪光
英文释义: to shine in a weak, faint, or unsteady way
例句: The water glimmers in the sunlight.
例句释义: 日照下水光在闪烁。

英文释义: a device with two or more blades that turn quickly and cause a ship or an aircraft to move forward
例句: I've been trained to fly single propeller planes.
例句释义: 我接受过训练，学习驾驶单螺旋桨飞机。

详细释义: adj.决定性的，无争论余地的
英文释义: proving something, and allowing no doubt or confusion
例句: The footprint is conclusive evidence that there was a burglary.
例句释义: 这个脚印是入室盗窃的确凿证据。

英文释义: a festival held before Lent that includes music and dancing
例句: Thousands of people flock to the street and celebrate the carnival.
例句释义: 成千上万的人聚集在街上庆祝狂欢节。

英文释义: a large area of flat land in northern parts of the world where there are no trees and the ground is always frozen
例句: Not many animals can live in the inhospitable frozen northern tundra.
例句释义: 很少有动物能在冻土地带生存。

详细释义: adj. 详尽的；彻底的；消耗的
英文释义: including everything possible; very thorough or complete
例句: The exhaustive content of this encyclopedia makes it very useful to children.
例句释义: 这本百科全书详尽的内容对孩子们很有用。

例句: I feel like this dirty air is suffocating me.
例句释义: 我感觉浑浊的空气快让我窒息了。

英文释义: to a much greater level or degree than seems reasonable or appropriate
例句: The businessman felt excessively tired because he worked all night.
例句释义: 由于工作了一整夜，这个商务人士感到极度疲倦。

英文释义: (of sounds) very pleasant when played or sung together; arranged together in a pleasing way so that each part goes well with the other; (of relationships, etc.) friendly, peaceful and without any disagreement
例句: The sounds of their instruments blended into a harmonious whole.
例句释义: 他们的乐器声混在一起非常悦耳。

英文释义: a metaphorical use of a word is not concerned with real objects or physical events, but with ideas or events of a non-physical kind
例句: The gap between men and women is a metaphorical representation of gender differences.
例句释义: 男女之间存在的鸿沟是性别差异的隐喻。

英文释义: to surprise somebody very much
例句: The magic astonished the kids.
例句释义: 整个魔术使孩子们感到很吃惊。

详细释义: n. 使者；预兆；  v. 预告；为……欢呼

例句释义: 张骞作为使节，出使西域去处理外交事务。

详细释义: adv. 在空中，在高处，在上面

例句: The balloon quickly went aloft into the blue sky.
例句释义: 热气球很快就升到蓝天中。

英文释义: an increase to counteract a perceived discrepancy

例句释义: 当局的疏忽导致了这次火灾的逐步扩大。

英文释义: not moving much :calm and steady

例句释义: 湖面很平静。

详细释义: adv. 向西；  adj. 西方的；  n. 西部

例句释义: 这艘船穿过太平洋向西行驶。

英文释义: giving the reasons for something; intended to describe how something works or to make something easier to understand
例句: The physics textbook contains many explanatory statements and illustrations.
例句释义: 物理课本包含许多理论的解释和插图。

英文释义: a piece of furniture with shelves to hold books
例句: My bookcase contains about a hundred books.
例句释义: 我的书架上有大约100本书。

英文释义: a person who makes pots, bowls, plates, etc., out of clay :a person who makes pottery by hand
例句: The potter has made many different sized pots.
例句释义: 这位陶工做了许多不同大小的罐子。

详细释义: v. 聚集；  adj. 聚集在一起的
英文释义: to come together in a group or crowd
例句: The visitors congregated around the entrance.
例句释义: 游客们聚集在入口处。

详细释义: n. 顶峰，（哥德式建筑的）小尖塔；  v. 置于尖顶上，置于高处
英文释义: a high mountain top

英文释义: something that is compiled (as into a single book or file)
例句: His latest album is a compilation of his best works from the five years.
例句释义: 他最新的这张专辑是五年来最佳作品的合辑。

详细释义: n. 文艺复兴；新生，复兴
英文释义: the Renaissance the period in Europe during the 14th, 15th and 16th centuries when people became interested in the ideas and culture of ancient Greece and Rome and used these influences in their own art, literature, etc.
例句: Many masterpieces were created during the Renaissance.
例句释义: 文艺复兴时期杰作层出不穷。

详细释义: n. 摆，钟摆；摇摆不定的事态（或局面）

例句: The car is driving on a bumpy road.

例句: The blades of a helicopter move in a rotary motion as it is flying.

英文释义: loaded heavily with something :having or carrying a large amount of something
例句: The ship is laden with all kinds of products.
例句释义: 那个船装满了各种货物。

详细释义: adj. 赏识的，感激的，有欣赏力的，承认有价值的

例句: My boss was very appreciative of my efforts.

英文释义: more than you think is reasonable or necessary

英文释义: not correct; based on wrong information

英文释义: a powder or liquid that is used to clean clothes, dishes, etc. :a chemical substance that is like soap

例句释义: 洗涤剂可以去除衣物上的污渍，使其变干净。

英文释义: to bring somebody/something under control, especially by using force; to calm or control your feelings
例句: The police subdue the criminal and pin him to the ground.

英文释义: the state of having knowledge or understanding
例句: The teacher's explanation provided enlightenment for many of his confused students.
例句释义: 老师的讲解给许多困惑的学生以启迪。

英文释义: a feeling of fear; an experience that makes you feel fear

英文释义: all the animals that live in a particular area, time period, or environment

英文释义: a bag usually with handles and pockets that is used by women to carry money and personal belongings
例句: I thought I put my money in my pocketbook, but I can't find it!
例句释义: 我想我把我的钱放在了钱包里，但是我找不到了！

例句: I use pegs to make sure my washing stays on the line.

英文释义: (especially of children) behaving badly; not willing to obey
例句: The naughty kid used paints to stain the wall.
例句释义: 这个淘气的小孩用颜料把墙壁弄脏了。

英文释义: the process of a law becoming official; a law which has been made official
例句: The enactment of the regulation on garbage classification gained lots of support.
例句释义: 垃圾分类条例的颁布得到了广泛的支持。

英文释义: needing great effort and energy

例句释义: 对于他来说，举起这些哑铃太费力了。

英文释义: a unit for measuring length; a 1?000th of a metre
例句: The thickness of a single coin is one millimeter.
例句释义: 一枚硬币的厚度是一毫米。

英文释义: a tool that is used in the house

例句释义: 叉、勺和刀是餐桌用具。

例句释义: 麦哲伦的环球航行证实了地球不是平的。

英文释义: very important or serious, especially because there may be important results

例句释义: 结婚日是他们一生中的重要时刻。

详细释义: n. 胸部，胸怀，内部，内心；  adj. 亲密的，知心的；  v. 把…藏心中
英文释义: a woman’s chest or breasts

例句释义: 我的胸呢？没了！

例句释义: 伦敦是一个国际大都市；这里的人来自不同国家。

英文释义: to change frequently in size, amount, quality, etc., especially from one extreme to another

例句释义: 价格上下波动。

例句释义: 女孩手机被没收了，因为她上课用手机。

英文释义: not clear because of fog

例句释义: 医生正在给他做健康检查。

例句: The victor raised the trophy in the air happily.

例句: He was hasty when running to the office.

详细释义: n. 倾斜，斜坡，斜面；  v. （使）倾斜，（使）倾向于

例句: The small ball is on an incline and would hit the big ball.
例句释义: 小球在斜面的一端，可能会撞向大球。

英文释义: a hard cover for holding sheets of paper, magazines, etc. together

例句释义: 这些活页夹帮我把不同学科的讲义分类。

英文释义: a long coat that is worn to keep a person warm during cold weather

例句释义: 这件棕色大衣看起来很暖和。

英文释义: the type of mathematics that deals with rates of change, for example in the slope of a curve or the speed of a falling object
例句: I understand how to do most math, but calculus confuses me.
例句释义: 大部分的数学题我都会做，但微积分使我困惑。

例句: He was very mistaken about where the target was.
例句释义: 他对靶子在哪里的判断是错的。

英文释义: a group of words whose meaning is different from the meanings of the individual words
例句: The idiom "rain cats and dogs" means "it's raining heavily".
例句释义: 习语“rain cats and dogs”的意思是“下倾盆大雨"。

英文释义: a man who is employed to do physical work; (with an adjective) a person who works in the way mentioned
例句: These workmen are busy building the house.
例句释义: 这些工人正忙着建房子。

详细释义: adj. 巨大的，庞大的；巨像（似）的

例句: That's one colossal pumpkin.

例句释义: 这个男人镇定自若地在两辆行进的卡车上劈叉。

英文释义: someone who owns or manages a shop or store

英文释义: consider it carefully or use statistical methods in order to fully understand it
例句: Knowing how to analyse the stock market, he made a lot of money.
例句释义: 因为他知道如何分析股票市场，所以他挣了不少钱。

英文释义: the item at the end

例句释义: 你应该先拿到票，再托运行李，最后过安检。

例句释义: 遵守交通指示牌，服从(它的命令)是你必须做的。

英文释义: acceptable according to the law or a particular set of rules

例句释义: 我18岁了！这意味着我已经能进酒吧了！

英文释义: not important

例句释义: 在中国，鸡毛和蒜皮代表不重要的事情。

英文释义: to make a place more able to resist attack, especially by building high walls
例句: The emperor ordered the people to fortify the Great Wall.
例句释义: 皇帝命令人民加固长城。

英文释义: not having enough of something, especially something that is essential

例句释义: 我旧电脑的处理器太慢了。

例句释义: 赢得诺贝尔奖是他职业生涯的最高潮。

详细释义: n. 灰熊；  adj. 灰色的

例句释义: 在维多利亚时代，人们的穿着和现在相比很不相同。

英文释义: a type of beer, usually sold in bottles or cans. There are several kinds of ale.
