例句释义: 我朋友和我都喜欢喝麦芽啤酒。

英文释义: a type of mathematics in which letters and symbols are used to represent quantities
例句: Letters such as x and y are used to represent unknown quantities in algebra.
例句释义: 在代数中，x和y等字母用来表示未知量。

详细释义: n. 唯物主义，物质主义
英文释义: the belief that money, possessions and physical comforts are more important than spiritual values; the belief that only material things exist
例句: Even though I don't believe in materialism, I'd still prefer a suit to this barrel!
例句释义: 虽然我不是一个物质主义者，但是比起这木桶，我还是更想要西装。

英文释义: set anew
例句: He reset his computer after it crashed.
例句释义: 电脑死机后，他重启了电脑。

例句: What an adorable kitten!
例句释义: 多可爱的一只小猫啊！

英文释义: in a habitual and long-standing manner
例句: The rabbit is chronically ill and is constantly in and out of hospital.
例句释义: 这个小兔子患有慢性病，经常进出医院。

例句: You can see from above how the river meanders.
例句释义: 你可以从高处看到这条河流的蜿蜒曲折。

英文释义: a light, soft material that is the thick bark of a type of Mediterranean oak tree; a small round object made of cork or plastic, that is used for closing bottles, especially wine bottles
例句: I popped the cork off the bottle.
例句释义: 我把软木塞从瓶口拔了下来。

英文释义: a pot that is used for making and serving tea and that has a spout and handle
例句: Don't touch the teapot―it's very hot.
例句释义: 不要碰那个茶壶，它非常烫。

详细释义: adj.狡猾的，精巧的；  n.狡猾，精巧
英文释义: clever and skilful; (disapproving) able to get what you want in a clever way, especially by tricking or cheating somebody
例句: The cunning mouse eventually got that cheese.
例句释义: 狡猾的老鼠最终得到了那块奶酪。

英文释义: causing unhappiness or sad feelings :not warm, cheerful, etc.
例句: It is very dreary to do the same job every day.
例句释义: 每天都做同样工作是很乏味的。

英文释义: used to talk about a man in a friendly way
例句: The smiling chap is very handsome.
例句释义: 这个微笑的小伙子非常帅。

详细释义: v. 解释，释义；  n. 转述，释义
英文释义: to express what somebody has said or written using different words, especially in order to make it easier to understand
例句: To paraphrase the famous saying, success comes from failure.
例句释义: 这句名言的意思是说，成功源于失败。

详细释义: n. 合计；总数；  v. 集合；  adj. 总的，总数的
英文释义: a total number or amount made up of smaller amounts that are collected together
例句: The player earned an aggregate of $48,000,000 from sponsorship deals.
例句释义: 这个运动员从赞助中获得的总收入有4800万美元。

英文释义: a piece of equipment that changes electrical signals into sound, used in public places for announcing things, playing music, etc.
例句: He talked to the boy with a loudspeaker.
例句释义: 他拿着喇叭对男孩儿说话。

英文释义: good for your health
例句: The food was filling and wholesome.
例句释义: 这些食物可以充饥，也很健康。

英文释义: a person who draws cartoons
例句: He is one of the most popular cartoonists in the world right now.
例句释义: 他现在是全世界最受欢迎的漫画家之一。

详细释义: v.（尤指因宗教或政治信仰不同）迫害
英文释义: to treat somebody in a cruel and unfair way, especially because of their race, religion or political beliefs
例句: Jewish people were persecuted during the Second World War.
例句释义: 犹太人在二战中遭到了迫害。

英文释义: using more of something than is necessary; not saving or keeping something that could be used
例句: There was a wasteful amount of food from the dinner party.
例句释义: 宴会上剩下的食物太多，这样很浪费。

英文释义: worry and anxiety that you show by behaving in a nervous way
例句: Apparently she is in a state of agitation.
例句释义: 显然她此刻身处忧虑之中。

英文释义: the crime of doing something that could cause danger to your country, such as helping its enemies during a war
例句: You know selling those secrets to a foreign country is treason, don't you?
例句释义: 你难道不知道把这些机密卖给别的国家是叛国罪吗？

详细释义: n. 年金，养老金；年金享受权
英文释义: an insurance policy or an investment that pays someone a fixed amount of money each year
例句: The old couple are drawing their monthly annuity from the bank.
例句释义: 那对老夫妇正从银行领取他们每月的养老金。

英文释义: to make (someone or something) completely wet
例句: The boy is drenched after playing in the water.
例句释义: 这个男孩玩水后浑身湿透了。

英文释义: too many to be counted; very many
例句: There are innumerable stars in the night sky.
例句释义: 夜空中有数不清的星星。

英文释义: an adherent of fascism or other right-wing authoritarian views
例句: Fascist ideologies have poisoned many people's minds.
例句释义: 法西斯主义毒害了很多人的思想。

英文释义: difficult or impossible to reach or to get
例句: This remote area is inaccessible to all but the most adventurous.
例句释义: 只有最勇敢的人才能接近这片边远地带。

英文释义: the state of being known for some unfavorable act or quality
例句: His treason gained him notoriety which has lasted even to this day.
例句释义: 他因叛国而至今声名狼藉。

详细释义: adj. 团结的；紧密结合的
英文释义: forming a united whole
例句: We must work as a cohesive group and support each other.
例句释义: 我们必须组成一个团结的小队并互相支持。

详细释义: v. 过高估计；过高评价；  n. 过高的估计；过高的评价
英文释义: to estimate something to be larger, better, more important, etc. than it really is
例句: I think that the baby overestimates his appetite.
例句释义: 我觉得这个宝宝高估了自己的食量。

英文释义: a form of air pollution that is or looks like a mixture of smoke and fog, especially in cities
例句: There is too much smog in this big city.
例句释义: 这个大城市里烟雾弥漫。

英文释义: not needed or useful
例句: The old steam train is redundant and has been replaced with newer trains.
例句释义: 旧的蒸汽火车被新式火车所取代，显得过时多余了。

例句: The inertia caused by the driver hitting the brakes made them all lean forward.
例句释义: 司机刹车造成的惯性让大家都往前扑。

英文释义: a well-known phrase or sentence that gives advice or says something that is generally true, for example ‘Waste not, want not.’
例句: The dog chasing the mouse reminded the old man of a Chinese proverb.
例句释义: 狗追老鼠的场景使这位老人想起了一句中国谚语。

英文释义: temporary accommodation
例句: You can find all kinds of lodgings available on this website.
例句释义: 你可以在这个网站上找到各种各样的出租房间。

英文释义: to use (something) again
例句: He reused the newspaper he had read to wrap the book.
例句释义: 他将读过的报纸作为书皮再次使用。

详细释义: v. 约会，幽会，（秘密）集会；  n. 集会，幽会，约会地点
英文释义: a meeting with someone that is arranged for a particular time and place and that is often secret
例句: Romeo and Juliet often had secret rendezvous at night.
例句释义: 罗密欧与朱丽叶常常在晚上幽会。

英文释义: a book giving instructions on how to use something or information about a particular subject
例句: Read the instructions in the handbook carefully before you use the machine.
例句释义: 使用机器前请仔细阅读手册上的指示。

英文释义: an act or the process of calculating something
例句: He's using a computer to help with the computation of some complicated figures.
例句释义: 他正在用电脑辅助计算一些复杂的数据。

详细释义: adj. 松懈的；[语]松弛元音的；  n. 松元音
英文释义: not strict, severe or careful enough about work, rules or standards of behaviour
例句: The security guard's lax attitude towards his work endangers us all.
例句释义: 保安对工作松懈的态度使我们所有人都处于危险之中。

英文释义: a person whose job is carrying people’s bags and other loads, especially at a train station, an airport or in a hotel
例句: The porter carries customers' suitcases.
例句释义: 行李员帮客人们搬行李箱。

详细释义: v. 苦干；费力地做；  n. 辛苦
英文释义: to work very hard for a long time
例句: Workers toiled at the construction site.
例句释义: 工人们在工地上辛苦工作。

英文释义: to treat somebody in a cruel and unfair way, especially by not giving them the same freedom, rights, etc. as other people
例句: The poor employees are oppressed by their cruel boss.
例句释义: 这些可怜的员工受到了他们冷酷的老板的压迫。

英文释义: to cover (something) with a flood of water
例句: The city was inundated by heavy rainfall, and was close to flooding.
例句释义: 这座城市被强降雨淹没，都快洪水泛滥了。

详细释义: v. 重新出现；重新提起
英文释义: to happen again or a number of times
例句: The shining smile recurred on her face when she was fully recovered.
例句释义: 当她完全康复时，她的脸上又出现了灿烂的笑容。

详细释义: n. 晶体管；半导体收音机
英文释义: a small electronic device used in computers, radios, televisions, etc. for controlling an electric current as it passes along a circuit
例句: Transistors are small but necessary to make computers.
例句释义: 晶体管虽小，可对于制造电脑是必要的。

英文释义: a magazine that is published every week, month, etc., especially one that is concerned with an academic subject
例句: She liked to read this periodical which is published every month.
例句释义: 她喜欢这本每月发行一次的杂志。

英文释义: too many to count or too much to measure
例句: There are an untold number of stars in the universe.
例句释义: 宇宙中有数不清的星星。

英文释义: to not allow yourself to do or express (something)
例句: He repressed the urge to shout at his cousin who broke his model.
例句释义: 他抑制住了冲动，没对弄坏他模型的表弟大吼大叫。

英文释义: quiet and peaceful
例句: The tranquil setting was perfect for practicing my yoga.
例句释义: 宁静的环境非常适合练瑜伽。

英文释义: having a strong taste or smell
例句: The onions are very pungent! I'll have to shut my nose.
例句释义: 洋葱很刺鼻，我得捂住鼻子。

详细释义: adj. 讽刺的，挖苦的，冷嘲热讽的
英文释义: showing or expressing sarcasm
例句: It was obvious that she was being sarcastic when she praised me.
例句释义: 她表扬我时显然是在挖苦我。

英文释义: thick and deep mud
例句: Our trucks got stuck in the muddy mire.
例句释义: 我们的卡车陷进泥沼中了。

英文释义: a room or hall with equipment for doing physical exercise, for example in a school
例句: The most popular facility in that gymnasium is the treadmill.
例句释义: 跑步机是那家健身房里最受欢迎的器材。

英文释义: a view of a wide area of land; a description, study or set of pictures that presents all the different aspects or stages of a particular subject, event, etc.
例句: This panorama shows the entire downtown skyline.
例句释义: 这张全景显示了整个城市的天际线。

英文释义: that you can rely on to be good, honest, sincere, etc.
例句: The positive comments prove that the online shop is trustworthy.
例句释义: 好评证明这家网店值得信赖。

详细释义: adj.抒情诗调的；感情丰富的
英文释义: having an artistically beautiful or expressive quality
例句: He waxed lyrical about the beauty of the moon.
例句释义: 他满怀深情地称颂明月之美。

英文释义: a creature with a shell, that lives in water, especially one of the types that can be eaten. Oysters and crabs are both shellfish.
例句: The seafood shellfish soup looks pretty nutritious.
例句释义: 这碗海鲜贝壳汤看上去很有营养。

英文释义: the act of building or putting up
例句: The erection of the new hospital took three months.
例句释义: 这所新医院的建造花了三个月的时间。

英文释义: the act of avoiding sb or of avoiding sth that you are supposed to do.
例句: Debt evasion is the intentional act of avoiding paying back the money you owe.
例句释义: 逃债是指故意逃避偿还欠款的行为。

详细释义: n. 喧闹声，嘈杂声；  v. 喧闹，喋喋不休地说
英文释义: a loud, confusing mixture of noises that lasts for a long time
例句: She found it difficult to study with the constant din of her family downstairs.
例句释义: 家人在楼下发出持续的喧闹声使她很难学习下去。

英文释义: expressing admiration, praise, etc.
例句: He's always using complimentary words to suck up to his boss.
例句释义: 他经常说恭维话来拍老板马屁。

英文释义: having or showing hatred and a desire to harm somebody or hurt their feelings; (of software or computer code) intended to damage somebody's computer or data files
例句: He took malicious pleasure in watching the dog being tortured.
例句释义: 他怀着恶意的愉悦看着那只狗被折磨。

详细释义: n. 快递员，通讯员，导游
英文释义: a person whose job is to carry messages, packages, etc., from one person or place to another
例句: The job of a courier is to deliver the parcels.
例句释义: 快递员的工作是投递包裹。

英文释义: an occurrence in which a group of people at a play, speech, sporting event, etc., show enthusiastic approval or appreciation by clapping their hands together over and over
例句: The staff stand in a line and give the customers a warm ovation.
例句释义: 员工们站成一排热烈欢迎他们的顾客。

详细释义: n. 遗迹，（生）退化的器官，残余，微量（一般用于否定句）
英文释义: a small part of something that still exists after the rest of it has stopped existing; usually used in negative sentences, to say that not even a small amount of something exists
例句: The frescos on the wall are a last vestige of an ancient culture.
例句释义: 这幅壁画是古老文化的最后遗迹。

详细释义: v. 使惊骇，使胆寒，吓坏；惊诧，惊讶；胆战心惊；大吃一惊
例句: The woman was appalled by the state of her son's bedroom.
例句释义: 这位女士被她儿子房间的脏乱程度吓到了。

详细释义: adj. 已不通用的；陈旧的，过时的，老式的
英文释义: old and no longer used
例句: Radios are becoming archaic today.
例句释义: 收音机现在已经很少有人用了。

英文释义: to consider or examine somebody/something and form an opinion about them or it
例句: The manager has appraised the two employees.
例句释义: 经理对这两个员工做出了评价。

英文释义: the quality of being able to speak or write a language, especially a foreign language, easily and well
例句: Compared to his friend, he could speak Chinese with great fluency.
例句释义: 跟他的朋友相比，他汉语说得非常流利。

英文释义: to show that (someone) should not be blamed for a crime, mistake, etc. :to show that (someone) is not guilty
例句: Snowfall in June vindicated this innocent woman.
例句释义: 六月飞雪证明了窦娥的无辜。

详细释义: adj. 不切实际的，不能实现的
英文释义: not sensible or realistic
例句: Stupid people often perform impractical acts.
例句释义: 愚蠢的人经常表现出不切实际的行为。

英文释义: a situation in which people shout and make a lot of noise because they are angry or upset about something
例句: The news caused an uproar in the class.
例句释义: 这个消息在班上引起了骚动。

详细释义: adj.愉快的，欢乐的；  adv.很，非常
英文释义: happy and cheerful
例句: Santa looks as jolly as ever! He must be happy with those cookies!
例句释义: 圣诞老人看起来一如既往地欢乐！他一定很喜欢那些饼干！

英文释义: the sister of your husband or wife; your brother’s or sister's wife; the wife of your husband or wife’s brother
例句: Damao's and Sanmao's wives are my sisters-in-law.
例句释义: 大毛和三毛的老婆是我的嫂子和弟妹。

英文释义: the state of being somewhat like something but not truly or fully the same thing
例句: You're a mere semblance of the real Superman!
例句释义: 你只是伪装成了超人！

详细释义: n.愚蠢之举；大错；  v.犯大错；绊倒；失策
英文释义: a stupid or careless mistake
例句: He forgot to bring his parachute! What a terrible blunder that is!
例句释义: 他居然忘了背降落伞，真是犯了个愚蠢的错误！

英文释义: the place where two or more roads or railway/railroad lines meet
例句: Turn left at the junction of the two highways.
例句释义: 在这两条公路的交叉路口左拐。

详细释义: adj. 多刺的；令人苦恼的
英文释义: having a lot of thorns
例句: The rose's beauty is protected by its thorny stem.
例句释义: 玫瑰多刺的茎保护着它的美丽。

英文释义: something that is kept as a reminder of a person, place, or thing
例句: I bought a small Eiffel tower as a memento of my trip.
例句释义: 我买了一个小的艾菲尔铁塔当旅行纪念品。

英文释义: with respect to its inherent nature
例句: Although he can be naughty, the monkey is intrinsically kind and good-hearted.
例句释义: 尽管猴子很顽皮，但他本质上是善良的。

英文释义: to give time, money, tasks, etc. to somebody/something as a share of what is available
例句: The students were allotted different tasks to clean up the classroom.
例句释义: 学生们被分配了不同的打扫教室的工作。

英文释义: a type of plant that grows in the sea
例句: Seaweed grows in deep areas of the ocean.
例句释义: 这种海藻生长在深海中。

英文释义: existing at or from the beginning of the world
例句: These primordial tools were used by people in the distant past.
例句释义: 很久以前，人们靠这些原始工具来生存。

英文释义: an amount of food or drink that you put in your mouth at one time
例句: Eat up one more big mouthful, then you can have dessert!
例句释义: 再吃一大口，你就能吃甜食了！

详细释义: adj. 多相的，异种的，不均匀的，由不同成分形成的
英文释义: consisting of many different kinds of people or things
例句: Although we live in a heterogeneous family, we all tend to keep our own characteristics.
例句释义: 虽然不同种类的我们在一起生活，我们都保留了各自的特色。

详细释义: v. 使标准化；使合乎标准；立下标准；制定标准
英文释义: to make objects or activities of the same type have the same features or qualities; to make something standard
例句: The factory standardized the shape of the products on the conveyor belt.
例句释义: 工厂对传送带上的产品的形状进行标准化加工。

英文释义: a radio or television program that reports the news
例句: If a mouse made a newscast, it would most likely be about cats or cheese.
例句释义: 如果是一个老鼠来做新闻广播的话，那个广播很有可能是关于猫或者奶酪的。

英文释义: a usually small amount or degree by which something is made larger or greater
例句: Increments in economy reduce the unemployment rate.
例句释义: 经济的增长降低了失业率。

英文释义: a person whose job is to connect, repair, etc. electrical equipment
例句: The professional electrician will check the wiring in the electrical box.
例句释义: 这位专业电工将会检查电气箱内的线路。

英文释义: the father of your husband or wife
例句: It was the first time that the man meet his father-in-law.
例句释义: 这是这个男人第一次和他的岳父会面。

英文释义: a device that is used to spray water on plants or soil
例句: The sprinkler waters the grass several times a day.
例句释义: 洒水装置一天给草坪浇好几次水。

英文释义: (of metal, rock, or glass) heated to a very high temperature so that it becomes liquid
例句: The molten iron is poured into molds to cool.
例句释义: 我们把铁水倒进模具里冷却。

详细释义: adj.即席的，即兴的；  adv.即席，即兴；  n.即兴之作
英文释义: done without preparation or planning
例句: He composed an impromptu poem within seven paces.
例句释义: 他在七步之内即兴作了首诗。

详细释义: v. 在（某处）开拓殖民地；（为政治目的）打入，混入（某部门等）
英文释义: to take control of an area or a country that is not your own, especially using force, and send people from your own country to live there
例句: Europeans colonized Africa during the 17th century.
例句释义: 17世纪欧洲人将非洲变为殖民地。

英文释义: without any doubt
例句: All three judges give me a pass unquestionably.
例句释义: 毫无疑问，三位评委都让我通过。

详细释义: n. 庆祝，礼仪，仪式；（法律习俗等的）遵守
英文释义: the practice of obeying a law, celebrating a festival or behaving according to a particular custom
例句: In observance of Christmas, we put up a tree and give each other gifts.
例句释义: 庆祝圣诞节时，我们会放置一棵圣诞树，还会给彼此赠送礼物。

英文释义: to form an opinion about something based on the information or evidence that is available
例句: The detective deduced that the criminal is blonde and without one finger.
例句释义: 侦探推断这个罪犯是金发，而且少一根手指。

详细释义: n. 扎，一刺，刺痛，锥，阴茎；  v. 刺，戳，刺痛，竖起
英文释义: a penis; an offensive word for a stupid or unpleasant man; an act of making a very small hole in something with a sharp point; a slight pain caused by a sharp point or something that feels like a sharp point
例句: A prick from one of these thorns will draw blood.
例句释义: 在这上面随便一刺都会扎出血。

英文释义: the giving or taking of bribes
例句: The squirrel had immersed himself in bribery for a long time.
例句释义: 这只松鼠长期陷于受贿之中。

详细释义: v. 征收（税等）；  n. 征税；税款
英文释义: to use official authority to demand and collect a payment, tax, etc.
例句: The government levies a tax on him for his personal income.
例句释义: 政府向他征收了个人所得税。

详细释义: v. 纵容，过分关怀，精心照料
英文释义: to treat (someone or something) very well :to give (someone or something) a lot of attention and care
例句: It's very common to see the grandparents pamper their grandson.
例句释义: 爷爷奶奶纵容自己的孙子，这种现象很常见。

详细释义: vt. （努力）取得；  vi. 介绍娼妓
英文释义: to get (something) by some action or effort
例句: I finally procured a signed photo of my idol!
例句释义: 我终于得到偶像的签名照啦！

英文释义: the cost of sending a letter, etc. by post
例句: The postage depends on the weight of your goods.
例句释义: 邮费由你的物品重量决定。

详细释义: v. 使平静，使安静，哄骗；  n. 间歇，暂停，暂时平静
英文释义: to make somebody relaxed and calm; to make something, or to become, less strong
例句: Mom sang a song to lull the baby to sleep.
例句释义: 妈妈唱了首歌，让孩子进入梦乡。

英文释义: a large board with a smooth black or dark green surface that teachers write on with a piece of chalk
例句: She is the student on duty today, so she needs to clean the blackboard.
例句释义: 她是今天的值日生，所以她要擦黑板。

英文释义: a metal container with small holes in it, that is placed over a pan of boiling water in order to cook food in the steam
例句: These yummy baozi are cooking in the steamer. "Eat me!" they say.
例句释义: 美味的包子在蒸笼里蒸着。“吃我吧！”它们说。

英文释义: an introduction to a book, especially one that explains the author’s aims
例句: The book's preface is a good introduction to the main text.
例句释义: 书的前言是对主要内容的一个很好的介绍。

例句: He has a habit of making impulsive purchases.
例句释义: 他有冲动消费的习惯。

详细释义: adj.矮胖的；勇敢的；激烈的；  n.矮胖子；烈性啤酒
英文释义: (of a person) rather fat
例句: The boy is quite stout for his age.
例句释义: 对于这个年龄的人来说，这个男孩太过肥胖了。

英文释义: a device for cooling the engine of a vehicle or an aircraft
例句: My car broke down because my radiator ran out of fluid.
例句释义: 我的车抛锚了，因为散热器的水烧干了。

详细释义: n. 匆忙；草率；  v. 赶快
英文释义: speed in doing something, especially because you do not have enough time
例句: They have to make haste to catch the flight.
例句释义: 他们必须赶快才能坐上飞机。

英文释义: a place where ships are built or repaired
例句: A new ship was built at the shipyard.
例句释义: 那个造船厂造了一艘新船。

英文释义: a feeling of doubt about something :a feeling that something might not be right or might not work as planned
例句: Many employees expressed misgivings about the method of assessment.
例句释义: 许多员工对考核方式很是担忧。

详细释义: n. 走私；  v. 走私
英文释义: secretly importing prohibited goods or goods on which duty is due
例句: Cell phone smuggling is against the law.
例句释义: 走私手机是犯法的。

英文释义: a garden tool with a broad metal blade and a long handle, used for digging
例句: A farmer uses a spade to remove soil easily.
例句释义: 农夫用铁锹就能轻松地把土铲起来。

英文释义: a political theory advocating an authoritarian hierarchical government (as opposed to democracy or liberalism)
例句: Many people believe that fascism caused World War II.
例句释义: 很多人认为法西斯主义导致了第二次世界大战。

英文释义: a person who enjoys exciting new experiences, especially going to unusual places
例句: A true adventurer goes traveling without making any plans.
例句释义: 他是一个冒险家，经常开始一段说走就走的旅行。

详细释义: n. 招摇，飘扬，藐视；  vi. 炫耀，飘扬；  vt. 炫耀
英文释义: to show (something) in a very open way so that other people will notice
例句: Look! This peacock is flaunting his beautiful feathers again!
例句释义: 快看！这只孔雀又在炫耀他的羽毛！

英文释义: a reptile with a hard round shell, that lives on land and moves very slowly
例句: Look, the little tortoise is eating leaves.
例句释义: 看，小乌龟在吃树叶。

详细释义: n. 主动表示，姿态，前奏曲，序言，事件的开端，提出问题；  vt. 作为一种主动姿态提出，向…提出建议
英文释义: a piece of music played at the start of an opera, a musical play, etc.
例句: The curtain was opened as the orchestra played the overture.
例句释义: 随着乐队演奏的前奏曲，帷幕被拉开。

英文释义: the state or quality of being recognized or acknowledged; a statement acknowledging something or someone
例句: The little boy gave his tutor a nod of acknowledgement.
例句释义: 小男孩向家教老师点头表示听明白了。

英文释义: to cause problems or difficulties for (someone or something)
例句: Various skin problems have beset her.
例句释义: 多种肌肤问题困扰着她。

详细释义: adj. 按照时间顺序排列的
英文释义: (of a number of events) arranged in the order in which they happened
例句: The list of these books is in chronological order.
例句释义: 这列书是按照时间先后顺序来排列的。

英文释义: water mixed with waste matter
例句: Wastewater is being dumped into the river.
例句释义: 废水正被排到河里。

详细释义: n. 前部，船头；  adj. 在前部的，以前的；  adv. 在前面，在船头；  prep. 在前
英文释义: in or into a place of importance
例句: Their manager stood at the fore while the team stood closely behind.
例句释义: 经理站在最前面，其余员工紧接在身后。

英文释义: (of an action) done, often in a way that is annoying or difficult to stop
例句: He is a habitual early riser who always gets up at 6 o'clock.
例句释义: 他习惯在清晨六点早起。

详细释义: adj. 不便的，打扰的；打扰的
英文释义: causing trouble or problems, especially concerning what you need or would like yourself
例句: The man received a call at an inconvenient time.
例句释义: 这电话来得不是时候。

英文释义: a very heavy fall of snow, usually with a strong wind
例句: He is walking alone in the snowstorm.
例句释义: 他在暴风雪中独自行走。

英文释义: a way of using words that are the opposite of what you mean in order to be unpleasant to somebody or to make fun of them
例句: I like her talk show; her sarcasm is funny and lightens our mood.
例句释义: 我喜欢她的脱口秀，她的反讽风趣幽默，让我们心情大好。

详细释义: vt. 使起波浪；弄皱；  n. 皱纹
英文释义: to move or lift (something) so that it is no longer smooth
例句: A gust of wind ruffled the flowers in the field.
例句释义: 一阵微风拂过，使花儿如波浪般起伏。

英文释义: the period of time in a day during which you work at a job
例句: There are usually five workdays in a week.
例句释义: 通常一周有五个工作日。

详细释义: adj.不适宜的，不合适的；不宜做……的，无法胜任的；不健康的；  v.不适合
英文释义: not of an acceptable standard; not suitable
例句: These shoes are unfit for me. They're too small!
例句释义: 这双鞋不适合我，它们太小了!

详细释义: n. （地壳，冰上的）裂口，深坑，峡谷
英文释义: a deep hole or opening in the surface of the earth
例句: The wolf looked curiously down the chasm.
例句释义: 狼好奇地望着裂口下面。

英文释义: to make something pure by removing substances that are dirty, harmful or not wanted
例句: The water has been purified before being drunk.
例句释义: 水在被饮用之前经过了净化。

英文释义: a false reason that you give for doing something, usually something bad, in order to hide the real reason; an excuse
例句: The pupil asked for leave on the pretext of having a stomachache.
例句释义: 这个小学生以肚子疼为借口请假。

英文释义: a type of fuel oil that is made from petroleum and that is used in the engines of planes and for heat and light. In British English it is usually called paraffin when it is used for heat and light.
例句: If you have no electricity, you can light your house with a kerosene lamp.
例句释义: 在没有电的时候，你可以点煤油灯照明。

英文释义: (used of opinions and actions) far beyond the norm
例句: The goat is an ultra who takes extreme, aggressive measures to fight for his cause.
例句释义: 山羊是个过激分子，他会为了自己的目标采取极端的、攻击性的手段。

英文释义: uselessness as a consequence of having no practical result
例句: The futility of her trying to move this large rock is saddening.
例句释义: 她企图推动这块大石头的无用功让人感到可悲。

英文释义: a substance that is found in certain foods (such as bread, rice, and potatoes)
例句: Corn starch is used as a thickener in stews.
例句释义: 玉米淀粉在烹饪中被用作增稠剂。

详细释义: n. （足球的）前锋；罢工者；锤，报点时钟
英文释义: a worker who has stopped working because of a disagreement over pay or conditions
例句: Players 7, 9, and 10 are strikers in this soccer team.
例句释义: 7、9和10号球员是这个足球队的前锋。

详细释义: adj. 令人迷惑的；  n. 解纵横题字谜的技巧
英文释义: making somebody feel confused because they do not understand something
例句: The end of the movie was puzzling. I don't really understand it.
例句释义: 电影的结尾很令人疑惑。我没有真正理解它。

英文释义: a letter that represents a vowel sound. In English the vowels are a, e, i, o and u.
例句: English has five vowels - a, e, i, o, and u.
例句释义: 英语中有五个元音字母，它们是a、e、i、o、u。

英文释义: the state or process that happens when no more of something can be accepted or added because there is already too much of it or too many of them
例句: The car park has reached saturation, meaning there are no spaces left.
例句释义: 这家停车场已经达到饱和状态，意味着没有空余车位了。

详细释义: adj. 可怕的，令人生畏的；（表情）冷峻的
英文释义: seeming unfriendly and frightening
例句: The old house looks forbidding in the dead of the night.
例句释义: 在夜深人静的时候，这个老房子看上去令人生畏。

英文释义: the use of machines to do work that was previously done by people
例句: Automation has made many manual factory jobs redundant.
例句释义: 自动化使工厂里的许多人力劳动变得多余。

详细释义: n. 忧郁，悲哀；  adj. 忧郁的，令人伤感的
英文释义: a deep feeling of sadness that lasts for a long time and often cannot be explained
例句: Her eyes were full of melancholy as she gazed out the window.
例句释义: 当她凝视窗外时，眼里充满了惆怅。

英文释义: sympathy that you feel for somebody when a person in their family or that they know well has died; an expression of this sympathy
例句: People lit candles to show their condolence for the earthquake victims.
例句释义: 人们点燃蜡烛，来向地震中的受害者表示哀悼。

英文释义: a loose piece of clothing worn before and after taking a bath
例句: I wear a bathrobe and drink coffee after a bath.
例句释义: 洗完澡后，我穿着浴袍喝了点咖啡。

详细释义: adj. 可渗透的，多孔的，可穿越的
英文释义: having many small holes that allow water or air to pass through slowly
例句: Sponges are porous meaning they can absorb water.
例句释义: 海绵是多孔的，这意味着它们可以吸水。

英文释义: a feeling of hatred for somebody that causes a desire to harm them
例句: He punctured the bicycle tyres out of pure malice.
例句释义: 他扎自行车轮胎完全是出于恶意。

英文释义: a ceremony during which degrees or diplomas are given to students who have graduated from a school or college
例句: The dean congratulated each graduate at the commencement ceremony.
例句释义: 院长在毕业典礼上向每个毕业生都表示了祝贺。

详细释义: adj.人口稠密的，人口众多的
英文释义: where a large number of people live
例句: This city is so populous; there're so many people on the street.
例句释义: 这个城市人口众多，街上都是人。

英文释义: the quality that allows someone to continue trying to do something even though it is difficult
例句: Perseverance is an important trait to have when learning English.
例句释义: 在学习英语的过程中，坚持不懈是一项很重要的特质。

英文释义: the act of making illegal copies of DVDs, computer programs, books, etc., in order to sell them
例句: Film piracy is pretty common nowadays.
例句释义: 影视侵权在如今十分普遍。

英文释义: (formal) to praise and worship God
例句: He spread his arms and glorified his god.
例句释义: 他张开双臂，赞美他的神。

详细释义: n. 传单，散页的印刷品
英文释义: a printed sheet of paper or a few printed pages that are given free to advertise or give information about something
例句: She is reading the leaflet attentively.
例句释义: 她正认真地看传单。

详细释义: n. 雪球；  vi. 滚雪球般扩大；  vt. 向…掷雪球
例句: We can make a snowman out of these big snowballs.
例句释义: 我们可以用这些大雪球做一个雪人。

英文释义: a narrow opening or crack in a hard surface and especially in rock
例句: There is a deep crevice in the ground; make sure not to fall in.
例句释义: 地上有个很深的裂缝；不要掉进去了。

英文释义: the finger that is next to the thumb
例句: Raising his forefinger, he began to give instructions to the team.
例句释义: 伸出食指，他开始指导团队工作。

详细释义: n. 水湾，小湾；进口，入口
英文释义: a narrow strip of water that stretches into the land from the sea or a lake, or between islands
例句: This part of the country has many small rivers and inlets.
例句释义: 乡村的这一边有许多小河和小湾。

详细释义: adj. 心照不宣的，静默的
英文释义: expressed or understood without being directly stated
例句: They exchanged a tacit glance when passing each other.
例句释义: 擦肩而过时，他们交换了一个心照不宣的目光。

英文释义: willing to do something or allow something
例句: The customer was agreeable to my suggestions.
例句释义: 顾客欣然接受了我的建议。

英文释义: a meal that you eat in the late morning as a combination of breakfast and lunch
例句: I get up late so I usually eat brunch at 10:30 am.
例句释义: 我早上起得晚，所以经常在10点半吃早午餐。

英文释义: the act of officially ending or stopping something :the act of abolishing something
例句: The abolition of apartheid has been implemented in South Africa.
例句释义: 在南非，种族隔离制度已经被废除了。

英文释义: the rules of correct behaviour
例句: He has a high sense of propriety and believes in being a gentleman.
例句释义: 他非常注重礼节，坚信自己要当一个绅士。

英文释义: a large piece of equipment for cooking food, containing an oven and gas or electric rings on top
例句: A cooker is a large device that uses gas or electricity to cook food.
例句释义: 炉灶是一种用天然气或电烹饪食物的大型设备。

英文释义: a small, brownish spot on someone's skin
例句: She has many freckles on her face.
例句释义: 她脸上有好多雀斑。

英文释义: if a liquid condenses or you condense it, it becomes thicker and stronger because it has lost some of its water
例句: All of the bad news was condensed into a few words at the telegram office.
例句释义: 在电报局，所有的坏消息都被精简成了几个字。

详细释义: v.不断地唠叨，恼人；  n.老马，驽马，劣等竞赛马，（做坐骑的）矮小马
英文释义: to annoy (someone) by often complaining about his or her behavior, appearance, etc.
例句: The mother always nags her daughter.
例句释义: 这位母亲总是唠叨她的女儿。

英文释义: (of a body, a design, an object, etc.) having two halves, parts or sides that are the same in size and shape
例句: The photo of the two swans is completely symmetrical.
例句释义: 这张有两只天鹅的照片是完全对称的。

详细释义: n.小提琴演奏者，小提琴家
英文释义: a person who plays the violin
例句: The young violinist impressed us with his great talent.
例句释义: 这位年轻的小提琴家以其极高的天赋给我们留下了深刻的印象。

英文释义: addition of extra material or illustration or clarifying detail
例句: An elaboration is often found next to a piece of art to help explain it.
例句释义: 一件艺术品旁边通常有一份用来解释它的详细说明。

例句: A noun refers to a person, a place or a thing.
例句释义: 名词可以指一个人、一处地点或者一样东西。

英文释义: (especially in the names of places) a narrow passage of water that connects two seas or large areas of water
例句: It may take 2 hours to swim across the strait.
例句释义: 游过这湾海峡可能得花2小时。

英文释义: connected with or used for punishment, especially by law
例句: He will be sent to a penal institution as punishment.
例句释义: 他将会被送到刑罚机构以示惩罚。

英文释义: a person who stays in a hospital while receiving treatment
例句: You're very sick: we've reserved you a hospital bed as an inpatient.
例句释义: 你病得很严重：我们为你预留一张住院病人的床位。

详细释义: n. 引人注目的中心舞台照明，聚光灯，舞台上照明部分
例句: She enjoys the feeling of being in the limelight.
例句释义: 她享受在聚光灯下众所瞩目的感觉。

详细释义: vi. 安静下来；  vt. 使安静
英文释义: (used especially in orders) to be quiet; to stop talking or crying
例句: "Hush, please be quiet."
例句释义: “嘘，请安静一点。”

英文释义: the highest social class in some countries :the people who have special titles
例句: Throughout history, the majority of the aristocracy have tended to dress luxuriously.
例句释义: 纵观历史，大多数贵族通常都穿着奢华。

英文释义: to continue trying to do or achieve something despite difficulties
例句: Despite a number of setbacks, he persevered with his experiments.
例句释义: 虽屡遭挫败，他仍然坚持做实验。

英文释义: clean; not likely to cause health problems
例句: The kitchen is more sanitary than before it was cleaned.
例句释义: 厨房比打扫之前更卫生了一些。

英文释义: to be different from something; to do something in a different way from what is usual or expected
例句: The hiker has deviated from the main route; let's hope he can reach his destination.
例句释义: 这位旅行者已经偏离了主要路线，希望他能到达他的目的地吧。

详细释义: n. 玉米；  adj. 黄色的，玉米色的
英文释义: tall annual cereal grass bearing kernels on large ears: widely cultivated in America in many varieties; the principal cereal in Mexico and Central and South America since pre-Columbian times
例句: The maize from the field is ready to be harvested.
例句释义: 地里的玉米准备被收割。

英文释义: holding a position or title that was passed on from your parent or an older relative
例句: Their beautiful blonde hair is hereditary.
例句释义: 他们漂亮的金发是遗传的。

例句: They want to buy their car through a reputable dealer.
例句释义: 他们想通过一位声誉好的经销商购车。

英文释义: to decide not to do or have something, especially something you like or enjoy, because it is bad for your health or considered morally wrong
例句: He took the doctor's advice and decided to abstain from alcohol.
例句释义: 他听取了医生的建议，决定戒酒。

英文释义: to come and live permanently in a country after leaving your own country
例句: He is filling in the visa application form and plans to immigrate.
例句释义: 他正在填写签证申请表，准备移民。

英文释义: unpleasant in a way that makes people feel offended, annoyed, or disgusted
例句: I'll get that obnoxious mosquito before he gets me!
例句释义: 我将在那个令人讨厌的蚊子叮我前抓住它。

英文释义: the size and shape of a person's body
例句: The man in the gym has a very muscular physique.
例句释义: 健身房里的这个男人有着强壮的体格。

英文释义: a short sound, word or phrase spoken suddenly to express an emotion. Oh!, Look out! and Ow! are exclamations.
例句: The author used three exclamation marks to express his anger.
例句释义: 作者用了三个感叹号来表达他的愤怒。

英文释义: a poor condition of health caused by a lack of food or a lack of the right type of food
例句: She suffers from malnutrition as a result of excessive dieting.
例句释义: 她因为过度节食导致营养不良。

详细释义: v.粘上；署名；将罪责加之于；  n.词缀；附加物
英文释义: to stick or attach something to something else
例句: The girl affixed her new award to the wall.
例句释义: 小女孩把她的新奖状粘到了墙上。

详细释义: v.反驳；  n.反驳，反击，回嘴
英文释义: to reply quickly to a comment, in an angry, offended or humorous way
例句: "You’re stupid!" I said; "So are you!" he retorted.
例句释义: “你真傻！” 我说。“彼此彼此！”他反驳道。

英文释义: to separate and go in different directions; (of opinions, views, etc.) to be different
例句: The paths diverge here - which way shall I go?
例句释义: 道路从这里分叉，我该走哪一条呢？

英文释义: in very bad condition because of age or lack of care
例句: This house is dilapidated! I couldn't possibly live here.
例句释义: 这房子各种破旧衰败，我才不可能住在这里呢。

英文释义: that exists but that is difficult to describe, understand or measure; (business) that does not exist as a physical thing but is still valuable to a company
例句: Knowledge is an intangible asset.
例句释义: 知识是无形的资产。

详细释义: n. 驼峰；小园丘，峰丘；  v. （使）隆起，弓起
英文释义: a large lump on the back of some animals, especially camels
例句: The hump on a camel's back stores plenty of fat.
例句释义: 骆驼背上的驼峰储藏了很多脂肪。

英文释义: (taxes) an amount that can be deducted (especially for the purposes of calculating income tax)
例句: The money spent on children's education is income tax deductible.
例句释义: 用于子女教育的钱可从所得税中扣除。

英文释义: the process of destroying something slowly, especially by chemical action; the condition that results from this process
例句: The corrosion of this metal joint indicates its need for replacement.
例句释义: 这个金属接头的腐蚀情况表明它需要更换了。

详细释义: adj. 成直角的，垂直的；直立的；  n. 垂直线
英文释义: forming an angle of 90° with another line or surface; vertical and going straight up
例句: The two lines are perpendicular to one another.
例句释义: 这两条线互相垂直。

详细释义: v. 缩回；收回；  n. 收缩核
英文释义: to move back into the main part of something; to pull something back into the main part of something
例句: A tortoise will retract its head into its shell to protect itself.
例句释义: 乌龟会把头缩进壳里来保护自己。

英文释义: the system in your body which digests your food; the ability to digest food; the process of digesting food
例句: Human's digestion includes esophagus, stomach, intestines and so on.
例句释义: 人的消化系统包括食道、胃和肠等。

详细释义: adj. 不动的，惰性的；行动迟钝的
英文释义: (chemistry) without active chemical or other properties (= characteristics); (formal) without power to move or act
例句: These are the common inert gases.
例句释义: 这些是常见的惰性气体。

英文释义: a small brush for cleaning your teeth
例句: There are six different toothbrushes in the cup.
例句释义: 杯子里有六支不同的牙刷。

详细释义: adj. 强制性的；义务的；必须的
英文释义: that you must do because of the law, rules, etc.; that you do because you always do it, or other people in the same situation always do it
例句: You can't skip class, attendance at school is obligatory!
例句释义: 你不能逃课，上学是你的义务。

详细释义: n. 混杂；混乱；  v. 使混乱；搞乱
英文释义: an untidy or confused mixture of things
例句: The dishes were in a jumble in the kitchen.
例句释义: 厨房里的餐具乱七八糟的。

英文释义: in a way that shows care and effort in your work or duties
例句: The young ballet students diligently practice every day.
例句释义: 这些芭蕾女孩们总是勤奋地练习着。

英文释义: musical instruments that you play by hitting them with your hand or with a stick, for example drums
例句: These students are playing percussion instruments in music class.
例句释义: 这些学生在音乐课上演奏打击乐器。

详细释义: n. 破裂；  v. 断绝（关系）
英文释义: the ending of agreement or of good relations between people, countries, etc.
例句: The rupture of their relationship broke her heart.
例句释义: 他们关系破裂，这让她伤心欲绝。

英文释义: lacking skill or ability
例句: The inept househusband made a hole in the T-shirt with the iron.
例句释义: 这个笨手笨脚的家庭妇男把衣服熨了个洞。

英文释义: a small bag of tissue that is attached to the large intestine. In humans, the appendix has no clear function.
例句: She?has?an?acute?pain?in?her?appendix.
例句释义: 她的阑尾痛得厉害。

英文释义: a final warning to a person or country that if they do not do what you ask, you will use force or take action against them
例句: My teacher gave me an ultimatum: hand in your homework today, or get a zero.
例句释义: 老师给我下了最后通牒：要么今天交作业，要么得零分。

英文释义: an African animal that looks like a horse and has black and white stripes covering its body
例句: The zebras are running across the river.
例句释义: 这群斑马正在横渡河流。

详细释义: v.居支配地位；在……中占优势
英文释义: to be greater in number or amount than other types of people or things
例句: In?this?yoga?class,?senior?people predominate.
例句释义: 这堂瑜伽课上，老年人占大多数。

英文释义: not clearly defined; lasting for a period of time that has no fixed end
例句: Which door should he go through? The answer is indefinite.
例句释义: 他应该通过哪扇门？答案是不确定的。

英文释义: a popular type of cola drink
例句: There's nothing like a cold Coke on a hot summer's day.
例句释义: 在炎热的夏天，没什么比得上来一杯冰可乐。

英文释义: paper, plastic, etc. used for covering sth in order to protect it
例句: I bought some colorful wrapping paper to wrap up my Christmas presents.
例句释义: 我买了一些彩色包装纸来包装圣诞礼物。

详细释义: v.谴责；对……深感遗憾；悲悼；痛惜
英文释义: to strongly disapprove of something and criticize it, especially publicly
例句: The hospital deplores any act of violence towards its medical staff.
例句释义: 医院强烈谴责任何暴力伤医行为。

详细释义: adj. 备用的，辅助的，协助的
英文释义: (of workers) giving help or support to the main group of workers; (of a piece of equipment) used if there is a problem with the main piece of equipment
例句: We have an auxiliary generator to deal with sudden black-outs.
例句释义: 我们有一个备用的发电机防止突然停电。

英文释义: professing feelings or virtues one does not have
例句: It was hypocritical of the boy to throw the gift into the dustbin the instant the girl left.
例句释义: 女孩刚走，这个男孩就把礼物扔进了垃圾桶，这可真虚伪。

英文释义: a dark red precious stone
例句: My grandmother's antique necklace includes several rubies.
例句释义: 我奶奶的古董项链上有几颗红宝石。

详细释义: adj. 有条件的，假定的；  n. 条件句，条件语
英文释义: expressing something that must happen or be true if another thing is to happen or be true; depending on something
例句: Cats' love for humans seems to be conditional.
例句释义: 看来，猫对人类的爱是有条件的。

英文释义: caused by the thing that has just been mentioned
例句: His muscular body is resultant of his tough workout regime.
例句释义: 他的好身材是严格锻炼的结果。

例句: He always cycles home by nightfall.
例句释义: 他总是在傍晚骑自行车回家。

英文释义: having no worries or responsibilities
例句: Under so much pressure now, she really misses her carefree childhood.
例句释义: 如今压力山大，她十分想念从前无忧无虑的童年。

详细释义: adj. 洪亮的，共振的，共鸣的
英文释义: producing a loud, clear, deep sound
例句: His resonant laugh filled the room.
例句释义: 他洪亮的笑声响彻了整个房间。

英文释义: relating to beliefs about right and wrong
例句: It's wrong to accept bribes, both legally and ethically.
例句释义: 收受贿赂是不对的，不论从法律上还是道德上。

详细释义: adj. 疏忽的，粗心大意的
英文释义: (law or formal) failing to give somebody/something enough care or attention, especially when this has serious results
例句: The worker was negligent in smoking cigarette with barrels of oil around him.
例句释义: 这个工人很粗心，在周围都是油桶的情况下抽烟。

详细释义: n. 妒嫉；忿忿不平；  v. 不情愿做
英文释义: a strong feeling of anger toward someone that lasts for a long time
例句: The queen held a grudge against Snow White because of her beauty.
例句释义: 王后嫉妒白雪公主的美貌。

英文释义: a strong feeling of dislike or hatred :a desire to oppose something you dislike or disagree with
例句: There was a lot of antagonism between the competitors before the boxing match.
例句释义: 拳击比赛开始前，双方的敌对情绪已经很明显了。

详细释义: n. 被逐出者；  adj. 被抛弃的，被逐出的
英文释义: someone who is not accepted by other people
例句: The red man is an outcast; nobody wants to talk to him.
例句释义: 那个红色的人被排斥了，没有人想要和他说话。

英文释义: the process of getting sth back, especially from a place where it should not be
例句: Her smart dog played an important part in the retrieval of her necklace.
例句释义: 她家聪明的狗很大程度上帮助她取回了项链。

详细释义: adj. 男子气概的，强壮的，适于男人的
英文释义: having the qualities or physical features that are admired or expected in a man
例句: He was manly when he seized the girl's arm and pulled her up.
例句释义: 他抓住女孩的胳膊并把她拉上来的时候显得男子气概十足。

英文释义: a list of books or articles about a particular subject or by a particular author; the list of books, etc. that have been used by somebody writing an article, etc.
例句: The bibliography is located at the end of the paper.
例句释义: 参考书目放在论文的最后。

英文释义: basic and important
例句: These four math signs are elemental for students.
例句释义: 这四个数学符号对于学生来说是最基本的。

英文释义: a small mistake or amount of bad luck
例句: The boy suffered a series of mishaps on the way to school.
例句释义: 这个男孩在上学的路上遭遇了一系列不幸事故。

详细释义: n. 墨水渍；  v. （用吸水纸）吸干墨水
英文释义: a spot or stain
例句: Water color paintings consist of many blots of paint.
例句释义: 水彩画由很多细小的彩墨水渍组成。

详细释义: adj. 温顺的，逆来顺受的，谦恭的
英文释义: having or showing a quiet and gentle nature :not wanting to fight or argue with other people
例句: The sheep is very meek and won't hurt you.
例句释义: 绵羊很温顺，不会伤害人。

英文释义: in a courageous manner
例句: The goat stood bravely in front of its friend.
例句释义: 这只山羊勇敢地挡在自己朋友的面前。

详细释义: v. 烧焦；枯萎；  vi. 高速行驶，疾驰，飞驰
英文释义: to burn and slightly damage a surface by making it too hot; to be slightly burned by heat
例句: The leaves have been scorched by the sun's heat.
例句释义: 树叶被太阳晒焦了。

英文释义: a person or animal that is adopted by a team or other group as a symbolic figure
例句: This is the mascot of Nanjing Youth Olympic Games.
例句释义: 这是南京青奥会的吉祥物。

英文释义: something that is believed to be a sign or warning of something that will happen in the future
例句: She believes that finding a four-leaf clover is an omen of good luck.
例句释义: 她认为找到四叶草是好运的预兆。

英文释义: a member of an aristocracy
例句: She was born an aristocrat who lived a life of luxury.
例句释义: 她天生就是一位过着富贵生活的贵族。

英文释义: good or useful in a particular situation
例句: Being knowledgable is likely to put you in an advantageous position in life.
例句释义: 丰富的学识很可能使你在人生路上处于有利的位置。

英文释义: making something valid by formally ratifying or confirming it
例句: They have a four-fifths majority in favor of the ratification of the treaty.
例句释义: 他们中有五分之四的多数票赞成批准该条约。

英文释义: an emphatic statement, answer, etc. is given with force to show that it is important
例句: To make the sentence more emphatic, she repeated it three times.
例句释义: 为了加强这句话的语气，她说了三次。

英文释义: the political and economic theories of Karl Marx (1818C83) which explain the changes and developments in society as the result of opposition between the social classes
例句: Marxism and capitalism are very different economic ideas.
例句释义: 马克思主义和资本主义是两种非常不同的经济理论。

英文释义: a bottle with a narrow top, used in scientific work for mixing or storing chemicals
例句: You can pour the chemicals from these flasks.
例句释义: 你可以从长颈瓶里倒出化学药品。

英文释义: lasting or used for only a short period of time
例句: The beauty of the flower?is?ephemeral; it lasts only a few minutes.
例句释义: 这朵花的美丽极其短暂，它只盛开了几分钟而已。

详细释义: adj. 可怕的，令人不快的；  adv. 恐怖地
英文释义: someone or something that you find unpleasant and dislike very much
例句: A ghastly figure appeared in the attic window.
例句释义: 阁楼的窗户上出现了一个可怕的人影。

英文释义: not willing or not able to believe something; showing an inability to believe something
例句: "You made it by yourself?" The lady said to her son in an incredulous tone.
例句释义: “你自己做的?”那位女士用怀疑的语气对儿子说。

英文释义: lacking a crew
例句: The unmanned rocket was launched successfully.
例句释义: 这架无人驾驶的火箭成功发射了。

英文释义: a small brown and grey bird, common in many parts of the world
例句: Sparrows are small brown and grey birds, and are common in many parts of the world.
例句释义: 麻雀是一种棕灰色的小鸟，常见于世界上很多地方。

详细释义: adj. 狂热的；热烈的，满怀热情的
英文释义: felt very strongly
例句: They are fervent fans of the German football team.
例句释义: 他们是德国足球队的狂热支持者。

英文释义: a substance that you put on a brush and use to clean your teeth
例句: The toothpaste helps make our teeth clean and white.
例句释义: 牙膏可以使我们的牙齿干净亮白。

英文释义: showing care and effort in your work or duties
例句: Compared with her deskmate, she is a very diligent student.
例句释义: 与她的同桌相比，她是一名非常勤奋的学生。

英文释义: the food and drink that people, animals and plants need to live and stay healthy
例句: Picking up rubbish is a vital source of sustenance for those poor tramps.
例句释义: 对于这些贫穷的流浪汉来说，捡垃圾是他们重要的生计来源。

英文释义: under a legal obligation to someone
例句: The mother is deeply indebted to the police for finding her daughter.
例句释义: 这位母亲非常感激警察帮她找到女儿。

英文释义: very large or powerful and causing surprise or admiration
例句: The forest is full of prodigious trees.
例句释义: 这片森林长满了高大的树木。

英文释义: happening immediately
例句: When stabbing the balloon, there was an instantaneous burst.
例句释义: 如果用针扎这个气球，它会瞬间爆炸。

英文释义: to undo a knot in something; to undo something that is tied
例句: He tied a knot that is very difficult to untie.
例句释义: 他打了一个非常难解的结。

英文释义: an open container with a handle, used for carrying or holding liquids, sand, etc.
例句: Please pick up the pail of butter and bring it over here.
例句释义: 请把这桶黄油提过来。

详细释义: v. 紧接着而到来；代替
英文释义: to take the place of (someone or something that is old, no longer useful, etc.) :to replace (someone or something)
例句: Robots superseding humans at playing Weiqi has become a reality.
例句释义: 机器人替代真人下围棋已成为现实。

详细释义: adv. 向东；  adj. 向东的
英文释义: towards the east
例句: He followed the map eastward, towards the treasure.
例句释义: 他沿着地图向东行进，朝着宝藏而去。

英文释义: the quality that something has of being able to stretch and return to its original size and shape (= of being elastic )
例句: The rubber toy has a high level of elasticity and can be stretched.
例句释义: 这个橡胶玩具很有弹性，可以被拉扯。

英文释义: the stopping of something; a pause in something
例句: The judge whistled and gestured to show the cessation of the game.
例句释义: 教练吹响口哨，并用手势表示比赛终止。

英文释义: patterns that are sewn onto cloth using threads of various colours; cloth that is decorated in this way
例句: This embroidery flower pattern is so beautiful and delicate.
例句释义: 这幅花卉刺绣是如此美丽和精致。

英文释义: getting annoyed easily; showing your anger
例句: He had been seated waiting for some time and was becoming irritable.
例句释义: 他坐着等了一会儿，开始变得急躁了起来。

详细释义: n. 帝王，王权；最高权威；壮丽；雄伟
英文释义: the impressive and attractive quality that something has
例句: I'll always be loyal to you, your majesty.
例句释义: 我将永远忠于您，陛下。

详细释义: n. 疯子；  adj. 精神错乱的，极蠢的
英文释义: a person who does crazy things that are often dangerous; a person who is severely mentally ill (the use of this word is now offensive)
例句: At first I thought he just had poor fashion sense, but then I realized that he was a real lunatic.
例句释义: 起先我认为只是他的时尚品味差，然后我才意识到他就是个不折不扣的疯子。

英文释义: something that will cause damage or injury to something or someone
例句: Staying up very late is a detriment to one’s health.
例句释义: 熬夜有害身体健康。

详细释义: n.分配；份额；<英>划分的土地
英文释义: a small area of land in a town which a person can rent in order to grow fruit and vegetables on it; an amount of something that somebody is given or allowed to have; the process of giving something to somebody
例句: His father had left him an allotment of one million dollars.
例句释义: 他父亲分给了他一百万美元。

英文释义: the side or slope of a mountain
例句: The trees on the mountainside are green all year round.
例句释义: 山坡上的树一年四季都是绿色的。

英文释义: used as a toast to wish everyone happiness
例句: They said "cheers" and lifted up their glasses.
例句释义: 他们说“干杯”并举起了杯子。

详细释义: v. 隔离；使隔离；  n. 检疫期
英文释义: to keep (a person or animal) away from others to prevent a disease from spreading :to put or keep (a person or animal) in quarantine
例句: The zombies have been quarantined in order to keep people safe.
例句释义: 丧尸已经被隔离以确保人类的安全。

英文释义: an amount of liquid or gas escaping through a hole in something; an occasion when there is a leak
例句: The loose connection between the two pipes caused the water leakage.
例句释义: 两只水管间的连接松动导致了水泄漏。

英文释义: to cause (something) to get caught
例句: My hair has become entangled into a knot.
例句释义: 我的头发缠成了一个结。

英文释义: showing ignorance or the laws of nature and faith in magic or chance
例句: The superstitious man believes in fortune telling.
例句释义: 那个迷信的人很相信算命。

详细释义: v. 有利，有助于；  n. 益处
英文释义: use to one's advantage.
例句: He availed himself of the exercise equipment in the park to stay fit and healthy.
例句释义: 他利用公园里的健身器材来保持健康。

详细释义: n. 阐述；展览会，博览会
英文释义: a full explanation of a theory, plan, etc.
例句: The professor is giving a clear exposition of the theory.
例句释义: 教授正在透彻地阐述这个理论。

详细释义: v. 使超载，使过载；使负担（或负荷）过重；  n. 过重负担
英文释义: to put too great a load on something
例句: That bicycle is overloaded, and it's so dangerous.
例句释义: 这辆自行车超载了，这太危险了。

英文释义: at the correct or expected time
例句: The plane duly arrived at the time they said it would.
例句释义: 飞机准时如约到达。

详细释义: n. 房屋；住户；租户；住屋，住宅
英文释义: a large building divided into flats/apartments, especially in a poor area of a city
例句: We stayed in a tenement for one year before moving into our own house.
例句释义: 我们在搬进自己房子前租了一年的房子。

详细释义: n. 口吃；  v. 口吃，结巴着说出
英文释义: to speak with many pauses and repetitions because you have a speech problem or because you are very nervous, frightened, etc.
例句: My stammer embarrassed me when I was dating a girl.
例句释义: 我的口吃让我在与女孩约会的时候出丑了。

英文释义: to cause (someone) to be more likely to behave in a particular way or to be affected by a particular condition
例句: Childhood obesity can be ascribed to the genetic predisposition.
例句释义: 儿童肥胖症可以被归因于遗传体质。

详细释义: n. 先见，预见；远见，深谋远虑
英文释义: the ability to predict what is likely to happen and to use this to prepare for the future
例句: This guy's foresight enables him to build a business empire.
例句释义: 这个男人的先见之明使他得以建立一个商业帝国。

详细释义: v. 目瞪口呆地凝视，打哈欠，张开，裂开；  n. 裂口，张嘴，打哈欠
英文释义: to open widely
例句: The baby is gaping at me. What is he thinking about?
例句释义: 我的宝贝张着嘴盯着我看。他在想什么呢？

英文释义: the quality of being likely to succeed and reasonable to do or use
例句: She paid more attention to the practicality of shoes on a rainy day.
例句释义: 她更注重鞋子在下雨天的实用性。

详细释义: n. （文学）少女，未嫁女子；  adj. 未婚的，处女的，初次的
英文释义: a young girl or woman who is not married
例句: There is a beautiful maiden sitting in the castle garden.
例句释义: 有一位美丽的少女坐在城堡的花园里。

英文释义: containing salt
例句: Salt often washes up on the shore of saline lakes.
例句释义: 盐湖里的盐经常会被冲到岸边。

英文释义: to put right something that is wrong
例句: I made a mistake, so I quickly rectified it.
例句释义: 我犯了一个错误，所以我迅速纠正了它。

详细释义: v. 闪烁，微微发亮；  n. 微光，闪光
英文释义: to shine with a light that seems to move slightly
例句: The sea was shimmering in the sunlight.
例句释义: 海水在阳光下闪闪发光。

英文释义: a chemical used for killing insects
例句: Spraying of insecticide keeps disease away.
例句释义: 喷洒杀虫剂可以防止疾病。

详细释义: v. 啄；  n. 轻吻；  v. 轻吻
英文释义: (of birds) to move the beak forward quickly and hit or bite something
例句: The chicken is pecking the grains on the ground.
例句释义: 这只鸡在啄食地上的谷物。

详细释义: n. 铆钉；  v. （用铆钉）铆接，敲打（螺栓）使成铆钉头，吸引（注意力）
英文释义: a special kind of metal bolt or pin that is used to hold pieces of metal together
例句: The rivets prevent others from stepping on my feet.
例句释义: 这些铆钉可以有效地防止他人踩我的脚。

详细释义: n. 食品杂货店主，食品杂货店员
英文释义: a shop/store that sells these things
例句: I buy food every day from the grocer.
例句释义: 我每天都去杂货店员那儿购买食品。

英文释义: a thing, a place or a group that has all the features and qualities of something much larger
例句: The lollipop seems to be a microcosm of the universe.
例句释义: 棒棒糖似乎是宇宙的缩影。

英文释义: a quick way of writing using special signs or abbreviations, used especially to record what somebody is saying
例句: She is taking down the speech in shorthand.
例句释义: 她正在用速记记录演讲内容。

详细释义: adj. 热情友好的，衷心的
英文释义: (formal) pleasant and friendly
例句: Our boss is cordial and kind with us.
例句释义: 我们的老板对我们非常热情友好。

详细释义: n. 年长，资历深，职位高
英文释义: the fact of being older or of a higher rank than others; the rank that you have in a company because of the length of time you have worked there
例句: People usually bow to seniority to show their respect.
例句释义: 人们通常向长辈鞠躬表示尊敬。

英文释义: a long pole with a flat blade at one end that is used for rowing a boat
例句: They pulled on the oars to make the boat go faster.
例句释义: 他们（用力）划桨，加速前进。

详细释义: n. 茶点；（会议或旅行期间提供的）饮料，点心，茶点
英文释义: drinks and small amounts of food that are provided or sold to people in a public place or at a public event;  (formal) food and drink
例句: Feel free to enjoy the refreshments on the table that we prepared for you.
例句释义: 请尽情享用桌上我们为您准备的茶点。

英文释义: the layer of air near the earth is cooler than an overlying layer
例句: In inversion yoga poses, the heart is higher from the ground than the head.
例句释义: 在倒立瑜伽姿势中，心脏比头部离地面更高。

英文释义: without considering something or being influenced by it
例句: Bookstores should be open to everyone, irrespective of whether they are rich or poor.
例句释义: 书店应该对每个人开放，不管他们是富裕还是贫穷。

英文释义: relating to or based on instinct :based on feelings or desires that do not come from thinking or learning
例句: Due to his instinctive response, the man avoided the ball immediately.
例句释义: 出于本能反应，他迅速躲过了这个球。

详细释义: n. 兔子；野兔；  vi. 飞跑
英文释义: an animal like a large rabbit with very strong back legs, that can run very fast
例句: I told the children the story of the tortoise and the hare.
例句释义: 我给孩子们讲了龟兔赛跑的故事。

详细释义: adj. （不辞）劳苦的，辛勤的；  n. 辛劳，煞费苦心
英文释义: needing a lot of care, effort and attention to detail
例句: After years of painstaking research, he finally invented the electric bulb.
例句释义: 经过多年的辛勤试验，他终于发明了电灯泡。

英文释义: the very small drops of water that form on the ground, etc. during the night
例句: Dew forms on the grass every morning.
例句释义: 每天清晨，露水在草上凝结。

英文释义: satisfied with how things are and not wanting to change them
例句: The complacent driver is too confident and hasn't noticed the danger on the icy road.
例句释义: 这个自以为是的司机太自信了，并没意识到在结冰的路上驾驶的危险。

详细释义: adj. 神经质的；神经官能病的；  n. 神经病患者
英文释义: often or always fearful or worried about something :tending to worry in a way that is not healthy or reasonable
例句: He is a very neurotic person and he worries too much about his safety.
例句释义: 他过于神经质，老是担心自己的人身安全。

英文释义: (of a person) pleased to welcome guests; generous and friendly to visitors
例句: He was very hospitable to the guests when they came to his house.
例句释义: 有人来访时，他表现得十分好客。

详细释义: adj. 可恨的，令人讨厌的，极坏的；可憎的
英文释义: very unkind or unpleasant
例句: They don't like each other. I can tell from their hateful looks.
例句释义: 我可以从她们憎恶的表情中看出来她们不喜欢对方。

英文释义: doing what you are told to do; willing to obey
例句: The dog is obedient, and does whatever the boy wants.
例句释义: 这狗很听话，小男孩让它干嘛就干嘛。

英文释义: to stop doing something, or leave something, especially something that you enjoy
例句: In order to lose weight, the man had to forsake his old unhealthy lifestyle.
例句释义: 为了减肥，这个男人必须放弃之前不健康的生活方式。

详细释义: adj. 和声的；和谐的，融洽的；  n. 【物】谐波
英文释义: relating to the way notes are played or sung together to make a pleasing sound
例句: The harmonic sequences made by his fingers can create beautiful sounds.
例句释义: 这位玩家凭借一双巧手奏出了美妙的和声乐。

详细释义: n.一窝，同窝幼崽；  v.冥思苦想；默想
英文释义: all the young birds or creatures that a mother produces at one time; (humorous) a large family of children
例句: The brood of young birds are waiting for their mother to feed them.
例句释义: 这一窝小鸟嗷嗷待哺，等着它们的母亲。

英文释义: showing or resulting from lack of judgment or wisdom
例句: It would be unwise to buy a house without researching its surroundings.
例句释义: 在不了解房子周围环境的情况下买它是很不明智的。

英文释义: a friend with whom a child plays
例句: Having a playmate is better than playing alone.
例句释义: 有个玩伴比独自一人好玩得多。

详细释义: adj. 合法的，法律许可的
英文释义: allowed or recognized by law; legal
例句: After he obtained the license, he could participate in lawful hunting activities.
例句释义: 取得执照后，他可以参加合法的狩猎活动。

详细释义: v. 推测；揣摩；  n. 猜想
英文释义: an opinion or idea formed without proof or sufficient evidence
例句: I can't see you, but I'll conjecture that you're my girlfriend, Sally.
例句释义: 我看不见你，但是我猜你是我的女朋友，Sally。

详细释义: adj. 美味的，合口味的，合心意的
英文释义: having a pleasant or agreeable taste
例句: The girl found this dish to be palatable.
例句释义: 女孩觉得这道菜很美味。

英文释义: the fact of being enough in quantity, or good enough in quality, for a particular purpose or need
例句: The adequacy of food ensures the squirrel will survive the cold winter.
例句释义: 松鼠有足够多的食物来度过寒冷的冬天。

英文释义: good at finding ways of doing things and solving problems, etc.
例句: This resourceful ancient Chinese strategist reused the arrows of his enemies.
例句释义: 这位足智多谋的中国古代军事家“借”到了敌军的箭。

详细释义: n. 拥抱；  v. 紧贴着身子睡
英文释义: to hold (someone or something) in your arms in order to show affection
例句: This baby needs a cuddle.
例句释义: 宝宝需要抱抱。

英文释义: a feeling of being satisfied with how things are and not wanting to try to make them better :a complacent feeling or condition
例句: His complacency when cycling led him to fall off.
例句释义: 他骑车时的自大让他摔了个大跟头。

英文释义: the organ of sight
例句: Optic nerves transfer visual information from our eyes to our brain.
例句释义: 视神经将视觉信息从眼睛传输到大脑中。

英文释义: the act of putting something inside something else; a thing that is put inside something else; a thing that is added to a book, piece of writing, etc.; the act of adding something
例句: Insertion of a USB stick should be done carefully, so as not to damage your computer.
例句释义: 插入移动硬盘时要小心，以防损害你的电脑。

英文释义: the decision of a court or a judge; the ability to make sensible decisions after carefully considering the best thing to do; an opinion that you form about something after thinking about it carefully; the act of making this opinion known to others; something bad that happens to somebody that is thought to be a punishment from God
例句: The court's judgement is that he is innocent.
例句释义: 法院的判决认为他是无罪的。

英文释义: an extremely strong wind
例句: A sudden gale almost knocked me down.
例句释义: 一阵狂风差点把我吹倒。

详细释义: adj.发烧的；狂热的，极其兴奋的
英文释义: suffering from a fever; caused by a fever
例句: I touched his forehead; he felt hot and feverish.
例句释义: 我摸了摸他的前额，感到很烫，他应该发烧了。

详细释义: n. 被接见者，被访问者
英文释义: a person who is interviewed
例句: The interviewee is trying to land a job in that company.
例句释义: 被接见者试图在那家公司谋得一份工作。

英文释义: the quality of being worthy of desiring
例句: As the number of charge stations for electric cars increases, so does their desirability.
例句释义: 随着电动汽车充电站数量的增加，电动汽车也更受欢迎了。

详细释义: n. 手风琴；  adj. 可折叠的
英文释义: a musical instrument that you hold in both hands to produce sounds. You press the two ends together and pull them apart and press buttons and/or keys to produce the different notes.
例句: Bob has mastered the accordion after 10 years of playing.
例句释义: 鲍勃弹了10年的手风琴，现在已经精通了。

英文释义: the ability to see
例句: Your eyesight is terrible! You need glasses.
例句释义: 你视力太差了！你需要配眼镜。

详细释义: adj. 坚忍不拔的，固执的，顽强的
英文释义: that does not stop holding something or give up something easily; determined; continuing to exist, have influence, etc. for longer than you might expect
例句: The boxer was very tenacious, and would not give up.
例句释义: 这个拳击手很顽强，不会认输。

详细释义: n. 监护人，保管人，看守人
英文释义: a person who cleans and takes care of a building
例句: He is happy to be a custodian of this forest.
例句释义: 他很乐意当一个森林看护人。

英文释义: never stopping
例句: The incessant buzzing of the fly is driving me crazy!
例句释义: 这苍蝇发出的无间断的嗡嗡声要把我逼疯啦！

详细释义: v. 给…染色，轻微地影响；  n. 淡淡的（颜色、神色），轻微，少量
英文释义: a slight color, flavor, or quality
例句: The maple leaf was tinged red in autumn.
例句释义: 枫叶在秋天被染成红色。

详细释义: n. 文具；（有配套信封的）信纸
英文释义: materials for writing and for using in an office, for example paper, pens and envelopes
例句: You can buy this nicely designed stationery from our online store.
例句释义: 你可以在我们的网上商城买到这些设计精良的文具。

英文释义: a large animal with black-and-white fur that looks like a bear, lives in China, and eats mostly bamboo shoots
例句: I wish I was a panda because they eat and play all day.
例句释义: 我希望我是个熊猫，这样可以整天有吃有玩的。

详细释义: n. 时髦，时尚；  adj. 流行的
英文释义: something (such as a way of dressing or behaving) that is fashionable or popular in a particular time and place
例句: Red dresses are really in vogue this year.
例句释义: 红色连衣裙今年很流行。

英文释义: marked by elaborately complex detail
例句: The price depends on the intricacy of the work.
例句释义: 价格取决于做工的复杂精细度。

英文释义: the condition or quality of being a virgin
例句: I love the untouched beauty and virginity of this place.
例句释义: 我爱这个地方不染尘嚣的美丽与纯净。

英文释义: a Greek epic poem (attributed to Homer) describing the journey of Odysseus after the fall of Troy
例句: An odyssey is a long exciting journey where lots of things can happen.
例句释义: 奥德赛是指一段漫长而激动人心的旅程，期间可以发生很多事情。

英文释义: having a bad smell
例句: I can't stand the smelly fruit anymore!
例句释义: 我受不了这么臭的水果了！

英文释义: death that is imposed because of the person's adherence of a religious faith or cause
例句: Jesus's martyrdom is considered the first in the history of Christianity.
例句释义: 耶稣的殉难被认为是基督教历史上的第一次殉难。

英文释义: using naturalism in art or literature :showing people or things as they really are
例句: Naturalistic artists present their art as it would appear in the natural world.
例句释义: 自然主义艺术家展示的作品，与自然世界呈现的一致。

英文释义: feeling or showing that you are sorry for doing something wrong or for causing a problem
例句: She was very apologetic for stepping on the man's foot.
例句释义: 踩到那个男士的脚，她感到很抱歉。

详细释义: vt. 并吞，强行占取；  n. 附属的建筑物
英文释义: to add (an area or region) to a country, state, etc. :to take control of (a territory or place)
例句: Austria was annexed by Germany.
例句释义: 奥地利曾被德国吞并。

英文释义: careful hard work :continued effort
例句: She showed great diligence in her completing schoolwork.
例句释义: 她在完成学业的过程中表现出了极其勤奋的精神。

详细释义: v. 漂白，使脱色；  n. 漂白剂
英文释义: to become white or pale by a chemical process or by the effect of light from the sun; to make something white or pale in this way
例句: She has bleached her hair blonde.
例句释义: 她把头发漂染成了金色。

英文释义: food that is needed to stay alive, grow and stay healthy
例句: Nourishment is beneficial to the development of babies.
例句释义: 营养有益于婴儿的发育。

详细释义: v. 刺破（车胎等），扎，穿孔；  n. 刺孔，刺
英文释义: to make a small hole in something; to get a small hole; to suddenly make somebody feel less confident, proud, etc.
例句: One of the tyres was punctured by a nail.
例句释义: 有个车轮被钉子刺穿了。

详细释义: n. 不和，争吵；（声音）不和谐
英文释义: lack of agreement between people, ideas, etc.
例句: Fights can result in lasting discord between people.
例句释义: 争吵会导致人与人之间的不和。

英文释义: to become ripe; to make something ripe
例句: The bananas are ripening when color is ranging from green to yellow.
例句释义: 香蕉的颜色正从绿色变成黄色，说明香蕉快要熟了。

详细释义: adj.作为结果（或后果）的，随之发生的
英文释义: happening as a result of something
例句: A consequent effect of staying up late is the bags under your eyes.
例句释义: 熬夜的一个后果就是：你的眼睛下面会有黑眼圈。

英文释义: pounding or beating strongly or violently

英文释义: the act of making something fit a normal pattern or condition; the fact of starting to fit a normal pattern or condition

例句: The barbershop provides a hair grooming service to male customers.
例句释义: 这家理发店为男性顾客提供理发服务。

英文释义: something added to foods to make them taste sweeter
例句: She used sweetener in place of sugar and honey.
例句释义: 她用甜味剂来代替糖和蜂蜜。

英文释义: a person who has great wealth and power in a particular business or industry
例句: These three business magnates made their wealth in the tech industry.
例句释义: 这三位商界大亨在科技行业发家致富。

详细释义: vt. 误传；  vi. 作虚假陈述

例句: The newspaper misrepresented him as arrogant for not standing up, but he was just injured.

英文释义: indicating opposition or resistance

例句释义: 猫和狗互相敌对是出了名的。

详细释义: n. 洪水；  v. 使泛滥

例句: The small town was flooded in the deluge.
例句释义: 小镇在暴雨中被洪水淹没。

英文释义: a strong feeling of sadness or worry

例句释义: 这个男人正在承受一段失败感情所带来的心痛。

英文释义: the part of the sky where planes fly, usually the part above a particular country that is legally controlled by that country
例句: A Rabbit jet entered Cat airspace without permission.

例句: She is reading a storybook.
例句释义: 她在看故事书。

英文释义: a very common wild plant that has bright yellow flowers
例句: She is holding many dandelions in her hands.
例句释义: 她手里拿着许多蒲公英。

英文释义: to dislike (someone or something) very strongly
例句: The internet bullies bothered the boy because they detest him so much.
例句释义: 网络暴民对他的百般憎恨让他苦恼不已。

详细释义: adj. 沉重的，难以负担的；难以负担的
英文释义: causing worry, difficulty or hard work
例句: It would be burdensome for some families to have two children.
例句释义: 有些家庭可能会难以负担两个孩子。

英文释义: conversations in a book, play, or film/movie; a formal discussion between two groups or countries, especially when they are trying to solve a problem, end a disagreement, etc.
例句: The two sides entered into a peace dialog.

英文释义: tireness

例句释义: 倦意袭来，导致他在地铁上睡着了。

英文释义: to supply water to an area of land through pipes or channels so that crops will grow
例句: This machine can irrigate the field.
例句释义: 这台机器可以灌溉田地。

英文释义: a feeling of extreme pleasure and happiness

例句释义: 当她赢得网球比赛时，简直欣喜若狂。

英文释义: a small orange or red fish which kept as pets in bowls or ponds.
例句: Cats and dogs are too messy, so I have a pet goldfish instead.
例句释义: 猫和狗太脏了，所以我养了一只金鱼做宠物。

详细释义: n. 小溪；  v. (常用于否定句或疑问句)容忍；忍受
英文释义: a small river
例句: I saw them rowing down the brook.
例句释义: 我看到他们沿着小溪划船。

英文释义: in a way that is connected with or involves scientific experiments; in a way that involves trying new ideas, forms or methods to find out what effect they have
例句: Approach the problem experimentally and keep an open mind.
例句释义: 要用实验来解决问题，并保持开放的头脑。

英文释义: an instrument for measuring air pressure to show when the weather will change
例句: The needle on the barometer is indicating sunny weather.

详细释义: adj. 补充的；附加的；  n. 补充者
英文释义: provided in addition to something else in order to improve or complete it

英文释义: connected with or similar to feudalism

详细释义: v. 狗吠，（因痛而）叫喊，叫喊着说

例句: The chef is stir-frying the noodles.
例句释义: 这位厨师正在炒面条。

详细释义: n. 登基，即位；加入（国际组织）

例句释义: 马戏团里的小丑过多了，只有一个小丑保住了工作！

例句释义: 拳击手靠激怒他的对手来扰乱他的心思。

英文释义: showing or feeling happiness or satisfaction, especially because your life is good
例句: The couple enjoyed a contented relaxing life after retiring.
例句释义: 退休后，这对夫妻过上了满足、惬意的生活。

英文释义: to introduce new things, ideas, or ways of doing sth
例句: Jobs succeeded in innovating the style of smart mobile phones.
例句释义: 乔布斯成功地对智能手机的样式进行了创新。

英文释义: someone who goes to or went to the same school as you
例句: My schoolmates and I go to school together every day.
例句释义: 我和我同学每天都一起上学。

详细释义: adj. 顽固的；顽强的；  vt. 跟踪
英文释义: showing determination; not giving up easily
例句: He is dogged in his determination to be a successful businessman.
例句释义: 他下定决心要成为一个成功的商人。

详细释义: adj. 表示悲痛的，伤心的
英文释义: expressing suffering or sadness :having a sad sound
例句: She was plaintive when I told her we had to break up.
例句释义: 当我告诉她我们必须分手时，她很痛苦。

英文释义: to drink so that you no longer feel thirsty
例句: The tennis player quenches her thirst with water.
例句释义: 这位网球运动员正喝水解渴。

英文释义: (of a person) attractive to other people because of having a pleasant appearance and character
例句: She's very personable - everyone who meets her, likes her.
例句释义: 她很有风度，每一个遇到她的人都喜欢她。

详细释义: adj. 顺从的，尽职的；有责任心的
英文释义: doing everything that you are expected to do; willing to obey and to show respect
例句: The dutiful dog fetched the frisbee back to its owner.
例句释义: 顺从的狗狗把飞盘叼给了主人。

详细释义: adj. 死后的；著作者死后出版的
英文释义: happening, done, or published after someone's death
例句: The artist would never have expected that he would achieve such posthumous fame today.
例句释义: 这个艺术家做梦也想不到会今天他会赢得如此高的声誉。

英文释义: a printed statement that describes something (such as a new business or investment) and that is sent to people who may want to be involved in it or invest in it
例句: He's reading the prospectuses of different universities so he can choose the best one.
例句释义: 他正在阅读不同大学的简介来选出最好的一所。

英文释义: beautiful handwriting that you do with a special pen or brush; the art of producing this
例句: Calligraphy is the art of beautiful handwriting.
例句释义: 书法是一种美观的书写艺术。

英文释义: a government official who is the representative of his or her country in a foreign city
例句: As the Zebra consul, he represents Zebra Country within the land of the Deer.
例句释义: 作为斑马国的领事，他是斑马国在鹿国的代表。

详细释义: n. （表演空中飞人、走钢丝等的）杂技演员，特技表演者，训练有素的体操运动员
英文释义: an entertainer who performs difficult acts such as balancing on high ropes, especially at a circus
例句: The acrobat is performing how to sleep on a tight rope.
例句释义: 杂技演员（小龙女）正在表演如何睡在一根绷紧的绳上。

详细释义: adj.可循环再用的，可回收利用的
英文释义: possible to use again
例句: These things are recyclable, which means they can be used again after they've been already used.
例句释义: 这些是可回收利用资源，这意味着它们在被使用过后还能被重新利用。

英文释义: deserving praise
例句: Her performance was laudable: everybody loved it.
例句释义: 她的表演值得称赞：每个人都喜欢。
